WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:23.640
Scholastic Audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:23.640 --> 00:00:27.660
Book 8, Escape in Peril, by 2ET

00:00:27.660 --> 00:00:30.780
Sutherland, read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:48.840 --> 00:00:56.159
The Jade Mountain Prophecy.

00:00:56.219 --> 00:01:00.479
Beware the darkness of dragons.

00:01:00.539 --> 00:01:03.780
Beware, the stalker of dreams.

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:07.620
Beware the talons of power and fire.

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:11.459
Beware one who is not what she seems.

00:01:11.579 --> 00:01:14.819
Something is coming to shake the earth.

00:01:14.879 --> 00:01:18.000
Something is coming to scorch the

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:18.359
ground.

00:01:18.420 --> 00:01:21.719
Jade Mountain will fall beneath thunder

00:01:21.719 --> 00:01:25.560
and ice unless the lost city of night can

00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:25.980
be found.

00:01:38.099 --> 00:01:41.040
Prologue.

00:01:41.219 --> 00:01:42.719
Seven years ago.

00:01:42.780 --> 00:01:47.340
No dragon was safe in the Sky Palace, but

00:01:47.340 --> 00:01:49.920
the ones in the most danger by far were

00:01:49.920 --> 00:01:51.599
the daughters of Queen Scarlet.

00:01:51.719 --> 00:01:54.719
Or was it now daughter singular?

00:01:54.780 --> 00:01:58.079
Ruby hadn't seen her sister Tourmaline in

00:01:58.079 --> 00:02:00.659
3 days, not since the night they went

00:02:00.659 --> 00:02:03.299
flying together and high in the starlit

00:02:03.299 --> 00:02:05.640
sky, glowing in the light of 2 of the

00:02:05.640 --> 00:02:08.159
moons, Tourmaline had whispered that she

00:02:08.159 --> 00:02:08.879
was almost ready.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:11.280
Don't be an idiot.

00:02:11.340 --> 00:02:14.159
You're only 10, and furthermore, you'll

00:02:14.159 --> 00:02:14.699
never be ready.

00:02:14.759 --> 00:02:16.680
Ruby had whispered back.

00:02:16.740 --> 00:02:20.280
She killed her mother, plus all 3 of her

00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:22.319
sisters and 11 of hours.

00:02:22.379 --> 00:02:23.939
There's no way to defeat her.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.439
She can't be queen forever, Tourmaline

00:02:28.439 --> 00:02:28.680
said.

00:02:28.740 --> 00:02:32.759
She has been queen forever, Ruby argued

00:02:32.819 --> 00:02:36.780
24 years is a long time, but not that

00:02:36.780 --> 00:02:38.819
long, said Tourmaline.

00:02:38.879 --> 00:02:41.400
Queen Oasis was queen longer than that

00:02:41.400 --> 00:02:42.599
and look what happened to her.

00:02:42.659 --> 00:02:45.780
Are you planning to throw a scavenger at

00:02:45.780 --> 00:02:46.139
mother?

00:02:46.199 --> 00:02:47.219
Ruby asked.

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:49.740
Because I'm sure she'd appreciate a snack

00:02:49.740 --> 00:02:50.520
before she kills you.

00:02:50.639 --> 00:02:53.819
It's always going to be like this.

00:02:53.939 --> 00:02:55.800
Tourmaline hissed.

00:02:55.860 --> 00:02:58.259
She flicked clouds away with her dark

00:02:58.259 --> 00:02:59.099
orange wings.

00:02:59.159 --> 00:03:02.219
Until one of us challenges her and wins.

00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:04.919
You and I are the only ones left now.

00:03:04.979 --> 00:03:07.740
The only hope the Skywings have of a

00:03:07.740 --> 00:03:08.460
decent queen.

00:03:08.520 --> 00:03:09.840
Ruby.

00:03:09.900 --> 00:03:12.960
If I defeat her and become queen, we can

00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:13.680
get out of this war.

00:03:13.740 --> 00:03:16.620
Ruby wasn't so sure about that.

00:03:16.680 --> 00:03:20.099
She'd met Bern, and she suspected the

00:03:20.099 --> 00:03:22.020
sand wing wouldn't let her allies go that

00:03:22.020 --> 00:03:22.379
easily.

00:03:22.439 --> 00:03:24.120
But it didn't matter.

00:03:24.180 --> 00:03:26.699
There was no way Tourmaline could win a

00:03:26.699 --> 00:03:27.539
battle with their mother.

00:03:27.599 --> 00:03:30.360
The prophecy will take care of the war.

00:03:30.419 --> 00:03:31.500
She argued.

00:03:31.560 --> 00:03:33.599
The brightest night is in 4 days.

00:03:33.659 --> 00:03:35.460
Right.

00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:37.500
Tourmaline rolled her eyes.

00:03:37.560 --> 00:03:39.900
I'll just wait for a bunch of eggs that

00:03:39.900 --> 00:03:41.520
haven't even hatched yet to save us.

00:03:41.580 --> 00:03:44.400
Ruby, I don't want to wait for things to

00:03:44.400 --> 00:03:45.000
happen to me.

00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:46.800
I want to make them happen.

00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:49.439
I don't want to watch you die.

00:03:49.560 --> 00:03:50.939
Ruby growled.

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:53.460
Her sister hovered in front of her for a

00:03:53.460 --> 00:03:53.639
moment.

00:03:53.759 --> 00:03:57.000
Stars glittered in her eyes, searching

00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:57.599
rubies.

00:03:57.659 --> 00:04:00.360
She's wondering if I want the throne for

00:04:00.360 --> 00:04:00.780
myself.

00:04:00.840 --> 00:04:02.159
Ruby thought.

00:04:02.219 --> 00:04:04.379
She thinks I'm trying to talk her out of

00:04:04.379 --> 00:04:06.719
it because I'm planning something like

00:04:06.719 --> 00:04:07.439
I'm that stupid.

00:04:07.500 --> 00:04:11.400
Well, don't worry, I won't do it yet.

00:04:11.520 --> 00:04:13.080
Termaline promised.

00:04:13.199 --> 00:04:15.659
Another few months of training, maybe.

00:04:15.719 --> 00:04:17.639
I'm feeling really strong though.

00:04:17.699 --> 00:04:19.800
I beat Vermilion in a fight the other

00:04:19.800 --> 00:04:20.040
day.

00:04:20.100 --> 00:04:21.180
Want to hear about it?

00:04:21.240 --> 00:04:24.720
Ruby had listened to the entire long play

00:04:23.699 --> 00:04:26.459
by-play of each move Tmaline had made.

00:04:26.519 --> 00:04:29.279
They'd spent an hour soaring around the

00:04:29.279 --> 00:04:31.620
peaks in the moonlight, and not once had

00:04:31.620 --> 00:04:33.120
Tourmaline said anything about leaving

00:04:33.120 --> 00:04:33.720
the palace.

00:04:33.779 --> 00:04:35.819
But then she was gone.

00:04:35.939 --> 00:04:39.360
And the most unsettling thing was, no one

00:04:39.360 --> 00:04:40.680
had even mentioned her absence.

00:04:40.740 --> 00:04:43.019
Her squadron was still here.

00:04:43.079 --> 00:04:45.360
Training and hunting as though nothing

00:04:45.360 --> 00:04:46.139
odd had happened.

00:04:46.199 --> 00:04:48.660
There were no patrols out looking for her

00:04:48.660 --> 00:04:52.019
no search parties scouring the woods, no

00:04:52.019 --> 00:04:54.000
missives flying out to other queens to

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.939
ask if they'd seen, or abducted, the

00:04:56.939 --> 00:04:58.319
older sky wing princess.

00:04:58.379 --> 00:05:01.500
Just a quiet vanishing into thin air.

00:05:01.620 --> 00:05:04.500
Ruby stood in the room she shared with

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:06.600
her sister, studying the piles of

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:07.259
blankets.

00:05:07.319 --> 00:05:09.660
The scroll was carelessly tossed aside

00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:11.939
the gold tasseled yellow curtains

00:05:11.939 --> 00:05:12.779
flapping at the window.

00:05:12.839 --> 00:05:16.439
There were no splatters of blood, no sign

00:05:16.439 --> 00:05:16.980
of a struggle.

00:05:17.040 --> 00:05:20.220
No note saying, oh, I've popped off to

00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:21.660
one of the outposts for a few days.

00:05:21.720 --> 00:05:22.620
See you soon.

00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:25.319
Did Termaline change her mind and run

00:05:25.319 --> 00:05:25.560
away?

00:05:25.620 --> 00:05:28.620
Could she have gone to find the talons of

00:05:28.620 --> 00:05:28.980
peace?

00:05:29.040 --> 00:05:31.980
But Ruby knew that wasn't what had

00:05:31.980 --> 00:05:32.279
happened.

00:05:32.339 --> 00:05:34.920
Her big sister wasn't the kind to ever

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:35.639
run away.

00:05:35.699 --> 00:05:39.600
More significantly, Queen Scarlet would

00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:41.100
never let the peace movement get their

00:05:41.100 --> 00:05:42.120
claws on her daughter.

00:05:42.180 --> 00:05:44.879
She'd find them and destroy them all

00:05:44.879 --> 00:05:45.660
first.

00:05:45.720 --> 00:05:49.800
Heavy talons were slowly squeezing Ruby's

00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:52.079
insides, digging their claws in harder

00:05:52.079 --> 00:05:53.819
every minute that Tourmaline was gone.

00:05:53.879 --> 00:05:57.540
If she found out, the tourmaline was

00:05:57.540 --> 00:05:58.379
planning to challenge her.

00:05:58.439 --> 00:06:00.480
What did mother do?

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:02.519
Princess Ruby?

00:06:02.579 --> 00:06:04.860
She jumped and whirled around.

00:06:04.920 --> 00:06:06.600
The guard in the doorway cleared his

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:06.839
throat.

00:06:06.899 --> 00:06:09.899
The queen has requested your presence in

00:06:09.899 --> 00:06:11.339
the throne room, he said.

00:06:11.399 --> 00:06:12.959
Immediately.

00:06:13.019 --> 00:06:14.339
Requested?

00:06:14.459 --> 00:06:15.720
Ruby echoed.

00:06:15.839 --> 00:06:18.420
The expression on his face said quite

00:06:18.420 --> 00:06:20.160
clearly that he didn't approve of the

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:20.399
question.

00:06:20.459 --> 00:06:22.980
Never let them see that you're

00:06:22.980 --> 00:06:23.519
terrified.

00:06:23.579 --> 00:06:25.860
That's what tourmaline said.

00:06:25.920 --> 00:06:29.759
Act like a queen, so that one day they'll

00:06:29.759 --> 00:06:31.500
be cheering for you to slit mother's

00:06:31.500 --> 00:06:31.920
throat.

00:06:31.980 --> 00:06:34.800
But now, Tourmaline was gone.

00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:37.620
And perhaps acting like a queen was

00:06:37.620 --> 00:06:39.420
exactly what had gotten her killed.

00:06:39.480 --> 00:06:43.860
Thank you, Ruby said, inclining her head

00:06:43.860 --> 00:06:45.120
of the guard as she went past him.

00:06:45.180 --> 00:06:47.639
Her heart beat drummed through her

00:06:47.639 --> 00:06:49.439
shoulders and out to her wing tips.

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:52.500
The tunnel felt too small, as though she

00:06:52.500 --> 00:06:54.540
were the size of a 1000 year old dragon

00:06:54.540 --> 00:06:57.240
instead of just a 5 year old dragonette.

00:06:57.300 --> 00:07:00.000
Whatever happened to Tourmaline?

00:07:00.120 --> 00:07:01.319
Am I next?

00:07:01.379 --> 00:07:04.379
Dragons huddled by the throne room

00:07:04.379 --> 00:07:05.759
entrance, whispering.

00:07:05.819 --> 00:07:07.800
They all straightened their heads and

00:07:07.800 --> 00:07:08.939
wings as she approached.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:11.279
Curiosity gleamed in their eyes.

00:07:11.339 --> 00:07:13.500
They must have known Tourmaline was

00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:15.540
missing, even if no one would talk about

00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:15.720
it.

00:07:15.779 --> 00:07:18.839
They must have been wondering, like Ruby

00:07:18.839 --> 00:07:21.420
was, whether Queen Scarlet had decided to

00:07:21.420 --> 00:07:24.060
dispose of all her potential, threatening

00:07:24.060 --> 00:07:24.480
airs.

00:07:24.600 --> 00:07:27.060
But I'm not threatening.

00:07:27.120 --> 00:07:28.139
I'm not.

00:07:28.199 --> 00:07:31.379
Ruby ducked her long neck as she entered

00:07:31.379 --> 00:07:31.680
the room.

00:07:31.740 --> 00:07:34.199
Blinking in the blaze of sunlight that

00:07:34.199 --> 00:07:36.420
reflected off all the gold inlaid in the

00:07:36.420 --> 00:07:37.019
walls.

00:07:37.079 --> 00:07:39.899
It felt like walking into a funeral pyre

00:07:39.899 --> 00:07:42.779
oppressive heat, and the smell of dragon

00:07:42.779 --> 00:07:45.060
fire, radiating off the crowd of

00:07:45.060 --> 00:07:47.759
courtiers, closed in around her scales.

00:07:47.819 --> 00:07:50.879
Queen Scarlet wouldn't kill her daughter

00:07:50.879 --> 00:07:52.740
in front of all these dragons.

00:07:52.800 --> 00:07:53.699
Would she?

00:07:53.759 --> 00:07:56.459
Ah, Ruby!

00:07:56.579 --> 00:07:58.980
The queen's voice lilted over all the

00:07:58.980 --> 00:07:59.399
others.

00:07:59.459 --> 00:08:00.899
And the room fell silent.

00:08:00.959 --> 00:08:02.459
At last.

00:08:02.579 --> 00:08:05.879
Court, many of you don't know my daughter

00:08:05.879 --> 00:08:08.759
Ruby, because she's been away in training

00:08:08.759 --> 00:08:09.839
and even when she is here.

00:08:09.899 --> 00:08:12.720
She mostly sits in her cave like a sleepy

00:08:12.720 --> 00:08:13.079
bat.

00:08:13.139 --> 00:08:17.040
If you ever have seen her, she's probably

00:08:17.040 --> 00:08:19.259
had her nose in a scroll.

00:08:19.319 --> 00:08:20.639
But despite the fact that she's nothing

00:08:20.639 --> 00:08:23.459
like me, she is still somehow my

00:08:23.459 --> 00:08:23.699
daughter.

00:08:23.759 --> 00:08:26.579
There was a dutiful smattering of

00:08:26.579 --> 00:08:27.180
applause.

00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:29.819
Well, now everyone is here.

00:08:29.879 --> 00:08:31.800
Everyone important, I mean.

00:08:31.860 --> 00:08:35.159
I have such a thrilling announcement.

00:08:35.220 --> 00:08:38.519
Ruby, don't lurk by the wall. like a

00:08:38.519 --> 00:08:39.600
jittery centipede.

00:08:39.659 --> 00:08:41.099
Come stand by your brothers.

00:08:41.159 --> 00:08:44.639
I want you, especially, to see this.

00:08:44.700 --> 00:08:47.940
The crowd parted to let Ruby through.

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:51.240
Their avid orange and amber eyes peeling

00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:52.860
off her scales as she slid by.

00:08:52.919 --> 00:08:55.500
There was just enough space for her to

00:08:55.500 --> 00:08:58.139
fit between vermilion and Hawk, both of

00:08:58.139 --> 00:08:59.100
them towering over her.

00:08:59.159 --> 00:09:02.100
Her other 2 brothers were on Hawke's

00:09:02.100 --> 00:09:02.399
other side.

00:09:02.460 --> 00:09:05.399
All of Scarlett's children were here

00:09:05.399 --> 00:09:07.200
except tourmaline.

00:09:07.259 --> 00:09:10.500
Vermillion snorted, and Edge just step

00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:12.840
away from her, but Hawk gave her a

00:09:12.840 --> 00:09:14.519
friendly-ish nudge of acknowledgment.

00:09:14.580 --> 00:09:17.399
Ruby always got the feeling that Hawke

00:09:17.399 --> 00:09:19.440
was cheerfully being nice to her because

00:09:19.440 --> 00:09:20.940
he knew she'd be dead soon.

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:23.700
He'd seen the rest of his sisters die

00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:25.080
under Scarlet's claws.

00:09:25.139 --> 00:09:28.679
Ruby suspected his good humor came from

00:09:28.679 --> 00:09:30.600
the security of knowing he could never

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:32.759
have the throne, so he wasn't worth

00:09:32.759 --> 00:09:33.120
killing.

00:09:33.179 --> 00:09:36.480
Their mother glowed like a poisonous

00:09:36.480 --> 00:09:39.360
orange from the top of her throne, peering

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:40.980
down at the dragons that packed the

00:09:40.980 --> 00:09:41.159
room.

00:09:41.279 --> 00:09:44.340
The sharp sparkle of diamonds above her

00:09:44.340 --> 00:09:46.799
eyes, and along her wings seized the

00:09:46.799 --> 00:09:47.580
light.

00:09:47.639 --> 00:09:50.580
Ruby's breath caught in her throat, at

00:09:50.580 --> 00:09:52.320
the sight of the hulking dragon at the

00:09:52.320 --> 00:09:53.100
queen's side.

00:09:53.159 --> 00:09:57.419
Burn, their sandwing ally, her face

00:09:57.419 --> 00:09:59.340
twisted in disgust and boredom.

00:09:59.399 --> 00:10:01.860
Everyone had been instructed to call her

00:10:01.860 --> 00:10:03.779
queen burn to her face.

00:10:03.840 --> 00:10:06.179
But Ruby found it hard to think of her

00:10:06.179 --> 00:10:06.779
that way.

00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:09.480
For one thing, she hadn't won the war

00:10:09.480 --> 00:10:09.779
yet.

00:10:09.840 --> 00:10:13.799
And for another, there was only one queen

00:10:13.799 --> 00:10:16.379
in Ruby's world, closing her deadly

00:10:16.379 --> 00:10:18.360
talons around everything in it.

00:10:18.419 --> 00:10:22.139
On the other side of Queen Scarlet, was a

00:10:22.139 --> 00:10:24.240
tall, oddly piled arrangement of black

00:10:24.240 --> 00:10:26.220
rocks that seemed to be smoking.

00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:31.080
Finally, Scarlet said, rolling her eyes

00:10:31.080 --> 00:10:32.820
as though including the rest of the court

00:10:32.820 --> 00:10:34.320
in her impatience with Ruby.

00:10:34.379 --> 00:10:36.840
A chuckle eddied around the crowd.

00:10:36.899 --> 00:10:39.059
Get on with it.

00:10:39.120 --> 00:10:40.679
Burn snapped.

00:10:40.740 --> 00:10:43.620
Queen Scarlet flicked her tail and

00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:45.360
stretched her wings with deliberate

00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:45.779
languor.

00:10:45.840 --> 00:10:49.139
Ruby had time to wonder if the thrilling

00:10:49.139 --> 00:10:50.460
announcement had anything to do with

00:10:50.460 --> 00:10:51.240
Tourmaline.

00:10:51.299 --> 00:10:53.820
I have the thrillingly murdered one

00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:54.179
daughter.

00:10:54.240 --> 00:10:55.919
Why stop there?

00:10:55.980 --> 00:10:57.419
Who needs daughters anyway, right?

00:10:57.539 --> 00:11:01.440
You may all have heard of a certain

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:02.039
prophecy.

00:11:02.159 --> 00:11:04.500
Queen Scarlet said instead.

00:11:04.559 --> 00:11:08.340
Mumbling about special dragonettes, who

00:11:08.340 --> 00:11:10.019
will hatch on the brightest night and

00:11:10.019 --> 00:11:12.360
stop the war, and you may all have

00:11:12.360 --> 00:11:15.000
noticed that the brightest night is

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:15.899
tonight.

00:11:15.960 --> 00:11:18.059
Isn't that terribly exciting?

00:11:18.120 --> 00:11:21.000
Tiny little heroes crawling out of their

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:22.379
eggs any minute now.

00:11:22.440 --> 00:11:27.539
That is, unless something simply dreadful

00:11:27.539 --> 00:11:29.100
happens, of course.

00:11:29.159 --> 00:11:32.940
She cast a sidelong glance at Bern

00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:34.620
smiling maliciously.

00:11:34.740 --> 00:11:37.440
What you all don't know is that someone

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:40.259
tried to steal a sky wing egg last

00:11:40.259 --> 00:11:40.500
night.

00:11:40.559 --> 00:11:43.379
A gasp ran around the room.

00:11:43.500 --> 00:11:47.340
I know, said Queen Scarlet.

00:11:47.399 --> 00:11:50.820
A nasty ice wing thief, got all the way

00:11:50.820 --> 00:11:53.100
in here, and actually escaped with an

00:11:53.100 --> 00:11:53.399
egg.

00:11:53.460 --> 00:11:56.759
The largest one in the hatchery, as it

00:11:56.759 --> 00:11:57.059
happens.

00:11:57.120 --> 00:12:00.720
The air crackled, as if it might burst

00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:02.039
into flames at any moment.

00:12:02.100 --> 00:12:05.460
Ruby tried to imagine life as a sky wing

00:12:05.460 --> 00:12:07.200
raised outside the sky kingdom.

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:09.720
The thief couldn't have been planning to

00:12:09.720 --> 00:12:10.799
take it to the ice kingdom.

00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:13.019
A sky wing would never survive there.

00:12:13.139 --> 00:12:16.379
So was he one of the talents of peace?

00:12:16.440 --> 00:12:19.620
Were they assembling the dragonettes of

00:12:19.620 --> 00:12:20.220
the prophecy?

00:12:20.279 --> 00:12:23.519
Was the dragonette in that stolen egg

00:12:23.519 --> 00:12:25.139
going to save them all?

00:12:25.200 --> 00:12:28.799
Oh, don't worry, her mother said.

00:12:28.860 --> 00:12:32.039
Queen Bern chased him down, killed him

00:12:32.039 --> 00:12:33.240
and destroyed the egg.

00:12:33.299 --> 00:12:37.080
We don't particularly like tiny little

00:12:37.080 --> 00:12:39.720
heroes after all, especially ones who

00:12:39.720 --> 00:12:40.980
might try to tell us what to do.

00:12:41.039 --> 00:12:42.720
So.

00:12:42.960 --> 00:12:45.240
She clapped her front talons together

00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:47.700
suddenly, snapping the tension in the

00:12:47.700 --> 00:12:48.840
room like a bowstring.

00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:51.899
Just to be perfectly safe.

00:12:51.960 --> 00:12:54.000
Queen Bern and I had a marvelous idea.

00:12:54.059 --> 00:12:58.500
We're going to make sure there are no sky

00:12:58.500 --> 00:13:01.379
wings hatching on the brightest night, not

00:13:01.379 --> 00:13:03.419
even one.

00:13:03.480 --> 00:13:04.440
Not even close.

00:13:04.559 --> 00:13:06.659
Bring them in.

00:13:06.720 --> 00:13:07.740
She called.

00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:11.940
Ruby watched in confusion as 7 guards

00:13:11.940 --> 00:13:14.940
filed in, each of them carrying an egg.

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:17.759
Red and orange shapes moved under the

00:13:17.759 --> 00:13:20.100
thin surface of the eggshells, and she

00:13:20.100 --> 00:13:22.080
could see cracks already spreading across

00:13:22.080 --> 00:13:22.860
3 of them.

00:13:22.919 --> 00:13:25.679
Queen Scarlet narrowed her eyes.

00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:28.559
There should be eight.

00:13:28.620 --> 00:13:30.120
She hissed.

00:13:30.179 --> 00:13:33.419
We'll find it, Your Majesty, said the

00:13:33.419 --> 00:13:34.200
tallest guard.

00:13:34.259 --> 00:13:36.779
I promise, she won't get far, and it was

00:13:36.779 --> 00:13:37.740
a runty one, anyhow.

00:13:37.799 --> 00:13:40.799
A skittering noise came from the pile of

00:13:40.799 --> 00:13:43.500
rocks beside the queen, and one of the

00:13:43.500 --> 00:13:44.879
stones trembled for a moment.

00:13:44.940 --> 00:13:47.519
Then came tumbling down and bounced

00:13:47.519 --> 00:13:50.700
across the floor, rolling to a stop at

00:13:50.700 --> 00:13:51.840
Ruby's talons.

00:13:51.899 --> 00:13:56.639
Fine, said Queen Scarlet, putting on her

00:13:56.639 --> 00:13:59.159
annoyed, but it's a celebration, so I'll

00:13:59.159 --> 00:14:01.019
just kill someone later, face.

00:14:01.080 --> 00:14:05.100
I have someone just wonderful.

00:14:05.159 --> 00:14:06.840
I want to introduce to you all.

00:14:06.899 --> 00:14:09.659
And this seemed like a perfect way to do

00:14:09.659 --> 00:14:09.840
it.

00:14:09.899 --> 00:14:12.840
Ooh, the suspense.

00:14:12.960 --> 00:14:16.620
A puff of impatient smoke snorted out of

00:14:16.620 --> 00:14:17.460
Burns nostrils.

00:14:17.519 --> 00:14:19.740
Always a spectacle.

00:14:19.799 --> 00:14:20.759
She muttered.

00:14:20.820 --> 00:14:23.220
Can't just kill something efficiently and

00:14:23.220 --> 00:14:24.120
be done already.

00:14:24.179 --> 00:14:26.279
Queen Scarlet ignored her.

00:14:26.340 --> 00:14:28.980
She was busy removing rocks from the top

00:14:28.980 --> 00:14:31.860
of the pile, slowly taking off the roof

00:14:31.860 --> 00:14:33.120
of the makeshift structure.

00:14:33.179 --> 00:14:36.179
Another scrabbling noise came from inside

00:14:36.179 --> 00:14:36.779
the rocks.

00:14:36.840 --> 00:14:40.860
There's something alive in there, Ruby

00:14:40.860 --> 00:14:41.159
thought.

00:14:41.220 --> 00:14:43.679
And then suddenly a little head popped

00:14:43.679 --> 00:14:44.759
over the edge of the rocks.

00:14:44.820 --> 00:14:47.639
Only a heart beat away from the queen's

00:14:47.639 --> 00:14:48.240
talons.

00:14:48.299 --> 00:14:51.840
Scarlet jerked back, and Ruby was shocked

00:14:51.840 --> 00:14:54.000
to see something that looked like a flash

00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:55.200
of fear in her eyes.

00:14:55.259 --> 00:14:57.779
She craned her neck to see better.

00:14:57.840 --> 00:15:00.779
What could possibly scare mother?

00:15:00.840 --> 00:15:02.879
She's not afraid of anything.

00:15:02.940 --> 00:15:06.299
It looked like an ordinary dragonette.

00:15:06.360 --> 00:15:09.360
About a year, or maybe a year and a half

00:15:09.360 --> 00:15:12.299
old, with unusually bright, coppery

00:15:12.299 --> 00:15:13.259
orange scales.

00:15:13.259 --> 00:15:16.860
But then, the dragonette swiveled her

00:15:16.860 --> 00:15:19.019
head, and her eyes met Ruby's.

00:15:19.080 --> 00:15:20.639
Her eyes.

00:15:20.759 --> 00:15:22.980
They were blue.

00:15:23.039 --> 00:15:27.120
The weirdest, creepiest blue Ruby had

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:27.539
ever seen.

00:15:27.600 --> 00:15:30.059
Far beyond the color of the sky.

00:15:30.120 --> 00:15:33.659
Like, someone had bundled up the sky and

00:15:33.659 --> 00:15:36.000
immersed it in fire until it burned from

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:37.019
the inside.

00:15:37.080 --> 00:15:40.139
That's it, Ruby thought.

00:15:40.200 --> 00:15:43.500
This dragonette looked like she was

00:15:43.500 --> 00:15:44.879
burning from the inside.

00:15:44.940 --> 00:15:47.580
Smoke was even rising from her scales.

00:15:47.639 --> 00:15:51.480
Over Ruby's head, Hawk and Vermilion

00:15:51.480 --> 00:15:52.500
exchanged looks.

00:15:52.559 --> 00:15:54.419
Did you know about this?

00:15:54.480 --> 00:15:57.779
Hawk growled softly under the hubbub of

00:15:57.779 --> 00:16:00.059
voices, whispering all around them.

00:16:00.120 --> 00:16:01.139
I thought it was dead.

00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:02.580
It should be dead.

00:16:02.639 --> 00:16:05.639
Don't question the queen.

00:16:05.759 --> 00:16:07.559
Vermilion muttered back.

00:16:07.620 --> 00:16:10.019
Keeping his eyes forward, and his mouth

00:16:10.019 --> 00:16:11.580
tensely still.

00:16:11.639 --> 00:16:13.200
It's an abomination.

00:16:13.259 --> 00:16:14.639
Hawk hissed.

00:16:14.759 --> 00:16:17.220
Skywing Law commands us to kill creatures

00:16:17.220 --> 00:16:18.179
like that at hatching.

00:16:18.240 --> 00:16:21.600
Ruby had a dim memory now of something

00:16:21.600 --> 00:16:23.220
that had happened over a year ago.

00:16:23.340 --> 00:16:26.159
An egg hatching with twins inside.

00:16:26.220 --> 00:16:29.100
The mother trying to escape with both of

00:16:29.100 --> 00:16:29.340
them.

00:16:29.399 --> 00:16:32.039
The palace had been in an uproar for

00:16:32.039 --> 00:16:34.860
weeks, but Ruby got only tiny scraps of

00:16:34.860 --> 00:16:37.139
gossip, usually through tourmaline if she

00:16:37.139 --> 00:16:37.500
was lucky.

00:16:37.559 --> 00:16:40.379
She thought they were all dead.

00:16:40.440 --> 00:16:42.360
The twins and the mother.

00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:45.059
Could this be the one with too much

00:16:45.059 --> 00:16:45.539
fire?

00:16:45.600 --> 00:16:49.440
The strange dragonet squeaked and tried

00:16:49.440 --> 00:16:50.940
to scramble up to the top of the rock

00:16:50.940 --> 00:16:54.000
wall, her tiny wings flapping hopefully.

00:16:54.059 --> 00:16:57.240
Scarlet seized a long metal scepter

00:16:57.240 --> 00:16:59.580
propped beside her throne, and jabbed the

00:16:59.580 --> 00:17:01.379
center of it into the dragonette's

00:17:01.379 --> 00:17:01.740
chest.

00:17:01.799 --> 00:17:04.440
Down, she snarled.

00:17:04.500 --> 00:17:06.960
The dragonette fell back with a yelp.

00:17:07.019 --> 00:17:10.200
As Scarlet withdrew the scepter, Ruby

00:17:10.200 --> 00:17:12.359
could see that the round tip of it had a

00:17:12.359 --> 00:17:14.460
blobby melted spot where it had touched

00:17:14.460 --> 00:17:15.720
the dragonette's scales.

00:17:15.779 --> 00:17:19.440
A worrying molten metal smell joined the

00:17:19.440 --> 00:17:20.400
heat in the room.

00:17:20.460 --> 00:17:23.220
Your majesty.

00:17:23.279 --> 00:17:27.000
Set a squat rust colored dragon near the

00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:28.380
front of the crowd.

00:17:28.440 --> 00:17:30.240
He was one of the oldest dragons in the

00:17:30.240 --> 00:17:32.640
palace, and had served as an advisor to

00:17:32.640 --> 00:17:34.440
Ruby's grandmother when she was queen.

00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:37.920
Whenever he saw Ruby, he invariably made

00:17:37.920 --> 00:17:40.140
an odd clicking sound with his teeth

00:17:40.140 --> 00:17:42.960
commented on how peculiarly long her neck

00:17:42.960 --> 00:17:45.359
was, and told her that the secret of long

00:17:45.359 --> 00:17:47.759
life was eating a goat kidney every day.

00:17:47.819 --> 00:17:50.400
And yet, she could never remember his

00:17:50.400 --> 00:17:50.640
name.

00:17:50.700 --> 00:17:53.339
She and Tourmaline called him kidney

00:17:53.339 --> 00:17:53.700
breath.

00:17:53.759 --> 00:17:58.079
Ahem, said kidney breath importantly

00:17:58.079 --> 00:18:00.779
waiting for the murmurs to die down and

00:18:00.779 --> 00:18:01.799
for everyone to look at him.

00:18:01.859 --> 00:18:04.799
Your majesty.

00:18:04.859 --> 00:18:10.259
Please assure us that this is not what it

00:18:10.259 --> 00:18:10.859
looks like.

00:18:10.980 --> 00:18:14.519
Queen Scarlet gave him a glittering all

00:18:14.519 --> 00:18:15.299
teeth smile.

00:18:15.420 --> 00:18:18.539
Does it look like I have the most

00:18:18.539 --> 00:18:20.519
fabulously dangerous new toy?

00:18:20.579 --> 00:18:24.240
Because that's exactly what this is.

00:18:24.299 --> 00:18:27.480
She flourished one of her wings in the

00:18:27.480 --> 00:18:28.619
dragonette's direction.

00:18:28.680 --> 00:18:32.940
Behold, my new and future champion.

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:35.940
The dragonette poked her head out again

00:18:35.940 --> 00:18:38.460
regarding them all with those sinister

00:18:38.460 --> 00:18:39.119
blue eyes.

00:18:39.180 --> 00:18:42.059
She glanced up at Scarlet's wing overhead

00:18:42.059 --> 00:18:44.519
and reached for it, but the queen kept it

00:18:44.519 --> 00:18:45.539
well out of her grasp.

00:18:45.599 --> 00:18:51.599
Your majesty is the wisest of all dragons

00:18:51.599 --> 00:18:53.400
said kidney breath.

00:18:53.460 --> 00:18:58.200
Your every thought is genius, and all

00:18:58.200 --> 00:19:00.779
your decisions are perfect in every way.

00:19:00.900 --> 00:19:02.940
But.

00:19:03.299 --> 00:19:07.619
Are you sure this is safe?

00:19:07.680 --> 00:19:13.380
Keeping that, that monster alive?

00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:16.259
She is not just any monster.

00:19:16.380 --> 00:19:18.539
Scarlet said smugly.

00:19:18.599 --> 00:19:23.579
She's my monster, and she's so very

00:19:23.579 --> 00:19:23.819
useful.

00:19:23.940 --> 00:19:26.460
Here, darling, show them what you can

00:19:26.460 --> 00:19:26.640
do.

00:19:26.700 --> 00:19:29.579
The queen plucked one of the eggs from a

00:19:29.579 --> 00:19:32.279
guard's talons and passed it casually to

00:19:32.279 --> 00:19:33.059
the dragonette.

00:19:33.119 --> 00:19:36.660
At least, she made it look casual.

00:19:36.779 --> 00:19:39.960
But Ruby could see how carefully Scarlet

00:19:39.960 --> 00:19:42.059
avoided touching the dragonette's claws

00:19:42.059 --> 00:19:44.220
and how quickly she snatched her talons

00:19:44.220 --> 00:19:44.519
back.

00:19:44.579 --> 00:19:47.460
The dragonette looked down at the egg

00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:49.619
which was almost a quarter of her own

00:19:49.619 --> 00:19:50.460
size.

00:19:50.519 --> 00:19:52.859
Her expression was curious and a little

00:19:52.859 --> 00:19:55.079
delighted, as if no one had ever given

00:19:55.079 --> 00:19:55.859
her a toy before.

00:19:55.920 --> 00:19:59.099
And then small tremors began to run

00:19:59.099 --> 00:20:01.740
across the eggshell, and the translucent

00:20:01.740 --> 00:20:04.319
whiteness began to fade gray, and the

00:20:04.319 --> 00:20:06.900
orange shape inside gave a shudder, and

00:20:06.900 --> 00:20:10.019
then turned black, black as coals, black

00:20:10.019 --> 00:20:13.319
as dead burnt husks of trees, before the

00:20:13.319 --> 00:20:15.599
whole egg went black, and no one could

00:20:15.599 --> 00:20:16.500
see inside anymore.

00:20:16.559 --> 00:20:19.559
A hush fell over the room.

00:20:19.619 --> 00:20:21.779
Nobody spoke.

00:20:21.839 --> 00:20:24.839
Nobody could speak.

00:20:24.900 --> 00:20:25.920
Ruby thought.

00:20:25.980 --> 00:20:28.079
She felt as though she couldn't even

00:20:28.079 --> 00:20:28.859
breathe.

00:20:28.920 --> 00:20:31.380
Like perhaps it would be safer to never

00:20:31.380 --> 00:20:32.039
breathe again.

00:20:32.099 --> 00:20:35.819
The egg crumbled into a pile of ash in

00:20:35.819 --> 00:20:37.140
the dragonette's talons.

00:20:37.200 --> 00:20:40.440
The dragonette stared down at her claws

00:20:40.440 --> 00:20:41.700
with an unreadable expression.

00:20:41.759 --> 00:20:43.440
Was she surprised?

00:20:43.500 --> 00:20:45.119
Pleased with herself?

00:20:45.180 --> 00:20:48.839
Did she know that with one simple act, by

00:20:48.839 --> 00:20:52.200
merely holding an egg, she'd managed to

00:20:52.200 --> 00:20:54.059
terrify every dragon in the room?

00:20:54.119 --> 00:20:57.420
She tilted her head slightly to peer up

00:20:57.420 --> 00:21:00.480
at the queen, and in that moment, Ruby

00:21:00.480 --> 00:21:02.400
caught a glimpse of something familiar in

00:21:02.400 --> 00:21:03.480
those weird eyes.

00:21:03.539 --> 00:21:07.259
The dragonette with too much fire was

00:21:07.259 --> 00:21:08.819
worried that Scarlet would be angry with

00:21:08.819 --> 00:21:09.059
her.

00:21:09.119 --> 00:21:11.940
It was Burne who finally broke the

00:21:11.940 --> 00:21:12.299
silence.

00:21:12.359 --> 00:21:16.200
Impressive, she growled.

00:21:16.259 --> 00:21:19.200
Now deal with the rest of them, or let me

00:21:19.200 --> 00:21:19.920
smash them myself.

00:21:19.980 --> 00:21:23.700
Scarlet reached over with a scepter and

00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:25.500
knocked down the wall of rocks in the

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:26.460
dragonette's way.

00:21:26.519 --> 00:21:29.339
Go touch the rest of the eggs.

00:21:29.400 --> 00:21:31.259
Peril she ordered.

00:21:31.319 --> 00:21:34.259
Peril, Ruby thought.

00:21:34.319 --> 00:21:36.180
The monster has a name.

00:21:36.240 --> 00:21:40.380
Peril glanced at the eggs, then down at

00:21:40.380 --> 00:21:42.720
her talons, then back at Queen Scarlet.

00:21:42.779 --> 00:21:45.660
She looked very small next to the 2

00:21:45.660 --> 00:21:46.019
queens.

00:21:46.140 --> 00:21:48.900
But, she said.

00:21:48.960 --> 00:21:51.839
Her voice swallowed by the hot air in the

00:21:51.839 --> 00:21:52.380
hushed room.

00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:54.420
But I burned it.

00:21:54.480 --> 00:21:59.220
You are my champion, said Queen Scarlet

00:21:59.220 --> 00:21:59.700
coldly.

00:21:59.759 --> 00:22:02.519
You do as I tell you to.

00:22:02.640 --> 00:22:06.779
Peril hesitated for a moment, looking

00:22:06.779 --> 00:22:09.900
around the wall of scales and wings and

00:22:09.900 --> 00:22:12.539
unfriendly, suspicious eyes around her.

00:22:12.599 --> 00:22:15.119
She stepped forward, and the guards

00:22:15.119 --> 00:22:17.039
holding the eggs all quickly place them

00:22:17.039 --> 00:22:18.900
on the ground, stumbling out of her way.

00:22:19.019 --> 00:22:24.059
One by one, peril stopped at each egg, and

00:22:24.059 --> 00:22:25.619
laid her claws on it, until the

00:22:25.619 --> 00:22:27.180
dragonette inside was dead.

00:22:27.180 --> 00:22:29.819
She could do that to anyone.

00:22:29.880 --> 00:22:31.740
Ruby realized.

00:22:31.799 --> 00:22:34.859
She can probably kill a full grown dragon

00:22:34.859 --> 00:22:35.880
just by touching him.

00:22:35.940 --> 00:22:38.819
She's the deadliest weapon mother has

00:22:38.819 --> 00:22:39.420
ever found.

00:22:39.480 --> 00:22:43.319
A ripple of horror ricocheted through her

00:22:43.319 --> 00:22:43.559
scales.

00:22:43.619 --> 00:22:47.099
Is that what happened to Tourmaline?

00:22:47.160 --> 00:22:50.039
She couldn't unhook her gaze from the

00:22:50.039 --> 00:22:51.240
murderous dragonette.

00:22:51.359 --> 00:22:54.359
Is my sister now a pile of ashes

00:22:54.359 --> 00:22:54.960
somewhere?

00:22:55.019 --> 00:22:59.339
As peril reached the last egg, Ruby

00:22:59.339 --> 00:23:01.680
finally tore her eyes free and lifted

00:23:01.680 --> 00:23:02.759
them toward the queen's.

00:23:02.819 --> 00:23:05.880
Scarlet was watching Ruby, with a

00:23:05.880 --> 00:23:08.700
satisfied, sinister look, a look that

00:23:08.700 --> 00:23:11.460
said, who would dare challenge me now?

00:23:11.519 --> 00:23:14.220
You, my dreaming daughter.

00:23:14.279 --> 00:23:15.539
Go ahead and try.

00:23:15.599 --> 00:23:18.779
If you even think about it, now you know

00:23:18.779 --> 00:23:21.180
whose talons will find your throat in the

00:23:21.180 --> 00:23:21.900
middle of the night.

00:23:21.960 --> 00:23:23.819
She was right.

00:23:23.880 --> 00:23:26.220
No one could stop Scarlet now.

00:23:26.279 --> 00:23:29.339
Ruby would never be queen.

00:23:29.400 --> 00:23:31.559
Peril would always be there.

00:23:31.619 --> 00:23:35.099
The threat lurking behind the throne, the

00:23:35.099 --> 00:23:37.259
smoking scales that lay in wait for any

00:23:37.259 --> 00:23:39.059
dragon who showed even a hint of

00:23:39.059 --> 00:23:39.420
ambition.

00:23:39.539 --> 00:23:42.839
So I won't, Ruby thought.

00:23:42.900 --> 00:23:45.359
I won't dream of the throne.

00:23:45.420 --> 00:23:48.960
I'll be obedient, loyal, agreeable

00:23:48.960 --> 00:23:50.519
anything she wants me to be.

00:23:50.579 --> 00:23:53.819
Anything that keeps me alive and as far

00:23:53.819 --> 00:23:57.119
away from that monster as I can get, You

00:23:57.119 --> 00:23:57.660
win, mother.

00:23:57.779 --> 00:24:00.839
The dragonette lifted her claws from the

00:24:00.839 --> 00:24:03.059
last smoking egg and turned to Queen

00:24:03.059 --> 00:24:04.980
Scarlet with a hungry look in her eyes.

00:24:05.039 --> 00:24:08.039
Ruby recognized that look too.

00:24:08.099 --> 00:24:10.740
The, do you love me now?

00:24:10.799 --> 00:24:11.700
Look.

00:24:11.759 --> 00:24:16.619
Excellent, said Queen Scarlet, flicking

00:24:16.619 --> 00:24:17.579
her tongue between her teeth.

00:24:17.640 --> 00:24:20.099
A thrilling demonstration.

00:24:20.160 --> 00:24:22.380
Everything I was hoping for.

00:24:22.440 --> 00:24:25.140
As you say, Queen Burn.

00:24:25.200 --> 00:24:27.359
So much for that prophecy now, right?

00:24:27.420 --> 00:24:28.740
Peril.

00:24:28.799 --> 00:24:29.759
Back to your place.

00:24:29.819 --> 00:24:33.180
I hope you know how to control your new

00:24:33.180 --> 00:24:34.200
champion, mother.

00:24:34.259 --> 00:24:36.779
Because she's not just a threat to me.

00:24:36.839 --> 00:24:40.200
The crowd of dragons surged back

00:24:40.200 --> 00:24:43.559
struggling to stay out of peril's path as

00:24:43.559 --> 00:24:45.900
the dragonette walked slowly back to the

00:24:45.900 --> 00:24:46.740
little cage of rocks.

00:24:46.859 --> 00:24:50.579
This dragon could destroy the entire

00:24:50.579 --> 00:24:50.940
world.

00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:55.559
Part one.

00:24:55.619 --> 00:24:57.960
Scales of fire.

00:24:58.019 --> 00:25:00.839
Chapter one.

00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:05.039
Deep in a cave in Jade Mountain, the most

00:25:05.039 --> 00:25:07.079
dangerous dragon empire was hiding.

00:25:07.200 --> 00:25:09.900
Which she was not particularly pleased

00:25:09.900 --> 00:25:10.140
about.

00:25:10.259 --> 00:25:14.279
Just until Ruby's gone, Pearl muttered

00:25:14.279 --> 00:25:14.759
pacing.

00:25:14.880 --> 00:25:16.200
That's what he said.

00:25:16.259 --> 00:25:17.880
Hours ago.

00:25:17.940 --> 00:25:20.039
He said he'd come get me as soon as it

00:25:20.039 --> 00:25:20.700
was safe.

00:25:20.759 --> 00:25:21.480
Ha!

00:25:21.539 --> 00:25:22.920
As if I should be afraid of her.

00:25:22.980 --> 00:25:24.720
I'm not afraid of anyone.

00:25:24.779 --> 00:25:26.940
Three moons.

00:25:27.000 --> 00:25:28.740
It's been forever.

00:25:28.799 --> 00:25:32.220
How long does it take to collect a body?

00:25:32.279 --> 00:25:34.440
And why should she have to hide anyway?

00:25:34.500 --> 00:25:36.299
That's what she wanted to know.

00:25:36.359 --> 00:25:38.940
Yes, she was banished from the Sky

00:25:38.940 --> 00:25:41.160
Kingdom, but Queen Ruby couldn't banish

00:25:41.160 --> 00:25:42.359
her from Jade Mountain 2.

00:25:42.539 --> 00:25:44.460
Clay had said it himself.

00:25:44.519 --> 00:25:46.559
This wasn't the Sky Palace.

00:25:46.619 --> 00:25:49.440
He'd said, you have every right to be

00:25:49.440 --> 00:25:49.680
here.

00:25:49.740 --> 00:25:51.660
Was that true?

00:25:51.720 --> 00:25:54.359
Did she actually have the right to be

00:25:54.359 --> 00:25:57.779
anywhere after everything she'd done?

00:25:57.839 --> 00:26:00.900
But all she wanted was to be with Clay.

00:26:00.960 --> 00:26:04.500
Near him, around him, breathing the same

00:26:04.500 --> 00:26:06.779
air and watching the same skies.

00:26:06.839 --> 00:26:08.339
That wasn't asking too much.

00:26:08.400 --> 00:26:10.859
And if it meant she wasn't hurting anyone

00:26:10.859 --> 00:26:12.660
anymore, wasn't that what everyone

00:26:12.660 --> 00:26:13.079
wanted?

00:26:13.140 --> 00:26:14.940
Maybe not.

00:26:15.000 --> 00:26:17.880
Maybe Queen Ruby wanted peril to be

00:26:17.880 --> 00:26:18.720
miserable and alone.

00:26:18.779 --> 00:26:20.819
Well.

00:26:20.940 --> 00:26:24.119
Peril hissed a tendril of smoke, and

00:26:24.119 --> 00:26:26.099
marched to the cave entrance, peering

00:26:26.099 --> 00:26:26.279
out.

00:26:26.339 --> 00:26:30.000
If any dragon, tried to keep her away

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:32.700
from clay, she would melt off their

00:26:32.700 --> 00:26:33.660
head.

00:26:33.720 --> 00:26:36.660
Even if that dragon was the new sky wing

00:26:36.660 --> 00:26:37.079
queen.

00:26:37.140 --> 00:26:40.859
Unless Clay told me not to, I guess.

00:26:40.920 --> 00:26:43.980
Peril went back to circling the small

00:26:43.980 --> 00:26:46.019
cave, flicking her wings at the

00:26:46.019 --> 00:26:47.519
claustrophobic stone walls.

00:26:47.579 --> 00:26:51.240
There had been a moment, months ago, in

00:26:51.240 --> 00:26:53.759
the chaos of the Skywing transition, when

00:26:53.759 --> 00:26:54.960
Pearl thought things were going to be

00:26:54.960 --> 00:26:55.319
different.

00:26:55.380 --> 00:26:57.900
After she'd helped Clay and the others

00:26:57.900 --> 00:27:00.900
escape from Scarlet's arena, she'd flown

00:27:00.900 --> 00:27:03.180
back to the palace, only to find Queen

00:27:03.180 --> 00:27:05.819
Scarlet and Queen Bern gone, and the

00:27:05.819 --> 00:27:07.259
whole tribe in a state of panic.

00:27:07.259 --> 00:27:09.059
Who'd be in charge now?

00:27:09.119 --> 00:27:11.339
What had happened to their invincible

00:27:11.339 --> 00:27:12.059
queen?

00:27:12.119 --> 00:27:15.000
The relief when Princess Ruby arrived and

00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:15.599
took over?

00:27:15.660 --> 00:27:17.519
Peril remembered it clearly.

00:27:17.579 --> 00:27:20.279
With a wince of pity for her idiotic

00:27:20.279 --> 00:27:21.359
hopeful former self.

00:27:21.420 --> 00:27:24.059
Along with everyone else, she had thought

00:27:24.059 --> 00:27:27.599
a new queen, one who isn't terrifying

00:27:27.599 --> 00:27:28.920
everything's going to change.

00:27:28.980 --> 00:27:30.900
It was true.

00:27:30.960 --> 00:27:33.000
Everything had changed.

00:27:33.059 --> 00:27:37.259
For the better. generally, for everyone

00:27:37.259 --> 00:27:38.220
but peril.

00:27:38.279 --> 00:27:41.099
There had been no thank yous, no

00:27:41.099 --> 00:27:42.779
celebrations or medals.

00:27:42.839 --> 00:27:45.480
Idiotic, hopeful former self had hoped

00:27:45.480 --> 00:27:46.619
for them.

00:27:46.680 --> 00:27:48.599
Idiotic hopeful former self was very

00:27:48.599 --> 00:27:49.079
stupid.

00:27:49.200 --> 00:27:52.319
In fact, there hadn't been any

00:27:52.319 --> 00:27:54.720
acknowledgment at all that peril had

00:27:54.720 --> 00:27:56.640
helped the dragonettes of destiny defeat

00:27:56.640 --> 00:27:57.539
Queen Scarlet.

00:27:57.599 --> 00:28:01.740
I mean, they did most of it, but I did

00:28:01.740 --> 00:28:02.099
help.

00:28:02.160 --> 00:28:03.900
Didn't anyone notice?

00:28:04.019 --> 00:28:08.579
Instead, Ruby's very 1st act as queen had

00:28:08.579 --> 00:28:10.319
been to banish peril from the Sky

00:28:10.319 --> 00:28:10.740
Kingdom.

00:28:10.799 --> 00:28:13.619
Peril could still hear her hissing.

00:28:13.680 --> 00:28:16.259
I never want to see you again.

00:28:16.319 --> 00:28:19.380
And she could still feel the strange

00:28:19.380 --> 00:28:22.799
falling vertigo it had given her, as if

00:28:22.799 --> 00:28:24.059
her wings had been sliced off.

00:28:24.119 --> 00:28:27.839
Until that moment, Ruby had always been

00:28:27.839 --> 00:28:31.799
not friendly, exactly, but not hostile

00:28:31.799 --> 00:28:32.279
either.

00:28:32.339 --> 00:28:34.799
Mostly she'd been quiet.

00:28:34.859 --> 00:28:38.460
She'd stayed out of peril's way, nodding

00:28:38.460 --> 00:28:40.680
politely in the halls, or leaving the

00:28:40.680 --> 00:28:42.420
room when peril came to talk to Scarlet.

00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:45.000
She'd never seemed very queenly, to be

00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:48.059
frank, so where did this imperious

00:28:48.059 --> 00:28:49.319
decisive dragon come from?

00:28:49.380 --> 00:28:51.900
But why?

00:28:51.960 --> 00:28:54.779
Peril had asked, trying to ignore the

00:28:54.779 --> 00:28:56.400
expressions on the guards that surrounded

00:28:56.400 --> 00:28:56.880
Ruby.

00:28:56.940 --> 00:28:59.640
Why did they look so pleased?

00:28:59.700 --> 00:29:02.759
Because you're a murderer?

00:29:02.819 --> 00:29:05.640
Ruby replied, as if that should have been

00:29:05.640 --> 00:29:07.259
perfectly self evident.

00:29:07.319 --> 00:29:09.660
But aren't we all murderers?

00:29:09.720 --> 00:29:11.160
Peril had thought.

00:29:11.220 --> 00:29:14.160
Didn't we all do terrible things because

00:29:14.160 --> 00:29:15.539
Queen Scarlet told us to?

00:29:15.660 --> 00:29:18.839
Can you find me one dragon who defied

00:29:18.839 --> 00:29:19.019
her?

00:29:19.079 --> 00:29:21.839
Why am I the only one getting punished

00:29:21.839 --> 00:29:22.740
for obedience?

00:29:22.799 --> 00:29:26.640
Then she'd looked into Ruby's eyes, and

00:29:26.640 --> 00:29:28.200
realized it was personal.

00:29:28.259 --> 00:29:31.259
Ruby actually hated her.

00:29:31.319 --> 00:29:33.960
Peril had never known that.

00:29:34.200 --> 00:29:36.900
And even now, she still wasn't sure why.

00:29:36.960 --> 00:29:39.900
Hadn't they both been loyal Skywing

00:29:39.900 --> 00:29:40.440
subjects?

00:29:40.500 --> 00:29:42.420
Hadn't they both always followed

00:29:42.420 --> 00:29:43.440
Scarlett's orders?

00:29:43.500 --> 00:29:46.980
Couldn't Ruby, of all dragons, understand

00:29:46.980 --> 00:29:48.599
everything that peril had done?

00:29:48.660 --> 00:29:53.519
Leave now, Ruby had said, or die

00:29:53.519 --> 00:29:54.480
whichever.

00:29:54.539 --> 00:29:57.299
And how do you plan to make me?

00:29:57.359 --> 00:30:01.019
Peril had felt fiery rage swelling under

00:30:01.019 --> 00:30:01.500
her scales?

00:30:01.559 --> 00:30:04.980
I could kill you right now as easily as

00:30:04.980 --> 00:30:05.400
breathing.

00:30:05.460 --> 00:30:07.980
I could kill everyone in this cave just

00:30:07.980 --> 00:30:09.299
by spreading my wings.

00:30:09.359 --> 00:30:11.460
She nearly had?

00:30:11.519 --> 00:30:14.579
She'd really, really wanted to.

00:30:14.640 --> 00:30:17.640
The only thing that had stopped her was

00:30:17.640 --> 00:30:18.539
thinking of clay.

00:30:18.599 --> 00:30:22.200
He said he saw good in her, which

00:30:22.200 --> 00:30:24.480
probably meant he didn't want her setting

00:30:24.480 --> 00:30:26.579
large groups of dragons on fire every

00:30:26.579 --> 00:30:27.900
time she got mad.

00:30:27.960 --> 00:30:30.299
He thought she could be more than Queen

00:30:30.299 --> 00:30:31.799
Scarlet's pet killer.

00:30:31.859 --> 00:30:35.220
And so, for him, she would be.

00:30:35.279 --> 00:30:38.460
Well, she would try.

00:30:38.519 --> 00:30:40.799
It was hard though.

00:30:40.859 --> 00:30:43.200
Dragons could be awful.

00:30:43.319 --> 00:30:45.180
Some of them really deserved to be set on

00:30:45.180 --> 00:30:45.480
fire.

00:30:45.539 --> 00:30:48.839
And she didn't like being told to sit in

00:30:48.839 --> 00:30:51.240
a cave for hours, just because the sight

00:30:51.240 --> 00:30:52.799
of her might make Ruby angry.

00:30:52.859 --> 00:30:55.980
The Skywing Queen was on her way to Jade

00:30:55.980 --> 00:30:57.779
Mountain to collect the body of the

00:30:57.779 --> 00:31:00.180
student who died, carnelian.

00:31:00.240 --> 00:31:03.240
So, yes, she probably wouldn't be in a

00:31:03.240 --> 00:31:04.200
very good mood to begin with.

00:31:04.319 --> 00:31:06.900
Peril could understand that it would be

00:31:06.900 --> 00:31:08.759
easier for Clay and his friends if she

00:31:08.759 --> 00:31:11.279
stayed out of the way, so that Ruby's

00:31:11.279 --> 00:31:13.140
visit would go as smoothly as possible.

00:31:13.200 --> 00:31:16.559
But why was it taking so long?

00:31:16.619 --> 00:31:20.220
Carol paced to the cave entrance again

00:31:20.220 --> 00:31:22.440
peering out into the dimly lit tunnel.

00:31:22.559 --> 00:31:25.859
Farther along the tunnel, deeper in the

00:31:25.859 --> 00:31:28.319
mountain, the faint sounds of splashing

00:31:28.319 --> 00:31:30.059
and laughter echoed from the underground

00:31:30.059 --> 00:31:30.420
lake.

00:31:30.539 --> 00:31:33.180
The sea wing students had decided the

00:31:33.180 --> 00:31:35.400
lake was their exclusive clubhouse and

00:31:35.400 --> 00:31:36.660
were there all the time now.

00:31:36.660 --> 00:31:39.180
Peril was always careful to avoid them.

00:31:39.240 --> 00:31:42.059
She avoided all the students as much as

00:31:42.059 --> 00:31:42.420
she could.

00:31:42.480 --> 00:31:46.200
Everyone here was afraid of her, but no

00:31:46.200 --> 00:31:49.619
one was careful of her, the way they'd

00:31:49.619 --> 00:31:50.579
been in the Sky Kingdom.

00:31:50.640 --> 00:31:53.339
Only the sky wings knew how to steer a

00:31:53.339 --> 00:31:54.180
wide path around her.

00:31:54.240 --> 00:31:57.240
The dragons in Scarlet's palace had been

00:31:57.240 --> 00:31:58.740
experts at avoiding peril.

00:31:58.799 --> 00:32:01.680
Wherever she'd gone, empty space opened

00:32:01.680 --> 00:32:02.220
up around her.

00:32:02.279 --> 00:32:06.240
Here, she had to be the cautious one.

00:32:06.299 --> 00:32:09.240
She was responsible for staying out of

00:32:09.240 --> 00:32:11.460
their way, even though they were

00:32:11.460 --> 00:32:13.799
terrified of her, the other students kept

00:32:13.799 --> 00:32:16.799
forgetting she was there, but what if she

00:32:16.799 --> 00:32:19.259
bumped into one of them, what if her tail

00:32:19.259 --> 00:32:20.819
brushed someone's wing by accident?

00:32:20.880 --> 00:32:23.400
How would Clay look at her then?

00:32:23.460 --> 00:32:26.940
He said she deserved a 2nd chance.

00:32:27.000 --> 00:32:30.000
But if she burned one of his students, she

00:32:30.000 --> 00:32:31.259
knew there wouldn't be a 3rd.

00:32:31.319 --> 00:32:34.619
Peril's claws twisted and clenched

00:32:34.619 --> 00:32:37.019
thinking of all the dragonettes Clay was

00:32:37.019 --> 00:32:37.500
protecting here.

00:32:37.619 --> 00:32:40.380
Did he love them more than her?

00:32:40.440 --> 00:32:42.420
He must.

00:32:42.480 --> 00:32:43.559
He should.

00:32:43.619 --> 00:32:45.059
Why wouldn't he?

00:32:45.119 --> 00:32:48.240
They were innocent symbols of the bright

00:32:48.240 --> 00:32:50.039
future he always talked about.

00:32:50.099 --> 00:32:51.839
None of them had murdered.

00:32:51.900 --> 00:32:55.259
Her mind shied away from the numbers, a

00:32:55.259 --> 00:32:56.519
whole lot of dragons.

00:32:56.579 --> 00:32:59.279
But none of them had saved his life

00:32:59.279 --> 00:32:59.759
either.

00:32:59.819 --> 00:33:03.660
And his friends. didn't matter.

00:33:03.779 --> 00:33:05.519
They still hated her.

00:33:05.579 --> 00:33:08.160
Those shining friends who stood between

00:33:08.160 --> 00:33:10.980
her and clay, like blue and green and

00:33:10.980 --> 00:33:13.680
gold flames, flaring suspiciously

00:33:13.680 --> 00:33:15.240
whenever she so much as looked at him.

00:33:15.299 --> 00:33:18.779
Down on the sands of Burns stronghold

00:33:18.779 --> 00:33:20.700
after she'd saved him.

00:33:20.759 --> 00:33:23.160
Under the eyes of all the tribes, Clay

00:33:23.160 --> 00:33:25.980
had said, maybe peril is our wings of

00:33:25.980 --> 00:33:26.279
fire.

00:33:26.400 --> 00:33:29.819
And for one surreal moment, she'd thought

00:33:29.819 --> 00:33:31.259
maybe I am.

00:33:31.319 --> 00:33:33.900
Maybe this makes up for everything I've

00:33:33.900 --> 00:33:34.200
done.

00:33:34.259 --> 00:33:37.559
Maybe by saving clay, I've saved the

00:33:37.559 --> 00:33:37.920
world.

00:33:37.980 --> 00:33:40.980
Maybe everyone will forgive me now.

00:33:41.039 --> 00:33:43.680
Maybe everyone will love me now.

00:33:43.740 --> 00:33:47.099
But that wasn't what it happened.

00:33:47.160 --> 00:33:49.559
After the end of the war.

00:33:49.619 --> 00:33:52.140
Peril had searched for Queen Scarlet for

00:33:52.140 --> 00:33:55.380
months, all across the continent, and

00:33:55.380 --> 00:33:57.779
everywhere she went, dragons fled

00:33:57.779 --> 00:33:59.220
screaming at the side of her.

00:33:59.279 --> 00:34:02.579
Or they fainted, or they threw spears and

00:34:02.579 --> 00:34:04.680
rocks at her, along with anything else

00:34:04.680 --> 00:34:06.900
sharp or pointy, or heavy that they could

00:34:06.900 --> 00:34:07.740
get their talons on.

00:34:07.799 --> 00:34:10.679
Once, she'd been walloped in the face by

00:34:10.679 --> 00:34:13.019
a dead crocodile, flung from the depths

00:34:13.019 --> 00:34:14.460
of the mud wing swamps.

00:34:14.519 --> 00:34:17.280
It was strange to realize that things

00:34:17.280 --> 00:34:18.960
like that could hurt more on the inside

00:34:18.960 --> 00:34:20.699
of your scales than the outside.

00:34:20.760 --> 00:34:24.659
It was strange to realize that a dragon

00:34:24.659 --> 00:34:27.599
who couldn't be hurt on the outside could

00:34:27.599 --> 00:34:29.880
have so many ragged holes on the inside.

00:34:29.940 --> 00:34:33.780
There, talons thumping on stone.

00:34:33.840 --> 00:34:35.940
The rough slither of a tail.

00:34:36.000 --> 00:34:37.019
Was it him?

00:34:37.079 --> 00:34:40.739
Peril nearly leaped into the corridor, and

00:34:40.739 --> 00:34:42.599
came within a wing flicker of colliding

00:34:42.599 --> 00:34:44.219
with a dragon who definitely wasn't

00:34:44.219 --> 00:34:45.179
clay.

00:34:45.239 --> 00:34:48.419
The dark green sea wing dragonette, didn't

00:34:48.419 --> 00:34:50.879
scream, or faint, or stagger back in

00:34:50.879 --> 00:34:51.299
terror.

00:34:51.360 --> 00:34:54.480
He simply froze, slamming his eyes closed

00:34:54.480 --> 00:34:56.579
as though danger would obligingly

00:34:56.579 --> 00:34:58.199
disappear the moment he couldn't see it

00:34:58.199 --> 00:34:58.440
anymore.

00:34:58.500 --> 00:35:01.199
What are you doing?

00:35:01.260 --> 00:35:04.019
Pearl yelped, jumping away from him?

00:35:04.139 --> 00:35:08.340
Um, he said in a low, rumbly voice

00:35:08.340 --> 00:35:12.480
walking in the halls, back to my cave.

00:35:12.539 --> 00:35:15.840
He risked opening one eye to peer at

00:35:15.840 --> 00:35:16.019
her.

00:35:16.079 --> 00:35:21.239
Well, that was very stupid of you, she

00:35:21.239 --> 00:35:21.659
snapped.

00:35:21.719 --> 00:35:24.420
He thought about that for a moment, then

00:35:24.420 --> 00:35:25.920
opened both eyes and regarded her

00:35:25.920 --> 00:35:26.460
peaceably.

00:35:26.519 --> 00:35:29.099
Oh, he said.

00:35:29.159 --> 00:35:30.360
Sorry.

00:35:30.420 --> 00:35:33.059
What a peculiar dragon.

00:35:33.179 --> 00:35:35.639
He seemed to have no fire about him at

00:35:35.639 --> 00:35:35.880
all.

00:35:35.940 --> 00:35:38.940
That wasn't a sea wing thing.

00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:41.340
Tsunami was a fireball that blazed up and

00:35:41.340 --> 00:35:43.500
down and sideways, and everything that

00:35:43.500 --> 00:35:45.780
made her mad, which was most things.

00:35:45.900 --> 00:35:48.480
And her sister, the little sea wing

00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:50.940
princess, at least from a distance, seemed

00:35:50.940 --> 00:35:53.159
to be a shower of bright orange sparks on

00:35:53.159 --> 00:35:53.579
the inside.

00:35:53.639 --> 00:35:58.139
This sea wing, on the other talon, was a

00:35:58.139 --> 00:36:01.559
puddle, a fireless puddle, blobbing

00:36:01.559 --> 00:36:03.360
quietly into the rocks in front of her

00:36:03.360 --> 00:36:04.980
not even trying to get away.

00:36:05.039 --> 00:36:08.280
Your peril, aren't you?

00:36:08.280 --> 00:36:09.179
he said.

00:36:09.239 --> 00:36:11.159
Queen Scarlet's.

00:36:11.280 --> 00:36:12.659
He trailed off.

00:36:12.719 --> 00:36:14.760
Perhaps realizing there was no good way

00:36:14.760 --> 00:36:15.780
to end that sentence.

00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:19.380
Champion, weapon, notorious death

00:36:19.380 --> 00:36:19.980
monster?

00:36:20.039 --> 00:36:21.420
Yes.

00:36:21.480 --> 00:36:22.920
She hissed.

00:36:22.980 --> 00:36:25.619
I'm Queen Scarlet's notorious Death

00:36:25.619 --> 00:36:26.039
Monster.

00:36:26.099 --> 00:36:29.280
He made an odd hiccuping noise and ducked

00:36:29.280 --> 00:36:29.519
his head.

00:36:29.579 --> 00:36:32.280
Uh, okay.

00:36:32.340 --> 00:36:35.219
I'll just go then.

00:36:35.280 --> 00:36:38.219
What would Clay want her to do in this

00:36:38.219 --> 00:36:38.760
situation?

00:36:38.820 --> 00:36:42.900
Maybe you'll make some friends here, he'd

00:36:42.900 --> 00:36:45.659
said, in that oblivious, magical way he

00:36:45.659 --> 00:36:48.360
had of thinking that any other dragons in

00:36:48.360 --> 00:36:49.980
the world might have open hearts like

00:36:49.980 --> 00:36:50.280
his.

00:36:50.400 --> 00:36:52.500
Who are you?

00:36:52.559 --> 00:36:54.000
She asked.

00:36:54.059 --> 00:36:55.739
Hmm.

00:36:55.800 --> 00:36:57.960
That came out more menacing than it

00:36:57.960 --> 00:36:58.860
sounded in my head.

00:36:58.920 --> 00:37:02.760
I mean, who are you?

00:37:02.940 --> 00:37:06.119
She tried, adding a sunnyish, cheerful

00:37:06.119 --> 00:37:07.260
lilt to her voice.

00:37:07.320 --> 00:37:09.059
Now I sound manic.

00:37:09.119 --> 00:37:12.780
I'm not being creepy, she added hastily.

00:37:12.840 --> 00:37:15.480
I'm not, like, putting you on a murder

00:37:15.480 --> 00:37:16.079
list or anything.

00:37:16.139 --> 00:37:18.960
I don't have a murder list, not a to be

00:37:18.960 --> 00:37:19.500
murdered list.

00:37:19.559 --> 00:37:21.179
I mean, wait, no.

00:37:21.239 --> 00:37:23.820
To be clear, I have no kind of murder

00:37:23.820 --> 00:37:25.980
list at all, definitely out of the

00:37:25.980 --> 00:37:27.000
murdering business me.

00:37:27.059 --> 00:37:28.679
Maybe I should stop saying the word

00:37:28.679 --> 00:37:29.159
murder.

00:37:29.219 --> 00:37:31.199
That would be great.

00:37:31.260 --> 00:37:33.480
The Seawing said.

00:37:33.539 --> 00:37:35.159
If you wouldn't mind.

00:37:35.219 --> 00:37:39.059
I just did what I was told, she said in a

00:37:39.059 --> 00:37:39.360
rush.

00:37:39.420 --> 00:37:41.579
She couldn't remember another dragon

00:37:41.579 --> 00:37:43.260
standing still long enough to hear her

00:37:43.260 --> 00:37:45.840
say that, not since Ruby had thrown her

00:37:45.840 --> 00:37:46.800
out of the Sky Palace.

00:37:46.860 --> 00:37:49.679
I was doing what my queen told me to do.

00:37:49.739 --> 00:37:51.119
Isn't that what everyone does?

00:37:51.179 --> 00:37:54.000
I can't help what I'm like. and what she

00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:54.539
made me do.

00:37:54.599 --> 00:37:56.039
Can I?

00:37:56.099 --> 00:37:58.980
Maybe it was that he didn't look scared.

00:37:59.039 --> 00:38:01.619
He didn't look thrilled to be having this

00:38:01.619 --> 00:38:03.960
conversation, but he hadn't run screaming

00:38:03.960 --> 00:38:04.199
yet.

00:38:04.260 --> 00:38:07.320
His green eyed gaze traveled thoughtfully

00:38:07.320 --> 00:38:10.139
along her smoking scales, shifted for a

00:38:10.139 --> 00:38:12.000
moment to his own talons, and then

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:12.719
dropped to the ground.

00:38:12.780 --> 00:38:15.300
I guess, he said.

00:38:15.360 --> 00:38:16.860
Turtle.

00:38:16.920 --> 00:38:19.440
Peril puzzled over this for a moment.

00:38:19.500 --> 00:38:21.659
Was it some kind of sea wing code?

00:38:21.719 --> 00:38:24.059
Was he calling her a turtle?

00:38:24.119 --> 00:38:25.440
Was that a good or a bad thing?

00:38:25.559 --> 00:38:27.900
Moose?

00:38:27.960 --> 00:38:30.119
She tried out, just to see what would

00:38:30.119 --> 00:38:30.360
happen.

00:38:30.420 --> 00:38:32.280
He squinted at her.

00:38:32.340 --> 00:38:36.900
Uh, I mean, my name is Turtle.

00:38:36.960 --> 00:38:39.480
Oh, she said.

00:38:39.539 --> 00:38:40.380
Right.

00:38:40.440 --> 00:38:41.340
Hello.

00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:43.739
Thank you for not screaming or fainting

00:38:43.739 --> 00:38:45.539
or throwing a crocodile at me.

00:38:45.599 --> 00:38:48.179
I thought about it, he said.

00:38:48.239 --> 00:38:50.159
I mean, not the crocodile.

00:38:50.219 --> 00:38:52.559
Definitely not in the reptile throwing

00:38:52.559 --> 00:38:53.219
business, me.

00:38:53.280 --> 00:38:56.699
Now it was her turn to narrow her eyes at

00:38:56.699 --> 00:38:57.059
him.

00:38:57.119 --> 00:38:58.800
Was he making fun of her?

00:38:58.860 --> 00:39:00.900
Ha ha.

00:39:00.960 --> 00:39:01.860
He tried.

00:39:01.980 --> 00:39:03.780
Friendly joke.

00:39:03.840 --> 00:39:05.820
Are those allowed?

00:39:05.880 --> 00:39:08.579
Why aren't you scared of me?

00:39:08.639 --> 00:39:09.780
She asked.

00:39:09.840 --> 00:39:12.719
I am, he said.

00:39:12.780 --> 00:39:16.679
I just, you're not the only dragon I know

00:39:16.679 --> 00:39:18.000
with dangerous powers.

00:39:18.059 --> 00:39:19.860
Really?

00:39:19.920 --> 00:39:20.940
She said.

00:39:21.000 --> 00:39:22.559
What did that mean?

00:39:22.619 --> 00:39:24.360
Who was he talking about?

00:39:24.420 --> 00:39:27.780
But before he could answer, a roar

00:39:27.780 --> 00:39:29.760
billowed down through the corridors like

00:39:29.760 --> 00:39:31.019
a rolling smoke cloud.

00:39:31.079 --> 00:39:34.380
Turtle flared his wings, his green eyes

00:39:34.380 --> 00:39:34.860
wide.

00:39:34.920 --> 00:39:36.780
What was that?

00:39:36.900 --> 00:39:39.179
Probably Queen Ruby?

00:39:39.239 --> 00:39:40.139
Carol said.

00:39:40.199 --> 00:39:42.059
Was Ruby yelling at clay?

00:39:42.119 --> 00:39:43.260
Was Clay all right?

00:39:43.320 --> 00:39:45.059
Did he need her to come protect him?

00:39:45.119 --> 00:39:47.519
She glanced back at the row of fire

00:39:47.519 --> 00:39:49.260
globes leading uphill to the school.

00:39:49.320 --> 00:39:52.380
Maybe they just told her that I'm here?

00:39:52.440 --> 00:39:54.179
Want to go find out?

00:39:54.239 --> 00:39:55.739
Turtle asked.

00:39:55.800 --> 00:39:57.599
Pearl frowned at him.

00:39:57.659 --> 00:40:00.420
So I can get roared at face to face?

00:40:00.480 --> 00:40:02.880
That does sound more fun.

00:40:02.940 --> 00:40:07.199
I don't mean go say hi, turtle

00:40:07.199 --> 00:40:07.800
protested.

00:40:07.860 --> 00:40:11.039
I mean, I'm going to eavesdrop to see

00:40:11.039 --> 00:40:11.699
what's happening.

00:40:11.760 --> 00:40:12.960
So do you want to come?

00:40:13.019 --> 00:40:15.659
Peril curled her wings in.

00:40:15.719 --> 00:40:16.980
Severely tempted.

00:40:17.039 --> 00:40:19.500
Oh no, I shouldn't.

00:40:19.619 --> 00:40:21.059
Clay would be upset with me.

00:40:21.119 --> 00:40:22.440
He told me to wait here.

00:40:22.500 --> 00:40:26.159
He doesn't have to know, Turtle said with

00:40:26.159 --> 00:40:26.579
a shrug.

00:40:26.639 --> 00:40:28.739
That's kind of the point of being

00:40:28.739 --> 00:40:31.199
stealthy, and if he doesn't catch you

00:40:31.199 --> 00:40:32.519
then you're not doing anything wrong.

00:40:32.579 --> 00:40:33.719
Are you?

00:40:33.780 --> 00:40:35.880
That sounded true.

00:40:36.000 --> 00:40:38.280
That sounded very true.

00:40:38.340 --> 00:40:41.099
Really, Clay just wanted her to stay out

00:40:41.099 --> 00:40:42.000
of Ruby's way.

00:40:42.059 --> 00:40:44.400
So if she didn't let Ruby see her, that

00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:45.840
was basically the same thing, right?

00:40:45.900 --> 00:40:51.000
After all, he didn't specifically say you

00:40:51.000 --> 00:40:52.800
must hide in a cave for hours like an

00:40:52.800 --> 00:40:53.940
obedient snail?

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:55.800
Stop for a moment.

00:40:55.860 --> 00:40:57.840
Think this through.

00:40:57.960 --> 00:41:00.300
On the one talent.

00:41:00.360 --> 00:41:02.400
She was still pretty sure Clay wouldn't

00:41:02.400 --> 00:41:03.239
approve of this plan.

00:41:03.300 --> 00:41:07.440
On the other talent, it sounded a lot

00:41:07.440 --> 00:41:09.659
more appealing than sitting in a cave

00:41:09.659 --> 00:41:10.500
waiting to be released.

00:41:10.619 --> 00:41:13.019
On the 3rd talent.

00:41:13.139 --> 00:41:15.539
Why was this strange sea wing offering to

00:41:15.539 --> 00:41:16.139
hang out with her?

00:41:16.199 --> 00:41:18.059
Did he have an agenda?

00:41:18.119 --> 00:41:20.820
Was it because if they got caught, she

00:41:20.820 --> 00:41:22.260
was sure to get in a lot more trouble

00:41:22.260 --> 00:41:22.920
than he would?

00:41:23.039 --> 00:41:27.719
Then again, on the 4th talon, shouldn't

00:41:27.719 --> 00:41:29.760
she say yes to the 1st friendly dragon

00:41:29.760 --> 00:41:30.780
she'd met at the school?

00:41:30.840 --> 00:41:34.619
Clay did want her to make friends, so in

00:41:34.619 --> 00:41:36.599
a way, she was doing something he would

00:41:36.599 --> 00:41:37.139
approve of.

00:41:37.199 --> 00:41:38.519
Right?

00:41:38.579 --> 00:41:42.840
Unless Clay secretly thought she was too

00:41:42.840 --> 00:41:44.820
dangerous for anyone to be friends with.

00:41:44.880 --> 00:41:46.619
He might think that.

00:41:46.739 --> 00:41:48.239
She kind of was.

00:41:48.300 --> 00:41:51.900
Her only friend before Clay, had been

00:41:51.900 --> 00:41:54.179
killed by Queen Scarlet for telling peril

00:41:54.179 --> 00:41:54.780
too much.

00:41:54.780 --> 00:41:58.440
Well, then, maybe she needed more friends

00:41:58.440 --> 00:41:59.760
so that some of them could be

00:41:59.760 --> 00:42:00.239
expendable.

00:42:00.300 --> 00:42:03.300
If anything happened to Clay right now, it

00:42:03.300 --> 00:42:06.780
would be the end of all things.

00:42:06.840 --> 00:42:09.719
She would literally burn down the world.

00:42:09.780 --> 00:42:12.719
She couldn't even think about it, or else

00:42:12.719 --> 00:42:14.519
the tunnel would soon be full of rage

00:42:14.519 --> 00:42:14.880
smoke.

00:42:14.940 --> 00:42:19.079
But if she had clay and turtle as friends

00:42:19.079 --> 00:42:21.300
and then Turtle got himself killed by

00:42:21.300 --> 00:42:23.880
Queen Scarlet, or accidentally set on

00:42:23.880 --> 00:42:24.239
fire.

00:42:24.300 --> 00:42:27.420
Well, then she'd survive okay, because

00:42:27.420 --> 00:42:28.500
she'd still have clay.

00:42:28.559 --> 00:42:31.619
It occurred to her that this was a rather

00:42:31.619 --> 00:42:33.360
morbid train of thought to be having

00:42:33.360 --> 00:42:34.199
about a new friend.

00:42:34.260 --> 00:42:38.219
Yes, she said decisively, making him

00:42:38.219 --> 00:42:38.460
jump.

00:42:38.519 --> 00:42:39.659
Let's go.

00:42:39.719 --> 00:42:42.420
You walk in front, so I don't whack you

00:42:42.420 --> 00:42:44.579
with my tail by accident, but don't move

00:42:44.579 --> 00:42:46.860
too slowly or I might accidentally step

00:42:46.860 --> 00:42:47.219
on you.

00:42:47.280 --> 00:42:50.099
She ducked into the cave again to let him

00:42:50.099 --> 00:42:50.699
buy safely.

00:42:50.760 --> 00:42:54.780
Turtle had an, I am now sensing this was

00:42:54.780 --> 00:42:57.719
a terrible idea, expression on his face

00:42:57.719 --> 00:43:00.539
but he took the lead without arguing, and

00:43:00.539 --> 00:43:02.400
managed to walk fast enough that peril

00:43:02.400 --> 00:43:03.119
wasn't annoyed.

00:43:03.179 --> 00:43:05.940
The roar echoed from above again.

00:43:06.000 --> 00:43:10.800
Together, more or less, Turtle and Peril

00:43:10.800 --> 00:43:12.239
headed straight for it.

00:43:12.300 --> 00:43:16.440
Chapter 2.

00:43:16.679 --> 00:43:20.699
For the past week, Carnelian's body had

00:43:20.699 --> 00:43:22.739
been kept in a cave near the peak of Jade

00:43:22.739 --> 00:43:23.579
Mountain.

00:43:23.639 --> 00:43:26.039
According to Skywing tradition, their

00:43:26.039 --> 00:43:28.260
dead were offered to the sky for 7 days

00:43:28.260 --> 00:43:29.460
before being burned.

00:43:29.519 --> 00:43:33.059
An old dragon named Osprey, the only one

00:43:33.059 --> 00:43:34.679
in the sky palace who would speak with

00:43:34.679 --> 00:43:37.440
peril voluntarily, had told peril that

00:43:37.440 --> 00:43:39.360
this was to make sure their spirits could

00:43:39.360 --> 00:43:42.960
fly free and return as sky wings, instead

00:43:42.960 --> 00:43:44.280
of coming back as any other kind of

00:43:44.280 --> 00:43:44.699
dragon.

00:43:44.760 --> 00:43:47.460
That kind of talk always made Queen

00:43:47.460 --> 00:43:48.780
Scarlet roll her eyes, though.

00:43:48.900 --> 00:43:51.599
She let her tribe follow whatever rituals

00:43:51.599 --> 00:43:53.699
they cared about, but she was not much

00:43:53.699 --> 00:43:55.559
interested in what happened to dragons

00:43:55.559 --> 00:43:56.340
after they were dead.

00:43:56.400 --> 00:44:00.179
Peril had visited the body twice, at

00:44:00.179 --> 00:44:02.099
night, when everyone else was asleep.

00:44:02.159 --> 00:44:04.559
She didn't remember ever meeting the

00:44:04.559 --> 00:44:06.780
fierce red dragonette in the Sky Kingdom

00:44:06.780 --> 00:44:10.079
but then she didn't know most Skywings by

00:44:10.079 --> 00:44:10.260
name.

00:44:10.320 --> 00:44:13.079
Queen Scarlet didn't like it when Pearl

00:44:13.079 --> 00:44:14.340
tried to talk to other dragons.

00:44:14.460 --> 00:44:17.099
To be honest, neither did the other

00:44:17.099 --> 00:44:17.579
dragons.

00:44:17.639 --> 00:44:20.820
So peril had seen the morning cave by

00:44:20.820 --> 00:44:23.880
moonlight, the tall, arched roof, the

00:44:23.880 --> 00:44:25.980
towering slender pillars of pale gray

00:44:25.980 --> 00:44:26.340
rock.

00:44:26.400 --> 00:44:29.579
All the windows and skylights that opened

00:44:29.579 --> 00:44:30.000
to the air.

00:44:30.059 --> 00:44:33.480
And she'd seen the burned dragon wrapped

00:44:33.480 --> 00:44:36.719
in white silk, as still and empty as any

00:44:36.719 --> 00:44:38.820
of the charred bodies Peril had left on

00:44:38.820 --> 00:44:40.500
Scarlet's arena sands.

00:44:40.559 --> 00:44:42.840
But she hadn't seen the cave in the

00:44:42.840 --> 00:44:43.380
daytime before.

00:44:43.440 --> 00:44:46.199
She hadn't seen the sunlight pouring in

00:44:46.199 --> 00:44:49.079
white and gold and backed with blue sky

00:44:49.079 --> 00:44:51.780
or the wind rippling the silk, so it

00:44:51.780 --> 00:44:53.159
looked like carnelian was breathing.

00:44:53.219 --> 00:44:56.280
Now it really looked like a place where

00:44:56.280 --> 00:44:57.420
spirit could be set free.

00:44:57.480 --> 00:45:00.539
A place where a new sky wing might rise

00:45:00.539 --> 00:45:00.780
again.

00:45:00.900 --> 00:45:04.019
Unless it was scared off by the angry

00:45:04.019 --> 00:45:06.059
dragons gathered around the body anyhow.

00:45:06.119 --> 00:45:09.119
On the plus side, at least all the

00:45:09.119 --> 00:45:11.400
shouting meant no one could hear turtle

00:45:11.400 --> 00:45:13.260
and pearl sneaking out the passage toward

00:45:13.260 --> 00:45:13.500
them.

00:45:13.559 --> 00:45:16.980
Turtle crouched behind a boulder near the

00:45:16.980 --> 00:45:17.760
cave entrance.

00:45:17.820 --> 00:45:20.820
Peril peeked in, long enough to see at

00:45:20.820 --> 00:45:22.800
least a dozen skywings crowding the

00:45:22.800 --> 00:45:25.320
chamber, and decided to stay farther back

00:45:25.320 --> 00:45:27.780
keeping a few curves of the wall and

00:45:27.780 --> 00:45:30.599
several columns between her and the Queen

00:45:30.599 --> 00:45:31.199
who hated her.

00:45:31.260 --> 00:45:36.059
I smell lies all over this story, snarled

00:45:36.059 --> 00:45:38.820
a Sky Wing, not Ruby, but Pearl didn't

00:45:38.820 --> 00:45:39.420
recognize the voice.

00:45:39.480 --> 00:45:42.539
First, you tell us you're harboring a

00:45:42.539 --> 00:45:44.219
violent bloodthirsty criminal.

00:45:44.219 --> 00:45:47.579
And then, you show us a dragonhead who

00:45:47.579 --> 00:45:50.460
has died in exactly the way that creature

00:45:50.460 --> 00:45:51.179
kills.

00:45:51.239 --> 00:45:56.099
Oh, that's me, Peril realized.

00:45:56.159 --> 00:45:59.519
I'm the violent, bloodthirsty criminal.

00:45:59.579 --> 00:46:00.900
Unfair.

00:46:00.960 --> 00:46:02.940
I don't thirst for blood.

00:46:03.000 --> 00:46:05.699
If I need to fry someone to cinders, I

00:46:05.699 --> 00:46:07.860
will, but I'm not rampaging around

00:46:07.860 --> 00:46:09.360
killing dragons for fun.

00:46:09.420 --> 00:46:11.639
I haven't even killed anyone in months.

00:46:11.699 --> 00:46:13.860
Bloodthirsty indeed.

00:46:13.920 --> 00:46:15.900
It was a fire.

00:46:15.960 --> 00:46:17.940
Tsunami's voice interjected.

00:46:18.000 --> 00:46:20.460
I don't like peril any more than you do

00:46:20.460 --> 00:46:22.320
but I promise she didn't do this to

00:46:22.320 --> 00:46:22.860
Carnelian.

00:46:22.920 --> 00:46:25.320
Very supportive.

00:46:25.380 --> 00:46:26.460
Thanks, tsunami.

00:46:26.579 --> 00:46:29.219
The unfamiliar Sky Wing hissed with

00:46:29.219 --> 00:46:29.820
disbelief.

00:46:29.880 --> 00:46:32.940
What sounds more likely to you?

00:46:32.940 --> 00:46:34.440
he snarled.

00:46:34.500 --> 00:46:38.099
That Scarlet's pet monster has murdered a

00:46:38.099 --> 00:46:41.099
dragon loyal to Queen Ruby, or that some

00:46:41.099 --> 00:46:43.440
mud wing figured out how to set off a

00:46:43.440 --> 00:46:46.380
dragon flame bomb and accidentally killed

00:46:46.380 --> 00:46:49.440
our soldier instead of her supposed ice

00:46:49.440 --> 00:46:50.340
wing target.

00:46:50.400 --> 00:46:53.760
I want to know where the mudwing is.

00:46:53.820 --> 00:46:56.820
Queen Ruby's voice was unreadable without

00:46:56.820 --> 00:46:58.019
her facial expression.

00:46:58.139 --> 00:47:02.519
Was that cold fury or grief or calm

00:47:02.519 --> 00:47:03.300
decisive leadership?

00:47:03.360 --> 00:47:04.920
Peril had no idea.

00:47:04.980 --> 00:47:08.099
This queen was so different from the

00:47:08.099 --> 00:47:10.260
submissive daughter she'd played all of

00:47:10.260 --> 00:47:11.099
peril's life.

00:47:11.159 --> 00:47:13.139
Carol couldn't figure her out at all.

00:47:13.199 --> 00:47:16.380
You don't seriously believe them.

00:47:16.440 --> 00:47:19.739
The other Skywing cried, his voice rising

00:47:19.739 --> 00:47:20.219
again.

00:47:20.280 --> 00:47:22.079
Look at cardnelian.

00:47:22.139 --> 00:47:24.900
Look at these burns, here, and here.

00:47:24.960 --> 00:47:27.780
These marks even look like talon prints.

00:47:27.900 --> 00:47:32.159
Peril coiled into herself, remembering

00:47:32.159 --> 00:47:33.960
the weight of the dragonette she'd

00:47:33.960 --> 00:47:36.840
dragged out of the burning cave, too late

00:47:36.840 --> 00:47:38.280
too late to save her.

00:47:38.340 --> 00:47:42.300
But if she had, if it had worked, if

00:47:42.300 --> 00:47:45.300
Carnelian were alive now, would Ruby have

00:47:45.300 --> 00:47:45.780
forgiven her?

00:47:45.840 --> 00:47:48.119
Would Clay have been proud of her?

00:47:48.179 --> 00:47:51.539
Would he have called her his wings of

00:47:51.539 --> 00:47:51.960
fire?

00:47:52.019 --> 00:47:52.559
Again?

00:47:52.619 --> 00:47:55.199
And would it have changed anything?

00:47:55.260 --> 00:47:59.340
Don't touch the body, the queen said

00:47:59.340 --> 00:47:59.880
sharply.

00:47:59.940 --> 00:48:02.880
Carol pulled Carnelian out of the fire.

00:48:02.940 --> 00:48:06.239
Sonny said, her voice more subdued than

00:48:06.239 --> 00:48:06.539
usual.

00:48:06.599 --> 00:48:09.599
So you will find Pearl's prints on her.

00:48:09.659 --> 00:48:12.480
But it's because she was trying to save

00:48:12.480 --> 00:48:12.780
her.

00:48:12.840 --> 00:48:15.840
Multiple hostiles snorts.

00:48:15.900 --> 00:48:18.659
The arguing Skywing clearly wasn't the

00:48:18.659 --> 00:48:20.400
only one suspicious of the true story.

00:48:20.460 --> 00:48:23.400
Tell me what you're doing to find and

00:48:23.400 --> 00:48:25.559
punish the mudwing who did this, said

00:48:25.559 --> 00:48:26.280
Queen Ruby.

00:48:26.340 --> 00:48:27.659
What is her name?

00:48:27.719 --> 00:48:29.340
Sora.

00:48:29.460 --> 00:48:30.840
That was clay.

00:48:30.900 --> 00:48:33.659
It felt like wings spreading inside her

00:48:33.659 --> 00:48:34.619
heart.

00:48:34.679 --> 00:48:37.139
Clay was speaking in his wonderful, warm

00:48:37.139 --> 00:48:37.679
voice.

00:48:37.739 --> 00:48:41.099
She, she's my sister.

00:48:41.159 --> 00:48:45.119
He sounded so, so sad.

00:48:45.179 --> 00:48:48.480
Peril wanted to burst into the cave and

00:48:48.480 --> 00:48:49.980
wrap her wings around him.

00:48:50.039 --> 00:48:52.320
No, that would only hurt him more.

00:48:52.440 --> 00:48:55.380
What she should do instead was wrap her

00:48:55.380 --> 00:48:57.300
wings around the sky wings who were being

00:48:57.300 --> 00:48:57.960
mean to him.

00:48:58.019 --> 00:49:00.480
Then she could watch them burn between

00:49:00.480 --> 00:49:01.500
her claws.

00:49:01.559 --> 00:49:04.800
Now, that was the kind of thought she

00:49:04.800 --> 00:49:06.480
probably shouldn't share with clay.

00:49:06.539 --> 00:49:08.460
Your sister.

00:49:08.519 --> 00:49:10.920
Said one of the other Sky Wings.

00:49:10.980 --> 00:49:13.679
This escape is looking more and more

00:49:13.679 --> 00:49:15.480
convenient, isn't it?

00:49:15.539 --> 00:49:18.599
Queen Morehen has agreed to meet with you

00:49:18.599 --> 00:49:21.179
Sonny said, a little desperately.

00:49:21.239 --> 00:49:24.119
Here or at her palace, whichever you

00:49:24.119 --> 00:49:26.280
prefer, we can send a messenger to her

00:49:26.280 --> 00:49:26.760
right now.

00:49:26.820 --> 00:49:29.280
She wants to help you find justice.

00:49:29.340 --> 00:49:30.539
We all do.

00:49:30.599 --> 00:49:34.260
Peril always thought of Clay's soul as a

00:49:34.260 --> 00:49:37.019
torch that never went out, burning clear

00:49:37.019 --> 00:49:38.639
and true all night long.

00:49:38.699 --> 00:49:42.480
Sunny, on the other talon, was a blaze of

00:49:42.480 --> 00:49:43.559
warm sunlight.

00:49:43.619 --> 00:49:45.960
The annoying kind, they gave a dragon

00:49:45.960 --> 00:49:48.059
headaches, and made you want to scorch

00:49:48.059 --> 00:49:50.940
things because stop smiling already, the

00:49:50.940 --> 00:49:52.380
world is horrible, go away.

00:49:52.500 --> 00:49:55.079
Peril knew this was bad.

00:49:55.139 --> 00:49:57.900
Sonny was the only one of Clay's friends

00:49:57.900 --> 00:50:00.480
who tried to be nice to Peril, and yet

00:50:00.480 --> 00:50:02.519
Peril still wanted to push her off a

00:50:02.519 --> 00:50:03.599
cliff on a daily basis.

00:50:03.659 --> 00:50:07.139
Sometimes she dreamed that she'd left

00:50:07.139 --> 00:50:09.539
Sonny in Scarlet's cage and run off with

00:50:09.539 --> 00:50:12.360
clay, and at the end, he'd turn to her

00:50:12.360 --> 00:50:14.159
and say, you were right.

00:50:14.219 --> 00:50:16.139
We don't need anyone else.

00:50:16.199 --> 00:50:19.500
Forget all the smiling sand wings and

00:50:19.500 --> 00:50:22.320
brave sea wings and beautiful rain wings

00:50:22.320 --> 00:50:22.920
we've ever known.

00:50:22.980 --> 00:50:26.579
But then, she supposed, he wouldn't be

00:50:26.579 --> 00:50:27.000
clay.

00:50:27.059 --> 00:50:28.920
Her clay.

00:50:28.980 --> 00:50:32.219
Who loved his friends so much, he kept

00:50:32.219 --> 00:50:33.659
trying to die for them.

00:50:33.719 --> 00:50:36.300
That was a plan, by the way, that was

00:50:36.300 --> 00:50:38.579
never going to happen on peril's watch.

00:50:38.639 --> 00:50:40.679
Your Majesty.

00:50:40.739 --> 00:50:42.659
A new voice cut in suddenly.

00:50:42.719 --> 00:50:45.059
Someone is approaching from the north.

00:50:45.179 --> 00:50:46.800
Queen Warren?

00:50:46.860 --> 00:50:47.760
Someone else asked.

00:50:47.820 --> 00:50:50.099
No, said the watcher.

00:50:50.219 --> 00:50:52.619
I see orange scales.

00:50:52.679 --> 00:50:55.320
She trailed off, and in the silence that

00:50:55.320 --> 00:50:57.960
followed, peril felt an overwhelming wave

00:50:57.960 --> 00:51:01.320
of horror, surge slowly, inexorably

00:51:01.320 --> 00:51:03.480
toward them, and then crash over everyone

00:51:03.480 --> 00:51:04.380
listening.

00:51:04.440 --> 00:51:06.300
It's Queen Scarlet.

00:51:06.360 --> 00:51:07.619
Ruby whispered.

00:51:07.679 --> 00:51:08.940
You are right.

00:51:09.000 --> 00:51:10.739
She's still alive.

00:51:10.800 --> 00:51:14.219
And coming to kill you, I bet.

00:51:14.280 --> 00:51:15.719
Peril thought.

00:51:15.780 --> 00:51:18.539
Since I wouldn't do it for her.

00:51:18.599 --> 00:51:22.860
It was the night after peril had freed

00:51:22.860 --> 00:51:25.139
Scarlet from Burns Weirdling Tower.

00:51:25.199 --> 00:51:27.840
The 2 of them were huddled around a fire

00:51:27.840 --> 00:51:30.239
in the unfriendly wasteland between the

00:51:30.239 --> 00:51:32.159
ice kingdom and the kingdom of sand.

00:51:32.280 --> 00:51:35.340
Scarlet was picking bits of reindeer out

00:51:35.340 --> 00:51:35.760
of her teeth.

00:51:35.820 --> 00:51:38.099
And Peril was trying not to stare at her

00:51:38.099 --> 00:51:39.780
queen's newly disfigured face.

00:51:39.840 --> 00:51:42.780
We'll go home tomorrow.

00:51:42.840 --> 00:51:44.039
Scarlett growled.

00:51:44.099 --> 00:51:46.380
I'll figure out how to kill those

00:51:46.380 --> 00:51:48.960
prophecy brats from there, with or

00:51:48.960 --> 00:51:49.380
without you.

00:51:49.500 --> 00:51:51.420
You should know.

00:51:51.539 --> 00:51:53.280
Carol hesitated.

00:51:53.340 --> 00:51:54.659
What?

00:51:54.780 --> 00:51:57.719
Scarlet threw a hoof at her, whacking

00:51:57.719 --> 00:51:59.219
peril hard just above her eyes.

00:51:59.280 --> 00:52:00.900
Don't mumble.

00:52:00.960 --> 00:52:02.579
I'm furious at you already.

00:52:02.639 --> 00:52:04.920
I cannot handle you being annoying as

00:52:04.920 --> 00:52:06.420
well as disobedient right now.

00:52:06.480 --> 00:52:10.260
Peril rubbed her forehead, and tried to

00:52:10.260 --> 00:52:12.420
remember why she thought rescuing Scarlet

00:52:12.420 --> 00:52:13.079
was a good idea.

00:52:13.139 --> 00:52:16.320
Or maybe she'd always known it was a bad

00:52:16.320 --> 00:52:16.739
idea.

00:52:16.800 --> 00:52:19.260
But she'd still felt as though it was her

00:52:19.260 --> 00:52:19.920
responsibility.

00:52:19.980 --> 00:52:23.280
Or maybe she'd just needed Scarlet to

00:52:23.280 --> 00:52:25.739
stop slithering through her dreams, making

00:52:25.739 --> 00:52:28.380
every night even worse than the days of

00:52:28.380 --> 00:52:30.659
crocodile throwing, and dragons screaming

00:52:30.659 --> 00:52:30.960
at her.

00:52:31.019 --> 00:52:35.159
It's just that Ruby is queen now, Pearl

00:52:35.159 --> 00:52:35.460
said.

00:52:35.519 --> 00:52:39.059
And the Sky Wings really love her.

00:52:39.119 --> 00:52:41.940
She added, a little vindictively.

00:52:42.000 --> 00:52:44.639
Scarlet flapped one dismissive wing.

00:52:44.760 --> 00:52:46.260
I know about that.

00:52:46.380 --> 00:52:49.380
But Ruby will roll right over and hand

00:52:49.380 --> 00:52:50.519
back my throne.

00:52:50.579 --> 00:52:53.280
She's a good daughter, unlike some

00:52:53.280 --> 00:52:55.079
dragons, I could mention.

00:52:55.199 --> 00:52:58.380
I don't think she will, Pearl said.

00:52:58.440 --> 00:53:00.480
She's made a lot of changes already.

00:53:00.539 --> 00:53:02.940
She doesn't do what Bern wants her to

00:53:02.940 --> 00:53:03.420
do.

00:53:03.480 --> 00:53:05.699
She's pulled back on all the fronts of

00:53:05.699 --> 00:53:07.619
the war, since destroying the Summer

00:53:07.619 --> 00:53:10.199
Palace, as if she is consolidating her

00:53:10.199 --> 00:53:12.480
power, and gathering her warriors to

00:53:12.480 --> 00:53:14.940
defend the palace, and herself.

00:53:15.000 --> 00:53:19.619
Plus, she, um, She banished me.

00:53:19.679 --> 00:53:21.960
She's a lot scarier than I thought she

00:53:21.960 --> 00:53:22.380
was.

00:53:22.440 --> 00:53:25.199
A lot scarier than you think she is.

00:53:25.260 --> 00:53:28.980
Scarlet glowered at peril, her yellow

00:53:28.980 --> 00:53:30.420
eyes full of flames.

00:53:30.480 --> 00:53:34.019
After a long moment, she said, That's

00:53:34.019 --> 00:53:34.980
what Byrne thought too.

00:53:35.039 --> 00:53:38.519
That if I tried to return, Ruby would

00:53:38.519 --> 00:53:38.940
defeat me.

00:53:39.000 --> 00:53:42.300
She threw back her head and laughed, a

00:53:42.300 --> 00:53:43.500
strange hollow cackle.

00:53:43.559 --> 00:53:46.199
Ruby, of all dragons.

00:53:46.260 --> 00:53:47.820
She's a mouse.

00:53:47.880 --> 00:53:51.000
She's not, Pearl said.

00:53:51.059 --> 00:53:54.119
Truthfully, peril wasn't sure what Ruby

00:53:54.119 --> 00:53:56.519
was, but a part of her knew.

00:53:56.579 --> 00:53:58.500
She was digging in her claws about it

00:53:58.500 --> 00:54:01.019
because she wanted to hurt Scarlet.

00:54:01.079 --> 00:54:03.239
She wanted to hurt her the way she'd been

00:54:03.239 --> 00:54:05.820
hurt, and she wanted to scare Scarlet

00:54:05.820 --> 00:54:07.199
away from the Sky Palace.

00:54:07.260 --> 00:54:11.280
True, if Scarlet returned to the Sky

00:54:11.280 --> 00:54:13.440
Palace, then peril could too.

00:54:13.500 --> 00:54:14.940
She'd have a home again.

00:54:15.000 --> 00:54:17.940
But it wouldn't be worth it, because then

00:54:17.940 --> 00:54:19.019
Clay would be in danger.

00:54:19.079 --> 00:54:22.199
The minute Scarlett had her army back

00:54:22.199 --> 00:54:25.199
she'd go after him, and peril wouldn't be

00:54:25.199 --> 00:54:25.860
able to stop her.

00:54:25.920 --> 00:54:29.400
Scarlet unconsciously reached one talent

00:54:29.400 --> 00:54:31.739
toward her scarred face but didn't touch

00:54:31.739 --> 00:54:31.860
it.

00:54:31.980 --> 00:54:35.579
You think Ruby would fight me?

00:54:35.579 --> 00:54:35.940
she asked.

00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:37.559
She couldn't win.

00:54:37.619 --> 00:54:39.539
Not against me.

00:54:39.599 --> 00:54:42.599
But peril could see it in her eyes.

00:54:42.659 --> 00:54:45.059
Scarlet knew what it was like to be

00:54:45.059 --> 00:54:45.599
afraid now.

00:54:45.659 --> 00:54:48.480
The venom attack had melted more than her

00:54:48.480 --> 00:54:48.900
scales.

00:54:48.960 --> 00:54:51.059
It had eaten away some of her

00:54:51.059 --> 00:54:51.480
confidence.

00:54:51.539 --> 00:54:54.960
The time she spent trapped in burns tower

00:54:54.960 --> 00:54:56.699
of horrors probably hadn't helped

00:54:56.699 --> 00:54:57.000
either.

00:54:57.059 --> 00:54:58.980
Pearl shrugged.

00:54:59.039 --> 00:55:00.719
I guess you'll find out.

00:55:00.780 --> 00:55:02.699
There was a pause.

00:55:02.760 --> 00:55:05.639
No, Scarlett said.

00:55:05.699 --> 00:55:07.679
I have a better idea.

00:55:07.739 --> 00:55:10.320
She bared her teeth at peril.

00:55:10.380 --> 00:55:13.559
You return to the Sky Palace and kill her

00:55:13.559 --> 00:55:14.340
before I get there.

00:55:14.400 --> 00:55:18.000
I can't do that, peril cried.

00:55:18.059 --> 00:55:20.340
I'm not even allowed in the Sky Palace.

00:55:20.400 --> 00:55:22.920
Ruby said she'd have me executed if I

00:55:22.920 --> 00:55:23.280
went back.

00:55:23.340 --> 00:55:27.239
She can't have you executed if you kill

00:55:27.239 --> 00:55:27.840
her first.

00:55:27.960 --> 00:55:29.519
Scarlet said.

00:55:29.579 --> 00:55:32.219
Well, I'm not going to kill her.

00:55:32.280 --> 00:55:35.460
Pearl said, you can't make me.

00:55:35.519 --> 00:55:38.159
You can't make me kill anyone else for

00:55:38.159 --> 00:55:38.340
you.

00:55:38.400 --> 00:55:41.099
I'm not that kind of dragon anymore.

00:55:41.159 --> 00:55:43.619
Scarlet's eyes narrowed.

00:55:43.679 --> 00:55:45.300
Oh, really?

00:55:45.420 --> 00:55:47.820
You think you've changed so much.

00:55:47.880 --> 00:55:49.440
I know you.

00:55:49.500 --> 00:55:52.679
You like killing dragons.

00:55:52.739 --> 00:55:54.179
You've always liked it.

00:55:54.239 --> 00:55:56.340
It's one of the things I can stand about

00:55:56.340 --> 00:55:56.579
you.

00:55:56.639 --> 00:55:59.400
None of the simpering, moaning guilt

00:55:59.400 --> 00:56:00.719
another dragon might have.

00:56:00.780 --> 00:56:04.739
You were born to burn your enemies, and

00:56:04.739 --> 00:56:05.159
mine.

00:56:05.219 --> 00:56:06.960
Mostly mine.

00:56:07.019 --> 00:56:10.559
I don't have to be, Peril said

00:56:10.559 --> 00:56:11.219
stubbornly.

00:56:11.280 --> 00:56:13.980
Clay says I can be whoever I want to be.

00:56:14.039 --> 00:56:17.219
She knew right away that mentioning him

00:56:17.219 --> 00:56:17.940
was a mistake.

00:56:18.000 --> 00:56:22.860
Oh, that mud wing.

00:56:22.920 --> 00:56:24.420
Scarlett snarled.

00:56:24.480 --> 00:56:27.239
He wouldn't like it if I killed Queen

00:56:27.239 --> 00:56:28.679
Ruby, Pearl said.

00:56:28.739 --> 00:56:30.960
He wouldn't like me at all if I did

00:56:30.960 --> 00:56:31.199
that.

00:56:31.260 --> 00:56:36.659
But I won't like you if you don't, Scarlet

00:56:36.659 --> 00:56:37.019
pointed out.

00:56:37.139 --> 00:56:40.500
Peril couldn't believe the stab of dismay

00:56:40.500 --> 00:56:41.340
that made her feel.

00:56:41.400 --> 00:56:43.500
Why did she still care?

00:56:43.559 --> 00:56:46.260
After everything Scarlett had done to

00:56:46.260 --> 00:56:46.440
her.

00:56:46.500 --> 00:56:49.380
Why did she feel suddenly horribly

00:56:49.380 --> 00:56:51.360
desperate to be Scarlet's favorite pet

00:56:51.360 --> 00:56:51.780
again?

00:56:51.840 --> 00:56:54.000
I don't care.

00:56:54.059 --> 00:56:55.380
Stop caring.

00:56:55.440 --> 00:57:00.659
Just one more dragon, Scarlet purred.

00:57:00.780 --> 00:57:02.940
Kill Ruby for me.

00:57:03.000 --> 00:57:06.300
And then you can go follow your

00:57:06.300 --> 00:57:08.400
aggravating mud dragon.

00:57:08.460 --> 00:57:10.739
It's the least you could do after you

00:57:10.739 --> 00:57:12.719
wouldn't let me kill that sandwing

00:57:12.719 --> 00:57:13.440
spitball.

00:57:13.500 --> 00:57:16.559
Peril poked her claw into a scorched

00:57:16.559 --> 00:57:18.179
circle of grass under her talons.

00:57:18.239 --> 00:57:22.199
This could be a way to please Scarlet, and

00:57:22.199 --> 00:57:23.639
perhaps save clay as well.

00:57:23.699 --> 00:57:27.059
Could she bargain Ruby's life for clays?

00:57:27.119 --> 00:57:29.639
Would Scarlet promise to let him live?

00:57:29.699 --> 00:57:33.659
But, for one thing, she couldn't trust

00:57:33.659 --> 00:57:36.960
Scarlet to keep her word, and for another

00:57:36.960 --> 00:57:40.320
Clay still wouldn't like it, even if she

00:57:40.320 --> 00:57:43.139
only did it to protect him, she knew he'd

00:57:43.139 --> 00:57:44.039
be disappointed in her.

00:57:44.099 --> 00:57:47.219
The last time they'd seen each other, he'd

00:57:47.219 --> 00:57:47.820
been hopeful.

00:57:47.880 --> 00:57:50.460
He could see another possible future for

00:57:50.460 --> 00:57:50.699
her.

00:57:50.760 --> 00:57:53.639
She wanted to be that dragon for him.

00:57:53.699 --> 00:57:56.639
No, she said.

00:57:56.699 --> 00:57:58.739
That's my final answer.

00:57:58.800 --> 00:58:02.099
Then you're useless to me.

00:58:02.159 --> 00:58:04.380
Scarlett hissed furiously.

00:58:04.440 --> 00:58:06.179
The next morning.

00:58:06.239 --> 00:58:07.619
Scarlet was gone.

00:58:07.679 --> 00:58:11.219
Carol had not been able to find her, and

00:58:11.219 --> 00:58:13.559
no one else had seen her for months, even

00:58:13.559 --> 00:58:14.519
in their dreams.

00:58:14.579 --> 00:58:17.880
Until she tried to get an ice wing

00:58:17.880 --> 00:58:20.340
student to kill the dragonettes for her.

00:58:20.400 --> 00:58:24.780
Still trying to make other dragons do her

00:58:24.780 --> 00:58:25.139
killing.

00:58:25.199 --> 00:58:27.659
So something had kept her scared.

00:58:27.719 --> 00:58:31.199
Maybe peril's words, or maybe hearing

00:58:31.199 --> 00:58:32.820
what had happened to burn and blister.

00:58:32.940 --> 00:58:36.179
But if she was coming this way now, then

00:58:36.179 --> 00:58:37.559
she wasn't scared anymore.

00:58:37.619 --> 00:58:40.800
Or perhaps her rage had finally surpassed

00:58:40.800 --> 00:58:41.460
her fear.

00:58:41.519 --> 00:58:43.079
Who was she looking for?

00:58:43.139 --> 00:58:45.300
Did she know peril was here?

00:58:45.360 --> 00:58:48.480
I'll go face her, Ruby said.

00:58:48.539 --> 00:58:49.980
Her voice clear and strong.

00:58:50.099 --> 00:58:53.400
No, cried one of the sky wings.

00:58:53.460 --> 00:58:55.199
We'll fight her off, all of us.

00:58:55.320 --> 00:58:57.659
That's right, said another.

00:58:57.719 --> 00:58:59.159
She's not a challenger.

00:58:59.219 --> 00:59:00.780
You don't have to face her alone.

00:59:00.840 --> 00:59:04.079
She is an enemy, said a third.

00:59:04.139 --> 00:59:06.119
And you're a much better queen than she

00:59:06.119 --> 00:59:06.480
was.

00:59:06.539 --> 00:59:08.400
We want you, not her.

00:59:08.460 --> 00:59:11.280
I agree, said Clay.

00:59:11.340 --> 00:59:14.699
The throne is yours now, and she can't

00:59:14.699 --> 00:59:15.179
have it back.

00:59:15.239 --> 00:59:17.219
We'll all fight beside you.

00:59:17.340 --> 00:59:19.739
A long pause.

00:59:19.800 --> 00:59:22.440
Peril stabbed at a crack in the rock wall

00:59:22.440 --> 00:59:24.000
beside her, scowling.

00:59:24.059 --> 00:59:26.460
She didn't like the sound of clay acting

00:59:26.460 --> 00:59:28.199
all loyal and supportive to someone who

00:59:28.199 --> 00:59:28.739
wasn't her.

00:59:28.800 --> 00:59:31.679
That was her special clay voice.

00:59:31.739 --> 00:59:35.099
That's the one he used when he told peril

00:59:35.099 --> 00:59:36.659
she would always have a place at Jade

00:59:36.659 --> 00:59:39.480
Mountain and said things like, I want you

00:59:39.480 --> 00:59:39.780
to stay.

00:59:39.840 --> 00:59:43.260
He wasn't supposed to use it willy-nilly

00:59:43.260 --> 00:59:44.579
on dragons who hated her.

00:59:44.699 --> 00:59:46.920
Ruby cleared her throat.

00:59:46.980 --> 00:59:49.260
Thank you, she said.

00:59:49.320 --> 00:59:52.500
If that's how you all feel, then we'll

00:59:52.500 --> 00:59:53.280
fly out there together.

00:59:53.400 --> 00:59:56.519
Harold heard claws scraping on the

00:59:56.519 --> 00:59:56.820
rocks.

00:59:56.880 --> 00:59:59.280
She pictured the queen spinning toward

00:59:59.280 --> 00:59:59.699
the sky.

00:59:59.760 --> 01:00:02.820
A moment later, the cave echoed with the

01:00:02.820 --> 01:00:04.500
sound of flapping wings as they all took

01:00:04.500 --> 01:00:04.739
off.

01:00:04.800 --> 01:00:08.639
Two sky wing queens who both dislike me

01:00:08.639 --> 01:00:09.539
quite a lot.

01:00:09.659 --> 01:00:11.280
I should hide.

01:00:11.340 --> 01:00:12.480
I should run.

01:00:12.539 --> 01:00:14.699
I should run and hide.

01:00:14.760 --> 01:00:18.300
But if Scarlet was out there, And Clay

01:00:18.300 --> 01:00:19.199
was flying toward her?

01:00:19.320 --> 01:00:21.780
Pearl couldn't let him face her alone.

01:00:21.840 --> 01:00:25.380
Scarlet was still her responsibility.

01:00:25.440 --> 01:00:28.619
She darted into the cave, barreling past

01:00:28.619 --> 01:00:29.159
Turtle.

01:00:29.280 --> 01:00:31.260
Where are you going?

01:00:31.320 --> 01:00:32.579
He called.

01:00:32.760 --> 01:00:34.199
What happened to stealth?

01:00:34.320 --> 01:00:37.860
I have to protect Clay, she called back

01:00:37.860 --> 01:00:39.000
spreading her wings.

01:00:39.059 --> 01:00:41.280
She couldn't hear his answer over her

01:00:41.280 --> 01:00:43.559
wing beats as she shot through one of the

01:00:43.559 --> 01:00:44.280
skylights.

01:00:44.340 --> 01:00:46.619
It was Scarlet.

01:00:46.679 --> 01:00:49.860
Pearl recognized the curve of her wings

01:00:49.860 --> 01:00:52.380
instantly, and she could see the dark

01:00:52.380 --> 01:00:54.900
scar on the side of her face, even from a

01:00:54.900 --> 01:00:55.739
distance.

01:00:55.800 --> 01:00:58.500
The former sky wing queen was beating her

01:00:58.500 --> 01:00:59.340
way toward them.

01:00:59.400 --> 01:01:02.099
Her whole body radiating fury and

01:01:02.099 --> 01:01:05.340
vengeance, Ruby and her soldiers were

01:01:05.340 --> 01:01:07.380
forming into a defensive wing to confront

01:01:07.380 --> 01:01:07.500
her.

01:01:07.559 --> 01:01:11.099
Peril spiraled up into the clouds, and

01:01:11.099 --> 01:01:12.360
hovered above the mountain peak

01:01:12.360 --> 01:01:13.320
indecisively.

01:01:13.380 --> 01:01:16.079
Should she fly down to join the soldiers

01:01:16.079 --> 01:01:17.699
around Queen Ruby and Clay?

01:01:17.760 --> 01:01:20.099
What if her appearance sent them into a

01:01:20.099 --> 01:01:22.619
panic, or distracted them from fighting

01:01:22.619 --> 01:01:22.980
Scarlet?

01:01:23.039 --> 01:01:25.739
As long as Clay was not in immediate

01:01:25.739 --> 01:01:26.460
danger.

01:01:26.519 --> 01:01:28.079
Maybe she should wait to see what

01:01:28.079 --> 01:01:29.400
happened before joining in.

01:01:29.460 --> 01:01:31.980
Why was Scarlet even here?

01:01:32.039 --> 01:01:34.559
She couldn't be planning to attack Jade

01:01:34.559 --> 01:01:36.179
Mountain all by herself, could she?

01:01:36.239 --> 01:01:39.000
Perhaps this had something to do with the

01:01:39.000 --> 01:01:40.679
students who'd gone looking for her.

01:01:40.739 --> 01:01:44.400
A group of 4 dragonettes had gone in

01:01:44.400 --> 01:01:46.800
search of Scarlet about a week ago, right

01:01:46.800 --> 01:01:48.059
after Cornelian died.

01:01:48.119 --> 01:01:51.179
Peril knew from Clay that they'd been in

01:01:51.179 --> 01:01:53.639
the rainforest with glory for a day, and

01:01:53.639 --> 01:01:55.199
then they'd flown away to find an ice

01:01:55.199 --> 01:01:57.119
wing that Scarlet supposedly had

01:01:57.119 --> 01:01:57.960
imprisoned somewhere.

01:01:58.079 --> 01:02:00.780
But no one knew if they'd found Scarlet

01:02:00.780 --> 01:02:02.880
and Perel sort of expected that if they

01:02:02.880 --> 01:02:04.559
had, they'd all be dead.

01:02:04.679 --> 01:02:06.719
Was that why Scarlet was here?

01:02:06.780 --> 01:02:09.179
Had the dragonettes done something to

01:02:09.179 --> 01:02:12.059
push her over the edge, from caution, to

01:02:12.059 --> 01:02:12.659
rage?

01:02:12.780 --> 01:02:15.599
She felt a sudden compression of alarm in

01:02:15.599 --> 01:02:16.380
her chest.

01:02:16.440 --> 01:02:19.679
Scarlet was carrying something in her

01:02:19.679 --> 01:02:20.340
claws.

01:02:20.400 --> 01:02:23.159
It was too small to be a body, surely.

01:02:23.219 --> 01:02:26.340
Scarlet wheeled about in the air suddenly

01:02:26.340 --> 01:02:28.739
out of flaming distance of the wall of

01:02:28.739 --> 01:02:30.360
Sky Wing soldiers facing her.

01:02:30.420 --> 01:02:34.800
Traitors, she shrieked, all of you

01:02:34.800 --> 01:02:36.659
disloyal cowards.

01:02:36.719 --> 01:02:39.539
She lifted whatever she was holding and

01:02:39.539 --> 01:02:40.139
shook it at them.

01:02:40.199 --> 01:02:43.800
I destroy anyone who opposes me.

01:02:43.860 --> 01:02:46.619
I will have my vengeance.

01:02:46.739 --> 01:02:48.900
And I will get my throne back.

01:02:48.960 --> 01:02:52.440
This is just one of the dragons I'll

01:02:52.440 --> 01:02:52.619
kill.

01:02:52.739 --> 01:02:55.500
And you'll all be next.

01:02:55.559 --> 01:02:58.920
She flung the object at them as hard as

01:02:58.920 --> 01:03:01.380
she could, then abruptly whirled around

01:03:01.380 --> 01:03:04.440
and flew away, her enormous wings eating

01:03:04.440 --> 01:03:06.480
up the distance with powerful strokes.

01:03:06.539 --> 01:03:09.840
One of the sky wings lunged forward to

01:03:09.840 --> 01:03:10.500
catch the missile.

01:03:10.559 --> 01:03:13.139
Peril couldn't hold back her curiosity.

01:03:13.199 --> 01:03:16.440
She swooped closer as the Sky Wing looked

01:03:16.440 --> 01:03:18.659
down at the thing in his talons, then

01:03:18.659 --> 01:03:21.719
turned, shuddering, to show it to Ruby

01:03:21.719 --> 01:03:22.139
and the others.

01:03:22.199 --> 01:03:25.860
Sonny began to scream, as though her

01:03:25.860 --> 01:03:27.539
heart was being ripped out of her chest.

01:03:27.599 --> 01:03:30.420
Clay reached to catch her before she fell

01:03:30.420 --> 01:03:31.079
out of the sky.

01:03:31.139 --> 01:03:34.380
The sky wing was holding the severed head

01:03:34.380 --> 01:03:37.440
of Queen Glory of the rain wings.

01:03:37.500 --> 01:03:41.519
Chapter 3.

01:03:41.820 --> 01:03:45.780
Tsunami's roar should have flattened the

01:03:45.780 --> 01:03:47.519
mountains and ripped holes in the sky.

01:03:47.579 --> 01:03:51.059
She shot after Queen Scarlet, a blue blur

01:03:51.059 --> 01:03:52.139
against the clouds.

01:03:52.440 --> 01:03:53.519
Go with her.

01:03:53.579 --> 01:03:56.219
Queen Ruby shouted at her soldiers.

01:03:56.280 --> 01:03:58.500
She grabbed the head from the dazed sky

01:03:58.500 --> 01:04:00.059
wing who held it.

01:04:00.119 --> 01:04:01.320
All of you, go now.

01:04:01.380 --> 01:04:04.559
They obeyed in one glittering mass of red

01:04:04.559 --> 01:04:07.440
and orange, except for one who turned the

01:04:07.440 --> 01:04:08.639
last minute to face Ruby.

01:04:08.699 --> 01:04:10.619
If we catch her.

01:04:10.679 --> 01:04:12.119
He said hesitantly.

01:04:12.179 --> 01:04:13.619
Do you want to?

01:04:13.619 --> 01:04:15.539
Do you want us to?

01:04:15.840 --> 01:04:16.679
Yes.

01:04:16.739 --> 01:04:19.260
Kill her, Ruby said.

01:04:19.320 --> 01:04:20.820
I don't mind who does it.

01:04:20.940 --> 01:04:24.000
He nodded, and wheeled around to follow

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:24.360
the others.

01:04:24.420 --> 01:04:26.760
Should I go with them?

01:04:26.820 --> 01:04:27.960
Peril wondered.

01:04:28.079 --> 01:04:30.599
Surely there were enough dragons chasing

01:04:30.599 --> 01:04:31.440
Scarlet without her.

01:04:31.500 --> 01:04:34.739
What she really wanted to do was take

01:04:34.739 --> 01:04:35.340
care of clay.

01:04:35.400 --> 01:04:38.519
Knowing how he was about his friends?

01:04:38.579 --> 01:04:41.579
peril guest, with a stab of jealousy that

01:04:41.579 --> 01:04:44.159
she was immediately ashamed of, that he

01:04:44.159 --> 01:04:45.059
must be devastated.

01:04:45.119 --> 01:04:48.960
Would he be devastated if that was my

01:04:48.960 --> 01:04:49.980
head?

01:04:50.039 --> 01:04:52.380
Stop thinking about yourself, peril?

01:04:52.440 --> 01:04:53.940
Worry about clay.

01:04:54.059 --> 01:04:57.480
He was half carrying Sonny down to a flat

01:04:57.480 --> 01:04:59.820
shelf of gray rock that angled out of the

01:04:59.820 --> 01:05:00.480
mountain below them.

01:05:00.539 --> 01:05:03.119
Ruby glanced at the head in her talons

01:05:03.119 --> 01:05:03.780
and then followed.

01:05:03.840 --> 01:05:06.960
So, this would be awkward.

01:05:07.019 --> 01:05:09.360
But it was clearly an emergency.

01:05:09.420 --> 01:05:12.119
Ruby would just have to deal with peril's

01:05:12.119 --> 01:05:14.400
presence, and if she didn't like it, it

01:05:14.400 --> 01:05:16.139
was her own fault for standing so close

01:05:16.139 --> 01:05:18.179
to clay when he was clearly suffering and

01:05:18.179 --> 01:05:18.840
needed peril.

01:05:18.960 --> 01:05:22.260
Peril dropped out of the sky, landing

01:05:22.260 --> 01:05:24.539
with a thump in front of clay and sunny.

01:05:24.599 --> 01:05:26.699
Sonny was sobbing too hard to notice her

01:05:26.699 --> 01:05:29.519
and at first, Clay didn't seem to see her

01:05:29.519 --> 01:05:29.820
either.

01:05:29.940 --> 01:05:33.179
His brown eyes stared blankly down at the

01:05:33.179 --> 01:05:35.400
little sand wing, as if his brain had

01:05:35.400 --> 01:05:36.420
been incinerated.

01:05:36.480 --> 01:05:39.300
So it was only Ruby who reacted

01:05:39.300 --> 01:05:42.059
immediately, recoiling with a hiss of

01:05:42.059 --> 01:05:43.559
fury at the side of peril.

01:05:43.739 --> 01:05:45.420
What are you doing here?

01:05:45.480 --> 01:05:46.980
Ruby demanded.

01:05:47.039 --> 01:05:48.539
In my mountains.

01:05:48.659 --> 01:05:52.619
These are my friends, Pearl said, lifting

01:05:52.619 --> 01:05:52.980
her chin.

01:05:53.039 --> 01:05:55.260
You can't make me stay away from my

01:05:55.260 --> 01:05:55.440
friends.

01:05:55.500 --> 01:05:59.940
Monsters don't have friends, hissed

01:05:59.940 --> 01:06:00.360
Ruby.

01:06:00.420 --> 01:06:04.019
Peril gave Clay a sideways glance, waiting

01:06:04.019 --> 01:06:06.179
for him to say something like, she's not

01:06:06.179 --> 01:06:09.780
a monster, or, we are her friends, but he

01:06:09.780 --> 01:06:11.099
still wasn't even looking at her.

01:06:11.159 --> 01:06:14.039
How could she have killed glory?

01:06:14.159 --> 01:06:15.360
Sonny cried.

01:06:15.420 --> 01:06:19.139
Gloria is amazing, and indestructible, and

01:06:19.139 --> 01:06:21.239
has magical death spit, plus death

01:06:21.239 --> 01:06:23.760
bringer, and a whole army of rain wings

01:06:23.760 --> 01:06:24.539
who would die for her.

01:06:24.599 --> 01:06:28.380
Clay, please, please tell me that's not

01:06:28.380 --> 01:06:28.739
her.

01:06:28.800 --> 01:06:33.659
Maybe it's a trick, Clay said, turning

01:06:33.659 --> 01:06:35.639
numbly toward the head in Ruby's talons.

01:06:35.699 --> 01:06:38.460
It didn't look like a trick to peril.

01:06:38.519 --> 01:06:41.340
That was definitely the head of the rain

01:06:41.340 --> 01:06:42.000
wing queen.

01:06:42.059 --> 01:06:44.760
Peril remembered Glory clearly from her

01:06:44.760 --> 01:06:47.579
time in the Sky Palace before she venomed

01:06:47.579 --> 01:06:49.019
Queen Scarlet.

01:06:49.079 --> 01:06:50.880
She also remembered her on the sands of

01:06:50.880 --> 01:06:53.699
burns stronghold, holding clay down while

01:06:53.699 --> 01:06:55.800
peril burned out the snake bite poison in

01:06:55.800 --> 01:06:56.699
his leg.

01:06:56.760 --> 01:06:59.400
She was the one who ruined Scarlet's

01:06:59.400 --> 01:06:59.639
face.

01:06:59.699 --> 01:07:01.980
The one Scarlet hated the most.

01:07:02.099 --> 01:07:06.059
But you'll be next, she thought, glancing

01:07:06.059 --> 01:07:06.719
at Ruby.

01:07:06.780 --> 01:07:09.480
And then, maybe me.

01:07:09.539 --> 01:07:12.840
Or maybe the other dragons from the

01:07:12.840 --> 01:07:13.440
prophecy.

01:07:13.500 --> 01:07:16.260
Was Clay on Scarlet's list?

01:07:16.320 --> 01:07:17.639
If she dared.

01:07:17.699 --> 01:07:22.380
If she came anywhere near him, Peril felt

01:07:22.380 --> 01:07:25.320
molten lava rippling under her scales and

01:07:25.320 --> 01:07:27.480
curled in her tail with a soft growl.

01:07:27.539 --> 01:07:31.800
Clay's big mud wing wings trembled as he

01:07:31.800 --> 01:07:33.539
tried to reach out and touch the severed

01:07:33.539 --> 01:07:33.840
head.

01:07:33.900 --> 01:07:35.880
If only she could do it for him.

01:07:35.940 --> 01:07:38.579
Then she could examine it and tell him

01:07:38.579 --> 01:07:39.360
the horrible truth.

01:07:39.420 --> 01:07:41.760
But she couldn't touch it at all.

01:07:41.820 --> 01:07:44.519
Or it would turn to charred black cinders

01:07:44.519 --> 01:07:45.239
in her claws.

01:07:45.360 --> 01:07:48.840
It looks like Queen Glory to me, said

01:07:48.840 --> 01:07:49.380
Ruby.

01:07:49.440 --> 01:07:51.239
I'm sorry for you both.

01:07:51.300 --> 01:07:55.500
Sonny broke down. covering her face with

01:07:55.500 --> 01:07:57.840
her talons and curling into a ball with

01:07:57.840 --> 01:07:58.860
her wings over her head.

01:07:58.920 --> 01:08:01.739
Clay closed his eyes, and his head

01:08:01.739 --> 01:08:02.159
dropped.

01:08:02.219 --> 01:08:03.960
Can I see?

01:08:04.019 --> 01:08:07.260
Pearl and Ruby both looked up and found

01:08:07.260 --> 01:08:09.659
Turtle flapping down from the sky.

01:08:09.719 --> 01:08:11.639
He landed, and carefully took the head

01:08:11.639 --> 01:08:14.219
for Ruby, studying it from all sides.

01:08:14.340 --> 01:08:16.199
Who are you?

01:08:16.260 --> 01:08:17.279
Ruby asked.

01:08:17.340 --> 01:08:19.140
Did you know Queen Glory?

01:08:19.199 --> 01:08:22.199
No, I never met her, he said.

01:08:22.260 --> 01:08:25.319
I'm one of the sons of Queen Coral. and a

01:08:25.319 --> 01:08:28.439
student here, but I feel like, I don't

01:08:28.439 --> 01:08:29.279
know, just...

01:08:29.279 --> 01:08:31.500
There's something strange about this.

01:08:31.560 --> 01:08:35.220
It is weird, Carol agreed.

01:08:35.279 --> 01:08:37.739
Glory was probably the best guarded

01:08:37.739 --> 01:08:38.879
dragon in Pyria.

01:08:38.939 --> 01:08:40.499
How did Scarlet get to her?

01:08:40.560 --> 01:08:42.119
Why go for her first?

01:08:42.180 --> 01:08:44.819
Killing Ruby 1st would make much more

01:08:44.819 --> 01:08:45.119
sense.

01:08:45.180 --> 01:08:47.460
Then she could have taken the whole Sky

01:08:47.460 --> 01:08:49.079
Wing army to attack the rainforest.

01:08:49.140 --> 01:08:52.439
That's Queen Ruby to you.

01:08:52.500 --> 01:08:54.479
The red dragon snarled.

01:08:54.539 --> 01:08:57.899
And I'm not that easy to kill either, no

01:08:57.899 --> 01:09:00.239
matter who you are, or what your claws

01:09:00.239 --> 01:09:00.600
can do.

01:09:00.659 --> 01:09:03.420
Peril glared back at her.

01:09:03.479 --> 01:09:06.119
Turtle squinted and held the head up

01:09:06.119 --> 01:09:06.779
toward the light.

01:09:06.840 --> 01:09:09.300
Does she have something in her ear?

01:09:09.359 --> 01:09:12.839
He tilted it toward Ruby, enough so that

01:09:12.839 --> 01:09:14.699
peril could see a flash of yellowy white

01:09:14.699 --> 01:09:16.619
tucked inside the dragon's ear.

01:09:16.680 --> 01:09:18.779
A message?

01:09:18.840 --> 01:09:20.760
Ruby guessed, taking it back from him.

01:09:20.819 --> 01:09:22.679
More threats?

01:09:22.739 --> 01:09:25.800
With careful claws, Turtle reached into

01:09:25.800 --> 01:09:28.319
the ear canal and slid out a small, rolled

01:09:28.319 --> 01:09:29.220
up scrap of paper.

01:09:29.279 --> 01:09:32.819
As he lifted it out, Glory's head began

01:09:32.819 --> 01:09:34.139
to move.

01:09:34.199 --> 01:09:36.779
The scales started rippling, as though

01:09:36.779 --> 01:09:38.880
they were flipping over, from emerald

01:09:38.880 --> 01:09:39.720
green to brown.

01:09:39.779 --> 01:09:43.139
The snout widened, and the brow went flat

01:09:43.139 --> 01:09:45.839
and the venomous fangs slid into the gums

01:09:45.839 --> 01:09:46.319
and banished.

01:09:46.439 --> 01:09:49.799
Ruby shrieked and dropped the head on the

01:09:49.799 --> 01:09:52.259
ground, where it bounced and rolled to a

01:09:52.259 --> 01:09:53.879
stop near Peril's talons.

01:09:53.939 --> 01:09:56.519
She peered down into a face that was now

01:09:56.519 --> 01:09:59.099
most definitely a mud wing and not glory

01:09:59.099 --> 01:09:59.399
at all.

01:09:59.460 --> 01:10:02.939
What in the name of all the moons?

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:06.779
Clay grabbed Sonny and nearly lifted her

01:10:06.779 --> 01:10:08.699
off the ground as he turned her to look.

01:10:08.760 --> 01:10:10.199
What happened?

01:10:10.260 --> 01:10:11.220
he cried.

01:10:11.279 --> 01:10:13.020
What happened to glory?

01:10:13.079 --> 01:10:15.000
Who is that?

01:10:15.119 --> 01:10:16.560
Ruby demanded.

01:10:16.619 --> 01:10:20.220
Not Queen Glory after all, said Turtle.

01:10:20.279 --> 01:10:23.100
This is magic, an enchantment of some

01:10:23.100 --> 01:10:23.340
kind.

01:10:23.460 --> 01:10:26.460
He held up the unrolled scrap of paper

01:10:26.460 --> 01:10:28.380
then brought it close to his nose to read

01:10:28.380 --> 01:10:28.859
it aloud.

01:10:28.920 --> 01:10:32.279
Enchant this piece of scroll so that

01:10:32.279 --> 01:10:34.739
whichever dragon wears it tucked inside

01:10:34.739 --> 01:10:37.979
his or her ear shall look exactly like

01:10:37.979 --> 01:10:39.720
glory of the rain wings.

01:10:39.779 --> 01:10:43.319
There was a long, confused silence.

01:10:43.380 --> 01:10:45.659
It's not glory.

01:10:45.720 --> 01:10:48.180
Sonny whispered, exhaling.

01:10:48.239 --> 01:10:49.260
Clay.

01:10:49.319 --> 01:10:51.000
Glory's still alive.

01:10:51.119 --> 01:10:54.119
Alive, Clay said.

01:10:54.180 --> 01:10:56.699
His whole face glowed with relief.

01:10:56.760 --> 01:11:01.079
But we have to warn her that Scarlet's

01:11:01.079 --> 01:11:02.460
definitely going after her.

01:11:02.520 --> 01:11:05.819
He took a deep breath, his wings drifting

01:11:05.819 --> 01:11:07.020
down like falling leaves.

01:11:07.079 --> 01:11:11.699
I wonder who this was, he said softly

01:11:11.699 --> 01:11:12.960
nodding at the head.

01:11:13.020 --> 01:11:15.359
Was Scarlet trying to trick you?

01:11:15.420 --> 01:11:16.800
Turtle puzzled.

01:11:16.859 --> 01:11:18.119
But why?

01:11:18.180 --> 01:11:20.699
I mean, you'd have figured out the truth

01:11:20.699 --> 01:11:22.560
sooner or later, once you heard from

01:11:22.560 --> 01:11:22.979
glory.

01:11:23.039 --> 01:11:25.619
No, Carol said.

01:11:25.680 --> 01:11:27.420
It wasn't about tricking them.

01:11:27.479 --> 01:11:29.520
She just wanted to scare them.

01:11:29.579 --> 01:11:31.560
That's her favorite kind of power.

01:11:31.619 --> 01:11:35.579
Ruby let out a hiss, and peril met her

01:11:35.579 --> 01:11:35.880
eyes.

01:11:35.939 --> 01:11:37.560
She saw it then.

01:11:37.619 --> 01:11:39.899
The new queen was scared of her mother.

01:11:39.960 --> 01:11:42.239
As scared of her as peril was.

01:11:42.359 --> 01:11:44.880
The peril caught a glimpse of something

01:11:44.880 --> 01:11:47.699
else, something bitter and deep inside

01:11:47.699 --> 01:11:48.539
Ruby.

01:11:48.600 --> 01:11:50.220
It had to do with peril herself.

01:11:50.279 --> 01:11:52.560
She curled her talons in.

01:11:52.619 --> 01:11:55.380
She'd been thinking of the ways Scarlet

01:11:55.380 --> 01:11:56.579
always terrified her.

01:11:56.699 --> 01:11:59.819
Not all the ways Scarlet had used her to

01:11:59.819 --> 01:12:00.539
terrify others.

01:12:00.600 --> 01:12:04.199
Ruby's dark red wings flapped open and

01:12:04.199 --> 01:12:06.779
closed, like a rug briskly thrown over a

01:12:06.779 --> 01:12:07.079
body.

01:12:07.140 --> 01:12:09.239
Wait, she said.

01:12:09.300 --> 01:12:10.859
An enchantment?

01:12:10.920 --> 01:12:13.020
Doesn't that mean that Scarlet must have

01:12:13.020 --> 01:12:13.920
an animus?

01:12:13.979 --> 01:12:18.119
No, Sonny said, stretching her neck

01:12:18.119 --> 01:12:18.899
uneasily.

01:12:18.960 --> 01:12:19.979
No.

01:12:20.039 --> 01:12:22.680
We'd all be dead already if that were

01:12:22.680 --> 01:12:23.100
true.

01:12:23.159 --> 01:12:25.920
Turtle pointed the piece of paper at the

01:12:25.920 --> 01:12:26.699
mudwings head.

01:12:26.760 --> 01:12:31.140
But, ah, what else is this?

01:12:31.199 --> 01:12:34.140
Ruby whipped around suddenly to glare at

01:12:34.140 --> 01:12:34.680
peril.

01:12:34.739 --> 01:12:38.100
You must know, is there an animus dragon

01:12:38.100 --> 01:12:38.760
working for her?

01:12:38.819 --> 01:12:40.739
Why would I know?

01:12:40.800 --> 01:12:42.119
peril demanded.

01:12:42.180 --> 01:12:43.739
Argh.

01:12:43.800 --> 01:12:47.460
It would be so satisfying to just stomp

01:12:47.460 --> 01:12:49.979
on this dragon's tail and watch it burst

01:12:49.979 --> 01:12:50.460
into flames.

01:12:50.520 --> 01:12:52.500
She didn't tell me things.

01:12:52.560 --> 01:12:56.159
I was her her weapon, not her friend.

01:12:56.220 --> 01:12:57.720
You're her daughter.

01:12:57.779 --> 01:12:58.619
Why don't you know?

01:12:58.739 --> 01:13:03.000
No one can stop an animus, said Clay.

01:13:03.060 --> 01:13:04.079
Right?

01:13:04.140 --> 01:13:06.779
Except another animus.

01:13:06.840 --> 01:13:09.779
He exchanged a glance with Sonny that

01:13:09.779 --> 01:13:11.520
looked aggravatingly stuffed with

01:13:11.520 --> 01:13:11.939
secrets.

01:13:12.060 --> 01:13:13.800
What was that?

01:13:13.859 --> 01:13:15.960
Do they know an animus?

01:13:16.020 --> 01:13:18.359
Why do they have secrets I don't know

01:13:18.359 --> 01:13:18.600
about?

01:13:18.659 --> 01:13:20.939
Doesn't Clay know he can tell me

01:13:20.939 --> 01:13:21.239
anything?

01:13:21.300 --> 01:13:25.140
Peril flicked her tail irritably, and

01:13:25.140 --> 01:13:27.239
Ruby leaped away from her, even though

01:13:27.239 --> 01:13:29.039
her tail hadn't been anywhere near the

01:13:29.039 --> 01:13:30.180
queen's precious scales.

01:13:30.300 --> 01:13:33.420
I thought the Sky Wings didn't have any

01:13:33.420 --> 01:13:36.539
animus dragons, Turtles said, not for

01:13:36.539 --> 01:13:38.159
100s of years, if ever.

01:13:38.220 --> 01:13:42.239
Not just Sky Wings, said Ruby, none of

01:13:42.239 --> 01:13:42.840
the tribes.

01:13:42.899 --> 01:13:45.000
Animus dragons are so rare.

01:13:45.060 --> 01:13:47.399
I don't think there's been one in Pyria

01:13:47.399 --> 01:13:48.000
in centuries.

01:13:48.060 --> 01:13:51.659
The next pause had an extremely strange

01:13:51.659 --> 01:13:52.800
awkwardness to it.

01:13:52.859 --> 01:13:56.399
Peril glanced from clay to turtle to

01:13:56.399 --> 01:13:59.340
sunny, and realized they all knew

01:13:59.340 --> 01:14:00.960
something she and Ruby didn't.

01:14:01.079 --> 01:14:02.939
What?

01:14:03.060 --> 01:14:03.779
peril demanded.

01:14:03.840 --> 01:14:05.159
What is it?

01:14:05.220 --> 01:14:10.199
Um, my father, Sonny said quickly.

01:14:10.260 --> 01:14:13.199
Stone mover, he's an animus.

01:14:13.260 --> 01:14:16.020
The old night wing who lives under this

01:14:16.020 --> 01:14:16.439
mountain?

01:14:16.500 --> 01:14:17.939
Turtle asked.

01:14:18.000 --> 01:14:20.640
Judging from his tone of surprise, that

01:14:20.640 --> 01:14:22.380
wasn't the secret he'd been thinking of.

01:14:22.439 --> 01:14:24.479
Peril wondered if she could threaten it

01:14:24.479 --> 01:14:25.020
out of him later.

01:14:25.079 --> 01:14:27.180
Wait, no.

01:14:27.239 --> 01:14:29.640
This was one of those things Clay had to

01:14:29.640 --> 01:14:30.539
remind her about sometimes.

01:14:30.600 --> 01:14:33.479
Apparently, friends didn't threaten to

01:14:33.479 --> 01:14:36.000
set each other on fire, not very often

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:36.539
anyhow.

01:14:36.659 --> 01:14:39.359
Yes, Sonny admitted.

01:14:39.420 --> 01:14:41.699
He made the tunnels that lead from the

01:14:41.699 --> 01:14:44.039
rainforest to the Nightwing Island, and

01:14:44.039 --> 01:14:46.380
the kingdom of sand, but he doesn't use

01:14:46.380 --> 01:14:47.340
his powers anymore.

01:14:47.399 --> 01:14:50.520
He might have to, Ruby said.

01:14:50.579 --> 01:14:52.739
If there's a new animus on the loose

01:14:52.800 --> 01:14:54.960
working for Scarlet, and he's the only

01:14:54.960 --> 01:14:55.979
one who can stop her.

01:14:56.039 --> 01:14:58.619
Could it be another night wing?

01:14:58.680 --> 01:14:59.819
Turtle guessed.

01:14:59.880 --> 01:15:02.640
Someone who escaped the volcanic island

01:15:02.640 --> 01:15:04.680
and went to team up with Scarlet?

01:15:04.739 --> 01:15:06.000
Clay shuddered.

01:15:06.119 --> 01:15:09.779
That would be not great for us.

01:15:09.840 --> 01:15:13.739
I'm not afraid of any animus, peril

01:15:13.739 --> 01:15:14.159
blurted.

01:15:14.220 --> 01:15:15.899
I bet I could stop it.

01:15:15.960 --> 01:15:17.699
Him, her, whatever.

01:15:17.760 --> 01:15:20.159
I just have to sneak up on them and then

01:15:20.159 --> 01:15:23.039
pow, brain melted, claws a pile of

01:15:23.039 --> 01:15:23.640
cinders.

01:15:23.699 --> 01:15:25.439
No more creepy enchantments.

01:15:25.500 --> 01:15:26.579
Everybody cheers.

01:15:26.640 --> 01:15:29.939
For me, everybody cheers for me.

01:15:30.000 --> 01:15:32.819
Or at least, Clay tells me I'm

01:15:32.819 --> 01:15:33.060
wonderful.

01:15:33.119 --> 01:15:36.840
Clay didn't have his your wonderful face

01:15:36.840 --> 01:15:37.500
on, though.

01:15:37.619 --> 01:15:39.539
He looked all troubled and worried

01:15:39.539 --> 01:15:39.899
instead.

01:15:39.960 --> 01:15:43.800
But it might not be a bad dragon, Sonny

01:15:43.800 --> 01:15:44.039
said.

01:15:44.100 --> 01:15:46.979
This animus could be someone Scarlet has

01:15:46.979 --> 01:15:49.079
tricked or forced into working for her.

01:15:49.140 --> 01:15:51.000
We shouldn't just kill them without

01:15:51.000 --> 01:15:51.840
knowing the whole story.

01:15:51.899 --> 01:15:55.859
This is definitely not me agreeing with

01:15:55.859 --> 01:15:59.039
her, Ruby said, flicking her tail at

01:15:59.039 --> 01:15:59.460
peril.

01:15:59.520 --> 01:16:01.979
But I think we absolutely should.

01:16:02.039 --> 01:16:05.520
Animus dragons are so dangerous, and more

01:16:05.520 --> 01:16:07.140
so the more they use their powers.

01:16:07.199 --> 01:16:10.199
According to our history, the sky wing

01:16:10.199 --> 01:16:11.819
tribe used to kill them the moment we

01:16:11.819 --> 01:16:12.659
figured out what they were.

01:16:12.720 --> 01:16:17.340
But, Sonny looked aghast, as did Turtle.

01:16:17.399 --> 01:16:19.619
You mean, when they were still

01:16:19.619 --> 01:16:20.520
dragonettes?

01:16:20.579 --> 01:16:22.260
Before they'd even done anything?

01:16:22.319 --> 01:16:26.100
Before they could do anything, Ruby

01:16:26.100 --> 01:16:26.399
said.

01:16:26.460 --> 01:16:29.159
That's our policy with all dragons who

01:16:29.159 --> 01:16:30.479
are too dangerous to live.

01:16:30.539 --> 01:16:34.199
She slid her narrowed eyes over to peril

01:16:34.199 --> 01:16:36.239
who had already figured out the subtext

01:16:36.239 --> 01:16:37.260
of this conversation.

01:16:37.319 --> 01:16:37.979
Thanks very much.

01:16:38.100 --> 01:16:42.300
Oh dear, Sonny said, in a small voice.

01:16:42.359 --> 01:16:46.140
That's not fair, Turtle protested.

01:16:46.199 --> 01:16:48.600
Animas dragons can maybe do good things

01:16:48.600 --> 01:16:48.899
too.

01:16:48.960 --> 01:16:52.140
Let's save worrying about it until we

01:16:52.140 --> 01:16:54.479
know she really has one, Clay said.

01:16:54.539 --> 01:16:56.460
And who it is.

01:16:56.520 --> 01:16:59.159
We have enough else to worry about

01:16:59.159 --> 01:16:59.760
already.

01:16:59.819 --> 01:17:02.819
Like the rest of my winglet, Turtle

01:17:02.819 --> 01:17:03.180
said.

01:17:03.239 --> 01:17:04.319
Lowering his head.

01:17:04.380 --> 01:17:06.359
Do you think Moon and the others are

01:17:06.359 --> 01:17:07.260
safe?

01:17:07.319 --> 01:17:08.579
Weren't they going after Scarlet?

01:17:08.640 --> 01:17:10.439
They were.

01:17:10.500 --> 01:17:13.199
But I don't know what's happened, Sonny

01:17:13.199 --> 01:17:14.939
said, pressing her claws together

01:17:14.939 --> 01:17:15.539
anxiously.

01:17:15.600 --> 01:17:19.199
I tried to dream visit Kinkaju and Kibli

01:17:19.199 --> 01:17:21.060
last night, but couldn't get into either

01:17:21.060 --> 01:17:21.720
of their dreams.

01:17:21.779 --> 01:17:24.060
I haven't been able to since they left.

01:17:24.119 --> 01:17:26.039
Oh, I hope they're all right.

01:17:26.100 --> 01:17:29.819
They probably are, peril said, or else

01:17:29.819 --> 01:17:31.079
Scarlet would have been throwing their

01:17:31.079 --> 01:17:31.680
heads at you.

01:17:31.739 --> 01:17:35.159
She thought that would be very reassuring

01:17:35.159 --> 01:17:37.500
but for some reason, it made Sonny look

01:17:37.500 --> 01:17:38.159
even more ill.

01:17:38.220 --> 01:17:40.560
Someone's coming back.

01:17:40.619 --> 01:17:43.859
Play said, standing up and spreading his

01:17:43.859 --> 01:17:45.420
wings to catch the attention of the

01:17:45.420 --> 01:17:46.319
dragons in the sky.

01:17:46.380 --> 01:17:49.560
Three of Ruby's soldiers swooped down

01:17:49.560 --> 01:17:52.020
spiraling gracefully until they spotted

01:17:52.020 --> 01:17:54.119
peril, at which point they all started

01:17:54.119 --> 01:17:57.180
flapping like insane pigeons on fire

01:17:57.180 --> 01:17:59.220
until they finally landed in a thumping

01:17:59.220 --> 01:18:00.899
row between her and Ruby.

01:18:01.020 --> 01:18:03.359
Don't you come near our queen.

01:18:03.420 --> 01:18:05.100
One of them snarled.

01:18:05.159 --> 01:18:07.439
I wasn't planning on it.

01:18:07.500 --> 01:18:09.180
Peril snapped back.

01:18:09.239 --> 01:18:11.880
Do you actually think you could stop me

01:18:11.880 --> 01:18:12.659
if I was?

01:18:12.720 --> 01:18:17.159
Peril, Clay said softly. warningly.

01:18:17.220 --> 01:18:19.079
Blah.

01:18:19.140 --> 01:18:21.659
It wasn't fair that they could be rude

01:18:21.659 --> 01:18:24.119
and she couldn't set them on fire, or

01:18:24.119 --> 01:18:25.199
even growl back at them.

01:18:25.260 --> 01:18:28.680
But Pearl bit her tongue, sat back, and

01:18:28.680 --> 01:18:31.079
folded her wings across her chest, making

01:18:31.079 --> 01:18:32.939
sure she took up as little of the space

01:18:32.939 --> 01:18:34.439
on the rock ledge as possible.

01:18:34.500 --> 01:18:37.500
Clay gave her a sweet, grateful smile

01:18:37.500 --> 01:18:39.600
which almost made it okay.

01:18:39.659 --> 01:18:41.579
Ignore her.

01:18:41.640 --> 01:18:43.439
Ruby ordered her guards.

01:18:43.500 --> 01:18:44.640
What happened?

01:18:44.699 --> 01:18:46.859
We overtook the sea wing.

01:18:46.920 --> 01:18:49.680
But couldn't find Scarlet, said the tall

01:18:49.680 --> 01:18:50.880
orange soldier.

01:18:51.000 --> 01:18:53.340
The rest are still looking, but we wanted

01:18:53.340 --> 01:18:54.539
to come back and make sure you were

01:18:54.539 --> 01:18:56.159
guarded, in case it was a trick.

01:18:56.220 --> 01:19:00.899
It was in a way, said Ruby, nodding at

01:19:00.899 --> 01:19:01.199
the head.

01:19:01.260 --> 01:19:04.800
Someone has to catch tsunami, said

01:19:04.800 --> 01:19:05.279
Sonny.

01:19:05.399 --> 01:19:07.500
We had to tell her it's not glory.

01:19:07.560 --> 01:19:09.119
She.

01:19:09.239 --> 01:19:10.500
Clay said.

01:19:10.560 --> 01:19:12.779
She was somebody.

01:19:12.899 --> 01:19:15.119
Even if she's not glory.

01:19:15.180 --> 01:19:18.060
He took a deep breath and picked up the

01:19:18.060 --> 01:19:18.300
head.

01:19:18.359 --> 01:19:21.659
Peril wished she could turn it to ashes.

01:19:21.720 --> 01:19:23.279
She didn't like the way the dead brown

01:19:23.279 --> 01:19:24.539
eyes were staring at her.

01:19:24.600 --> 01:19:27.420
Piles of ashes were much tidier and less

01:19:27.420 --> 01:19:29.460
horrifying than stray body parts.

01:19:29.520 --> 01:19:33.300
Wait, if we can figure out who she is and

01:19:33.300 --> 01:19:36.479
where she's from, Ruby said suddenly, it

01:19:36.479 --> 01:19:38.039
might be a clue about where Scarlet is

01:19:38.039 --> 01:19:38.340
hiding.

01:19:38.399 --> 01:19:39.899
You're right.

01:19:39.960 --> 01:19:42.539
Let's take her to Queen Warren.

01:19:42.600 --> 01:19:45.720
Clay turned toward Ruby, wincing as he

01:19:45.720 --> 01:19:47.159
set his weight on his injured leg.

01:19:47.220 --> 01:19:49.619
That's the best place to start.

01:19:49.680 --> 01:19:51.539
She nodded.

01:19:51.600 --> 01:19:53.760
Tilting her diamond shaped head toward

01:19:53.760 --> 01:19:54.600
the orange dragon.

01:19:54.659 --> 01:19:57.060
Go catch the sea wing and tell her to

01:19:57.060 --> 01:19:58.380
return, she ordered.

01:19:58.439 --> 01:20:01.020
My soldiers should split up.

01:20:01.079 --> 01:20:03.479
Half keep looking for Scarlet, and the

01:20:03.479 --> 01:20:04.439
other half return to me.

01:20:04.500 --> 01:20:06.600
We'll leave for Warren's Palace at

01:20:06.600 --> 01:20:07.020
midnight.

01:20:07.079 --> 01:20:10.199
All the sky wings whirled into the air.

01:20:10.260 --> 01:20:13.380
The orange soldier went north, while

01:20:13.380 --> 01:20:15.539
Queen Ruby and the other 2 swept south

01:20:15.539 --> 01:20:16.560
toward Jade Mountain.

01:20:16.619 --> 01:20:19.680
I'm going to try the dream visitor again

01:20:19.680 --> 01:20:21.180
Sonny said to Clay.

01:20:21.300 --> 01:20:24.300
He reached over, and twined his tail

01:20:24.300 --> 01:20:27.239
around hers, and peril felt a stab of

01:20:27.239 --> 01:20:28.439
jealousy so fierce.

01:20:28.500 --> 01:20:30.720
She was surprised flames didn't come

01:20:30.720 --> 01:20:31.800
shooting out of her eyeballs.

01:20:31.920 --> 01:20:33.779
They're all right.

01:20:33.840 --> 01:20:37.319
I'm sure they are, Clay said quietly to

01:20:37.319 --> 01:20:37.739
Sonny.

01:20:37.800 --> 01:20:40.260
She shook her head without answering, and

01:20:40.260 --> 01:20:41.340
lifted off into the sky.

01:20:41.399 --> 01:20:44.460
Only clay and peril were left on the

01:20:44.460 --> 01:20:44.819
ledge.

01:20:44.939 --> 01:20:48.659
At last, she gazed deep into his warm

01:20:48.659 --> 01:20:49.859
brown eyes.

01:20:50.039 --> 01:20:53.100
So Scarlet is pretty scary, huh?

01:20:53.159 --> 01:20:55.079
Oh, right.

01:20:55.199 --> 01:20:56.520
And turtle.

01:20:56.579 --> 01:20:59.460
The sea wing edged closer to them

01:20:59.460 --> 01:21:01.319
twitching his wings curiously.

01:21:01.380 --> 01:21:03.840
Peril tried giving him a significant look

01:21:03.840 --> 01:21:06.779
of the go away, we're having a moment

01:21:06.779 --> 01:21:09.300
variety, but he didn't seem to notice.

01:21:09.359 --> 01:21:12.239
Yes, she is.

01:21:12.300 --> 01:21:14.039
Clay said with a sigh.

01:21:14.100 --> 01:21:16.560
What kind of sigh was that?

01:21:16.619 --> 01:21:17.880
Peril wondered.

01:21:17.939 --> 01:21:21.180
Was it an, I wish I were alone with peril

01:21:21.180 --> 01:21:21.539
Si?

01:21:21.539 --> 01:21:24.300
Or a, worried about my students, Si.

01:21:24.420 --> 01:21:26.039
Knowing clay?

01:21:26.159 --> 01:21:28.500
It could also be a, we're all out of

01:21:28.500 --> 01:21:30.899
goats and I really wanted one, Si.

01:21:31.020 --> 01:21:33.420
What are you going to do?

01:21:33.479 --> 01:21:34.439
she asked him.

01:21:34.500 --> 01:21:38.220
I should stay here and guard the

01:21:38.220 --> 01:21:38.760
academy.

01:21:38.819 --> 01:21:42.300
He said thoughtfully, but if Ruby agrees

01:21:42.300 --> 01:21:44.100
to leave enough guards to protect the

01:21:44.100 --> 01:21:44.460
students.

01:21:44.520 --> 01:21:47.579
I might go with her to see Queen Warren.

01:21:47.640 --> 01:21:49.859
Carol didn't like that plan.

01:21:49.920 --> 01:21:52.380
She had a feeling she wouldn't be invited

01:21:52.380 --> 01:21:54.420
along on any diplomatic missions

01:21:54.420 --> 01:21:56.699
especially any that involved going inside

01:21:56.699 --> 01:21:59.399
other queens' palaces, and possibly

01:21:59.399 --> 01:22:01.500
incinerating their national treasures by

01:22:01.500 --> 01:22:02.760
accident or whatever.

01:22:02.939 --> 01:22:04.439
What about me?

01:22:04.500 --> 01:22:05.399
She asked.

01:22:05.460 --> 01:22:06.779
What should I do?

01:22:06.840 --> 01:22:09.539
He gave her a rueful smile that lit

01:22:09.539 --> 01:22:10.680
candles in her heart.

01:22:10.739 --> 01:22:13.380
Whatever you want to do, peril.

01:22:13.439 --> 01:22:15.779
That's the whole point of being free from

01:22:15.779 --> 01:22:17.039
scarlet, isn't it?

01:22:17.100 --> 01:22:19.859
But what do you want me to do?

01:22:19.920 --> 01:22:20.760
She pressed.

01:22:20.880 --> 01:22:23.520
Peril, Clay said.

01:22:23.579 --> 01:22:26.159
I'm not going to be a new scarlet for

01:22:26.159 --> 01:22:26.340
you.

01:22:26.399 --> 01:22:28.680
You get to make your own choices now.

01:22:28.739 --> 01:22:32.520
I am making my own choices.

01:22:32.579 --> 01:22:34.260
Peril thought grumpily.

01:22:34.319 --> 01:22:36.899
I'm choosing to do whatever you think I

01:22:36.899 --> 01:22:37.500
should do.

01:22:37.560 --> 01:22:40.140
Maybe she could figure out what he wanted

01:22:40.140 --> 01:22:41.340
from the clues.

01:22:41.399 --> 01:22:44.100
Sometimes, when Queen Scarlet was really

01:22:44.100 --> 01:22:46.319
angry, She wouldn't speak to peril for

01:22:46.319 --> 01:22:48.539
weeks, and then peril had to figure out

01:22:48.539 --> 01:22:51.180
on her own what she'd done wrong and how

01:22:51.180 --> 01:22:53.100
to fix it to make Queen Scarlet happy

01:22:53.100 --> 01:22:53.340
again.

01:22:53.399 --> 01:22:57.000
So, what did Clay want?

01:22:57.060 --> 01:23:00.659
She studied him from horns to tail?

01:23:00.720 --> 01:23:03.180
He had turned to gaze back at Jade

01:23:03.180 --> 01:23:05.399
Mountain, his wings drooping heavily.

01:23:05.460 --> 01:23:08.460
All right, it was pretty obvious.

01:23:08.520 --> 01:23:10.920
He wanted his friends and his school to

01:23:10.920 --> 01:23:11.279
be safe.

01:23:11.340 --> 01:23:14.880
And the only way to do that was to get

01:23:14.880 --> 01:23:16.319
rid of Queen Scarlet forever.

01:23:16.380 --> 01:23:19.079
Peril inhaled a sharp breath.

01:23:19.140 --> 01:23:20.460
That was it.

01:23:20.520 --> 01:23:22.680
Clay would never say it out loud.

01:23:22.739 --> 01:23:24.779
He'd never ask her for it directly.

01:23:24.840 --> 01:23:27.899
But what he really wanted her to do was

01:23:27.899 --> 01:23:30.239
find Queen Scarlet and kill her for him.

01:23:30.300 --> 01:23:33.840
She might be the only dragon empire who

01:23:33.840 --> 01:23:34.079
could.

01:23:34.140 --> 01:23:36.899
Especially if an animus was protecting

01:23:36.899 --> 01:23:37.560
Scarlet now.

01:23:37.619 --> 01:23:41.699
So as much as she never, never wanted to

01:23:41.699 --> 01:23:43.920
see Scarlet again, and as much as the

01:23:43.920 --> 01:23:45.899
idea of leaving Clay to find her was

01:23:45.899 --> 01:23:47.939
heart wrenching, that was what she was

01:23:47.939 --> 01:23:48.659
going to have to do.

01:23:48.720 --> 01:23:51.899
It's all right, Clay, she thought.

01:23:51.960 --> 01:23:53.520
You don't have to tell me.

01:23:53.579 --> 01:23:56.279
I know what you want, and I'll do it for

01:23:56.279 --> 01:23:56.520
you.

01:23:56.579 --> 01:24:00.359
I'll find Queen Scarlet, and I'll make

01:24:00.359 --> 01:24:02.460
sure she never, ever hurts you again.

01:24:02.520 --> 01:24:06.840
Chapter 4.

01:24:07.079 --> 01:24:10.380
The plan was to sneak away in the middle

01:24:10.380 --> 01:24:10.800
of the night.

01:24:10.859 --> 01:24:13.199
That sounded like something a hero would

01:24:13.199 --> 01:24:13.500
do.

01:24:13.560 --> 01:24:15.840
She would set off on her quest alone.

01:24:15.899 --> 01:24:19.560
Boldly, but quietly, without giving

01:24:19.560 --> 01:24:21.479
anyone a chance to talk her out of it.

01:24:21.539 --> 01:24:24.539
Peril could imagine flying bravely into

01:24:24.539 --> 01:24:28.199
the night, and even better than that, she

01:24:28.199 --> 01:24:29.939
could imagine the scene the next morning

01:24:29.939 --> 01:24:32.699
when Clay found her gone, and threw back

01:24:32.699 --> 01:24:35.640
his head and cried, no, peril.

01:24:35.699 --> 01:24:37.439
She's gone to save us all.

01:24:37.500 --> 01:24:40.619
She's so noble and self sacrificing.

01:24:40.680 --> 01:24:42.420
But what am I going to do without her?

01:24:42.479 --> 01:24:45.479
Oh, the unbearable pain.

01:24:45.539 --> 01:24:47.819
But here was the problem.

01:24:47.880 --> 01:24:49.979
When she kept going with that scene in

01:24:49.979 --> 01:24:51.960
her head, The next thing that happened

01:24:51.960 --> 01:24:54.960
was sunny, or a tsunami, or a Starflight

01:24:54.960 --> 01:24:55.739
showing up.

01:24:55.800 --> 01:24:57.359
And then one of them would say something

01:24:57.359 --> 01:25:00.600
like, Or, hey, maybe she's run off

01:25:00.600 --> 01:25:02.220
because she's actually evil and in

01:25:02.220 --> 01:25:05.760
cahoots with Scarlet after all, and or, I

01:25:05.760 --> 01:25:07.260
knew we couldn't trust her.

01:25:07.319 --> 01:25:09.359
And it all went downhill from there.

01:25:09.420 --> 01:25:12.720
Carol didn't want to leave Clay wondering

01:25:12.720 --> 01:25:13.739
what she was really up to.

01:25:13.800 --> 01:25:16.020
She didn't care what the others thought

01:25:16.020 --> 01:25:19.680
of her, but in all the world, Clay was

01:25:19.680 --> 01:25:21.779
the only dragon who saw more good in her

01:25:21.779 --> 01:25:22.619
than bad.

01:25:22.680 --> 01:25:25.079
She didn't want him to have even a moment

01:25:25.079 --> 01:25:28.079
of, is peril really as dangerous and

01:25:28.079 --> 01:25:30.420
unstable as everyone's been telling me?

01:25:30.479 --> 01:25:33.659
So clearly, she had to say goodbye to

01:25:33.659 --> 01:25:33.840
him.

01:25:33.899 --> 01:25:35.100
That was obvious.

01:25:35.159 --> 01:25:37.800
It wasn't just that she wanted to see him

01:25:37.800 --> 01:25:40.319
one more time, or that she was hoping

01:25:40.319 --> 01:25:41.819
he'd tell her not to go.

01:25:41.880 --> 01:25:43.380
No, no none of those.

01:25:43.439 --> 01:25:45.659
It was for his own sake.

01:25:45.720 --> 01:25:46.140
Really?

01:25:46.199 --> 01:25:50.100
She waited until the halls were quiet, and

01:25:50.100 --> 01:25:51.659
then she slipped out of her sleeping cave

01:25:51.659 --> 01:25:54.359
which was as bare and empty as the day

01:25:54.359 --> 01:25:55.260
she'd stepped into it.

01:25:55.319 --> 01:25:57.899
Everyone else in the school had to share

01:25:57.899 --> 01:26:00.539
their sleeping cave, but then, no one

01:26:00.539 --> 01:26:02.579
else could accidentally burn up her claw

01:26:02.579 --> 01:26:04.500
mates just by rolling over in the middle

01:26:04.500 --> 01:26:05.039
of the night.

01:26:05.100 --> 01:26:08.880
Clay had offered peril a cave closer to

01:26:08.880 --> 01:26:10.800
the other students, but he seemed

01:26:10.800 --> 01:26:12.539
relieved when she refused it.

01:26:12.600 --> 01:26:15.239
So hers was close to the dragonettes who

01:26:15.239 --> 01:26:17.520
ran the school instead, but she still had

01:26:17.520 --> 01:26:19.020
to go through the main central cave to

01:26:19.020 --> 01:26:19.619
get to clay.

01:26:19.680 --> 01:26:22.500
Which is where she nearly ran into Turtle

01:26:22.500 --> 01:26:23.880
for the 2nd time that day.

01:26:24.060 --> 01:26:24.960
Seriously?

01:26:25.020 --> 01:26:27.539
If a dragonette insisted on flopping like

01:26:27.539 --> 01:26:29.579
a lumpy boulder in the middle of a dimly

01:26:29.579 --> 01:26:32.460
lit cave, wasn't it his own fault?

01:26:32.460 --> 01:26:34.079
If he got set on fire?

01:26:34.140 --> 01:26:36.239
Ah!

01:26:36.300 --> 01:26:38.520
Why are you always in the way?

01:26:38.579 --> 01:26:41.699
she demanded, backpedaling at the last

01:26:41.699 --> 01:26:43.680
minute to avoid stepping on his talons.

01:26:43.800 --> 01:26:45.239
Am I?

01:26:45.300 --> 01:26:47.819
He said sleepily. lifting his head.

01:26:47.880 --> 01:26:50.939
I'm not usually, I don't think.

01:26:51.060 --> 01:26:54.180
Other dragons go around me, or over me

01:26:54.180 --> 01:26:54.779
pretty well.

01:26:54.840 --> 01:26:58.859
You won't be pleased if I go over you

01:26:58.859 --> 01:27:00.180
Peril pointed out.

01:27:00.239 --> 01:27:02.520
Why aren't you in your own sleeping

01:27:02.520 --> 01:27:02.939
cave?

01:27:03.000 --> 01:27:05.220
Turtle gave a little shiver.

01:27:05.279 --> 01:27:08.640
It feels weird in there now that umber is

01:27:08.640 --> 01:27:08.939
gone.

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:11.159
And all the rest of my winglet too.

01:27:11.220 --> 01:27:13.079
I should have gone with them.

01:27:13.140 --> 01:27:14.579
He mumbled.

01:27:14.640 --> 01:27:16.739
Not if they're all dead now.

01:27:16.800 --> 01:27:18.600
Peril said sensibly.

01:27:18.659 --> 01:27:21.420
If Scarlet has killed them, then staying

01:27:21.420 --> 01:27:22.920
here was obviously the smart choice.

01:27:23.039 --> 01:27:25.020
He sat up fast.

01:27:25.079 --> 01:27:27.960
And peril tilted her head, trying to read

01:27:27.960 --> 01:27:30.720
his expression, alarmed or horrified?

01:27:30.840 --> 01:27:32.279
Anxiety?

01:27:32.340 --> 01:27:33.479
Guilt?

01:27:33.539 --> 01:27:34.680
All of the above?

01:27:34.739 --> 01:27:36.539
No.

01:27:36.600 --> 01:27:38.039
Turtle protested.

01:27:38.100 --> 01:27:39.420
Are you crazy?

01:27:39.479 --> 01:27:41.100
That would be even worse.

01:27:41.159 --> 01:27:43.199
What if you're right, and they're dead

01:27:43.199 --> 01:27:44.520
and I could have saved them.

01:27:44.579 --> 01:27:45.960
Really?

01:27:46.020 --> 01:27:47.640
You?

01:27:47.699 --> 01:27:49.079
Peril said.

01:27:49.140 --> 01:27:54.000
I do not appreciate your skeptical tone

01:27:54.000 --> 01:27:57.119
he said, sounding briefly like an actual

01:27:57.119 --> 01:27:57.600
prince.

01:27:57.659 --> 01:28:00.479
Just because I don't particularly like

01:28:00.479 --> 01:28:03.659
danger or uncertainty or or exercise

01:28:03.659 --> 01:28:06.659
doesn't mean I couldn't be useful in a

01:28:06.659 --> 01:28:06.960
fight.

01:28:07.020 --> 01:28:10.619
Peril paused, trying to figure out how to

01:28:10.619 --> 01:28:12.600
say what she wanted to say without the

01:28:12.600 --> 01:28:13.380
skeptical tone.

01:28:13.500 --> 01:28:15.840
Really?

01:28:15.899 --> 01:28:17.460
She tried.

01:28:17.520 --> 01:28:19.439
Infusing the word with as much

01:28:19.439 --> 01:28:21.600
enthusiastic curiosity as she could.

01:28:21.659 --> 01:28:23.460
You?

01:28:23.640 --> 01:28:25.859
Turtle burst out laughing.

01:28:25.920 --> 01:28:28.680
You're so weird, he said.

01:28:28.739 --> 01:28:31.260
I'm not the one sleeping in the entrance

01:28:31.260 --> 01:28:34.439
hall, Pearl said, asking to get trampled

01:28:34.439 --> 01:28:35.039
and scorched.

01:28:35.100 --> 01:28:38.220
Well, the other thing is that tsunami

01:28:38.220 --> 01:28:39.840
isn't back yet, he admitted.

01:28:39.899 --> 01:28:41.699
I'm sort of waiting for her.

01:28:41.760 --> 01:28:45.119
Uh-oh, peril said.

01:28:45.239 --> 01:28:47.159
He gave her an anxious look, and she

01:28:47.159 --> 01:28:49.739
added quickly, I mean, that probably

01:28:49.739 --> 01:28:50.699
doesn't mean anything.

01:28:50.760 --> 01:28:53.340
Anything involving decapitation, that

01:28:53.340 --> 01:28:53.819
is.

01:28:53.880 --> 01:28:57.119
You have this uncanny ability.

01:28:57.180 --> 01:28:59.640
To say whatever is the opposite of

01:28:59.640 --> 01:29:00.239
comforting.

01:29:00.300 --> 01:29:02.279
He observed wryly.

01:29:02.340 --> 01:29:04.140
That wasn't comforting?

01:29:04.140 --> 01:29:05.220
she asked.

01:29:05.399 --> 01:29:08.880
Um, how about, I'm sure she's fine

01:29:08.880 --> 01:29:11.100
because a sea wing dragonette like her

01:29:11.100 --> 01:29:13.260
could never possibly catch up with a full

01:29:13.260 --> 01:29:14.819
grown sky wing like Scarlet.

01:29:14.880 --> 01:29:18.779
Oh, unless it was a trap, and Scarlet

01:29:18.779 --> 01:29:19.500
ambushed her.

01:29:19.560 --> 01:29:23.159
Turtle wrinkled his snout at her, imperil

01:29:23.159 --> 01:29:24.539
shifted on her talons.

01:29:24.600 --> 01:29:26.279
Okay, I know.

01:29:26.340 --> 01:29:27.420
I heard it that time.

01:29:27.539 --> 01:29:30.239
But it was a smart thought, wasn't it?

01:29:30.300 --> 01:29:32.939
He turned to look out at the stars.

01:29:33.000 --> 01:29:34.979
So what do we do?

01:29:35.039 --> 01:29:36.239
He asked.

01:29:36.300 --> 01:29:38.520
Send more dragons to look for her?

01:29:38.579 --> 01:29:40.920
What if Scarlet ambushes everyone?

01:29:40.979 --> 01:29:43.920
We don't know how many dragons she might

01:29:43.920 --> 01:29:44.640
have working for her.

01:29:44.760 --> 01:29:47.579
What if this is her plan?

01:29:47.640 --> 01:29:49.500
And she kills everyone we send after

01:29:49.500 --> 01:29:50.159
tsunami.

01:29:50.220 --> 01:29:53.520
She can't kill me, Pearl pointed out.

01:29:53.579 --> 01:29:55.439
I'd like to see her try.

01:29:55.500 --> 01:29:56.100
Ha.

01:29:56.159 --> 01:29:59.100
Turtle gave her an odd glittering look.

01:29:59.159 --> 01:30:01.439
You're right, he said.

01:30:01.500 --> 01:30:04.079
You and me, we should go.

01:30:04.199 --> 01:30:06.300
That's what I...

01:30:06.840 --> 01:30:09.180
Wait, no, she said.

01:30:09.239 --> 01:30:10.020
What?

01:30:10.079 --> 01:30:11.819
She can definitely kill you.

01:30:11.939 --> 01:30:14.880
Maybe not, he said.

01:30:14.939 --> 01:30:18.420
Anyway, tsunami's my sister, and my

01:30:18.420 --> 01:30:19.680
winglet is out there somewhere.

01:30:19.739 --> 01:30:22.800
You hope, Pearl interjected.

01:30:22.859 --> 01:30:24.300
Err.

01:30:24.359 --> 01:30:27.300
I mean, yes, they are.

01:30:27.420 --> 01:30:30.359
Turtle lifted one of his wings to shush

01:30:30.359 --> 01:30:31.500
her, tilting his head.

01:30:31.560 --> 01:30:33.000
Someone's coming.

01:30:33.060 --> 01:30:34.199
He whispered.

01:30:34.260 --> 01:30:35.100
Hide.

01:30:35.159 --> 01:30:38.399
He ran over to the enormous gong in the

01:30:38.399 --> 01:30:40.380
center of the hall and dove behind it.

01:30:40.439 --> 01:30:44.100
Startled, Pearl twisted around in a

01:30:44.100 --> 01:30:46.079
circle before she found a shadowy corner

01:30:46.079 --> 01:30:47.880
where there was an outgrowth of

01:30:47.880 --> 01:30:49.260
stalagmites to hide behind.

01:30:49.319 --> 01:30:51.659
She tucked herself into the darkness and

01:30:51.659 --> 01:30:54.300
whispered loudly, Why are we hiding?

01:30:54.420 --> 01:30:57.359
Turtle answered.

01:30:57.420 --> 01:31:00.000
Peril tried to remember the last time

01:31:00.000 --> 01:31:01.739
she'd ever hidden from anyone before

01:31:01.739 --> 01:31:02.760
she'd met Turtle.

01:31:02.819 --> 01:31:05.699
Maybe in the kingdom of sand, when she

01:31:05.699 --> 01:31:07.140
was trying to sneak up on Burns

01:31:07.140 --> 01:31:10.140
stronghold to rescue Scarlet, but hiding

01:31:10.140 --> 01:31:11.520
was not normally her approach to

01:31:11.520 --> 01:31:12.119
problems.

01:31:12.180 --> 01:31:13.380
Why hide?

01:31:13.439 --> 01:31:14.939
When you could always set your problem on

01:31:14.939 --> 01:31:15.600
fire.

01:31:15.659 --> 01:31:18.119
Now she could hear voices approaching.

01:31:18.180 --> 01:31:21.359
One of them sounded like Clay, who was

01:31:21.359 --> 01:31:23.579
exactly the dragon she was looking for

01:31:23.579 --> 01:31:25.979
except now, if she popped out of her

01:31:25.979 --> 01:31:29.640
hiding place, he'd be like, um, what were

01:31:29.640 --> 01:31:30.420
you doing back there?

01:31:30.539 --> 01:31:34.260
And it would look so, so weird and maybe

01:31:34.260 --> 01:31:35.279
suspicious too.

01:31:35.340 --> 01:31:37.020
Argh!

01:31:37.079 --> 01:31:39.060
Thanks a lot, turtle.

01:31:39.119 --> 01:31:41.520
What is with this dragon in the

01:31:41.520 --> 01:31:42.420
eavesdropping?

01:31:42.479 --> 01:31:45.539
10 soldiers should be enough to guard

01:31:45.539 --> 01:31:46.619
this place.

01:31:46.680 --> 01:31:47.880
Ruby's voice said.

01:31:47.939 --> 01:31:50.880
Peril heard 3 sets of talons enter the

01:31:50.880 --> 01:31:52.979
cave, and she pressed herself closer to

01:31:52.979 --> 01:31:53.340
the floor.

01:31:53.399 --> 01:31:56.520
And with luck, we'll be back in 3 days.

01:31:56.579 --> 01:31:58.680
I don't want to be away from the Sky

01:31:58.680 --> 01:31:59.520
Palace for too long.

01:31:59.579 --> 01:32:02.279
I have someone waiting for me.

01:32:02.340 --> 01:32:04.800
Thank you, Queen Ruby.

01:32:04.859 --> 01:32:07.319
That was Starflight, the Nightwing

01:32:07.319 --> 01:32:07.920
librarian.

01:32:07.979 --> 01:32:10.560
Did your student tell you anything else

01:32:10.560 --> 01:32:11.159
we should know?

01:32:11.220 --> 01:32:12.539
Ruby asked.

01:32:12.600 --> 01:32:14.939
Apart from the disturbing news about my

01:32:14.939 --> 01:32:16.199
mother's new ally?

01:32:16.260 --> 01:32:19.920
Not much, play said with a sigh.

01:32:20.039 --> 01:32:23.579
Moons in Possibility with Kibley.

01:32:23.640 --> 01:32:27.300
Sunny is dream visiting with glory now, so

01:32:27.300 --> 01:32:29.220
she can send someone up to the town to

01:32:29.220 --> 01:32:30.359
take care of Kinkachu.

01:32:30.420 --> 01:32:34.380
Poor Kinkaju, Starflight said softly.

01:32:34.439 --> 01:32:36.119
Uh-oh.

01:32:36.180 --> 01:32:37.199
Peril thought.

01:32:37.319 --> 01:32:40.199
She had seen the bouncy little rain wing

01:32:40.199 --> 01:32:42.479
from a distance, but mostly she'd only

01:32:42.479 --> 01:32:43.680
heard about her from clay.

01:32:43.739 --> 01:32:46.619
If she was hurt, he must be upset.

01:32:46.680 --> 01:32:48.960
And what had happened to the other

01:32:48.960 --> 01:32:50.279
missing dragonette?

01:32:50.340 --> 01:32:52.800
Winter, the ice wing who hated her.

01:32:52.859 --> 01:32:55.199
Peril would be all right with him being

01:32:55.199 --> 01:32:58.560
dead out of the 4 dragonettes, but Clay

01:32:58.560 --> 01:32:59.579
wouldn't, of course.

01:32:59.640 --> 01:33:02.279
He'd feel all responsible and protective

01:33:02.279 --> 01:33:03.119
and worried.

01:33:03.119 --> 01:33:05.279
Oh dear, was he all right?

01:33:05.340 --> 01:33:07.319
She wished she could see his face.

01:33:07.439 --> 01:33:11.279
One last word of warning, although I know

01:33:11.279 --> 01:33:13.739
you won't listen to me, Ruby said

01:33:13.739 --> 01:33:16.140
stopping with a loud swish of her tail.

01:33:16.199 --> 01:33:19.079
You cannot trust my mother's creature.

01:33:19.140 --> 01:33:21.720
She's unpredictable, and knows nothing

01:33:21.720 --> 01:33:22.619
but killing.

01:33:22.680 --> 01:33:25.800
If you won't banish her, at least don't

01:33:25.800 --> 01:33:27.239
leave her unguarded for an instant.

01:33:27.300 --> 01:33:29.760
I can trust peril.

01:33:29.819 --> 01:33:31.140
Clay said.

01:33:31.199 --> 01:33:34.500
And in her shadows, peril felt her entire

01:33:34.500 --> 01:33:36.420
soul turn into a fireball.

01:33:36.479 --> 01:33:38.699
She saved my life.

01:33:38.760 --> 01:33:43.319
Plus, she's in love with Clay, Starflight

01:33:43.319 --> 01:33:43.680
added.

01:33:43.739 --> 01:33:46.439
Pearl wondered if anyone would notice if

01:33:46.439 --> 01:33:48.899
she flew over, ripped out his tongue and

01:33:48.899 --> 01:33:50.460
vanished into the night sky forever.

01:33:50.520 --> 01:33:55.800
Ah, clay said. 3 moon Starfight.

01:33:55.859 --> 01:34:00.960
That's not, it's not even, we're, no, no

01:34:00.960 --> 01:34:01.199
no.

01:34:01.260 --> 01:34:04.020
I trust her because there's good in her.

01:34:04.079 --> 01:34:06.300
And we just need to give her a chance to

01:34:06.300 --> 01:34:07.020
show it to us.

01:34:07.079 --> 01:34:11.399
She may have a fragment of good in her

01:34:11.399 --> 01:34:14.819
somewhere, Ruby said doubtfully, but

01:34:14.819 --> 01:34:16.380
she'll never be good enough for you.

01:34:16.439 --> 01:34:19.439
And if he's right, and if she ever thinks

01:34:19.439 --> 01:34:21.960
you don't love her back, she will set all

01:34:21.960 --> 01:34:22.979
your friends on fire.

01:34:23.039 --> 01:34:25.079
That's just the truth.

01:34:25.140 --> 01:34:28.140
Um, said Starflight.

01:34:28.199 --> 01:34:30.720
For the record, I don't like the sound of

01:34:30.720 --> 01:34:31.140
that at all.

01:34:31.140 --> 01:34:33.600
Peril closed her eyes.

01:34:33.659 --> 01:34:35.159
Was it true?

01:34:35.220 --> 01:34:37.439
What would happen if Clay didn't love

01:34:37.439 --> 01:34:37.680
her?

01:34:37.739 --> 01:34:39.960
Or if he ever tried to send her away?

01:34:40.020 --> 01:34:43.079
It was a horrible, soul crushing

01:34:43.079 --> 01:34:43.439
thought.

01:34:43.500 --> 01:34:45.779
But she wouldn't really set his friends

01:34:45.779 --> 01:34:47.039
on fire, would she?

01:34:47.100 --> 01:34:50.039
Not all of them anyway?

01:34:50.100 --> 01:34:53.520
No, she told herself severely.

01:34:53.579 --> 01:34:56.279
None of them, not even if it's their

01:34:56.279 --> 01:34:57.420
fault he doesn't love me.

01:34:57.479 --> 01:35:01.619
But what a tsunami convinced him to get

01:35:01.619 --> 01:35:02.279
rid of her.

01:35:02.520 --> 01:35:04.079
She might totally do something like

01:35:04.079 --> 01:35:04.319
that.

01:35:04.380 --> 01:35:07.800
Then could peril set just the tiniest

01:35:07.800 --> 01:35:08.880
part of her on fire?

01:35:08.939 --> 01:35:11.159
No, no, no.

01:35:11.220 --> 01:35:14.159
Because there's always the chance he

01:35:14.159 --> 01:35:15.539
might still love me one day.

01:35:15.659 --> 01:35:18.359
But he definitely won't if there's any

01:35:18.359 --> 01:35:19.619
friend burning at all.

01:35:19.680 --> 01:35:23.699
Let's not talk about this, Clay said

01:35:23.699 --> 01:35:24.300
awkwardly.

01:35:24.359 --> 01:35:27.960
Your majesty, I'll meet you back here at

01:35:27.960 --> 01:35:28.560
midnight.

01:35:28.619 --> 01:35:31.920
All right, well, she said.

01:35:31.979 --> 01:35:33.720
You've been warned.

01:35:33.779 --> 01:35:36.840
She swept majestically out of the cave.

01:35:36.899 --> 01:35:39.479
Her tail making quiet, dramatic swishing

01:35:39.479 --> 01:35:41.039
noises against the stone floor.

01:35:41.100 --> 01:35:43.199
Should I be worried?

01:35:43.260 --> 01:35:44.819
Starflight asked.

01:35:44.880 --> 01:35:47.039
Am I going to wake up on fire one day?

01:35:47.100 --> 01:35:49.079
How worried should I be?

01:35:49.140 --> 01:35:52.500
Not at all, Clay said.

01:35:52.619 --> 01:35:54.840
Peril is not going to set you on fire.

01:35:54.899 --> 01:35:58.020
I wonder if I have any scrolls about

01:35:58.020 --> 01:35:59.279
sociopaths.

01:35:59.340 --> 01:36:00.779
Starflight muttered.

01:36:00.840 --> 01:36:02.220
Stop that.

01:36:02.279 --> 01:36:04.380
Clay stamped one of his feet.

01:36:04.439 --> 01:36:07.380
I'm going to ask Sonny to dream visit

01:36:07.380 --> 01:36:09.359
tsunami and see if she can find her.

01:36:09.420 --> 01:36:12.539
Queen Ruby will never believe peril has

01:36:12.539 --> 01:36:14.520
changed, Starflight called after him.

01:36:14.640 --> 01:36:17.399
There was a pause as Clay's footsteps

01:36:17.399 --> 01:36:18.060
faded away.

01:36:18.119 --> 01:36:21.840
Not sure we will either, he added to

01:36:21.840 --> 01:36:24.300
himself, and then peril heard his talons

01:36:24.300 --> 01:36:26.220
scrape against the rock as he bustled off

01:36:26.220 --> 01:36:27.000
to the library.

01:36:27.060 --> 01:36:29.760
Silence, fell across the cavern.

01:36:29.819 --> 01:36:33.300
Pearl curled her claws in and took a deep

01:36:33.300 --> 01:36:33.779
breath.

01:36:33.840 --> 01:36:37.199
Sorry about that, Turtle said.

01:36:37.260 --> 01:36:39.239
His voice whispering across the empty

01:36:39.239 --> 01:36:39.600
space.

01:36:39.659 --> 01:36:42.840
A few moments later, his head popped

01:36:42.840 --> 01:36:44.279
around the edge of the rocks she was

01:36:44.279 --> 01:36:44.760
hiding behind.

01:36:44.819 --> 01:36:48.420
I've been doing that all my life, and

01:36:48.420 --> 01:36:49.979
I've never heard anyone say anything

01:36:49.979 --> 01:36:50.399
about me.

01:36:50.460 --> 01:36:53.039
That's because you're boring and

01:36:53.039 --> 01:36:54.960
forgettable, Pearl snapped.

01:36:55.020 --> 01:36:57.960
I know, he said unexpectedly.

01:36:58.020 --> 01:36:59.220
I try to be.

01:36:59.279 --> 01:37:02.699
Well, I don't have that option, she said

01:37:02.699 --> 01:37:05.159
spreading her smoking talons.

01:37:05.220 --> 01:37:06.479
Roar.

01:37:06.539 --> 01:37:08.760
This would be a really good time to have

01:37:08.760 --> 01:37:10.020
a dungeon full of enemies.

01:37:10.079 --> 01:37:11.399
What?

01:37:11.520 --> 01:37:12.300
He said.

01:37:12.359 --> 01:37:13.380
Why?

01:37:13.439 --> 01:37:17.399
Because, she said, when you're mad, it's

01:37:17.399 --> 01:37:19.079
useful to have dragons around that you

01:37:19.079 --> 01:37:20.699
can set on fire without getting in

01:37:20.699 --> 01:37:20.880
trouble.

01:37:20.939 --> 01:37:22.619
He rolled his eyes.

01:37:22.680 --> 01:37:25.500
Somehow, I don't think Clay and

01:37:25.500 --> 01:37:27.119
Starflight would be pleased if you said

01:37:27.119 --> 01:37:29.579
anyone on fire, even their enemies.

01:37:29.640 --> 01:37:33.119
That makes no sense, Pearl said.

01:37:33.180 --> 01:37:35.460
Everyone wants to see their enemies on

01:37:35.460 --> 01:37:36.060
fire.

01:37:36.119 --> 01:37:38.039
Are you telling me your mother never

01:37:38.039 --> 01:37:40.140
cheered herself up by having someone

01:37:40.140 --> 01:37:41.939
torch a bunch of bad guys in front of

01:37:41.939 --> 01:37:42.119
her?

01:37:42.180 --> 01:37:45.840
Um, no, said Turtle.

01:37:45.899 --> 01:37:48.479
First of all, we're sea wings, so we

01:37:48.479 --> 01:37:49.680
don't have fire, remember?

01:37:49.739 --> 01:37:52.560
Secondly, my mother mostly cheered

01:37:52.560 --> 01:37:54.479
herself up by writing scrolls about all

01:37:54.479 --> 01:37:55.319
her problems.

01:37:55.380 --> 01:37:58.380
And third, she used her prisoners as

01:37:58.380 --> 01:38:00.119
bargaining chips, not toys.

01:38:00.180 --> 01:38:03.779
Our prisoners were definitely Scarlet's

01:38:03.779 --> 01:38:05.220
toys, Pearl said.

01:38:05.340 --> 01:38:08.039
And so were you, it sounds like.

01:38:08.100 --> 01:38:11.100
Carol snorted a burst of flame, and he

01:38:11.100 --> 01:38:11.520
jumped back.

01:38:11.579 --> 01:38:14.460
No, I was more than that.

01:38:14.520 --> 01:38:16.079
I was like a daughter to her.

01:38:16.140 --> 01:38:17.460
All right.

01:38:17.520 --> 01:38:19.979
All right, he said.

01:38:20.039 --> 01:38:22.800
So what are you going to do about Ruby

01:38:22.800 --> 01:38:24.000
and Clay and all of that?

01:38:24.060 --> 01:38:26.399
What can I do?

01:38:26.460 --> 01:38:27.300
She said.

01:38:27.420 --> 01:38:29.819
You heard Starflight?

01:38:29.880 --> 01:38:32.039
They'll never trust me with clay, and

01:38:32.039 --> 01:38:32.520
they're right.

01:38:32.579 --> 01:38:34.560
I'm not good enough for him.

01:38:34.619 --> 01:38:38.340
He's good all the way through, not just

01:38:38.340 --> 01:38:39.359
in little fragments.

01:38:39.420 --> 01:38:42.600
I mean, if Saving Clay's life wasn't

01:38:42.600 --> 01:38:44.520
enough, what else is there?

01:38:44.640 --> 01:38:47.699
I can think of one thing, he said.

01:38:47.760 --> 01:38:50.279
I bet it would make everyone forgive you

01:38:50.279 --> 01:38:51.420
even Ruby.

01:38:51.479 --> 01:38:54.300
Well, Pearl said.

01:38:54.960 --> 01:38:56.819
Yes, I thought of that.

01:38:56.880 --> 01:39:00.779
You have to kill Queen Scarlet, he said

01:39:00.779 --> 01:39:02.699
and I'm coming with you.

01:39:02.760 --> 01:39:07.079
Chapter 5.

01:39:07.380 --> 01:39:11.159
The clouds swept past them like ribbons

01:39:11.159 --> 01:39:13.560
of smoke, sliced and scattered by the

01:39:13.560 --> 01:39:14.520
slash of their wings.

01:39:14.579 --> 01:39:17.579
Below them, the claws of the clouds

01:39:17.579 --> 01:39:19.979
mountains lurked like the long, long

01:39:19.979 --> 01:39:23.579
spine of a giant sleeping dragon, black

01:39:23.579 --> 01:39:25.439
except where the craggy peaks were

01:39:25.439 --> 01:39:27.180
studded with light from the moons.

01:39:27.420 --> 01:39:30.119
Peril could see the silver flicker of the

01:39:30.119 --> 01:39:32.340
winding tail river, running along the

01:39:32.340 --> 01:39:34.020
eastern edge of the mountain range.

01:39:34.079 --> 01:39:36.420
They were about to fly over the curve

01:39:36.420 --> 01:39:38.159
where it veered east and then north

01:39:38.159 --> 01:39:38.939
again.

01:39:39.000 --> 01:39:40.920
She loved flying.

01:39:40.979 --> 01:39:43.619
And not just because she was a sky wing

01:39:43.619 --> 01:39:45.539
and all Sky Wings loved to fly.

01:39:45.600 --> 01:39:47.399
It was more than that for her.

01:39:47.460 --> 01:39:50.579
There was nothing else in her life that

01:39:50.579 --> 01:39:52.380
she could love in such a joyful

01:39:52.380 --> 01:39:53.460
uncomplicated way.

01:39:53.520 --> 01:39:56.880
Up in the sky, she could stretch her

01:39:56.880 --> 01:39:58.680
wings as wide as she wanted.

01:39:58.739 --> 01:40:02.100
She could whip her tail and dive and soar

01:40:02.100 --> 01:40:04.380
and spin, and she didn't have to keep all

01:40:04.380 --> 01:40:06.479
her limbs so carefully close to her

01:40:06.479 --> 01:40:08.579
watching her perimeter every moment.

01:40:08.640 --> 01:40:12.300
Up here, there was nothing to burn.

01:40:12.420 --> 01:40:16.199
Everyone and everything was safe from her

01:40:16.199 --> 01:40:18.060
as long as she was in the sky.

01:40:18.119 --> 01:40:21.300
At least, that was usually the case.

01:40:21.359 --> 01:40:23.760
She didn't normally have a sea wing

01:40:23.760 --> 01:40:25.140
flapping around on her tail.

01:40:25.199 --> 01:40:27.720
He was doing a reasonably good job of

01:40:27.720 --> 01:40:30.060
keeping his distance, but she felt a

01:40:30.060 --> 01:40:32.279
startled jolt every time she saw him out

01:40:32.279 --> 01:40:33.180
of the corner of her eye.

01:40:33.239 --> 01:40:36.119
Peril still wished she could have talked

01:40:36.119 --> 01:40:37.260
to Clay before she left.

01:40:37.319 --> 01:40:39.840
But she wasn't sure she could look him in

01:40:39.840 --> 01:40:41.819
the face anymore, after the conversation

01:40:41.819 --> 01:40:42.899
she'd overheard.

01:40:42.960 --> 01:40:46.079
Not until I am bringing him the charred

01:40:46.079 --> 01:40:48.060
bones of Queen Scarlet anyway.

01:40:48.119 --> 01:40:49.739
Where are we going?

01:40:49.800 --> 01:40:51.960
Turtle called from behind her.

01:40:52.020 --> 01:40:54.239
She twisted in midair to give him an

01:40:54.239 --> 01:40:55.739
incredulous look.

01:40:55.800 --> 01:40:58.260
To kill Queen Scarlet, she said.

01:40:58.319 --> 01:40:59.399
Remember?

01:40:59.579 --> 01:41:01.199
There was a whole conversation a few

01:41:01.199 --> 01:41:01.739
hours ago.

01:41:01.800 --> 01:41:04.140
I'm pretty sure you were there because I

01:41:04.140 --> 01:41:06.539
was like, you're not coming with me, and

01:41:06.539 --> 01:41:08.279
you were all, how are you going to stop

01:41:08.279 --> 01:41:08.579
me?

01:41:08.640 --> 01:41:11.159
And I was all, I can think of a pretty

01:41:11.159 --> 01:41:13.500
good way, and you were like, by setting

01:41:13.500 --> 01:41:14.340
me on fire.

01:41:14.399 --> 01:41:16.140
That sounds like cutting off your tail

01:41:16.140 --> 01:41:17.100
despite your wings.

01:41:17.159 --> 01:41:20.039
And I was like, I could cut off your tail

01:41:20.039 --> 01:41:22.140
and you were all, let's just go before

01:41:22.140 --> 01:41:23.039
Ruby comes back.

01:41:23.100 --> 01:41:24.720
All right.

01:41:24.779 --> 01:41:26.640
Turtle finally interrupted.

01:41:26.699 --> 01:41:27.720
I know all that.

01:41:27.779 --> 01:41:30.600
I mean, where are we going to kill Queen

01:41:30.600 --> 01:41:31.199
Scarlet?

01:41:31.260 --> 01:41:33.239
How do we even start looking for her?

01:41:33.300 --> 01:41:34.739
Or my sister?

01:41:34.800 --> 01:41:36.060
Oh.

01:41:36.119 --> 01:41:38.880
Carol did a looping flip in the sky.

01:41:38.939 --> 01:41:41.340
She had searched for Scarlet for months

01:41:41.340 --> 01:41:43.380
after releasing her from Burns Weirdling

01:41:43.380 --> 01:41:45.659
Tower with no success.

01:41:45.720 --> 01:41:46.800
What did she think would be different

01:41:46.800 --> 01:41:47.100
now?

01:41:47.159 --> 01:41:49.680
The mountains?

01:41:49.800 --> 01:41:53.939
she suggested Maybe we could fly around

01:41:53.939 --> 01:41:54.300
them.

01:41:54.300 --> 01:41:55.739
A lot.

01:41:55.859 --> 01:41:59.520
Forgive me for mentioning this, Turtle

01:41:59.520 --> 01:42:01.560
said, but I'm getting the impression that

01:42:01.560 --> 01:42:02.880
you're not much of a planner.

01:42:03.000 --> 01:42:05.579
What have I ever needed to plan?

01:42:05.640 --> 01:42:07.079
Peril demanded.

01:42:07.140 --> 01:42:09.060
Do you know anything about my life?

01:42:09.119 --> 01:42:10.560
Here's how it went.

01:42:10.619 --> 01:42:12.779
Wake up, eat breakfast.

01:42:12.840 --> 01:42:14.760
Queen Scarlet tells me to kill one of her

01:42:14.760 --> 01:42:15.239
prisoners.

01:42:15.300 --> 01:42:18.300
I kill that prisoner, eat dinner, go back

01:42:18.300 --> 01:42:18.659
to sleep.

01:42:18.720 --> 01:42:20.819
Pretty simple.

01:42:20.880 --> 01:42:22.500
Not a lot of big decision making

01:42:22.500 --> 01:42:23.039
involved.

01:42:23.100 --> 01:42:24.720
Really?

01:42:24.779 --> 01:42:26.100
Turtle asked.

01:42:26.159 --> 01:42:27.600
Were you happy?

01:42:27.659 --> 01:42:30.720
Peril let herself drop to a warmer air

01:42:30.720 --> 01:42:33.600
current, trying to think, happy.

01:42:33.659 --> 01:42:35.939
Was that how she'd felt back then?

01:42:36.000 --> 01:42:39.720
It was definitely easier than life after

01:42:39.720 --> 01:42:40.680
Queen Scarlet?

01:42:40.680 --> 01:42:43.800
Or rather, life after meeting Clay?

01:42:43.859 --> 01:42:47.220
In the Sky Palace, she'd had a purpose.

01:42:47.279 --> 01:42:49.859
There was a reason for her scales to be

01:42:49.859 --> 01:42:50.939
as deadly as they were.

01:42:51.000 --> 01:42:54.180
She'd been loyal to the queen, and she'd

01:42:54.180 --> 01:42:55.560
thought the queen cared about her too.

01:42:55.619 --> 01:42:57.119
Most of the time.

01:42:57.180 --> 01:42:58.920
Maybe half the time.

01:42:58.979 --> 01:43:02.039
Well, some of the time anyhow.

01:43:02.100 --> 01:43:04.380
She was probably supposed to say

01:43:04.380 --> 01:43:07.020
something about how terrible it was to

01:43:07.020 --> 01:43:10.140
kill all those dragons, how it ate her up

01:43:10.140 --> 01:43:12.479
inside every night and made her miserable

01:43:12.479 --> 01:43:14.039
but it didn't.

01:43:14.100 --> 01:43:17.100
Not back then, not while it was

01:43:17.100 --> 01:43:17.640
happening.

01:43:17.699 --> 01:43:19.800
She'd been killing dragons for Queen

01:43:19.800 --> 01:43:21.420
Scarlet for as long as she could

01:43:21.420 --> 01:43:21.840
remember.

01:43:21.899 --> 01:43:24.899
That was just... her life.

01:43:24.960 --> 01:43:28.140
I had an idea, Turtle said.

01:43:28.260 --> 01:43:30.840
I bet tsunami will head for water if

01:43:30.840 --> 01:43:31.920
she's stopped anywhere.

01:43:31.979 --> 01:43:34.079
Can we check for clues down by the

01:43:34.079 --> 01:43:34.260
river?

01:43:34.319 --> 01:43:37.319
Peril was too busy thinking to argue with

01:43:37.319 --> 01:43:37.500
him.

01:43:37.560 --> 01:43:39.899
She followed him down in a drifting

01:43:39.899 --> 01:43:42.300
spiral. until they reached a rocky spot

01:43:42.300 --> 01:43:43.199
along the riverbank.

01:43:43.319 --> 01:43:46.319
Turtle landed in the water with a splash

01:43:46.319 --> 01:43:48.720
while peril came down gently on the

01:43:48.720 --> 01:43:48.960
shore.

01:43:49.020 --> 01:43:51.600
She'd tried to aim for a spot with

01:43:51.600 --> 01:43:54.119
nothing but rocks and sand, but her tail

01:43:54.119 --> 01:43:55.739
accidentally flicked against a small

01:43:55.739 --> 01:43:57.180
shrub growing near the water.

01:43:57.239 --> 01:44:00.359
It instantly burst into flames, and

01:44:00.359 --> 01:44:02.340
almost as quickly burned out into a

01:44:02.340 --> 01:44:04.560
blackened heap, shriveled branches

01:44:04.560 --> 01:44:06.720
sticking out of it like skeletal claws.

01:44:06.779 --> 01:44:10.739
Ach, Pearl said, curling her tail in.

01:44:10.800 --> 01:44:11.760
Sorry.

01:44:11.819 --> 01:44:15.180
Turtle blinked at the planned, but didn't

01:44:15.180 --> 01:44:15.600
say anything.

01:44:15.659 --> 01:44:17.819
He stuck his nose in the river and then

01:44:17.819 --> 01:44:20.039
shook it, spraying droplets everywhere.

01:44:20.100 --> 01:44:23.159
A few hit peril, sizzling on her scales.

01:44:23.220 --> 01:44:25.319
Maybe I wasn't happy.

01:44:25.380 --> 01:44:26.760
She blurted.

01:44:26.819 --> 01:44:29.939
He looked startled and a little confused

01:44:29.939 --> 01:44:31.680
as if he'd forgotten what they were

01:44:31.680 --> 01:44:32.100
talking about.

01:44:32.159 --> 01:44:34.859
She couldn't stop herself from barreling

01:44:34.859 --> 01:44:35.279
on, though.

01:44:35.340 --> 01:44:38.039
But I also wasn't so worried all the

01:44:38.039 --> 01:44:38.460
time.

01:44:38.520 --> 01:44:41.640
I only had one dragon to please, and I

01:44:41.640 --> 01:44:44.039
didn't always manage that, but at least I

01:44:44.039 --> 01:44:46.140
understood what I needed to do.

01:44:46.199 --> 01:44:47.880
Now everything is confusing.

01:44:47.939 --> 01:44:49.979
I guess.

01:44:50.100 --> 01:44:52.260
I mean, which would you rather be?

01:44:52.319 --> 01:44:53.699
Lonely?

01:44:53.760 --> 01:44:54.600
or insecure?

01:44:54.659 --> 01:44:57.659
The seawing spread his wings across the

01:44:57.659 --> 01:44:59.880
surface of the water, sending ripples out

01:44:59.880 --> 01:45:01.500
in all directions.

01:45:01.560 --> 01:45:03.359
Well, he said.

01:45:03.420 --> 01:45:07.260
I've tried lonely, so maybe I'd pick

01:45:07.260 --> 01:45:08.340
insecure.

01:45:08.399 --> 01:45:12.300
He pounced suddenly, sending a cascade of

01:45:12.300 --> 01:45:14.579
water over Parel's talons, and then sat

01:45:14.579 --> 01:45:17.279
up, brandishing a fish speared on one of

01:45:17.279 --> 01:45:17.819
his claws.

01:45:17.880 --> 01:45:19.079
Hungry?

01:45:19.140 --> 01:45:21.899
No thanks, Pearl said.

01:45:21.960 --> 01:45:23.819
She glanced up and down the river.

01:45:23.939 --> 01:45:26.819
Two of the moons were up, so she could

01:45:26.819 --> 01:45:28.920
see the outline of trees on the far side

01:45:28.920 --> 01:45:30.899
and the small flutterings of owls

01:45:30.899 --> 01:45:32.460
swooping through hunting.

01:45:32.520 --> 01:45:35.760
Turtle began splashing upriver, and peril

01:45:35.760 --> 01:45:38.100
followed him, pacing along the river bank

01:45:38.100 --> 01:45:39.600
and avoiding anything that looked

01:45:39.600 --> 01:45:40.199
flammable.

01:45:40.260 --> 01:45:42.840
Maybe we should head to possibility.

01:45:42.899 --> 01:45:44.279
Turtle said.

01:45:44.340 --> 01:45:46.800
We can meet up with Moon and Kibley there

01:45:46.859 --> 01:45:49.680
and find out what happened to Winter and

01:45:49.680 --> 01:45:50.579
Kinkaju.

01:45:50.640 --> 01:45:53.159
His voice hitched slightly on the last

01:45:53.159 --> 01:45:55.680
word, and peril gave him a sharp look.

01:45:55.739 --> 01:45:57.420
What was that?

01:45:57.479 --> 01:45:58.380
she demanded.

01:45:58.439 --> 01:46:00.060
Are you about to cry?

01:46:00.119 --> 01:46:04.619
No, he said, biting a head off the fish.

01:46:04.680 --> 01:46:08.399
I'm just worried about them They're safer

01:46:08.399 --> 01:46:09.960
in possibility than anywhere.

01:46:10.020 --> 01:46:10.979
Pearl said.

01:46:11.039 --> 01:46:13.739
It's a town full of dragons, and more

01:46:13.739 --> 01:46:15.359
than half of them aren't too fond of

01:46:15.359 --> 01:46:16.199
Queen Scarlet.

01:46:16.260 --> 01:46:19.439
At least, they really, really don't like

01:46:19.439 --> 01:46:20.340
being asked about her.

01:46:20.399 --> 01:46:23.279
They tend to throw things, which they

01:46:23.279 --> 01:46:25.380
also do when you set even the smallest

01:46:25.380 --> 01:46:27.060
basket of snails on fire.

01:46:27.119 --> 01:46:28.859
By accident, mind you.

01:46:28.979 --> 01:46:31.319
Frankly, I think they should rename the

01:46:31.319 --> 01:46:33.960
place unnecessary violent overreaction.

01:46:34.020 --> 01:46:36.060
In the moonlight.

01:46:36.119 --> 01:46:38.039
She couldn't tell if turtle's expression

01:46:38.039 --> 01:46:39.899
was concerned or mildly amused.

01:46:40.020 --> 01:46:43.859
Anyway, she went on, I'm not looking for

01:46:43.859 --> 01:46:44.699
an entourage.

01:46:44.760 --> 01:46:46.920
If I take more dragons with me to face

01:46:46.920 --> 01:46:49.680
Queen Scarlet, it just means more dragons

01:46:49.680 --> 01:46:50.279
for her to kill.

01:46:50.340 --> 01:46:53.279
Is that what you think is going to happen

01:46:53.279 --> 01:46:53.699
to me?

01:46:53.760 --> 01:46:54.600
he asked.

01:46:54.659 --> 01:46:57.060
Probably, she said.

01:46:57.119 --> 01:47:00.720
I mean, wait, what's the reassuring thing

01:47:00.720 --> 01:47:01.020
to say?

01:47:01.079 --> 01:47:03.840
No, he said.

01:47:03.899 --> 01:47:05.579
That one's pretty easy.

01:47:05.640 --> 01:47:08.220
The correct answer is no.

01:47:08.279 --> 01:47:10.319
Oh, she said.

01:47:10.439 --> 01:47:11.399
Okay, that.

01:47:11.460 --> 01:47:14.460
But Moon and Kibli might know where

01:47:14.460 --> 01:47:15.060
Scarlet is.

01:47:15.180 --> 01:47:16.800
Turtle pointed out.

01:47:16.920 --> 01:47:19.500
A choir of yawping frogs had been

01:47:19.500 --> 01:47:21.659
burbling away nearby, but cut off

01:47:21.659 --> 01:47:23.579
abruptly as the dragons approached.

01:47:23.640 --> 01:47:26.279
Ruby said they told Sonny something about

01:47:26.279 --> 01:47:27.720
a new ally of hers.

01:47:27.779 --> 01:47:28.260
Remember?

01:47:28.380 --> 01:47:30.000
Peril frowned.

01:47:30.060 --> 01:47:32.760
How could Queen Scarlet have a new ally?

01:47:32.819 --> 01:47:34.260
Who was it?

01:47:34.319 --> 01:47:35.819
And where did he come from?

01:47:35.880 --> 01:47:39.000
Does she like him more than me?

01:47:39.060 --> 01:47:41.579
She called herself with a stamp of

01:47:41.579 --> 01:47:44.399
annoyance that sent sparks flying off one

01:47:44.399 --> 01:47:45.359
of the stones underfoot?

01:47:45.420 --> 01:47:47.939
Of course, Scarlet would like her new

01:47:47.939 --> 01:47:49.199
ally more than peril.

01:47:49.260 --> 01:47:51.720
Whoever it was must have agreed to help

01:47:51.720 --> 01:47:52.979
her when peril wouldn't.

01:47:53.039 --> 01:47:56.460
Also, more importantly, peril shouldn't

01:47:56.460 --> 01:47:57.000
care anymore.

01:47:57.060 --> 01:48:00.060
It was habit to want Scarlet to like her

01:48:00.060 --> 01:48:02.760
more than anyone, but it was a bad habit

01:48:02.760 --> 01:48:05.159
and she wished she could scour it out of

01:48:05.159 --> 01:48:05.819
her brain.

01:48:05.880 --> 01:48:07.619
The new ally.

01:48:07.680 --> 01:48:10.020
Was it an animus dragon?

01:48:10.079 --> 01:48:12.239
The one who had enchanted the severed

01:48:12.239 --> 01:48:12.479
head?

01:48:12.539 --> 01:48:15.239
Did that mean other magic was lurking up

01:48:15.239 --> 01:48:15.720
ahead for them?

01:48:15.779 --> 01:48:17.880
Um...

01:48:17.880 --> 01:48:20.579
Does it seem quieter than it should be?

01:48:20.640 --> 01:48:23.640
Turtle asked, pausing in the center of

01:48:23.640 --> 01:48:24.000
the river.

01:48:24.060 --> 01:48:26.340
Peril stopped and listened too.

01:48:26.399 --> 01:48:29.579
The water shivered softly around turtles

01:48:29.579 --> 01:48:31.979
talons, as if it were trying to echo the

01:48:31.979 --> 01:48:33.720
rustling leaves in the wind overhead.

01:48:33.779 --> 01:48:37.800
But there were no more owls swooping, no

01:48:37.800 --> 01:48:38.880
frogs glurping.

01:48:38.939 --> 01:48:41.579
It seemed as though even the insects had

01:48:41.579 --> 01:48:42.239
fallen silent.

01:48:42.300 --> 01:48:46.439
Peril slowly twisted in place, scanning

01:48:46.439 --> 01:48:48.600
the dark trees, wishing she had night

01:48:48.600 --> 01:48:49.079
vision.

01:48:49.140 --> 01:48:52.079
Was that a glimmer of silver scales off

01:48:52.079 --> 01:48:52.560
to the left?

01:48:52.619 --> 01:48:55.560
Did she just imagine the crack of a

01:48:55.560 --> 01:48:57.119
branch snapping under talons?

01:48:57.239 --> 01:49:00.060
Could she smell a hint of smoke on the

01:49:00.060 --> 01:49:00.239
air?

01:49:00.300 --> 01:49:04.140
And then, all of a sudden, the river

01:49:04.140 --> 01:49:04.979
exploded.

01:49:05.039 --> 01:49:08.819
Turtle let out a yell of fright as 3

01:49:08.819 --> 01:49:11.159
dragons burst out of the water almost

01:49:11.159 --> 01:49:12.779
directly beneath his talons.

01:49:12.840 --> 01:49:15.539
They seized his wings and tail, and

01:49:15.539 --> 01:49:17.399
pinned him down with a violent splash

01:49:17.399 --> 01:49:19.979
that cascaded over Peril's scales.

01:49:20.039 --> 01:49:23.819
At the same moment, 2 more dragons flew

01:49:23.819 --> 01:49:25.680
out of the forest, their claws

01:49:25.680 --> 01:49:27.359
outstretched and teeth bared.

01:49:27.479 --> 01:49:30.600
Carol whirled to face them, flinging her

01:49:30.600 --> 01:49:31.020
wings open.

01:49:31.079 --> 01:49:32.880
Try to grab me.

01:49:32.939 --> 01:49:34.199
Just try.

01:49:34.319 --> 01:49:36.899
A dazzling thrill darted through her like

01:49:36.899 --> 01:49:37.380
lightning.

01:49:37.439 --> 01:49:39.720
These dragons were attacking her.

01:49:39.779 --> 01:49:42.359
She could totally set them on fire

01:49:42.359 --> 01:49:43.859
without getting in trouble.

01:49:43.920 --> 01:49:46.319
I'm not being bad, Clay.

01:49:46.380 --> 01:49:47.819
I'm just defending myself.

01:49:47.880 --> 01:49:51.300
She flexed her talons and tried to squash

01:49:51.300 --> 01:49:51.899
her grin.

01:49:51.960 --> 01:49:55.500
Don't touch her, turtle bellowed

01:49:55.500 --> 01:49:57.659
thrashing around like a vomiting whale.

01:49:57.720 --> 01:49:58.979
It'll kill you.

01:49:59.039 --> 01:50:00.659
Her scales are fire.

01:50:00.720 --> 01:50:04.020
The 2 dragons skidded to a stop just out

01:50:04.020 --> 01:50:04.859
of her reach.

01:50:04.920 --> 01:50:07.680
Their claws left grooves in the pebbled

01:50:07.680 --> 01:50:10.020
sand, and their wings flung a blanket of

01:50:10.020 --> 01:50:10.979
hot air in her direction.

01:50:11.039 --> 01:50:14.279
Way to spoil my fun, turtle.

01:50:14.399 --> 01:50:16.739
Although, yes, fine.

01:50:16.800 --> 01:50:18.720
Warning them was probably the clay

01:50:18.720 --> 01:50:20.220
approved thing to do.

01:50:20.279 --> 01:50:24.060
He's right, she said, glowering at her

01:50:24.060 --> 01:50:24.600
attackers.

01:50:24.659 --> 01:50:27.060
I am peril of the sky wings.

01:50:27.119 --> 01:50:28.439
Perhaps you've heard of me?

01:50:28.500 --> 01:50:31.859
One of the dragons was a big red sky wing

01:50:31.859 --> 01:50:34.079
and Perel definitely saw her flinch and

01:50:34.079 --> 01:50:34.800
take a step back.

01:50:34.859 --> 01:50:37.199
But if you'd like to find out whether

01:50:37.199 --> 01:50:39.600
he's telling the truth, come a bit closer

01:50:39.600 --> 01:50:42.180
and we can do a fun experiment.

01:50:42.239 --> 01:50:45.420
She spread her wet front talons in front

01:50:45.420 --> 01:50:48.060
of her, and smiled wickedly at the coils

01:50:48.060 --> 01:50:49.680
of steam still rising from them.

01:50:49.739 --> 01:50:53.039
It's true, said the sky wing.

01:50:53.100 --> 01:50:54.779
I recognize her now.

01:50:54.840 --> 01:50:56.279
Stay back, Sirius.

01:50:56.340 --> 01:50:59.399
The other dragon, a severe looking ice

01:50:59.399 --> 01:51:02.579
wing, gave peril a scornful look, as if

01:51:02.579 --> 01:51:04.859
he highly doubted anyone, even a fire

01:51:04.859 --> 01:51:07.260
scales dragon could possibly be a match

01:51:07.260 --> 01:51:07.680
for him.

01:51:07.739 --> 01:51:13.020
Ooh, please try it, peril thought, giving

01:51:13.020 --> 01:51:14.340
him an innocent expression.

01:51:14.460 --> 01:51:17.039
So it's not scarlet.

01:51:17.159 --> 01:51:19.319
Asked one of the sea wings.

01:51:19.380 --> 01:51:21.659
The Skywing lashed her tail.

01:51:21.720 --> 01:51:24.539
No, this is peril, who might be worse.

01:51:24.659 --> 01:51:28.800
I beg your pardon, said peril, genuinely

01:51:28.800 --> 01:51:29.340
offended.

01:51:29.399 --> 01:51:30.960
Maybe you haven't heard?

01:51:31.020 --> 01:51:33.420
I'm friends with the dragonettes of

01:51:33.420 --> 01:51:34.020
destiny now.

01:51:34.079 --> 01:51:36.180
I don't set other dragons on fire

01:51:36.180 --> 01:51:37.020
anymore.

01:51:37.079 --> 01:51:40.439
Not unless they provoke me, she added

01:51:40.500 --> 01:51:42.720
shooting the ice wing of fierce glare.

01:51:42.840 --> 01:51:46.020
That is one of the rumors going around

01:51:46.020 --> 01:51:49.020
said the Sky Wing, but we all know a

01:51:49.020 --> 01:51:50.819
dragon can't change her scales.

01:51:50.939 --> 01:51:56.039
Maybe not, but I can change my mind, peril

01:51:56.039 --> 01:51:59.220
said defiantly, unlike some dragons

01:51:59.220 --> 01:51:59.760
apparently.

01:51:59.760 --> 01:52:01.920
I've not only heard of you, little

01:52:01.920 --> 01:52:04.079
monster, said the sky wing.

01:52:04.199 --> 01:52:06.600
I was one of the guards sent after your

01:52:06.600 --> 01:52:08.039
mother when she tried to escape with

01:52:08.039 --> 01:52:08.220
you.

01:52:08.279 --> 01:52:11.880
She took a step toward peril, lashing her

01:52:11.880 --> 01:52:13.079
tail and looking murderous.

01:52:13.140 --> 01:52:17.279
Avalanche, one of the sea wings said

01:52:17.279 --> 01:52:17.819
softly.

01:52:17.880 --> 01:52:19.319
Careful.

01:52:19.380 --> 01:52:24.060
My biggest regret, said avalanche, smoke

01:52:24.060 --> 01:52:25.739
billowing from her mouth and ears.

01:52:25.859 --> 01:52:27.840
Is that we didn't kill you then?

01:52:27.899 --> 01:52:30.539
I don't care that Kestrel got away.

01:52:30.600 --> 01:52:32.819
But if I'd known Scarlet would keep you

01:52:32.819 --> 01:52:33.119
alive.

01:52:33.239 --> 01:52:37.859
Wait, said Cyrus, flaring his silver

01:52:37.859 --> 01:52:38.640
white wings.

01:52:38.699 --> 01:52:41.220
Did you say kestrel?

01:52:41.340 --> 01:52:43.920
Avalanche gave him an irritated look.

01:52:43.979 --> 01:52:46.140
Yes, what?

01:52:46.260 --> 01:52:49.199
Kestrel of the sky wings.

01:52:49.260 --> 01:52:50.760
Sarah said.

01:52:50.819 --> 01:52:54.300
Big, red, grumpy looking.

01:52:54.359 --> 01:52:57.840
You've just described 50% of all Skywings

01:52:57.840 --> 01:52:59.640
said the mudwing, sitting on top of

01:52:59.640 --> 01:53:00.060
turtle.

01:53:00.119 --> 01:53:03.899
The other half is big, orange, and grumpy

01:53:03.899 --> 01:53:04.199
looking.

01:53:04.319 --> 01:53:07.380
What does she have to do with anything?

01:53:07.500 --> 01:53:09.060
Cyrus asked.

01:53:09.119 --> 01:53:11.939
She was this creature's mother.

01:53:12.000 --> 01:53:14.760
Avalanche said, the one who wouldn't hand

01:53:14.760 --> 01:53:15.659
her over to be killed.

01:53:15.720 --> 01:53:19.439
Cyrus frowned, carving deep canyons

01:53:19.439 --> 01:53:20.640
across his forehead.

01:53:20.699 --> 01:53:22.199
That can't be right.

01:53:22.260 --> 01:53:25.560
Kestrel never had any dragonettes.

01:53:25.619 --> 01:53:27.420
Ha!

01:53:27.479 --> 01:53:28.859
Avalanche muttered.

01:53:28.920 --> 01:53:31.020
We all wish that were true.

01:53:31.079 --> 01:53:33.239
Did you know her?

01:53:33.300 --> 01:53:35.340
Harold asked Sirius.

01:53:35.399 --> 01:53:37.920
He was shaking his head, but there was

01:53:37.920 --> 01:53:39.899
something weird in his expression.

01:53:39.960 --> 01:53:41.640
I doubt you would have met.

01:53:41.760 --> 01:53:44.640
Said the sea wing who'd spoken before.

01:53:44.699 --> 01:53:47.699
She joined the talons of peace before you

01:53:47.699 --> 01:53:49.859
did, and then she was assigned to

01:53:49.859 --> 01:53:51.779
guarding the dragonettes underground

01:53:51.779 --> 01:53:52.800
before you came to us.

01:53:52.920 --> 01:53:55.680
Once the guardians went into hiding with

01:53:55.680 --> 01:53:56.159
the eggs.

01:53:56.220 --> 01:53:58.560
Most of the talons of peace never saw

01:53:58.560 --> 01:53:58.800
them.

01:53:58.859 --> 01:54:00.600
But you did?

01:54:00.720 --> 01:54:03.060
Peril asked the ice wing again.

01:54:03.180 --> 01:54:06.779
Cyrus looked as if a pile of ashes was

01:54:06.779 --> 01:54:09.000
slowly turning back into a dragon right

01:54:09.000 --> 01:54:11.520
in front of his eyes, but was he happy?

01:54:11.579 --> 01:54:12.779
Angry?

01:54:12.779 --> 01:54:14.460
confused?

01:54:14.520 --> 01:54:16.380
She couldn't tell what he even thought

01:54:16.380 --> 01:54:18.779
about Kestrel, although he was clearly

01:54:18.779 --> 01:54:19.500
feeling something.

01:54:19.560 --> 01:54:21.600
No.

01:54:21.659 --> 01:54:24.420
He said, shaking his head again more

01:54:24.420 --> 01:54:25.020
vigorously.

01:54:25.079 --> 01:54:26.399
Not.

01:54:26.520 --> 01:54:29.880
That is, only by reputation.

01:54:29.939 --> 01:54:32.460
Peril wondered if he was lying.

01:54:32.579 --> 01:54:34.920
But how could an ice wing have known her

01:54:34.920 --> 01:54:35.220
mother?

01:54:35.279 --> 01:54:37.380
If they didn't meet in the talons of

01:54:37.380 --> 01:54:37.619
peace.

01:54:37.680 --> 01:54:40.680
Can I get back to my menacing story now?

01:54:40.739 --> 01:54:42.300
Avalanche demanded.

01:54:42.359 --> 01:54:46.020
Oh, let me skip to the ending, Peril

01:54:46.020 --> 01:54:46.319
said.

01:54:46.380 --> 01:54:49.199
You failed to catch or kill my mother as

01:54:49.199 --> 01:54:49.800
she escaped.

01:54:49.859 --> 01:54:51.060
You were punished.

01:54:51.119 --> 01:54:53.340
Then you discovered that I was still

01:54:53.340 --> 01:54:55.859
alive, instead of flung off a cliff like

01:54:55.859 --> 01:54:58.859
most fire scales dragonettes, and you've

01:54:58.859 --> 01:55:00.600
been seething about it ever since.

01:55:00.659 --> 01:55:03.539
Which is funny because I have never had

01:55:03.539 --> 01:55:05.819
even one thought about you in my entire

01:55:05.819 --> 01:55:06.239
life.

01:55:06.300 --> 01:55:09.539
Avalanche glowered at her for a long

01:55:09.539 --> 01:55:10.079
moment.

01:55:10.140 --> 01:55:13.560
Peril flicked her tail gently, casually

01:55:13.560 --> 01:55:16.199
and a clump of reeds burst into flames

01:55:16.199 --> 01:55:16.680
behind her.

01:55:16.739 --> 01:55:19.739
Oops, she said.

01:55:19.800 --> 01:55:22.680
There was something very satisfying about

01:55:22.680 --> 01:55:24.840
how the sea wings yelped and went

01:55:24.840 --> 01:55:27.539
scrambling around, splashing water over

01:55:27.539 --> 01:55:28.619
the fire with their wings.

01:55:28.680 --> 01:55:31.920
Of course, peril had really done it to

01:55:31.920 --> 01:55:34.319
see that expression of powerless fury on

01:55:34.319 --> 01:55:35.460
avalanches' face.

01:55:35.520 --> 01:55:38.939
Are you in league with Scarlet?

01:55:39.000 --> 01:55:40.380
One of the sea wings asked breathlessly

01:55:40.380 --> 01:55:41.159
when the fire was out.

01:55:41.220 --> 01:55:43.800
We heard she was recently seen not far

01:55:43.800 --> 01:55:44.159
from here.

01:55:44.220 --> 01:55:45.659
Do you know where she is?

01:55:45.720 --> 01:55:48.720
No, peril snapped.

01:55:48.779 --> 01:55:52.439
We're looking for her too, turtle

01:55:52.439 --> 01:55:52.920
offered.

01:55:52.979 --> 01:55:55.380
His voice muffled by the mud winged tail

01:55:55.380 --> 01:55:56.399
draped across his face.

01:55:56.460 --> 01:56:01.020
I mean, he added hastily, not to join her

01:56:01.020 --> 01:56:03.000
to, uh, kill her and stuff.

01:56:03.060 --> 01:56:06.539
We need to have a chat about oversharing

01:56:06.539 --> 01:56:07.079
turtle.

01:56:07.140 --> 01:56:09.659
Who are you?

01:56:09.720 --> 01:56:12.300
Pearl demanded, hoping to turn the tables

01:56:12.300 --> 01:56:12.840
on them?

01:56:12.960 --> 01:56:15.899
We're from the talons of peace.

01:56:15.960 --> 01:56:19.260
My name is Nautilus, said the green

01:56:19.260 --> 01:56:21.479
seawing, who done the most talking.

01:56:21.539 --> 01:56:24.300
We spotted you flying, and we've been

01:56:24.300 --> 01:56:25.260
tracking you for a while.

01:56:25.319 --> 01:56:27.779
There are several groups out looking for

01:56:27.779 --> 01:56:29.340
an orange sky wing tonight.

01:56:29.399 --> 01:56:33.720
Since I'm clearly not Scarlet, said

01:56:33.720 --> 01:56:36.840
Turtle's squash sounding voice, is there

01:56:36.840 --> 01:56:38.220
any chance I could get up now?

01:56:38.279 --> 01:56:40.920
Oh, yes, sorry.

01:56:40.979 --> 01:56:43.739
Nautilus flicked his tail at the other 2

01:56:43.739 --> 01:56:45.539
dragons, motioning them away.

01:56:45.600 --> 01:56:48.180
The mud wings scowled as she heaved

01:56:48.180 --> 01:56:49.439
herself off turtle's wings.

01:56:49.500 --> 01:56:52.020
How did you know Scarlet was around?

01:56:52.079 --> 01:56:53.340
Turtle asked.

01:56:53.399 --> 01:56:55.500
Stretching his wings and neck with little

01:56:55.500 --> 01:56:56.460
crackling noises?

01:56:56.520 --> 01:56:58.140
Did someone see her?

01:56:58.199 --> 01:57:02.039
One of your alleged friends, in fact

01:57:02.039 --> 01:57:04.380
avalanche sneered at peril.

01:57:04.439 --> 01:57:08.100
Tsunami tried to chase her, but when she

01:57:08.100 --> 01:57:09.659
lost Scarlet not far from here.

01:57:09.720 --> 01:57:12.779
She came to the talons of peace for extra

01:57:12.779 --> 01:57:13.319
help.

01:57:13.380 --> 01:57:15.960
Nautilus puffed up his chest.

01:57:16.020 --> 01:57:19.439
With all of us looking, Scarlet won't get

01:57:19.439 --> 01:57:19.619
far.

01:57:19.739 --> 01:57:23.039
Tsunami is with you, turtle blurted.

01:57:23.159 --> 01:57:23.939
Where?

01:57:24.000 --> 01:57:24.840
Can we see her?

01:57:24.899 --> 01:57:26.100
We have a message for her.

01:57:26.159 --> 01:57:29.699
She's out hunting Scarlet with riptide in

01:57:29.699 --> 01:57:30.539
his group right now.

01:57:30.600 --> 01:57:32.579
Nautilus said haughtily.

01:57:32.640 --> 01:57:34.800
But I can pass along anything you want

01:57:34.800 --> 01:57:35.220
her to know.

01:57:35.279 --> 01:57:36.720
All right.

01:57:36.779 --> 01:57:40.560
Tell her glory isn't dead, Turtle said.

01:57:40.619 --> 01:57:42.300
Tell her it was a trick.

01:57:42.359 --> 01:57:44.220
It was a different dragon.

01:57:44.279 --> 01:57:45.840
Glory is fine.

01:57:45.960 --> 01:57:48.180
You have to tell her that as soon as

01:57:48.180 --> 01:57:48.539
possible.

01:57:48.659 --> 01:57:53.340
Nautilus and Avalanche exchanged glances

01:57:53.340 --> 01:57:55.439
and peril realized that now they believed

01:57:55.439 --> 01:57:55.739
them.

01:57:55.800 --> 01:57:59.220
So maybe Turtle's forest fire approach to

01:57:59.220 --> 01:58:01.380
blathering information was not so

01:58:01.380 --> 01:58:02.100
terrible after all.

01:58:02.159 --> 01:58:05.880
Oh, go, said the other Seawing.

01:58:05.939 --> 01:58:07.859
I think I know where their patrol went.

01:58:07.920 --> 01:58:10.619
He spread his wings and took off from the

01:58:10.619 --> 01:58:13.319
water in one smooth motion, like a small

01:58:13.319 --> 01:58:15.539
island suddenly whisking into the sky.

01:58:15.659 --> 01:58:19.560
Nautilus watched him go, but peril saw

01:58:19.560 --> 01:58:22.140
that the ice wing, Sirius, still had his

01:58:22.140 --> 01:58:23.159
glittering eyes on her.

01:58:23.220 --> 01:58:26.760
Are you wondering if my fire works on ice

01:58:26.760 --> 01:58:27.720
wing scales?

01:58:27.779 --> 01:58:28.560
She asked him.

01:58:28.619 --> 01:58:30.180
The answer is yes.

01:58:30.239 --> 01:58:33.659
Your wings and talons and face will melt

01:58:33.659 --> 01:58:35.819
and shrivel into ash just like anyone

01:58:35.819 --> 01:58:36.300
else's.

01:58:36.420 --> 01:58:37.859
I know from experience.

01:58:37.920 --> 01:58:41.460
We're not going to release them into the

01:58:41.460 --> 01:58:42.000
wild.

01:58:42.119 --> 01:58:44.880
Sarah's hissed at the others, ignoring

01:58:44.880 --> 01:58:45.060
her.

01:58:45.119 --> 01:58:47.340
You said it yourself.

01:58:47.399 --> 01:58:50.340
She's even more dangerous than Scarlet.

01:58:50.399 --> 01:58:55.439
Wow, you have a very confused and amusing

01:58:55.439 --> 01:58:57.720
view of this situation, Pearl said.

01:58:57.779 --> 01:58:59.640
We're not your prisoners.

01:58:59.699 --> 01:59:02.159
You couldn't take me a prisoner even with

01:59:02.159 --> 01:59:05.220
an army of ice wings, not even if all of

01:59:05.220 --> 01:59:07.020
them had arrogant foreheads like yours.

01:59:07.079 --> 01:59:10.380
There isn't actually a world in which you

01:59:10.380 --> 01:59:12.899
need to decide whether to release me.

01:59:12.960 --> 01:59:16.560
I released myself a long time ago, but

01:59:16.560 --> 01:59:17.159
thanks anyway.

01:59:17.220 --> 01:59:19.979
She thought she was actually showing

01:59:19.979 --> 01:59:22.020
remarkably noble restraint here.

01:59:22.079 --> 01:59:24.420
He was basically asking to have his

01:59:24.420 --> 01:59:25.800
talents scorched off.

01:59:25.920 --> 01:59:29.640
We have no reason to hold them. said

01:59:29.640 --> 01:59:30.300
Nautilus.

01:59:30.359 --> 01:59:34.140
Especially since you literally can't

01:59:34.140 --> 01:59:35.579
peril pointed out.

01:59:35.640 --> 01:59:38.100
Maybe she needed to set something else on

01:59:38.100 --> 01:59:39.180
fire to make this point.

01:59:39.239 --> 01:59:42.659
Hey, we're all on the same side here

01:59:42.659 --> 01:59:43.920
Turtle said.

01:59:43.979 --> 01:59:47.460
Avalanche snorted, sending tiny puffs of

01:59:47.460 --> 01:59:48.600
smoke out of her ears.

01:59:48.659 --> 01:59:51.000
We all want to catch Scarlet.

01:59:51.060 --> 01:59:54.600
And where are you going to look for her?

01:59:54.720 --> 01:59:56.640
Siri demanded.

01:59:56.699 --> 02:00:00.060
We're going to possibility first, said

02:00:00.060 --> 02:00:00.479
Turtle.

02:00:00.539 --> 02:00:04.079
Not that it's any of your business, Peril

02:00:04.079 --> 02:00:06.119
said, giving Turtle a stern look.

02:00:06.180 --> 02:00:10.439
To find our friends, Turtle added, as if

02:00:10.439 --> 02:00:12.960
stern looks completely meant nothing in

02:00:12.960 --> 02:00:15.960
his universe, please tell tsunami that

02:00:15.960 --> 02:00:16.140
too.

02:00:16.260 --> 02:00:19.380
We will, said Nautilus.

02:00:19.439 --> 02:00:21.539
He nudged one of turtles' wings with

02:00:21.539 --> 02:00:21.779
his.

02:00:21.840 --> 02:00:24.659
It was one of those casual things peril

02:00:24.659 --> 02:00:26.699
saw dragons due to other members of their

02:00:26.699 --> 02:00:27.720
tribes all the time.

02:00:27.779 --> 02:00:30.779
In this case, it was the kind of touch

02:00:30.779 --> 02:00:33.180
that she guessed meant, we're both sea

02:00:33.180 --> 02:00:34.979
wings, so in the end we'll stick

02:00:34.979 --> 02:00:35.279
together.

02:00:35.340 --> 02:00:39.000
Nobody had ever nudged peril that way.

02:00:39.060 --> 02:00:41.340
Apart from the fact that it would

02:00:41.340 --> 02:00:42.359
probably kill them.

02:00:42.420 --> 02:00:44.579
No other Sky Wing had ever wanted to

02:00:44.579 --> 02:00:46.199
acknowledge that they were in the same

02:00:46.199 --> 02:00:46.500
tribe.

02:00:46.560 --> 02:00:49.260
There was this whole language of nudges

02:00:49.260 --> 02:00:51.779
and tail flicks and wing brushing that

02:00:51.779 --> 02:00:52.560
peril couldn't speak.

02:00:52.619 --> 02:00:54.600
Except with clay.

02:00:54.659 --> 02:00:57.960
But trying to speak it with clay, made

02:00:57.960 --> 02:00:59.939
her feel like a dragon with no tongue and

02:00:59.939 --> 02:01:00.659
no ears.

02:01:00.720 --> 02:01:03.119
What did it mean when he brushed her wing

02:01:03.119 --> 02:01:05.039
with his as he went by in the tunnels?

02:01:05.100 --> 02:01:08.220
Did it mean, I love you as much as you

02:01:08.220 --> 02:01:10.560
love me, even if our deep, powerful

02:01:10.560 --> 02:01:13.020
feelings cannot be expressed aloud?

02:01:13.079 --> 02:01:15.479
Or don't worry.

02:01:15.539 --> 02:01:18.479
I see how nervous you are, but remember

02:01:18.479 --> 02:01:19.859
I'm always here to take care of you.

02:01:19.920 --> 02:01:24.600
Or it's a dark world, peril, but you and

02:01:24.600 --> 02:01:26.279
I will stand in the fire and be safe

02:01:26.279 --> 02:01:28.380
because we have each other.

02:01:28.439 --> 02:01:31.260
Sometimes she worried that it just meant

02:01:31.260 --> 02:01:32.399
hey.

02:01:32.520 --> 02:01:34.619
But she couldn't ask him.

02:01:34.680 --> 02:01:36.840
She couldn't let him know that she was

02:01:36.840 --> 02:01:39.000
even weirder and more confused than he

02:01:39.000 --> 02:01:39.779
realized.

02:01:39.960 --> 02:01:42.840
Good luck, Nautilus said.

02:01:42.899 --> 02:01:45.239
You too, said Turtle.

02:01:45.359 --> 02:01:47.100
I hope you die.

02:01:47.159 --> 02:01:49.020
Avalanche said to peril.

02:01:49.079 --> 02:01:52.439
I would say it's mutual, said peril

02:01:52.439 --> 02:01:54.659
except that I'm going to forget you exist

02:01:54.659 --> 02:01:57.180
in about a minute, so I don't actually

02:01:57.180 --> 02:01:57.539
care.

02:01:57.600 --> 02:02:00.840
She was rewarded for that brilliance with

02:02:00.840 --> 02:02:03.000
another expression of helpless rage.

02:02:03.060 --> 02:02:06.000
That's right, you self-righteous fish

02:02:06.000 --> 02:02:06.779
nose.

02:02:06.840 --> 02:02:09.239
I learned a few things from Queen Scarlet

02:02:09.239 --> 02:02:11.520
who could burn dragons without touching

02:02:11.520 --> 02:02:11.699
them.

02:02:11.760 --> 02:02:15.239
Shooting a scornful look at avalanche and

02:02:15.239 --> 02:02:17.760
cirrus, peril leaped into the sky with

02:02:17.760 --> 02:02:19.020
turtle not far behind her.

02:02:19.079 --> 02:02:22.380
As she wheeled to fly north, she thought

02:02:22.380 --> 02:02:24.119
about what she'd said to avalanche.

02:02:24.180 --> 02:02:26.579
I'll forget you exist in a minute.

02:02:26.640 --> 02:02:28.140
I don't actually care.

02:02:28.199 --> 02:02:31.020
If only it were true.

02:02:31.140 --> 02:02:35.279
Part two.

02:02:35.340 --> 02:02:37.079
Possibility.

02:02:37.140 --> 02:02:40.020
Chapter 6.

02:02:40.079 --> 02:02:43.800
They flew north toward possibility for 2

02:02:43.800 --> 02:02:44.220
days.

02:02:44.279 --> 02:02:47.399
Two days of soaring over the mountains, 2

02:02:47.399 --> 02:02:49.380
days of arguing over weather to even go

02:02:49.380 --> 02:02:51.960
to possibility at all, although in the

02:02:51.960 --> 02:02:54.300
end, peril gave in, because she couldn't

02:02:54.300 --> 02:02:55.739
think of any better ways to track

02:02:55.739 --> 02:02:56.699
Scarlet.

02:02:56.760 --> 02:02:59.279
She quickly learned that Turtle didn't

02:02:59.279 --> 02:03:01.140
have half the stamina as she did for long

02:03:01.140 --> 02:03:01.560
flights.

02:03:01.619 --> 02:03:04.680
That was probably a sea wing sky wing

02:03:04.680 --> 02:03:07.439
thing, or possibly a turtle would rather

02:03:07.439 --> 02:03:09.239
be napping than exercising thing.

02:03:09.300 --> 02:03:12.600
They had to rest, ridiculously often.

02:03:12.659 --> 02:03:15.899
He would find a lake and float around

02:03:15.899 --> 02:03:18.779
moaning about his sore wings, while she

02:03:18.779 --> 02:03:21.539
swooped in ever widening circles, scanning

02:03:21.539 --> 02:03:22.920
the ground with sharp eyes.

02:03:22.979 --> 02:03:25.619
There was no sign of Scarlet anywhere

02:03:25.619 --> 02:03:25.920
though.

02:03:25.979 --> 02:03:29.039
Once, they saw another wing of dragons

02:03:29.039 --> 02:03:30.840
who were probably from the talons of

02:03:30.840 --> 02:03:32.760
peace, given the different colors of

02:03:32.760 --> 02:03:35.159
their scales, but it was far off in the

02:03:35.159 --> 02:03:35.460
distance.

02:03:35.520 --> 02:03:37.380
Perhaps they had heard about the

02:03:37.380 --> 02:03:39.720
encounter by the river, because they

02:03:39.720 --> 02:03:41.460
didn't come over to investigate peril.

02:03:41.520 --> 02:03:44.939
Peril also spotted several sky wings

02:03:44.939 --> 02:03:46.979
spiraling around the mountain peaks.

02:03:47.039 --> 02:03:49.500
She wondered if Ruby had sent out more

02:03:49.500 --> 02:03:51.600
soldiers to search for Queen Scarlet.

02:03:51.659 --> 02:03:54.720
Ruby's throne was in danger, now that

02:03:54.720 --> 02:03:56.399
everyone knew the former queen was

02:03:56.399 --> 02:03:59.039
definitely alive and out for vengeance

02:03:59.159 --> 02:04:01.979
until someone killed her.

02:04:02.039 --> 02:04:03.659
Scarlet would always have supporters in

02:04:03.659 --> 02:04:04.439
the sky kingdom.

02:04:04.500 --> 02:04:07.500
What if one of them decided to kill Ruby

02:04:07.500 --> 02:04:08.159
on her behalf?

02:04:08.220 --> 02:04:11.760
I bet she wishes she'd been nicer to me

02:04:11.760 --> 02:04:12.000
now.

02:04:12.060 --> 02:04:14.220
Who'd be a better guard than me?

02:04:14.279 --> 02:04:16.380
Yes, I'm dangerous.

02:04:16.439 --> 02:04:18.600
That's exactly what's awesome about me.

02:04:18.659 --> 02:04:20.939
That's why she needs me.

02:04:21.000 --> 02:04:24.539
I should be right next to the queen, not

02:04:24.539 --> 02:04:26.279
banished from the whole smoldering

02:04:26.279 --> 02:04:26.640
kingdom.

02:04:26.699 --> 02:04:30.600
But then, if she'd stayed with Ruby, she

02:04:30.600 --> 02:04:31.979
couldn't be wherever Clay was.

02:04:31.979 --> 02:04:35.220
So I'll do this one thing for Ruby.

02:04:35.279 --> 02:04:38.640
I'll find Queen Scarlet, turn her into a

02:04:38.640 --> 02:04:41.159
pile of ashes, get all redeemed and

02:04:41.159 --> 02:04:43.439
pardoned, and welcomed back everywhere

02:04:43.439 --> 02:04:46.439
and then return to Clay as a beloved Sky

02:04:46.439 --> 02:04:48.539
Wing who can go anywhere I want.

02:04:48.600 --> 02:04:53.340
And be with anyone I want, because I'll

02:04:53.340 --> 02:04:54.060
be a hero too.

02:04:54.119 --> 02:04:58.020
Peril did 3 backward loops in the sky

02:04:58.020 --> 02:04:59.760
waiting for Turtle to catch up.

02:04:59.819 --> 02:05:03.840
She could see the rosy, fuzzy glow around

02:05:03.840 --> 02:05:05.819
the ridiculous fantasy she was building

02:05:05.819 --> 02:05:07.859
in her head, but she couldn't help it.

02:05:07.920 --> 02:05:10.439
She still kind of believed it could come

02:05:10.439 --> 02:05:10.739
true.

02:05:10.800 --> 02:05:13.800
Turtle flapped up, panting a little.

02:05:13.859 --> 02:05:17.699
I think, he wheezed, someone might be

02:05:17.699 --> 02:05:19.380
following us.

02:05:19.439 --> 02:05:21.119
Really?

02:05:21.180 --> 02:05:24.000
Peril scanned the horizon behind them.

02:05:24.060 --> 02:05:26.939
They were out of the mountains now, flying

02:05:26.939 --> 02:05:29.399
over the rocky, sloping hills that led to

02:05:29.399 --> 02:05:31.140
the river plain, and then north to

02:05:31.140 --> 02:05:31.619
possibility.

02:05:31.680 --> 02:05:34.560
The smudge of the town was visible in the

02:05:34.560 --> 02:05:34.920
distance.

02:05:34.979 --> 02:05:36.960
They could probably reach it by

02:05:36.960 --> 02:05:37.439
nightfall.

02:05:37.500 --> 02:05:40.619
Well, she could, if she were flying

02:05:40.619 --> 02:05:41.039
alone.

02:05:41.159 --> 02:05:43.619
With a gasping sea wing on her tail

02:05:43.619 --> 02:05:45.779
they'd probably have to sleep on it and

02:05:45.779 --> 02:05:46.439
get there in the morning.

02:05:46.500 --> 02:05:49.979
In any case, the landscape below and

02:05:49.979 --> 02:05:52.079
behind them was relatively flat compared

02:05:52.079 --> 02:05:54.659
to the claws of the clouds mountains, so

02:05:54.659 --> 02:05:56.340
it would be harder for a dragon following

02:05:56.340 --> 02:05:57.239
them to hide.

02:05:57.300 --> 02:05:59.880
I don't see anything, she said.

02:05:59.939 --> 02:06:03.420
That grove of trees back there.

02:06:03.479 --> 02:06:04.680
Turtle pointed.

02:06:04.739 --> 02:06:07.319
I thought I saw a dragon dive into them

02:06:07.319 --> 02:06:08.220
when I turned around.

02:06:08.279 --> 02:06:11.640
Peril squinted, trying to figure out if

02:06:11.640 --> 02:06:13.260
she could see wings moving in the

02:06:13.260 --> 02:06:14.939
scraggly clump of wishful forest.

02:06:15.000 --> 02:06:18.060
One way to find out, of course, would be

02:06:18.060 --> 02:06:19.260
to go set the trees on fire.

02:06:19.319 --> 02:06:21.359
It didn't seem worth the effort, though.

02:06:21.420 --> 02:06:24.239
Was it an orange dragon?

02:06:24.359 --> 02:06:24.779
she asked.

02:06:24.840 --> 02:06:27.659
No, Turtle said.

02:06:27.720 --> 02:06:29.039
Black, I think.

02:06:29.100 --> 02:06:30.840
Pearl shrugged.

02:06:30.899 --> 02:06:33.060
All right, whatever.

02:06:33.119 --> 02:06:36.300
She lifted herself to another current, so

02:06:36.300 --> 02:06:38.039
she could spin around at a safe distance

02:06:38.039 --> 02:06:40.380
from turtle, and began flying north

02:06:40.380 --> 02:06:40.619
again.

02:06:40.739 --> 02:06:42.539
Really?

02:06:42.600 --> 02:06:45.239
Turtle said, beating his wings to keep

02:06:45.239 --> 02:06:45.479
up.

02:06:45.539 --> 02:06:47.579
We're not worried about that.

02:06:47.640 --> 02:06:50.100
Why would we be?

02:06:50.159 --> 02:06:52.199
Pearl asked, amused.

02:06:52.260 --> 02:06:54.239
As long as it's not Scarlet?

02:06:54.300 --> 02:06:54.899
Who cares?

02:06:55.020 --> 02:06:56.699
It's not like anyone can hurt us.

02:06:56.760 --> 02:06:59.460
Well, me, no one can hurt me.

02:06:59.520 --> 02:07:01.920
I guess you are welcome to worry.

02:07:01.979 --> 02:07:05.699
Oh, thanks very much, Turtle said.

02:07:05.819 --> 02:07:07.199
And that's not true.

02:07:07.260 --> 02:07:09.300
I'm sure dragons can hurt you.

02:07:09.359 --> 02:07:10.979
How?

02:07:11.039 --> 02:07:12.060
Peril demanded.

02:07:12.119 --> 02:07:13.979
No, they can't.

02:07:14.039 --> 02:07:15.840
I'm fine as long as I don't listen to

02:07:15.840 --> 02:07:16.079
them.

02:07:16.140 --> 02:07:17.939
They're all stupid anyway.

02:07:18.000 --> 02:07:20.579
Who cares what a bunch of ruby butt noses

02:07:20.579 --> 02:07:20.939
say?

02:07:21.000 --> 02:07:23.039
Not me, that's for sure.

02:07:23.100 --> 02:07:25.680
I mean, come over here and say that with

02:07:25.680 --> 02:07:27.000
my talons up your snout.

02:07:27.060 --> 02:07:27.720
Ha!

02:07:27.779 --> 02:07:29.699
He gave her an odd look.

02:07:29.760 --> 02:07:33.479
Actually, I meant with a spear, or frost

02:07:33.479 --> 02:07:34.140
breath, or something.

02:07:34.199 --> 02:07:38.340
Oh, peril said, I guess, maybe.

02:07:38.399 --> 02:07:40.439
The dragons in the arena never had

02:07:40.439 --> 02:07:41.039
spears.

02:07:41.100 --> 02:07:44.279
And their wings were bound, so they

02:07:44.279 --> 02:07:45.000
couldn't fly, right?

02:07:45.060 --> 02:07:46.500
Turtle asked.

02:07:46.560 --> 02:07:48.539
Peril frowned at him.

02:07:48.600 --> 02:07:50.819
I didn't fly while we were fighting

02:07:50.819 --> 02:07:52.380
either, she said.

02:07:52.439 --> 02:07:54.119
That wasn't to make them easier to kill.

02:07:54.180 --> 02:07:56.399
That was so they wouldn't be boring and

02:07:56.399 --> 02:07:56.699
run away.

02:07:56.760 --> 02:08:01.560
You mean be sensible and run away, Turtles

02:08:01.560 --> 02:08:01.800
said.

02:08:01.859 --> 02:08:03.960
He twisted around to look behind them

02:08:03.960 --> 02:08:04.140
again.

02:08:04.199 --> 02:08:05.760
Nothing.

02:08:05.819 --> 02:08:07.979
Whoever it is is still hiding.

02:08:08.039 --> 02:08:10.439
Or you hallucinated it.

02:08:10.500 --> 02:08:12.119
Perl said grumpily.

02:08:12.180 --> 02:08:14.819
Frost breath doesn't do anything to my

02:08:14.819 --> 02:08:17.520
scales, by the way, and I bet a spear

02:08:17.520 --> 02:08:19.020
would burn up before it could stab me.

02:08:19.079 --> 02:08:21.779
Not if someone threw it at you really

02:08:21.779 --> 02:08:22.140
hard.

02:08:22.199 --> 02:08:23.640
Turtle mused.

02:08:23.699 --> 02:08:27.060
Then it would be like, bam, spear through

02:08:27.060 --> 02:08:27.420
the heart.

02:08:27.479 --> 02:08:29.579
And even if it did then burst into

02:08:29.579 --> 02:08:30.180
flames.

02:08:30.239 --> 02:08:31.380
Well, too late.

02:08:31.439 --> 02:08:35.520
This conversation is fun, Perl said.

02:08:35.579 --> 02:08:38.460
Next, let's talk about all the ways you

02:08:38.460 --> 02:08:39.060
could possibly die.

02:08:39.119 --> 02:08:40.739
I have a few ideas.

02:08:40.800 --> 02:08:44.880
Or if Scarlet has an animus, she could

02:08:44.880 --> 02:08:47.100
enchant something to kill you, Turtle

02:08:47.100 --> 02:08:49.140
pointed out, then there's nothing you

02:08:49.140 --> 02:08:49.979
could do about it.

02:08:50.039 --> 02:08:53.579
But if she could do that, glory really

02:08:53.579 --> 02:08:56.699
would be dead already, Peril argued, and

02:08:56.699 --> 02:08:57.659
Ruby.

02:08:57.720 --> 02:08:59.340
Those are the 2 she would start with.

02:08:59.399 --> 02:09:02.699
I'm only like 7th or 8th on our list

02:09:02.699 --> 02:09:03.300
probably.

02:09:03.359 --> 02:09:05.880
So I'm not going to worry about imaginary

02:09:05.880 --> 02:09:09.180
animus dragons until those guys start

02:09:09.180 --> 02:09:09.720
turning up dead.

02:09:09.779 --> 02:09:12.300
She fell silent abruptly.

02:09:12.359 --> 02:09:15.300
Realizing that Clay was probably in

02:09:15.300 --> 02:09:18.000
Scarlet's top 5 on her to be murdered

02:09:18.000 --> 02:09:18.359
list.

02:09:18.420 --> 02:09:21.239
Maybe I shouldn't have left him alone.

02:09:21.300 --> 02:09:24.000
Maybe he's the one I should be guarding

02:09:24.000 --> 02:09:27.479
all the time, day and night, never

02:09:27.479 --> 02:09:28.439
leaving his side.

02:09:28.500 --> 02:09:32.220
She let herself imagine that for a while

02:09:32.220 --> 02:09:33.539
before coming back to reality with a

02:09:33.539 --> 02:09:33.840
sigh.

02:09:33.960 --> 02:09:37.500
No, the best way to protect Clay was

02:09:37.500 --> 02:09:40.079
exactly what she was doing, going after

02:09:40.079 --> 02:09:40.619
Scarlet.

02:09:40.680 --> 02:09:43.020
How are you going to find your friends

02:09:43.020 --> 02:09:44.100
and possibility?

02:09:44.100 --> 02:09:45.539
she asked Turtle.

02:09:45.600 --> 02:09:48.539
It's a big city, full of dragons who have

02:09:48.539 --> 02:09:50.279
irrationally negative feelings about me

02:09:50.279 --> 02:09:53.159
and too many wooden buildings too close

02:09:53.159 --> 02:09:53.640
together.

02:09:53.699 --> 02:09:54.600
I don't like it.

02:09:54.659 --> 02:09:56.819
For the record, it's a stupid place.

02:09:56.880 --> 02:10:00.539
You've mentioned that, Turtle said

02:10:00.539 --> 02:10:02.340
glancing over his shoulder again.

02:10:02.399 --> 02:10:05.220
Can we rest for the night and figure it

02:10:05.220 --> 02:10:06.840
out in the morning when we get there?

02:10:06.899 --> 02:10:09.119
My wings are so sore.

02:10:09.180 --> 02:10:11.220
I swear they're about to fall off.

02:10:11.279 --> 02:10:13.619
They've never been in this much pain

02:10:13.619 --> 02:10:14.520
ever.

02:10:14.579 --> 02:10:17.760
Harold traced the river below them with

02:10:17.760 --> 02:10:19.859
her eyes, up to the town in the near

02:10:19.859 --> 02:10:20.220
distance.

02:10:20.279 --> 02:10:22.380
It was so close.

02:10:22.500 --> 02:10:26.039
Then again, why was she hurrying to get

02:10:26.039 --> 02:10:26.399
somewhere?

02:10:26.460 --> 02:10:27.600
She didn't even want to be at all?

02:10:27.659 --> 02:10:29.399
All right.

02:10:29.460 --> 02:10:30.539
Pearl agreed.

02:10:30.600 --> 02:10:33.180
Let's find a spot with fewer trees and

02:10:33.180 --> 02:10:33.779
more rocks.

02:10:33.840 --> 02:10:37.199
The sun was sinking way out beyond the

02:10:37.199 --> 02:10:39.359
desert when they came down to land near

02:10:39.359 --> 02:10:42.180
the river, in a spot where giant boulders

02:10:42.180 --> 02:10:44.279
overlapped one another halfway into the

02:10:44.279 --> 02:10:47.100
water, and small rapids bustled noisily

02:10:47.100 --> 02:10:47.460
around them.

02:10:47.579 --> 02:10:50.819
Peril tried to be careful, but there were

02:10:50.819 --> 02:10:53.340
too many patches of moss, and she felt a

02:10:53.340 --> 02:10:55.680
twinge of familiar guilt as some of them

02:10:55.680 --> 02:10:57.479
curled into blackened ash below her

02:10:57.479 --> 02:10:57.899
claws.

02:10:57.960 --> 02:11:01.560
Also, as she settled on a boulder, her

02:11:01.560 --> 02:11:03.720
tail slipped into a little pool nearby

02:11:03.720 --> 02:11:06.000
and immediately boiled the 2 fish

02:11:06.000 --> 02:11:08.340
swimming there, they floated to the

02:11:08.340 --> 02:11:10.739
surface, white bellies turned up to the

02:11:10.739 --> 02:11:12.060
purpling sky.

02:11:12.119 --> 02:11:14.159
Shoot, peril said.

02:11:14.220 --> 02:11:17.520
I mean, hey, look, dinner.

02:11:17.579 --> 02:11:20.100
Turtle splashed over through the river

02:11:20.100 --> 02:11:22.260
speared one of the fish with a claw and

02:11:22.260 --> 02:11:22.979
winced.

02:11:23.039 --> 02:11:24.239
Ouch.

02:11:24.300 --> 02:11:26.220
I don't think I could ever get used to

02:11:26.220 --> 02:11:27.479
eating hot prey.

02:11:27.539 --> 02:11:29.340
And such a weird feeling in my mouth.

02:11:29.399 --> 02:11:33.659
I've never eaten prey any other way, Pearl

02:11:33.659 --> 02:11:34.199
pointed out.

02:11:34.260 --> 02:11:36.359
It's always black and crunchy.

02:11:36.420 --> 02:11:39.239
A little like the black rocks Queen

02:11:39.239 --> 02:11:41.159
Scarlet tricked me into eating when I was

02:11:41.159 --> 02:11:41.399
younger.

02:11:41.520 --> 02:11:45.000
The queen had convinced Pearl that

02:11:45.000 --> 02:11:47.579
because of her fire scales condition, she

02:11:47.579 --> 02:11:49.140
needed to eat a certain kind of black

02:11:49.140 --> 02:11:50.460
rock every day.

02:11:50.520 --> 02:11:52.859
It could only be found in the mountains

02:11:52.859 --> 02:11:55.680
and Scarlett took charge of Peril's

02:11:55.680 --> 02:11:55.979
supply.

02:11:56.039 --> 02:11:58.560
I'm the one keeping you alive.

02:11:58.619 --> 02:12:00.600
That's what she always said.

02:12:00.659 --> 02:12:05.640
But it was a lie, a trick, to keep peril

02:12:05.640 --> 02:12:08.220
confined to the Sky Palace, and dependent

02:12:08.220 --> 02:12:09.659
on Queen Scarlet.

02:12:09.659 --> 02:12:12.000
Even though peril had always obeyed the

02:12:12.000 --> 02:12:14.699
Queen's every order, Scarlet still never

02:12:14.699 --> 02:12:15.359
trusted her.

02:12:15.420 --> 02:12:18.000
What did she think I would do?

02:12:18.060 --> 02:12:19.260
Run away?

02:12:19.319 --> 02:12:21.420
Try to steal the throne?

02:12:21.479 --> 02:12:23.340
Join the talons of peace?

02:12:23.399 --> 02:12:25.560
Think for myself?

02:12:25.619 --> 02:12:28.500
Peril shook off that thought with a

02:12:28.500 --> 02:12:28.979
growl.

02:12:29.100 --> 02:12:31.680
It wasn't personal, though, she had to

02:12:31.680 --> 02:12:32.520
remind herself.

02:12:32.579 --> 02:12:35.340
Queen Scarlet manipulated everyone she

02:12:35.340 --> 02:12:37.920
came into contact with, not only peril.

02:12:37.979 --> 02:12:42.239
Well, that's just sad, Turtle said.

02:12:42.300 --> 02:12:45.239
And after a minute, peril realized he was

02:12:45.239 --> 02:12:47.100
still talking about how she only ate

02:12:47.100 --> 02:12:48.060
burnt prey.

02:12:48.119 --> 02:12:50.340
He rolled his shoulders back and forth

02:12:50.340 --> 02:12:53.220
stretching his neck and making agonized

02:12:53.220 --> 02:12:54.899
faces at his sore muscles.

02:12:54.960 --> 02:12:57.479
You should try its normal way.

02:12:57.539 --> 02:13:00.060
Here, open your mouth and I'll throw some

02:13:00.060 --> 02:13:00.239
in.

02:13:00.300 --> 02:13:02.760
He snared another fish from the river

02:13:02.760 --> 02:13:03.840
beside his boulder.

02:13:03.899 --> 02:13:05.939
That sounds insane.

02:13:06.060 --> 02:13:07.619
Peril observed.

02:13:07.680 --> 02:13:08.939
What are you talking about?

02:13:09.000 --> 02:13:12.539
Keep your mouth open and the fish won't

02:13:12.539 --> 02:13:14.159
touch your scales, he said.

02:13:14.220 --> 02:13:16.859
Placidly ripping the fish into small

02:13:16.859 --> 02:13:17.399
pieces.

02:13:17.460 --> 02:13:20.460
That way it won't get burned, and you can

02:13:20.460 --> 02:13:22.619
see what it tastes like to most dragons.

02:13:22.680 --> 02:13:25.859
Dubiously, Pearl stretched her jaws wide

02:13:25.859 --> 02:13:26.460
open.

02:13:26.520 --> 02:13:28.739
A fish head smacked her in the eye.

02:13:28.859 --> 02:13:30.479
Yuck!

02:13:30.600 --> 02:13:32.819
she roared, surging up with her wings

02:13:32.819 --> 02:13:34.140
flared.

02:13:34.199 --> 02:13:35.579
Try that again, Seawing.

02:13:35.640 --> 02:13:38.159
I'm sorry, he yelled.

02:13:38.220 --> 02:13:39.600
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

02:13:39.659 --> 02:13:40.500
I missed.

02:13:40.560 --> 02:13:42.180
Here, let me try again.

02:13:42.239 --> 02:13:44.399
She eyed him suspiciously.

02:13:44.460 --> 02:13:48.180
He looked not so much deeply repentant as

02:13:48.180 --> 02:13:49.920
trying to hide his giggles.

02:13:49.979 --> 02:13:52.380
Did you do that on purpose?

02:13:52.439 --> 02:13:53.640
She demanded.

02:13:53.699 --> 02:13:57.539
No, I swear, he said, but I don't have

02:13:57.539 --> 02:13:59.520
very good aim, not a lot of practice.

02:13:59.640 --> 02:14:01.140
Give me another chance.

02:14:01.260 --> 02:14:03.720
Growling softly.

02:14:03.779 --> 02:14:05.340
Peril opened her mouth again.

02:14:05.460 --> 02:14:09.000
The next 2 pieces sailed straight past

02:14:09.000 --> 02:14:11.760
her head, but the 3rd finally splatted

02:14:11.760 --> 02:14:13.800
between her teeth, and she snapped her

02:14:13.800 --> 02:14:14.819
jaws shut around it.

02:14:14.880 --> 02:14:18.539
It felt like a cold, slimy frog had just

02:14:18.539 --> 02:14:20.039
leaped into her mouth.

02:14:20.100 --> 02:14:22.439
She chewed for a moment, as long as she

02:14:22.439 --> 02:14:24.539
could bear it, and then swallowed fast.

02:14:24.600 --> 02:14:28.859
No, she said, definitely no.

02:14:28.920 --> 02:14:32.760
Horrifying amounts of no, that was 100

02:14:32.760 --> 02:14:34.020
disgusting.

02:14:34.140 --> 02:14:36.119
Turtle laughed.

02:14:36.180 --> 02:14:38.340
You're so wrong, he said.

02:14:38.460 --> 02:14:39.600
It's awesome.

02:14:39.659 --> 02:14:41.460
That's how fish should be eaten.

02:14:41.520 --> 02:14:45.060
Pearl said strongly.

02:14:45.180 --> 02:14:47.460
She hopped to the next boulder, heading

02:14:47.460 --> 02:14:47.939
for the shore.

02:14:48.000 --> 02:14:50.340
I'm going to find something that is the

02:14:50.340 --> 02:14:52.920
opposite of fish, scorch it, and then

02:14:52.920 --> 02:14:54.779
coat my tongue with char to get that

02:14:54.779 --> 02:14:55.739
taste out of my mouth.

02:14:55.800 --> 02:14:57.659
Yuck.

02:14:57.720 --> 02:14:58.859
You are the worst.

02:14:58.920 --> 02:15:01.560
I would be so justified in setting you on

02:15:01.560 --> 02:15:02.880
fire while you're asleep tonight.

02:15:02.939 --> 02:15:04.859
Duly noted.

02:15:04.920 --> 02:15:06.720
Turtle said serenely.

02:15:06.779 --> 02:15:09.239
Did I mention I'll be sleeping in the

02:15:09.239 --> 02:15:10.140
bottom of the river?

02:15:10.199 --> 02:15:12.300
You know, if you're looking for me.

02:15:12.420 --> 02:15:14.399
He grinned at her.

02:15:14.460 --> 02:15:17.399
Peril paused on the river bank, squinting

02:15:17.399 --> 02:15:17.819
at him.

02:15:17.880 --> 02:15:19.560
She had been joking, of course.

02:15:19.619 --> 02:15:21.840
There were a number of excellent reasons

02:15:21.840 --> 02:15:24.239
not to set turtle on fire, which

02:15:24.239 --> 02:15:26.100
outweighed any potential benefits to

02:15:26.100 --> 02:15:26.460
doing so.

02:15:26.579 --> 02:15:29.520
But it unsettled her for a moment to

02:15:29.520 --> 02:15:31.680
realize that by sleeping in the river

02:15:31.680 --> 02:15:34.619
even by standing in the river right now

02:15:34.619 --> 02:15:38.159
he could foil any plan she did make if

02:15:38.159 --> 02:15:39.539
she ever needed to burn him up.

02:15:39.600 --> 02:15:43.020
Not that I would, probably.

02:15:43.079 --> 02:15:46.619
I most likely would never need to, and I

02:15:46.619 --> 02:15:48.659
wouldn't want to, of course, that too.

02:15:48.720 --> 02:15:51.539
But she'd never run into a situation

02:15:51.539 --> 02:15:53.340
where someone could stop her like that

02:15:53.340 --> 02:15:54.899
apart from clay.

02:15:55.020 --> 02:15:58.619
Maybe I did have an unfair advantage

02:15:58.619 --> 02:16:00.359
fighting sea wings in the arena.

02:16:00.420 --> 02:16:02.760
If I were fighting them in their own part

02:16:02.760 --> 02:16:04.979
of the world, somewhere they could go

02:16:04.979 --> 02:16:07.859
underwater to escape, or even drag me

02:16:07.859 --> 02:16:08.699
underwater with them.

02:16:08.760 --> 02:16:11.699
She didn't like that train of thought.

02:16:11.760 --> 02:16:15.420
She didn't like one single thing about

02:16:15.420 --> 02:16:15.539
it.

02:16:15.600 --> 02:16:18.479
I'll be back in a minute, she snapped.

02:16:18.539 --> 02:16:22.920
I'll be here, apologizing to my woebegone

02:16:22.920 --> 02:16:24.300
wings, he said.

02:16:24.359 --> 02:16:27.420
She stomped off, ignoring the trail of

02:16:27.420 --> 02:16:29.880
scorched grass she left in her wake as

02:16:29.880 --> 02:16:31.500
she searched the shoreline for prey.

02:16:31.560 --> 02:16:34.979
After a few minutes, a hare bolted out of

02:16:34.979 --> 02:16:36.659
a burrow in front of her, and she was

02:16:36.659 --> 02:16:38.459
able to catch it and wolf it down.

02:16:38.520 --> 02:16:41.700
On her way back, she caught sight of

02:16:41.700 --> 02:16:43.200
turtle lying on one of the boulders.

02:16:43.260 --> 02:16:46.319
The sun was halfway down, casting warm

02:16:46.319 --> 02:16:48.840
orange light across his dark green scales

02:16:48.840 --> 02:16:51.239
and the seawing was doing something odd.

02:16:51.360 --> 02:16:54.120
She paused to stare at him for a moment.

02:16:54.180 --> 02:16:57.059
It looked as if he was rolling a small

02:16:57.059 --> 02:16:58.799
river stone across his shoulders.

02:16:58.860 --> 02:17:01.319
What are you doing?

02:17:01.379 --> 02:17:03.479
she asked coming up behind him.

02:17:03.540 --> 02:17:07.379
He jumped, looking fascinatingly guilty.

02:17:07.500 --> 02:17:10.260
There was definitely something not right

02:17:10.260 --> 02:17:10.680
about this.

02:17:10.799 --> 02:17:13.559
Nothing, he said.

02:17:13.620 --> 02:17:16.379
Just trying to work out the kinks in my

02:17:16.379 --> 02:17:16.860
back.

02:17:16.920 --> 02:17:18.780
I've never flown this much before.

02:17:18.840 --> 02:17:23.340
So you've mentioned a few 100 times, Pearl

02:17:23.340 --> 02:17:23.639
said.

02:17:23.700 --> 02:17:25.379
Can I see the rock you're using?

02:17:25.440 --> 02:17:27.540
Oh, this?

02:17:27.540 --> 02:17:28.559
he said.

02:17:28.620 --> 02:17:30.600
Just a rock I picked up from the river.

02:17:30.659 --> 02:17:33.000
He held it out casually.

02:17:33.059 --> 02:17:35.639
The smooth gray white stone, looking like

02:17:35.639 --> 02:17:37.559
a hawk's egg in his webbed talons.

02:17:37.620 --> 02:17:39.899
Does it really help?

02:17:39.959 --> 02:17:40.259
She asked.

02:17:40.319 --> 02:17:43.799
Uh, he said, a little.

02:17:43.860 --> 02:17:45.600
He rolled his shoulders again.

02:17:45.659 --> 02:17:49.020
Anyway, woo, I'm tired.

02:17:49.079 --> 02:17:50.219
I'll see you in the morning.

02:17:50.280 --> 02:17:53.700
He dove into the water and vanished below

02:17:53.700 --> 02:17:55.680
the surface, taking the rock with him.

02:17:55.739 --> 02:17:59.399
Pearl sat down on her boulder and flipped

02:17:59.399 --> 02:18:00.420
her tail over her talons.

02:18:00.479 --> 02:18:03.420
It was hard to tell in the growing dusk

02:18:03.420 --> 02:18:06.000
but she was pretty sure the blurry shape

02:18:06.000 --> 02:18:08.340
of turtle was still applying the rock to

02:18:08.340 --> 02:18:09.420
his scales underwater.

02:18:09.479 --> 02:18:12.600
That was weird, she mused.

02:18:12.719 --> 02:18:15.059
He could have stayed up here and talked

02:18:15.059 --> 02:18:16.319
to me for a little bit longer.

02:18:16.379 --> 02:18:18.899
Did he think I was going to steal his

02:18:18.899 --> 02:18:19.259
rock?

02:18:19.319 --> 02:18:22.260
Is it some kind of sea wing secret?

02:18:22.319 --> 02:18:22.860
I shouldn't know?

02:18:22.920 --> 02:18:25.559
River rocks can heal them or something?

02:18:25.620 --> 02:18:28.680
That sounded pretty implausible.

02:18:28.739 --> 02:18:31.079
Even to someone who had been raised not

02:18:31.079 --> 02:18:32.520
to know much about other tribes.

02:18:32.579 --> 02:18:35.340
Maybe he was simply trying to get away

02:18:35.340 --> 02:18:35.700
from her.

02:18:35.819 --> 02:18:39.239
Maybe he'd finally realized, like every

02:18:39.239 --> 02:18:41.760
other dragon in the world, that she was a

02:18:41.760 --> 02:18:43.260
terrible dragon to be friends with.

02:18:43.319 --> 02:18:45.959
But he'd been laughing with her only a

02:18:45.959 --> 02:18:46.680
few minutes earlier.

02:18:46.739 --> 02:18:50.159
Doesn't matter, she thought fiercely.

02:18:50.219 --> 02:18:52.979
Whatever it is, that's just fine.

02:18:53.040 --> 02:18:56.040
He can keep his secrets or stop being

02:18:56.040 --> 02:18:57.600
friends with me or whatever he wants.

02:18:57.659 --> 02:19:01.680
I can always go back to clay, my real

02:19:01.680 --> 02:19:02.040
friend.

02:19:02.100 --> 02:19:04.680
You're not that important to me either

02:19:04.680 --> 02:19:05.280
Sea Wing.

02:19:05.340 --> 02:19:06.299
Humph.

02:19:06.360 --> 02:19:09.719
She lay down and closed her eyes, but

02:19:09.719 --> 02:19:12.059
sleep was a long time coming.

02:19:12.120 --> 02:19:16.379
Chapter 7.

02:19:16.440 --> 02:19:19.860
The next morning, Turtle was mostly

02:19:19.860 --> 02:19:22.620
normal, a little jittery, but it could

02:19:22.620 --> 02:19:24.299
have been excitement about being so close

02:19:24.299 --> 02:19:25.799
to finding his winglet again.

02:19:25.860 --> 02:19:29.399
His friends, and then he'll probably

02:19:29.399 --> 02:19:30.180
ditch me.

02:19:30.239 --> 02:19:31.860
Carol realized.

02:19:31.920 --> 02:19:34.200
She guessed the others wouldn't be too

02:19:34.200 --> 02:19:35.579
thrilled about her coming along

02:19:35.579 --> 02:19:39.059
especially that ice wing, if he was still

02:19:39.059 --> 02:19:40.500
alive and around anywhere.

02:19:40.559 --> 02:19:43.799
Well, if she had to find Scarlet on her

02:19:43.799 --> 02:19:45.959
own, that was probably better anyway.

02:19:45.959 --> 02:19:49.259
She sat on the boulder where she'd slept

02:19:49.259 --> 02:19:51.359
watching turtles splash around after his

02:19:51.359 --> 02:19:53.999
breakfast, he had a small waterproof

02:19:53.999 --> 02:19:55.919
pouch around his neck, which looked

02:19:55.919 --> 02:19:57.419
heavier than usual this morning.

02:19:57.479 --> 02:19:59.879
From the way it thumped against his chest

02:19:59.879 --> 02:20:02.040
Perl guessed that he'd put one of the

02:20:02.040 --> 02:20:02.760
river rocks in there.

02:20:02.819 --> 02:20:06.120
His only other accessory was a gold

02:20:06.120 --> 02:20:09.180
armband with 3 sparkly black rocks set in

02:20:09.180 --> 02:20:12.059
it, +3 holes where it seemed as though

02:20:12.059 --> 02:20:13.500
other rocks should have been.

02:20:13.559 --> 02:20:16.020
Peril had noticed that he fiddled with it

02:20:16.020 --> 02:20:16.620
when he was nervous.

02:20:16.680 --> 02:20:19.079
Sticking his claws into the holes and

02:20:19.079 --> 02:20:21.180
tugging the armband up and down.

02:20:21.239 --> 02:20:23.040
Why are you glaring at me?

02:20:23.100 --> 02:20:24.360
Turtle asked.

02:20:24.420 --> 02:20:27.899
I'm not glaring, Pearl snapped.

02:20:27.959 --> 02:20:29.219
This is my face.

02:20:29.280 --> 02:20:33.299
Your face kind of looks like it hates me

02:20:33.299 --> 02:20:35.040
today, Turtle observed.

02:20:35.100 --> 02:20:36.899
Can you remind it that I'm really quite

02:20:36.899 --> 02:20:37.200
nice?

02:20:37.260 --> 02:20:40.440
Carol concentrated on her expression for

02:20:40.440 --> 02:20:42.360
a moment, but she could feel her frown

02:20:42.360 --> 02:20:43.319
only getting deeper.

02:20:43.379 --> 02:20:47.159
All right, now I'm glaring at you, she

02:20:47.159 --> 02:20:48.059
said.

02:20:48.120 --> 02:20:49.680
Can we get on with this annoying day

02:20:49.680 --> 02:20:50.040
already?

02:20:50.100 --> 02:20:52.440
Are you nervous about going to

02:20:52.440 --> 02:20:53.040
possibility?

02:20:53.100 --> 02:20:54.840
Turtle said shrewdly.

02:20:54.899 --> 02:20:56.579
We won't have to be there long.

02:20:56.639 --> 02:20:58.620
Maybe no one will even notice you.

02:20:58.680 --> 02:21:02.040
You really have no idea what it's like to

02:21:02.040 --> 02:21:02.459
be me.

02:21:02.520 --> 02:21:05.579
Pearl said, arching her neck and flaring

02:21:05.579 --> 02:21:06.120
her wings.

02:21:06.180 --> 02:21:09.239
The rising sun slammed into her scales

02:21:09.239 --> 02:21:11.520
scattering into bright orange reflections

02:21:11.520 --> 02:21:12.360
in the water below her.

02:21:12.420 --> 02:21:16.020
I've never not been noticed.

02:21:16.079 --> 02:21:17.940
That's not an option for me.

02:21:18.000 --> 02:21:21.180
Imagine my life as the literal opposite

02:21:21.180 --> 02:21:21.659
of yours.

02:21:21.719 --> 02:21:23.520
He didn't answer.

02:21:23.639 --> 02:21:26.760
Pearl squinted at him and realized he was

02:21:26.760 --> 02:21:28.500
peering at a spot along the muddy shore

02:21:28.500 --> 02:21:28.860
of the river.

02:21:28.920 --> 02:21:30.899
What?

02:21:30.959 --> 02:21:31.680
she demanded.

02:21:31.739 --> 02:21:33.659
What's so fascinating?

02:21:33.780 --> 02:21:37.500
I'm guessing these talon prints aren't

02:21:37.500 --> 02:21:38.819
yours, he said.

02:21:38.879 --> 02:21:41.579
Peril hopped into the river and splashed

02:21:41.579 --> 02:21:44.100
over to him, sending up clouds of steam

02:21:44.100 --> 02:21:44.819
all around her.

02:21:44.879 --> 02:21:48.120
Turtle didn't flail away in a panic like

02:21:48.120 --> 02:21:49.500
most dragons would.

02:21:49.559 --> 02:21:51.899
He moved over quietly, so she could see

02:21:51.899 --> 02:21:54.000
the mud, where a set of prints were

02:21:54.000 --> 02:21:56.520
clearly embedded, along with the sweep of

02:21:56.520 --> 02:21:57.420
a tail around them.

02:21:57.479 --> 02:22:00.180
Someone had been standing here.

02:22:00.239 --> 02:22:04.379
Then sitting here, very recently, someone

02:22:04.379 --> 02:22:07.020
bigger than Pearl, facing the river

02:22:07.020 --> 02:22:09.299
facing the boulder where she'd been

02:22:09.299 --> 02:22:09.600
sleeping.

02:22:09.659 --> 02:22:11.520
Hello!

02:22:11.579 --> 02:22:14.159
Pearl yelled, making turtle jump.

02:22:14.219 --> 02:22:17.159
If you're spying on us, just come out

02:22:17.159 --> 02:22:17.579
already.

02:22:17.639 --> 02:22:20.100
Turtle rubbed his ears.

02:22:20.280 --> 02:22:24.239
So stealth isn't your strong suit either

02:22:24.239 --> 02:22:24.479
I see.

02:22:24.540 --> 02:22:28.319
Sorry, Carol said, unrepentantly.

02:22:28.379 --> 02:22:30.420
I know it's your only suit.

02:22:30.479 --> 02:22:33.420
Whoever you are, just come out and say

02:22:33.420 --> 02:22:35.459
whatever you have to say.

02:22:35.520 --> 02:22:37.379
There was no response.

02:22:37.440 --> 02:22:40.559
The leaves on the trees whispered quietly

02:22:40.559 --> 02:22:43.079
as if gossiping about the crazy copper

02:22:43.079 --> 02:22:45.659
dragon shouting at nothingness, Pearl

02:22:45.659 --> 02:22:46.200
shrugged.

02:22:46.260 --> 02:22:47.819
I guess they left.

02:22:47.879 --> 02:22:50.399
Maybe they just wanted to catch a glimpse

02:22:50.399 --> 02:22:51.420
of a fire monster.

02:22:51.479 --> 02:22:54.299
Or maybe they thought I was scarlet, and

02:22:54.299 --> 02:22:56.100
then realized who I am and fled in

02:22:56.100 --> 02:22:56.399
terror.

02:22:56.459 --> 02:22:57.719
That could be it.

02:22:57.780 --> 02:23:02.159
Hmm, Turtle said, with just a shade too

02:23:02.159 --> 02:23:03.540
much skepticism in his voice.

02:23:03.600 --> 02:23:07.020
He twisted around, scanning the trees and

02:23:07.020 --> 02:23:09.360
sky and river, but there was no sign of

02:23:09.360 --> 02:23:10.139
anybody.

02:23:10.200 --> 02:23:13.139
I have a plan for possibility, Perl

02:23:13.139 --> 02:23:13.379
said.

02:23:13.440 --> 02:23:14.399
Let's go.

02:23:14.459 --> 02:23:17.219
She spread her wings and launched herself

02:23:17.219 --> 02:23:18.959
into the sky like a burst of flames.

02:23:19.020 --> 02:23:22.020
The sun had crept over the mountaintops

02:23:22.020 --> 02:23:24.360
spilling in golden stripes down the

02:23:24.360 --> 02:23:25.799
canyons and across the hills.

02:23:25.860 --> 02:23:27.000
To the west.

02:23:27.059 --> 02:23:29.639
Pearl saw a line of camels plodding

02:23:29.639 --> 02:23:32.040
across the desert, with smaller shapes on

02:23:32.040 --> 02:23:33.600
their backs and around their heels

02:23:33.600 --> 02:23:35.159
scavengers perhaps.

02:23:35.280 --> 02:23:38.399
Turtle flapped wetly up beside her

02:23:38.399 --> 02:23:40.620
splattering her with spray from his tail

02:23:40.620 --> 02:23:41.280
and wings.

02:23:41.340 --> 02:23:44.399
In the sunlight, his jewel toned scales

02:23:44.399 --> 02:23:46.200
looked more like emeralds than ever.

02:23:46.260 --> 02:23:48.959
A plan would be good, he said.

02:23:49.020 --> 02:23:50.219
Tell me your plan.

02:23:50.280 --> 02:23:52.379
Easy.

02:23:52.440 --> 02:23:54.180
We'll just dive right into the middle of

02:23:54.180 --> 02:23:56.700
the market, and then all those dragons

02:23:56.700 --> 02:23:59.040
will start stampeding around yelling

02:23:59.040 --> 02:24:01.379
about what a menace I am, and then you

02:24:01.379 --> 02:24:04.139
shout, Moon and Kibli, meet us outside

02:24:04.139 --> 02:24:06.180
town, and then we fly away again.

02:24:06.239 --> 02:24:08.760
Peril nodded with satisfaction.

02:24:08.819 --> 02:24:10.379
I think that would work.

02:24:10.500 --> 02:24:13.139
Turtle wrinkled a snout at her.

02:24:13.200 --> 02:24:16.860
I have a slightly less insane idea, he

02:24:16.860 --> 02:24:18.540
said, if you can swim.

02:24:18.600 --> 02:24:22.559
I can do anything, Pearl said, tossing

02:24:22.559 --> 02:24:23.100
her head.

02:24:23.159 --> 02:24:25.379
There was a lake by this waterfall near

02:24:25.379 --> 02:24:27.479
the Sky Palace that I swam in once.

02:24:27.540 --> 02:24:28.920
I didn't like it though.

02:24:28.979 --> 02:24:32.100
It was weird, being surrounded by water.

02:24:32.159 --> 02:24:35.340
In a way, it was like flying because she

02:24:35.340 --> 02:24:37.139
couldn't exactly burn anything while she

02:24:37.139 --> 02:24:39.059
was underwater, but it was also

02:24:39.059 --> 02:24:39.719
unsettling.

02:24:39.780 --> 02:24:42.479
Dragons shouldn't be underwater.

02:24:42.540 --> 02:24:45.059
Fire shouldn't be underwater.

02:24:45.120 --> 02:24:48.479
If we swim into the city, no one will

02:24:48.479 --> 02:24:48.959
notice you.

02:24:49.020 --> 02:24:50.159
Turtles said.

02:24:50.219 --> 02:24:52.200
We'll be able to scout it out without

02:24:52.200 --> 02:24:53.700
attracting a lot of attention.

02:24:53.760 --> 02:24:56.879
I don't care about attention, Perl said.

02:24:56.940 --> 02:24:59.459
If a dragon wants to stare at me and hate

02:24:59.459 --> 02:25:01.680
me and think horrible thoughts about all

02:25:01.680 --> 02:25:04.260
the things they can't do to me, then they

02:25:04.260 --> 02:25:04.979
can go right ahead.

02:25:05.040 --> 02:25:07.739
She twisted around to glance back at

02:25:07.739 --> 02:25:08.219
Turtle.

02:25:08.280 --> 02:25:11.040
A movement far below them caught her eye

02:25:11.040 --> 02:25:13.200
and she angled one wing to look down.

02:25:13.319 --> 02:25:17.159
There was a black dragon, standing on the

02:25:17.159 --> 02:25:18.840
boulder where Peril had slept the night

02:25:18.840 --> 02:25:19.139
before.

02:25:19.200 --> 02:25:22.079
He lowered his snout for a moment

02:25:22.079 --> 02:25:25.200
studying the moss she'd burned, and then

02:25:25.200 --> 02:25:26.639
lifted his head to scan the sky.

02:25:26.700 --> 02:25:30.360
Although he was miles away now, Peril

02:25:30.360 --> 02:25:32.819
felt his eyes snag on her scales, like

02:25:32.819 --> 02:25:35.399
wickedly sharp fish hooks, he didn't

02:25:35.399 --> 02:25:36.059
move.

02:25:36.120 --> 02:25:37.500
He didn't come flying after them.

02:25:37.559 --> 02:25:42.540
He just stared, eerie and still, watching

02:25:42.540 --> 02:25:44.520
her beat more and more distance between

02:25:44.520 --> 02:25:47.579
them, getting smaller and smaller.

02:25:47.639 --> 02:25:49.319
Whoever he was.

02:25:49.379 --> 02:25:51.780
Peril had a feeling he wasn't done with

02:25:51.780 --> 02:25:52.079
her yet.

02:25:52.139 --> 02:25:55.559
Turtle did a flip in the sky to see what

02:25:55.559 --> 02:25:56.159
she was looking at.

02:25:56.219 --> 02:25:59.100
He nearly lost the wind under him as he

02:25:59.100 --> 02:25:59.819
spotted the dragon.

02:25:59.879 --> 02:26:02.520
I was right, he cried.

02:26:02.579 --> 02:26:03.479
See?

02:26:03.540 --> 02:26:04.620
He's following us.

02:26:04.680 --> 02:26:08.219
He's not, Pearl pointed out.

02:26:08.280 --> 02:26:10.620
Mostly he's just staring at us.

02:26:10.680 --> 02:26:13.860
It's creepy, but to be fair, if he tried

02:26:13.860 --> 02:26:16.020
to do that from any closer up, I'd have

02:26:16.020 --> 02:26:17.639
to stick something sharp and burning into

02:26:17.639 --> 02:26:18.420
his eyeballs.

02:26:18.479 --> 02:26:20.819
All right, Turtle said.

02:26:20.879 --> 02:26:22.559
Thank you for that visual.

02:26:22.620 --> 02:26:24.540
Do you know any night wings?

02:26:24.600 --> 02:26:27.600
Starflight, peril answered.

02:26:27.659 --> 02:26:30.420
And that other fluff brained one at the

02:26:30.420 --> 02:26:32.219
school, but it's too big to be either of

02:26:32.219 --> 02:26:32.399
them.

02:26:32.459 --> 02:26:35.579
Turtle flicked his tail nervously and

02:26:35.579 --> 02:26:36.840
beat his wings faster.

02:26:36.899 --> 02:26:39.000
Keeping up with her easily for the 1st

02:26:39.000 --> 02:26:41.340
time since they'd left Jade Mountain.

02:26:41.399 --> 02:26:42.959
I did hear a rumor.

02:26:42.959 --> 02:26:44.040
He started.

02:26:44.100 --> 02:26:45.840
A rumor?

02:26:45.899 --> 02:26:46.860
Pearl asked.

02:26:46.920 --> 02:26:49.559
Or dragons having a conversation you

02:26:49.559 --> 02:26:50.700
weren't supposed to overhear.

02:26:50.819 --> 02:26:53.940
Nobody said I couldn't stand in the

02:26:53.940 --> 02:26:56.459
tunnel outside and listen, Turtle said

02:26:56.459 --> 02:26:57.120
defensively.

02:26:57.180 --> 02:27:01.079
Anyway, Sonny was telling tsunami that

02:27:01.079 --> 02:27:03.120
some Nightwing prisoners had escaped from

02:27:03.120 --> 02:27:04.440
Thorn's stronghold.

02:27:04.500 --> 02:27:05.879
Maybe it's one of them.

02:27:05.940 --> 02:27:08.760
Why would a night wing prisoner be

02:27:08.760 --> 02:27:09.600
interested in us?

02:27:09.659 --> 02:27:10.860
Pearl asked.

02:27:10.920 --> 02:27:12.360
True.

02:27:12.420 --> 02:27:15.420
Maybe it's someone working with Scarlet

02:27:15.420 --> 02:27:16.440
Turtles said.

02:27:16.500 --> 02:27:18.299
Maybe it's her new ally.

02:27:18.360 --> 02:27:21.540
Peril swiveled violently around in the

02:27:21.540 --> 02:27:21.899
sky.

02:27:21.959 --> 02:27:23.940
How did I not think of that?

02:27:24.000 --> 02:27:27.659
What if it's a nightwing animus, coming

02:27:27.659 --> 02:27:29.340
after me on Scarlet's orders?

02:27:29.399 --> 02:27:32.159
Maybe I'm higher on her vengeance list

02:27:32.159 --> 02:27:32.879
than I thought.

02:27:32.940 --> 02:27:35.579
The Black Dragon was gone.

02:27:35.639 --> 02:27:38.219
Wonderful, she said.

02:27:38.280 --> 02:27:40.079
You couldn't have mentioned that a bit

02:27:40.079 --> 02:27:40.559
sooner?

02:27:40.620 --> 02:27:43.260
Now all I can do is worry about it.

02:27:43.319 --> 02:27:45.780
I hate worrying about things.

02:27:45.840 --> 02:27:49.500
It's almost time for us to swim, Turtle

02:27:49.500 --> 02:27:50.219
said cheerfully.

02:27:50.280 --> 02:27:51.899
You can worry about that instead.

02:27:51.959 --> 02:27:54.780
He canted his wings and swooped down

02:27:54.780 --> 02:27:55.319
toward the river.

02:27:55.440 --> 02:27:58.440
Uneasily, peril followed him.

02:27:58.500 --> 02:27:59.940
Don't think about it.

02:28:00.000 --> 02:28:02.579
There's nothing I can do about this night

02:28:02.579 --> 02:28:03.719
wing right now anyway.

02:28:03.780 --> 02:28:07.139
I have to wait until he shows his face a

02:28:07.139 --> 02:28:07.920
bit closer to me.

02:28:07.979 --> 02:28:10.979
And then I can burn it off, and then

02:28:10.979 --> 02:28:11.879
everything will be fine.

02:28:11.940 --> 02:28:15.719
She flexed her talons, feeling the warm

02:28:15.719 --> 02:28:18.059
shift of her fire scales, and then

02:28:18.059 --> 02:28:20.040
splashed down right behind turtle.

02:28:20.100 --> 02:28:25.020
The river was cold, and extremely wet, and

02:28:25.020 --> 02:28:26.760
full of flappy slippery things.

02:28:26.819 --> 02:28:30.000
Peril did not like it, one bit.

02:28:30.059 --> 02:28:32.760
The flappy slippery things.

02:28:32.819 --> 02:28:35.700
She assumed most of them were fish, kept

02:28:35.700 --> 02:28:38.819
touching her, and then not bursting into

02:28:38.819 --> 02:28:41.340
flames, and that was so weird.

02:28:41.399 --> 02:28:44.399
Even the feeling of water all around her

02:28:44.399 --> 02:28:47.760
scales, pressing in on her was extremely

02:28:47.760 --> 02:28:48.420
unsettling.

02:28:48.479 --> 02:28:52.020
She was also not particularly fond of how

02:28:52.020 --> 02:28:53.940
much faster than her turtle could

02:28:53.940 --> 02:28:54.479
suddenly go.

02:28:54.540 --> 02:28:58.200
He powered forward in huge wing beats

02:28:58.200 --> 02:29:01.020
steering gracefully with a current, while

02:29:01.020 --> 02:29:03.540
she flopped around snorting water upper

02:29:03.540 --> 02:29:05.340
snout, and generally feeling like a

02:29:05.340 --> 02:29:05.819
hippo.

02:29:05.879 --> 02:29:09.420
A hippo floated past, eyeing her with

02:29:09.420 --> 02:29:11.100
serene scorn.

02:29:11.159 --> 02:29:14.520
Fine, not like a hippo, like an ostrich

02:29:14.520 --> 02:29:16.440
suddenly plunked in the middle of an

02:29:16.440 --> 02:29:16.860
ocean.

02:29:16.920 --> 02:29:17.879
How about that?

02:29:18.000 --> 02:29:22.020
Far ahead, turtle swerved majestically

02:29:22.020 --> 02:29:24.540
around a bend in the river and clambered

02:29:24.540 --> 02:29:26.520
onto a submerged boulder to wait for

02:29:26.520 --> 02:29:26.639
her.

02:29:26.700 --> 02:29:29.100
Peril floundered toward him.

02:29:29.159 --> 02:29:31.799
Finally finding pebbles below her talons

02:29:31.799 --> 02:29:34.139
and a moment to gasp for breath.

02:29:34.200 --> 02:29:37.139
Couldn't we fly a little closer?

02:29:37.200 --> 02:29:38.340
She spat.

02:29:38.399 --> 02:29:41.940
Not if we want you to arrive incognito.

02:29:42.000 --> 02:29:44.280
Turtle pointed to the increasing number

02:29:44.280 --> 02:29:45.780
of dragons flying overhead.

02:29:45.840 --> 02:29:48.719
The wings flashing in the sky were mostly

02:29:48.719 --> 02:29:51.180
red, orange, or sandy yellow.

02:29:51.239 --> 02:29:53.760
Although peril spotted shades of brown

02:29:53.760 --> 02:29:54.840
and blue up there as well.

02:29:54.899 --> 02:29:56.879
Don't worry.

02:29:56.940 --> 02:29:59.399
Soon we'll be swimming into possibility.

02:29:59.459 --> 02:30:02.100
Hopefully, no one will notice your scales

02:30:02.100 --> 02:30:05.040
underwater, and hopefully we'll be able

02:30:05.040 --> 02:30:06.959
to spot Moon and Kibli from the river.

02:30:07.020 --> 02:30:10.739
He dove back into the river, and peril

02:30:10.739 --> 02:30:12.540
had no choice but to follow him.

02:30:12.600 --> 02:30:15.299
The outskirts of possibility swept up on

02:30:15.299 --> 02:30:16.680
either side of the riverbank.

02:30:16.739 --> 02:30:19.139
These were the smaller dwellings of

02:30:19.139 --> 02:30:20.520
dragons who'd moved to the city

02:30:20.520 --> 02:30:20.940
recently.

02:30:21.000 --> 02:30:24.780
Peril swam past a family of sea wings who

02:30:24.780 --> 02:30:27.420
splashed in the shallows, blue scales

02:30:27.420 --> 02:30:29.399
flickering like broken shards of sky.

02:30:29.520 --> 02:30:32.340
The 2 dragonettes yelped and wrestled

02:30:32.340 --> 02:30:35.280
while their father watched, smiling in a

02:30:35.280 --> 02:30:38.459
way that no one had ever, ever smiled at

02:30:38.459 --> 02:30:38.940
peril.

02:30:39.000 --> 02:30:42.120
A little farther downstream, on the other

02:30:42.120 --> 02:30:44.700
side of the river, 3 mud wings near

02:30:44.700 --> 02:30:46.500
Peril's age were planting a garden.

02:30:46.500 --> 02:30:48.780
The biggest one pointed to a crooked

02:30:48.780 --> 02:30:51.420
furrow, and thwapped one of her siblings

02:30:51.420 --> 02:30:51.959
Bossily.

02:30:52.020 --> 02:30:54.959
Her brother flung a carrot at her, and

02:30:54.959 --> 02:30:56.879
the 3rd sibling giggled until she nearly

02:30:56.879 --> 02:30:57.299
fell over.

02:30:57.360 --> 02:31:00.059
It wasn't until the mud wings were behind

02:31:00.059 --> 02:31:02.879
them that peril realized the littlest

02:31:02.879 --> 02:31:04.440
sister had been missing an arm.

02:31:04.500 --> 02:31:07.739
She took a closer look at the next set of

02:31:07.739 --> 02:31:09.840
dragons they passed and spotted another

02:31:09.840 --> 02:31:12.780
war wound, a scar that ran nearly the

02:31:12.780 --> 02:31:15.540
length of the sky wing's tail, but this

02:31:15.540 --> 02:31:18.239
dragon too was smiling, leaning over to

02:31:18.239 --> 02:31:20.219
show a smaller dragon how to fix a broken

02:31:20.219 --> 02:31:21.000
door frame.

02:31:21.000 --> 02:31:23.219
He must have felt her staring at him

02:31:23.219 --> 02:31:24.959
because he turned his head toward the

02:31:24.959 --> 02:31:27.600
river, but peril submerged her head and

02:31:27.600 --> 02:31:30.299
swam faster, and when she surfaced again

02:31:30.299 --> 02:31:31.799
there was an island between them.

02:31:31.860 --> 02:31:35.579
More islands began to dot the river as it

02:31:35.579 --> 02:31:37.799
widened out and the current slowed

02:31:37.799 --> 02:31:40.920
sometimes trailing into wandering streams

02:31:40.920 --> 02:31:42.840
or muddling about in clumps of tall

02:31:42.840 --> 02:31:43.319
reeds.

02:31:43.379 --> 02:31:46.680
Peril and turtle swam under a bridge

02:31:46.680 --> 02:31:49.440
packed end to end with merchant stalls

02:31:49.440 --> 02:31:52.379
and dragons calling out to customers.

02:31:52.440 --> 02:31:54.299
The finest rugs and possibility.

02:31:54.360 --> 02:31:58.139
The actual finest rugs and possibility.

02:31:58.260 --> 02:32:00.659
Roaster crocodile on sale.

02:32:00.719 --> 02:32:02.040
Don't eat that.

02:32:02.100 --> 02:32:04.440
His crocodile was riding in the streets

02:32:04.440 --> 02:32:05.100
yesterday.

02:32:05.159 --> 02:32:07.739
We have seagulls caught in the air this

02:32:07.739 --> 02:32:07.979
morning.

02:32:08.040 --> 02:32:11.219
The next bridge glowed with bright colors

02:32:11.219 --> 02:32:14.579
and shook with thumping talons as dragons

02:32:14.579 --> 02:32:15.840
danced along its length.

02:32:15.899 --> 02:32:18.840
Peril could feel the music vibrating in

02:32:18.840 --> 02:32:19.620
the water around her.

02:32:19.680 --> 02:32:22.379
Beaten silver circles hung from the

02:32:22.379 --> 02:32:24.600
railings, and under the bridge like giant

02:32:24.600 --> 02:32:25.079
coins.

02:32:25.200 --> 02:32:29.579
A full moon festival, Turtle said, popping

02:32:29.579 --> 02:32:31.079
his head out of the water right next to

02:32:31.079 --> 02:32:31.260
her.

02:32:31.319 --> 02:32:34.739
It used to be a sand wing tradition, but

02:32:34.739 --> 02:32:35.700
they didn't have much time for them

02:32:35.700 --> 02:32:36.299
during the war.

02:32:36.420 --> 02:32:38.459
I heard they were coming back.

02:32:38.520 --> 02:32:41.940
Peril floated under the bridge, watching

02:32:41.940 --> 02:32:44.520
the whirling dragons overhead, as they

02:32:44.520 --> 02:32:46.379
clapped their wings and twined their

02:32:46.379 --> 02:32:46.860
tails together.

02:32:46.979 --> 02:32:49.620
She would never dance in a crowd like

02:32:49.620 --> 02:32:53.040
that, wearing bangles of silver moons, and

02:32:53.040 --> 02:32:54.659
singing until her voice cracked.

02:32:54.719 --> 02:32:57.719
She would never paint huge canvases side

02:32:57.719 --> 02:33:00.360
by side with other sky wings, and sand

02:33:00.360 --> 02:33:03.120
wings, dipping their tails into the same

02:33:03.120 --> 02:33:05.879
buckets of moonlit white, and midnight

02:33:05.879 --> 02:33:08.579
blue paint, and laughing as it spattered

02:33:08.579 --> 02:33:10.139
across their claws and snouts.

02:33:10.200 --> 02:33:14.040
She'd been in this town only 4 months ago

02:33:14.040 --> 02:33:16.739
searching for scarlet, but something was

02:33:16.739 --> 02:33:17.219
different now.

02:33:17.280 --> 02:33:20.700
It felt lighter and more open than before

02:33:20.700 --> 02:33:23.100
as if the war was starting to melt away

02:33:23.100 --> 02:33:25.739
as if their world was starting to feel

02:33:25.739 --> 02:33:28.739
safer under thorn and ruby than it ever

02:33:28.739 --> 02:33:30.299
had been with burn and scarlet.

02:33:30.360 --> 02:33:32.399
But it's not safe.

02:33:32.459 --> 02:33:35.340
Not as long as Queen Scarlet is still out

02:33:35.340 --> 02:33:35.879
there.

02:33:35.940 --> 02:33:37.500
Smoldering with hate.

02:33:37.559 --> 02:33:41.040
Moon should be easy to spot here, Turtle

02:33:41.040 --> 02:33:41.280
said.

02:33:41.340 --> 02:33:43.920
His snout half buried in the water, so

02:33:43.920 --> 02:33:45.420
his voice rose through bubbles.

02:33:45.479 --> 02:33:47.760
Not a lot of night wings around.

02:33:47.819 --> 02:33:51.120
No night wings at all that peril could

02:33:51.120 --> 02:33:51.479
see.

02:33:51.540 --> 02:33:53.219
She wondered if they knew about this

02:33:53.219 --> 02:33:55.500
place, and whether any of them would

02:33:55.500 --> 02:33:56.760
eventually choose to come here.

02:33:56.819 --> 02:33:59.639
It wouldn't suit their tribal air of

02:33:59.639 --> 02:34:01.860
mystery, mingling with so many other

02:34:01.860 --> 02:34:02.940
dragons like this.

02:34:03.000 --> 02:34:06.120
But on the other talent, it might give

02:34:06.120 --> 02:34:07.979
them more self-respect than living under

02:34:07.979 --> 02:34:09.719
a rain wing queen's claws.

02:34:09.780 --> 02:34:12.180
She'd never been to the rainforest

02:34:12.180 --> 02:34:12.540
herself.

02:34:12.600 --> 02:34:15.600
Clay had strongly discouraged the idea

02:34:15.600 --> 02:34:18.360
saying something about how many trees

02:34:18.360 --> 02:34:21.180
there were and forest fires and blah, blah

02:34:21.180 --> 02:34:22.739
blah, but that was fine.

02:34:22.799 --> 02:34:25.079
Peril was sure she wouldn't like feeling

02:34:25.079 --> 02:34:26.459
so hemmed in anyway.

02:34:26.520 --> 02:34:28.620
It sounded claustrophobic.

02:34:28.680 --> 02:34:31.680
Plus, full of dragons who could sneak up

02:34:31.680 --> 02:34:34.139
on you with like, invisibility scales.

02:34:34.200 --> 02:34:37.500
That sounded absolutely creepy.

02:34:37.559 --> 02:34:39.959
Not to mention that Queen Glory was far

02:34:39.959 --> 02:34:41.459
from peril's biggest fan.

02:34:41.520 --> 02:34:44.639
The drums and zithers of the full moon

02:34:44.639 --> 02:34:46.500
festival were starting to fade behind

02:34:46.500 --> 02:34:49.079
them, and peril could see glimmers of the

02:34:49.079 --> 02:34:50.280
open bay ahead in the distance.

02:34:50.340 --> 02:34:53.819
This part of possibility seemed to have

02:34:53.819 --> 02:34:56.819
older, bigger, sturdier buildings set

02:34:56.819 --> 02:34:58.920
around open, cobblestoned plazas.

02:34:58.979 --> 02:35:01.260
The palm trees looked more deliberately

02:35:01.260 --> 02:35:04.020
spaced, casting strategic patches of

02:35:04.020 --> 02:35:06.780
shade, bright yellow trumpet shaped

02:35:06.780 --> 02:35:09.360
flowers swarmed along dark green vines

02:35:09.360 --> 02:35:11.399
that seemed to be tangled everywhere.

02:35:12.120 --> 02:35:15.659
Wait, Turtle said, turning so suddenly

02:35:15.659 --> 02:35:17.639
that he splashed water up Peril's nose

02:35:17.639 --> 02:35:19.920
she backpedaled against the current

02:35:19.920 --> 02:35:20.760
scowling at him.

02:35:20.819 --> 02:35:22.020
What?

02:35:22.020 --> 02:35:22.620
she said.

02:35:22.739 --> 02:35:24.120
Can we give up now?

02:35:24.180 --> 02:35:26.159
We could just fly over the town.

02:35:26.219 --> 02:35:28.620
It'll be easier to spot a black dragon

02:35:28.620 --> 02:35:29.639
from up there anyhow.

02:35:29.700 --> 02:35:31.860
It's not like anyone is going to come up

02:35:31.860 --> 02:35:32.639
and try to fight me.

02:35:32.700 --> 02:35:36.000
I thought I saw Kibley, Turtle said.

02:35:36.059 --> 02:35:38.459
He spread his wings to float in a circle

02:35:38.459 --> 02:35:40.379
and craned his neck, peering at the

02:35:40.379 --> 02:35:41.639
dragons along the waterfront.

02:35:41.700 --> 02:35:45.059
Those sand wings over there, arguing with

02:35:45.059 --> 02:35:45.899
the red sky wing.

02:35:46.020 --> 02:35:48.059
Doesn't one of them look like Kibley?

02:35:48.120 --> 02:35:50.700
Pearl realized that she didn't have the

02:35:50.700 --> 02:35:52.739
faintest idea what Kibley looked like.

02:35:52.799 --> 02:35:54.420
Had she ever met him before?

02:35:54.479 --> 02:35:57.000
All sand wings looked pretty much the

02:35:57.000 --> 02:35:57.540
same to her.

02:35:57.659 --> 02:36:00.540
Apart from Sonny, of course, who had

02:36:00.540 --> 02:36:02.940
oddly colored scales and a perpetually

02:36:02.940 --> 02:36:05.219
cheerful expression that was just asking

02:36:05.219 --> 02:36:06.299
to be clawed off.

02:36:06.420 --> 02:36:08.879
Uh, sure?

02:36:08.940 --> 02:36:10.559
Let's go see.

02:36:10.620 --> 02:36:13.139
Turtle charged out of the river before

02:36:13.139 --> 02:36:14.159
peril could argue.

02:36:14.280 --> 02:36:17.100
His emerald green tail left a slick wet

02:36:17.100 --> 02:36:18.540
path on the cobblestones behind him.

02:36:18.600 --> 02:36:22.379
She scanned the nearby dragons, but they

02:36:22.379 --> 02:36:23.819
were all focused on their own business.

02:36:23.879 --> 02:36:25.500
No one was watching the river.

02:36:25.559 --> 02:36:29.040
And now she could see the dragon's turtle

02:36:29.040 --> 02:36:29.520
was aiming for.

02:36:29.579 --> 02:36:32.219
The red sky wings stood with his wings

02:36:32.219 --> 02:36:34.319
folded back, and his head cocked

02:36:34.319 --> 02:36:36.780
arrogantly at the 2 burly sand wings in

02:36:36.780 --> 02:36:39.000
front of him, one of whom was lashing her

02:36:39.000 --> 02:36:39.780
menacing tail.

02:36:39.840 --> 02:36:43.020
Both sand wings were wearing medallions

02:36:43.020 --> 02:36:44.940
around their necks, stamped with the

02:36:44.940 --> 02:36:45.899
image of a large bird.

02:36:45.959 --> 02:36:48.479
Arranged on the stones around their

02:36:48.479 --> 02:36:51.420
talons, were several odd looking, brownish

02:36:51.420 --> 02:36:53.879
greenish pink spheres, studded with

02:36:53.879 --> 02:36:54.540
little spikes.

02:36:54.600 --> 02:36:57.659
Pearl slithered out of the water and

02:36:57.659 --> 02:36:59.819
hurried after turtle, keeping her head

02:36:59.819 --> 02:37:01.799
low, and her wings tucked in close.

02:37:01.860 --> 02:37:05.879
You said 30, she heard the bigger sand

02:37:05.879 --> 02:37:06.659
wing yell.

02:37:06.719 --> 02:37:08.040
That was the agreement.

02:37:08.100 --> 02:37:11.219
You are welcome to come to the mountains

02:37:11.219 --> 02:37:13.620
and try harvesting these yourself, spat

02:37:13.620 --> 02:37:14.940
the sky wing.

02:37:15.000 --> 02:37:16.260
It is much more difficult than your

02:37:16.260 --> 02:37:18.180
paltry pouch of gold would cover.

02:37:18.299 --> 02:37:20.280
Let's just take them.

02:37:20.340 --> 02:37:22.620
The male Sandwing growled.

02:37:22.680 --> 02:37:25.260
He won't be pleased, and you know it.

02:37:25.379 --> 02:37:26.879
His partner snapped.

02:37:26.940 --> 02:37:29.760
Turtle paused several feet away from them

02:37:29.760 --> 02:37:31.860
and turned back to peril, shaking his

02:37:31.860 --> 02:37:32.040
head.

02:37:32.100 --> 02:37:34.620
Not Kibley.

02:37:34.680 --> 02:37:38.100
She stopped too, in the most empty patch

02:37:38.100 --> 02:37:38.940
of stone she could find.

02:37:39.059 --> 02:37:42.120
From here, the plaza became cluttered

02:37:42.120 --> 02:37:44.459
with wares spread on carpets, flowers

02:37:44.459 --> 02:37:47.520
growing out of window boxes, and dragons

02:37:47.520 --> 02:37:49.799
blithely trampling around everywhere

02:37:49.799 --> 02:37:51.959
without worrying at all about whose

02:37:51.959 --> 02:37:53.639
scales they might blunder into.

02:37:53.700 --> 02:37:57.360
Danger tingled just beyond peril's

02:37:57.360 --> 02:37:57.540
reach.

02:37:57.600 --> 02:37:59.940
She could sense all the terrible things

02:37:59.940 --> 02:38:02.219
that might happen if she stepped any

02:38:02.219 --> 02:38:03.239
farther into the town.

02:38:03.299 --> 02:38:06.780
She needed to get back to the river, where

02:38:06.780 --> 02:38:07.920
she wouldn't be such a threat.

02:38:07.979 --> 02:38:10.739
She glanced around and began to

02:38:10.739 --> 02:38:13.440
cautiously turn, keeping her tail curled

02:38:13.440 --> 02:38:14.159
safely in.

02:38:14.219 --> 02:38:18.299
And then, one of the sand wings muttered

02:38:18.299 --> 02:38:20.579
something furious and kicked one of the

02:38:20.579 --> 02:38:20.940
spheres.

02:38:21.000 --> 02:38:25.739
Oh, it's a cactus, Peril realized

02:38:25.739 --> 02:38:28.020
spotting the roots as it bounced across

02:38:28.020 --> 02:38:29.040
the stones toward her.

02:38:29.100 --> 02:38:31.319
I've seen those in the mountains, I

02:38:31.319 --> 02:38:31.739
think.

02:38:31.799 --> 02:38:33.540
She glanced up.

02:38:33.600 --> 02:38:37.020
And the last thing peril saw was turtle's

02:38:37.020 --> 02:38:39.959
green eyes widening, as the sphere rolled

02:38:39.959 --> 02:38:42.600
up to her talons, brushed against her

02:38:42.600 --> 02:38:46.500
scales, and exploded in an enormous

02:38:46.500 --> 02:38:47.280
fireball.

02:38:47.340 --> 02:38:51.659
Chapter 8.

02:38:51.719 --> 02:38:55.139
Peril came too, because her body decided

02:38:55.139 --> 02:38:55.860
not to drown.

02:38:55.920 --> 02:38:59.040
She surged up out of the water, where the

02:38:59.040 --> 02:39:00.959
explosion had thrown her, coughing and

02:39:00.959 --> 02:39:03.239
sputtering, into a cloud of thick black

02:39:03.239 --> 02:39:05.700
smoke that was not particularly fun to

02:39:05.700 --> 02:39:06.420
breathe either.

02:39:06.479 --> 02:39:08.940
Her eyes were stinging, and everything

02:39:08.940 --> 02:39:10.440
was blurry and muffled.

02:39:10.500 --> 02:39:12.479
But she could see there were dragons

02:39:12.479 --> 02:39:14.940
yelling and screaming all along the bank

02:39:14.940 --> 02:39:17.819
and more flapping in from the rooftops.

02:39:17.879 --> 02:39:19.920
At least 3 dragons were rolling in the

02:39:19.920 --> 02:39:21.899
river with scorch marks on their scales.

02:39:21.959 --> 02:39:24.780
Small fires flickered in the smoke all

02:39:24.780 --> 02:39:25.739
across the courtyard.

02:39:25.799 --> 02:39:27.959
She wasn't burned.

02:39:28.020 --> 02:39:31.319
Her scales couldn't burn, but there were

02:39:31.319 --> 02:39:34.379
incredibly sharp blossoms of pain spiking

02:39:34.379 --> 02:39:35.879
all up and down her body.

02:39:35.940 --> 02:39:37.620
What was this?

02:39:37.680 --> 02:39:39.659
Why did it hurt so much?

02:39:39.719 --> 02:39:42.239
Who could she set on fire to make it

02:39:42.239 --> 02:39:42.600
stop?

02:39:42.719 --> 02:39:46.379
She roared her agony as loud as she could

02:39:46.379 --> 02:39:48.780
but it made barely a scratch in the

02:39:48.780 --> 02:39:50.159
jangling chaos all around.

02:39:50.219 --> 02:39:53.700
A dragon suddenly came galloping into the

02:39:53.700 --> 02:39:56.219
river beside her, and she jumped back

02:39:56.219 --> 02:39:58.139
hissing at him before she recognized

02:39:58.139 --> 02:39:58.680
Turtle.

02:39:58.739 --> 02:40:03.600
You, he said, shaking his head, are

02:40:03.600 --> 02:40:06.360
without question, the least stealthy

02:40:06.360 --> 02:40:08.100
dragon in all of Pyria.

02:40:08.159 --> 02:40:11.700
That wasn't my fault, she snarled

02:40:11.700 --> 02:40:12.899
writhing in pain.

02:40:12.959 --> 02:40:15.659
Nothing had ever managed to hurt her like

02:40:15.659 --> 02:40:15.840
this.

02:40:15.899 --> 02:40:18.899
There were tiny teeth eating under her

02:40:18.899 --> 02:40:19.440
scales.

02:40:19.500 --> 02:40:22.979
Everything hurts, and I hate the world.

02:40:23.100 --> 02:40:26.219
Let's find a safer place to be before

02:40:26.219 --> 02:40:28.200
someone sees you and connects the dots

02:40:28.200 --> 02:40:29.459
Turtle said.

02:40:29.520 --> 02:40:32.520
She realized that trickles of blood were

02:40:32.520 --> 02:40:34.200
running down his shoulders and along his

02:40:34.200 --> 02:40:34.739
tail.

02:40:34.799 --> 02:40:37.500
He waded into the water until it covered

02:40:37.500 --> 02:40:39.360
everything but his head and began

02:40:39.360 --> 02:40:42.000
swimming upstream, back toward the full

02:40:42.000 --> 02:40:43.020
moon festival bridge.

02:40:43.079 --> 02:40:47.159
It was agony to move, but she did

02:40:47.159 --> 02:40:49.680
flailing after him, and hoping the smoke

02:40:49.680 --> 02:40:51.719
would hide her shining copper scales.

02:40:51.780 --> 02:40:54.719
Turtle finally coasted to a stop in

02:40:54.719 --> 02:40:57.180
clearer air on the muddy bank of one of

02:40:57.180 --> 02:40:59.520
the small islands, not far from where the

02:40:59.520 --> 02:41:01.979
festival music was still going on, he

02:41:01.979 --> 02:41:03.780
pulled himself half onto the shore

02:41:03.780 --> 02:41:06.540
wincing, and peril crawled up into the

02:41:06.540 --> 02:41:08.639
mud as far away from him as she could.

02:41:08.639 --> 02:41:11.760
The reeds and shrubs below her curled

02:41:11.760 --> 02:41:14.700
into a dark scorched mess, but she was in

02:41:14.700 --> 02:41:16.860
too much pain to worry about it.

02:41:16.920 --> 02:41:18.659
She wondered if this was what being on

02:41:18.659 --> 02:41:20.819
fire felt like to other dragons.

02:41:20.879 --> 02:41:22.680
Why?

02:41:22.680 --> 02:41:23.760
she growled.

02:41:23.819 --> 02:41:25.319
What is happening?

02:41:25.379 --> 02:41:29.219
It was a dragon flame cactus, Turtle

02:41:29.219 --> 02:41:29.399
said.

02:41:29.459 --> 02:41:31.860
He twisted and started to pry at

02:41:31.860 --> 02:41:34.079
something stuck under his left wing in a

02:41:34.079 --> 02:41:34.920
small pool of blood.

02:41:34.979 --> 02:41:37.920
Like the one that exploded in the history

02:41:37.920 --> 02:41:38.879
cave at school.

02:41:38.940 --> 02:41:41.520
I have no idea why anyone would want to

02:41:41.520 --> 02:41:43.079
buy one now that the war is over.

02:41:43.139 --> 02:41:46.979
They didn't want to buy just one, peril

02:41:46.979 --> 02:41:47.579
remembered.

02:41:47.639 --> 02:41:48.899
They wanted to buy 30.

02:41:49.200 --> 02:41:52.260
Whatever their reason was, she thought

02:41:52.260 --> 02:41:54.239
perhaps burning out their eyeballs would

02:41:54.239 --> 02:41:55.260
make her feel better.

02:41:55.319 --> 02:41:58.139
Turtle extracted the object from his

02:41:58.139 --> 02:41:59.819
scales and held it out for her to see.

02:41:59.879 --> 02:42:03.600
It's like a little ball of thorns, he

02:42:03.600 --> 02:42:03.899
said.

02:42:03.959 --> 02:42:06.780
The dragon flame cactus seed pod.

02:42:06.840 --> 02:42:09.420
You have about 100 of them stuck all over

02:42:09.420 --> 02:42:11.700
you, since it exploded right at your feet

02:42:11.700 --> 02:42:13.200
but I don't know what to do.

02:42:13.260 --> 02:42:15.420
I can't pull them out of your scales

02:42:15.420 --> 02:42:17.879
without getting burned, but we can't

02:42:17.879 --> 02:42:18.299
leave them.

02:42:18.360 --> 02:42:19.739
Oh.

02:42:20.040 --> 02:42:22.379
He trailed off, staring at her.

02:42:22.440 --> 02:42:23.579
What?

02:42:23.700 --> 02:42:24.959
Carol demanded.

02:42:25.020 --> 02:42:27.420
She was starting to feel a little better

02:42:27.420 --> 02:42:29.040
maybe, now that she was out of the

02:42:29.040 --> 02:42:29.639
water.

02:42:29.819 --> 02:42:33.180
They're burning up, Turtle explained.

02:42:33.239 --> 02:42:35.579
Your scales are burning the seed pods

02:42:35.579 --> 02:42:35.819
away.

02:42:35.879 --> 02:42:39.540
Peril held out one front leg and saw a

02:42:39.540 --> 02:42:41.700
ball of thorns embedded between our claws

02:42:41.700 --> 02:42:44.219
right before it caught fire and shriveled

02:42:44.219 --> 02:42:45.180
into black ash.

02:42:45.239 --> 02:42:47.520
That's right, she said.

02:42:47.579 --> 02:42:50.399
Die, you little monster plants.

02:42:50.459 --> 02:42:53.159
May your roots always be thirsty, and

02:42:53.159 --> 02:42:55.440
your seeds all meet a fiery death until

02:42:55.440 --> 02:42:56.760
you're extinct forever.

02:42:56.819 --> 02:42:57.600
I hate you.

02:42:57.659 --> 02:42:59.639
Yow.

02:42:59.700 --> 02:43:00.899
Turtle said.

02:43:00.959 --> 02:43:04.559
You don't ever have mild feelings, do

02:43:04.559 --> 02:43:04.799
you?

02:43:04.860 --> 02:43:07.860
Peril wasn't sure what a mild feeling

02:43:07.860 --> 02:43:08.579
would feel like.

02:43:08.639 --> 02:43:11.760
She turned to blink downriver at the

02:43:11.760 --> 02:43:13.979
pillar of black smoke rising from the

02:43:13.979 --> 02:43:14.760
distant courtyard.

02:43:14.879 --> 02:43:21.059
Was, um, did you see if the explosion, uh

02:43:21.059 --> 02:43:23.579
peril trailed off?

02:43:23.639 --> 02:43:25.920
I don't think anyone was killed, Turtle

02:43:25.920 --> 02:43:26.159
said.

02:43:26.219 --> 02:43:28.559
It looked like your body blocked the

02:43:28.559 --> 02:43:30.659
worst of the fire and caught most of the

02:43:30.659 --> 02:43:31.440
seed pods.

02:43:31.500 --> 02:43:33.899
I saw other dragons injured, but nobody

02:43:33.899 --> 02:43:36.719
liked nobody liked carnelian.

02:43:36.780 --> 02:43:38.940
Peril finished.

02:43:39.000 --> 02:43:40.379
She tried to hide the relief in her

02:43:40.379 --> 02:43:40.620
voice.

02:43:40.680 --> 02:43:43.139
Although Clay would forgive her for an

02:43:43.139 --> 02:43:45.479
accident, surely, even if someone had

02:43:45.479 --> 02:43:45.780
died.

02:43:45.840 --> 02:43:49.139
It wouldn't really be her fault, except

02:43:49.139 --> 02:43:50.760
in the sense that everything was her

02:43:50.760 --> 02:43:53.280
fault because she was a walking menace to

02:43:53.280 --> 02:43:54.360
the entire universe.

02:43:54.479 --> 02:43:57.479
Anyway, peril said indignantly.

02:43:57.540 --> 02:44:00.000
What kind of idiot spreads a bunch of

02:44:00.000 --> 02:44:02.159
flammable cacti all over the street?

02:44:02.219 --> 02:44:04.260
Anyone could have set one of those off by

02:44:04.260 --> 02:44:04.739
accident.

02:44:04.799 --> 02:44:07.860
Not a sea wing, Turtle said

02:44:07.860 --> 02:44:08.399
thoughtfully.

02:44:08.459 --> 02:44:10.200
Or an ice wing?

02:44:10.260 --> 02:44:13.620
Oh, hey, now we know one more thing that

02:44:13.620 --> 02:44:14.340
can't kill you.

02:44:14.399 --> 02:44:17.040
They shouldn't be allowed to sell things

02:44:17.040 --> 02:44:18.180
like that to just anyone.

02:44:18.299 --> 02:44:21.180
Pearl went on, ignoring him.

02:44:21.239 --> 02:44:23.040
She twitched her tail around to check for

02:44:23.040 --> 02:44:25.079
any more thorns, but they all seem to be

02:44:25.079 --> 02:44:25.200
gone.

02:44:25.260 --> 02:44:28.739
Would they sell a sword to any dragon who

02:44:28.739 --> 02:44:29.159
came along?

02:44:29.219 --> 02:44:31.979
Um, Turtle said.

02:44:32.040 --> 02:44:33.120
Yes.

02:44:33.180 --> 02:44:36.239
His smile fell off his face as he winced

02:44:36.239 --> 02:44:36.600
again.

02:44:36.659 --> 02:44:39.299
Another ball of thorns was dripping blood

02:44:39.299 --> 02:44:41.579
down his tail, but he couldn't twist far

02:44:41.579 --> 02:44:42.239
enough to reach it.

02:44:42.299 --> 02:44:46.139
I could set it on fire, Pearl offered

02:44:46.139 --> 02:44:48.479
spreading her claws, but it might burn

02:44:48.479 --> 02:44:49.020
you a little bit.

02:44:49.079 --> 02:44:50.700
I don't know if that would be worse.

02:44:50.819 --> 02:44:53.579
Turtle thought for a moment, then

02:44:53.579 --> 02:44:54.780
shuffled a step toward her.

02:44:54.840 --> 02:44:56.700
Yes, do it.

02:44:56.760 --> 02:44:59.700
If I jump straight into the river after.

02:44:59.760 --> 02:45:00.239
I'll be fine.

02:45:00.299 --> 02:45:03.479
Peril hadn't actually expected him to say

02:45:03.479 --> 02:45:03.840
yes.

02:45:03.899 --> 02:45:06.120
Nobody ever let her help with anything.

02:45:06.180 --> 02:45:09.180
Even Clay usually got sort of flappy and

02:45:09.180 --> 02:45:10.379
nervous whenever she offered.

02:45:10.440 --> 02:45:12.840
She folded her wings back and reached

02:45:12.840 --> 02:45:14.940
forward tentatively with one claw.

02:45:15.000 --> 02:45:17.819
Turtle closed his eyes, frozen in place.

02:45:17.879 --> 02:45:21.239
Peril's claw lightly brushed the thorny

02:45:21.239 --> 02:45:23.459
seed pod, and it burst into flames.

02:45:23.520 --> 02:45:26.700
Immediately, she saw a dark scorched

02:45:26.700 --> 02:45:28.739
patch start to spread where the thorns

02:45:28.739 --> 02:45:31.139
touched turtle's scales, but she only

02:45:31.139 --> 02:45:33.479
caught a glimpse of it before turtle dove

02:45:33.479 --> 02:45:35.219
into the water and swam to the bottom.

02:45:35.280 --> 02:45:38.579
She paced along the bank, trying to

02:45:38.579 --> 02:45:39.899
squint at him through the shifting

02:45:39.899 --> 02:45:40.379
reflections.

02:45:40.440 --> 02:45:43.379
He was a huddled green lump at the bottom

02:45:43.379 --> 02:45:45.659
of the river for way too long.

02:45:45.719 --> 02:45:47.639
It made her own lungs ache to wait for

02:45:47.639 --> 02:45:50.340
him, but he was clearly fine, definitely

02:45:50.340 --> 02:45:52.979
moving, and fiddling with something that

02:45:52.979 --> 02:45:54.000
flashed white gray.

02:45:54.059 --> 02:45:55.379
Weird.

02:45:55.440 --> 02:45:59.159
Finally, he surfaced, spraying water out

02:45:59.159 --> 02:46:01.739
of his nose and looking extremely pleased

02:46:01.739 --> 02:46:02.340
with himself.

02:46:02.399 --> 02:46:05.219
Parel's eyes went straight to the spot

02:46:05.219 --> 02:46:06.360
where she'd burned him.

02:46:06.420 --> 02:46:09.120
But there was no scorch mark there

02:46:09.120 --> 02:46:09.420
anymore.

02:46:09.479 --> 02:46:12.659
His scales looked whole and unblemished

02:46:12.659 --> 02:46:15.600
all over, as if neither fire nor thorns

02:46:15.600 --> 02:46:16.559
had ever wounded him.

02:46:16.620 --> 02:46:18.959
She couldn't even figure out where the

02:46:18.959 --> 02:46:20.100
seed pods had been.

02:46:20.159 --> 02:46:22.200
How did you do that?

02:46:22.260 --> 02:46:24.059
she demanded.

02:46:24.120 --> 02:46:25.860
Water doesn't heal sea wings that

02:46:25.860 --> 02:46:26.159
quickly.

02:46:26.219 --> 02:46:29.639
It wasn't that bad, Turtle said with a

02:46:29.639 --> 02:46:30.000
shrug.

02:46:30.059 --> 02:46:31.079
I'm fine.

02:46:31.139 --> 02:46:32.040
Don't worry.

02:46:32.100 --> 02:46:33.719
I'm not worried.

02:46:33.780 --> 02:46:37.799
I'm deeply suspicious. peril clarified.

02:46:37.860 --> 02:46:40.319
That's not normal scale behavior right

02:46:40.319 --> 02:46:40.500
there.

02:46:40.559 --> 02:46:42.299
Turtle?

02:46:42.360 --> 02:46:44.940
They both jumped at the voice that came

02:46:44.940 --> 02:46:45.659
from the sky.

02:46:45.719 --> 02:46:47.940
Peril realized she'd been watching

02:46:47.940 --> 02:46:49.139
turtles so closely.

02:46:49.200 --> 02:46:50.760
She hadn't kept an eye out for

02:46:50.760 --> 02:46:53.100
approaching danger, or anyone who might

02:46:53.100 --> 02:46:55.260
realize she'd set off the cactus.

02:46:55.319 --> 02:46:57.180
Genius peril.

02:46:57.239 --> 02:46:59.639
If there is an animus night wing stalking

02:46:59.639 --> 02:47:01.739
you, you're making it pretty easy for

02:47:01.739 --> 02:47:02.459
him.

02:47:02.520 --> 02:47:05.100
But the dragon above them was a sandwing

02:47:05.100 --> 02:47:07.739
and Turtle gave a cry of delight when he

02:47:07.739 --> 02:47:08.100
saw him.

02:47:08.159 --> 02:47:10.079
Kibli!

02:47:10.200 --> 02:47:12.239
Turtle leaped into the air and nearly

02:47:12.239 --> 02:47:13.979
bowled him out of the sky.

02:47:14.040 --> 02:47:15.420
They swooped around each other for a

02:47:15.420 --> 02:47:17.579
moment, doing cheerful flips in the air

02:47:17.579 --> 02:47:20.159
and thumping one another's wings, which

02:47:20.159 --> 02:47:21.840
appeared to be some kind of code for

02:47:21.840 --> 02:47:22.860
happy to see you.

02:47:22.979 --> 02:47:26.340
A moment later, a small night wing came

02:47:26.340 --> 02:47:27.899
soaring over from the direction of the

02:47:27.899 --> 02:47:30.420
explosion, and Turtle made more dopey

02:47:30.420 --> 02:47:31.440
delighted noises at her.

02:47:31.500 --> 02:47:34.319
I guess we found his friends.

02:47:34.379 --> 02:47:37.500
Carol flicked her tail and accidentally

02:47:37.500 --> 02:47:38.700
splashed herself in the face.

02:47:38.760 --> 02:47:41.700
Probably thanks to me, by the way.

02:47:41.760 --> 02:47:44.760
I bet they came to check out the fire.

02:47:44.819 --> 02:47:46.979
I wonder if Turtle will realize that.

02:47:47.100 --> 02:47:50.340
She stood up and paced in a circle in the

02:47:50.340 --> 02:47:50.700
mud.

02:47:50.760 --> 02:47:53.280
All the places she'd been stabbed with

02:47:53.280 --> 02:47:55.860
thorns still hurt, but at least the seed

02:47:55.860 --> 02:47:56.520
pods were gone.

02:47:56.579 --> 02:47:59.399
Maybe she should fly away before Turtle

02:47:59.399 --> 02:48:00.959
came down with his judgmental friends.

02:48:01.020 --> 02:48:03.479
Maybe she didn't need anyone else to look

02:48:03.479 --> 02:48:04.559
for Scarlet anyhow.

02:48:04.620 --> 02:48:06.239
But it was too late.

02:48:06.299 --> 02:48:09.000
Green and black and yellow wings were

02:48:09.000 --> 02:48:11.340
descending toward the island, along with

02:48:11.340 --> 02:48:13.979
3 dragon faces that ranged from friendly

02:48:13.979 --> 02:48:16.620
through wary, and straight on to hostel.

02:48:16.680 --> 02:48:20.100
Which is fine, Peril thought, meeting

02:48:20.100 --> 02:48:22.139
Kibley's eyes with all the fires she

02:48:22.139 --> 02:48:23.100
could put into hers.

02:48:23.159 --> 02:48:25.319
I am prepared to dislike you too.

02:48:25.379 --> 02:48:27.120
Who cares what you think?

02:48:27.180 --> 02:48:30.120
Are you the most dangerous dragon in

02:48:30.120 --> 02:48:30.780
Pyrea?

02:48:30.840 --> 02:48:33.000
No, I think not.

02:48:33.059 --> 02:48:37.319
Peril, this is Moon and Cubli, said

02:48:37.319 --> 02:48:39.959
Turtle, beaming all over his stupid round

02:48:39.959 --> 02:48:42.059
face, as if this should be the most

02:48:42.059 --> 02:48:43.920
delightful thing that had ever happened

02:48:43.920 --> 02:48:44.819
to any of them.

02:48:44.879 --> 02:48:47.639
She couldn't remember noticing either of

02:48:47.639 --> 02:48:48.540
these dragons before.

02:48:48.659 --> 02:48:51.840
They looked completely ordinary, not like

02:48:51.840 --> 02:48:54.000
anyone worth crossing an entire continent

02:48:54.000 --> 02:48:56.819
to find, not like dragons who are so much

02:48:56.819 --> 02:48:58.500
more awesome to be friends with than

02:48:58.500 --> 02:48:58.680
her.

02:48:58.739 --> 02:49:01.680
The night wing had a glittering silver

02:49:01.680 --> 02:49:03.780
scale at the corners of each eye, like

02:49:03.780 --> 02:49:06.059
teardrops, and little furrows in her

02:49:06.059 --> 02:49:07.860
forehead as though she had a perpetual

02:49:07.860 --> 02:49:08.219
headache.

02:49:08.280 --> 02:49:10.979
Now that everyone knew Nightwings didn't

02:49:10.979 --> 02:49:13.440
have powers after all, Peril was sure

02:49:13.440 --> 02:49:15.239
Moon would be an easy opponent to take

02:49:15.239 --> 02:49:16.079
down in the arena.

02:49:16.139 --> 02:49:19.319
Hypothetically, if there still had been

02:49:19.319 --> 02:49:20.700
an arena, of course.

02:49:20.760 --> 02:49:22.920
The sand wing didn't look like much of a

02:49:22.920 --> 02:49:25.200
threat either, apart from that venomous

02:49:25.200 --> 02:49:25.500
tale.

02:49:25.559 --> 02:49:28.440
Peril had been in plenty of fights where

02:49:28.440 --> 02:49:30.899
her 1st move was grabbing a sand wings

02:49:30.899 --> 02:49:32.700
tail to burn off the barb at the end.

02:49:32.760 --> 02:49:35.040
As long as Scarlet didn't need her to

02:49:35.040 --> 02:49:37.559
drag out the fight, most sand wings only

02:49:37.559 --> 02:49:38.760
took a few minutes to defeat.

02:49:38.819 --> 02:49:41.340
No doubt this one was pretty dim and

02:49:41.340 --> 02:49:42.360
correspondingly slow.

02:49:42.420 --> 02:49:46.440
You're wrong about that, Moon said.

02:49:46.500 --> 02:49:48.659
Peril shifted her gaze to the black

02:49:48.659 --> 02:49:51.420
dragon, who was studying peril intently.

02:49:51.479 --> 02:49:52.020
What?

02:49:52.079 --> 02:49:53.159
Pearl asked.

02:49:53.219 --> 02:49:56.399
Kibley is probably one of the smartest

02:49:56.399 --> 02:49:58.920
dragons Empirea, Moon answered.

02:49:58.979 --> 02:50:01.079
I bet he's already figured out 5

02:50:01.079 --> 02:50:02.819
different ways to defeat you right here

02:50:02.819 --> 02:50:03.479
if you needed to.

02:50:03.540 --> 02:50:07.020
Kibli cocked his head, and gave Moon a

02:50:07.020 --> 02:50:08.100
delighted sideways smile.

02:50:08.159 --> 02:50:11.040
Only 3 so far, he said.

02:50:11.100 --> 02:50:11.819
But thanks.

02:50:11.879 --> 02:50:15.000
Peril blinked at moon, feeling like

02:50:15.000 --> 02:50:17.040
little dragon flame cacti were going off

02:50:17.040 --> 02:50:18.000
inside her head.

02:50:18.299 --> 02:50:19.139
Did you?

02:50:19.200 --> 02:50:23.219
But, Yes, Moon said.

02:50:23.280 --> 02:50:26.100
I'm a mind reader, so you should probably

02:50:26.100 --> 02:50:28.500
stop thinking about how exactly you would

02:50:28.500 --> 02:50:29.819
kill us if you needed to.

02:50:29.879 --> 02:50:32.100
Was she really?

02:50:32.159 --> 02:50:34.620
Turtle said. sounding perfectly

02:50:34.620 --> 02:50:37.559
astonished, as if that wasn't the 1st

02:50:37.559 --> 02:50:39.479
thing most dragons thought about when

02:50:39.479 --> 02:50:40.979
they met dragons outside their own

02:50:40.979 --> 02:50:41.520
tribes.

02:50:41.639 --> 02:50:43.260
Wasn't it?

02:50:43.319 --> 02:50:45.959
Peril whipped her head around to glare at

02:50:45.959 --> 02:50:46.379
Turtle.

02:50:46.440 --> 02:50:49.319
You brought me to meet a mind reader, she

02:50:49.319 --> 02:50:51.420
said, and you didn't think that might be

02:50:51.420 --> 02:50:53.639
worth mentioning sometime before now?

02:50:53.700 --> 02:50:56.700
Was this a test?

02:50:56.760 --> 02:50:58.860
Maybe this was his plan all along.

02:50:58.920 --> 02:51:02.579
Maybe he never trusted me, like Scarlet

02:51:02.579 --> 02:51:04.860
never trusted me, and he wanted to see

02:51:04.860 --> 02:51:06.239
what moon would find in my head.

02:51:06.299 --> 02:51:08.399
Turtle shrugged.

02:51:08.459 --> 02:51:10.319
It's Moon's secret.

02:51:10.379 --> 02:51:12.299
It's up to her who she tells.

02:51:12.360 --> 02:51:16.020
I'm not entirely sure why Scarlet's

02:51:16.020 --> 02:51:18.420
dancing monkey of fiery doom gets to be

02:51:18.420 --> 02:51:21.120
on that list, frankly, said Kibley.

02:51:21.180 --> 02:51:22.920
And remind me?

02:51:23.040 --> 02:51:25.920
Your thorns dancing monkey of what

02:51:25.920 --> 02:51:26.459
exactly?

02:51:26.520 --> 02:51:27.959
Peril demanded.

02:51:28.020 --> 02:51:31.139
At least I was useful to my queen.

02:51:31.200 --> 02:51:35.280
I told her, Moon interjected, opening one

02:51:35.280 --> 02:51:37.440
wing pointedly between them before Kibley

02:51:37.440 --> 02:51:38.520
could lunge at peril.

02:51:38.579 --> 02:51:40.500
Because it's the right thing to do.

02:51:40.559 --> 02:51:42.780
And because there's no way to give her

02:51:42.780 --> 02:51:43.680
any skyfire.

02:51:43.739 --> 02:51:46.680
And also because I am hoping that if she

02:51:46.680 --> 02:51:48.719
knows I'm listening, she'll try to have

02:51:48.719 --> 02:51:49.920
less disturbing thoughts.

02:51:49.979 --> 02:51:52.739
That sounded complicated.

02:51:52.860 --> 02:51:55.319
Peril wrinkled or snout.

02:51:55.379 --> 02:51:58.260
How am I supposed to change my thoughts?

02:51:58.319 --> 02:52:00.000
They just appear in my head.

02:52:00.059 --> 02:52:02.219
I've never had to worry about them

02:52:02.219 --> 02:52:04.260
disturbing anyone before.

02:52:04.319 --> 02:52:07.920
Maybe you should stop listening instead

02:52:07.920 --> 02:52:09.659
peril said.

02:52:09.719 --> 02:52:10.440
Moon shook her head.

02:52:10.500 --> 02:52:13.799
It doesn't work that way, but don't worry

02:52:13.799 --> 02:52:14.340
about it too much.

02:52:14.399 --> 02:52:16.620
Your thoughts are actually really hard to

02:52:16.620 --> 02:52:17.340
hear.

02:52:17.399 --> 02:52:19.860
Mostly all I get from your mind is heat

02:52:19.860 --> 02:52:24.000
and flames and she broke off, twitching

02:52:24.000 --> 02:52:25.559
her wings back awkwardly for a moment.

02:52:25.620 --> 02:52:29.520
Anyway, it's not as clear as most minds.

02:52:29.579 --> 02:52:31.139
You're mostly safe from me.

02:52:31.200 --> 02:52:35.340
Tremendously comforting, Peril said.

02:52:35.399 --> 02:52:37.440
She tried to fill up her head with more

02:52:37.440 --> 02:52:39.719
fire, hoping to burn out anything she

02:52:39.719 --> 02:52:42.059
didn't want Moon to see, although really

02:52:42.059 --> 02:52:44.579
that was either everything or nothing.

02:52:44.639 --> 02:52:48.120
Whenever Moon already thought of her, from

02:52:48.120 --> 02:52:50.040
whatever scraps of thoughts she'd heard

02:52:50.040 --> 02:52:51.600
none of the rest would make any

02:52:51.600 --> 02:52:52.020
difference.

02:52:52.079 --> 02:52:54.899
Either she could stand all of peril just

02:52:54.899 --> 02:52:57.420
the way she was, or she'd hate her for a

02:52:57.420 --> 02:52:59.579
small piece of her as much as for all the

02:52:59.579 --> 02:52:59.940
rest of it.

02:53:00.000 --> 02:53:02.760
Now she was giving herself a headache.

02:53:02.819 --> 02:53:05.399
Is Kinkajou all right?

02:53:05.459 --> 02:53:07.680
Turtle asked, where is she?

02:53:07.739 --> 02:53:11.159
And you're a hostile ice dragon?

02:53:11.219 --> 02:53:12.120
Peril added.

02:53:12.180 --> 02:53:15.299
Winter has gone back to the ice kingdom

02:53:15.299 --> 02:53:16.319
Moon said.

02:53:16.379 --> 02:53:18.000
She glanced at Kibley.

02:53:18.059 --> 02:53:21.000
Kibley thinks he's coming back, but I'm

02:53:21.000 --> 02:53:21.479
not so sure.

02:53:21.540 --> 02:53:25.620
Kinkachu is, well, she's recovering, we

02:53:25.620 --> 02:53:27.959
think, but she still hasn't woken up.

02:53:28.079 --> 02:53:30.959
She blinked several times rapidly.

02:53:31.020 --> 02:53:34.260
She would be so excited to see you here

02:53:34.260 --> 02:53:36.600
she said to Turtle, with a sad smile.

02:53:36.659 --> 02:53:39.479
We were attacked by a dragon who's

02:53:39.479 --> 02:53:41.819
working with Scarlett, Kibley said.

02:53:41.879 --> 02:53:44.100
He squinted at peril, then turned to

02:53:44.100 --> 02:53:44.520
Moon.

02:53:44.579 --> 02:53:46.440
What did she think about that?

02:53:46.559 --> 02:53:48.840
Can you tell if she's working for Scarlet

02:53:48.840 --> 02:53:49.500
too?

02:53:49.559 --> 02:53:52.799
No, I don't think she is, said Moon.

02:53:52.860 --> 02:53:56.760
But now she's gone back to fantasizing

02:53:56.760 --> 02:53:57.659
about ways to kill you.

02:53:57.719 --> 02:54:01.979
Because that was rude. peril flared

02:54:01.979 --> 02:54:04.620
poking around inside my brain to find the

02:54:04.620 --> 02:54:06.420
answer to a question I've already

02:54:06.420 --> 02:54:08.700
answered over and over.

02:54:08.760 --> 02:54:11.040
You can go stuff a mountain goat up your

02:54:11.040 --> 02:54:13.200
nose, Sandwing, horns first.

02:54:13.260 --> 02:54:16.079
I'm looking for Scarlet to stop her, not

02:54:16.079 --> 02:54:16.559
help her.

02:54:16.620 --> 02:54:19.079
Why are there so many stupid dragons who

02:54:19.079 --> 02:54:19.680
can't see that?

02:54:19.739 --> 02:54:22.680
Well, Kibley said.

02:54:22.739 --> 02:54:25.260
You did help her escape from Burns

02:54:25.260 --> 02:54:26.819
stronghold not that long ago.

02:54:26.879 --> 02:54:30.120
That, peril sputtered.

02:54:30.180 --> 02:54:33.600
That was just that, that Byrne was the

02:54:33.600 --> 02:54:34.260
bad guy then.

02:54:34.319 --> 02:54:36.420
I couldn't leave my queen trapped in that

02:54:36.420 --> 02:54:36.780
place.

02:54:36.840 --> 02:54:37.799
Nobody would.

02:54:37.860 --> 02:54:39.899
Your queen?

02:54:40.020 --> 02:54:41.340
Kibley challenged.

02:54:41.399 --> 02:54:43.260
Isn't Ruby your queen now?

02:54:43.319 --> 02:54:46.620
Parel drew herself up, glaring at him

02:54:46.680 --> 02:54:48.780
knowing that Moon must be hearing all her

02:54:48.780 --> 02:54:51.000
fears about Ruby scattering about inside

02:54:51.000 --> 02:54:51.299
her head.

02:54:51.360 --> 02:54:54.420
I don't have to explain myself to you

02:54:54.420 --> 02:54:55.319
sand snorter.

02:54:55.379 --> 02:54:57.899
We are only here to find out what you

02:54:57.899 --> 02:54:59.219
know about where Scarlet is.

02:54:59.340 --> 02:55:02.579
She turned her fierce gaze on Moon. and

02:55:02.579 --> 02:55:03.600
the night wings lynched.

02:55:03.659 --> 02:55:06.479
Then I'll take my disturbing thoughts

02:55:06.479 --> 02:55:09.180
right out of your life forever is the

02:55:09.180 --> 02:55:09.360
plan.

02:55:09.479 --> 02:55:11.399
It's true.

02:55:11.459 --> 02:55:12.719
We have to find her.

02:55:12.780 --> 02:55:14.340
Turtle explained.

02:55:14.399 --> 02:55:16.500
She attacked Jade Academy.

02:55:16.559 --> 02:55:19.799
Moon blinked, and Kibley's tail arched

02:55:19.799 --> 02:55:20.520
reflexively.

02:55:20.579 --> 02:55:22.680
His talons digging into the mud.

02:55:22.739 --> 02:55:26.940
She did not, Peril said, rolling her eyes

02:55:26.940 --> 02:55:27.360
at him.

02:55:27.420 --> 02:55:30.840
She flew by, threw a decapitated head at

02:55:30.840 --> 02:55:31.860
us and flew away again.

02:55:31.920 --> 02:55:33.659
That wasn't an attack.

02:55:33.719 --> 02:55:36.000
That was more like a declaration of war.

02:55:36.059 --> 02:55:38.639
If she ever decides to really attack you

02:55:38.639 --> 02:55:39.840
you'll know.

02:55:39.899 --> 02:55:42.180
A decapitated head?

02:55:42.239 --> 02:55:44.639
Moon echoed with alarm?

02:55:44.700 --> 02:55:46.680
Sonny said Scarlet was there making

02:55:46.680 --> 02:55:49.260
threats, but she didn't mention a head.

02:55:49.319 --> 02:55:51.180
Was it our fault?

02:55:51.239 --> 02:55:52.979
Kimberly asked immediately.

02:55:53.040 --> 02:55:55.620
She must be furious about us escaping

02:55:55.620 --> 02:55:56.459
with Hillstorm.

02:55:56.520 --> 02:55:58.739
What if we enraged her into coming out of

02:55:58.739 --> 02:55:59.040
hiding?

02:55:59.100 --> 02:56:03.899
That seems extremely likely, Peril said.

02:56:03.959 --> 02:56:06.659
I imagine just meeting you would enrage

02:56:06.659 --> 02:56:08.520
Queen Scarlet to the point of wanting to

02:56:08.520 --> 02:56:09.780
kill several dragons.

02:56:09.840 --> 02:56:13.799
Ha ha, Turtle said, as though peril were

02:56:13.799 --> 02:56:15.540
kidding, which she clearly was not.

02:56:15.600 --> 02:56:18.180
So where did you encounter Scarlet?

02:56:18.239 --> 02:56:21.420
In a part of the mountains not far from

02:56:21.420 --> 02:56:23.100
here, Moon said.

02:56:23.159 --> 02:56:25.139
But I'm sure she wouldn't still be

02:56:25.139 --> 02:56:25.319
there.

02:56:25.379 --> 02:56:27.299
I don't see how we can help you.

02:56:27.360 --> 02:56:29.940
The only way we found her before was

02:56:29.940 --> 02:56:32.100
because she was using the dream visitor

02:56:32.100 --> 02:56:33.120
and left clues.

02:56:33.180 --> 02:56:36.299
Pearl hated that dream visitor.

02:56:36.360 --> 02:56:39.180
Scarlett showed up in her dreams all the

02:56:39.180 --> 02:56:41.700
time, and half the time, peril wasn't

02:56:41.700 --> 02:56:42.600
even sure if she was real.

02:56:42.659 --> 02:56:44.399
Whether she was or not.

02:56:44.459 --> 02:56:47.280
There was always yelling and guilt and

02:56:47.280 --> 02:56:49.500
ominous remarks about Clay's future.

02:56:49.559 --> 02:56:51.780
I knew they wouldn't be helpful.

02:56:51.840 --> 02:56:53.700
She said to Turtle.

02:56:53.760 --> 02:56:58.500
Well, Turtle said uncertainly, maybe if

02:56:58.500 --> 02:57:00.239
you show us on a map where she was.

02:57:00.299 --> 02:57:02.459
We can at least start searching from

02:57:02.459 --> 02:57:02.639
there.

02:57:02.700 --> 02:57:06.059
Kibley looked up at the sky, where the

02:57:06.059 --> 02:57:07.739
sun was meandering toward the midpoint.

02:57:07.799 --> 02:57:10.680
Sure, but right now we should get back to

02:57:10.680 --> 02:57:11.159
the clinic.

02:57:11.219 --> 02:57:13.079
The dragons from glory are supposed to

02:57:13.079 --> 02:57:13.500
arrive soon.

02:57:13.620 --> 02:57:16.319
Carol wondered if he was changing the

02:57:16.319 --> 02:57:17.700
subject because he didn't trust her.

02:57:17.819 --> 02:57:21.899
Consider the feeling mutual sandwing, she

02:57:21.899 --> 02:57:23.579
thought, eyeing him narrowly.

02:57:23.700 --> 02:57:25.559
The clinic?

02:57:25.559 --> 02:57:27.299
Where Kikachu is?

02:57:27.360 --> 02:57:30.059
Turtle's face brightened hopefully, then

02:57:30.059 --> 02:57:33.540
fell as he turned toward peril, but peril

02:57:33.540 --> 02:57:34.500
can't go into the city.

02:57:34.559 --> 02:57:37.739
She spread her gold veined wings to

02:57:37.739 --> 02:57:39.899
indicate, remember?

02:57:39.959 --> 02:57:41.219
Deadly fire scales over here?

02:57:41.280 --> 02:57:43.620
But she accidentally hit a branch

02:57:43.620 --> 02:57:45.780
overhead, which burst into flames.

02:57:45.840 --> 02:57:48.780
Kibli promptly smacked his tail in the

02:57:48.780 --> 02:57:51.360
river, sending up a wave that cascaded

02:57:51.360 --> 02:57:54.540
over the branch and peril, soaking her

02:57:54.540 --> 02:57:55.739
and putting the fire out.

02:57:55.799 --> 02:57:59.459
Peril regarded him coldly, water dripping

02:57:59.459 --> 02:58:00.000
from her snout.

02:58:00.120 --> 02:58:03.719
Don't feel bad, Moon said to Turtle.

02:58:03.780 --> 02:58:05.639
Kinkaju wouldn't know you were there

02:58:05.639 --> 02:58:06.000
anyway.

02:58:06.059 --> 02:58:08.700
Turtles' wings drooped.

02:58:08.760 --> 02:58:10.979
And peril had a sudden, very strong

02:58:10.979 --> 02:58:13.260
feeling that there was a right thing to

02:58:13.260 --> 02:58:13.680
say here.

02:58:13.739 --> 02:58:15.959
It was written in the slump of his

02:58:15.959 --> 02:58:18.479
shoulders, and the way he poked one claw

02:58:18.479 --> 02:58:20.159
gloomily at the mud puddle beside him.

02:58:20.280 --> 02:58:23.940
Something reassuring about Kinkachu?

02:58:24.000 --> 02:58:25.319
No?

02:58:25.379 --> 02:58:26.760
Something else.

02:58:26.819 --> 02:58:30.000
Something she didn't want to say, but she

02:58:30.000 --> 02:58:32.040
saw that she kind of had to, and the

02:58:32.040 --> 02:58:33.959
others were even leaving an odd moment of

02:58:33.959 --> 02:58:36.239
quiet in the conversation, waiting for

02:58:36.239 --> 02:58:36.780
her to say it.

02:58:36.840 --> 02:58:41.280
You should go, she said, forcing it out

02:58:41.280 --> 02:58:42.780
past the growl in her throat.

02:58:42.840 --> 02:58:47.280
I'll just wait for you out here

02:58:47.280 --> 02:58:48.180
somewhere.

02:58:48.239 --> 02:58:49.860
Really?

02:58:49.920 --> 02:58:52.860
Turtles said with an enormous smile.

02:58:52.979 --> 02:58:54.059
You don't mind?

02:58:54.120 --> 02:58:55.260
We'll be back soon.

02:58:55.319 --> 02:58:57.360
I bet.

02:58:57.420 --> 02:58:59.819
After you've all talked in secret about

02:58:59.819 --> 02:59:02.100
me and what you're going to do next and

02:59:02.100 --> 02:59:03.299
whether to fly off without me.

02:59:03.420 --> 02:59:07.680
Sure, Peril said, then wondered if that

02:59:07.680 --> 02:59:09.299
sounded sarcastic and tried again.

02:59:09.420 --> 02:59:10.860
Sure.

02:59:10.920 --> 02:59:13.559
Okay, that one sounded worse.

02:59:13.620 --> 02:59:15.959
I mean yes, fine.

02:59:16.020 --> 02:59:18.180
I want to go hunt in the desert anyway.

02:59:18.239 --> 02:59:21.719
There's a big sandstone arch west of the

02:59:21.719 --> 02:59:23.819
city, set up high so you can see

02:59:23.819 --> 02:59:25.680
practically the whole kingdom of sand

02:59:25.680 --> 02:59:26.639
Moon said.

02:59:26.700 --> 02:59:29.399
That's where Kibli and I have been going

02:59:29.399 --> 02:59:30.239
to wait for winter.

02:59:30.299 --> 02:59:33.299
Whenever we're not with Kinkaju or in the

02:59:33.299 --> 02:59:33.840
library.

02:59:33.899 --> 02:59:35.340
Let's meet back there.

02:59:35.399 --> 02:59:40.139
Winter still has 2 more days, Kibley said

02:59:40.139 --> 02:59:40.559
quietly.

02:59:40.620 --> 02:59:42.780
We told him we'd wait a week.

02:59:42.840 --> 02:59:45.840
He's not coming, Moon said.

02:59:45.899 --> 02:59:48.180
I've seen inside his mind, Kibley.

02:59:48.239 --> 02:59:50.459
He's so loyal to his family and his

02:59:50.459 --> 02:59:50.760
tribe.

02:59:50.819 --> 02:59:53.100
I don't think anything will change that.

02:59:53.159 --> 02:59:56.340
Kibley made a face that peril couldn't

02:59:56.340 --> 02:59:56.639
figure out.

02:59:56.700 --> 03:00:00.059
Moon, sometimes you're so busy listening

03:00:00.059 --> 03:00:02.219
to what dragons are thinking, you miss

03:00:02.219 --> 03:00:04.260
the things they're actually doing, which

03:00:04.260 --> 03:00:05.459
can tell you a lot more about what

03:00:05.459 --> 03:00:06.059
they're really like.

03:00:06.120 --> 03:00:09.059
That makes no sense.

03:00:09.120 --> 03:00:10.260
She said.

03:00:10.319 --> 03:00:13.500
Should I bring Kinkaju something?

03:00:13.620 --> 03:00:15.600
Turtle said, hopping from one foot to the

03:00:15.600 --> 03:00:17.520
other in a very unturtle like way.

03:00:17.579 --> 03:00:20.940
Peril had never seen him expand even an

03:00:20.940 --> 03:00:22.920
iota more energy than necessary for

03:00:22.920 --> 03:00:23.700
whatever he was doing.

03:00:23.760 --> 03:00:25.559
Flowers?

03:00:25.620 --> 03:00:26.459
A fish?

03:00:26.520 --> 03:00:28.860
No, she doesn't like fish.

03:00:28.920 --> 03:00:30.120
Um, kumquat?

03:00:30.180 --> 03:00:34.739
He likes moon and kibli, peril guest, but

03:00:34.739 --> 03:00:36.540
he's really here for kinkachu.

03:00:36.600 --> 03:00:39.180
Why did he even want to travel with me in

03:00:39.180 --> 03:00:40.379
the 1st place?

03:00:40.440 --> 03:00:41.700
He could have come here without me.

03:00:41.760 --> 03:00:44.280
Did he think I'd be useful protection

03:00:44.280 --> 03:00:44.700
along the way?

03:00:44.760 --> 03:00:47.219
He didn't need to pretend to be friends

03:00:47.219 --> 03:00:48.059
with me.

03:00:48.120 --> 03:00:50.100
Boring green puddle dragon.

03:00:50.159 --> 03:00:51.059
Humph.

03:00:51.120 --> 03:00:54.360
Peril caught Moon's eyes on her, and

03:00:54.360 --> 03:00:56.340
didn't like whatever mysterious emotion

03:00:56.340 --> 03:00:57.180
was going on in them.

03:00:57.239 --> 03:01:01.020
Sympathy, pity, bewilderment?

03:01:01.079 --> 03:01:03.600
Whatever she was getting from peril's

03:01:03.600 --> 03:01:04.920
brain, Kibley was right.

03:01:04.979 --> 03:01:07.020
It didn't mean Moon knew anything about

03:01:07.020 --> 03:01:07.799
her, really.

03:01:07.860 --> 03:01:11.219
Peril sat down and started examining her

03:01:11.219 --> 03:01:13.739
claws as if she found all these dragons

03:01:13.739 --> 03:01:15.059
exceedingly boring.

03:01:15.120 --> 03:01:17.639
This was another trick she'd learned from

03:01:17.639 --> 03:01:18.540
watching Scarlet.

03:01:18.600 --> 03:01:20.700
Although she had a feeling she wasn't

03:01:20.700 --> 03:01:22.200
conveying quite the right amount of

03:01:22.200 --> 03:01:23.819
disdain in the tilt of her wings.

03:01:23.879 --> 03:01:27.360
You don't need anything, Kibley said to

03:01:27.360 --> 03:01:27.719
Turtle.

03:01:27.780 --> 03:01:29.819
Just having you there would be enough for

03:01:29.819 --> 03:01:30.299
her.

03:01:30.360 --> 03:01:32.159
Maybe she'll be able to hear your voice.

03:01:32.280 --> 03:01:35.879
See you soon, Pearl, Turtle said

03:01:35.879 --> 03:01:36.600
enthusiastically.

03:01:36.719 --> 03:01:41.100
Yeah, maybe, Peril said to the empty air

03:01:41.159 --> 03:01:42.899
drowned out by the flapping of their

03:01:42.899 --> 03:01:45.180
wings as all 3 of them took off and

03:01:45.180 --> 03:01:45.959
headed into the city.

03:01:46.020 --> 03:01:49.260
She waited a minute, to be sure they

03:01:49.260 --> 03:01:51.540
wouldn't turn around, and then she lifted

03:01:51.540 --> 03:01:53.579
her head to watch the glowing green shape

03:01:53.579 --> 03:01:55.920
of her supposed friend flying away from

03:01:55.920 --> 03:01:56.159
her.

03:01:56.219 --> 03:02:00.780
Chapter 9.

03:02:00.840 --> 03:02:04.139
Peril didn't quite realize that she was

03:02:04.139 --> 03:02:06.479
still in pain from the thorn balls until

03:02:06.479 --> 03:02:08.819
she was up in the air again, flying with

03:02:08.819 --> 03:02:10.920
muscles that protested with tiny sparks

03:02:10.920 --> 03:02:11.639
of agony.

03:02:11.700 --> 03:02:14.520
She gritted her teeth, determined to

03:02:14.520 --> 03:02:15.840
ignore it until it went away.

03:02:15.899 --> 03:02:19.319
She spent the rest of the morning flying

03:02:19.319 --> 03:02:21.600
out into the desert, chasing down a

03:02:21.600 --> 03:02:24.360
desert fox, who escaped into a hole and

03:02:24.360 --> 03:02:27.000
was kind of too cute to eat anyway, and

03:02:27.000 --> 03:02:28.799
then catching a large white bird in

03:02:28.799 --> 03:02:30.180
midair and eating that instead.

03:02:30.299 --> 03:02:33.360
She also set fire to a tall cactus

03:02:33.360 --> 03:02:35.579
because it was giving her a superior look

03:02:35.579 --> 03:02:36.299
and she felt like it.

03:02:36.360 --> 03:02:38.340
One advantage of a desert.

03:02:38.399 --> 03:02:40.200
She didn't have to worry about forest

03:02:40.200 --> 03:02:43.319
fires, or accidentally scorching a field

03:02:43.319 --> 03:02:45.719
of sky wing crops, or whatever other

03:02:45.719 --> 03:02:48.059
reasons the queen had always had for

03:02:48.059 --> 03:02:49.139
keeping her in the palace.

03:02:49.200 --> 03:02:51.120
The queen.

03:02:51.299 --> 03:02:53.219
I do still think of her that way.

03:02:53.280 --> 03:02:56.459
Kibli's words kept going around in her

03:02:56.459 --> 03:03:00.059
head, which was very annoying and made

03:03:00.059 --> 03:03:02.280
the next cactus over look like tempting

03:03:02.280 --> 03:03:03.059
kindling as well.

03:03:03.120 --> 03:03:06.000
Isn't Ruby your queen now?

03:03:06.059 --> 03:03:08.700
Well, yes, technically.

03:03:08.760 --> 03:03:10.920
But how could you swear loyalty to a

03:03:10.920 --> 03:03:12.420
queen who didn't even want you in her

03:03:12.420 --> 03:03:12.780
kingdom?

03:03:12.840 --> 03:03:16.079
How could anyone feel loyal to a queen

03:03:16.079 --> 03:03:18.180
who clearly just wanted you dead?

03:03:18.239 --> 03:03:21.059
Peril swerved to fly back toward

03:03:21.059 --> 03:03:23.700
possibility and saw a huddle of camels a

03:03:23.700 --> 03:03:25.500
short ways off to the south?

03:03:25.559 --> 03:03:27.299
Maybe a camel would make her feel

03:03:27.299 --> 03:03:27.540
better.

03:03:27.600 --> 03:03:31.260
But as she came closer, she saw that the

03:03:31.260 --> 03:03:33.479
camels were tied to a palm tree, and

03:03:33.479 --> 03:03:36.000
surrounded by bustling scavengers, at

03:03:36.000 --> 03:03:38.399
least 10 of them, setting up tents and

03:03:38.399 --> 03:03:40.920
scooping water from a small oasis pond.

03:03:40.979 --> 03:03:43.739
They all went gratifyingly still when she

03:03:43.739 --> 03:03:44.700
shot overhead.

03:03:44.760 --> 03:03:47.940
She studied their upturned faces, which

03:03:47.940 --> 03:03:49.620
looked like they were mostly eyes

03:03:49.620 --> 03:03:51.299
terrified eyes.

03:03:51.360 --> 03:03:54.120
She'd never seen such dopey prey.

03:03:54.180 --> 03:03:55.799
What were they doing out in the open

03:03:55.799 --> 03:03:58.440
desert, where it would be so easy to

03:03:58.440 --> 03:03:59.340
catch and eat them?

03:03:59.399 --> 03:04:02.219
She'd never eaten a scavenger before.

03:04:02.280 --> 03:04:05.520
Queen Scarlet always saved them, either

03:04:05.520 --> 03:04:07.979
to fight in the arena, or be served at

03:04:07.979 --> 03:04:10.139
special banquets, which peril was never

03:04:10.139 --> 03:04:13.260
invited to, because blah, blah, setting

03:04:13.260 --> 03:04:15.840
the guests on fire would be unhospitable

03:04:15.840 --> 03:04:16.500
blah, blah.

03:04:16.559 --> 03:04:19.559
She circled around again, trying to

03:04:19.559 --> 03:04:20.760
decide how hungry she was.

03:04:20.879 --> 03:04:24.239
As she did, she spotted one scavenger

03:04:24.239 --> 03:04:26.399
sitting apart from the others, a little

03:04:26.399 --> 03:04:27.840
ways up the nearest dune.

03:04:27.899 --> 03:04:30.780
This one wasn't looking up at peril.

03:04:30.840 --> 03:04:33.420
Its shoulders were slumped, and its head

03:04:33.420 --> 03:04:35.819
was buried in its little brown arms, so

03:04:35.819 --> 03:04:37.799
all peril could see was a thicket of dark

03:04:37.799 --> 03:04:40.620
fur on top of its head, a sand colored

03:04:40.620 --> 03:04:42.719
cloth wrapped around it, and 2 little

03:04:42.719 --> 03:04:43.860
brown feet sticking out.

03:04:43.920 --> 03:04:46.739
It looked sad.

03:04:46.799 --> 03:04:50.520
That's hilarious, Pearl thought.

03:04:50.579 --> 03:04:52.319
Do camels get sad?

03:04:52.379 --> 03:04:54.299
Do mountain goats mope?

03:04:54.360 --> 03:04:56.520
Does a hawk ever have a day where it

03:04:56.520 --> 03:04:58.319
feels like none of the other hawks want

03:04:58.319 --> 03:04:59.040
to be friends with it?

03:04:59.100 --> 03:05:01.680
Maybe I should burn up the other

03:05:01.680 --> 03:05:03.899
scavengers and see if that makes this one

03:05:03.899 --> 03:05:04.319
feel better.

03:05:04.379 --> 03:05:07.860
She thought about it for a moment, but

03:05:07.860 --> 03:05:09.239
there was something about the curve of

03:05:09.239 --> 03:05:11.340
the scavenger's back that was almost too

03:05:11.340 --> 03:05:14.819
achingly familiar, and in the end, peril

03:05:14.819 --> 03:05:17.219
turned around and flew away, leaving the

03:05:17.219 --> 03:05:19.079
scavengers and camels to deal with their

03:05:19.079 --> 03:05:19.620
own problems.

03:05:19.680 --> 03:05:23.579
The sandstone arch was easy to find.

03:05:23.639 --> 03:05:25.860
High on a butte to the west of

03:05:25.860 --> 03:05:28.020
possibility, looping out of the ground

03:05:28.020 --> 03:05:30.479
and back into it, in a shape like a rain

03:05:30.479 --> 03:05:33.180
wing tail, Peril flew through the hole of

03:05:33.180 --> 03:05:35.639
the archway, feeling her wing tips brush

03:05:35.639 --> 03:05:37.620
the stone on either side, and then

03:05:37.620 --> 03:05:40.500
spiraled around to land on top of it, the

03:05:40.500 --> 03:05:41.760
desert spread out before her.

03:05:41.819 --> 03:05:44.520
Vast and endless in the hot afternoon

03:05:44.520 --> 03:05:45.120
sun.

03:05:45.180 --> 03:05:48.000
When she turned around, she could see the

03:05:48.000 --> 03:05:49.260
whole town of possibility.

03:05:49.319 --> 03:05:51.959
The taller structures clustered around

03:05:51.959 --> 03:05:54.479
the river delta, and the trail of smaller

03:05:54.479 --> 03:05:56.100
ones leading away along the river.

03:05:56.159 --> 03:05:59.280
From here, the dragons winding through

03:05:59.280 --> 03:06:00.659
the streets looked no bigger than

03:06:00.659 --> 03:06:03.120
scavengers, and sometimes it was even

03:06:03.120 --> 03:06:04.799
hard to tell what color their scales

03:06:04.799 --> 03:06:05.040
were.

03:06:05.100 --> 03:06:08.879
Beyond possibility, across the eastern

03:06:08.879 --> 03:06:11.819
horizon, cut the jagged tooth shapes of

03:06:11.819 --> 03:06:14.459
the claws of the clouds mountains.

03:06:14.520 --> 03:06:15.899
Scarlet was in there somewhere.

03:06:15.959 --> 03:06:17.700
Peril was sure of it.

03:06:17.760 --> 03:06:20.219
The queen wasn't the kind of dragon to

03:06:20.219 --> 03:06:22.200
let herself be uncomfortable somewhere

03:06:22.200 --> 03:06:24.659
weird, like the rainforest or the mud

03:06:24.659 --> 03:06:25.200
swamps.

03:06:25.260 --> 03:06:27.540
She knew the sky kingdom perhaps better

03:06:27.540 --> 03:06:29.639
than anyone, and she must have found

03:06:29.639 --> 03:06:31.200
somewhere she didn't mind hiding.

03:06:31.260 --> 03:06:34.559
A flicker of movement caught Peril's eye

03:06:34.559 --> 03:06:36.780
and she swiveled her head to see a dragon

03:06:36.780 --> 03:06:38.879
winging his way toward her from the edge

03:06:38.879 --> 03:06:39.540
of possibility.

03:06:39.600 --> 03:06:43.079
He was a big golden orange sky wing.

03:06:43.139 --> 03:06:46.200
Not anyone she recognized, although it

03:06:46.200 --> 03:06:47.940
did seem as though he was flying directly

03:06:47.940 --> 03:06:48.420
toward her.

03:06:48.420 --> 03:06:51.719
Maybe he recognized me from all the way

03:06:51.719 --> 03:06:52.680
down there.

03:06:52.920 --> 03:06:55.620
Maybe he's coming to yell at me about how

03:06:55.620 --> 03:06:57.840
I should leave his precious flammable

03:06:57.840 --> 03:06:58.379
town alone.

03:06:58.440 --> 03:07:01.200
Is he the one with a basket of snails

03:07:01.200 --> 03:07:01.739
from last time?

03:07:01.799 --> 03:07:04.440
Or perhaps I flambayed one of his

03:07:04.440 --> 03:07:05.819
relatives and he's still grumpy about

03:07:05.819 --> 03:07:06.000
it.

03:07:06.059 --> 03:07:08.399
She flexed her talons.

03:07:08.459 --> 03:07:10.680
Well, if he'd like a fight?

03:07:10.739 --> 03:07:12.540
I am certainly in the mood for it.

03:07:12.600 --> 03:07:16.260
Clay flashed into her head, wearing his

03:07:16.260 --> 03:07:18.899
disappointed face, which was frustrating

03:07:18.899 --> 03:07:21.360
because it both made her miss him, and

03:07:21.360 --> 03:07:23.340
also made her want to yell at him, that

03:07:23.340 --> 03:07:26.219
she hadn't killed anybody, yet, and

03:07:26.219 --> 03:07:28.379
couldn't he appreciate that instead of

03:07:28.379 --> 03:07:30.180
anticipating her next bad thing?

03:07:30.239 --> 03:07:33.899
And then she felt silly, because she was

03:07:33.899 --> 03:07:35.940
busy getting mad at him for an imaginary

03:07:35.940 --> 03:07:38.579
conversation, when really, she just

03:07:38.579 --> 03:07:40.200
wished he was there to nudge her wings

03:07:40.200 --> 03:07:41.760
and tell her what to do next.

03:07:41.819 --> 03:07:45.420
The Sky Wing was definitely aiming for

03:07:45.420 --> 03:07:47.100
the arch and looking at her.

03:07:47.159 --> 03:07:49.379
But when he was only a few wing beats

03:07:49.379 --> 03:07:52.079
away, he suddenly jerked back, with an

03:07:52.079 --> 03:07:53.819
expression peril had seen many times

03:07:53.819 --> 03:07:57.420
before, that wonderful fear slash hatred

03:07:57.420 --> 03:07:59.760
combination that just the sight of her

03:07:59.760 --> 03:08:01.979
face seemed to magically induce.

03:08:02.040 --> 03:08:05.040
Except this time, it wasn't for her.

03:08:05.100 --> 03:08:07.200
He wasn't looking at her anymore.

03:08:07.260 --> 03:08:08.700
He was looking beyond her.

03:08:08.760 --> 03:08:11.940
And whatever he saw made him wheel around

03:08:11.940 --> 03:08:14.100
abruptly and hightail it back to

03:08:14.100 --> 03:08:15.840
possibility as fast as he could fly.

03:08:15.899 --> 03:08:19.440
Peril turned and scanned the desert sky.

03:08:19.500 --> 03:08:22.260
Two more dragons were flying her way.

03:08:22.319 --> 03:08:25.379
This time, it was an ice wing and a big

03:08:25.379 --> 03:08:27.479
night wing coming from the northwest.

03:08:27.540 --> 03:08:29.879
Another night wing?

03:08:29.879 --> 03:08:30.659
Out here?

03:08:30.719 --> 03:08:33.659
Could it be one of the ones who escaped

03:08:33.659 --> 03:08:34.739
from Thorn's prison?

03:08:34.799 --> 03:08:37.079
Or Scarlet's ally?

03:08:37.139 --> 03:08:40.139
The sunlight sparked and danced across

03:08:40.139 --> 03:08:42.780
the ice wings silver scales, like a 100

03:08:42.780 --> 03:08:44.219
little moons on fire.

03:08:44.280 --> 03:08:46.860
Peril curled her tail around her talons

03:08:46.860 --> 03:08:48.719
and watched him with narrow eyes.

03:08:48.780 --> 03:08:52.200
She vaguely remembered the ice wings

03:08:52.200 --> 03:08:53.579
who'd yelled at her in the big entrance

03:08:53.579 --> 03:08:56.280
hall at Jade Academy, but she doubted

03:08:56.280 --> 03:08:57.899
she'd be able to pick Winter or his

03:08:57.899 --> 03:08:59.579
sister out from a crowd of white

03:08:59.579 --> 03:09:00.059
dragons.

03:09:00.120 --> 03:09:02.760
Keeping faces in her head, wasn't a

03:09:02.760 --> 03:09:03.840
particular skill of hers.

03:09:03.899 --> 03:09:06.000
She always forgot to concentrate on

03:09:06.000 --> 03:09:08.280
storing their features, usually because

03:09:08.280 --> 03:09:10.020
she was sizing them up as a potential

03:09:10.020 --> 03:09:11.219
combatant instead.

03:09:11.280 --> 03:09:14.040
Mostly, she'd never had to remember the

03:09:14.040 --> 03:09:16.920
dragons she met anyway, since she'd

03:09:16.920 --> 03:09:18.899
killed almost all the ones who got close

03:09:18.899 --> 03:09:20.520
enough to be faces in the 1st place.

03:09:20.579 --> 03:09:23.399
She definitely saw the moment when the

03:09:23.399 --> 03:09:25.020
ice dragon recognized her, though.

03:09:25.079 --> 03:09:28.260
He immediately altered his flight path to

03:09:28.260 --> 03:09:30.840
hurdle in her direction, and his face

03:09:30.840 --> 03:09:32.399
wasn't exactly throwing her an

03:09:32.399 --> 03:09:34.379
enthusiastic full moon festival.

03:09:34.440 --> 03:09:36.299
What are you doing here?

03:09:36.360 --> 03:09:39.299
He yelled down apparel, circling over her

03:09:39.299 --> 03:09:39.479
head.

03:09:39.600 --> 03:09:42.120
The Nightwing stayed back, beating her

03:09:42.120 --> 03:09:43.139
wings to hover in place.

03:09:43.200 --> 03:09:45.059
What do you care?

03:09:45.180 --> 03:09:46.379
Pearl shouted.

03:09:46.440 --> 03:09:48.600
It made her instantly grumpy to see how

03:09:48.600 --> 03:09:50.940
he stayed up in the air, forcing her to

03:09:50.940 --> 03:09:52.739
look up at him as he flew around and

03:09:52.739 --> 03:09:53.340
around.

03:09:53.399 --> 03:09:55.920
That was basic dragon etiquette that even

03:09:55.920 --> 03:09:56.940
peril knew.

03:09:56.940 --> 03:09:58.680
If you want to talk to someone on the

03:09:58.680 --> 03:10:00.780
ground, you land and look them in the

03:10:00.780 --> 03:10:01.079
eye.

03:10:01.139 --> 03:10:03.420
Did Scarlet send you?

03:10:03.479 --> 03:10:04.500
He called.

03:10:04.559 --> 03:10:06.360
Did she send you?

03:10:06.420 --> 03:10:07.319
she snapped back.

03:10:07.440 --> 03:10:10.020
Last I heard, it was your sister who was

03:10:10.020 --> 03:10:11.219
working for her, not me.

03:10:11.280 --> 03:10:15.360
That went in, sharp as a sandwing barb.

03:10:15.420 --> 03:10:18.059
Winter flinched and frowned even harder.

03:10:18.120 --> 03:10:20.340
I'm not going to let you herd my friends

03:10:20.340 --> 03:10:21.899
if that's what you're here for.

03:10:21.959 --> 03:10:23.579
That's funny.

03:10:23.639 --> 03:10:24.600
Pearl said.

03:10:24.659 --> 03:10:26.399
I mean, the part where you think you

03:10:26.399 --> 03:10:27.000
could stop me.

03:10:27.059 --> 03:10:30.479
Even as she said it, she knew Clay would

03:10:30.479 --> 03:10:32.040
think it was exactly the wrong thing to

03:10:32.040 --> 03:10:32.219
say.

03:10:32.280 --> 03:10:34.979
She knew she was provoking the ice wing

03:10:34.979 --> 03:10:36.780
on purpose, because she was already

03:10:36.780 --> 03:10:39.059
having a bad day, and he was making it

03:10:39.059 --> 03:10:41.399
worse, and she knew she should stop and

03:10:41.399 --> 03:10:43.620
explain everything, and tell him where

03:10:43.620 --> 03:10:46.440
his friends were, but by all the moons.

03:10:46.500 --> 03:10:48.719
If he couldn't even handle landing to

03:10:48.719 --> 03:10:51.239
have a civil conversation, then why

03:10:51.239 --> 03:10:53.760
should she do all the work of keeping

03:10:53.760 --> 03:10:54.299
things polite?

03:10:54.420 --> 03:10:55.920
Seriously.

03:10:55.979 --> 03:10:59.280
Still, she could probably have guessed

03:10:59.280 --> 03:11:00.120
what would happen next.

03:11:00.180 --> 03:11:04.200
Winter whirled with a roar and shot a

03:11:04.200 --> 03:11:05.879
blast of frost breath at one of her

03:11:05.879 --> 03:11:06.360
wings.

03:11:06.420 --> 03:11:09.420
As she'd learned over many arena battles

03:11:09.420 --> 03:11:11.459
with ice wings, this did essentially

03:11:11.459 --> 03:11:14.159
nothing, except make the spot feel numb

03:11:14.159 --> 03:11:16.260
for a few minutes, while her fire scales

03:11:16.260 --> 03:11:17.159
combated the ice.

03:11:17.219 --> 03:11:20.280
But it was still rude, and she didn't

03:11:20.280 --> 03:11:20.760
like it.

03:11:20.819 --> 03:11:23.639
She flung herself into the air and

03:11:23.639 --> 03:11:25.559
blasted fire right back at him.

03:11:25.620 --> 03:11:28.860
Clay's voice in her head, made her aim to

03:11:28.860 --> 03:11:30.479
his left so she wouldn't actually hurt

03:11:30.479 --> 03:11:33.000
him, but surely it was all right to scare

03:11:33.000 --> 03:11:33.600
him a little bit.

03:11:33.659 --> 03:11:36.659
He shot out of the way, no doubt

03:11:36.659 --> 03:11:38.520
congratulating himself on moving so

03:11:38.520 --> 03:11:41.159
quickly, rather than realizing she'd

03:11:41.159 --> 03:11:42.180
deliberately spared him.

03:11:42.239 --> 03:11:45.600
With a deft flip of his tail, the ice

03:11:45.600 --> 03:11:48.000
wing dodged below her, and then swung up

03:11:48.000 --> 03:11:50.100
suddenly to frost breath her back legs

03:11:50.100 --> 03:11:52.379
before looping away again.

03:11:52.440 --> 03:11:55.500
That doesn't do anything to me, you one

03:11:55.500 --> 03:11:57.299
trick dragon, she cried.

03:11:57.360 --> 03:11:59.819
How about some claw to claw combat?

03:11:59.879 --> 03:12:01.620
Or are you too much of a coward for

03:12:01.620 --> 03:12:01.860
that?

03:12:01.920 --> 03:12:05.579
Whether or not he was a coward, he was

03:12:05.579 --> 03:12:06.299
fast.

03:12:06.360 --> 03:12:09.719
He swept around her in dizzying spirals

03:12:09.719 --> 03:12:11.940
flashing headaches straight into her

03:12:11.940 --> 03:12:14.219
skull with every sun reflecting spin.

03:12:14.280 --> 03:12:17.280
She lashed out with her front claws, half

03:12:17.280 --> 03:12:19.739
sure she wouldn't catch him, and half

03:12:19.739 --> 03:12:22.020
starting not to care if she did, because

03:12:22.020 --> 03:12:25.020
this dragon was seriously asking for it.

03:12:25.079 --> 03:12:27.840
Fighting in the air was hard.

03:12:27.899 --> 03:12:30.959
How did dragons focus on staying aloft

03:12:30.959 --> 03:12:33.420
and attacking, and defending all at the

03:12:33.420 --> 03:12:34.139
same time?

03:12:34.680 --> 03:12:36.719
She'd never practiced against an opponent

03:12:36.719 --> 03:12:37.319
in the sky.

03:12:37.379 --> 03:12:39.959
Her wings felt all clumsy and in the

03:12:39.959 --> 03:12:40.139
way.

03:12:40.200 --> 03:12:43.319
Why didn't Scarlet let me learn to fight

03:12:43.319 --> 03:12:43.920
properly?

03:12:43.979 --> 03:12:46.620
If this is how dragons normally do it?

03:12:46.680 --> 03:12:49.319
Why did she only pit me against prisoners

03:12:49.319 --> 03:12:50.459
with their wings bound?

03:12:50.520 --> 03:12:52.860
For the 1st time in her life?

03:12:52.920 --> 03:12:56.040
Peril began to wonder, if maybe she

03:12:56.040 --> 03:12:59.040
wasn't actually the most dangerous dragon

03:12:59.040 --> 03:12:59.819
in Pyria.

03:12:59.879 --> 03:13:02.280
But I am, I am.

03:13:02.340 --> 03:13:04.620
I just have to touch him and he's dead.

03:13:04.680 --> 03:13:05.760
Wait.

03:13:05.819 --> 03:13:07.500
That would be bad.

03:13:07.559 --> 03:13:10.440
That would be very, very bad.

03:13:10.500 --> 03:13:12.540
Peril suddenly remembered.

03:13:12.600 --> 03:13:15.120
This was one of Clay's Jade Mountain

03:13:15.120 --> 03:13:15.600
students.

03:13:15.659 --> 03:13:17.639
He was Turtle's friend.

03:13:17.700 --> 03:13:19.860
Even though he technically attacked her

03:13:19.860 --> 03:13:20.459
first.

03:13:20.520 --> 03:13:22.979
She still knew how much trouble she'd be

03:13:22.979 --> 03:13:23.879
in if she hurt him.

03:13:23.940 --> 03:13:26.219
Stop, she yelled.

03:13:26.280 --> 03:13:27.659
Don't make me kill you.

03:13:27.719 --> 03:13:30.479
Nope, that wasn't the right thing to say

03:13:30.479 --> 03:13:30.840
either.

03:13:30.899 --> 03:13:34.200
She tucked in her wings abruptly and dove

03:13:34.200 --> 03:13:36.239
toward the arch, trying to put a safe

03:13:36.239 --> 03:13:37.739
distance between her and Winter.

03:13:37.860 --> 03:13:41.459
But at that exact moment, he did another

03:13:41.459 --> 03:13:44.760
flip to swoop below her again, and the 2

03:13:44.760 --> 03:13:46.559
dragons collided in midair.

03:13:46.680 --> 03:13:50.579
Fire and ice, copper and silver.

03:13:50.639 --> 03:13:53.219
Winter, and certain death.

03:13:53.280 --> 03:13:57.420
Chapter 10.

03:13:57.719 --> 03:14:02.940
At first, all peril felt was cold limbs

03:14:02.940 --> 03:14:05.760
cold scales, cold wings slamming into

03:14:05.760 --> 03:14:06.780
hers.

03:14:06.840 --> 03:14:08.639
The shock knocked the breath out of her

03:14:08.639 --> 03:14:10.799
for a moment, and they tangled in

03:14:10.799 --> 03:14:11.940
startled free fall.

03:14:12.000 --> 03:14:14.879
And then winter started screaming, and

03:14:14.879 --> 03:14:17.280
Pearl shoved him away, and he plummeted

03:14:17.280 --> 03:14:18.840
toward the ground with smoke already

03:14:18.840 --> 03:14:21.600
rising from his scales, falling as hard

03:14:21.600 --> 03:14:24.840
and fast as Pearl's heart. 3 moons.

03:14:24.899 --> 03:14:26.040
What have I done?

03:14:26.100 --> 03:14:29.459
Oh my, said the night wing in the air

03:14:29.459 --> 03:14:30.000
above them.

03:14:30.059 --> 03:14:31.500
Peril had forgotten about her.

03:14:31.559 --> 03:14:33.180
Fire scales.

03:14:33.239 --> 03:14:34.739
I haven't seen that in a long time.

03:14:34.799 --> 03:14:36.479
Get help.

03:14:36.540 --> 03:14:37.920
Peril yelled.

03:14:37.979 --> 03:14:40.440
She plunged after Winter, who missed the

03:14:40.440 --> 03:14:42.299
arch and tumbled to the hard rock below

03:14:42.299 --> 03:14:42.479
it.

03:14:42.540 --> 03:14:45.479
At the last minute, he managed to spread

03:14:45.479 --> 03:14:47.819
his wings, so it wasn't a crash landing

03:14:47.819 --> 03:14:51.000
but as he did, peril saw the ropes of

03:14:51.000 --> 03:14:53.639
black burns smeared across them, he was

03:14:53.639 --> 03:14:56.100
burning, burning up everywhere she'd

03:14:56.100 --> 03:14:57.120
accidentally touched him.

03:14:57.180 --> 03:15:01.020
He landed heavily and collapsed, writhing

03:15:01.020 --> 03:15:01.379
in pain.

03:15:01.440 --> 03:15:05.219
I'm sorry, peril cried. landing beside

03:15:05.219 --> 03:15:05.399
him.

03:15:05.459 --> 03:15:07.379
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

03:15:07.440 --> 03:15:08.459
I was trying to get away.

03:15:08.520 --> 03:15:09.840
I didn't mean to burn you.

03:15:09.899 --> 03:15:10.799
I really didn't.

03:15:10.860 --> 03:15:12.540
I'm here to help your friends stop

03:15:12.540 --> 03:15:13.079
Scarlet.

03:15:13.200 --> 03:15:15.479
Stop dying and listen to me.

03:15:15.540 --> 03:15:17.219
He's going to die.

03:15:17.340 --> 03:15:20.520
Winter is going to die, and Clay is never

03:15:20.520 --> 03:15:21.540
going to speak to me again.

03:15:21.600 --> 03:15:24.000
I'm going to be alone forever.

03:15:24.059 --> 03:15:27.600
She took a hopeless step toward him, but

03:15:27.600 --> 03:15:28.500
there was nothing she could do.

03:15:28.559 --> 03:15:30.600
Touching him would only make it worse.

03:15:30.659 --> 03:15:34.200
Not that it could get worse, except he'd

03:15:34.200 --> 03:15:36.120
die faster, and maybe that would be a

03:15:36.120 --> 03:15:36.479
mercy.

03:15:36.540 --> 03:15:38.040
Look at him.

03:15:38.100 --> 03:15:41.100
I am as bad as everyone thinks I am.

03:15:41.159 --> 03:15:43.920
I'm the one who did this, me and my

03:15:43.920 --> 03:15:45.059
monstrous claws.

03:15:45.120 --> 03:15:47.579
Peril had never cried.

03:15:47.639 --> 03:15:49.620
She wasn't sure if she could.

03:15:49.680 --> 03:15:53.100
But she had felt vast emptiness like this

03:15:53.100 --> 03:15:53.399
before.

03:15:53.459 --> 03:15:57.059
Opening up inside her, when Osprey died.

03:15:57.180 --> 03:15:59.879
When she had to leave clay the 1st time

03:15:59.879 --> 03:16:02.520
when she found out her mother was dead.

03:16:02.579 --> 03:16:06.420
And worst of all, when she saw the dragon

03:16:06.420 --> 03:16:09.659
bite viper sink its fangs into Clay's leg

03:16:09.659 --> 03:16:11.940
and she thought he would die, and she

03:16:11.940 --> 03:16:14.100
would lose him, and the world would not

03:16:14.100 --> 03:16:15.299
be worth living in anymore.

03:16:15.360 --> 03:16:19.680
This emptiness, though, had freezing wind

03:16:19.680 --> 03:16:22.260
shrieking through the darkness, shrieking

03:16:22.260 --> 03:16:25.559
this is your fault, your fault, your

03:16:25.559 --> 03:16:26.040
fault.

03:16:26.100 --> 03:16:28.920
You deserve to be the most hated dragon

03:16:28.920 --> 03:16:29.579
empirea.

03:16:29.639 --> 03:16:31.680
Your fault, your fault.

03:16:31.739 --> 03:16:35.340
Moon, Winter gasped.

03:16:35.399 --> 03:16:37.020
Tell...

03:16:37.020 --> 03:16:37.979
Moon.

03:16:38.040 --> 03:16:40.739
He closed his eyes, folding into

03:16:40.739 --> 03:16:41.100
himself.

03:16:41.159 --> 03:16:42.600
Winter.

03:16:42.719 --> 03:16:44.639
A voice shouted from the sky.

03:16:44.700 --> 03:16:46.260
Winter?

03:16:46.319 --> 03:16:48.059
Of course they were here.

03:16:48.120 --> 03:16:50.819
Just in time to see what peril had done

03:16:50.819 --> 03:16:52.979
to witness her monstrosity.

03:16:53.040 --> 03:16:56.340
She jumped back out of the way as Moon

03:16:56.340 --> 03:16:58.979
Kibley, and Turtle thudded down and

03:16:58.979 --> 03:17:00.659
surged into a crowd around winter.

03:17:00.719 --> 03:17:04.860
Winter, moon cried again, grabbing his

03:17:04.860 --> 03:17:06.000
front talons in hers.

03:17:06.120 --> 03:17:08.399
Oh, no, oh, no, oh, no.

03:17:08.459 --> 03:17:11.219
It was an accident, peril said.

03:17:11.280 --> 03:17:12.540
I didn't mean to burn him.

03:17:12.600 --> 03:17:13.079
I didn't.

03:17:13.139 --> 03:17:15.239
What are our options?

03:17:15.299 --> 03:17:16.739
Kibley said frantically.

03:17:16.799 --> 03:17:17.879
I know.

03:17:17.940 --> 03:17:19.799
Winter frost breath your scales.

03:17:19.860 --> 03:17:21.479
That should numb the injuries long enough

03:17:21.479 --> 03:17:22.440
to get him to the river.

03:17:22.500 --> 03:17:24.540
Isn't there a cactus sat that heals

03:17:24.540 --> 03:17:25.020
burns?

03:17:25.079 --> 03:17:25.680
Winter.

03:17:25.739 --> 03:17:26.940
Come on, don't pass out.

03:17:27.000 --> 03:17:27.959
We can fix this.

03:17:28.079 --> 03:17:31.200
The silver dragon lay limply on the rocks

03:17:31.200 --> 03:17:34.139
in front of them, shuddering in agony.

03:17:34.200 --> 03:17:35.819
He didn't respond to either Moon or

03:17:35.819 --> 03:17:36.540
Kibley.

03:17:36.600 --> 03:17:39.540
Peril couldn't bear to look at him at the

03:17:39.540 --> 03:17:41.879
black scorch marks imprinted all over his

03:17:41.879 --> 03:17:43.020
snow white scales.

03:17:43.079 --> 03:17:45.180
That had to be too many burns to

03:17:45.180 --> 03:17:45.780
survive.

03:17:45.840 --> 03:17:48.479
He was probably going into shock if he

03:17:48.479 --> 03:17:49.139
hadn't already.

03:17:49.200 --> 03:17:51.360
She couldn't look at turtle either.

03:17:51.420 --> 03:17:53.760
He was clutching his head and pacing

03:17:53.760 --> 03:17:57.120
around Winter's tail, and she knew if she

03:17:57.120 --> 03:17:59.760
met his eyes, she'd see how much he must

03:17:59.760 --> 03:18:00.719
hate her now.

03:18:00.719 --> 03:18:02.520
What can we do?

03:18:02.639 --> 03:18:04.440
Kibley asked Moon.

03:18:04.500 --> 03:18:06.540
And when she didn't answer because she

03:18:06.540 --> 03:18:08.700
was crying too hard, he whirled on

03:18:08.700 --> 03:18:09.059
peril.

03:18:09.120 --> 03:18:10.799
What can we do?

03:18:10.860 --> 03:18:14.040
I don't know, peril cried.

03:18:14.100 --> 03:18:16.139
I'm the problem, not the solution.

03:18:16.260 --> 03:18:19.379
Use this, Turtle said.

03:18:19.440 --> 03:18:21.479
Scrabbling in the pouch around his neck.

03:18:21.540 --> 03:18:24.659
His voice sounded weird, like it was

03:18:24.659 --> 03:18:26.159
being mangled as it came out of his

03:18:26.159 --> 03:18:28.680
throat, and his expression was closer to

03:18:28.680 --> 03:18:30.959
terror than anger, now that peril could

03:18:30.959 --> 03:18:31.739
see it.

03:18:31.799 --> 03:18:33.959
He yanked the grayish white river rock

03:18:33.959 --> 03:18:35.579
from the pouch and held it out.

03:18:35.639 --> 03:18:38.040
Nothing could have looked more ordinary

03:18:38.040 --> 03:18:39.059
or useless.

03:18:39.120 --> 03:18:40.440
What?

03:18:40.559 --> 03:18:42.959
Kimley said, blinking back tears.

03:18:43.020 --> 03:18:47.219
A rock isn't going to, peril started, but

03:18:47.219 --> 03:18:49.500
she trailed off as Turtle pushed Kibli

03:18:49.500 --> 03:18:52.020
aside and placed the rock on top of one

03:18:52.020 --> 03:18:53.040
of Winter's burns.

03:18:53.100 --> 03:18:56.340
Winter let out a yelp of pain at the

03:18:56.340 --> 03:18:59.040
sudden contact, and Moon reached toward

03:18:59.040 --> 03:19:01.079
Turtle's talons, then stopped.

03:19:01.139 --> 03:19:04.739
Below the rock, the burn looked as if it

03:19:04.739 --> 03:19:05.760
was evaporating.

03:19:05.819 --> 03:19:09.120
The blackness disappeared, and the scales

03:19:09.120 --> 03:19:12.239
smoothed over, silver and untouched

03:19:12.239 --> 03:19:12.600
again.

03:19:12.659 --> 03:19:16.620
Turtle moved the rock, sliding it gently

03:19:16.620 --> 03:19:19.020
over the burns all along winter's torso

03:19:19.020 --> 03:19:19.500
and wings.

03:19:19.620 --> 03:19:22.319
It looked as though he was sweeping snow

03:19:22.319 --> 03:19:23.340
along behind it.

03:19:23.459 --> 03:19:25.559
Every injury disappeared.

03:19:25.620 --> 03:19:29.340
Every wound knitted itself back together

03:19:29.340 --> 03:19:29.819
and vanished.

03:19:29.879 --> 03:19:33.420
The ice wing's breathing became slower

03:19:33.420 --> 03:19:34.260
and less ragged.

03:19:34.319 --> 03:19:36.780
He opened his eyes, and watched the

03:19:36.780 --> 03:19:39.420
progress of the rock, his face a mask of

03:19:39.420 --> 03:19:41.040
confusion and awe.

03:19:41.100 --> 03:19:42.719
Within a few moments.

03:19:42.780 --> 03:19:44.940
Winter was completely healed.

03:19:45.000 --> 03:19:48.899
Everyone stared at Turtle, who very much

03:19:48.899 --> 03:19:50.940
looked as though he wanted a deep ocean

03:19:50.940 --> 03:19:53.459
chasm to hide in, he stepped back

03:19:53.459 --> 03:19:56.459
awkwardly twisting the rock in his talons

03:19:56.459 --> 03:19:58.319
as though it was a strange growth that

03:19:58.319 --> 03:19:59.100
had just appeared.

03:19:59.219 --> 03:20:01.379
Did I get all of it?

03:20:01.379 --> 03:20:02.280
he asked.

03:20:02.340 --> 03:20:04.200
What?

03:20:04.319 --> 03:20:05.399
Moon said.

03:20:05.459 --> 03:20:07.739
She shook her head and crouched beside

03:20:07.739 --> 03:20:10.319
Winter, gently running one talon over a

03:20:10.319 --> 03:20:12.540
patch of smooth scales on his torso.

03:20:12.600 --> 03:20:13.920
Turtle.

03:20:13.979 --> 03:20:14.879
What?

03:20:15.000 --> 03:20:18.719
Her voice faded away, swallowed by the

03:20:18.719 --> 03:20:21.959
disbelief swooping across her face, Winter

03:20:21.959 --> 03:20:24.299
sat up, holding out his talons with an

03:20:24.299 --> 03:20:27.239
awed expression, his wings cautiously

03:20:27.239 --> 03:20:29.399
expanded to their full width, then closed

03:20:29.399 --> 03:20:29.879
again.

03:20:29.940 --> 03:20:31.799
The burns were really gone.

03:20:31.860 --> 03:20:33.840
Turtle.

03:20:33.899 --> 03:20:35.340
Kibley said carefully.

03:20:35.399 --> 03:20:38.340
Why do you have a magic healing rock?

03:20:38.520 --> 03:20:39.420
No wait.

03:20:39.479 --> 03:20:42.899
How do you have a magic healing rock?

03:20:42.959 --> 03:20:45.360
Peril couldn't put our thoughts in

03:20:45.360 --> 03:20:45.899
order?

03:20:45.959 --> 03:20:47.879
She couldn't wrap her brain around winter

03:20:47.879 --> 03:20:49.979
surviving what she'd done.

03:20:50.040 --> 03:20:51.840
She couldn't even feel relieved yet.

03:20:51.899 --> 03:20:55.559
It was too immense and strange and

03:20:55.559 --> 03:20:56.100
impossible.

03:20:56.159 --> 03:20:59.100
There wasn't any room in her head for all

03:20:59.100 --> 03:21:00.600
her new questions about turtle.

03:21:00.659 --> 03:21:03.059
She pulled her wings in as close as

03:21:03.059 --> 03:21:05.579
possible, watching Winter's perfectly

03:21:05.579 --> 03:21:08.579
unharmed scales shift and half expecting

03:21:08.579 --> 03:21:10.440
him to suddenly collapse into a pile of

03:21:10.440 --> 03:21:11.159
ashes anyway.

03:21:11.219 --> 03:21:15.600
It's an animus touched object, Moon said

03:21:15.600 --> 03:21:16.200
to Turtle.

03:21:16.260 --> 03:21:17.879
Where did you get?

03:21:17.879 --> 03:21:19.440
Oh.

03:21:19.559 --> 03:21:22.680
Her eyes suddenly went as wide as the

03:21:22.680 --> 03:21:24.239
moons she was named after.

03:21:24.299 --> 03:21:26.219
Kibley got it a 2nd later.

03:21:26.280 --> 03:21:30.600
You didn't find it somewhere, he said

03:21:30.600 --> 03:21:32.219
sounding awestruck.

03:21:32.280 --> 03:21:33.239
You made it.

03:21:33.299 --> 03:21:35.940
You're an animus dragon.

03:21:36.000 --> 03:21:39.899
That's your secret, Moon breathed.

03:21:39.959 --> 03:21:42.299
She had an expression like someone who'd

03:21:42.299 --> 03:21:45.120
just managed to finally alphabetize a

03:21:45.120 --> 03:21:46.680
1000000 scrolls exactly right.

03:21:46.739 --> 03:21:49.079
An animus.

03:21:49.139 --> 03:21:52.139
That's why he thinks he can handle Queen

03:21:52.139 --> 03:21:54.120
Scarlet, Pearl realized.

03:21:54.180 --> 03:21:58.260
Turtle said, shivering his wings.

03:21:58.319 --> 03:22:00.780
I've never heard anyone say that out loud

03:22:00.780 --> 03:22:01.200
before.

03:22:01.260 --> 03:22:03.059
Nobody else knows.

03:22:03.120 --> 03:22:06.659
Actually, can we not talk about it?

03:22:06.840 --> 03:22:07.799
It's really not a big deal.

03:22:07.860 --> 03:22:12.600
Not, uh, Winter suddenly chimed in, then

03:22:12.600 --> 03:22:14.879
cut himself off with a growl lashing his

03:22:14.879 --> 03:22:15.120
tail.

03:22:15.180 --> 03:22:18.659
You could have told me, Pearl said to

03:22:18.659 --> 03:22:19.079
Turtle.

03:22:19.139 --> 03:22:20.760
Wasn't that what friends did?

03:22:20.819 --> 03:22:23.280
He hadn't told her about Moon's power

03:22:23.280 --> 03:22:26.219
because it was her secret, but he could

03:22:26.219 --> 03:22:27.000
have told her this.

03:22:27.120 --> 03:22:30.899
I was thinking about it, Turtle said to

03:22:30.899 --> 03:22:31.319
Parel.

03:22:31.379 --> 03:22:34.739
I mean, so we're not so different, you

03:22:34.739 --> 03:22:35.760
and I, right?

03:22:35.819 --> 03:22:40.799
Well, I never had the option of hiding my

03:22:40.799 --> 03:22:42.899
gift, peril thought.

03:22:42.959 --> 03:22:45.180
That's a pretty big difference.

03:22:45.239 --> 03:22:47.879
Would anyone else like to make a dramatic

03:22:47.879 --> 03:22:49.020
confession?

03:22:49.020 --> 03:22:49.739
Kibley asked.

03:22:49.799 --> 03:22:51.780
Who else is hiding magic powers?

03:22:51.840 --> 03:22:53.760
Winter, anything we should know?

03:22:53.819 --> 03:22:56.520
A secret ice wing ability to kill dragons

03:22:56.520 --> 03:22:57.180
with a sneer?

03:22:57.239 --> 03:22:58.379
No.

03:22:58.440 --> 03:22:59.700
Trust me.

03:22:59.760 --> 03:23:01.020
I'm nothing special.

03:23:01.139 --> 03:23:02.700
Winter growled.

03:23:02.760 --> 03:23:04.440
Same here.

03:23:04.500 --> 03:23:07.680
Kibley glanced around at Moon, Peril, and

03:23:07.680 --> 03:23:08.340
Turtle.

03:23:08.399 --> 03:23:10.620
At least, that makes 2 of us.

03:23:10.680 --> 03:23:12.899
When did you make this rock?

03:23:13.020 --> 03:23:14.819
Moon asked Turtle.

03:23:14.879 --> 03:23:16.500
Are you all right?

03:23:16.559 --> 03:23:19.260
How much have you used your power so

03:23:19.260 --> 03:23:19.739
far?

03:23:19.799 --> 03:23:22.559
She rubbed her forehead, her wings

03:23:22.559 --> 03:23:24.540
flickering like moths around a candle.

03:23:24.600 --> 03:23:28.860
Don't worry, my soul is fine, Turtle said

03:23:28.860 --> 03:23:29.819
waving at the air.

03:23:29.879 --> 03:23:32.159
I have an enchanted very many things.

03:23:32.219 --> 03:23:35.280
I mean, I didn't want anyone to notice I

03:23:35.280 --> 03:23:36.600
can do this, obviously.

03:23:36.659 --> 03:23:38.159
But why?

03:23:38.219 --> 03:23:39.780
Winter exploded.

03:23:39.840 --> 03:23:41.819
Why would you hide your power?

03:23:41.879 --> 03:23:43.920
You could have served your tribe during

03:23:43.920 --> 03:23:44.340
the war.

03:23:44.399 --> 03:23:46.620
Your queen needed you.

03:23:46.680 --> 03:23:48.299
You could have won the war easily with a

03:23:48.299 --> 03:23:48.899
gift like that.

03:23:48.959 --> 03:23:53.219
Well, Turtles said, shying away from

03:23:53.219 --> 03:23:53.459
him.

03:23:53.520 --> 03:23:55.920
Um, exactly.

03:23:55.979 --> 03:24:00.180
Wait, so it would be all right with you

03:24:00.180 --> 03:24:03.299
Pearl said suddenly to Winter, for his

03:24:03.299 --> 03:24:06.299
queen to use him as a weapon, but it was

03:24:06.299 --> 03:24:08.280
the most unforgivable crime in history

03:24:08.280 --> 03:24:10.559
for my queen to use me as one?

03:24:10.620 --> 03:24:14.100
An awkward silence dropped over the group

03:24:14.100 --> 03:24:17.639
like a dragon flame cactus, full of guilt

03:24:17.639 --> 03:24:21.180
suspicion, distrust, judgment, superiority

03:24:21.180 --> 03:24:22.440
instead of thorn seeds.

03:24:22.559 --> 03:24:25.620
Nobody would meet peril's eyes, not even

03:24:25.620 --> 03:24:26.100
turtle.

03:24:26.159 --> 03:24:27.899
I get it.

03:24:27.959 --> 03:24:30.299
Moon said finally to Turtle.

03:24:30.360 --> 03:24:33.360
You should be the one who decides what to

03:24:33.360 --> 03:24:36.780
do with your abilities, not your queen, or

03:24:36.780 --> 03:24:37.379
anyone else.

03:24:37.440 --> 03:24:41.219
Now she glanced at peril quickly, almost

03:24:41.219 --> 03:24:42.959
as if she were throwing out a tail for

03:24:42.959 --> 03:24:44.219
peril to grab.

03:24:44.280 --> 03:24:45.360
Me?

03:24:45.420 --> 03:24:46.379
Peril thought.

03:24:46.440 --> 03:24:48.600
Did she mean that for me too?

03:24:48.659 --> 03:24:51.059
I never get to decide anything?

03:24:51.180 --> 03:24:54.360
If I did, I'd probably mess up and nearly

03:24:54.360 --> 03:24:56.219
kill or really kill someone else.

03:24:56.280 --> 03:24:59.760
Would that rock work on Kinkaju?

03:24:59.819 --> 03:25:00.840
Kibli asked.

03:25:00.899 --> 03:25:02.280
Could we heal her too?

03:25:02.340 --> 03:25:04.260
Turtle squirmed.

03:25:04.319 --> 03:25:06.540
We could try, he said.

03:25:06.600 --> 03:25:09.299
But I'm afraid I enchanted it to heal

03:25:09.299 --> 03:25:12.360
scales and muscles, not internal organs

03:25:12.360 --> 03:25:12.899
or bones.

03:25:12.959 --> 03:25:15.540
It was only supposed to help me feel less

03:25:15.540 --> 03:25:16.979
sore after flying all day.

03:25:17.040 --> 03:25:18.780
I know.

03:25:18.840 --> 03:25:19.620
I was an idiot.

03:25:19.680 --> 03:25:21.360
I should have made it more useful.

03:25:21.420 --> 03:25:25.079
And more obvious, Pearl said.

03:25:25.139 --> 03:25:27.000
What a dopey thing to enchant.

03:25:27.059 --> 03:25:28.979
It looks like every other rock in the

03:25:28.979 --> 03:25:29.280
world.

03:25:29.340 --> 03:25:31.680
If you drop it while you're leaning over

03:25:31.680 --> 03:25:33.479
a river one day, you'll never find it

03:25:33.479 --> 03:25:34.139
again.

03:25:34.200 --> 03:25:36.299
It might work on your scar, though.

03:25:36.420 --> 03:25:38.340
Turtle said to Kibley.

03:25:38.399 --> 03:25:40.379
He held out the rock and Kibley jumped

03:25:40.379 --> 03:25:40.860
away from it.

03:25:40.920 --> 03:25:44.459
No way, he said, touching his snout.

03:25:44.520 --> 03:25:45.959
I like my scar.

03:25:46.020 --> 03:25:46.860
It's part of who I am.

03:25:46.920 --> 03:25:49.500
Get your magic nonsense away from me.

03:25:49.559 --> 03:25:52.979
Hey, Winter interrupted suddenly.

03:25:53.040 --> 03:25:55.260
Where's Foe Slayer?

03:25:55.319 --> 03:25:56.879
Who?

03:25:56.940 --> 03:25:57.840
Moon asked.

03:25:57.899 --> 03:26:00.479
I was traveling with a night wing?

03:26:00.540 --> 03:26:01.319
He said.

03:26:01.379 --> 03:26:02.340
Where'd she go?

03:26:02.399 --> 03:26:05.639
Peril glanced up and realized the big

03:26:05.639 --> 03:26:07.319
night wing was no longer in the sky above

03:26:07.319 --> 03:26:07.620
them.

03:26:07.680 --> 03:26:10.139
She tried to remember when she'd last

03:26:10.139 --> 03:26:13.020
seen her, right after the fight, before

03:26:13.020 --> 03:26:14.280
Turtle and the others showed up.

03:26:14.340 --> 03:26:18.360
Uh, she said, I might have told her to go

03:26:18.360 --> 03:26:18.780
get help.

03:26:18.899 --> 03:26:22.620
Or she might have decided I was dead and

03:26:22.620 --> 03:26:24.239
left before the same thing happened to

03:26:24.239 --> 03:26:24.479
her.

03:26:24.540 --> 03:26:26.340
Winter said bitterly.

03:26:26.399 --> 03:26:29.100
He stood up in one quick coiling motion.

03:26:29.159 --> 03:26:30.600
We needed her.

03:26:30.659 --> 03:26:32.579
She was going to help us find the lost

03:26:32.579 --> 03:26:33.299
city of night.

03:26:33.420 --> 03:26:35.639
The what?

03:26:35.700 --> 03:26:36.659
peril said.

03:26:36.719 --> 03:26:40.620
Hey Moon said to Winter, trying to nudge

03:26:40.620 --> 03:26:41.100
him back down.

03:26:41.159 --> 03:26:43.799
Maybe don't make any sudden movements

03:26:43.799 --> 03:26:45.360
until we're sure you're all right.

03:26:45.420 --> 03:26:48.239
Also, I'm glad you came back, by the

03:26:48.239 --> 03:26:48.420
way.

03:26:48.540 --> 03:26:50.399
I'm all right.

03:26:50.459 --> 03:26:53.100
Winter said, stretching his wings and

03:26:53.100 --> 03:26:53.579
neck again.

03:26:53.639 --> 03:26:55.860
It's like it never happened.

03:26:55.920 --> 03:26:59.459
He turned accusing eyes on peril, who

03:26:59.459 --> 03:27:01.079
felt them like little blades of ice

03:27:01.079 --> 03:27:02.760
stabbing her own eyeballs.

03:27:02.819 --> 03:27:04.799
Except that it did.

03:27:04.860 --> 03:27:07.500
This monster threatened you and then

03:27:07.500 --> 03:27:08.819
claimed she was here to help you.

03:27:08.879 --> 03:27:12.899
I didn't threaten anyone, Pearl protested

03:27:12.899 --> 03:27:13.979
not.

03:27:14.100 --> 03:27:16.620
I mean, not really.

03:27:16.680 --> 03:27:20.760
She is here to help us, Turtle said at

03:27:20.760 --> 03:27:21.299
the same time.

03:27:21.420 --> 03:27:22.799
At least I think so.

03:27:22.920 --> 03:27:25.139
You think so?

03:27:25.200 --> 03:27:27.360
Pearl cried, wounded.

03:27:27.420 --> 03:27:32.100
I mean, he said anxiously, I guess I wish

03:27:32.100 --> 03:27:33.659
you hadn't burned winter is all.

03:27:33.719 --> 03:27:35.639
It was an accident.

03:27:35.700 --> 03:27:37.319
Perl said.

03:27:37.379 --> 03:27:39.600
I was trying to get away from him, and we

03:27:39.600 --> 03:27:40.860
crashed.

03:27:40.920 --> 03:27:42.479
It looked like a fight from what we saw

03:27:42.479 --> 03:27:44.700
Kimley said accusingly.

03:27:44.760 --> 03:27:47.760
Beware the talons of power and fire.

03:27:47.819 --> 03:27:49.620
Moon said softly.

03:27:49.680 --> 03:27:51.840
Maybe it is her.

03:27:51.899 --> 03:27:55.020
Pearl looked from one phase to another

03:27:55.020 --> 03:27:56.340
her heart pounding.

03:27:56.399 --> 03:27:58.260
What are you talking about?

03:27:58.260 --> 03:27:59.399
she said.

03:27:59.459 --> 03:28:01.319
Moon had a vision.

03:28:01.440 --> 03:28:03.420
A prophecy.

03:28:03.479 --> 03:28:04.620
Turtle said.

03:28:04.680 --> 03:28:06.479
About me?

03:28:06.540 --> 03:28:08.940
That couldn't be a good sign.

03:28:09.059 --> 03:28:11.819
If moon saw peril in a vision doing

03:28:11.819 --> 03:28:14.340
terrible things, then maybe peril's bad

03:28:14.340 --> 03:28:16.139
side really was going to win out in the

03:28:16.139 --> 03:28:16.379
end.

03:28:16.440 --> 03:28:18.360
Maybe it was inevitable.

03:28:18.479 --> 03:28:20.760
Maybe she shouldn't even try to fight

03:28:20.760 --> 03:28:21.000
it.

03:28:21.120 --> 03:28:25.260
But Clay said, Clay believes in me.

03:28:25.319 --> 03:28:27.659
He can't be wrong.

03:28:27.719 --> 03:28:28.920
Can he?

03:28:28.979 --> 03:28:33.059
Not specifically about you, Moon said.

03:28:33.120 --> 03:28:36.360
I couldn't see any dragons' faces in the

03:28:36.360 --> 03:28:38.639
vision, but there was one line at the

03:28:38.639 --> 03:28:38.940
beginning.

03:28:39.000 --> 03:28:42.239
Excuse me, Winter said.

03:28:42.299 --> 03:28:44.639
Are we really going to tell the villain

03:28:44.639 --> 03:28:46.319
everything we know about their evil

03:28:46.319 --> 03:28:46.620
plan?

03:28:46.680 --> 03:28:48.959
I don't have an evil plan.

03:28:49.079 --> 03:28:51.600
Pearl said, starting to panic.

03:28:51.659 --> 03:28:53.940
All my evilest spur of the moment.

03:28:54.000 --> 03:28:55.860
Turtle, tell them how bad I am at

03:28:55.860 --> 03:28:56.219
planning.

03:28:56.280 --> 03:29:00.000
Maybe if she knows about the prophecy, she

03:29:00.000 --> 03:29:02.399
can do something different, Moon said.

03:29:02.459 --> 03:29:05.159
We can change the future, you know.

03:29:05.219 --> 03:29:08.760
She turned apparel and said, Listen

03:29:08.760 --> 03:29:12.059
Beware the darkness of dragons.

03:29:12.180 --> 03:29:15.360
Beware the stalker of dreams.

03:29:15.420 --> 03:29:19.500
Beware the talons of power and fire.

03:29:19.559 --> 03:29:24.360
Beware one who is not what she seems.

03:29:24.420 --> 03:29:27.299
Something is coming to shake the earth.

03:29:28.379 --> 03:29:30.479
Something is coming to scorch the

03:29:30.479 --> 03:29:30.959
ground.

03:29:31.020 --> 03:29:34.500
Jade mountain will fall beneath thunder

03:29:34.500 --> 03:29:38.100
and ice, unless the lost city of night

03:29:38.100 --> 03:29:39.239
can be found.

03:29:39.299 --> 03:29:42.120
Peril looked from her to the others.

03:29:42.180 --> 03:29:45.719
Moon's eyes were glowing, as though she

03:29:45.719 --> 03:29:47.579
was delivering a message from the stars

03:29:47.579 --> 03:29:48.120
themselves.

03:29:48.180 --> 03:29:51.780
Her voice got all low and shivery, and it

03:29:51.780 --> 03:29:53.399
was decidedly creepy.

03:29:53.459 --> 03:29:57.239
Well, Moon asked, what do you think?

03:29:57.360 --> 03:30:01.020
You think that 1st part is about me?

03:30:01.079 --> 03:30:02.159
Perl said.

03:30:02.219 --> 03:30:04.200
Was that what Turtle thought too?

03:30:04.260 --> 03:30:07.739
Was he just keeping an eye on her in case

03:30:07.739 --> 03:30:09.600
she started scorching the ground and

03:30:09.600 --> 03:30:10.860
knocking over mountains?

03:30:10.920 --> 03:30:13.559
I don't stalk anyone's dreams?

03:30:13.620 --> 03:30:16.139
And I'm exactly what I seem like on the

03:30:16.139 --> 03:30:16.620
outside.

03:30:16.680 --> 03:30:20.579
Also, sure I have talons of fire, but no

03:30:20.579 --> 03:30:21.719
power whatsoever.

03:30:21.780 --> 03:30:24.840
If I did have any power, my life would be

03:30:24.840 --> 03:30:26.520
pretty different from what it is now

03:30:26.520 --> 03:30:27.360
believe me.

03:30:27.420 --> 03:30:31.200
Death is a power, winter said.

03:30:31.260 --> 03:30:33.719
You carry death in your talent.

03:30:33.780 --> 03:30:36.719
He lashed his tail, shooting a hard look

03:30:36.719 --> 03:30:37.920
at Kibley and Moon.

03:30:37.979 --> 03:30:40.440
Is this really your new ally?

03:30:40.500 --> 03:30:43.079
I leave for 5 days and you start working

03:30:43.079 --> 03:30:44.219
with a mass murderer?

03:30:44.340 --> 03:30:47.879
You left pretty firmly, Kibley pointed

03:30:47.879 --> 03:30:48.059
out.

03:30:48.120 --> 03:30:50.819
You said you weren't coming back, so why

03:30:50.819 --> 03:30:51.540
should you get a vote?

03:30:51.600 --> 03:30:54.059
Also, she just showed up with Turtle.

03:30:54.120 --> 03:30:58.020
And I can just leave again too. peril

03:30:58.020 --> 03:30:58.379
cried.

03:30:58.440 --> 03:31:01.260
It felt as if the thorns were still there

03:31:01.260 --> 03:31:02.940
digging under her scales.

03:31:03.000 --> 03:31:05.399
It felt like another crocodile in the

03:31:05.399 --> 03:31:05.639
face.

03:31:05.700 --> 03:31:07.979
If what she had with turtle was

03:31:07.979 --> 03:31:09.840
friendship, and this was what came with

03:31:09.840 --> 03:31:13.020
it, then friends were so not worth it.

03:31:13.079 --> 03:31:14.879
I don't need this.

03:31:14.940 --> 03:31:16.860
I don't even want to work with any of

03:31:16.860 --> 03:31:17.040
you.

03:31:17.100 --> 03:31:19.739
I can find Scarlet on my own.

03:31:19.799 --> 03:31:21.239
That's what I wanted to do in the 1st

03:31:21.239 --> 03:31:21.780
place anyway.

03:31:21.840 --> 03:31:24.600
She launched herself into the sky.

03:31:24.659 --> 03:31:27.360
Peril, turtle shouted.

03:31:27.420 --> 03:31:28.020
Wait.

03:31:28.079 --> 03:31:30.899
That was what she'd wanted him to say.

03:31:30.959 --> 03:31:32.040
But it wasn't enough.

03:31:32.100 --> 03:31:34.440
It wouldn't be enough, even if he could

03:31:34.440 --> 03:31:37.079
catch up to her, which he couldn't, and

03:31:37.079 --> 03:31:39.120
even if he apologized for his awful

03:31:39.120 --> 03:31:41.219
friends, and promised he didn't think she

03:31:41.219 --> 03:31:43.620
was some predestined, sinister bad guy.

03:31:43.680 --> 03:31:46.079
Which he wouldn't.

03:31:46.079 --> 03:31:49.920
Maybe, if he told me he'd leave them and

03:31:49.920 --> 03:31:51.000
just be friends with me.

03:31:51.059 --> 03:31:53.700
But he wasn't going to do that either.

03:31:53.760 --> 03:31:56.940
She wasn't nearly as important to him as

03:31:56.940 --> 03:31:58.319
his precious winglet.

03:31:58.379 --> 03:31:59.940
Well, that was just fine.

03:32:00.000 --> 03:32:03.000
She'd wasted enough time on him.

03:32:03.059 --> 03:32:05.459
Now she could get on with finding Queen

03:32:05.459 --> 03:32:07.979
Scarlet, killing her, and going back to

03:32:07.979 --> 03:32:08.459
clay.

03:32:08.520 --> 03:32:11.700
Peril said her course for the Claws of

03:32:11.700 --> 03:32:14.040
the Clouds Mountains, soaring directly

03:32:14.040 --> 03:32:16.260
over possibility, and beating her wings

03:32:16.260 --> 03:32:17.819
to fly as fast as she could.

03:32:17.879 --> 03:32:21.420
She did not look back to see if Turtle

03:32:21.420 --> 03:32:22.020
tried to follow her.

03:32:22.079 --> 03:32:24.059
Well, maybe once.

03:32:24.120 --> 03:32:26.100
But he wasn't so it didn't matter.

03:32:26.159 --> 03:32:30.120
After some time though, when possibility

03:32:30.120 --> 03:32:32.340
was well in the distance, she became

03:32:32.340 --> 03:32:34.260
aware of the sound of wing beats behind

03:32:34.260 --> 03:32:34.500
her.

03:32:34.559 --> 03:32:37.319
It seemed highly unlikely that any of

03:32:37.319 --> 03:32:39.719
those inferiorly winged dragonettes could

03:32:39.719 --> 03:32:41.579
have caught up to her, but she swung

03:32:41.579 --> 03:32:43.559
around with her dangerous face on just in

03:32:43.559 --> 03:32:44.219
case.

03:32:44.280 --> 03:32:47.520
Oh, said the sky wing behind her.

03:32:47.579 --> 03:32:49.920
Catching air below his wings to stop and

03:32:49.920 --> 03:32:50.340
hover.

03:32:50.399 --> 03:32:52.139
And then he smiled.

03:32:52.200 --> 03:32:54.000
He smiled.

03:32:54.059 --> 03:32:57.659
That never happened, not when dragons 1st

03:32:57.659 --> 03:32:58.079
met her.

03:32:58.139 --> 03:32:59.879
What was that about?

03:32:59.940 --> 03:33:02.399
What do you want?

03:33:02.520 --> 03:33:03.719
Peril demanded.

03:33:03.780 --> 03:33:06.719
She was pretty sure this was the Sky Wing

03:33:06.719 --> 03:33:08.340
who had flown out of possibility to meet

03:33:08.340 --> 03:33:10.799
her, but had run away again once he saw

03:33:10.799 --> 03:33:12.239
Winter and Foe Slayer.

03:33:12.299 --> 03:33:14.040
Had he been watching for her?

03:33:14.100 --> 03:33:15.959
Waiting for her to leave them?

03:33:16.020 --> 03:33:20.100
Uh, he said, nothing.

03:33:20.159 --> 03:33:23.459
Peril hovered in the air. scrutinizing

03:33:23.459 --> 03:33:23.579
him.

03:33:23.700 --> 03:33:27.479
He was big, a lot older than her, with

03:33:27.479 --> 03:33:30.780
warm orange scales and amber eyes, no

03:33:30.780 --> 03:33:32.940
scars that she could see, which was

03:33:32.940 --> 03:33:35.159
unusual for a full grown sky wing under

03:33:35.159 --> 03:33:36.059
Scarlet's reign.

03:33:36.180 --> 03:33:39.840
Huge, powerful wings, long horns with

03:33:39.840 --> 03:33:41.639
faint golden markings on them.

03:33:41.819 --> 03:33:43.799
He also looked wealthier than the average

03:33:43.799 --> 03:33:44.760
sky wing.

03:33:44.819 --> 03:33:48.059
There were gold rings on 3 of his claws, a

03:33:48.059 --> 03:33:50.340
black necklace with gold spikes circled

03:33:50.340 --> 03:33:53.340
his throat, and an armband wove like a

03:33:53.340 --> 03:33:55.020
snake all the way up one of his front

03:33:55.020 --> 03:33:58.020
legs, with tiny rubies glittering like

03:33:58.020 --> 03:33:58.920
eyes at one end.

03:33:58.979 --> 03:34:01.920
He also had a kind of black metal sheath

03:34:01.920 --> 03:34:04.379
fitted tightly across his chest with a

03:34:04.379 --> 03:34:06.420
padlock on the outside, perhaps

03:34:06.420 --> 03:34:07.440
containing more treasure.

03:34:07.500 --> 03:34:11.280
She was reasonably certain she'd never

03:34:11.280 --> 03:34:13.200
seen this particular sky wing before

03:34:13.200 --> 03:34:16.020
although it was equally possible she had

03:34:16.020 --> 03:34:17.700
and just didn't remember him.

03:34:17.760 --> 03:34:20.940
Was he one of Queen Scarlet generals?

03:34:21.000 --> 03:34:24.120
Maybe he'd been away overseeing soldiers

03:34:24.120 --> 03:34:24.479
in the war.

03:34:24.540 --> 03:34:27.540
But then, surely he'd have a war wound or

03:34:27.540 --> 03:34:28.079
2 somewhere.

03:34:28.200 --> 03:34:31.020
Your peril, he said.

03:34:31.079 --> 03:34:31.920
Right?

03:34:31.979 --> 03:34:34.440
You say that like there's actually a

03:34:34.440 --> 03:34:36.959
chance I'm someone else, Pearl said.

03:34:37.020 --> 03:34:40.440
Well, he said, there's always a chance

03:34:40.440 --> 03:34:41.100
isn't there?

03:34:41.159 --> 03:34:43.440
That was a weird thing to say.

03:34:43.500 --> 03:34:45.540
She tilted her head at him.

03:34:45.600 --> 03:34:48.420
I have no idea who you are.

03:34:48.479 --> 03:34:53.879
My name, he said importantly, is sore.

03:34:54.000 --> 03:34:56.760
Oh, Pearl said.

03:34:56.819 --> 03:34:58.620
She thought for a moment.

03:34:58.680 --> 03:34:59.280
Really?

03:34:59.340 --> 03:35:02.459
That's unusual.

03:35:02.520 --> 03:35:03.540
Is it?

03:35:03.600 --> 03:35:05.579
he asked, deflating.

03:35:05.639 --> 03:35:08.459
Well, yes, she said.

03:35:08.520 --> 03:35:13.319
Not very, um, aspirational, I guess.

03:35:13.379 --> 03:35:16.500
But it's a very sky wing name, right?

03:35:16.559 --> 03:35:17.639
He said.

03:35:17.700 --> 03:35:19.260
Why?

03:35:19.260 --> 03:35:19.979
she said.

03:35:20.040 --> 03:35:22.379
It's not like we get more sore than other

03:35:22.379 --> 03:35:23.040
dragons.

03:35:23.100 --> 03:35:25.680
It's probably the other way around since

03:35:25.680 --> 03:35:27.659
we're built for flying longer distances.

03:35:27.719 --> 03:35:29.879
Wait, he broke in.

03:35:29.940 --> 03:35:30.899
No, no, no.

03:35:30.959 --> 03:35:33.120
Not sore.

03:35:33.239 --> 03:35:34.500
Soar.

03:35:34.559 --> 03:35:38.940
S-O-A-R, like flying high over the

03:35:38.940 --> 03:35:39.420
kingdom.

03:35:39.479 --> 03:35:41.399
Oh, good grief.

03:35:41.520 --> 03:35:43.620
Have other dragons been thinking my name

03:35:43.620 --> 03:35:44.940
is sore, all these years?

03:35:45.000 --> 03:35:48.479
Probably, Pearl said.

03:35:48.540 --> 03:35:51.180
Why are you the 1st dragon to say

03:35:51.180 --> 03:35:51.479
anything?

03:35:51.540 --> 03:35:52.799
He demanded.

03:35:52.860 --> 03:35:54.840
Peril thought for a moment.

03:35:54.899 --> 03:35:58.440
Because I'm not polite, she said finally

03:35:58.440 --> 03:36:00.299
no one ever taught me to be.

03:36:00.360 --> 03:36:03.420
I don't care what dragons think, because

03:36:03.420 --> 03:36:05.459
they won't like me even if I say all the

03:36:05.459 --> 03:36:08.100
right things, and bow the right way, and

03:36:08.100 --> 03:36:09.840
smile until my snout hurts.

03:36:09.899 --> 03:36:11.280
So why should I bother?

03:36:11.340 --> 03:36:14.700
I know what you mean, he said.

03:36:14.760 --> 03:36:18.239
You can do and say everything exactly the

03:36:18.239 --> 03:36:19.440
same as everyone else.

03:36:19.559 --> 03:36:22.979
But if there's one thing different about

03:36:22.979 --> 03:36:23.219
you.

03:36:23.280 --> 03:36:24.840
That's all they care about.

03:36:24.959 --> 03:36:28.500
I assume so, Pearl said.

03:36:28.559 --> 03:36:30.780
I've never actually tried acting like

03:36:30.780 --> 03:36:31.379
other dragons.

03:36:31.440 --> 03:36:35.520
Well, it doesn't work, he said.

03:36:35.639 --> 03:36:38.459
Something was glowing in his eyes.

03:36:38.520 --> 03:36:40.319
An old, old anger.

03:36:40.379 --> 03:36:44.280
Trust me, you still end up banished from

03:36:44.280 --> 03:36:44.819
your own home.

03:36:44.879 --> 03:36:47.700
Carol looked at him in surprise.

03:36:47.760 --> 03:36:50.399
You were banished from the Sky Kingdom

03:36:50.399 --> 03:36:50.700
too?

03:36:50.760 --> 03:36:51.719
When?

03:36:51.780 --> 03:36:53.819
By Ruby or by Scarlet?

03:36:53.879 --> 03:36:54.540
What for?

03:36:54.600 --> 03:36:57.000
It's a long story.

03:36:57.059 --> 03:36:58.139
He said.

03:36:58.260 --> 03:36:59.940
I'll tell you all of it someday.

03:37:00.059 --> 03:37:03.299
But the short answer is for being

03:37:03.299 --> 03:37:03.780
myself.

03:37:03.840 --> 03:37:07.020
Because I had no choice back then.

03:37:07.079 --> 03:37:10.979
For a moment, Peril wasn't sure whether

03:37:10.979 --> 03:37:12.780
he felt familiar because she actually

03:37:12.780 --> 03:37:15.420
knew him or because he sounded so much

03:37:15.420 --> 03:37:16.079
like herself.

03:37:16.079 --> 03:37:19.920
You don't need those other dragons, he

03:37:19.920 --> 03:37:20.639
said.

03:37:20.700 --> 03:37:21.659
The ones you were just with.

03:37:21.719 --> 03:37:23.700
They can't understand you.

03:37:23.819 --> 03:37:26.940
But I can help you find what you're

03:37:26.940 --> 03:37:27.360
looking for.

03:37:27.420 --> 03:37:29.159
Oh, really?

03:37:29.219 --> 03:37:30.479
Pearl said.

03:37:30.540 --> 03:37:32.399
Do you even know what that is?

03:37:32.459 --> 03:37:34.500
I think so.

03:37:34.559 --> 03:37:36.059
He said.

03:37:36.120 --> 03:37:38.159
He flashed around her suddenly, heading

03:37:38.159 --> 03:37:38.879
for the mountains.

03:37:38.940 --> 03:37:40.260
Follow me.

03:37:40.319 --> 03:37:43.559
That wasn't terribly convincing.

03:37:43.620 --> 03:37:45.479
But it wasn't as though peril had a

03:37:45.479 --> 03:37:46.979
particularly clear alternate plan

03:37:46.979 --> 03:37:47.639
anyway.

03:37:47.700 --> 03:37:51.180
I don't like following anyone, she

03:37:51.180 --> 03:37:51.540
called.

03:37:51.600 --> 03:37:53.760
With a flick of her tail, she spun

03:37:53.760 --> 03:37:55.680
herself around, and caught up to fly

03:37:55.680 --> 03:37:56.159
beside him.

03:37:56.219 --> 03:37:59.159
Hey, why haven't I ever met you before?

03:37:59.219 --> 03:38:02.579
An excellent question, he said.

03:38:02.639 --> 03:38:05.100
The only answer I've been able to come to

03:38:05.100 --> 03:38:07.920
is that Queen Scarlet prefers to keep her

03:38:07.920 --> 03:38:09.239
toys separate from each other.

03:38:09.299 --> 03:38:14.219
I'm no one's toy, Peril hissed, curling

03:38:14.219 --> 03:38:15.000
her claws in.

03:38:15.059 --> 03:38:17.459
Why do dragons keep saying that about her

03:38:17.459 --> 03:38:18.299
and Scarlet?

03:38:18.360 --> 03:38:21.239
Anyone who tries to play with me will

03:38:21.239 --> 03:38:22.680
find that out very fast.

03:38:22.739 --> 03:38:25.860
He tipped his head in a conciliatory

03:38:25.860 --> 03:38:26.100
way.

03:38:26.219 --> 03:38:27.719
My apologies.

03:38:27.780 --> 03:38:30.360
I confess, I don't see myself that way

03:38:30.360 --> 03:38:30.659
either.

03:38:30.719 --> 03:38:33.239
Perhaps it would be more accurate to

03:38:33.239 --> 03:38:33.659
say.

03:38:33.719 --> 03:38:36.180
Scarlet didn't want her most powerful

03:38:36.180 --> 03:38:38.159
friend joining forces against her.

03:38:38.219 --> 03:38:41.819
Carol snorted a laugh, sending a little

03:38:41.819 --> 03:38:43.139
burst of flames into the sky.

03:38:43.200 --> 03:38:46.500
You're one of her most powerful friends.

03:38:46.559 --> 03:38:47.760
What can you do?

03:38:47.819 --> 03:38:50.159
Pay enemy dragons to run away?

03:38:50.280 --> 03:38:54.479
Well, he said, I doubt Scarlet would

03:38:54.479 --> 03:38:56.700
consider this useful, but among other

03:38:56.700 --> 03:38:58.620
things, it appears that I can father

03:38:58.620 --> 03:39:00.659
dragonettes with fire scales.

03:39:00.719 --> 03:39:02.639
Peril blinked at him.

03:39:02.700 --> 03:39:05.760
He stared back at her, his amber eyes

03:39:05.760 --> 03:39:06.899
almost twinkling.

03:39:06.959 --> 03:39:09.360
He seemed to be waiting for her to

03:39:09.360 --> 03:39:11.819
collapse in a fit of joy, or run around

03:39:11.819 --> 03:39:13.500
shrieking with delight or something.

03:39:13.559 --> 03:39:15.659
Oh, really?

03:39:15.719 --> 03:39:16.620
Pearl said.

03:39:16.680 --> 03:39:18.000
Do you mean me?

03:39:18.059 --> 03:39:20.520
Was that your idea of a heartwarming

03:39:20.520 --> 03:39:21.059
revelation?

03:39:21.120 --> 03:39:23.280
You're my father?

03:39:23.340 --> 03:39:25.799
Yes.

03:39:25.920 --> 03:39:27.659
He said carefully.

03:39:27.719 --> 03:39:30.479
You don't seem very excited about that.

03:39:30.540 --> 03:39:32.879
Why should I believe you?

03:39:33.000 --> 03:39:34.139
She demanded.

03:39:34.200 --> 03:39:36.360
Where have you been my whole life?

03:39:36.420 --> 03:39:38.579
Why haven't you ever talked to me

03:39:38.579 --> 03:39:39.000
before?

03:39:39.059 --> 03:39:40.979
What are you trying to get out of me

03:39:40.979 --> 03:39:41.280
now?

03:39:41.340 --> 03:39:43.559
What made you suddenly decide to say

03:39:43.559 --> 03:39:44.040
hello?

03:39:44.100 --> 03:39:47.700
Hey, hey, calm down, he said.

03:39:47.760 --> 03:39:49.200
Yeah, all right.

03:39:49.260 --> 03:39:51.959
That certainly sounded patronizing enough

03:39:51.959 --> 03:39:54.299
to make you my dad, Pearl said.

03:39:54.360 --> 03:39:55.079
Do it again.

03:39:55.139 --> 03:39:57.120
Tell me you know what's best for me.

03:39:57.180 --> 03:40:00.120
Say something about how I don't really

03:40:00.120 --> 03:40:02.280
understand the world, and you're here to

03:40:02.280 --> 03:40:04.319
guide me and teach me and help me grow up

03:40:04.319 --> 03:40:06.659
because I couldn't possibly do that on my

03:40:06.659 --> 03:40:06.840
own.

03:40:06.899 --> 03:40:09.000
Listen.

03:40:09.059 --> 03:40:10.079
He said.

03:40:10.139 --> 03:40:12.120
I didn't know you were alive.

03:40:12.180 --> 03:40:15.719
I'm usually away doing things for the

03:40:15.719 --> 03:40:16.079
queen.

03:40:16.139 --> 03:40:18.780
So I missed the entire episode where

03:40:18.780 --> 03:40:20.639
Kestrel tried to escape with you and your

03:40:20.639 --> 03:40:21.180
brother.

03:40:21.239 --> 03:40:24.239
By the time I returned, Queen Scarlett

03:40:24.239 --> 03:40:25.079
told me you were dead.

03:40:25.139 --> 03:40:27.659
She said none of Kestrel's dragonettes

03:40:27.659 --> 03:40:29.700
had survived, and that Kestrel had gone

03:40:29.700 --> 03:40:30.959
to join the talons of peace.

03:40:31.020 --> 03:40:33.780
Everyone was forbidden to speak of

03:40:33.780 --> 03:40:35.459
Kestrel, and I had no idea.

03:40:35.520 --> 03:40:39.420
I mean, I knew you existed.

03:40:39.479 --> 03:40:42.479
The dragonette with fire scales, but I

03:40:42.479 --> 03:40:44.520
didn't know you were my daughter until a

03:40:44.520 --> 03:40:44.940
few days ago.

03:40:45.000 --> 03:40:48.299
Well, Pearl said.

03:40:48.360 --> 03:40:50.100
I bet that came as quite a

03:40:50.100 --> 03:40:50.819
disappointment.

03:40:50.879 --> 03:40:53.819
Not to me, he said.

03:40:53.879 --> 03:40:57.360
My daughter is powerful and amazing and

03:40:57.360 --> 03:40:59.760
terrifying, who wouldn't be proud of

03:40:59.760 --> 03:40:59.940
that.

03:41:00.000 --> 03:41:03.420
Peril sort of wished he'd left the

03:41:03.420 --> 03:41:06.120
terrifying out of that description, but

03:41:06.120 --> 03:41:08.459
still, it was a weird feeling to be

03:41:08.459 --> 03:41:10.739
featured in a sentence anywhere near the

03:41:10.739 --> 03:41:11.520
word proud.

03:41:11.579 --> 03:41:14.940
So, how did you find out?

03:41:14.940 --> 03:41:15.360
she asked.

03:41:15.420 --> 03:41:19.139
A, uh, a friend told me.

03:41:19.200 --> 03:41:21.299
A friend?

03:41:21.299 --> 03:41:22.620
Parel echoed.

03:41:22.680 --> 03:41:24.420
He certainly took his time about it.

03:41:24.479 --> 03:41:26.639
He didn't know either.

03:41:26.700 --> 03:41:28.260
Sor protested.

03:41:28.319 --> 03:41:30.299
His name is Sirius.

03:41:30.360 --> 03:41:32.819
He's with the talons of peace, and when

03:41:32.819 --> 03:41:36.239
he told me I had to, I mean, I

03:41:36.239 --> 03:41:37.979
immediately came looking for you.

03:41:38.040 --> 03:41:39.600
If I'd known sooner.

03:41:39.719 --> 03:41:41.819
He trailed off.

03:41:41.879 --> 03:41:43.020
You would have what?

03:41:43.079 --> 03:41:44.399
Pearl asked.

03:41:44.459 --> 03:41:47.399
Saved me from the arena, told me the

03:41:47.399 --> 03:41:49.739
truth about the black rocks, stopped

03:41:49.739 --> 03:41:51.239
Queen Scarlet from using me?

03:41:51.299 --> 03:41:53.760
Stopped Ruby from banishing me?

03:41:53.819 --> 03:41:56.219
Could you actually have been useful ever

03:41:56.219 --> 03:41:57.180
in my life?

03:41:57.239 --> 03:41:58.620
I'm guessing no.

03:41:58.680 --> 03:42:01.559
I could be useful now. he said.

03:42:01.620 --> 03:42:05.159
I can change everything for you.

03:42:05.219 --> 03:42:08.639
I doubt that, Peril said.

03:42:08.700 --> 03:42:11.940
She twisted into a spiral, arrowing for

03:42:11.940 --> 03:42:13.620
the gap between the 1st 2 mountain

03:42:13.620 --> 03:42:14.219
peaks.

03:42:14.280 --> 03:42:16.739
The wind buffeted her wings, trying to

03:42:16.739 --> 03:42:18.840
knock her off course, but she stayed

03:42:18.840 --> 03:42:20.700
straight and true through the path

03:42:20.700 --> 03:42:23.760
sweeping up into a mossy valley dotted

03:42:23.760 --> 03:42:25.260
here and there with doomed sheep.

03:42:25.319 --> 03:42:29.760
As the sheep stampeded in alarm and sore

03:42:29.760 --> 03:42:32.280
caught up to peril, she spotted movement

03:42:32.280 --> 03:42:34.079
in a cluster of trees higher up the

03:42:34.079 --> 03:42:34.379
slope.

03:42:34.440 --> 03:42:36.479
Her breath caught in her throat.

03:42:36.540 --> 03:42:40.440
She knew that color orange, knew it like

03:42:40.440 --> 03:42:43.200
a bloodbath of fear and awe sweeping

03:42:43.200 --> 03:42:43.500
through her.

03:42:43.559 --> 03:42:47.579
With slow, majestic wing beats.

03:42:47.639 --> 03:42:50.159
A glittering dragon rose out of the trees

03:42:50.159 --> 03:42:51.959
and plunged toward them.

03:42:52.020 --> 03:42:54.479
It was Queen Scarlet.

03:42:54.479 --> 03:42:56.340
Peril had found her.

03:42:56.459 --> 03:42:58.860
Or she had found peril.

03:42:58.920 --> 03:43:00.360
At last.

03:43:00.420 --> 03:43:04.799
Chapter 11.

03:43:05.159 --> 03:43:09.780
It's the queen, Peril said, squaring her

03:43:09.780 --> 03:43:10.260
shoulders.

03:43:10.319 --> 03:43:11.459
You run.

03:43:11.520 --> 03:43:12.239
I'll stop her.

03:43:12.299 --> 03:43:14.159
That's what I'm here for.

03:43:14.219 --> 03:43:16.739
This is the moment when I tick her down

03:43:16.739 --> 03:43:17.159
forever.

03:43:17.219 --> 03:43:20.040
I'll finally use my fire for something

03:43:20.040 --> 03:43:22.079
that will make Pyria a safer place.

03:43:22.139 --> 03:43:25.319
Wait, Sor said.

03:43:25.500 --> 03:43:27.840
Before you attack her, hear her out.

03:43:27.899 --> 03:43:31.139
Peril whirled around and read the

03:43:31.139 --> 03:43:33.360
betrayal in his face before her mind had

03:43:33.360 --> 03:43:34.440
even processed his words.

03:43:34.500 --> 03:43:38.280
You're working with her, she growled.

03:43:38.340 --> 03:43:40.680
You brought me to her on purpose.

03:43:40.739 --> 03:43:45.000
Well, he said, to be fair, that's what

03:43:45.000 --> 03:43:47.819
she wanted, but it's also what you wanted

03:43:47.819 --> 03:43:48.420
isn't it?

03:43:48.479 --> 03:43:51.780
So does that really count as a betrayal?

03:43:51.840 --> 03:43:53.639
I mean, now everyone's happy.

03:43:53.760 --> 03:43:56.579
So, yay me?

03:43:56.639 --> 03:43:59.760
Queen Scarlet arrived then with a wish of

03:43:59.760 --> 03:44:02.100
hot air, circling maddeningly around

03:44:02.100 --> 03:44:03.420
peril and sore.

03:44:03.420 --> 03:44:05.879
Peril had forgotten how bad the scar on

03:44:05.879 --> 03:44:06.420
her face was.

03:44:06.479 --> 03:44:09.780
The queen looked thin and ragged, but

03:44:09.780 --> 03:44:12.840
still alight with fury, like a cold flame

03:44:12.840 --> 03:44:13.860
that would never go out.

03:44:13.920 --> 03:44:16.440
Oh, ho!

03:44:16.500 --> 03:44:18.479
Scarlet called to soar.

03:44:18.540 --> 03:44:20.639
That's a phase I haven't seen in a

03:44:20.639 --> 03:44:20.879
while.

03:44:20.940 --> 03:44:22.500
Me?

03:44:22.559 --> 03:44:23.520
Peril thought.

03:44:23.579 --> 03:44:26.639
I've been looking for you, she called

03:44:26.639 --> 03:44:28.979
back, whipping around to keep the queen

03:44:28.979 --> 03:44:29.520
in sight.

03:44:29.579 --> 03:44:31.739
You can't threaten my friends like that

03:44:31.739 --> 03:44:32.760
and get away with it.

03:44:32.819 --> 03:44:35.100
Friends?

03:44:35.159 --> 03:44:37.200
Queen Scarlet laughed.

03:44:37.260 --> 03:44:39.719
A hi, genuine laugh that bounds to

03:44:39.719 --> 03:44:41.280
merrily off the mountain peaks.

03:44:41.340 --> 03:44:44.100
Is that what you think glory is to you

03:44:44.100 --> 03:44:44.459
darling?

03:44:44.520 --> 03:44:47.700
I'm sure she cares about you so very

03:44:47.700 --> 03:44:48.120
much.

03:44:48.180 --> 03:44:52.379
Do you think anyone would cry if I'd

03:44:52.379 --> 03:44:54.659
dropped your decapitated head in their

03:44:54.659 --> 03:44:55.139
talons?

03:44:55.200 --> 03:44:56.940
Admit it?

03:44:57.059 --> 03:45:00.000
Nobody loves you the way you are except

03:45:00.000 --> 03:45:00.420
me.

03:45:00.479 --> 03:45:04.620
That's always been true, and it always

03:45:04.620 --> 03:45:05.639
will be true.

03:45:05.700 --> 03:45:09.180
No, it's not, Carol cried.

03:45:09.239 --> 03:45:11.159
There are other dragons who like me.

03:45:11.219 --> 03:45:14.520
But wouldn't they all change you if they

03:45:14.520 --> 03:45:15.059
could?

03:45:15.180 --> 03:45:17.280
Scarlet said pityingly.

03:45:17.340 --> 03:45:20.159
They would strip away your fire scales

03:45:20.159 --> 03:45:23.579
and squash your lovely craziness into a

03:45:23.579 --> 03:45:24.659
well mannered box.

03:45:24.719 --> 03:45:25.920
Not me, though.

03:45:25.979 --> 03:45:28.979
I think every inch of you is just

03:45:28.979 --> 03:45:29.700
perfect.

03:45:29.760 --> 03:45:34.079
As long as I do what you want, Peril

03:45:34.079 --> 03:45:36.360
pointed out, the minute I have a thought

03:45:36.360 --> 03:45:37.799
of my own, you hate me.

03:45:37.860 --> 03:45:41.219
Oh, Scarlet said.

03:45:41.280 --> 03:45:43.559
That sounds new.

03:45:43.620 --> 03:45:46.440
Have you had any of these thoughts of

03:45:46.440 --> 03:45:47.159
your own yet?

03:45:47.219 --> 03:45:50.639
All I've seen from you so far are those

03:45:50.639 --> 03:45:52.500
mud wings, thoughts, and decisions.

03:45:52.559 --> 03:45:55.500
If you actually do have one of your very

03:45:55.500 --> 03:45:57.719
own, I can't wait to hear about it.

03:45:57.780 --> 03:46:00.959
Can you 2 please stop arguing?

03:46:01.020 --> 03:46:03.299
Peril's father interjected.

03:46:03.360 --> 03:46:06.180
He angled down to land on a circle of

03:46:06.180 --> 03:46:08.760
giant boulders, peril swooped after him

03:46:08.760 --> 03:46:11.280
choosing the barest rock she could find

03:46:11.280 --> 03:46:13.200
and Scarlett joined them a moment later.

03:46:13.260 --> 03:46:16.680
The 3 Skywings glowered at one another

03:46:16.680 --> 03:46:17.760
for a long moment.

03:46:17.819 --> 03:46:20.700
At least, Pearl and Scarlet were

03:46:20.700 --> 03:46:23.459
glowering, Thor looked infuriatingly

03:46:23.459 --> 03:46:24.479
pleased with himself.

03:46:24.540 --> 03:46:28.680
I'm smarter than you think, he said to

03:46:28.680 --> 03:46:29.819
Queen Scarlet.

03:46:29.879 --> 03:46:31.079
I figured it out.

03:46:31.139 --> 03:46:33.899
You lied to me all these years, but I

03:46:33.899 --> 03:46:34.680
know the truth now.

03:46:34.739 --> 03:46:37.500
How thrilling for you.

03:46:37.559 --> 03:46:40.920
She replied with lidded eyes, hissing

03:46:40.920 --> 03:46:42.180
smoke out her nostrils.

03:46:42.239 --> 03:46:47.219
This is Kestrel's daughter, he said, his

03:46:47.219 --> 03:46:48.000
voice rising.

03:46:48.059 --> 03:46:49.680
My daughter.

03:46:49.739 --> 03:46:53.219
His tail flicked toward perils, as though

03:46:53.219 --> 03:46:55.440
he were tempted to twine it around hers

03:46:55.440 --> 03:46:57.120
but stopped at the last moment.

03:46:57.180 --> 03:46:59.819
Yes, I know.

03:46:59.879 --> 03:47:01.319
Scarlett said.

03:47:01.379 --> 03:47:04.440
She certainly is, but you didn't deserve

03:47:04.440 --> 03:47:04.739
to know.

03:47:04.799 --> 03:47:06.840
You had no right to do what you did.

03:47:06.899 --> 03:47:10.799
And so I decided you'd never get to meet

03:47:10.799 --> 03:47:12.420
the monster that came of it.

03:47:12.479 --> 03:47:15.959
I'm sure every queen in Pyria would agree

03:47:15.959 --> 03:47:16.260
with me.

03:47:16.319 --> 03:47:17.879
Why?

03:47:17.940 --> 03:47:19.739
What did he do?

03:47:19.799 --> 03:47:20.940
Pearl asked.

03:47:21.000 --> 03:47:23.399
Her heart felt like a campfire that was

03:47:23.399 --> 03:47:24.540
about to be stomped out.

03:47:24.600 --> 03:47:26.340
Scarlet smirked.

03:47:26.399 --> 03:47:29.520
So, you still haven't told her.

03:47:29.579 --> 03:47:31.260
I love it.

03:47:31.319 --> 03:47:34.319
Acting all indignant and self-righteous

03:47:34.319 --> 03:47:36.899
about me lying to you, and yet here you

03:47:36.899 --> 03:47:39.420
are, lying to your own daughter right

03:47:39.420 --> 03:47:40.319
now.

03:47:40.379 --> 03:47:43.319
Tisk, tisk, tisk.

03:47:43.379 --> 03:47:45.479
I'm not agreeing with her.

03:47:45.540 --> 03:47:48.360
Peril said to Soor, but I don't like

03:47:48.360 --> 03:47:49.139
being lied to.

03:47:49.200 --> 03:47:50.879
What is she talking about?

03:47:50.940 --> 03:47:56.819
Now is, is not the time, Thor said

03:47:56.819 --> 03:47:57.479
awkwardly.

03:47:57.540 --> 03:48:00.059
I'll tell her everything later.

03:48:00.120 --> 03:48:03.540
You don't need to tell her, said the

03:48:03.540 --> 03:48:03.959
queen.

03:48:04.020 --> 03:48:06.059
I'll just go ahead and show her.

03:48:06.120 --> 03:48:08.399
In a lightning fast move.

03:48:08.520 --> 03:48:10.920
She suddenly leaped from her boulder to

03:48:10.920 --> 03:48:13.559
sores, flipped him onto his back and

03:48:13.559 --> 03:48:14.399
pinned him to the boulder.

03:48:14.520 --> 03:48:16.139
Stop.

03:48:16.200 --> 03:48:19.200
Sora cried, pushing ineffectively at

03:48:19.200 --> 03:48:22.440
Scarlet's claws, peril reared up with her

03:48:22.440 --> 03:48:23.760
wings flared wide.

03:48:23.819 --> 03:48:25.020
This is it.

03:48:25.079 --> 03:48:26.159
I should kill her.

03:48:26.219 --> 03:48:28.020
I'd be saving my father.

03:48:28.079 --> 03:48:29.760
This is the right moment.

03:48:29.819 --> 03:48:32.700
Even Clay would want me to.

03:48:32.700 --> 03:48:33.059
Now.

03:48:33.120 --> 03:48:34.500
Do it now, peril.

03:48:34.559 --> 03:48:39.540
But, what was the truth, Scarlet wanted

03:48:39.540 --> 03:48:40.379
her to know.

03:48:40.440 --> 03:48:42.600
And what if she attacked the wrestling

03:48:42.600 --> 03:48:44.819
dragons and accidentally burned her

03:48:44.819 --> 03:48:45.479
father as well?

03:48:45.540 --> 03:48:48.600
And how could she kill the dragon who'd

03:48:48.600 --> 03:48:50.879
kept her alive when everyone else wanted

03:48:50.879 --> 03:48:51.719
her dead?

03:48:51.899 --> 03:48:53.700
And what if the queen was right?

03:48:53.760 --> 03:48:56.879
What if no one else ever did love peril?

03:48:56.940 --> 03:49:00.000
What if killing Scarlet didn't work to

03:49:00.000 --> 03:49:01.079
change everyone's minds?

03:49:01.139 --> 03:49:03.840
What if she made another mistake, like

03:49:03.840 --> 03:49:04.739
she had with winter?

03:49:04.799 --> 03:49:07.260
Only someone really died?

03:49:07.319 --> 03:49:10.020
And then even Clay had to hate her, and

03:49:10.020 --> 03:49:11.639
she got thrown out of Jade Mountain

03:49:11.639 --> 03:49:12.120
forever.

03:49:12.180 --> 03:49:15.180
And all the queens and all the kingdoms

03:49:15.180 --> 03:49:17.219
banished her, and she had nowhere to go

03:49:17.219 --> 03:49:18.899
and no one else in the world.

03:49:19.020 --> 03:49:21.899
Wouldn't she regret killing her queen

03:49:21.899 --> 03:49:22.319
then?

03:49:22.379 --> 03:49:24.899
Wouldn't she wished there was someone

03:49:24.899 --> 03:49:26.700
left alive who loved her?

03:49:26.760 --> 03:49:29.399
All these thoughts flashed through her

03:49:29.399 --> 03:49:32.100
head at once, making peril hesitate long

03:49:32.100 --> 03:49:34.680
enough to realize that Scarlet wasn't

03:49:34.680 --> 03:49:35.639
attacking sore.

03:49:35.700 --> 03:49:38.399
The queen was merely holding sore down

03:49:38.399 --> 03:49:41.040
while she sliced off the gold spiked

03:49:41.040 --> 03:49:42.120
necklace he was wearing.

03:49:42.180 --> 03:49:45.180
For such a big, strong looking sky wing

03:49:45.180 --> 03:49:47.219
he was obviously not much of a fighter.

03:49:47.280 --> 03:49:50.819
He protested loudly, but barely

03:49:50.819 --> 03:49:51.299
struggled.

03:49:51.360 --> 03:49:54.420
Finally, Queen Scarlet was able to rip

03:49:54.420 --> 03:49:56.520
the leather in two, and the choker

03:49:56.520 --> 03:49:58.680
clattered to the ground, revealing a

03:49:58.680 --> 03:50:01.319
strip of something small and white tucked

03:50:01.319 --> 03:50:02.579
into a hidden pocket inside it.

03:50:02.700 --> 03:50:04.680
There.

03:50:04.799 --> 03:50:07.680
Scarlet said, stepping back with a

03:50:07.680 --> 03:50:09.120
satisfied toss of her head.

03:50:09.180 --> 03:50:12.540
Sor scrambled to his feet, scowling.

03:50:12.600 --> 03:50:15.120
But his eyes were no longer amber.

03:50:15.180 --> 03:50:18.840
And his orange scales were shifting

03:50:18.840 --> 03:50:22.139
shrinking and changing color, just like

03:50:22.139 --> 03:50:24.420
the decapitated not glory head.

03:50:24.479 --> 03:50:27.719
Peril jumped back, leaving scorch marks

03:50:27.719 --> 03:50:29.340
across the moss on the edge of the rock.

03:50:29.399 --> 03:50:32.159
He's not a sky wing.

03:50:32.219 --> 03:50:34.020
Was he a night wing?

03:50:34.079 --> 03:50:36.120
Could he be the night wing who had

03:50:36.120 --> 03:50:37.440
followed her and turtle earlier?

03:50:37.500 --> 03:50:41.520
If I'm half Nightwing, maybe I have some

03:50:41.520 --> 03:50:43.319
cool powers I don't know about.

03:50:43.379 --> 03:50:45.299
Maybe their tribe would take me in.

03:50:45.360 --> 03:50:48.059
I bet they'd like me if they could figure

03:50:48.059 --> 03:50:48.840
out how to use me.

03:50:48.959 --> 03:50:52.559
But sores scales weren't turning black

03:50:52.559 --> 03:50:53.040
either.

03:50:53.100 --> 03:50:56.760
They were turning green.

03:50:56.819 --> 03:51:00.059
Not a rich, dark green like turtles

03:51:00.059 --> 03:51:00.719
scales.

03:51:00.780 --> 03:51:04.200
In fact, not a color green that peril had

03:51:04.200 --> 03:51:06.479
ever seen on any sea wing before.

03:51:06.540 --> 03:51:10.020
Sor was now the color of limes and jungle

03:51:10.020 --> 03:51:12.840
parakeets, a sort of nondescript

03:51:12.840 --> 03:51:15.420
yellowish green that clashed horribly

03:51:15.420 --> 03:51:16.440
with the moss under him.

03:51:16.500 --> 03:51:19.139
He was also skinnier than he had been

03:51:19.139 --> 03:51:22.500
before, with narrower shoulders and less

03:51:22.500 --> 03:51:23.459
shiny teeth.

03:51:23.520 --> 03:51:27.239
His wings were smaller and his tail, his

03:51:27.239 --> 03:51:29.639
tail coiled in a loop behind him like a

03:51:29.639 --> 03:51:33.719
monkey's or like a, A rain wing?

03:51:33.780 --> 03:51:34.860
Peril said.

03:51:34.920 --> 03:51:36.000
Seriously?

03:51:36.059 --> 03:51:38.159
My father is a rain wing?

03:51:38.219 --> 03:51:39.540
Is this a joke?

03:51:39.600 --> 03:51:43.620
He is not much of a rain wing, Scarlett

03:51:43.620 --> 03:51:44.639
said, smirking.

03:51:44.700 --> 03:51:46.319
That's why they threw him out.

03:51:46.379 --> 03:51:48.180
Just like you, actually.

03:51:48.239 --> 03:51:50.100
Banished from his kingdom.

03:51:50.159 --> 03:51:52.860
Like father, like daughter.

03:51:52.979 --> 03:51:55.200
No one wants either of you anywhere.

03:51:55.260 --> 03:51:57.780
Except me, of course.

03:51:57.840 --> 03:52:00.719
Wouldn't a little gratitude be in order

03:52:00.719 --> 03:52:01.020
here?

03:52:01.079 --> 03:52:04.739
So what if I am a rain wing?

03:52:04.799 --> 03:52:06.719
Pearl's father said to the queen.

03:52:06.780 --> 03:52:09.840
When I met Kestrel, I was a full Sky

03:52:09.840 --> 03:52:10.260
Wing.

03:52:10.319 --> 03:52:12.000
She never knew I was anything else.

03:52:12.059 --> 03:52:14.520
Our dragonettes would have been full sky

03:52:14.520 --> 03:52:15.239
wings.

03:52:15.299 --> 03:52:16.079
That's how it works.

03:52:16.200 --> 03:52:18.180
Ha!

03:52:18.239 --> 03:52:19.559
Scarlet snorted.

03:52:19.620 --> 03:52:20.700
You don't know that.

03:52:20.760 --> 03:52:23.219
I say it's no coincidence.

03:52:23.280 --> 03:52:24.600
This one turned out the way she did.

03:52:24.659 --> 03:52:27.600
Sky Wing should only have eggs with other

03:52:27.600 --> 03:52:30.479
Sky Wings, and here's your proof.

03:52:30.540 --> 03:52:33.959
That's not proof, he snapped.

03:52:34.020 --> 03:52:37.200
Skywings have been having dragonets with

03:52:37.200 --> 03:52:38.700
fire scales for centuries.

03:52:38.760 --> 03:52:40.200
You can't blame that on me.

03:52:40.260 --> 03:52:43.559
It has nothing to do with... with who I

03:52:43.559 --> 03:52:43.979
really am.

03:52:44.040 --> 03:52:46.559
I'm a hybrid?

03:52:46.620 --> 03:52:49.020
Pearl said, not quite following this

03:52:49.020 --> 03:52:49.979
conversation.

03:52:50.040 --> 03:52:52.020
How can I be half rain wing?

03:52:52.079 --> 03:52:53.819
I don't look anything like them.

03:52:53.940 --> 03:52:56.940
She held out her talons and tried to will

03:52:56.940 --> 03:52:58.379
her scales to change color.

03:52:58.440 --> 03:52:59.879
When nothing happened?

03:52:59.940 --> 03:53:02.399
She touched her front fangs, wondering

03:53:02.399 --> 03:53:04.319
whether they could secretly shoot venom.

03:53:04.379 --> 03:53:07.500
Not that she needed extra weaponry, but

03:53:07.500 --> 03:53:08.639
it would be pretty cool anyway.

03:53:08.700 --> 03:53:13.799
You are not a hybrid, said her father, a

03:53:13.799 --> 03:53:15.899
little impatiently, considering he was

03:53:15.899 --> 03:53:18.120
dropping a basket full of crazy on her

03:53:18.120 --> 03:53:18.299
head.

03:53:18.360 --> 03:53:21.899
I was a sky wing when I met Kestrel and

03:53:21.899 --> 03:53:22.620
fathered you.

03:53:22.680 --> 03:53:24.840
You wouldn't have any rain wing

03:53:24.840 --> 03:53:25.680
characteristics.

03:53:25.739 --> 03:53:27.479
You're all Skywing.

03:53:27.540 --> 03:53:30.000
But what are you talking about?

03:53:30.059 --> 03:53:31.739
You were a Sky Wing.

03:53:31.799 --> 03:53:33.000
Peril asked.

03:53:33.120 --> 03:53:35.399
Turning your scales orange doesn't make

03:53:35.399 --> 03:53:36.360
you a sky wing.

03:53:36.420 --> 03:53:38.100
Ha, ha, ha.

03:53:38.159 --> 03:53:39.540
Scarlet laughed.

03:53:39.600 --> 03:53:41.040
You can't even do that, my dear.

03:53:41.159 --> 03:53:44.399
No, but I can do other things, he

03:53:44.399 --> 03:53:44.819
snapped.

03:53:44.879 --> 03:53:48.239
I have a gift, peril.

03:53:48.299 --> 03:53:49.440
Look.

03:53:49.500 --> 03:53:51.840
He picked up the ripped necklace and held

03:53:51.840 --> 03:53:52.680
it around his neck.

03:53:52.739 --> 03:53:56.040
Once more, his scales rippled, this time

03:53:56.040 --> 03:53:59.399
back to orange, and suddenly soar the sky

03:53:59.399 --> 03:54:01.079
wing was standing in front of peril

03:54:01.079 --> 03:54:01.319
again.

03:54:01.379 --> 03:54:05.700
See, he said, in his deeper, stronger

03:54:05.700 --> 03:54:06.180
voice.

03:54:06.239 --> 03:54:08.760
I can change my entire self.

03:54:08.819 --> 03:54:11.879
Now, I'm a full sky wing.

03:54:11.940 --> 03:54:15.780
With a terrible name you gave yourself

03:54:15.780 --> 03:54:18.479
peril guest, that explains that.

03:54:18.540 --> 03:54:19.979
What's your real name?

03:54:20.040 --> 03:54:24.420
Chameleon, he said, dropping the necklace

03:54:24.420 --> 03:54:26.280
and turning back into the defensive green

03:54:26.280 --> 03:54:26.819
dragon.

03:54:26.879 --> 03:54:29.819
Some dragons might say that was a cruel

03:54:29.819 --> 03:54:32.819
irony, while others, for instance, an

03:54:32.819 --> 03:54:36.239
entire tribe of rain wings, might laugh

03:54:36.239 --> 03:54:39.959
and laugh for days once everyone realizes

03:54:39.959 --> 03:54:43.559
that the dragon named Chameleon is the

03:54:43.559 --> 03:54:45.840
only one in the rainforest who can't

03:54:45.840 --> 03:54:46.680
change his scales.

03:54:46.799 --> 03:54:50.940
Peril wasn't particularly interested in

03:54:50.940 --> 03:54:52.860
his sob stories from the past.

03:54:52.920 --> 03:54:54.840
Pieces were starting to come together in

03:54:54.840 --> 03:54:55.200
her head.

03:54:55.260 --> 03:54:58.739
You're the one who enchanted the head to

03:54:58.739 --> 03:55:00.899
look like glory, Peril said.

03:55:00.959 --> 03:55:03.180
You're helping Queen Scarlet scare my

03:55:03.180 --> 03:55:03.719
friends.

03:55:03.780 --> 03:55:08.219
Hey, she pays very well, he said

03:55:08.219 --> 03:55:10.260
displaying the rings on his claws.

03:55:10.319 --> 03:55:12.659
At least she used to.

03:55:12.719 --> 03:55:16.200
I've had more treasure than any rain wing

03:55:16.200 --> 03:55:18.120
in the history of Pyria for years now.

03:55:18.180 --> 03:55:20.700
The last several months haven't been

03:55:20.700 --> 03:55:21.780
quite the same, though.

03:55:21.840 --> 03:55:24.360
He shot a disapproving look at the

03:55:24.360 --> 03:55:24.719
queen.

03:55:24.780 --> 03:55:27.959
I'll have my kingdom back soon enough

03:55:27.959 --> 03:55:29.579
Queen Scarlet said.

03:55:29.639 --> 03:55:32.819
Although I think you owe me for the prize

03:55:32.819 --> 03:55:34.020
you lost a few days ago.

03:55:34.139 --> 03:55:37.500
Peril closed her eyes, frowning.

03:55:37.620 --> 03:55:39.840
This conversation was distracting her

03:55:39.840 --> 03:55:42.780
from her goal, killing Scarlet.

03:55:42.840 --> 03:55:45.239
If that was still the right thing to do

03:55:45.239 --> 03:55:46.680
was it?

03:55:46.739 --> 03:55:49.500
Queen Scarlet didn't seem so terrifying

03:55:49.500 --> 03:55:52.319
and monstrous here in this quiet valley

03:55:52.319 --> 03:55:54.959
talking about peril's lovely craziness

03:55:54.959 --> 03:55:55.979
and her father.

03:55:56.040 --> 03:55:59.280
Remember all the terrible things she's

03:55:59.280 --> 03:55:59.520
done?

03:55:59.579 --> 03:56:02.459
That random mud wings she killed to get

03:56:02.459 --> 03:56:02.819
that head?

03:56:02.879 --> 03:56:05.520
Sending Clay and his friends to fight in

03:56:05.520 --> 03:56:06.120
the arena?

03:56:06.180 --> 03:56:08.579
Forcing my mother to kill my twin

03:56:08.579 --> 03:56:08.940
brother?

03:56:09.000 --> 03:56:11.520
But she kept me alive.

03:56:11.579 --> 03:56:14.579
When everyone else in the tribe would

03:56:14.579 --> 03:56:17.340
have had me killed the moment I hatched

03:56:17.340 --> 03:56:19.979
and she's right, she never wanted to

03:56:19.979 --> 03:56:20.459
change me.

03:56:20.520 --> 03:56:23.159
She likes my scales the way they are.

03:56:23.219 --> 03:56:26.280
I'm not sure even clay feels that way.

03:56:26.340 --> 03:56:29.280
She remembered him wincing when he

03:56:29.280 --> 03:56:31.260
touched her, and the way he watched her

03:56:31.260 --> 03:56:32.879
wings carefully when she was near

03:56:32.879 --> 03:56:33.899
anything flammable.

03:56:33.959 --> 03:56:36.959
Did Scarlet really have to die?

03:56:37.020 --> 03:56:39.120
Oh, clay.

03:56:39.180 --> 03:56:41.700
Why can't you be here to tell me what's

03:56:41.700 --> 03:56:41.940
right?

03:56:42.000 --> 03:56:44.700
She opened her eyes and looked at

03:56:44.700 --> 03:56:46.860
Chameleon, who was fiddling with the

03:56:46.860 --> 03:56:48.239
metal sheath around his chest.

03:56:48.299 --> 03:56:51.659
This was Scarlet's mysterious new ally.

03:56:51.719 --> 03:56:55.559
Peril's own father, a disgraced rain wing

03:56:55.559 --> 03:56:57.540
with strange shape shifting abilities.

03:56:57.600 --> 03:56:59.879
He wasn't so terrifying either.

03:57:00.000 --> 03:57:03.120
Would it be so bad if Scarlet did get her

03:57:03.120 --> 03:57:03.719
thrown back?

03:57:03.780 --> 03:57:07.379
What if Ruby agreed to step down, and

03:57:07.379 --> 03:57:09.360
Scarlet agreed to leave peril's friends

03:57:09.360 --> 03:57:12.120
alone, and peril agreed to stop setting

03:57:12.120 --> 03:57:14.940
dragons on fire, unless they really

03:57:14.940 --> 03:57:15.360
deserved it.

03:57:15.479 --> 03:57:18.120
And everything went mostly back to

03:57:18.120 --> 03:57:18.780
normal.

03:57:18.840 --> 03:57:22.379
Peril, said Chameleon, breaking into her

03:57:22.379 --> 03:57:22.739
thoughts.

03:57:22.799 --> 03:57:25.260
I know I haven't been a father to you

03:57:25.260 --> 03:57:27.059
before, but I can change that.

03:57:27.120 --> 03:57:29.819
I think I can give you a gift that's

03:57:29.819 --> 03:57:31.379
everything you've always wanted.

03:57:31.440 --> 03:57:35.159
There's nothing I've always wanted, Pearl

03:57:35.159 --> 03:57:35.399
said.

03:57:35.459 --> 03:57:38.219
The image of clay wrapping his wings

03:57:38.219 --> 03:57:40.559
around her and never letting go flashed

03:57:40.559 --> 03:57:42.479
through her head, but she shoved it

03:57:42.479 --> 03:57:42.659
away.

03:57:42.719 --> 03:57:45.659
She was a long way off from getting that

03:57:45.659 --> 03:57:48.600
or deserving it, or feeling as if she

03:57:48.600 --> 03:57:51.659
could accept it even if Clay ever stop

03:57:51.659 --> 03:57:52.620
thinking about this.

03:57:52.739 --> 03:57:54.360
She ordered herself.

03:57:54.420 --> 03:57:56.700
Oh, really?

03:57:56.760 --> 03:57:59.700
Chameleon pulled out a thick chain of

03:57:59.700 --> 03:58:02.159
silvery black metal links, with a black

03:58:02.159 --> 03:58:03.899
locket dangling from one end of it.

03:58:03.959 --> 03:58:06.959
Peril recognized the metal as the kind

03:58:06.959 --> 03:58:10.020
scarlet used to bind the wings and ankles

03:58:10.020 --> 03:58:12.600
of her prisoners, impervious to most

03:58:12.600 --> 03:58:14.819
dragonfire, but not to perils.

03:58:14.940 --> 03:58:17.579
Carved on the outside of the locket was a

03:58:17.579 --> 03:58:20.340
dragon shape, wings spread and tail

03:58:20.340 --> 03:58:23.280
curled in 2 loops below, inlaid with a

03:58:23.280 --> 03:58:25.559
golden copper metal that glinted in the

03:58:25.559 --> 03:58:27.899
sunlight, like perils scales.

03:58:27.959 --> 03:58:29.819
Peril regarded it for a moment.

03:58:29.879 --> 03:58:32.639
You're right, she said.

03:58:32.700 --> 03:58:35.940
All my life, I have desperately wanted an

03:58:35.940 --> 03:58:36.780
ugly necklace.

03:58:36.840 --> 03:58:40.680
Hey, Chameleon protested, as Queen

03:58:40.680 --> 03:58:42.120
Scarlet gave a shout of laughter.

03:58:42.239 --> 03:58:45.239
Especially one that will melt the moment

03:58:45.239 --> 03:58:47.579
I put it on, Pearl said.

03:58:47.700 --> 03:58:50.159
Thank you so much.

03:58:50.219 --> 03:58:52.260
Best dad ever.

03:58:52.319 --> 03:58:56.159
This is the kind of parenting fun you've

03:58:56.159 --> 03:58:58.620
missed out on, Scarlett said to him.

03:58:58.680 --> 03:58:59.459
You're welcome.

03:58:59.520 --> 03:59:03.719
It's not just a necklace, Chameleon

03:59:03.719 --> 03:59:05.399
insisted, ignoring Scarlet.

03:59:05.459 --> 03:59:06.899
Peril.

03:59:06.959 --> 03:59:08.879
No, do you understand what I can do?

03:59:08.940 --> 03:59:11.639
I can turn you into anyone you want.

03:59:11.700 --> 03:59:15.120
I can make you a sea wing or an ice wing

03:59:15.120 --> 03:59:16.559
or even a scavenger.

03:59:16.620 --> 03:59:19.200
If you particularly wanted to get eaten

03:59:19.200 --> 03:59:21.780
for some reason, I can make you a mud

03:59:21.780 --> 03:59:22.139
wing.

03:59:22.200 --> 03:59:26.280
I can take away your fire scales.

03:59:26.340 --> 03:59:28.079
Don't you see?

03:59:28.139 --> 03:59:30.000
You could be normal.

03:59:30.059 --> 03:59:33.180
You could be a dragon who can touch other

03:59:33.180 --> 03:59:33.719
dragons.

03:59:33.780 --> 03:59:37.020
You don't have to be this monster

03:59:37.020 --> 03:59:38.399
everyone is afraid of.

03:59:38.459 --> 03:59:41.940
I can change you.

03:59:42.000 --> 03:59:45.899
Peril stared at him, wondering if her

03:59:45.899 --> 03:59:47.760
scales were floating off into the clouds

03:59:47.760 --> 03:59:49.260
the way it felt like they might be.

03:59:49.319 --> 03:59:53.159
I thought your power was only meant to be

03:59:53.159 --> 03:59:54.540
used for special cases.

03:59:54.600 --> 03:59:56.459
Scarlet mused.

03:59:56.520 --> 03:59:59.399
Something about consequences and risks

03:59:59.399 --> 04:00:00.420
and something blah.

04:00:00.540 --> 04:00:03.479
This is a special case.

04:00:03.600 --> 04:00:05.100
Chameleon said.

04:00:05.159 --> 04:00:08.159
I'd do anything for my dragonette.

04:00:08.219 --> 04:00:10.260
Aw.

04:00:10.379 --> 04:00:12.299
Scarlet said sarcastically.

04:00:12.360 --> 04:00:15.420
What a rare and unusual parent.

04:00:15.479 --> 04:00:18.239
Something seemed to strike her, and she

04:00:18.239 --> 04:00:20.579
inhaled a plume of smoke, turning her

04:00:20.579 --> 04:00:22.079
head to gaze thoughtfully toward the

04:00:22.079 --> 04:00:22.379
north.

04:00:22.440 --> 04:00:25.739
You're serious, Peril said to her

04:00:25.739 --> 04:00:25.979
father.

04:00:26.040 --> 04:00:27.780
This is real.

04:00:27.899 --> 04:00:31.319
I put that necklace on, and I won't be me

04:00:31.319 --> 04:00:31.620
anymore?

04:00:31.739 --> 04:00:34.620
She couldn't figure out how she felt

04:00:34.620 --> 04:00:35.040
about that.

04:00:35.100 --> 04:00:39.420
It sounded glorious and awful at the same

04:00:39.420 --> 04:00:39.659
time.

04:00:39.719 --> 04:00:43.860
No more peril, no more peril.

04:00:43.920 --> 04:00:46.799
Everyone would be safe from her forever.

04:00:46.860 --> 04:00:50.399
But without my fire scales.

04:00:50.459 --> 04:00:51.780
Who am I?

04:00:51.840 --> 04:00:55.379
It's up to you, he answered.

04:00:55.440 --> 04:00:57.899
This particular necklace is only

04:00:57.899 --> 04:01:00.059
enchanted to take away your fire scales.

04:01:00.120 --> 04:01:04.079
You'll still be you, the same peril, with

04:01:04.079 --> 04:01:06.059
all your own personality and history.

04:01:06.120 --> 04:01:09.000
But you'll have normal sky wing scales.

04:01:09.059 --> 04:01:11.639
And you'll be able to touch whoever you

04:01:11.639 --> 04:01:13.260
want without hurting them.

04:01:13.319 --> 04:01:15.299
Can you imagine?

04:01:15.420 --> 04:01:18.360
You'd be a regular dragon.

04:01:18.420 --> 04:01:21.540
But if you want a different enchantment

04:01:21.540 --> 04:01:24.600
turning you into someone else entirely, I

04:01:24.600 --> 04:01:25.079
could do that too.

04:01:25.139 --> 04:01:27.659
I could be a mudwing.

04:01:27.780 --> 04:01:30.780
Someone Clay could be with and love

04:01:30.780 --> 04:01:32.520
without anyone hating me for it.

04:01:32.579 --> 04:01:34.620
They don't even need to know that I used

04:01:34.620 --> 04:01:35.280
to be peril.

04:01:35.340 --> 04:01:37.200
Except for him.

04:01:37.319 --> 04:01:40.139
I need him to know who I really am.

04:01:40.200 --> 04:01:42.360
I'd have to tell him about this

04:01:42.360 --> 04:01:44.399
transformation as myself 1st.

04:01:44.459 --> 04:01:46.260
I could be peril for now.

04:01:46.319 --> 04:01:50.219
Save peril, no fire scales, no danger to

04:01:50.219 --> 04:01:53.879
anyone, and then, after I talk to him, I

04:01:53.879 --> 04:01:55.260
could become whoever he won.

04:01:55.319 --> 04:01:56.760
Clay could decide.

04:01:56.819 --> 04:01:59.579
He could imagine the perfect dragon for

04:01:59.579 --> 04:02:01.440
himself, and that's what I could become.

04:02:01.500 --> 04:02:05.040
Exactly what he wants in every detail.

04:02:05.100 --> 04:02:06.959
Then he would have to love me.

04:02:07.020 --> 04:02:08.100
Wouldn't he?

04:02:08.219 --> 04:02:10.920
She started to reach for the necklace

04:02:10.920 --> 04:02:11.819
then pulled back.

04:02:11.879 --> 04:02:14.579
It won't work, she said.

04:02:14.639 --> 04:02:16.920
That necklace will melt and fall apart

04:02:16.920 --> 04:02:18.479
the moment it touches my scales.

04:02:18.540 --> 04:02:21.959
This metal is thick and strong.

04:02:22.020 --> 04:02:24.899
Chameleon said, and the transformation

04:02:24.899 --> 04:02:25.979
only takes a moment.

04:02:26.040 --> 04:02:28.440
I think it will last until your scales

04:02:28.440 --> 04:02:29.040
are safe.

04:02:29.100 --> 04:02:30.360
If you put it on quickly.

04:02:30.420 --> 04:02:32.399
It's worth a try, isn't it?

04:02:32.459 --> 04:02:34.920
And if it doesn't work, we'll make

04:02:34.920 --> 04:02:35.520
something else.

04:02:35.579 --> 04:02:38.940
But if it does work, don't take it off.

04:02:39.000 --> 04:02:42.659
The more times it goes on and off, the

04:02:42.659 --> 04:02:44.579
more chances there are of destroying it.

04:02:44.639 --> 04:02:48.239
Peril hesitated, one last time.

04:02:48.299 --> 04:02:50.760
This isn't a trick, right?

04:02:50.819 --> 04:02:52.920
I'll still be myself?

04:02:52.979 --> 04:02:56.100
Of course, said Chameleon.

04:02:56.159 --> 04:02:59.819
Just like I am always myself, but each of

04:02:59.819 --> 04:03:01.739
my faces is a better version of me.

04:03:01.799 --> 04:03:06.299
You'll be peril, but finally, apparel

04:03:06.299 --> 04:03:08.219
that dragons can love.

04:03:08.280 --> 04:03:11.579
And if it is a trick, Pearl thought.

04:03:11.639 --> 04:03:13.139
And I disappear.

04:03:13.200 --> 04:03:15.899
Would it be such a great loss for the

04:03:15.899 --> 04:03:16.079
world?

04:03:16.139 --> 04:03:18.239
Would clay even miss me?

04:03:18.299 --> 04:03:21.479
Wouldn't turtle be happy never to see me

04:03:21.479 --> 04:03:21.780
again?

04:03:21.840 --> 04:03:24.840
She snatched the necklace from

04:03:24.840 --> 04:03:27.000
Chameleon's claws and dropped it over her

04:03:27.000 --> 04:03:29.940
head, over her horns, until it landed

04:03:29.940 --> 04:03:32.159
around her neck, the locket hitting her

04:03:32.159 --> 04:03:33.059
chest with a thump.

04:03:33.120 --> 04:03:36.239
She waited for it to curl into a molten

04:03:36.239 --> 04:03:36.540
mess.

04:03:36.600 --> 04:03:38.100
But it didn't.

04:03:38.219 --> 04:03:39.899
Nothing happened.

04:03:39.959 --> 04:03:42.899
Actually, nothing.

04:03:42.959 --> 04:03:44.520
It just sat there.

04:03:44.639 --> 04:03:46.979
Peril felt exactly the same.

04:03:47.100 --> 04:03:49.200
She poked the necklace.

04:03:49.319 --> 04:03:52.860
Nothing, just a necklace, hanging around

04:03:52.860 --> 04:03:56.639
her neck, ostentatiously not melting.

04:03:56.700 --> 04:03:58.799
How do you feel?

04:03:58.860 --> 04:04:00.059
Chameleon asked.

04:04:00.120 --> 04:04:02.459
Carol looked up to find both of them

04:04:02.459 --> 04:04:03.360
squinting at her.

04:04:03.420 --> 04:04:05.879
She held out her talons to examine them.

04:04:05.940 --> 04:04:08.399
Do I look any different?

04:04:08.459 --> 04:04:11.520
Not much, said Chameleon.

04:04:11.579 --> 04:04:15.600
Less incandescent, said Scarlett.

04:04:15.659 --> 04:04:17.340
More disappointing.

04:04:17.399 --> 04:04:19.860
More ordinary.

04:04:19.979 --> 04:04:22.920
She spat out the last word like a rotten

04:04:22.920 --> 04:04:25.860
pear, but it sounded beautiful to peril.

04:04:25.920 --> 04:04:27.180
Really?

04:04:27.299 --> 04:04:30.360
Peril turned, and saw a small yellow

04:04:30.360 --> 04:04:32.280
flower growing out of a crack in the

04:04:32.280 --> 04:04:35.340
boulder she sat on, she slowly reached

04:04:35.340 --> 04:04:38.940
out one claw, her whole arm trembling, and

04:04:38.940 --> 04:04:40.379
brushed the pedals.

04:04:40.440 --> 04:04:41.879
The flower wobbled.

04:04:41.940 --> 04:04:45.840
The flower bent with peril's claw, slipped

04:04:45.840 --> 04:04:48.360
back to its place, and fluttered its

04:04:48.360 --> 04:04:50.159
yellowness cheerfully in the wind.

04:04:50.280 --> 04:04:52.500
The flower lived.

04:04:52.620 --> 04:04:54.600
Did you see that?

04:04:54.659 --> 04:04:56.280
Pearl gasped.

04:04:56.340 --> 04:04:59.459
Yawn, said Scarlett.

04:04:59.520 --> 04:05:02.760
Perl poked the flower again, and when it

04:05:02.760 --> 04:05:05.159
still didn't burst into flame, she leaped

04:05:05.159 --> 04:05:07.739
off the boulder entirely, landing on all

04:05:07.739 --> 04:05:08.940
4s in the grass below.

04:05:09.000 --> 04:05:11.219
The grass lived.

04:05:11.280 --> 04:05:14.219
Peril ran full out across the meadow

04:05:14.219 --> 04:05:16.379
stomping her talons into the grass

04:05:16.379 --> 04:05:19.559
flicking branches with her wings rolling

04:05:19.559 --> 04:05:22.440
in patches of ivy, ramming her side into

04:05:22.440 --> 04:05:22.860
trees.

04:05:22.920 --> 04:05:25.319
Everything lived.

04:05:25.379 --> 04:05:28.260
She startled a sheep out of its hiding

04:05:28.260 --> 04:05:30.479
place in a cave, and it galloped across

04:05:30.479 --> 04:05:33.059
her path, bleeding with shaggy terror.

04:05:33.059 --> 04:05:35.940
Delighted, Pearl thwacked it with her

04:05:35.940 --> 04:05:38.040
tail, sending it bouncing across the

04:05:38.040 --> 04:05:38.940
grass several feet.

04:05:39.000 --> 04:05:42.479
It leaped up and kept running away, and a

04:05:42.479 --> 04:05:44.879
grin the size of jade mountains spread

04:05:44.879 --> 04:05:46.020
across peril's face.

04:05:46.079 --> 04:05:47.520
Look at me!

04:05:47.579 --> 04:05:50.219
She shouted to her father and her queen.

04:05:50.280 --> 04:05:52.620
She grabbed a tree with her front talons

04:05:52.620 --> 04:05:55.020
and shook it until a mortified squirrel

04:05:55.020 --> 04:05:55.379
fell out.

04:05:55.440 --> 04:05:57.180
I can do anything.

04:05:57.299 --> 04:06:01.020
Except wreak fiery vengeance on my

04:06:01.020 --> 04:06:01.379
enemies.

04:06:01.500 --> 04:06:03.959
Queen Scarlet muttered grumpily.

04:06:04.020 --> 04:06:06.600
Peril skipped back across the grass to

04:06:06.600 --> 04:06:09.180
them, settling herself on top of the most

04:06:09.180 --> 04:06:12.540
flammable patch of foliage she could find

04:06:12.540 --> 04:06:13.319
and it survived.

04:06:13.379 --> 04:06:16.379
Nothing was on fire in this hole entire

04:06:16.379 --> 04:06:17.040
valley.

04:06:17.100 --> 04:06:20.579
This was the most beautiful place in the

04:06:20.579 --> 04:06:20.819
world.

04:06:20.879 --> 04:06:24.719
Don't worry, she said to the queen

04:06:24.719 --> 04:06:27.120
breathing a small spurt of perfectly

04:06:27.120 --> 04:06:28.799
normal dragon flame from her mouth.

04:06:28.860 --> 04:06:30.479
We can still do that.

04:06:30.540 --> 04:06:33.180
The vengeance, enemies, whatever thing.

04:06:33.239 --> 04:06:34.260
Where do you want to start?

04:06:34.319 --> 04:06:37.200
Queen Scarlet sat up and looked at her.

04:06:37.260 --> 04:06:39.420
Then she looked at Chameleon.

04:06:39.479 --> 04:06:40.620
He bowed deeply.

04:06:40.680 --> 04:06:42.479
His wings spread wide.

04:06:42.540 --> 04:06:46.379
Add your service, your majesty.

04:06:46.440 --> 04:06:47.879
He said with a smile.

04:06:47.940 --> 04:06:51.180
I do have one great idea.

04:06:51.299 --> 04:06:54.540
Queen Scarlet said, regarding peril

04:06:54.540 --> 04:06:55.139
thoughtfully.

04:06:55.200 --> 04:06:57.239
Then what are we waiting for?

04:06:57.299 --> 04:06:58.620
Pearl asked.

04:06:58.680 --> 04:07:00.600
Let's go get your kingdom back.

04:07:00.659 --> 04:07:05.040
Part three.

04:07:05.100 --> 04:07:07.200
A new peril.

04:07:07.260 --> 04:07:09.959
Chapter 12.

04:07:10.319 --> 04:07:14.459
They flew north immediately, as darkness

04:07:14.459 --> 04:07:16.079
began to stretch across the mountains

04:07:16.079 --> 04:07:18.540
below them, and the tiny heartbeats of

04:07:18.540 --> 04:07:20.340
stars started to flicker in the sky.

04:07:20.399 --> 04:07:23.399
Peril felt light, lighter than she

04:07:23.399 --> 04:07:25.500
thought she'd ever felt before.

04:07:25.559 --> 04:07:27.959
She was like smoke on the wind, like a

04:07:27.959 --> 04:07:29.639
drift of dandelion seeds.

04:07:29.700 --> 04:07:31.620
She was free.

04:07:31.680 --> 04:07:34.920
I have nothing to worry about anymore.

04:07:34.979 --> 04:07:39.059
She did a flip in the air, swooped up

04:07:39.059 --> 04:07:41.639
behind her father, who was back in his

04:07:41.639 --> 04:07:44.040
sky wing shape as sore, although somehow

04:07:44.040 --> 04:07:45.719
without his ripped necklace, that was

04:07:45.719 --> 04:07:45.899
weird.

04:07:46.020 --> 04:07:47.819
She should ask him how he'd done that

04:07:47.819 --> 04:07:50.040
later, probably by enchanting something

04:07:50.040 --> 04:07:50.340
else.

04:07:50.399 --> 04:07:51.719
Whatever, no big deal.

04:07:51.780 --> 04:07:55.079
And tackled him, so he toppled sideways

04:07:55.079 --> 04:07:57.180
and had to do a funny, frantic flapping

04:07:57.180 --> 04:07:58.319
spiral to recover.

04:07:58.379 --> 04:08:00.780
Peril laughed and laughed.

04:08:00.840 --> 04:08:03.540
I've never been able to do that to anyone

04:08:03.540 --> 04:08:05.159
before, she cried.

04:08:05.219 --> 04:08:07.739
I've always wanted to tackle someone in

04:08:07.739 --> 04:08:08.219
midair.

04:08:08.280 --> 04:08:10.860
She zoomed around him and nudged one of

04:08:10.860 --> 04:08:12.540
his wings heartily with one of hers

04:08:12.540 --> 04:08:15.899
unbalancing him again, and that I've

04:08:15.899 --> 04:08:16.860
always wanted to do that.

04:08:16.920 --> 04:08:19.979
Could you perhaps save some of your

04:08:19.979 --> 04:08:22.020
affectionate impulses for when I'm not

04:08:22.020 --> 04:08:23.579
fighting an updraft?

04:08:23.639 --> 04:08:25.020
Chameleon asked.

04:08:25.079 --> 04:08:27.540
Ducking out of her way as she dive bombed

04:08:27.540 --> 04:08:27.840
him again?

04:08:27.899 --> 04:08:29.520
I mean, I love it.

04:08:29.579 --> 04:08:30.059
Thank you.

04:08:30.120 --> 04:08:32.219
But it's a little vigorous for night

04:08:32.219 --> 04:08:32.940
flying for me.

04:08:33.000 --> 04:08:36.540
You're the best, Pearl said.

04:08:36.600 --> 04:08:38.520
She couldn't stop herself from body

04:08:38.520 --> 04:08:39.840
checking him in the side again.

04:08:39.899 --> 04:08:41.700
That was the last time.

04:08:41.819 --> 04:08:44.639
I promise, she called as he reeled away.

04:08:44.760 --> 04:08:47.639
Because when we get to the Sky Palace

04:08:47.639 --> 04:08:49.620
there will be lots of dragons to do this

04:08:49.620 --> 04:08:52.440
too, I'm going to nudge wings and poke

04:08:52.440 --> 04:08:54.479
tails and hug everyone.

04:08:54.600 --> 04:08:56.219
No.

04:08:56.280 --> 04:08:58.440
Queen Scarlet said sharply.

04:08:58.500 --> 04:09:01.079
She swung around and lined herself up to

04:09:01.079 --> 04:09:02.219
fly alongside peril.

04:09:02.340 --> 04:09:05.760
You can do that, not until I have the

04:09:05.760 --> 04:09:06.239
throne back.

04:09:06.360 --> 04:09:08.520
No one can know that you're powerless

04:09:08.520 --> 04:09:09.180
now.

04:09:09.239 --> 04:09:12.180
I need the threat of you, which should be

04:09:12.180 --> 04:09:14.280
as effective as the actual fire of you

04:09:14.280 --> 04:09:15.780
after the last 7 years.

04:09:15.840 --> 04:09:18.899
Once we've secured the throne, and I've

04:09:18.899 --> 04:09:19.739
killed Ruby.

04:09:19.860 --> 04:09:22.680
Then you can be as dippy and cuddly and

04:09:22.680 --> 04:09:23.879
stupid as you want.

04:09:23.940 --> 04:09:28.440
Oh, Peril said, her light dimming a

04:09:28.440 --> 04:09:28.620
little.

04:09:28.680 --> 04:09:30.840
She had been hoping for a triumphant

04:09:30.840 --> 04:09:34.979
return as safe peril, ordinary peril, one

04:09:34.979 --> 04:09:37.559
of you, a regular sky wing who can

04:09:37.559 --> 04:09:39.899
totally just be part of the tribe now.

04:09:39.959 --> 04:09:40.680
Let's be friends.

04:09:40.799 --> 04:09:41.340
Hooray!

04:09:41.399 --> 04:09:43.920
But Queen Scarlet had a point.

04:09:43.979 --> 04:09:46.920
She needed peril's help, and that's what

04:09:46.920 --> 04:09:48.059
peril was here for after all.

04:09:48.180 --> 04:09:52.200
All right, peril said, with a flick of

04:09:52.200 --> 04:09:52.500
her tail.

04:09:52.620 --> 04:09:54.659
It won't take long to make you queen

04:09:54.659 --> 04:09:55.319
again anyway.

04:09:55.379 --> 04:09:58.680
You'll have to pay attention, said the

04:09:58.680 --> 04:09:58.920
queen.

04:09:58.979 --> 04:10:00.479
Don't do anything stupid.

04:10:00.540 --> 04:10:04.020
Act exactly as you always have, and don't

04:10:04.020 --> 04:10:04.799
touch anything.

04:10:04.860 --> 04:10:08.280
In fact, don't say anything either.

04:10:08.340 --> 04:10:12.120
Just stand there and look menacing.

04:10:12.180 --> 04:10:13.799
I can do that.

04:10:13.860 --> 04:10:15.780
Pearl said cheerfully.

04:10:15.840 --> 04:10:18.000
I'll practice my menacing face right

04:10:18.000 --> 04:10:18.420
now.

04:10:18.479 --> 04:10:24.600
You sound like you're digesting an

04:10:24.600 --> 04:10:26.100
overweight grizzly bear.

04:10:26.219 --> 04:10:28.500
Scarlet commented acidly.

04:10:28.559 --> 04:10:32.639
I think it's perfect, said Chameleon.

04:10:32.700 --> 04:10:33.899
Thanks, Dad.

04:10:33.959 --> 04:10:35.340
Pearl said grinning.

04:10:35.399 --> 04:10:38.219
Dragonettes, Scarlett muttered.

04:10:38.280 --> 04:10:39.899
I never saw the appeal.

04:10:39.959 --> 04:10:43.200
The Sky Palace came into view ahead of

04:10:43.200 --> 04:10:43.500
them.

04:10:43.559 --> 04:10:46.500
Its towers and turrets and spires jutting

04:10:46.500 --> 04:10:47.879
through the clouds around the mountain

04:10:47.879 --> 04:10:50.340
peaks like long spindly claws.

04:10:50.399 --> 04:10:53.040
The fading sunlight seemed to catch for a

04:10:53.040 --> 04:10:55.319
moment in the queen's eyes, adding a

04:10:55.319 --> 04:10:57.780
glimmer of menace to her yellow gaze as

04:10:57.780 --> 04:10:58.739
she regarded the palace.

04:10:58.799 --> 04:11:02.040
That's why this never occurred to me

04:11:02.040 --> 04:11:03.659
before, she went on.

04:11:03.719 --> 04:11:05.340
But I should have remembered.

04:11:05.399 --> 04:11:07.680
It was only a couple of months before the

04:11:07.680 --> 04:11:08.700
whole catastrophe.

04:11:08.760 --> 04:11:11.819
Chameleon cleared his throat, and the

04:11:11.819 --> 04:11:13.920
queen glanced at him, trading some kind

04:11:13.920 --> 04:11:15.899
of significant unspoken message.

04:11:15.959 --> 04:11:18.239
Won't there be guards?

04:11:18.299 --> 04:11:20.879
Chameleon asked quickly, patrolling

04:11:20.879 --> 04:11:21.479
around the mountains.

04:11:21.540 --> 04:11:24.780
Not as many as there would be if Ruby

04:11:24.780 --> 04:11:27.899
were home, Queen Scarlet said, but she's

04:11:27.899 --> 04:11:30.180
still off hunting for me, and trying to

04:11:30.180 --> 04:11:31.620
identify missing heads.

04:11:31.680 --> 04:11:33.659
It's the perfect opportunity to take

04:11:33.659 --> 04:11:33.959
over.

04:11:34.020 --> 04:11:37.379
And get the leverage I need to keep it

04:11:37.379 --> 04:11:37.739
that way.

04:11:37.799 --> 04:11:41.459
Two Skywings suddenly emerged from the

04:11:41.459 --> 04:11:43.799
mist, flapping toward them with spears

04:11:43.799 --> 04:11:46.139
clutched in their talons and fearsome

04:11:46.139 --> 04:11:47.760
scowls etched on their snouts.

04:11:47.819 --> 04:11:50.520
Still, Chameleon said.

04:11:50.579 --> 04:11:54.840
Um, any guards seems like a problem

04:11:54.840 --> 04:11:55.079
right?

04:11:55.139 --> 04:11:57.180
Not for us.

04:11:57.239 --> 04:11:59.760
Queen Scarlet said, tossing her head

04:11:59.760 --> 04:12:00.899
triumphantly at peril.

04:12:00.959 --> 04:12:02.700
Let's go, darling.

04:12:02.760 --> 04:12:04.620
Darling.

04:12:04.739 --> 04:12:07.319
Peril thought with delight as she soared

04:12:07.319 --> 04:12:08.219
up behind the queen.

04:12:08.340 --> 04:12:09.659
That's me.

04:12:09.719 --> 04:12:10.799
She does love me.

04:12:10.860 --> 04:12:14.040
The 2 guards lifted their spears when

04:12:14.040 --> 04:12:16.559
they saw Queen Scarlet approaching, but a

04:12:16.559 --> 04:12:19.680
moment later, they saw peril, and she saw

04:12:19.680 --> 04:12:22.559
them recognize her, and she saw the fear

04:12:22.559 --> 04:12:23.520
that engulfed them.

04:12:23.639 --> 04:12:26.340
One dropped his spear and turned tail

04:12:26.340 --> 04:12:29.100
instantly, fleeing back to the palace as

04:12:29.100 --> 04:12:30.540
fast as his wings could carry him.

04:12:30.600 --> 04:12:33.239
The other hovered indecisively for a

04:12:33.239 --> 04:12:35.639
moment, shifting her weapon from talon to

04:12:35.639 --> 04:12:38.040
talon, and flicking her tail like a leaf

04:12:38.040 --> 04:12:39.360
about to be blown off a tree.

04:12:39.420 --> 04:12:42.479
Then she, too, broke down and fled.

04:12:42.540 --> 04:12:46.440
Peril watched them go, feeling hurt and

04:12:46.440 --> 04:12:49.620
lonely, and misunderstood exactly the way

04:12:49.620 --> 04:12:52.260
she always had, and trying to reach for

04:12:52.260 --> 04:12:54.239
that part of her that was too fierce and

04:12:54.239 --> 04:12:55.739
scary to care.

04:12:55.799 --> 04:12:58.139
But it's different now, she told

04:12:58.139 --> 04:12:58.620
herself.

04:12:58.680 --> 04:13:01.079
It'll all be different once they know

04:13:01.079 --> 04:13:01.799
that I'm normal.

04:13:01.920 --> 04:13:03.959
Maybe we'll even be friends.

04:13:04.020 --> 04:13:05.219
That would be cool.

04:13:05.280 --> 04:13:07.319
I've never had a real friend before.

04:13:07.379 --> 04:13:10.500
Something poked to the corners of her

04:13:10.500 --> 04:13:11.100
mind.

04:13:11.159 --> 04:13:14.879
Oh, that sea wing, turtle.

04:13:14.940 --> 04:13:17.819
I guess he was sort of a friend, apart

04:13:17.819 --> 04:13:18.659
from lying to me.

04:13:18.719 --> 04:13:21.420
She realized that she should tell Queen

04:13:21.420 --> 04:13:23.100
Scarlet that the sea wings had an

04:13:23.100 --> 04:13:23.520
animus.

04:13:23.579 --> 04:13:26.100
That was definitely the kind of thing the

04:13:26.100 --> 04:13:27.000
queen would want to know.

04:13:27.059 --> 04:13:29.700
Plus, it would be pretty impressive to be

04:13:29.700 --> 04:13:31.680
the dragon who got to tell her such an

04:13:31.680 --> 04:13:33.360
important and surprising secret.

04:13:33.420 --> 04:13:37.319
She twisted toward the queen, but Scarlet

04:13:37.319 --> 04:13:39.719
was already in a dive, aiming for an

04:13:39.719 --> 04:13:41.819
opening high in one of the towers.

04:13:41.879 --> 04:13:44.399
It was a room peril had never been to, as

04:13:44.399 --> 04:13:46.739
far as she could remember, and she flew

04:13:46.739 --> 04:13:48.959
after Scarlet, puzzling over what it

04:13:48.959 --> 04:13:49.500
could be.

04:13:49.559 --> 04:13:53.159
If she'd had a normal dragonette hood, she

04:13:53.159 --> 04:13:54.719
might have been able to guess from the

04:13:54.719 --> 04:13:56.940
murmur of little voices that came through

04:13:56.940 --> 04:13:57.420
the windows.

04:13:57.479 --> 04:14:00.420
Then again, if she'd had a normal

04:14:00.420 --> 04:14:02.579
dragonette hood, she'd have spent most of

04:14:02.579 --> 04:14:03.059
it right here.

04:14:03.120 --> 04:14:05.940
They swooped through the highest opening

04:14:05.940 --> 04:14:09.059
of the tower, straight into an enormous

04:14:09.059 --> 04:14:11.520
space full of Sky Wing Dragonettes.

04:14:11.579 --> 04:14:14.639
The wingery, peril realized.

04:14:14.700 --> 04:14:17.040
Of course, I'd never have been allowed in

04:14:17.040 --> 04:14:19.860
here, staying out of the way of clumsy

04:14:19.860 --> 04:14:21.959
floppy dragonettes was always the hardest

04:14:21.959 --> 04:14:24.059
thing about moving around the palace.

04:14:24.120 --> 04:14:27.299
In fact, the danger of running into peril

04:14:27.299 --> 04:14:29.520
was probably why most dragonettes were

04:14:29.520 --> 04:14:31.559
confined to the wingery until they had

04:14:31.559 --> 04:14:32.819
better control of their limbs.

04:14:32.879 --> 04:14:35.760
The youngest dragonettes were play

04:14:35.760 --> 04:14:37.979
fighting on the floor, far below peril

04:14:37.979 --> 04:14:40.440
near the base of the tower, where black

04:14:40.440 --> 04:14:41.879
and gold rugs overlapped.

04:14:41.940 --> 04:14:44.399
Toy weapons were scattered around them.

04:14:44.459 --> 04:14:48.000
Blunt spears and dented shields, leaning

04:14:48.000 --> 04:14:49.860
haphazardly against balls and attack

04:14:49.860 --> 04:14:52.139
dummies, and what appeared to be toy

04:14:52.139 --> 04:14:54.299
cooking supplies stacked with bits of

04:14:54.299 --> 04:14:56.520
half chewed goat bones and other snacks

04:14:56.520 --> 04:14:59.459
slightly older dragonettes swarmed the

04:14:59.459 --> 04:15:01.319
walls and climbing structures above the

04:15:01.319 --> 04:15:04.379
rugs, clambering busily along fake rocky

04:15:04.379 --> 04:15:06.719
outcroppings, and jumping to gradually

04:15:06.719 --> 04:15:08.219
higher and higher platforms.

04:15:08.280 --> 04:15:10.979
A few of them slipped and fell, but the

04:15:10.979 --> 04:15:12.540
padded rugs below caught them without

04:15:12.540 --> 04:15:12.899
injury.

04:15:13.020 --> 04:15:16.139
At the highest levels, closer to the

04:15:16.139 --> 04:15:18.420
ceiling was space for flying practice

04:15:18.420 --> 04:15:21.659
longer spaces to cross with each leap

04:15:21.659 --> 04:15:24.420
ropes to catch on mid-flight, obstacles

04:15:24.420 --> 04:15:25.860
to practice swerving around.

04:15:25.920 --> 04:15:28.620
Here the biggest dragonettes stretched

04:15:28.620 --> 04:15:31.379
their wings, red and orange, swerving

04:15:31.379 --> 04:15:33.840
around one another as they cat called and

04:15:33.840 --> 04:15:34.739
showed off new moves.

04:15:34.799 --> 04:15:37.559
They all seemed so happy.

04:15:37.620 --> 04:15:39.360
Not just happy.

04:15:39.420 --> 04:15:42.719
Unworried, like nothing could trouble

04:15:42.719 --> 04:15:45.360
them, like all they needed was a place to

04:15:45.360 --> 04:15:46.920
fly and friends to fly with.

04:15:46.979 --> 04:15:51.239
What would I be like if I'd grown up in

04:15:51.239 --> 04:15:51.899
this wingery?

04:15:51.959 --> 04:15:53.280
Peril wondered.

04:15:53.340 --> 04:15:55.020
Would I have friends?

04:15:55.079 --> 04:15:57.239
Would I giggle like that?

04:15:57.299 --> 04:16:00.479
The memory of turtle tugged at her again

04:16:00.479 --> 04:16:01.440
and she shook it off.

04:16:01.500 --> 04:16:03.899
She'd known him for what?

04:16:03.959 --> 04:16:04.500
4 days?

04:16:04.559 --> 04:16:06.719
That hardly counted as true friendship.

04:16:06.780 --> 04:16:08.819
He was probably glad she was gone.

04:16:08.879 --> 04:16:12.180
The walls in here were not as embellished

04:16:12.180 --> 04:16:13.979
with gold and jewels as the rest of the

04:16:13.979 --> 04:16:14.399
palace.

04:16:14.459 --> 04:16:17.280
Peril wondered if Queen Scarlet didn't

04:16:17.280 --> 04:16:18.959
trust dragonettes to keep their grubby

04:16:18.959 --> 04:16:20.040
claws off her treasure.

04:16:20.100 --> 04:16:23.340
Instead, the room was full of light and

04:16:23.340 --> 04:16:26.100
air from windows and skylights, most of

04:16:26.100 --> 04:16:27.899
which were barred, especially on the

04:16:27.899 --> 04:16:28.500
lower levels.

04:16:28.559 --> 04:16:31.139
So none of the crawlers or new flyers

04:16:31.139 --> 04:16:31.680
could fall out.

04:16:31.739 --> 04:16:34.979
The only decoration was a portrait of

04:16:34.979 --> 04:16:37.860
Scarlet, 5 times the size of the actual

04:16:37.860 --> 04:16:38.459
queen.

04:16:38.520 --> 04:16:42.059
It covered a huge swath of wall, forcing

04:16:42.059 --> 04:16:44.340
dragonettes to find ways to climb or flap

04:16:44.340 --> 04:16:44.700
around it.

04:16:44.760 --> 04:16:48.120
Queen Scarlet's perfect orange scales

04:16:48.120 --> 04:16:50.819
bright yellow eyes, and cascades of

04:16:50.819 --> 04:16:53.819
jewelry glowed over the whole wingery, as

04:16:53.819 --> 04:16:55.260
if she were approving of their play while

04:16:55.260 --> 04:16:57.780
also imprinting their young brains, with

04:16:57.780 --> 04:16:59.700
a constant reminder that she was the

04:16:59.700 --> 04:17:03.000
queen, and always would be, hinted her

04:17:03.000 --> 04:17:03.420
expression.

04:17:03.479 --> 04:17:07.020
In fact, it was surprising that Ruby

04:17:07.020 --> 04:17:08.100
hadn't taken that down yet.

04:17:08.159 --> 04:17:09.780
Peril reflected.

04:17:09.840 --> 04:17:12.180
Perhaps the interior design of her palace

04:17:12.180 --> 04:17:13.979
wasn't quite as high a priority for her

04:17:13.979 --> 04:17:15.479
as it had been for her mother.

04:17:15.540 --> 04:17:19.739
Look how beautiful Scarlet was, Parel

04:17:19.739 --> 04:17:20.159
thought.

04:17:20.219 --> 04:17:23.100
She glanced at the disfiguring scar glory

04:17:23.100 --> 04:17:25.319
had left on the queen's face and gave a

04:17:25.319 --> 04:17:26.219
little shudder of pity.

04:17:26.280 --> 04:17:30.059
Glory, how did she get to the queen?

04:17:30.120 --> 04:17:32.760
What was I doing when that happened?

04:17:32.819 --> 04:17:34.799
How did I fail her?

04:17:34.860 --> 04:17:38.459
Queen Scarlet swooped to a perch at the

04:17:38.459 --> 04:17:40.739
peak of the tower on a winding branch

04:17:40.739 --> 04:17:41.639
carved from wood.

04:17:41.700 --> 04:17:44.399
It twisted across the roof as though it

04:17:44.399 --> 04:17:45.899
was the finish line for all the

04:17:45.899 --> 04:17:48.180
dragonettes, trying to reach the top of

04:17:48.180 --> 04:17:48.479
the room.

04:17:48.540 --> 04:17:51.479
Peril wanted to sit on it herself.

04:17:51.540 --> 04:17:54.420
Her wings were starting to get tired, but

04:17:54.420 --> 04:17:55.559
she remembered that she was still

04:17:55.559 --> 04:17:57.600
supposed to be all fire scales.

04:17:57.659 --> 04:18:00.420
So instead, she made herself hover just

04:18:00.420 --> 04:18:01.079
below the queen.

04:18:01.139 --> 04:18:03.780
A hush fell over the wingery.

04:18:03.899 --> 04:18:07.440
Very slowly, as several dragonettes were

04:18:07.440 --> 04:18:09.299
too busy playing to notice either the

04:18:09.299 --> 04:18:11.819
growing quiet, or the giant dragon

04:18:11.819 --> 04:18:14.879
glowering from above, the Queen Scarlet

04:18:14.879 --> 04:18:17.459
waited, smoke hissing from her snout and

04:18:17.459 --> 04:18:18.120
ears.

04:18:18.120 --> 04:18:21.239
As they noticed her, many of the

04:18:21.239 --> 04:18:23.219
dragonettes let out squeals of fear.

04:18:23.280 --> 04:18:25.799
A few of them near the floor dove under

04:18:25.799 --> 04:18:27.840
whatever they could reach, hiding their

04:18:27.840 --> 04:18:30.840
faces behind shields, or rugs, or goat

04:18:30.840 --> 04:18:33.180
spattered saucepots, although their

04:18:33.180 --> 04:18:34.979
trembling tails were still stuck out in

04:18:34.979 --> 04:18:35.340
the open.

04:18:35.399 --> 04:18:38.159
A few of the others began to whisper.

04:18:38.280 --> 04:18:40.920
Is that the dragon in the picture?

04:18:40.979 --> 04:18:44.520
That's not the old missing queen, is it?

04:18:44.579 --> 04:18:46.860
What's wrong with her face?

04:18:46.979 --> 04:18:49.979
She don't look like her picture.

04:18:50.100 --> 04:18:53.040
How'd she get all meltedish?

04:18:53.100 --> 04:18:55.440
That's really gross.

04:18:55.500 --> 04:18:58.319
Grows like cardinal drooling when he

04:18:58.319 --> 04:18:58.799
sleeps.

04:18:58.860 --> 04:18:59.760
Shut up.

04:18:59.819 --> 04:19:01.860
Way grosser than that.

04:19:01.920 --> 04:19:05.639
I wish my face was all melty and scary.

04:19:05.700 --> 04:19:08.459
Ew, you do not.

04:19:08.520 --> 04:19:10.500
We would so never play with you if it

04:19:10.500 --> 04:19:10.680
was.

04:19:10.739 --> 04:19:14.399
But you'd be scared of me, and then I

04:19:14.399 --> 04:19:16.559
could creep up on anyone in the dark and

04:19:16.559 --> 04:19:18.180
give them nightmares forever.

04:19:18.239 --> 04:19:20.100
It would be awesome.

04:19:20.159 --> 04:19:21.719
Yak.

04:19:21.780 --> 04:19:24.000
I bet she can't even look in mirrors

04:19:24.000 --> 04:19:24.299
anymore.

04:19:24.360 --> 04:19:27.719
My mom said she used to be wicked scary.

04:19:27.840 --> 04:19:31.920
And kind of mean, not like Queen Ruby.

04:19:31.979 --> 04:19:35.280
She looked kind of meanish now, I

04:19:35.280 --> 04:19:35.639
thinking.

04:19:35.700 --> 04:19:38.399
Should we be more scared?

04:19:38.459 --> 04:19:41.879
Gradually, the Whispers too fell silent

04:19:41.879 --> 04:19:43.979
under Queen Scarlet's withering glare.

04:19:44.040 --> 04:19:46.979
Hello, dragonettes.

04:19:47.100 --> 04:19:48.899
She finally hissed.

04:19:48.959 --> 04:19:53.700
I am your queen, Queen Scarlet of the Sky

04:19:53.700 --> 04:19:54.299
Wings.

04:19:54.360 --> 04:19:58.139
I have returned to take my throne, but I

04:19:58.139 --> 04:19:58.860
need something from you.

04:19:58.920 --> 04:20:02.159
Someone, actually.

04:20:02.219 --> 04:20:03.899
Excuse me?

04:20:03.959 --> 04:20:05.760
A little voice piped up.

04:20:05.879 --> 04:20:07.979
I'm thinking maybe you in the wrong

04:20:07.979 --> 04:20:09.659
palace, maybe?

04:20:09.719 --> 04:20:10.920
We already has a queen.

04:20:10.979 --> 04:20:13.500
Queen Ruby, she's super nice.

04:20:13.559 --> 04:20:15.719
Ruby is not your queen.

04:20:15.780 --> 04:20:17.520
Scarlet snarled.

04:20:17.579 --> 04:20:19.079
She is an imposter.

04:20:19.139 --> 04:20:21.840
I am your queen.

04:20:21.899 --> 04:20:24.120
What's a...

04:20:24.120 --> 04:20:27.420
Nymposser, asked another voice.

04:20:27.540 --> 04:20:31.139
It's furry and sleeps upside down and has

04:20:31.139 --> 04:20:33.719
a really chewy tail, said another.

04:20:33.780 --> 04:20:37.020
Melty face, ma'am, use wrong.

04:20:37.079 --> 04:20:38.940
Ruby's not furry at all.

04:20:39.000 --> 04:20:42.659
And I bet her tail's not chewy either, but

04:20:42.659 --> 04:20:43.379
I hasn't checked.

04:20:43.500 --> 04:20:48.059
She's a very nice queen offered yet

04:20:48.059 --> 04:20:50.639
another dragonette, and she visits all

04:20:50.639 --> 04:20:53.940
the time, and knows all our names, and

04:20:53.940 --> 04:20:56.399
says sorry when she bumps into someone

04:20:56.399 --> 04:20:59.879
and brings us snacks, and we like her

04:20:59.879 --> 04:21:00.180
lots.

04:21:00.239 --> 04:21:03.479
Maybe you could be queen of someone

04:21:03.479 --> 04:21:03.840
else.

04:21:03.899 --> 04:21:06.719
A small orange dragonette suggested.

04:21:06.780 --> 04:21:09.899
Because we already got to good one, but I

04:21:09.899 --> 04:21:11.700
hear that there are some night wings

04:21:11.700 --> 04:21:14.159
maybe looking for a new queen, and maybe

04:21:14.159 --> 04:21:15.899
because they spooky too.

04:21:15.959 --> 04:21:18.120
Maybe they like your spooky face.

04:21:18.180 --> 04:21:21.659
Ooh, yes, a few others agreed.

04:21:21.719 --> 04:21:24.959
She'd be super good, spooky.

04:21:25.020 --> 04:21:27.360
They could change their name to spooky

04:21:27.360 --> 04:21:30.299
wings, our nightmare faces.

04:21:30.360 --> 04:21:32.340
Stop talking this instant.

04:21:32.399 --> 04:21:34.559
Queen Scarlet bellowed.

04:21:34.620 --> 04:21:37.440
Peril was finding it close to impossible

04:21:37.440 --> 04:21:38.399
to keep a straight face.

04:21:38.459 --> 04:21:40.920
She wished there had been a chorus of

04:21:40.920 --> 04:21:43.079
impertinent dragonets around for every

04:21:43.079 --> 04:21:45.360
conversation she'd ever had with the

04:21:45.360 --> 04:21:45.780
queen.

04:21:45.840 --> 04:21:47.639
Perched on the windowsill.

04:21:47.760 --> 04:21:50.219
Chameleon wasn't even trying to hide how

04:21:50.219 --> 04:21:51.540
his shoulders were shaking with

04:21:51.540 --> 04:21:51.840
laughter.

04:21:51.899 --> 04:21:54.000
Sheesh!

04:21:54.059 --> 04:21:56.159
One of the little voices muttered as they

04:21:56.159 --> 04:21:57.180
subsided.

04:21:57.239 --> 04:22:00.299
Just making some helpful suggestibles.

04:22:00.360 --> 04:22:02.700
No need to be crank monstery.

04:22:02.819 --> 04:22:07.680
I am looking, Queen Scarlet said, cold

04:22:07.680 --> 04:22:09.780
and clear. with iron in her voice.

04:22:09.840 --> 04:22:13.379
For a dragonette named Cliff.

04:22:13.440 --> 04:22:16.799
Now everyone really was silent.

04:22:16.860 --> 04:22:19.559
The Skywing Dragonettes glanced around

04:22:19.559 --> 04:22:22.319
and easily, and then gradually one head

04:22:22.319 --> 04:22:24.659
after another turned toward a small, dark

04:22:24.659 --> 04:22:28.020
red dragon with a long neck, who was

04:22:28.020 --> 04:22:29.399
clinging to a platform near the ground.

04:22:29.459 --> 04:22:32.100
He looked no more than 8 or 9 months

04:22:32.100 --> 04:22:32.340
old.

04:22:32.459 --> 04:22:36.059
He stared up at Queen Scarlet in peril

04:22:36.059 --> 04:22:37.920
his tiny claws trembling.

04:22:37.979 --> 04:22:41.040
Suddenly, peril didn't feel like laughing

04:22:41.040 --> 04:22:41.280
anymore.

04:22:41.399 --> 04:22:44.579
A grim smile spread across Queen

04:22:44.579 --> 04:22:45.780
Scarlet's face.

04:22:45.840 --> 04:22:49.319
Hello, little prince, she said.

04:22:49.379 --> 04:22:51.780
I thought it was time for you to meet

04:22:51.780 --> 04:22:52.680
your grandmother.

04:22:52.739 --> 04:22:57.239
Chapter 13.

04:22:57.420 --> 04:23:01.200
Prince Cliff was by far the teeniest

04:23:01.200 --> 04:23:03.000
dragon peril had ever been this close

04:23:03.000 --> 04:23:03.299
to.

04:23:03.360 --> 04:23:06.120
If she hadn't known that her scales were

04:23:06.120 --> 04:23:08.399
safe to touch, she would never have dared

04:23:08.399 --> 04:23:11.100
to stand so close, no matter what Queen

04:23:11.100 --> 04:23:12.239
Scarlet's orders were.

04:23:12.299 --> 04:23:14.760
She tried to wink at him in a friendly

04:23:14.760 --> 04:23:16.739
way, but she must have done it wrong.

04:23:16.799 --> 04:23:19.200
Friendly wings weren't exactly something

04:23:19.200 --> 04:23:21.180
she'd ever had a chance to practice.

04:23:21.299 --> 04:23:23.340
Since it just made him throw his wings

04:23:23.340 --> 04:23:25.799
over his head and curl into a shivering

04:23:25.799 --> 04:23:25.979
ball.

04:23:26.100 --> 04:23:28.379
She didn't love that.

04:23:28.440 --> 04:23:30.239
She wanted to hug him.

04:23:30.299 --> 04:23:33.059
She could hug dragons now, and tell him

04:23:33.059 --> 04:23:35.040
not to be scared, that she wasn't scary

04:23:35.040 --> 04:23:38.159
at all, not anymore, but she had her

04:23:38.159 --> 04:23:40.260
orders, and she couldn't ruin Queen

04:23:40.260 --> 04:23:42.420
Scarlet's plan, not when it was working

04:23:42.420 --> 04:23:43.020
so well.

04:23:43.079 --> 04:23:46.020
They'd marched the dragonette out of the

04:23:46.020 --> 04:23:48.120
wingery, and down the long winding

04:23:48.120 --> 04:23:50.100
tunnels with sky wings scattering and

04:23:50.100 --> 04:23:53.040
panic before them. 3 guards had tried to

04:23:53.040 --> 04:23:55.739
resist, standing firm at the entrance to

04:23:55.739 --> 04:23:58.260
the throne room, but when Parel stepped

04:23:58.260 --> 04:24:00.299
toward them with her talons outstretched

04:24:00.299 --> 04:24:03.360
one outright fainted with terror, and the

04:24:03.360 --> 04:24:05.159
other 2 were distracted long enough for

04:24:05.159 --> 04:24:07.739
Scarlet to leap forward and kill them.

04:24:07.799 --> 04:24:10.739
Much better, Scarlett said with

04:24:10.739 --> 04:24:13.079
satisfaction, shoving the bodies to the

04:24:13.079 --> 04:24:15.420
side at the door, and then setting all 3

04:24:15.420 --> 04:24:16.139
guards on fire.

04:24:16.200 --> 04:24:19.020
The one who was only unconscious woke up

04:24:19.020 --> 04:24:21.180
screaming, but the screams didn't last

04:24:21.180 --> 04:24:21.600
very long.

04:24:21.659 --> 04:24:24.959
Chameleon herded Cliff into the throne

04:24:24.959 --> 04:24:26.940
room, and plunked him on the lower

04:24:26.940 --> 04:24:29.280
visitor's throne, which Byrne had often

04:24:29.280 --> 04:24:31.200
used during alliance meetings.

04:24:31.260 --> 04:24:34.440
Queen Scarlet swarmed onto her own throne

04:24:34.440 --> 04:24:36.600
the tall column carved in the shape of

04:24:36.600 --> 04:24:39.120
clouds that sat in the center of nearly

04:24:39.120 --> 04:24:40.620
all perils memories of her.

04:24:40.680 --> 04:24:43.079
Queen Scarlet issuing orders.

04:24:43.139 --> 04:24:45.719
Queen Scarlet, scolding peril for

04:24:45.719 --> 04:24:48.479
whatever new thing she'd done wrong, Queen

04:24:48.479 --> 04:24:51.000
Scarlet, choosing who would die under

04:24:51.000 --> 04:24:52.379
peril's talons today.

04:24:52.440 --> 04:24:55.379
The queen poked at her throne for a few

04:24:55.379 --> 04:24:57.899
minutes, sniffing with disgust as though

04:24:57.899 --> 04:25:00.479
she could smell traces of ruby on it, and

04:25:00.479 --> 04:25:02.819
then she settled herself majestically and

04:25:02.819 --> 04:25:04.620
stared out the open wall opposite her.

04:25:04.680 --> 04:25:07.920
From up there, peril knew, the queen

04:25:07.920 --> 04:25:09.360
could see a sweeping view of her

04:25:09.360 --> 04:25:09.659
kingdom.

04:25:09.719 --> 04:25:12.000
The claws of the clouds mountains

04:25:12.000 --> 04:25:14.579
scratching the sky all the way to the far

04:25:14.579 --> 04:25:15.239
horizon.

04:25:15.299 --> 04:25:18.959
Stand next to the prince, Scarlett

04:25:18.959 --> 04:25:19.860
ordered peril.

04:25:19.920 --> 04:25:22.020
Close enough to grab him if anyone comes

04:25:22.020 --> 04:25:22.260
in.

04:25:22.319 --> 04:25:25.200
Cliff whimpered. and tried to make

04:25:25.200 --> 04:25:25.920
himself smaller.

04:25:26.040 --> 04:25:30.360
I remember when you hatched, Queen

04:25:30.360 --> 04:25:31.860
Scarlet said to the little red

04:25:31.860 --> 04:25:32.760
dragonette.

04:25:32.819 --> 04:25:35.520
It was like someone had woken up Ruby for

04:25:35.520 --> 04:25:36.360
the 1st time in years.

04:25:36.420 --> 04:25:39.360
I'm afraid your mother has always been

04:25:39.360 --> 04:25:40.559
very, very boring.

04:25:40.680 --> 04:25:44.340
No spark in her at all, which, of course

04:25:44.340 --> 04:25:45.840
is why I allowed her to live.

04:25:45.899 --> 04:25:49.020
But when she saw you for the 1st time

04:25:49.020 --> 04:25:52.020
suddenly, there were sparks.

04:25:52.079 --> 04:25:55.020
You'd think your scales were plated with

04:25:55.020 --> 04:25:57.000
gold, and you'd crawled out with

04:25:57.000 --> 04:25:59.159
sapphires wrapped around your tail.

04:25:59.219 --> 04:26:01.739
I can understand a dragon getting excited

04:26:01.739 --> 04:26:05.100
about treasure, but that excited about an

04:26:05.100 --> 04:26:06.959
ordinary dragonette.

04:26:07.020 --> 04:26:08.280
It was very weird.

04:26:08.340 --> 04:26:11.639
You are merely ordinary, aren't you

04:26:11.639 --> 04:26:12.360
little grandson?

04:26:12.479 --> 04:26:13.739
I can tell.

04:26:13.860 --> 04:26:18.299
No, Cliff said suddenly, sitting up and

04:26:18.299 --> 04:26:19.200
puffing out his chest.

04:26:19.260 --> 04:26:21.299
I is not.

04:26:21.360 --> 04:26:24.479
Scuffling and stamping sounds came from

04:26:24.479 --> 04:26:26.940
the hall outside the throne room, as if a

04:26:26.940 --> 04:26:28.500
couple of dragons were trying to put out

04:26:28.500 --> 04:26:29.819
the last of the fire.

04:26:29.879 --> 04:26:32.819
The queen watched with narrow eyes, as a

04:26:32.819 --> 04:26:35.280
dragon with bright red scales edged

04:26:35.280 --> 04:26:37.739
inside and threw himself into a deep bow

04:26:37.739 --> 04:26:38.159
before her.

04:26:38.219 --> 04:26:42.719
Mother, he said, with a little too much

04:26:42.719 --> 04:26:43.620
enthusiasm.

04:26:43.680 --> 04:26:46.500
She kept her gaze fixed on him, smoke

04:26:46.500 --> 04:26:47.879
rising from her nostrils.

04:26:47.940 --> 04:26:51.000
Your majesty, he added quickly.

04:26:51.059 --> 04:26:52.319
You're alive.

04:26:52.379 --> 04:26:53.760
You've returned.

04:26:53.819 --> 04:26:57.959
What a, uh, what a glorious day for the

04:26:57.959 --> 04:26:58.739
Sky Kingdom.

04:26:58.799 --> 04:27:03.600
We are all so, so, so, uh, blessed and

04:27:03.600 --> 04:27:04.139
lucky.

04:27:04.200 --> 04:27:05.340
And relieved.

04:27:05.399 --> 04:27:07.920
Yes, this is thrilling.

04:27:07.920 --> 04:27:08.940
It really is.

04:27:09.000 --> 04:27:11.639
Vermillion.

04:27:11.700 --> 04:27:15.540
Said the queen, and peril shivered.

04:27:15.600 --> 04:27:18.360
The weight of the fury in that one word.

04:27:18.420 --> 04:27:21.180
Peril hoped she'd never have to hear

04:27:21.180 --> 04:27:24.059
Scarlet say, peril, like that.

04:27:24.120 --> 04:27:26.459
She might as well have called her son

04:27:26.459 --> 04:27:27.840
disappointment.

04:27:27.899 --> 04:27:30.299
Uh, great day.

04:27:30.360 --> 04:27:33.059
He said, his voice hiccuping over the

04:27:33.059 --> 04:27:33.299
words.

04:27:33.360 --> 04:27:36.719
He threw a confused look at peril, as if

04:27:36.719 --> 04:27:38.760
he didn't expect to see her there, which

04:27:38.760 --> 04:27:40.979
was odd because where else would she be?

04:27:41.040 --> 04:27:43.200
So...

04:27:43.200 --> 04:27:44.639
Great.

04:27:44.700 --> 04:27:49.319
Tell me, Vermilion, the queen growled.

04:27:49.379 --> 04:27:52.799
Why exactly did you allow your sister to

04:27:52.799 --> 04:27:54.540
steal my throne?

04:27:54.600 --> 04:27:58.500
Steel, she, he stammered.

04:27:58.559 --> 04:28:00.600
I didn't, we thought.

04:28:00.659 --> 04:28:03.659
Did you really think I was dead?

04:28:03.719 --> 04:28:07.079
Queen Scarlet sat up and spread her wings

04:28:07.079 --> 04:28:09.239
so she loomed over the whole space.

04:28:09.239 --> 04:28:10.500
Me?

04:28:10.559 --> 04:28:12.780
Yeah, yeah.

04:28:12.840 --> 04:28:14.280
Yes?

04:28:14.340 --> 04:28:15.719
He tried.

04:28:15.780 --> 04:28:18.059
His expression clearly indicating that he

04:28:18.059 --> 04:28:19.860
wasn't sure which answer would get him

04:28:19.860 --> 04:28:20.639
killed faster.

04:28:20.700 --> 04:28:23.100
Really, she said.

04:28:23.219 --> 04:28:26.520
Oh, never mind dreams, is that it?

04:28:26.639 --> 04:28:30.180
Every night, for months, I came to you.

04:28:30.239 --> 04:28:32.700
I told you where I was.

04:28:32.760 --> 04:28:34.559
I told you to send an army for me.

04:28:34.680 --> 04:28:38.700
Then, after I escaped from Bern, I told

04:28:38.700 --> 04:28:39.420
you to meet me.

04:28:39.479 --> 04:28:41.940
I told you to form a plan to get my

04:28:41.940 --> 04:28:42.719
throne back.

04:28:42.780 --> 04:28:44.700
I told you to kill your sister.

04:28:44.760 --> 04:28:49.920
Did you do even one of those things?

04:28:50.040 --> 04:28:51.659
Vermilion?

04:28:51.719 --> 04:28:53.399
Yikes.

04:28:53.520 --> 04:28:54.479
Parold thought.

04:28:54.540 --> 04:28:57.239
She remembered the nightly visits from

04:28:57.239 --> 04:29:00.360
Scarlet, full of guilt and rage and

04:29:00.360 --> 04:29:01.260
expectations.

04:29:01.319 --> 04:29:03.600
It hadn't occurred to her that Queen

04:29:03.600 --> 04:29:05.819
Scarlet might be using the dream visitor

04:29:05.819 --> 04:29:08.100
to stalk other dragons besides her.

04:29:08.159 --> 04:29:10.079
Poor vermilion.

04:29:10.139 --> 04:29:15.000
But I didn't know it was real. he

04:29:15.000 --> 04:29:18.780
protested weakly, could have been my, um

04:29:18.780 --> 04:29:19.920
subconscious.

04:29:19.979 --> 04:29:22.739
You mean your guilty conscience.

04:29:22.799 --> 04:29:26.280
Queen Scarlet snapped, except I told you

04:29:26.280 --> 04:29:27.540
about the dream visitor.

04:29:27.600 --> 04:29:30.299
I followed you through every normal dream

04:29:30.299 --> 04:29:30.780
you had.

04:29:30.840 --> 04:29:33.719
Every night you promised to do as I

04:29:33.719 --> 04:29:34.319
commanded.

04:29:34.379 --> 04:29:37.260
And then I woke up.

04:29:37.379 --> 04:29:41.100
He said miserably, and it seemed crazy to

04:29:41.100 --> 04:29:42.360
obey a dream.

04:29:42.420 --> 04:29:45.840
Or a queen who wasn't right in front of

04:29:45.840 --> 04:29:48.899
you, Scarlet guessed, because it was

04:29:48.899 --> 04:29:51.780
easier to be a coward, and obey my little

04:29:51.780 --> 04:29:54.299
mouse daughter, and hope I never came

04:29:54.299 --> 04:29:56.940
back, rather than to be loyal to your

04:29:56.940 --> 04:29:57.659
true queen.

04:29:57.719 --> 04:29:59.879
I'm sorry.

04:29:59.940 --> 04:30:03.180
Vermilion dropped his head, and his wings

04:30:03.180 --> 04:30:04.200
drooped to the floor.

04:30:04.260 --> 04:30:06.840
I know you're going to kill me.

04:30:06.899 --> 04:30:09.479
Or would you rather have me kill myself?

04:30:09.540 --> 04:30:12.659
Not just yet?

04:30:12.780 --> 04:30:15.299
Scarlet said, flicking her tail.

04:30:15.360 --> 04:30:18.899
I want to know what Ruby has ruined in my

04:30:18.899 --> 04:30:19.440
absence.

04:30:19.500 --> 04:30:21.659
It looks like she's been prying my

04:30:21.659 --> 04:30:24.059
treasure right out of the walls in here.

04:30:24.120 --> 04:30:27.659
Pearl glanced around and realized the

04:30:27.659 --> 04:30:28.200
queen was right.

04:30:28.260 --> 04:30:30.959
The throne room used to have so much gold

04:30:30.959 --> 04:30:33.600
inlaid in the walls that stepping inside

04:30:33.600 --> 04:30:35.700
on a bright day would give you an instant

04:30:35.700 --> 04:30:36.120
headache.

04:30:36.180 --> 04:30:39.420
At least half of that gold was gone now

04:30:39.420 --> 04:30:41.760
maybe only wisps of cloud shapes here and

04:30:41.760 --> 04:30:41.940
there.

04:30:42.059 --> 04:30:45.059
Um, said Vermilion.

04:30:45.120 --> 04:30:47.459
Yes, about that.

04:30:47.520 --> 04:30:51.360
Or was it other dragons stealing from me

04:30:51.360 --> 04:30:52.860
Queen Scarlet guest.

04:30:52.920 --> 04:30:55.200
As soon as they thought I was gone, and

04:30:55.200 --> 04:30:57.780
they knew a weakling was in power, did

04:30:57.780 --> 04:30:59.579
they immediately start stripping the

04:30:59.579 --> 04:31:00.420
bones of the palace?

04:31:00.540 --> 04:31:03.840
No, no, Vermilion said.

04:31:03.899 --> 04:31:05.159
No one did that.

04:31:05.219 --> 04:31:06.600
It was Ruby.

04:31:06.719 --> 04:31:09.059
She took the gold and used it to...

04:31:09.059 --> 04:31:12.780
Uh, she spit it out.

04:31:12.840 --> 04:31:14.340
The queen hissed.

04:31:14.399 --> 04:31:17.700
She turned your arena into a hospital.

04:31:17.760 --> 04:31:18.659
He blurted.

04:31:18.719 --> 04:31:21.180
She pardoned all the prisoners and

04:31:21.180 --> 04:31:23.159
brought in doctors and healers from other

04:31:23.159 --> 04:31:25.739
tribes to teach ours everything they know

04:31:25.739 --> 04:31:28.319
and she made space for all the wounded

04:31:28.319 --> 04:31:30.719
soldiers from the war, and she's been

04:31:30.719 --> 04:31:33.239
finding them all places to live and jobs

04:31:33.239 --> 04:31:35.040
to do, and using the gold for all of

04:31:35.040 --> 04:31:35.219
that.

04:31:35.340 --> 04:31:38.280
A long silence followed.

04:31:38.340 --> 04:31:41.760
Queen Scarlet flicked her tongue out and

04:31:41.760 --> 04:31:44.459
in, regarding vermilion with slitted

04:31:44.459 --> 04:31:45.120
yellow eyes.

04:31:45.180 --> 04:31:47.340
You like her.

04:31:47.399 --> 04:31:49.260
She said suddenly.

04:31:49.319 --> 04:31:52.379
You think Ruby is a good queen.

04:31:52.440 --> 04:31:56.219
No, he protested, flapping his wings with

04:31:56.219 --> 04:31:56.579
alarm.

04:31:56.639 --> 04:31:57.840
Never.

04:31:57.899 --> 04:31:59.579
You're the only good queen.

04:31:59.639 --> 04:32:01.319
I liked my arena job.

04:32:01.379 --> 04:32:03.899
It's absolutely terrible here now.

04:32:03.959 --> 04:32:07.020
We always loved all the, uh, the

04:32:07.020 --> 04:32:07.739
fighting.

04:32:07.799 --> 04:32:09.780
We missed you so much.

04:32:09.899 --> 04:32:13.319
Hmm, said the queen.

04:32:13.379 --> 04:32:16.739
Well, luckily your opinion counts for

04:32:16.739 --> 04:32:17.100
nothing.

04:32:17.159 --> 04:32:19.139
The throne is mine again now.

04:32:19.200 --> 04:32:22.500
And Ruby can either accept that, or fight

04:32:22.500 --> 04:32:23.340
me and die.

04:32:23.459 --> 04:32:26.700
She cast a sideways glance at Prince

04:32:26.700 --> 04:32:29.399
Cliff, and a serpentine grin slipped

04:32:29.399 --> 04:32:29.940
across her face.

04:32:30.000 --> 04:32:34.139
When is my hapless daughter scheduled to

04:32:34.139 --> 04:32:34.620
return?

04:32:34.620 --> 04:32:35.399
she asked.

04:32:35.459 --> 04:32:38.879
Tomorrow morning, said Vermilion.

04:32:38.940 --> 04:32:40.680
She sent an advanced messenger.

04:32:40.799 --> 04:32:42.780
Excellent.

04:32:42.840 --> 04:32:45.840
Queen Scarlet tapped her claws on the

04:32:45.840 --> 04:32:46.620
edge of the throne.

04:32:46.680 --> 04:32:50.159
I think I'll wait for her right here.

04:32:50.219 --> 04:32:51.840
Vermilion.

04:32:51.899 --> 04:32:54.719
Make an effort to be useful and send up

04:32:54.719 --> 04:32:55.559
food from the kitchens.

04:32:55.680 --> 04:32:58.799
She hesitated, then added with a growl.

04:32:58.920 --> 04:33:01.500
Perhaps it's worth noting to anyone

04:33:01.500 --> 04:33:04.680
involved that Prince Cliff will be

04:33:04.680 --> 04:33:06.479
tasting everything before I eat it.

04:33:06.540 --> 04:33:09.900
Oh, peril thought.

04:33:09.959 --> 04:33:12.299
She's afraid of being poisoned?

04:33:12.360 --> 04:33:14.159
She never was before.

04:33:14.220 --> 04:33:17.939
Vermilion bowed again, and stumbled out

04:33:17.939 --> 04:33:19.380
the door in his haste to be gone.

04:33:19.439 --> 04:33:23.159
The night wore on with a procession of

04:33:23.159 --> 04:33:25.259
sky wings, skittering through the throne

04:33:25.259 --> 04:33:27.419
room, bowing and scraping, and

04:33:27.419 --> 04:33:29.999
apologizing, and extolling the wonders of

04:33:29.999 --> 04:33:30.899
Scarlet's return.

04:33:31.020 --> 04:33:33.840
But peril couldn't help thinking, there

04:33:33.840 --> 04:33:34.560
should be more of them.

04:33:34.680 --> 04:33:37.259
The halls were quieter than she

04:33:37.259 --> 04:33:39.360
remembered them being, and there was a

04:33:39.360 --> 04:33:41.880
general hush over the palace, as if half

04:33:41.880 --> 04:33:44.220
the dragons were in hiding, waiting for

04:33:44.220 --> 04:33:47.159
something to change, waiting for Ruby to

04:33:47.159 --> 04:33:49.740
return presumably, waiting to see what

04:33:49.740 --> 04:33:51.599
would happen, and who would win?

04:33:51.659 --> 04:33:54.299
The ones who came in were betting on

04:33:54.299 --> 04:33:54.779
Scarlet.

04:33:54.900 --> 04:33:57.180
Hoping that by throwing themselves at her

04:33:57.180 --> 04:34:00.060
feet right away, they'd be safe, and

04:34:00.060 --> 04:34:02.040
perhaps even elevated in her renewed

04:34:02.040 --> 04:34:02.759
regime.

04:34:02.759 --> 04:34:05.459
Peril could see Queen Scarlet assessing

04:34:05.459 --> 04:34:05.819
them each.

04:34:05.880 --> 04:34:08.400
Filing their faces away in her memory.

04:34:08.520 --> 04:34:11.639
Five of the biggest dragons were assigned

04:34:11.639 --> 04:34:14.159
to stand guard, filling the throne room

04:34:14.159 --> 04:34:15.720
the way it had always been filled.

04:34:15.779 --> 04:34:17.219
And yet.

04:34:17.340 --> 04:34:20.520
Peril was sure she wasn't the only one in

04:34:20.520 --> 04:34:23.700
here, wondering how deep each Sky Wing's

04:34:23.700 --> 04:34:24.599
loyalty really went.

04:34:24.659 --> 04:34:28.319
At least she has me, she thought.

04:34:28.380 --> 04:34:30.840
She stretched out her talons to look at

04:34:30.840 --> 04:34:32.340
them, feeling pleased.

04:34:32.400 --> 04:34:34.680
It'll be worth it eventually.

04:34:34.740 --> 04:34:37.560
All these looks of hatred I keep getting

04:34:37.560 --> 04:34:40.200
because soon they'll know this new me.

04:34:40.259 --> 04:34:43.379
Soon, Queen Scarlet will be back in power

04:34:43.379 --> 04:34:46.079
safe and sound, and I can start changing

04:34:46.079 --> 04:34:47.279
everyone's minds about me.

04:34:47.400 --> 04:34:51.060
Still, there was something unsettling

04:34:51.060 --> 04:34:53.400
about the looks, as though her scales

04:34:53.400 --> 04:34:54.959
were thinner now that they weren't fire

04:34:54.959 --> 04:34:55.560
scales.

04:34:55.619 --> 04:34:58.079
Or maybe the looks were different.

04:34:58.139 --> 04:35:00.540
There was something about them that said

04:35:00.540 --> 04:35:05.520
betrayal, and backstabber, where before

04:35:05.520 --> 04:35:07.500
it had just been normal fear.

04:35:07.560 --> 04:35:09.060
Strange.

04:35:09.180 --> 04:35:11.040
Maybe she was imagining things.

04:35:11.159 --> 04:35:15.959
Long after midnight, Queen Scarlet curled

04:35:15.959 --> 04:35:17.400
her tail in and fell asleep on her

04:35:17.400 --> 04:35:17.819
throne.

04:35:17.880 --> 04:35:20.580
Perel's father too, was already asleep.

04:35:20.639 --> 04:35:23.340
His big orange wings flopped out on the

04:35:23.340 --> 04:35:25.319
floor on the far side of the throne from

04:35:25.319 --> 04:35:26.159
peril and cliff.

04:35:26.279 --> 04:35:28.799
The little prince was not asleep though.

04:35:28.919 --> 04:35:31.499
He was tracing his claws along the

04:35:31.499 --> 04:35:33.599
grooves in the rock below him, singing

04:35:33.599 --> 04:35:35.099
softly to himself.

04:35:35.159 --> 04:35:38.099
At one point he sat up, looked up at the

04:35:38.099 --> 04:35:39.900
sleeping queen, and then glanced

04:35:39.900 --> 04:35:40.740
hopefully at peril.

04:35:40.799 --> 04:35:45.180
Sorry, she said, hoping her voice sounded

04:35:45.180 --> 04:35:47.880
kind, although to her ears it mostly

04:35:47.880 --> 04:35:48.659
sounded drippy.

04:35:48.779 --> 04:35:51.899
I'm under orders to stay awake all night

04:35:51.899 --> 04:35:54.359
which means not letting you escape.

04:35:54.419 --> 04:35:56.519
He looked down at his claws again.

04:35:56.580 --> 04:35:58.799
Okay.

04:35:58.860 --> 04:36:02.279
He poked the rock once more, then raised

04:36:02.279 --> 04:36:03.659
his giant eyes to her again.

04:36:03.720 --> 04:36:07.080
They were sort of the color of goldfish, a

04:36:07.080 --> 04:36:08.939
golden orange that was much prettier than

04:36:08.939 --> 04:36:10.200
scarlet's yellow eyes.

04:36:10.259 --> 04:36:12.659
Want to hear a song?

04:36:12.720 --> 04:36:14.040
He whispered.

04:36:14.099 --> 04:36:15.539
A song?

04:36:15.599 --> 04:36:16.559
Pearl said.

04:36:16.619 --> 04:36:17.459
Really?

04:36:17.520 --> 04:36:22.139
I made it up myself just nowish, he

04:36:22.139 --> 04:36:22.380
said.

04:36:22.439 --> 04:36:23.999
All right.

04:36:24.119 --> 04:36:26.699
But quietly, said Pearl.

04:36:26.759 --> 04:36:28.979
The queen would really hate to be woken

04:36:28.979 --> 04:36:29.159
up.

04:36:29.220 --> 04:36:31.200
The queen.

04:36:31.319 --> 04:36:32.759
Oh.

04:36:32.819 --> 04:36:35.819
You mean grandmother, he said.

04:36:35.880 --> 04:36:37.740
Peril stifled a laugh.

04:36:37.799 --> 04:36:39.959
She didn't think anyone had ever dared

04:36:39.959 --> 04:36:42.299
call Queen Scarlet grandmother before.

04:36:42.360 --> 04:36:44.459
Ready?

04:36:44.520 --> 04:36:47.220
Prince Cliff flipped his wings back and

04:36:47.220 --> 04:36:49.139
stretched his long neck theatrically.

04:36:49.200 --> 04:36:51.900
You, the audience.

04:36:51.959 --> 04:36:52.799
So listen up.

04:36:52.860 --> 04:36:56.400
We, the dragons of the sky.

04:36:56.459 --> 04:36:59.700
We can fly and fly and fly.

04:36:59.759 --> 04:37:02.339
We go up so super high.

04:37:02.400 --> 04:37:05.279
We the dragons of the sky.

04:37:05.340 --> 04:37:10.380
And we know my mom is best, better queen

04:37:10.380 --> 04:37:11.520
and all the rest.

04:37:11.580 --> 04:37:14.939
She come save us from this mess.

04:37:15.000 --> 04:37:18.959
We, the dragons, dragons, dragons of the

04:37:18.959 --> 04:37:19.380
sky.

04:37:19.439 --> 04:37:22.319
Peril arched her browse at him.

04:37:22.380 --> 04:37:24.119
Cliff gave her a cheeky smile.

04:37:24.240 --> 04:37:25.740
What you think?

04:37:25.860 --> 04:37:26.819
He asked.

04:37:26.880 --> 04:37:30.299
I think maybe don't sing that song to

04:37:30.299 --> 04:37:32.099
your grandma, Pearl suggested.

04:37:32.159 --> 04:37:39.779
I think maybe mess and rest don't rhyme

04:37:39.779 --> 04:37:41.819
so right, he said.

04:37:41.880 --> 04:37:45.840
Test, West, Vest.

04:37:45.900 --> 04:37:47.040
Hmm.

04:37:47.159 --> 04:37:49.979
I'm a good rhymer, mommy says so.

04:37:50.099 --> 04:37:53.339
You don't seem all that scared anymore

04:37:53.339 --> 04:37:53.879
said Pearl.

04:37:53.939 --> 04:37:57.779
Yeah, he said, with a small flick of his

04:37:57.779 --> 04:37:58.499
dark red tail.

04:37:58.619 --> 04:38:02.819
Because Uncle Vermilion said, mommy's

04:38:02.819 --> 04:38:04.619
coming in the morning, and she makes

04:38:04.619 --> 04:38:07.019
everything better no matter what.

04:38:07.080 --> 04:38:09.720
Pearl wondered if she could actually

04:38:09.720 --> 04:38:12.060
collapse around the chasm that had

04:38:12.060 --> 04:38:13.439
suddenly yawned in her chest.

04:38:13.500 --> 04:38:16.380
She makes everything better.

04:38:16.439 --> 04:38:18.659
Peril had never felt that way about

04:38:18.659 --> 04:38:19.139
anyone.

04:38:19.200 --> 04:38:23.279
Queen Scarlet kept her alive, gave her a

04:38:23.279 --> 04:38:27.000
purpose, valued her, but made things

04:38:27.000 --> 04:38:28.860
better, no.

04:38:28.919 --> 04:38:31.499
Mostly perils days were made worse

04:38:31.499 --> 04:38:33.059
whenever she encountered the queen.

04:38:33.119 --> 04:38:35.999
So why do you follow her?

04:38:36.060 --> 04:38:38.639
Whispered a tiny part of her brain?

04:38:38.700 --> 04:38:41.520
Because what choice do I have?

04:38:41.580 --> 04:38:43.319
peril whispered back.

04:38:43.380 --> 04:38:45.479
Who else am I going to follow?

04:38:45.540 --> 04:38:47.279
No one else wants me.

04:38:47.340 --> 04:38:49.799
Grandma's kind of mean.

04:38:49.860 --> 04:38:53.099
Cliff observed, watching Pearl's face

04:38:53.099 --> 04:38:53.580
closely.

04:38:53.639 --> 04:38:57.599
Mommy said she was, but I thought she

04:38:57.599 --> 04:39:00.419
couldn't be because no one is ever mean

04:39:00.419 --> 04:39:03.180
to me, but then she really was.

04:39:03.299 --> 04:39:04.860
Did you see?

04:39:04.919 --> 04:39:07.319
What did you think was so mean?

04:39:07.380 --> 04:39:09.360
Parel asked curiously.

04:39:09.419 --> 04:39:13.319
She said eyes ordinary.

04:39:13.380 --> 04:39:16.380
Cliff drew himself up to his full tiny

04:39:16.380 --> 04:39:18.240
height, looking outraged.

04:39:18.299 --> 04:39:19.319
Me.

04:39:19.380 --> 04:39:22.080
I never, so mean.

04:39:22.200 --> 04:39:25.500
What's so bad about being ordinary?

04:39:25.560 --> 04:39:28.020
Parel opened and closed her talons

04:39:28.020 --> 04:39:28.319
again.

04:39:28.380 --> 04:39:30.959
Feeling her new secret prickle along her

04:39:30.959 --> 04:39:31.560
palms.

04:39:31.680 --> 04:39:33.419
Sounds great to me.

04:39:33.479 --> 04:39:35.159
What?

04:39:35.279 --> 04:39:37.799
Cliff's voice was loud enough to make

04:39:37.799 --> 04:39:40.079
Queen Scarlet stir in her sleep, and

04:39:40.079 --> 04:39:41.279
peril shushed him quickly.

04:39:41.340 --> 04:39:43.560
He lowered himself into a crouch and

04:39:43.560 --> 04:39:46.860
whispered furiously, Mommy says I'm

04:39:46.860 --> 04:39:47.279
special.

04:39:47.340 --> 04:39:49.380
Everyone say it.

04:39:49.439 --> 04:39:53.159
I'd be number one most beautiful singer

04:39:53.159 --> 04:39:54.720
Empirea one day.

04:39:54.779 --> 04:39:57.419
Friends with every dragon in the whole

04:39:57.419 --> 04:39:58.020
world.

04:39:58.080 --> 04:40:01.200
Mommy thinks I can do anything and great

04:40:01.200 --> 04:40:02.400
things at all things.

04:40:02.520 --> 04:40:07.139
Wow, Pearl said, friends with every

04:40:07.139 --> 04:40:08.040
dragon?

04:40:08.099 --> 04:40:10.860
Yup, Cliff said proudly.

04:40:10.919 --> 04:40:14.939
I gotta practice my, no, no, leave me

04:40:14.939 --> 04:40:17.639
alone, face, or else everyone want to be

04:40:17.639 --> 04:40:19.799
with me all the time.

04:40:19.860 --> 04:40:23.340
Don't wish to be alone, peril advised.

04:40:23.400 --> 04:40:24.659
Alone is awful.

04:40:24.779 --> 04:40:28.259
Yeah, he said, probably.

04:40:28.319 --> 04:40:31.020
Better than ordinary though.

04:40:31.080 --> 04:40:32.700
She shook her head.

04:40:32.759 --> 04:40:35.099
You're a weird little dragonette.

04:40:35.220 --> 04:40:37.080
Cliff's eyes were hopeful again.

04:40:37.200 --> 04:40:41.340
So, Maybe escape now then?

04:40:41.400 --> 04:40:43.919
He sidled toward the edge of the throne.

04:40:44.040 --> 04:40:48.720
Nope, no, sorry, peril said, waving him

04:40:48.720 --> 04:40:48.900
back.

04:40:48.959 --> 04:40:51.779
We wait for your mother, and then she

04:40:51.779 --> 04:40:52.799
won't be queen anymore.

04:40:52.860 --> 04:40:54.060
You know that, right?

04:40:54.119 --> 04:40:56.279
He hummed a line of his song.

04:40:56.400 --> 04:40:58.139
We see.

04:40:58.200 --> 04:41:01.020
He paced around the top of the throne for

04:41:01.020 --> 04:41:03.360
a moment before finally lying down, and

04:41:03.360 --> 04:41:06.540
then, at last, quietly singing himself to

04:41:06.540 --> 04:41:06.720
sleep.

04:41:06.779 --> 04:41:10.080
Peril did not sleep.

04:41:10.139 --> 04:41:13.560
She watched the stars creep slowly across

04:41:13.560 --> 04:41:14.400
the night sky.

04:41:14.459 --> 04:41:17.400
She watched a distant meteor streak

04:41:17.400 --> 04:41:18.419
between 2 of the moons.

04:41:18.479 --> 04:41:21.240
She watched the little prince's breath

04:41:21.240 --> 04:41:23.880
rise and fall in small puffs of smoke.

04:41:24.000 --> 04:41:27.180
She watched the sun slide and sprawl

04:41:27.180 --> 04:41:29.279
lazily across the mountain peaks as it

04:41:29.279 --> 04:41:32.939
rose, and very soon after sunrise, she

04:41:32.939 --> 04:41:34.860
saw the shapes of a wing of dragons

04:41:34.860 --> 04:41:36.419
flying toward them at full speed.

04:41:36.479 --> 04:41:39.959
Ruby knows, peril guest.

04:41:40.020 --> 04:41:41.759
Someone snuck out to warn her.

04:41:41.819 --> 04:41:45.060
Your majesty, she whispered to the

04:41:45.060 --> 04:41:45.299
Queen.

04:41:45.360 --> 04:41:47.099
Ruby is coming.

04:41:47.159 --> 04:41:49.979
Queen Scarlet was awake in an instant.

04:41:50.040 --> 04:41:52.799
She ran her talons over her spikes and

04:41:52.799 --> 04:41:53.819
flexed her claws.

04:41:53.880 --> 04:41:55.919
She made sure her jewelry was all

04:41:55.919 --> 04:41:56.819
adjusted perfectly.

04:41:56.880 --> 04:41:58.259
For a moment.

04:41:58.319 --> 04:42:00.720
Her talons hovered over her scarred face

04:42:00.720 --> 04:42:03.000
as if she wanted to tear it off.

04:42:03.060 --> 04:42:05.580
But then they dropped, and she lifted her

04:42:05.580 --> 04:42:08.040
chin, glowering defiantly out at the

04:42:08.040 --> 04:42:09.000
approaching dragons.

04:42:09.060 --> 04:42:12.060
It wasn't long before they swooped in

04:42:12.060 --> 04:42:12.720
through the opening.

04:42:12.779 --> 04:42:15.779
Ruby, and more guards than peril could

04:42:15.779 --> 04:42:18.299
count in a glance, but Ruby was in the

04:42:18.299 --> 04:42:20.639
lead, landing in a run that brought her

04:42:20.639 --> 04:42:22.860
nearly to the foot of the thrones before

04:42:22.860 --> 04:42:24.540
the 5 guards stepped in her way.

04:42:24.599 --> 04:42:26.520
Mommy!

04:42:26.580 --> 04:42:27.959
Cliff cried.

04:42:28.020 --> 04:42:30.779
He leaped up, waving his wings joyfully.

04:42:30.840 --> 04:42:33.900
Not another step.

04:42:33.959 --> 04:42:37.619
Queen Scarlet said, in a voice of pure

04:42:37.619 --> 04:42:37.919
ice.

04:42:37.979 --> 04:42:41.759
Or you know exactly, what will happen to

04:42:41.759 --> 04:42:43.560
your precious dragonette?

04:42:43.680 --> 04:42:47.939
Chapter 14.

04:42:48.180 --> 04:42:52.560
Ruby stood frozen, quivering with fury.

04:42:52.619 --> 04:42:55.319
The guards standing between her and the

04:42:55.319 --> 04:42:57.720
Thrones had their shoulders hunched, a

04:42:57.720 --> 04:42:59.580
kind of shame sketched in the shape of

04:42:59.580 --> 04:43:01.799
their wings, but she wasn't glaring at

04:43:01.799 --> 04:43:03.659
them, or even at scarlet.

04:43:03.720 --> 04:43:06.599
The full force of her anger was directed

04:43:06.599 --> 04:43:08.819
at peril, who stood a step behind the

04:43:08.819 --> 04:43:09.119
prince.

04:43:09.180 --> 04:43:14.099
If you touch him, Ruby choked out, if you

04:43:14.099 --> 04:43:14.700
dare.

04:43:14.759 --> 04:43:19.619
She won't, unless I tell her to, said the

04:43:19.619 --> 04:43:20.639
queen imperiously.

04:43:20.700 --> 04:43:24.240
But believe me, she will, the moment I

04:43:24.240 --> 04:43:24.779
give the order.

04:43:24.840 --> 04:43:26.700
Huh?

04:43:26.759 --> 04:43:27.840
Peril thought.

04:43:27.900 --> 04:43:28.979
Would I?

04:43:29.099 --> 04:43:31.560
If I still had fire scales?

04:43:31.619 --> 04:43:34.080
And Scarlet ordered me to burn the

04:43:34.080 --> 04:43:34.439
prints?

04:43:34.560 --> 04:43:36.000
What would I do?

04:43:36.060 --> 04:43:37.979
He's so little.

04:43:38.099 --> 04:43:42.779
And I don't kill dragons anymore, rang a

04:43:42.779 --> 04:43:44.580
different kind of note inside Peril's

04:43:44.580 --> 04:43:47.700
mind, familiar, and unfamiliar at the

04:43:47.700 --> 04:43:48.000
same time.

04:43:48.060 --> 04:43:50.459
She blinked.

04:43:50.520 --> 04:43:51.599
Don't I?

04:43:51.659 --> 04:43:52.919
Why not?

04:43:52.979 --> 04:43:54.959
I knew it.

04:43:55.080 --> 04:43:56.340
Ruby spat.

04:43:56.400 --> 04:43:59.220
I knew you couldn't be trusted, you fire

04:43:59.220 --> 04:44:00.299
scales monster.

04:44:00.360 --> 04:44:04.139
I'm just following orders, Parel

04:44:04.139 --> 04:44:04.680
protested.

04:44:04.740 --> 04:44:07.380
She was queen first, you know, and she

04:44:07.380 --> 04:44:10.200
didn't banish me or wish me dead, unlike

04:44:10.200 --> 04:44:10.979
some dragons.

04:44:11.040 --> 04:44:13.740
I don't know why you'd expect me to be

04:44:13.740 --> 04:44:14.819
loyal to you instead.

04:44:14.939 --> 04:44:17.819
I don't want your loyalty.

04:44:17.939 --> 04:44:20.220
Ruby shouted, but this?

04:44:20.340 --> 04:44:23.400
threatening innocent dragonettes, helping

04:44:23.400 --> 04:44:25.139
her, after everything.

04:44:25.200 --> 04:44:27.959
That's not exactly the great peaceful new

04:44:27.959 --> 04:44:30.000
dragon you are claiming to be, is it?

04:44:30.060 --> 04:44:31.680
I knew you were lying.

04:44:31.740 --> 04:44:34.139
You have always been the reason for

04:44:34.139 --> 04:44:35.759
everything that's wrong with the Sky

04:44:35.759 --> 04:44:36.360
Kingdom.

04:44:36.419 --> 04:44:37.919
Me?

04:44:37.979 --> 04:44:40.500
Pearl cried, astonished.

04:44:40.560 --> 04:44:43.439
Ruby really did hate her more than anyone

04:44:43.439 --> 04:44:43.740
else.

04:44:43.799 --> 04:44:46.020
Peril wasn't just being paranoid.

04:44:46.080 --> 04:44:47.279
But why?

04:44:47.340 --> 04:44:49.680
I just do what I'm told.

04:44:49.740 --> 04:44:51.060
Like everyone else?

04:44:51.119 --> 04:44:53.700
I kill Queen Scarlet's enemies.

04:44:53.759 --> 04:44:54.299
That's all.

04:44:54.419 --> 04:44:56.159
What did I ever do to you?

04:44:56.279 --> 04:45:00.540
Excuse me, said Queen Scarlet from the

04:45:00.540 --> 04:45:01.259
top of her throne.

04:45:01.319 --> 04:45:03.540
I feel like we're getting off topic.

04:45:03.599 --> 04:45:06.060
I'm the one who's here to take back the

04:45:06.060 --> 04:45:06.419
kingdom.

04:45:06.479 --> 04:45:10.560
Those eggs on the brightest night, Ruby

04:45:10.560 --> 04:45:12.000
said. clutching the floor.

04:45:12.060 --> 04:45:15.240
Behind her, Pearl saw several of her

04:45:15.240 --> 04:45:18.299
guards nodding, frowning, remembering

04:45:18.299 --> 04:45:20.759
something awful, and hating peril for it

04:45:20.759 --> 04:45:22.619
when Pearl couldn't even remember it

04:45:22.619 --> 04:45:22.919
herself.

04:45:22.979 --> 04:45:24.299
Or could she?

04:45:24.360 --> 04:45:27.659
She saw a flash of white eggshells

04:45:27.659 --> 04:45:30.360
turning to black between her talons, here

04:45:30.360 --> 04:45:31.380
in this very room.

04:45:31.439 --> 04:45:34.139
What did I do?

04:45:34.200 --> 04:45:36.000
What did Scarlet make me do?

04:45:36.060 --> 04:45:40.080
And my sister, Ruby hissed.

04:45:40.139 --> 04:45:43.200
Do you even remember her among the 100s

04:45:43.200 --> 04:45:44.580
of dragons you've killed?

04:45:44.639 --> 04:45:47.819
Peril stared at her for a long moment

04:45:47.819 --> 04:45:49.380
racking her brain.

04:45:49.439 --> 04:45:51.900
No, she said finally.

04:45:51.959 --> 04:45:53.340
Who?

04:45:53.400 --> 04:45:57.299
Ruby shrieked a long scream of rage.

04:45:57.360 --> 04:45:59.700
So apparently that was the wrong thing to

04:45:59.700 --> 04:45:59.939
say.

04:46:00.060 --> 04:46:03.419
But high up on her cloud thrown, Queen

04:46:03.419 --> 04:46:04.740
Scarlet was laughing.

04:46:04.860 --> 04:46:09.419
Oh Ruby, she said, shaking her head.

04:46:09.479 --> 04:46:12.959
Ruby, you empty headed princess.

04:46:13.020 --> 04:46:14.819
Is that what you thought all these

04:46:14.819 --> 04:46:15.119
years?

04:46:15.180 --> 04:46:17.639
Have you been hating my poor little

04:46:17.639 --> 04:46:20.520
champion for the one terrible thing she

04:46:20.520 --> 04:46:22.740
actually didn't do?

04:46:22.799 --> 04:46:26.400
A blistering hush swept over the throne

04:46:26.400 --> 04:46:26.639
room.

04:46:26.700 --> 04:46:29.220
Ruby was looking at her mother now

04:46:29.220 --> 04:46:31.619
confusion starting to ebb between the

04:46:31.619 --> 04:46:33.119
lines of fury and her expression.

04:46:33.180 --> 04:46:34.860
What?

04:46:34.919 --> 04:46:36.060
she said finally.

04:46:36.119 --> 04:46:39.540
Peril didn't kill Tourmaline.

04:46:39.599 --> 04:46:41.400
Queen Scarlet said airily.

04:46:41.459 --> 04:46:43.380
She's not even dead, actually.

04:46:43.439 --> 04:46:44.880
She's not?

04:46:45.000 --> 04:46:46.080
said Ruby.

04:46:46.139 --> 04:46:47.759
Where is she?

04:46:47.819 --> 04:46:50.459
Let's try to focus.

04:46:50.520 --> 04:46:51.299
Shall we?

04:46:51.299 --> 04:46:52.139
said the queen.

04:46:52.200 --> 04:46:53.939
I'm here for my throne.

04:46:54.000 --> 04:46:56.759
Thank you for keeping it warm for me, but

04:46:56.759 --> 04:46:57.779
it's time to give it back.

04:46:57.840 --> 04:47:01.080
Mommy, Cliff called.

04:47:01.139 --> 04:47:03.419
Mommy, I have to tell you something.

04:47:03.540 --> 04:47:04.439
Mommy.

04:47:04.500 --> 04:47:07.439
Grandma is kind of mean.

04:47:07.500 --> 04:47:10.139
I know, sweetheart.

04:47:10.200 --> 04:47:12.240
Don't worry, Ruby said.

04:47:12.299 --> 04:47:15.000
She clenched your jaw, fixing her eyes on

04:47:15.000 --> 04:47:15.540
her mother again.

04:47:15.599 --> 04:47:18.240
You can't have the throne back.

04:47:18.360 --> 04:47:21.000
You can't just saunter in here and claim

04:47:21.000 --> 04:47:22.319
it after being gone for months.

04:47:22.380 --> 04:47:25.139
A queen who abandons her throne has

04:47:25.139 --> 04:47:26.400
abdicated it forever.

04:47:26.459 --> 04:47:28.380
Oh, really?

04:47:28.439 --> 04:47:29.880
Scarlett said.

04:47:29.939 --> 04:47:32.400
I don't believe this question has ever

04:47:32.400 --> 04:47:34.319
come up in the Sky Kingdom before.

04:47:34.380 --> 04:47:37.919
So where did that convenient rule come

04:47:37.919 --> 04:47:38.159
from?

04:47:38.279 --> 04:47:42.060
Ruby lifted her chin, her eyes burning.

04:47:42.119 --> 04:47:43.919
I decreed it.

04:47:43.979 --> 04:47:45.360
As queen.

04:47:45.419 --> 04:47:47.340
Aha.

04:47:47.400 --> 04:47:51.299
I see, said Scarlett.

04:47:51.360 --> 04:47:53.880
She leaned over the edge of her throne

04:47:53.880 --> 04:47:57.180
arching her neck as a little burst of

04:47:57.180 --> 04:47:58.619
flames curled from her nose.

04:47:58.680 --> 04:48:05.580
Then, as queen, I un decree it.

04:48:05.639 --> 04:48:07.860
What are you going to do about that?

04:48:07.919 --> 04:48:10.139
I am the queen.

04:48:10.200 --> 04:48:13.200
Ruby said firmly, and you can't challenge

04:48:13.200 --> 04:48:13.680
me for it.

04:48:13.740 --> 04:48:15.900
Only sisters, daughters.

04:48:15.959 --> 04:48:18.959
Yes, yes, yes, blah, blah.

04:48:19.020 --> 04:48:21.720
Scarlett said, waving one talent in the

04:48:21.720 --> 04:48:21.959
air.

04:48:22.020 --> 04:48:25.439
But my dear, you can quote rules at me

04:48:25.439 --> 04:48:28.200
all day long, and it won't change one

04:48:28.200 --> 04:48:31.020
particular important fact.

04:48:31.080 --> 04:48:32.580
I have your son.

04:48:32.700 --> 04:48:35.700
Ruby looked down at Prince Cliff again.

04:48:35.759 --> 04:48:38.819
He waved timidly, and she made a little

04:48:38.819 --> 04:48:41.040
gesture with her shoulders, which seemed

04:48:41.040 --> 04:48:43.259
to be a quiet signal to sit up and look

04:48:43.259 --> 04:48:45.360
brave, because that was what he did

04:48:45.360 --> 04:48:46.139
next.

04:48:46.200 --> 04:48:50.700
Peril felt a brief, wild impulse to pick

04:48:50.700 --> 04:48:52.860
up the dragonette and throw him to the

04:48:52.860 --> 04:48:54.240
safety of his mother's arms.

04:48:54.299 --> 04:48:56.220
I can't do that.

04:48:56.279 --> 04:48:59.040
That would really ruin everything for my

04:48:59.040 --> 04:48:59.400
queen.

04:48:59.459 --> 04:49:02.099
But is it the right thing to do?

04:49:02.159 --> 04:49:05.819
Came that strange whisper again, as

04:49:05.819 --> 04:49:07.560
though her mind was haunted by some other

04:49:07.560 --> 04:49:10.439
version of herself, she poked one claw

04:49:10.439 --> 04:49:13.080
into her ear, scratching, as if she could

04:49:13.080 --> 04:49:14.459
drag it out and examine it.

04:49:14.520 --> 04:49:16.860
So really?

04:49:16.919 --> 04:49:19.979
There's only one question, said Queen

04:49:19.979 --> 04:49:23.040
Scarlet, with all the self important glee

04:49:23.040 --> 04:49:25.139
that had ever been mustered in Pyria.

04:49:25.200 --> 04:49:27.119
Which would you rather have?

04:49:27.240 --> 04:49:30.720
The throne or your dragonette?

04:49:30.840 --> 04:49:34.319
Your majesty, said one of the dragons

04:49:34.319 --> 04:49:36.659
behind Ruby, and it took peril a moment

04:49:36.659 --> 04:49:38.759
to realize he was talking to Ruby, and

04:49:38.759 --> 04:49:39.900
not Scarlet.

04:49:39.959 --> 04:49:41.040
We can fight.

04:49:41.099 --> 04:49:42.540
We will fight for you.

04:49:42.599 --> 04:49:45.419
Your supporters outnumber hers and we're

04:49:45.419 --> 04:49:45.840
more loyal.

04:49:45.959 --> 04:49:48.720
I know, said Ruby.

04:49:48.779 --> 04:49:52.259
But a 100,000 Skywings still couldn't

04:49:52.259 --> 04:49:54.840
save Cliff in the next minute if my

04:49:54.840 --> 04:49:56.400
mother sets her creature on him.

04:49:56.459 --> 04:50:00.360
Peril felt the sting of Ruby's bitterness

04:50:00.360 --> 04:50:01.439
from across the room.

04:50:01.500 --> 04:50:04.979
The confirmation that once again, peril

04:50:04.979 --> 04:50:06.540
had ruined everything for her.

04:50:06.779 --> 04:50:09.360
I'm just being who I am.

04:50:09.419 --> 04:50:10.860
Pearl thought.

04:50:10.979 --> 04:50:14.099
Although, I'm not a creature anymore

04:50:14.099 --> 04:50:14.700
actually.

04:50:14.759 --> 04:50:17.580
I'm only pretending to be dangerous for

04:50:17.580 --> 04:50:18.479
Queen Scarlet.

04:50:18.599 --> 04:50:21.779
So I'm not really being my new self at

04:50:21.779 --> 04:50:22.139
all.

04:50:22.200 --> 04:50:24.779
But I promised to be loyal to her.

04:50:24.840 --> 04:50:27.540
Isn't that an important part of me?

04:50:27.599 --> 04:50:30.299
So why haven't I been?

04:50:30.360 --> 04:50:33.240
Something was shaking at the corner's

04:50:33.240 --> 04:50:35.939
apparel's brain, shaking and tugging and

04:50:35.939 --> 04:50:38.700
pulling and trying to come loose, but she

04:50:38.700 --> 04:50:40.080
couldn't sink her teeth into it.

04:50:40.139 --> 04:50:42.840
She couldn't remember.

04:50:42.900 --> 04:50:44.520
All right.

04:50:44.580 --> 04:50:47.819
Ruby said to Queen Scarlet, you win.

04:50:47.880 --> 04:50:50.580
If you promise me that Cliff will be safe

04:50:50.580 --> 04:50:52.979
I'll give up my kingdom.

04:50:53.099 --> 04:50:57.119
No, exploded one of Ruby's soldiers

04:50:57.119 --> 04:50:58.080
stumbling forward.

04:50:58.139 --> 04:51:00.599
To peril's surprise, he was not a

04:51:00.599 --> 04:51:01.200
Skywing.

04:51:01.259 --> 04:51:02.639
He was a mudwing.

04:51:02.700 --> 04:51:05.459
Skinny and tired looking and spattered

04:51:05.459 --> 04:51:05.880
with dirt.

04:51:05.939 --> 04:51:07.680
Peril.

04:51:07.740 --> 04:51:10.680
He said, holding out his talons

04:51:10.680 --> 04:51:11.580
beseechingly.

04:51:11.639 --> 04:51:13.020
What are you doing?

04:51:13.080 --> 04:51:14.580
You don't want this.

04:51:14.700 --> 04:51:16.200
Nobody wants this.

04:51:16.259 --> 04:51:18.060
What would Clay think?

04:51:18.119 --> 04:51:20.819
Peril tilted her head at him.

04:51:20.880 --> 04:51:23.520
The thing in her mind was really flapping

04:51:23.520 --> 04:51:26.159
now, but it still didn't have a shape or

04:51:26.159 --> 04:51:28.020
anything useful that she could pin down.

04:51:28.080 --> 04:51:29.700
Clay?

04:51:29.759 --> 04:51:30.779
She echoed.

04:51:30.900 --> 04:51:32.220
Who's that?

04:51:32.340 --> 04:51:36.540
Chapter 15.

04:51:36.959 --> 04:51:40.860
In the silence that fell, the only sound

04:51:40.860 --> 04:51:42.959
was Ruby inhaling sharply.

04:51:43.020 --> 04:51:45.299
It's a spell, she said.

04:51:45.360 --> 04:51:46.979
What did you do to her?

04:51:47.040 --> 04:51:49.020
She whirled towards Scarlet.

04:51:49.080 --> 04:51:52.380
Behind her, in the huddle of Skywing

04:51:52.380 --> 04:51:53.759
guards who are now flapping and

04:51:53.759 --> 04:51:56.400
whispering among themselves, Pearl saw 2

04:51:56.400 --> 04:51:58.799
of them slip out into the sky and wheel

04:51:58.799 --> 04:51:59.880
around to fly south.

04:51:59.939 --> 04:52:02.340
If they were up to something, she

04:52:02.340 --> 04:52:03.540
couldn't imagine what it might be.

04:52:03.659 --> 04:52:06.060
So she decided she didn't need to point

04:52:06.060 --> 04:52:08.279
them out to the queen, who was, in any

04:52:08.279 --> 04:52:10.680
case, quite busy giving Ruby an

04:52:10.680 --> 04:52:12.540
exaggeratedly shocked expression.

04:52:12.659 --> 04:52:15.419
Ah, didn't do anything at all.

04:52:15.479 --> 04:52:18.659
Scarlett protested, batting her wings

04:52:18.659 --> 04:52:19.259
airily.

04:52:19.380 --> 04:52:23.580
Peril is my most loyal subject, just as

04:52:23.580 --> 04:52:25.139
she always has been.

04:52:25.200 --> 04:52:29.279
That's why she's my champion, and you are

04:52:29.279 --> 04:52:30.240
going to be dead soon.

04:52:30.299 --> 04:52:34.259
Peril would never just forget about clay

04:52:34.259 --> 04:52:35.279
said Ruby.

04:52:35.340 --> 04:52:37.500
How did you erase him from her brain?

04:52:37.560 --> 04:52:40.259
What kind of horrible animus touched

04:52:40.259 --> 04:52:41.759
object did you get your claws on?

04:52:41.819 --> 04:52:46.380
Hey, I'm not under a spell, Peril

04:52:46.380 --> 04:52:46.919
interjected.

04:52:46.979 --> 04:52:48.720
I just don't know who you're talking

04:52:48.720 --> 04:52:49.020
about.

04:52:49.080 --> 04:52:51.180
I don't have a great memory.

04:52:51.240 --> 04:52:53.400
No need to get all smoky and bothered.

04:52:53.459 --> 04:52:56.759
On the other side of Queen Scarlet, orange

04:52:56.759 --> 04:52:59.520
scales moved, and Perel remembered that

04:52:59.520 --> 04:53:01.139
her father was there, listening.

04:53:01.259 --> 04:53:03.419
Her father.

04:53:03.540 --> 04:53:06.959
Clay is the dragon who changed you, Ruby

04:53:06.959 --> 04:53:09.060
said, at least according to you.

04:53:09.119 --> 04:53:11.580
He's one of the dragonettes from the

04:53:11.580 --> 04:53:12.959
prophecy who ended the war.

04:53:13.020 --> 04:53:13.740
Remember?

04:53:13.799 --> 04:53:15.659
You met in the arena?

04:53:15.720 --> 04:53:18.240
You saved his life in the kingdom of sand

04:53:18.240 --> 04:53:20.759
when a dragon bite viper bit him.

04:53:20.819 --> 04:53:22.619
He's.

04:53:22.680 --> 04:53:24.900
She stopped and looked down at her

04:53:24.900 --> 04:53:25.500
talons.

04:53:25.560 --> 04:53:28.500
He's the only dragon who is willing to

04:53:28.500 --> 04:53:29.520
give you a 2nd chance.

04:53:29.580 --> 04:53:33.720
Well, there's me, Scarlett said

04:53:33.720 --> 04:53:34.500
smoothly.

04:53:34.560 --> 04:53:37.200
The dragon who gave you your 1st chance

04:53:37.200 --> 04:53:39.180
and never required a second.

04:53:39.240 --> 04:53:41.459
That's all you really need to remember.

04:53:41.580 --> 04:53:44.159
I am the one who cares about you.

04:53:44.220 --> 04:53:46.619
That sounded true.

04:53:46.680 --> 04:53:49.919
And not true.

04:53:49.979 --> 04:53:51.599
Wait.

04:53:51.659 --> 04:53:54.360
There's turtle, peril blurted.

04:53:54.419 --> 04:53:56.819
That was the one dragon she could think

04:53:56.819 --> 04:53:58.319
of who'd ever been friendly to her.

04:53:58.380 --> 04:54:01.139
He laughed at her jokes, even the ones

04:54:01.139 --> 04:54:02.580
that peril hadn't done on purpose.

04:54:02.639 --> 04:54:04.860
She remembered that.

04:54:04.919 --> 04:54:06.000
And hang on.

04:54:06.060 --> 04:54:08.520
Why would Turtle be friends with her?

04:54:08.580 --> 04:54:10.979
If she was really Scarlet's dangerous

04:54:10.979 --> 04:54:11.400
weapon.

04:54:11.459 --> 04:54:15.180
He liked me with my fire scales.

04:54:15.240 --> 04:54:16.979
But without my queen.

04:54:17.040 --> 04:54:19.979
Who's turtle?

04:54:20.040 --> 04:54:21.599
Her father said tensely.

04:54:21.659 --> 04:54:24.060
He glanced up at Queen Scarlet.

04:54:24.119 --> 04:54:26.459
You never mentioned anyone named Turtle.

04:54:26.520 --> 04:54:31.979
Anyway, Scarlett said, we were in the

04:54:31.979 --> 04:54:33.659
middle of a wonderfully peaceful transfer

04:54:33.659 --> 04:54:34.439
of power.

04:54:34.500 --> 04:54:38.759
Ruby, dear, since obviously I can't trust

04:54:38.759 --> 04:54:39.540
you anymore.

04:54:39.599 --> 04:54:42.240
I'm going to have to lock you up until I

04:54:42.240 --> 04:54:43.380
figure out what to do with you.

04:54:43.439 --> 04:54:45.779
I'm picturing some kind of grand

04:54:45.779 --> 04:54:47.700
ceremonial execution.

04:54:47.759 --> 04:54:51.000
Maybe to celebrate turning my arena back

04:54:51.000 --> 04:54:53.340
into an arena the way it's supposed to

04:54:53.340 --> 04:54:53.520
be.

04:54:53.639 --> 04:54:56.939
But Cliff, Ruby started.

04:54:57.000 --> 04:55:00.360
He'll be fine, Scarlett said, safe with

04:55:00.360 --> 04:55:01.560
his loving grandmother.

04:55:01.619 --> 04:55:02.759
For now.

04:55:02.819 --> 04:55:04.680
At least until this whole

04:55:04.680 --> 04:55:07.439
misunderstanding is quite cleared up, and

04:55:07.439 --> 04:55:09.540
the balance of power is right back where

04:55:09.540 --> 04:55:10.200
it should be.

04:55:10.259 --> 04:55:13.500
Guards, she added commandingly.

04:55:13.560 --> 04:55:16.259
Take Ruby to the prison in the great hall

04:55:16.259 --> 04:55:18.240
the one where we kept Kestrel.

04:55:18.360 --> 04:55:21.119
Lock her in, and then notify all the

04:55:21.119 --> 04:55:24.060
cowards in this palace that it's time to

04:55:24.060 --> 04:55:26.819
come out and swear their allegiance to

04:55:26.819 --> 04:55:27.060
me.

04:55:27.119 --> 04:55:31.259
There was a long, dreadful pause that

04:55:31.259 --> 04:55:33.599
felt like someone taking a dragon wing

04:55:33.599 --> 04:55:39.000
and stretching, stretching, stretching it

04:55:39.000 --> 04:55:42.299
just beyond its extension.

04:55:42.360 --> 04:55:45.060
Scarlet hissed dangerously.

04:55:45.119 --> 04:55:47.819
Or, she said.

04:55:47.880 --> 04:55:50.639
We can all watch this little prince burn

04:55:50.639 --> 04:55:53.759
to death, followed by every disobedient

04:55:53.759 --> 04:55:55.020
dragon in this room.

04:55:55.080 --> 04:55:57.180
Do as she says.

04:55:57.240 --> 04:56:00.119
Ruby turned to the soldiers behind her.

04:56:00.180 --> 04:56:03.060
Whatever it takes to keep Cliff safe.

04:56:03.119 --> 04:56:04.439
You too.

04:56:04.560 --> 04:56:06.840
I want you to be the ones to lock me up.

04:56:06.900 --> 04:56:11.279
But your majesty, one of them began, then

04:56:11.279 --> 04:56:12.959
stopped as Ruby shook her head.

04:56:13.020 --> 04:56:14.700
It's done.

04:56:14.759 --> 04:56:15.720
She said.

04:56:15.779 --> 04:56:16.740
Let's go.

04:56:16.799 --> 04:56:18.240
Cliff.

04:56:18.360 --> 04:56:20.099
I love you, little one.

04:56:20.220 --> 04:56:21.599
Don't be scared.

04:56:21.659 --> 04:56:24.000
You're still going to change the world

04:56:24.000 --> 04:56:24.720
all right?

04:56:24.779 --> 04:56:28.500
The dragonette nodded, his wings drooping

04:56:28.500 --> 04:56:29.279
forlornly.

04:56:29.340 --> 04:56:31.080
He looked back at peril.

04:56:31.139 --> 04:56:33.720
Can I give mommy a hog?

04:56:33.779 --> 04:56:35.099
He whispered.

04:56:35.159 --> 04:56:37.380
I think she need a hug.

04:56:37.439 --> 04:56:39.479
Pearl shook her head.

04:56:39.540 --> 04:56:41.159
Sorry, little friend.

04:56:41.279 --> 04:56:44.459
Cliff watched Ruby walk out of the throne

04:56:44.459 --> 04:56:44.759
room.

04:56:44.819 --> 04:56:47.520
Her head held high, and he did a little

04:56:47.520 --> 04:56:49.500
shake with his wings, as if trying to

04:56:49.500 --> 04:56:50.520
imitate her stance.

04:56:50.580 --> 04:56:52.560
Clear out.

04:56:52.619 --> 04:56:55.139
Scarlett snarled at the other soldiers.

04:56:55.200 --> 04:56:57.419
I don't want to look at you anymore.

04:56:57.479 --> 04:57:00.959
Someone muttered, the feeling is mutual.

04:57:01.020 --> 04:57:03.599
As most of the Skywings filed out.

04:57:03.659 --> 04:57:06.779
The one mud wing gave peril an anguished

04:57:06.779 --> 04:57:07.919
look as he followed them.

04:57:07.979 --> 04:57:11.580
Try to remember clay, he whispered.

04:57:11.639 --> 04:57:12.840
Please.

04:57:13.080 --> 04:57:14.639
Soon they were gone.

04:57:14.700 --> 04:57:17.279
And peril was left alone with her father

04:57:17.279 --> 04:57:19.619
Queen Scarlet, and the little prince.

04:57:19.740 --> 04:57:22.200
Who is Clay?

04:57:22.259 --> 04:57:23.520
She asked the queen.

04:57:23.580 --> 04:57:25.020
Should I remember him?

04:57:25.080 --> 04:57:26.279
Do you?

04:57:26.340 --> 04:57:28.380
Scarlett shrugged.

04:57:28.439 --> 04:57:29.520
Barely.

04:57:29.580 --> 04:57:32.159
He's some nobody who thinks he's a hero.

04:57:32.220 --> 04:57:33.000
Don't worry about it.

04:57:33.060 --> 04:57:37.259
They seemed really sure that I knew him.

04:57:37.380 --> 04:57:39.659
Peril said slowly.

04:57:39.659 --> 04:57:42.360
Ruby said I saved his life.

04:57:42.419 --> 04:57:46.080
But I don't remember ever saving anyone's

04:57:46.080 --> 04:57:46.500
life.

04:57:46.560 --> 04:57:48.479
I would definitely remember that.

04:57:48.540 --> 04:57:49.919
Wouldn't I?

04:57:49.979 --> 04:57:52.860
Maybe she's got you confused with some

04:57:52.860 --> 04:57:55.259
other dragon, Scarlett said.

04:57:55.319 --> 04:57:57.959
This conversation is ever so boring.

04:57:58.080 --> 04:58:00.299
I'm going to tour the palace to see what

04:58:00.299 --> 04:58:02.459
other damage my dreadful daughter has

04:58:02.459 --> 04:58:02.939
done.

04:58:03.000 --> 04:58:03.959
Vermilion.

04:58:04.080 --> 04:58:06.779
The red dragon poked his head in the door

04:58:06.779 --> 04:58:09.119
immediately, as if he'd been hovering a

04:58:09.119 --> 04:58:09.900
claw step away.

04:58:09.900 --> 04:58:11.040
Yes?

04:58:11.159 --> 04:58:14.639
Are my prisoner towers still in place at

04:58:14.639 --> 04:58:14.819
least?

04:58:14.939 --> 04:58:16.319
Scarlett demanded.

04:58:16.380 --> 04:58:18.840
Er, he said.

04:58:18.900 --> 04:58:23.099
I'll take it, that's a no, she said.

04:58:23.159 --> 04:58:26.279
She let out an enormous, aggrieved sigh.

04:58:26.400 --> 04:58:30.119
Those took ages to build, and they were

04:58:30.119 --> 04:58:30.720
genius.

04:58:30.779 --> 04:58:33.119
I'm going to have to kill at least 7

04:58:33.119 --> 04:58:35.040
disloyal traitors to cheer myself up.

04:58:35.099 --> 04:58:36.479
Fine.

04:58:36.599 --> 04:58:37.860
You too.

04:58:37.919 --> 04:58:40.080
She barked at peril and chameleon.

04:58:40.139 --> 04:58:43.439
Take this dragonette to the tallest spire

04:58:43.439 --> 04:58:45.659
of my palace and stick him on the highest

04:58:45.659 --> 04:58:46.560
ledge you can find.

04:58:46.619 --> 04:58:47.880
Wait.

04:58:47.939 --> 04:58:50.459
Lizard, can you fly yet?

04:58:50.520 --> 04:58:55.560
My name isn't Lizard, is Cliff, said the

04:58:55.560 --> 04:58:56.340
prince boldly.

04:58:56.400 --> 04:58:57.599
And...

04:58:57.599 --> 04:58:59.400
Not so much.

04:58:59.459 --> 04:59:03.360
I practice lots, but I falled lots too.

04:59:03.419 --> 04:59:06.119
Good, said the queen.

04:59:06.180 --> 04:59:08.759
As long as he can't fly away, he'll be

04:59:08.759 --> 04:59:09.299
stuck up there.

04:59:09.360 --> 04:59:12.060
Keep an eye on him until I get back.

04:59:12.119 --> 04:59:15.000
She swept out of the throne room with

04:59:15.000 --> 04:59:17.220
Vermilion. leaving peril with a

04:59:17.220 --> 04:59:19.500
bewildering impression that the queen had

04:59:19.500 --> 04:59:21.119
just run away from an awkward

04:59:21.119 --> 04:59:21.599
conversation.

04:59:21.659 --> 04:59:25.080
Chameleon picked up Prince Cliff and

04:59:25.080 --> 04:59:26.099
perched him on his back.

04:59:26.159 --> 04:59:28.439
Hold on tight, he said.

04:59:28.500 --> 04:59:31.319
The prince obligingly threw his arms and

04:59:31.319 --> 04:59:33.720
wings around Chameleon's neck and buried

04:59:33.720 --> 04:59:34.080
his face.

04:59:34.139 --> 04:59:38.159
They flew out the open wall and soared in

04:59:38.159 --> 04:59:40.080
a circle for a moment, assessing the

04:59:40.080 --> 04:59:40.439
palace.

04:59:40.500 --> 04:59:44.279
Peril realized that the tallest spire she

04:59:44.279 --> 04:59:46.380
could see was the chimney for the

04:59:46.380 --> 04:59:49.439
crematorium, a long, long tower that

04:59:49.439 --> 04:59:51.900
carried the smoke of burning bodies as

04:59:51.900 --> 04:59:53.759
high and far away from the rest of the

04:59:53.759 --> 04:59:54.720
palace as possible.

04:59:54.779 --> 04:59:57.540
But sitting on top of it, would put them

04:59:57.540 --> 04:59:59.220
right in the middle of the smoke and the

04:59:59.220 --> 05:00:01.500
smells, and Perel had a feeling that

05:00:01.500 --> 05:00:03.360
might be a little traumatizing for Cliff

05:00:03.360 --> 05:00:06.000
plus not much fun for her and Chameleon

05:00:06.000 --> 05:00:06.180
either.

05:00:06.240 --> 05:00:09.419
So instead, she chose the 2nd tallest

05:00:09.419 --> 05:00:09.959
spire.

05:00:10.020 --> 05:00:12.959
A lookout for guards near the outer wall

05:00:12.959 --> 05:00:13.799
of the palace.

05:00:13.860 --> 05:00:15.959
At the top of the tower was a small

05:00:15.959 --> 05:00:19.139
pavilion, with room for 5 or 6 dragons to

05:00:19.139 --> 05:00:19.740
fit comfortably.

05:00:19.799 --> 05:00:22.500
A shallow hole in the floor was intended

05:00:22.500 --> 05:00:25.139
as a fire pit, for heating the tower when

05:00:25.139 --> 05:00:26.939
it was cold, or for cooking prey.

05:00:27.000 --> 05:00:30.299
The walls were open on all sides, but the

05:00:30.299 --> 05:00:31.740
position of the tower was clearly

05:00:31.740 --> 05:00:34.380
directed west to watch for attacks from

05:00:34.380 --> 05:00:36.540
ice wings or sand wings.

05:00:36.599 --> 05:00:39.599
Cliff slid off Chameleon's back and began

05:00:39.599 --> 05:00:41.099
to prowl around the pavilion.

05:00:41.159 --> 05:00:45.119
There's no things to play with here, he

05:00:45.119 --> 05:00:45.540
complained.

05:00:45.659 --> 05:00:49.560
Use your imagination, Chameleon said

05:00:49.560 --> 05:00:50.580
unsympathetically.

05:00:50.639 --> 05:00:54.119
The prince snorted, flicked his tail at

05:00:54.119 --> 05:00:56.159
the fire pit, and curled up in a small

05:00:56.159 --> 05:00:58.380
ball, with his wings flopped out to

05:00:58.380 --> 05:00:59.580
either side.

05:00:59.639 --> 05:01:01.560
If his intention was to make a point by

05:01:01.560 --> 05:01:04.439
sulking, it didn't last long, because he

05:01:04.439 --> 05:01:05.639
was asleep a few minutes later.

05:01:05.700 --> 05:01:09.540
Peril sat at the edge of the tower and

05:01:09.540 --> 05:01:11.279
looked down at the Sky Palace.

05:01:11.340 --> 05:01:15.299
It still seemed very quiet.

05:01:15.360 --> 05:01:18.000
Usually there were dragons flying from

05:01:18.000 --> 05:01:20.700
tower to tower, or coming in with reports

05:01:20.700 --> 05:01:22.619
or sailing out with messages.

05:01:22.680 --> 05:01:25.020
Usually the palace fluttered with

05:01:25.020 --> 05:01:27.479
activity, and wing beats filled the air.

05:01:27.540 --> 05:01:28.979
But not today.

05:01:29.040 --> 05:01:32.459
Today, an eerie stillness suffused the

05:01:32.459 --> 05:01:32.939
clouds.

05:01:33.000 --> 05:01:35.459
The mountain peaks looked frozen in

05:01:35.459 --> 05:01:35.759
time.

05:01:35.819 --> 05:01:37.979
Where was everyone?

05:01:38.040 --> 05:01:40.680
A light rain began to fall?

05:01:40.740 --> 05:01:44.279
Peril glanced up and saw darker storm

05:01:44.279 --> 05:01:46.680
clouds rolling in, thickening the fog

05:01:46.680 --> 05:01:48.000
around the palace spires.

05:01:48.060 --> 05:01:51.180
The daylight had a smoky green tinge to

05:01:51.180 --> 05:01:53.880
it, as if the sky, too, knew that

05:01:53.880 --> 05:01:54.479
something was wrong.

05:01:54.599 --> 05:01:57.419
Something was unbalanced in the world

05:01:57.419 --> 05:01:57.779
below.

05:01:57.840 --> 05:02:01.860
Even the sky rejects the old queen, she

05:02:01.860 --> 05:02:02.159
thought.

05:02:02.220 --> 05:02:05.099
The sky itself chooses Ruby.

05:02:05.159 --> 05:02:08.040
She shook out her wings, trying to

05:02:08.040 --> 05:02:09.540
dislodge the unfaithful thought.

05:02:09.599 --> 05:02:12.540
How are you feeling, daughter?

05:02:12.599 --> 05:02:13.740
Chameleon asked.

05:02:13.799 --> 05:02:15.599
Pearl glanced at him.

05:02:15.659 --> 05:02:17.340
Wondering whether she should call him

05:02:17.340 --> 05:02:19.919
sore while he was a Sky Wing, or if it

05:02:19.919 --> 05:02:21.540
was all right to keep just one name in

05:02:21.540 --> 05:02:22.139
her head for him.

05:02:22.200 --> 05:02:24.959
He was fiddling with a sheath on his

05:02:24.959 --> 05:02:27.060
chest, as though he were trying to avoid

05:02:27.060 --> 05:02:27.900
her eyes.

05:02:27.959 --> 05:02:30.299
Great, peril said.

05:02:30.419 --> 05:02:33.360
She stretched her wings, her safe

05:02:33.360 --> 05:02:35.759
touchable wings, and thought for a moment

05:02:35.759 --> 05:02:37.919
was she still feeling great?

05:02:37.979 --> 05:02:41.580
She'd been so happy yesterday, but the

05:02:41.580 --> 05:02:44.639
pretending, and the hatred from Ruby, and

05:02:44.639 --> 05:02:47.459
Cliff's drooping wings, and this weird

05:02:47.459 --> 05:02:49.080
feeling of holes in her brain.

05:02:49.139 --> 05:02:51.419
It was all kind of making her happiness

05:02:51.419 --> 05:02:52.680
flicker and dim.

05:02:52.740 --> 05:02:55.439
A little worried, she admitted.

05:02:55.500 --> 05:02:59.279
Don't listen to those other dragons, said

05:02:59.279 --> 05:02:59.939
Chameleon.

05:03:00.000 --> 05:03:02.340
You're essentially the 2nd in command of

05:03:02.340 --> 05:03:02.819
this palace.

05:03:02.880 --> 05:03:05.159
I wish I'd had that much power in my

05:03:05.159 --> 05:03:05.580
tribe.

05:03:05.639 --> 05:03:08.639
I'd have made everybody regret every

05:03:08.639 --> 05:03:11.880
moment of disrespect, every mocking laugh

05:03:11.880 --> 05:03:13.500
and disgusted whisper.

05:03:13.500 --> 05:03:15.599
Why were they mocking you?

05:03:15.659 --> 05:03:16.860
Pearl asked.

05:03:16.919 --> 05:03:19.439
I thought rain wings were all mellow and

05:03:19.439 --> 05:03:22.200
calm and friendly, and sleepy all the

05:03:22.200 --> 05:03:22.439
time.

05:03:22.500 --> 05:03:23.939
Ha!

05:03:24.000 --> 05:03:25.740
Chameleon said bitterly.

05:03:25.799 --> 05:03:28.139
As long as you aren't too different

05:03:28.139 --> 05:03:28.439
sure.

05:03:28.500 --> 05:03:31.380
But I had the one problem the tribe

05:03:31.380 --> 05:03:32.220
couldn't understand.

05:03:32.279 --> 05:03:34.680
I can't change my scales.

05:03:34.740 --> 05:03:37.259
You saw my rain wing color.

05:03:37.319 --> 05:03:38.880
When I'm a rain wing?

05:03:38.939 --> 05:03:39.959
I'm stuck that way.

05:03:40.020 --> 05:03:42.479
The same green all the time.

05:03:42.540 --> 05:03:46.139
No camouflage, no flamboyant emotional

05:03:46.139 --> 05:03:49.380
outbursts, no self absorbed displays of

05:03:49.380 --> 05:03:50.520
clever special effects.

05:03:50.639 --> 05:03:53.639
I could never play their little rain wing

05:03:53.639 --> 05:03:54.000
games.

05:03:54.060 --> 05:03:57.000
Oh, peril said.

05:03:57.060 --> 05:03:59.520
Weren't there any other rain wings like

05:03:59.520 --> 05:04:00.060
you?

05:04:00.119 --> 05:04:02.819
Not in living memory, he said.

05:04:02.880 --> 05:04:05.279
The healers guessed that it was because

05:04:05.279 --> 05:04:06.419
of my sleep problem.

05:04:06.479 --> 05:04:09.240
As myself, I can never sleep for longer

05:04:09.240 --> 05:04:11.819
than a few minutes at a time, an hour at

05:04:11.819 --> 05:04:12.000
most.

05:04:12.060 --> 05:04:14.279
They thought it affected my scale

05:04:14.279 --> 05:04:15.419
shifting abilities.

05:04:15.479 --> 05:04:17.279
But knowing that didn't help.

05:04:17.340 --> 05:04:20.520
Everyone still teased me, and then

05:04:20.520 --> 05:04:21.299
whispered about me.

05:04:21.360 --> 05:04:23.580
And then avoided me.

05:04:23.639 --> 05:04:27.479
Finally, the queen banished me, saying I

05:04:27.479 --> 05:04:30.000
was making everyone uncomfortable, and

05:04:30.000 --> 05:04:32.099
perhaps there was a better tribe for me

05:04:32.099 --> 05:04:34.020
outside the rainforest somewhere.

05:04:34.020 --> 05:04:36.840
Ouch, peril said.

05:04:36.900 --> 05:04:40.860
That seems really unfair to throw you out

05:04:40.860 --> 05:04:42.360
for something you couldn't control?

05:04:42.419 --> 05:04:45.419
Exactly, he said.

05:04:45.479 --> 05:04:48.659
He brooded for a moment, staring down at

05:04:48.659 --> 05:04:50.099
the fog with hooded eyes.

05:04:50.159 --> 05:04:52.919
Then he let out a bark of laughter that

05:04:52.919 --> 05:04:54.779
made Prince Cliff shiver in his sleep.

05:04:54.840 --> 05:04:58.020
The joke's on them though, isn't it?

05:04:58.080 --> 05:04:59.400
What I can do now?

05:04:59.459 --> 05:05:01.439
My shape shifting power.

05:05:01.500 --> 05:05:05.459
It's far more magnificent camouflage than

05:05:05.459 --> 05:05:07.080
anything a mere rain wing could

05:05:07.080 --> 05:05:07.500
accomplish.

05:05:07.560 --> 05:05:10.740
He held out its orange talons to admire

05:05:10.740 --> 05:05:13.020
humming softly with pride.

05:05:13.080 --> 05:05:15.299
Peril studied him out of the corner of

05:05:15.299 --> 05:05:17.459
her eye, wishing she could think of a

05:05:17.459 --> 05:05:19.740
clever sideways way to find out what she

05:05:19.740 --> 05:05:21.959
wanted to know, but that wasn't her

05:05:21.959 --> 05:05:24.540
clever or sideways.

05:05:24.599 --> 05:05:25.979
How does it work?

05:05:26.040 --> 05:05:27.299
She finally asked.

05:05:27.419 --> 05:05:30.659
Flying at the question directly was the

05:05:30.659 --> 05:05:32.040
only way she could think up to attack

05:05:32.040 --> 05:05:32.400
it.

05:05:32.459 --> 05:05:34.919
How did you get your shape shifting

05:05:34.919 --> 05:05:35.159
power?

05:05:35.220 --> 05:05:37.799
He flicked his tail and looked at her

05:05:37.799 --> 05:05:38.279
thoughtfully.

05:05:38.340 --> 05:05:41.279
Peril tried to arrange her face to look

05:05:41.279 --> 05:05:43.740
deeply, immensely trustworthy.

05:05:43.799 --> 05:05:47.459
Not even Scarlet knows this.

05:05:47.520 --> 05:05:48.540
He whispered.

05:05:48.599 --> 05:05:51.419
He glanced back at the prince, who was

05:05:51.419 --> 05:05:52.020
fast asleep.

05:05:52.080 --> 05:05:55.259
A quiver of excitement ran through peril

05:05:55.259 --> 05:05:56.040
a secret.

05:05:56.099 --> 05:05:58.799
She never got to be the only dragon who

05:05:58.799 --> 05:05:59.340
knew a secret.

05:05:59.459 --> 05:06:00.840
Oh.

05:06:00.900 --> 05:06:03.720
I forgot to tell Queen Scarlet about the

05:06:03.720 --> 05:06:05.400
sea wings having an animus.

05:06:05.459 --> 05:06:08.340
Okay, later, I'll have to remember next

05:06:08.340 --> 05:06:08.939
time I see her.

05:06:09.000 --> 05:06:12.479
You can tell me, she whispered back.

05:06:12.540 --> 05:06:14.700
There's no one I would tell anyway.

05:06:14.759 --> 05:06:17.459
Not even Queen Scarlet.

05:06:17.520 --> 05:06:18.599
He asked.

05:06:18.659 --> 05:06:19.860
She shook her head.

05:06:19.919 --> 05:06:22.500
You're my father, she said.

05:06:22.560 --> 05:06:25.500
You changed my scales, and made me safe

05:06:25.500 --> 05:06:26.159
and normal.

05:06:26.279 --> 05:06:29.819
My loyalty is to you first, her second.

05:06:29.880 --> 05:06:32.220
Hmm, he said.

05:06:32.279 --> 05:06:34.020
Very interesting.

05:06:34.080 --> 05:06:37.500
You have a stronger personality than most

05:06:37.500 --> 05:06:40.139
um, most dragons I've met.

05:06:40.259 --> 05:06:42.659
She wondered what he'd been about to

05:06:42.659 --> 05:06:42.900
say.

05:06:42.959 --> 05:06:44.580
Most what?

05:06:44.639 --> 05:06:47.880
That is one of the many things most

05:06:47.880 --> 05:06:50.340
dragons don't like about me, she

05:06:50.340 --> 05:06:50.759
admitted.

05:06:50.819 --> 05:06:53.520
I like it. he said.

05:06:53.580 --> 05:06:55.319
It's something we have in common.

05:06:55.439 --> 05:06:58.139
He touched the metal sheath around his

05:06:58.139 --> 05:07:00.240
chest, fiddling with the lock for a

05:07:00.240 --> 05:07:01.439
moment before it clicked open.

05:07:01.500 --> 05:07:05.279
Inside, the sheath were 2 things, a small

05:07:05.279 --> 05:07:07.200
pouch that seemed to be full of coins or

05:07:07.200 --> 05:07:09.599
jewelry, and a scroll wrapped in a black

05:07:09.599 --> 05:07:10.319
leather binding.

05:07:10.380 --> 05:07:12.840
Chameleon laid them carefully on the

05:07:12.840 --> 05:07:15.540
stone between him and peril, shifting so

05:07:15.540 --> 05:07:17.459
their backs were to cliff, and spreading

05:07:17.459 --> 05:07:19.619
his wings, so the prince wouldn't see the

05:07:19.619 --> 05:07:20.700
objects if he woke up.

05:07:20.759 --> 05:07:23.580
He tapped the pouch first.

05:07:23.639 --> 05:07:25.979
In here are my other shapes.

05:07:26.040 --> 05:07:28.740
Each piece enchanted with someone new.

05:07:28.860 --> 05:07:31.319
All my beautiful faces.

05:07:31.380 --> 05:07:33.419
I can take on and off whenever I want

05:07:33.419 --> 05:07:33.720
to.

05:07:33.779 --> 05:07:35.880
I have one for each tribe.

05:07:35.939 --> 05:07:37.860
You've met one of them before, actually.

05:07:37.919 --> 05:07:40.020
I have?

05:07:40.020 --> 05:07:43.080
Pearl said, her scales prickling.

05:07:43.139 --> 05:07:45.959
Sirius, the ice wing, he said.

05:07:46.020 --> 05:07:47.099
Remember him?

05:07:47.159 --> 05:07:49.680
Queen Scarlet's spy in the talons of

05:07:49.680 --> 05:07:50.220
peace?

05:07:50.220 --> 05:07:52.799
Perfect, because there are so few ice

05:07:52.799 --> 05:07:54.840
wings in the talons, that they never

05:07:54.840 --> 05:07:57.360
figured out how little I knew, or that

05:07:57.360 --> 05:07:58.799
I've never been to the ice kingdom.

05:07:58.919 --> 05:08:02.220
I made him cold and calculating and not

05:08:02.220 --> 05:08:02.939
much of a talker.

05:08:03.060 --> 05:08:05.819
That's when you 1st found out about me.

05:08:05.880 --> 05:08:07.500
Peril realized.

05:08:07.619 --> 05:08:09.900
That conversation about Kestrel.

05:08:09.959 --> 05:08:11.880
You were standing right in front of me.

05:08:11.939 --> 05:08:14.340
Yes, he said.

05:08:14.400 --> 05:08:17.580
Scarlet had sent me to find out if the

05:08:17.580 --> 05:08:19.799
talons knew where those dragonettes went

05:08:19.799 --> 05:08:21.599
the ones who stole her prisoner?

05:08:21.659 --> 05:08:22.979
They didn't, of course.

05:08:23.040 --> 05:08:25.560
The talons have always been remarkably

05:08:25.560 --> 05:08:26.939
useless, in my opinion.

05:08:27.000 --> 05:08:29.580
Apart from gathering the dragonettes of

05:08:29.580 --> 05:08:32.040
the prophecy, and giving serious excuses

05:08:32.040 --> 05:08:33.000
to practice killing.

05:08:33.060 --> 05:08:34.979
He spoke casually.

05:08:35.040 --> 05:08:38.099
But his words sent a chill down Peril's

05:08:38.099 --> 05:08:38.459
spine.

05:08:38.520 --> 05:08:41.939
He was looking for Moon, and Kibli, and

05:08:41.939 --> 05:08:42.360
Winter.

05:08:42.419 --> 05:08:44.639
Would he have killed them if he found

05:08:44.639 --> 05:08:44.880
them?

05:08:44.939 --> 05:08:47.159
Would I kill them now?

05:08:47.220 --> 05:08:49.560
If Queen Scarlet told me to?

05:08:49.619 --> 05:08:53.580
She frowned at her claws, hearing that

05:08:53.580 --> 05:08:54.720
echo in her head again.

05:08:54.779 --> 05:08:57.479
I don't kill dragons anymore.

05:08:57.540 --> 05:08:59.400
But why?

05:08:59.459 --> 05:09:01.020
But why, but why?

05:09:01.080 --> 05:09:03.900
And then I followed you.

05:09:03.959 --> 05:09:06.599
Chameleon went on without noticing her

05:09:06.599 --> 05:09:09.299
distraction, he touched the pouch again

05:09:09.299 --> 05:09:10.020
fondly.

05:09:10.080 --> 05:09:12.479
In my night wing form.

05:09:12.540 --> 05:09:13.919
That one's my favorite.

05:09:13.979 --> 05:09:16.500
I call myself Shapeshifter.

05:09:16.560 --> 05:09:18.840
Isn't that a perfect nightwing name?

05:09:18.959 --> 05:09:21.360
A bit on the nose?

05:09:21.419 --> 05:09:22.619
Peril offered.

05:09:22.680 --> 05:09:24.360
Exactly, he said.

05:09:24.419 --> 05:09:26.459
Like all night wing names.

05:09:26.520 --> 05:09:27.840
I'm quite proud of that shape.

05:09:27.900 --> 05:09:31.380
And then you found me, she said.

05:09:31.439 --> 05:09:34.200
But I still don't understand how you make

05:09:34.200 --> 05:09:35.279
these shapes at all.

05:09:35.340 --> 05:09:39.360
Now he touched the scroll carefully

05:09:39.360 --> 05:09:40.439
reverently.

05:09:40.500 --> 05:09:43.139
This, he whispered.

05:09:43.259 --> 05:09:45.900
It's the strongest magic in the world.

05:09:46.020 --> 05:09:50.099
He undid the binding, and slowly rolled

05:09:50.099 --> 05:09:50.939
the scroll open.

05:09:51.000 --> 05:09:54.659
As he did, Peril could see that the 1st

05:09:54.659 --> 05:09:57.299
3rd of the scroll had riding on it, while

05:09:57.299 --> 05:09:58.500
the rest of the scroll was blank.

05:09:58.560 --> 05:10:01.860
I've never read the whole thing, he

05:10:01.860 --> 05:10:02.159
said.

05:10:02.220 --> 05:10:03.900
I still don't really like reading.

05:10:03.959 --> 05:10:06.540
I had to find someone to teach me to read

05:10:06.540 --> 05:10:08.759
so I could understand the scroll in the

05:10:08.759 --> 05:10:11.400
1st place, but then, I only had to read

05:10:11.400 --> 05:10:13.080
the beginning to realize what it could

05:10:13.080 --> 05:10:13.259
do.

05:10:13.319 --> 05:10:16.860
Chameleon rolled it to the end, where it

05:10:16.860 --> 05:10:18.240
looked like some of the scroll had been

05:10:18.240 --> 05:10:18.659
torn out.

05:10:18.779 --> 05:10:23.040
And then I had to learn how to write, he

05:10:23.040 --> 05:10:24.000
added wryly.

05:10:24.060 --> 05:10:25.439
That was frustrating.

05:10:25.500 --> 05:10:28.799
Peril remembered Osprey teaching her how

05:10:28.799 --> 05:10:31.080
to read and write, although she couldn't

05:10:31.080 --> 05:10:33.360
hold a scroll or any writing instrument

05:10:33.360 --> 05:10:35.580
so it didn't do her very much good.

05:10:35.639 --> 05:10:38.040
She could read street signs and scrape

05:10:38.040 --> 05:10:39.959
out messages in the sand if necessary.

05:10:40.020 --> 05:10:40.919
That was about it.

05:10:40.979 --> 05:10:43.560
Oh, she realized.

05:10:43.619 --> 05:10:45.659
That can all be different now.

05:10:45.720 --> 05:10:48.779
Without fire scales, I could read every

05:10:48.779 --> 05:10:50.939
scroll in the world if I want to.

05:10:51.000 --> 05:10:53.759
That cheered her up quite a lot.

05:10:53.819 --> 05:10:56.639
She leaned toward the scroll, giving her

05:10:56.639 --> 05:10:58.020
father her eager attention.

05:10:58.080 --> 05:11:02.220
I write my enchantment here, Chameleon

05:11:02.220 --> 05:11:04.259
said, brushing the paper with his claw.

05:11:04.319 --> 05:11:07.080
I describe the shape I want to shift into

05:11:07.080 --> 05:11:09.779
riding the magic into that piece of paper

05:11:09.779 --> 05:11:12.119
then I tear off that part of the scroll

05:11:12.119 --> 05:11:15.240
and hide it in something, usually an item

05:11:15.240 --> 05:11:17.520
of jewelry, like a necklace or bracelet.

05:11:17.520 --> 05:11:20.400
Or an ear, Pearl said.

05:11:20.459 --> 05:11:22.740
Suddenly remembering a disembodied head

05:11:22.740 --> 05:11:24.119
changing shape in front of her.

05:11:24.180 --> 05:11:26.040
Where was that?

05:11:26.099 --> 05:11:30.060
Uh, yes, he said.

05:11:30.119 --> 05:11:31.740
Only that once, though.

05:11:31.799 --> 05:11:33.360
I don't use this very often.

05:11:33.419 --> 05:11:35.759
I've told Queen Scarlet that I have a

05:11:35.759 --> 05:11:38.459
limited animus power to transform dragons

05:11:38.459 --> 05:11:40.860
and that it's dangerous for me to do it

05:11:40.860 --> 05:11:41.099
very much.

05:11:41.159 --> 05:11:43.020
I don't want her to know about the

05:11:43.020 --> 05:11:43.380
scroll.

05:11:43.439 --> 05:11:45.720
Why not?

05:11:45.779 --> 05:11:46.919
Peril asked.

05:11:46.979 --> 05:11:49.439
He looked at her in alarm, and she

05:11:49.439 --> 05:11:52.139
quickly added, don't worry, I still won't

05:11:52.139 --> 05:11:52.560
tell her.

05:11:52.619 --> 05:11:55.139
But why would you help her as much as you

05:11:55.139 --> 05:11:56.700
do and not tell her everything.

05:11:56.759 --> 05:11:58.919
If she knew about this.

05:11:58.979 --> 05:12:00.299
He said.

05:12:00.360 --> 05:12:01.860
She would take it away from me.

05:12:01.919 --> 05:12:04.799
He started to roll up the scroll again

05:12:04.799 --> 05:12:07.619
and once she didn't need me anymore.

05:12:07.740 --> 05:12:08.939
She would probably kill me.

05:12:09.000 --> 05:12:12.479
Besides, I want to be in charge of what

05:12:12.479 --> 05:12:13.560
this scroll does.

05:12:13.619 --> 05:12:14.580
It's mine.

05:12:14.700 --> 05:12:17.759
If Scarlet knew I had unlimited power.

05:12:17.819 --> 05:12:19.919
She'd make me do much more terrible

05:12:19.919 --> 05:12:21.720
things than anything I've done so far.

05:12:21.779 --> 05:12:24.720
He stopped and looked at peril.

05:12:24.779 --> 05:12:27.479
I'm not an evil dragon peril.

05:12:27.540 --> 05:12:30.360
I like the security of having a queen who

05:12:30.360 --> 05:12:32.220
will pay me handsomely for my services

05:12:32.220 --> 05:12:35.220
and I love the luxury of so much

05:12:35.220 --> 05:12:35.880
treasure.

05:12:35.939 --> 05:12:38.880
But I'm not going to give anyone all this

05:12:38.880 --> 05:12:41.520
power, especially not Queen Scarlet.

05:12:41.580 --> 05:12:43.439
I am much too smart for that.

05:12:43.500 --> 05:12:46.439
Oh, Pearl said.

05:12:46.500 --> 05:12:48.119
Her mind was spinning a little.

05:12:48.180 --> 05:12:50.580
Was he implying that peril wasn't that

05:12:50.580 --> 05:12:50.880
smart?

05:12:50.939 --> 05:12:53.880
Would she have given Scarlet that scroll

05:12:53.880 --> 05:12:54.959
without even thinking about it?

05:12:55.020 --> 05:12:57.720
Wasn't that what loyalty was about?

05:12:57.779 --> 05:13:00.119
And if he didn't trust Scarlet

05:13:00.119 --> 05:13:00.599
completely?

05:13:00.659 --> 05:13:02.040
Why help her at all?

05:13:02.099 --> 05:13:04.680
Have you done anything else with a

05:13:04.680 --> 05:13:05.040
scroll?

05:13:05.099 --> 05:13:05.880
she asked.

05:13:05.939 --> 05:13:09.419
I mean, Couldn't you use it to make your

05:13:09.419 --> 05:13:11.700
own treasure somehow, instead of waiting

05:13:11.700 --> 05:13:13.020
for Scarlet to pay you?

05:13:13.080 --> 05:13:16.979
Chameleon opened his mouth, closed it, and

05:13:16.979 --> 05:13:17.759
blinked at her for a moment.

05:13:17.819 --> 05:13:22.740
I suppose I could, he said slowly.

05:13:22.799 --> 05:13:25.740
Scarlet hired me before I'd gotten very

05:13:25.740 --> 05:13:27.000
far with using the scroll.

05:13:27.060 --> 05:13:30.060
She caught me transforming, and gave me

05:13:30.060 --> 05:13:32.580
the option of explaining how I did it, or

05:13:32.580 --> 05:13:33.419
coming to work for her.

05:13:33.479 --> 05:13:37.680
I chose option B, obviously, and I

05:13:37.680 --> 05:13:39.540
haven't wanted to do anything risky that

05:13:39.540 --> 05:13:40.439
she might find out about.

05:13:40.560 --> 05:13:42.959
I have a very nice life, though.

05:13:43.080 --> 05:13:45.840
He said quickly, and so can you.

05:13:45.900 --> 05:13:49.439
Once this kingdom is all sorted out, we'll

05:13:49.439 --> 05:13:51.840
be her right claw dragons, and we'll be

05:13:51.840 --> 05:13:52.080
together.

05:13:52.139 --> 05:13:55.080
Maybe you can help me come up with clever

05:13:55.080 --> 05:13:56.040
uses for the scroll.

05:13:56.099 --> 05:13:59.459
It'll be nice to have family at last.

05:13:59.520 --> 05:14:02.759
Yes, peril agreed.

05:14:02.759 --> 05:14:04.020
Family.

05:14:04.080 --> 05:14:06.360
That sounded amazing, actually.

05:14:06.419 --> 05:14:09.240
She'd barely had a chance to meet Kestrel

05:14:09.240 --> 05:14:10.319
before her mother died.

05:14:10.380 --> 05:14:12.479
And if there were any other dragons

05:14:12.479 --> 05:14:15.000
related to her in the Sky Palace, they'd

05:14:15.000 --> 05:14:16.259
never introduced themselves.

05:14:16.319 --> 05:14:19.200
But something new was starting to bother

05:14:19.200 --> 05:14:19.439
her.

05:14:19.500 --> 05:14:23.580
Wait, she said, if you're the one who's

05:14:23.580 --> 05:14:25.979
been helping Queen Scarlet all along.

05:14:26.040 --> 05:14:27.779
Does that mean you're the one who put

05:14:27.779 --> 05:14:29.099
Kinkaju in the hospital?

05:14:29.159 --> 05:14:31.860
Chameleon stared at her for a long

05:14:31.860 --> 05:14:32.220
moment.

05:14:32.340 --> 05:14:35.400
The muscles in his jaw tensing and moving

05:14:35.400 --> 05:14:37.500
like little snakes crawling over one

05:14:37.500 --> 05:14:37.740
another.

05:14:37.799 --> 05:14:40.319
He picked up the scroll and the pouch

05:14:40.319 --> 05:14:42.419
locking them back in his chest sheath

05:14:42.419 --> 05:14:43.139
before answering.

05:14:43.200 --> 05:14:46.979
You mean that rain wing who was traveling

05:14:46.979 --> 05:14:48.240
with the ice wing prince?

05:14:48.299 --> 05:14:49.319
He said finally.

05:14:49.380 --> 05:14:50.520
She's not dead.

05:14:50.580 --> 05:14:53.700
You actually were trying to kill her?

05:14:53.759 --> 05:14:55.740
Pearl said, appalled.

05:14:55.799 --> 05:14:56.759
Really?

05:14:56.819 --> 05:14:58.680
She's just a dragonette.

05:14:58.740 --> 05:15:02.340
She's a rain wing, he hissed.

05:15:02.400 --> 05:15:04.860
She'd laugh at me just as much as any of

05:15:04.860 --> 05:15:07.259
her tribe, if she'd met me before I found

05:15:07.259 --> 05:15:08.220
my power.

05:15:08.279 --> 05:15:11.459
Wow, Peril said.

05:15:11.520 --> 05:15:14.099
She tried to picture the tiny, brightly

05:15:14.099 --> 05:15:15.119
colored rain wing.

05:15:15.180 --> 05:15:17.580
I've never met anyone who hated rain

05:15:17.580 --> 05:15:18.299
wings before.

05:15:18.360 --> 05:15:20.639
They're so inoffensive.

05:15:20.700 --> 05:15:23.759
It's like hating caterpillars.

05:15:23.819 --> 05:15:26.700
I'm not terribly fond of caterpillars

05:15:26.700 --> 05:15:26.939
either.

05:15:27.060 --> 05:15:28.560
Chameleon observed.

05:15:28.619 --> 05:15:30.360
Nasty crawly things.

05:15:30.419 --> 05:15:33.900
Of all dragons, peril thought.

05:15:33.900 --> 05:15:35.939
I should be the one who can understand

05:15:35.939 --> 05:15:39.180
fury and vengeance and wanting to lash

05:15:39.180 --> 05:15:40.560
out whenever someone hurts me.

05:15:40.619 --> 05:15:42.060
He's my father.

05:15:42.119 --> 05:15:44.099
And she's a dragonette.

05:15:44.159 --> 05:15:44.700
I don't even know.

05:15:44.759 --> 05:15:46.979
I should be on his side.

05:15:47.040 --> 05:15:51.000
But still, it seemed as brutal and

05:15:51.000 --> 05:15:52.979
unnecessary as the idea of hurting the

05:15:52.979 --> 05:15:54.360
little Sky Wing Prince.

05:15:54.419 --> 05:15:57.779
She glanced over her shoulder at Cliff, or

05:15:57.779 --> 05:15:59.939
rather, at the space where Cliff used to

05:15:59.939 --> 05:16:03.240
be, she whirled around, her eyes tearing

05:16:03.240 --> 05:16:05.520
apart the empty pavilion, but there was

05:16:05.520 --> 05:16:06.000
no mistake.

05:16:06.060 --> 05:16:09.000
The Skywing Prince, was gone.

05:16:09.119 --> 05:16:13.680
Chapter 16.

05:16:13.860 --> 05:16:15.900
Cliff?

05:16:15.959 --> 05:16:17.340
Peril cried.

05:16:17.400 --> 05:16:18.360
Cliff.

05:16:18.419 --> 05:16:20.819
Chameleon flared his wings with a

05:16:20.819 --> 05:16:21.840
horrified expression.

05:16:21.900 --> 05:16:23.459
Where did he go?

05:16:23.520 --> 05:16:26.340
Peril ran to the opposite edge of the

05:16:26.340 --> 05:16:26.700
tower.

05:16:26.759 --> 05:16:28.860
Had he rolled off in his sleep?

05:16:28.919 --> 05:16:31.259
It was a long, long way down.

05:16:31.380 --> 05:16:33.599
Wouldn't he have woken up and cried out?

05:16:33.659 --> 05:16:35.040
Wouldn't they have heard him?

05:16:35.099 --> 05:16:37.979
She frantically searched the slick wet

05:16:37.979 --> 05:16:40.619
rocks and rooftops below for a broken red

05:16:40.619 --> 05:16:40.979
figure.

05:16:41.040 --> 05:16:44.819
And then, through a break in the fog, she

05:16:44.819 --> 05:16:47.159
saw a tiny flapping shape struggling in

05:16:47.159 --> 05:16:47.819
the rain.

05:16:48.060 --> 05:16:50.639
He can fly, she cried.

05:16:50.759 --> 05:16:54.900
That little liar, Chameleon yelled, after

05:16:54.900 --> 05:16:55.439
him.

05:16:55.500 --> 05:16:57.959
He leaped from the tower and plummeted

05:16:57.959 --> 05:16:58.860
toward the dragonette.

05:16:58.979 --> 05:17:01.919
You know, Peril called, catching up to

05:17:01.919 --> 05:17:02.159
him.

05:17:02.220 --> 05:17:04.919
I thought I remembered that Skywing

05:17:04.919 --> 05:17:06.479
Dragonettes could fly pretty young.

05:17:06.540 --> 05:17:08.880
That's so funny that Scarlet didn't know

05:17:08.880 --> 05:17:11.040
that because she avoids dragonettes like

05:17:11.040 --> 05:17:11.520
the plague.

05:17:11.580 --> 05:17:14.759
Rain pelted her wings and snout and

05:17:14.759 --> 05:17:17.040
scales, falling harder and harder every

05:17:17.040 --> 05:17:17.340
moment.

05:17:17.400 --> 05:17:20.159
Shut up and catch him.

05:17:20.220 --> 05:17:21.659
Chameleon shouted.

05:17:21.720 --> 05:17:23.639
Nearly drowned out by a crack of

05:17:23.639 --> 05:17:24.060
thunder.

05:17:24.119 --> 05:17:27.360
Or we lose the palace, and Scarlet kills

05:17:27.360 --> 05:17:27.659
us both.

05:17:27.779 --> 05:17:31.439
She wouldn't dare, Parel thought.

05:17:31.500 --> 05:17:33.419
Well, all right.

05:17:33.479 --> 05:17:35.580
She might dare, but she can't.

05:17:35.639 --> 05:17:37.740
Not if I take off this necklace and use

05:17:37.740 --> 05:17:38.759
my fire scales again.

05:17:38.819 --> 05:17:42.299
The locket thumped against her chest, and

05:17:42.299 --> 05:17:44.639
Perel realized it must have a scrap of

05:17:44.639 --> 05:17:47.220
that scroll inside of it, enchanted to

05:17:47.220 --> 05:17:47.700
make her normal.

05:17:47.759 --> 05:17:50.220
She hadn't seen her father write it.

05:17:50.279 --> 05:17:54.180
In fact, it had been all ready for her, so

05:17:54.180 --> 05:17:55.500
he must have written it before they even

05:17:55.500 --> 05:17:55.860
met.

05:17:55.919 --> 05:17:58.259
Because he loves me.

05:17:58.319 --> 05:18:01.080
Because he understood what it's like to

05:18:01.080 --> 05:18:03.540
be different, and he predicted my wish to

05:18:03.540 --> 05:18:03.959
be normal.

05:18:04.020 --> 05:18:06.479
There was something though.

05:18:06.540 --> 05:18:09.000
Something that still felt wrong.

05:18:09.060 --> 05:18:12.540
Cliff looked over his shoulder and saw

05:18:12.540 --> 05:18:14.099
the 2 dragons hurtling toward him.

05:18:14.099 --> 05:18:17.099
With a terrified squeak, he flung himself

05:18:17.099 --> 05:18:18.240
through the nearest window and

05:18:18.240 --> 05:18:18.720
disappeared.

05:18:18.779 --> 05:18:22.080
Worse luck, it was a window big enough

05:18:22.080 --> 05:18:24.779
for a year old dragonette, but too small

05:18:24.779 --> 05:18:27.240
for peril or her father's sky wing

05:18:27.240 --> 05:18:27.720
shape.

05:18:27.959 --> 05:18:30.360
Chameleon roared in frustration.

05:18:30.419 --> 05:18:33.240
You know the palace, he shouted at

05:18:33.240 --> 05:18:33.720
peril.

05:18:33.779 --> 05:18:34.860
How do we get in there?

05:18:34.919 --> 05:18:37.439
He thumped the stone wall with his tail.

05:18:37.500 --> 05:18:40.500
Peril wiped rain from her eyes and looked

05:18:40.500 --> 05:18:40.860
around.

05:18:40.919 --> 05:18:43.919
The window was in a covered rampart that

05:18:43.919 --> 05:18:46.439
led to the central keep of the palace, the

05:18:46.439 --> 05:18:48.479
keep where the throne room, the great

05:18:48.479 --> 05:18:50.939
hall, and Ruby's prison were.

05:18:51.060 --> 05:18:54.540
Come on, she said, beating her wings.

05:18:54.599 --> 05:18:56.700
One option was going through the open

05:18:56.700 --> 05:18:59.040
wall of the throne room, but if Queen

05:18:59.040 --> 05:19:00.900
Scarlet was in there, things would get

05:19:00.900 --> 05:19:01.619
ugly fast.

05:19:01.680 --> 05:19:04.380
A better choice was to fly to the top of

05:19:04.380 --> 05:19:06.599
the keep and enter through the open roof

05:19:06.599 --> 05:19:08.819
like she had done once to rescue

05:19:08.819 --> 05:19:09.419
Kestrel.

05:19:09.540 --> 05:19:11.220
She shook her head hard.

05:19:11.279 --> 05:19:13.560
Who did I do that with?

05:19:13.619 --> 05:19:15.779
Why is it all fuzzy?

05:19:15.840 --> 05:19:19.439
As they soared up the cliffside, peril

05:19:19.439 --> 05:19:22.020
had a dizzying sense of déjà vu, a

05:19:22.020 --> 05:19:25.500
feeling of wild freedom, terror, and hope

05:19:25.500 --> 05:19:27.060
that didn't match the current situation

05:19:27.060 --> 05:19:27.779
at all.

05:19:27.840 --> 05:19:31.560
She glanced behind her and realized she

05:19:31.560 --> 05:19:33.360
was expecting to see someone other than

05:19:33.360 --> 05:19:33.779
her father.

05:19:33.840 --> 05:19:35.459
Who?

05:19:35.520 --> 05:19:39.419
A moment later, they reached the top and

05:19:39.419 --> 05:19:41.279
dove through the hole into the great hall

05:19:41.279 --> 05:19:44.340
which was as eerie and deserted as the

05:19:44.340 --> 05:19:47.040
rest of the palace, Peril saw one or 2

05:19:47.040 --> 05:19:49.139
snouts poke out curiously at the sound of

05:19:49.139 --> 05:19:51.060
her wing beats, and then vanish in a

05:19:51.060 --> 05:19:51.299
hurry.

05:19:51.419 --> 05:19:54.479
A guard stood listlessly by the throne

05:19:54.479 --> 05:19:56.459
room, but she didn't even look up as

05:19:56.459 --> 05:19:57.299
peril flew by.

05:19:57.360 --> 05:20:00.060
Down at the bottom of the hall.

05:20:00.119 --> 05:20:02.159
Ruby was trapped below a grate of metal

05:20:02.159 --> 05:20:04.919
bars in the lowliest prison Scarlet had

05:20:04.919 --> 05:20:06.779
been able to come up with for her least

05:20:06.779 --> 05:20:07.979
favorite prisoners.

05:20:08.040 --> 05:20:11.759
I guess someone fixed the great, Pearl

05:20:11.759 --> 05:20:13.799
thought, remembering her own claws

05:20:13.799 --> 05:20:15.540
burning through those very bars.

05:20:15.599 --> 05:20:18.479
Two sky wings stood beside the grate

05:20:18.479 --> 05:20:20.819
looking less like guards and more like

05:20:20.819 --> 05:20:21.479
guardians.

05:20:21.540 --> 05:20:23.819
They were staring up at the commotion of

05:20:23.819 --> 05:20:25.799
peril and chameleon diving toward them

05:20:25.799 --> 05:20:28.020
and so they didn't see the small red

05:20:28.020 --> 05:20:30.119
shape that darted into the room from a

05:20:30.119 --> 05:20:30.840
hall behind them.

05:20:30.900 --> 05:20:33.599
Prince Cliff reached the prison bars

05:20:33.599 --> 05:20:34.619
before peril did.

05:20:34.680 --> 05:20:37.259
He threw himself on top of the grate and

05:20:37.259 --> 05:20:39.419
reached through, clasping one of his

05:20:39.419 --> 05:20:41.099
mother's talons in both of his.

05:20:41.099 --> 05:20:43.560
Cliff, Ruby cried.

05:20:43.619 --> 05:20:44.459
Get back.

05:20:44.580 --> 05:20:47.700
And suddenly, a moment before peril

05:20:47.700 --> 05:20:50.279
touched down on the stone floor, Ruby

05:20:50.279 --> 05:20:52.619
came surging out of her cell, flinging

05:20:52.619 --> 05:20:54.419
aside the crisscrossed bars as if they

05:20:54.419 --> 05:20:54.720
were nothing.

05:20:54.840 --> 05:20:59.880
As if it wasn't actually locked, or never

05:20:59.880 --> 05:21:01.020
really fixed at all.

05:21:01.080 --> 05:21:03.840
That's it, peril thought.

05:21:03.900 --> 05:21:06.180
Ruby wouldn't have wanted a prison like

05:21:06.180 --> 05:21:06.720
that anyway.

05:21:06.840 --> 05:21:09.240
And the Skywings who locked her in were

05:21:09.240 --> 05:21:09.840
loyal to her.

05:21:09.900 --> 05:21:13.080
They only pretended to do it, enough to

05:21:13.080 --> 05:21:13.979
make Scarlet believe it.

05:21:14.040 --> 05:21:16.139
She isn't giving up.

05:21:16.200 --> 05:21:18.720
She's not the mouse her mother thinks she

05:21:18.720 --> 05:21:18.900
is.

05:21:18.959 --> 05:21:21.540
What else is Scarlet wrong about?

05:21:21.599 --> 05:21:25.020
The 2 guards threw their wings open

05:21:25.020 --> 05:21:28.080
facing peril in battle positions as Ruby

05:21:28.080 --> 05:21:30.240
cleared the cell in one leap and called

05:21:30.240 --> 05:21:32.220
her son up in her arms.

05:21:32.279 --> 05:21:35.040
I knew you could do it, she said to him

05:21:35.040 --> 05:21:37.380
you clever, clever, clever little

05:21:37.380 --> 05:21:38.040
moonbeam.

05:21:38.099 --> 05:21:42.240
I'm not a moonbeam, he protested

05:21:42.240 --> 05:21:43.860
snuggling into her chest.

05:21:43.919 --> 05:21:47.880
Today, I'm a super secret self agent

05:21:47.880 --> 05:21:49.619
flyer, hero of the world.

05:21:49.740 --> 05:21:53.099
Yes, you are, she said.

05:21:53.159 --> 05:21:56.279
A deafening roar suddenly shook the

05:21:56.279 --> 05:21:56.939
entire hall.

05:21:57.000 --> 05:21:59.939
Peril pressed her talons over her ears

05:21:59.939 --> 05:22:02.220
unconsciously trying to make herself as

05:22:02.220 --> 05:22:03.180
small as possible.

05:22:03.240 --> 05:22:05.759
This was a familiar war.

05:22:05.819 --> 05:22:09.060
A roar that always heralded shouting

05:22:09.060 --> 05:22:11.400
scorn, and severe punishments.

05:22:11.459 --> 05:22:13.979
Queen Scarlet could never hit her, of

05:22:13.979 --> 05:22:16.139
course, but she'd found plenty of other

05:22:16.139 --> 05:22:18.299
ways to make peril's life miserable.

05:22:18.360 --> 05:22:21.180
The sky wing queen seemed to arrive from

05:22:21.180 --> 05:22:23.580
everywhere at once, her flapping orange

05:22:23.580 --> 05:22:25.979
wings filling peril's whole field of

05:22:25.979 --> 05:22:26.220
vision.

05:22:26.279 --> 05:22:29.220
No, Scarlet shrieked.

05:22:29.279 --> 05:22:31.680
Hurtling past the guards and slamming

05:22:31.680 --> 05:22:33.659
straight into Ruby and Cliff.

05:22:33.720 --> 05:22:35.639
The 3 of them tumbled and crashed into

05:22:35.639 --> 05:22:37.860
the back wall, and before Ruby could

05:22:37.860 --> 05:22:40.020
stand up again, Scarlet grabbed her neck

05:22:40.020 --> 05:22:41.759
and pinned her against the stone.

05:22:41.819 --> 05:22:44.459
Cliff scrambled under his mother's wing

05:22:44.459 --> 05:22:46.680
and she tightened it around him, glaring

05:22:46.680 --> 05:22:47.340
at Scarlet.

05:22:47.400 --> 05:22:51.299
You think you're so smart, pathetic

05:22:51.299 --> 05:22:53.220
daughter, Scarlet hissed.

05:22:53.279 --> 05:22:55.979
But your love for this dragonette is a

05:22:55.979 --> 05:22:56.340
weakness.

05:22:56.400 --> 05:22:58.139
After I kill you.

05:22:58.200 --> 05:23:00.240
Do you want to know what I'm going to do

05:23:00.240 --> 05:23:00.720
to him?

05:23:00.779 --> 05:23:03.360
I'm going to make him fear me.

05:23:03.419 --> 05:23:07.319
I'm going to make him so loyal to me that

05:23:07.319 --> 05:23:08.459
he'll forget your name.

05:23:08.520 --> 05:23:11.279
He'll obey my every command.

05:23:11.340 --> 05:23:15.479
Will not, Cliff said defiantly.

05:23:15.540 --> 05:23:17.099
Scarlet ignored him.

05:23:17.159 --> 05:23:20.700
I'll use him, until he becomes a dragon

05:23:20.700 --> 05:23:21.779
you wouldn't recognize.

05:23:21.840 --> 05:23:25.139
By the time I'm done with him, he'd kill

05:23:25.139 --> 05:23:27.060
you with his own talons if I tell him

05:23:27.060 --> 05:23:27.419
to.

05:23:27.540 --> 05:23:30.959
Will not, Cliff said again.

05:23:31.020 --> 05:23:33.299
Sounding both outraged and scared.

05:23:33.360 --> 05:23:35.159
Would never.

05:23:35.279 --> 05:23:39.240
He'll be my adorable little weapon. said

05:23:39.240 --> 05:23:41.580
Scarlet, and he'll forget all about you.

05:23:41.700 --> 05:23:44.459
I will be his everything.

05:23:44.520 --> 05:23:48.419
I'm the only one who cares about you.

05:23:48.479 --> 05:23:52.200
No one will ever love you except me.

05:23:52.259 --> 05:23:56.520
You'll always be a monster to everyone

05:23:56.520 --> 05:23:57.060
else.

05:23:57.119 --> 05:24:01.020
Scarlet's words rang louder and louder in

05:24:01.020 --> 05:24:03.119
peril's head, what she was describing.

05:24:03.180 --> 05:24:06.360
That's what she did to me.

05:24:06.419 --> 05:24:08.939
She made me obedient.

05:24:09.000 --> 05:24:11.099
She made me loyal to her.

05:24:11.159 --> 05:24:14.040
She made me think I had no choice.

05:24:14.099 --> 05:24:15.900
But I do.

05:24:15.959 --> 05:24:19.259
Stop, peril shouted.

05:24:19.319 --> 05:24:20.700
She stepped forward.

05:24:20.759 --> 05:24:23.700
And for a moment, the guards wavered, as

05:24:23.700 --> 05:24:25.200
if wondering whether this was the right

05:24:25.200 --> 05:24:27.299
moment to sacrifice themselves on her

05:24:27.299 --> 05:24:28.860
burning scales.

05:24:28.919 --> 05:24:30.840
She stepped forward again, and they

05:24:30.840 --> 05:24:33.000
parted before her, leaving her a clear

05:24:33.000 --> 05:24:34.740
path to the tangle of royal family

05:24:34.740 --> 05:24:35.220
members.

05:24:35.279 --> 05:24:38.700
Queen Scarlet glowered at peril with

05:24:38.700 --> 05:24:40.080
narrow yellow eyes.

05:24:40.139 --> 05:24:41.700
What did you say?

05:24:41.759 --> 05:24:45.659
I won't let you hurt Cliff, Pearl said.

05:24:45.779 --> 05:24:48.419
I won't let you do any of that to him

05:24:48.419 --> 05:24:48.779
either.

05:24:48.840 --> 05:24:50.220
It's not right.

05:24:50.279 --> 05:24:52.080
He's not your toy.

05:24:52.139 --> 05:24:54.419
And if you can't earn a dragon's loyalty

05:24:54.419 --> 05:24:56.819
by being a good queen, then you don't

05:24:56.819 --> 05:24:57.479
deserve it at all.

05:24:57.540 --> 05:25:00.299
She reached for the black chain around

05:25:00.299 --> 05:25:03.419
her neck and saw Scarlet's eyes widened.

05:25:03.479 --> 05:25:05.459
No, Chameleon cried.

05:25:05.520 --> 05:25:07.259
Don't take that off.

05:25:07.319 --> 05:25:09.060
Three moons.

05:25:09.119 --> 05:25:11.279
I am under a spell.

05:25:11.340 --> 05:25:14.459
It hit peril with the force of a 1000

05:25:14.459 --> 05:25:15.180
sons.

05:25:15.240 --> 05:25:16.919
There's something else in the

05:25:16.919 --> 05:25:17.520
enchantment.

05:25:17.580 --> 05:25:18.959
Ruby was right.

05:25:19.020 --> 05:25:21.000
My father betrayed me.

05:25:21.119 --> 05:25:24.000
Peril ripped the necklace over her head

05:25:24.000 --> 05:25:27.060
and dropped it, just as the metal began

05:25:27.060 --> 05:25:27.900
to sizzle.

05:25:27.959 --> 05:25:32.220
Chapter 17.

05:25:32.459 --> 05:25:35.340
Everything came rushing back.

05:25:35.400 --> 05:25:38.939
Clay, clay, clay, clay.

05:25:39.000 --> 05:25:40.319
Peril's heart sang.

05:25:40.380 --> 05:25:42.299
How could she have forgotten about him?

05:25:42.360 --> 05:25:44.279
How could any spell do that?

05:25:44.340 --> 05:25:47.159
She looked around at the circle of

05:25:47.159 --> 05:25:49.860
watching Skywings, orange and red heads

05:25:49.860 --> 05:25:52.560
peering over the balconies and wing beats

05:25:52.560 --> 05:25:53.459
bringing in more.

05:25:53.520 --> 05:25:56.040
Ruby and Cliff trapped under Scarlet's

05:25:56.040 --> 05:25:58.439
claws, the guards watching her warily.

05:25:58.500 --> 05:26:01.380
Is this what I become without him?

05:26:01.439 --> 05:26:03.900
I go right back to being a monster?

05:26:04.020 --> 05:26:06.419
She held out her talons.

05:26:06.479 --> 05:26:09.240
Wisps of smoke were starting to rise from

05:26:09.240 --> 05:26:09.659
them again.

05:26:09.720 --> 05:26:13.020
The fire skills aren't what make me

05:26:13.020 --> 05:26:13.439
dangerous.

05:26:13.500 --> 05:26:15.119
Even without them.

05:26:15.180 --> 05:26:18.299
I was as bad as ever, because I was

05:26:18.299 --> 05:26:19.380
willing to follow her.

05:26:19.439 --> 05:26:23.459
Pearl lowered her claws and advanced on

05:26:23.459 --> 05:26:24.119
Scarlet.

05:26:24.180 --> 05:26:27.720
You stay away from me, Scarlet Hissed.

05:26:27.779 --> 05:26:28.680
Get back.

05:26:28.740 --> 05:26:29.639
Do you hear me?

05:26:29.700 --> 05:26:31.560
I'm your queen, remember?

05:26:31.619 --> 05:26:33.119
You are my champion.

05:26:33.180 --> 05:26:35.580
You do what I tell you to do.

05:26:35.639 --> 05:26:37.439
Not anymore.

05:26:37.500 --> 05:26:39.419
Peril said.

05:26:39.479 --> 05:26:42.299
She reached toward the scarred ex queen

05:26:42.299 --> 05:26:44.040
and Scarlet leaped off Ruby with a

05:26:44.040 --> 05:26:44.340
shriek.

05:26:44.459 --> 05:26:47.099
Her orange wings flailed in the air as

05:26:47.099 --> 05:26:48.060
she backed away from peril.

05:26:48.119 --> 05:26:51.360
Have you ever wondered what it felt

05:26:51.360 --> 05:26:51.659
like?

05:26:51.720 --> 05:26:52.979
Peril said.

05:26:53.099 --> 05:26:55.799
What you made me do to all those

05:26:55.799 --> 05:26:56.580
dragons?

05:26:56.639 --> 05:26:58.619
Because it's over now.

05:26:58.680 --> 05:27:01.259
You are the last dragon I will ever

05:27:01.259 --> 05:27:01.619
kill.

05:27:01.740 --> 05:27:04.560
Wait, Ruby said suddenly.

05:27:04.619 --> 05:27:06.299
Peril, stop.

05:27:06.360 --> 05:27:07.680
Stop.

05:27:07.740 --> 05:27:10.139
Scarlet was so close.

05:27:10.200 --> 05:27:12.779
And Perel finally had the courage to do

05:27:12.779 --> 05:27:14.880
what she should have done a long time ago

05:27:14.880 --> 05:27:17.880
and this was the right moment with

05:27:17.880 --> 05:27:19.500
everyone watching to cheer her on.

05:27:19.560 --> 05:27:22.259
But Ruby was her new queen.

05:27:22.319 --> 05:27:24.959
And if Pearl wanted to prove she could be

05:27:24.959 --> 05:27:27.900
trusted, if she could ever be trusted

05:27:27.900 --> 05:27:28.200
again.

05:27:28.259 --> 05:27:30.779
She should start by listening to her.

05:27:30.840 --> 05:27:32.759
She stopped.

05:27:32.819 --> 05:27:35.459
Keeping her wings spread so Scarlet

05:27:35.459 --> 05:27:36.000
couldn't escape.

05:27:36.060 --> 05:27:39.840
Yes, Your Majesty, she said to Ruby.

05:27:39.900 --> 05:27:43.860
There was a stunned little pause, dappled

05:27:43.860 --> 05:27:46.619
with growls and hisses from Scarlet, and

05:27:46.619 --> 05:27:47.880
then Ruby collected herself.

05:27:47.939 --> 05:27:50.939
Don't kill her, Ruby said.

05:27:51.000 --> 05:27:52.860
You shouldn't have to.

05:27:52.919 --> 05:27:55.380
This is my fight.

05:27:55.439 --> 05:27:59.580
She gently moved Cliff behind her, tucking

05:27:59.580 --> 05:28:01.619
him back against the wall, and then stood

05:28:01.619 --> 05:28:02.159
up tall.

05:28:02.279 --> 05:28:06.599
Queen Scarlet of the Sky Wings, I hereby

05:28:06.599 --> 05:28:09.180
challenge you to a duel for throne and

05:28:09.180 --> 05:28:09.720
kingdom.

05:28:09.779 --> 05:28:13.080
A gasp scattered around the hall like

05:28:13.080 --> 05:28:14.400
leaves in a windstorm.

05:28:14.459 --> 05:28:17.639
You don't have to do that, said one of

05:28:17.639 --> 05:28:19.979
the nearby guards, very bravely peril

05:28:19.979 --> 05:28:20.340
thought.

05:28:20.400 --> 05:28:23.159
It meant he'd be the 1st one in flames if

05:28:23.159 --> 05:28:24.119
Scarlet ended up winning.

05:28:24.180 --> 05:28:27.419
You are the queen we want, Queen Ruby.

05:28:27.479 --> 05:28:29.279
Just order us to kill her for you.

05:28:29.340 --> 05:28:32.159
Or me, Parel offered.

05:28:32.279 --> 05:28:33.720
Order me to do it.

05:28:33.779 --> 05:28:35.819
Ruby shook her head.

05:28:35.880 --> 05:28:38.759
I want to take my throne the right way.

05:28:38.819 --> 05:28:41.279
The way I should have done before.

05:28:41.400 --> 05:28:43.319
If I hadn't been such a coward.

05:28:43.380 --> 05:28:46.919
I'm going to follow Skywing tradition, and

05:28:46.919 --> 05:28:49.560
when I win, no one will be able to

05:28:49.560 --> 05:28:50.819
question my position anymore.

05:28:50.880 --> 05:28:53.040
Scarlet chuckled.

05:28:53.099 --> 05:28:55.319
Smoke billowing from her snout.

05:28:55.380 --> 05:28:57.779
When you win.

05:28:57.900 --> 05:29:00.599
How thrillingly hilarious.

05:29:00.659 --> 05:29:04.080
After all the challengers I've killed, you

05:29:04.080 --> 05:29:05.939
think you stand any chance at all?

05:29:06.000 --> 05:29:09.240
My mousey daughter, who can barely speak

05:29:09.240 --> 05:29:11.220
in a room with more than 2 other dragons

05:29:11.220 --> 05:29:11.639
in it.

05:29:11.700 --> 05:29:16.319
Let's find out, Ruby said, flexing her

05:29:16.319 --> 05:29:16.860
claws.

05:29:16.919 --> 05:29:19.200
Maybe I'm not who you think I am.

05:29:19.259 --> 05:29:22.139
Queen Scarlet started to laugh.

05:29:22.200 --> 05:29:25.380
She laughed and laughed so much that

05:29:25.380 --> 05:29:27.840
peril was extremely tempted to set her on

05:29:27.840 --> 05:29:29.220
fire just to shut her up.

05:29:29.279 --> 05:29:31.259
Very well.

05:29:31.319 --> 05:29:33.000
She cried finally.

05:29:33.060 --> 05:29:35.279
I accept your challenge.

05:29:35.400 --> 05:29:37.500
Come at me, daughter.

05:29:37.619 --> 05:29:41.220
Peril stepped aside, so the 2 dragons

05:29:41.220 --> 05:29:41.880
could face each other.

05:29:41.939 --> 05:29:45.119
Ruby met Pearl's eyes, and something

05:29:45.119 --> 05:29:47.580
entirely new passed between them.

05:29:47.639 --> 05:29:50.400
I'll protect Cliff, Pearl said to her.

05:29:50.459 --> 05:29:52.020
No matter what happens.

05:29:52.080 --> 05:29:55.439
Thank you, said Ruby.

05:29:55.500 --> 05:29:57.299
That was all she needed to say.

05:29:57.360 --> 05:30:00.599
That was more, peril suspected, than

05:30:00.599 --> 05:30:02.340
Scarlet had ever said to either of them.

05:30:02.400 --> 05:30:04.799
To the arena then.

05:30:04.979 --> 05:30:06.779
Scarlett growled.

05:30:06.840 --> 05:30:08.220
Ruby shook her head.

05:30:08.279 --> 05:30:11.159
It's full of wounded soldiers and healing

05:30:11.159 --> 05:30:11.700
supplies.

05:30:11.759 --> 05:30:13.139
Choose somewhere else.

05:30:13.200 --> 05:30:16.919
Scarlet looked momentarily unsettled, but

05:30:16.919 --> 05:30:17.759
recovered quickly.

05:30:17.819 --> 05:30:20.459
She glanced around at the gathering crowd

05:30:20.459 --> 05:30:22.799
and peril wondered if she'd choose to

05:30:22.799 --> 05:30:24.060
fight right here in the great hall.

05:30:24.180 --> 05:30:28.380
And then maybe Ruby could accidentally

05:30:28.380 --> 05:30:30.840
throw her right into me, and I could

05:30:30.840 --> 05:30:34.139
accidentally catch her, and whoosh, no

05:30:34.139 --> 05:30:34.860
more scarlet.

05:30:34.919 --> 05:30:37.560
Perhaps the same thought occurred to

05:30:37.560 --> 05:30:39.479
Scarlet, because she nodded at the open

05:30:39.479 --> 05:30:41.880
roof and said, up there.

05:30:41.939 --> 05:30:45.360
The 2 sky wing queens took off 1st

05:30:45.360 --> 05:30:46.799
soaring toward the sky.

05:30:46.860 --> 05:30:49.020
And then what seemed to be the entire

05:30:49.020 --> 05:30:52.139
palace lifted off to follow them, dragons

05:30:52.139 --> 05:30:54.240
jostling for airspace as they competed

05:30:54.240 --> 05:30:55.979
for a ringside seat at the fight.

05:30:56.040 --> 05:30:58.799
Peril couldn't fly through a crowd like

05:30:58.799 --> 05:31:00.959
that, not without seriously hurting

05:31:00.959 --> 05:31:01.200
someone.

05:31:01.259 --> 05:31:03.720
She backed up against the wall next to

05:31:03.720 --> 05:31:04.380
Cliff.

05:31:04.439 --> 05:31:06.479
Hello, he said.

05:31:06.540 --> 05:31:09.840
I think today, I'mma be a warrior

05:31:09.840 --> 05:31:12.720
champion, and go swish, swish with my

05:31:12.720 --> 05:31:15.900
claws, and whar with my mouth, and save

05:31:15.900 --> 05:31:16.380
mommy.

05:31:16.439 --> 05:31:19.020
Maybe we should stay down here.

05:31:19.080 --> 05:31:20.279
Peril said.

05:31:20.340 --> 05:31:22.619
She didn't want poor little Cliff to have

05:31:22.619 --> 05:31:24.659
to watch his mother die if everything

05:31:24.659 --> 05:31:26.340
went wrong and Ruby lost.

05:31:26.400 --> 05:31:28.259
It probably wouldn't be the greatest

05:31:28.259 --> 05:31:30.240
feeling to watch his mother kill his

05:31:30.240 --> 05:31:32.520
grandmother either, even though he had

05:31:32.520 --> 05:31:35.099
experienced Scarlet's evil firsthand.

05:31:35.159 --> 05:31:36.900
No!

05:31:37.020 --> 05:31:39.599
Cliff shrieked at her. making her jump.

05:31:39.659 --> 05:31:41.340
I want to see it.

05:31:41.400 --> 05:31:45.240
Three moons calm down, Peril said.

05:31:45.299 --> 05:31:47.880
I just don't want you to get upset, and

05:31:47.880 --> 05:31:51.119
bites can be very, um, upsetting.

05:31:51.180 --> 05:31:54.840
I won't get upset, Cliff shouted.

05:31:54.900 --> 05:31:59.759
I want to see mommy kill grandma.

05:31:59.880 --> 05:32:02.639
Carol had to stifle a giggle.

05:32:02.700 --> 05:32:05.459
All right, you bloodthirsty little

05:32:05.459 --> 05:32:06.959
barbarian, she said.

05:32:07.020 --> 05:32:09.419
Let's wait until there's space and up

05:32:09.419 --> 05:32:10.020
we'll go.

05:32:10.080 --> 05:32:12.119
He gave her a sideways look.

05:32:12.180 --> 05:32:14.459
You different now?

05:32:14.520 --> 05:32:17.340
Yes, Pearl said.

05:32:17.400 --> 05:32:18.299
I'm better now.

05:32:18.360 --> 05:32:21.240
Not a bad guy?

05:32:21.240 --> 05:32:22.020
he said.

05:32:22.080 --> 05:32:26.520
Well, I hope I'm not a bad guy, Pearl

05:32:26.520 --> 05:32:26.819
said.

05:32:26.880 --> 05:32:28.860
I was under a spell before.

05:32:28.919 --> 05:32:31.560
Hmm, said Cliff.

05:32:31.619 --> 05:32:33.000
A spell.

05:32:33.060 --> 05:32:35.340
He scampered over and picked out the

05:32:35.340 --> 05:32:35.939
necklace.

05:32:36.000 --> 05:32:37.500
From this?

05:32:37.680 --> 05:32:40.500
Right, peril said.

05:32:40.560 --> 05:32:42.599
She took the necklace and clasped it

05:32:42.599 --> 05:32:44.939
between her claws, letting it melt into a

05:32:44.939 --> 05:32:45.900
blackened hunk of metal.

05:32:45.959 --> 05:32:48.540
I wasn't thinking for myself.

05:32:48.599 --> 05:32:51.000
I was thinking what someone else wanted

05:32:51.000 --> 05:32:51.900
me to think.

05:32:51.959 --> 05:32:53.459
But I'm all right now.

05:32:53.580 --> 05:32:55.380
She hesitated.

05:32:55.439 --> 05:32:58.619
Now that I'm thinking what Clay wants me

05:32:58.619 --> 05:32:58.919
to think.

05:32:58.979 --> 05:33:01.919
What if he really was gone from my life?

05:33:01.979 --> 05:33:04.020
What would I be like then?

05:33:04.080 --> 05:33:06.479
Which reminded her?

05:33:06.540 --> 05:33:08.939
She turned to scan the hall, but

05:33:08.939 --> 05:33:10.500
Chameleon had flown off along with

05:33:10.500 --> 05:33:11.099
everyone else.

05:33:11.159 --> 05:33:14.040
There seemed to be a clear enough path to

05:33:14.040 --> 05:33:14.939
the roof now.

05:33:15.000 --> 05:33:17.400
We can go up, Perl said.

05:33:17.459 --> 05:33:19.860
Stay close to me, but don't touch me.

05:33:19.979 --> 05:33:21.779
Why not?

05:33:21.840 --> 05:33:24.479
Cliff asked, immediately reaching for her

05:33:24.479 --> 05:33:24.779
tail.

05:33:24.900 --> 05:33:27.659
She flicked it out of his reach, because

05:33:27.659 --> 05:33:29.700
I'm very hot and you'll get burned.

05:33:29.759 --> 05:33:32.279
Oh, he scoffed.

05:33:32.340 --> 05:33:34.380
I'm not afraid of me burned.

05:33:34.439 --> 05:33:37.020
I am, peril said.

05:33:37.139 --> 05:33:39.720
Be careful, and don't get close to mommy

05:33:39.720 --> 05:33:40.259
either.

05:33:40.319 --> 05:33:43.020
She's very busy right now, so you need to

05:33:43.020 --> 05:33:43.560
leave her alone.

05:33:43.619 --> 05:33:48.840
Until she wins, Cliff sang, vaulting into

05:33:48.840 --> 05:33:49.380
the air.

05:33:49.439 --> 05:33:53.759
If she wins, peril thought, as they flew

05:33:53.759 --> 05:33:55.500
up and out into the driving rain.

05:33:55.560 --> 05:33:58.200
What happens to Cliff if she doesn't?

05:33:58.259 --> 05:34:02.040
The roof of the keep led out onto a rocky

05:34:02.040 --> 05:34:04.860
mountaintop with dizzying views of peaks

05:34:04.860 --> 05:34:05.400
all around them.

05:34:05.459 --> 05:34:08.159
Small tufts of fierce little scrub

05:34:08.159 --> 05:34:10.200
brushes clung to the dirt here and there

05:34:10.200 --> 05:34:13.259
but mostly it was all rocks, long

05:34:13.259 --> 05:34:15.419
overlapping shelves of gray rock, and

05:34:15.419 --> 05:34:17.819
lumps of boulders like giant stone eggs.

05:34:17.880 --> 05:34:20.819
Scarlet and ruby were grappling in the

05:34:20.819 --> 05:34:22.139
center of a crowd of dragons.

05:34:22.200 --> 05:34:25.139
Some were standing on the rocks, and many

05:34:25.139 --> 05:34:26.939
were hovering in the air, so they could

05:34:26.939 --> 05:34:29.340
watch, but also make a quick escape if

05:34:29.340 --> 05:34:29.700
necessary.

05:34:29.759 --> 05:34:33.479
The sky kingdom is going to be a mess if

05:34:33.479 --> 05:34:35.700
Scarlet wins, Peril thought.

05:34:35.759 --> 05:34:38.040
She's going to want to kill at least half

05:34:38.040 --> 05:34:39.840
the dragons here for disloyalty.

05:34:39.900 --> 05:34:43.319
Cliff wobbled over to a boulder that was

05:34:43.319 --> 05:34:45.119
taller than the others, with a view of

05:34:45.119 --> 05:34:45.720
the battlefield.

05:34:45.779 --> 05:34:48.720
The dragons on it saw him and peril

05:34:48.720 --> 05:34:50.099
coming and cleared off quickly.

05:34:50.159 --> 05:34:53.159
As her talons landed on the slippery, wet

05:34:53.159 --> 05:34:55.619
rock, peril could see that already the

05:34:55.619 --> 05:34:58.619
battle was not going well for Ruby, a

05:34:58.619 --> 05:35:00.540
long slash down her neck, and another

05:35:00.540 --> 05:35:02.939
across her back were bleeding, turning

05:35:02.939 --> 05:35:04.740
the puddles thick and red around her

05:35:04.740 --> 05:35:05.340
talons.

05:35:05.400 --> 05:35:08.520
The venom scarred side of Scarlet's face

05:35:08.520 --> 05:35:11.159
always looked as if it were melting, but

05:35:11.159 --> 05:35:13.080
the rain slithering off it now made it

05:35:13.080 --> 05:35:13.979
even worse.

05:35:14.040 --> 05:35:16.380
The triumphant Lear didn't help either.

05:35:16.439 --> 05:35:19.979
She looked absolutely terrifying, and a

05:35:19.979 --> 05:35:20.819
little bit insane.

05:35:20.880 --> 05:35:24.419
Scarlet whirled around and cracked her

05:35:24.419 --> 05:35:26.159
tail across Ruby's snout.

05:35:26.220 --> 05:35:28.560
Ruby let out a yelp of pain and jumped

05:35:28.560 --> 05:35:31.020
back, blinking blood and rain out of her

05:35:31.020 --> 05:35:31.200
eyes.

05:35:31.259 --> 05:35:34.200
She tried slashing at Scarlet's nearest

05:35:34.200 --> 05:35:36.599
wing, but missed, stumbling on the slick

05:35:36.599 --> 05:35:37.139
rocks.

05:35:37.200 --> 05:35:39.779
Cliff edged a little closer to peril's

05:35:39.779 --> 05:35:39.959
heat.

05:35:40.020 --> 05:35:42.659
Mommy, he whispered.

05:35:42.720 --> 05:35:45.299
This poor little dragonette.

05:35:45.360 --> 05:35:47.700
What do I do if Ruby loses?

05:35:47.700 --> 05:35:50.459
Maybe then I can kill Scarlet myself.

05:35:50.520 --> 05:35:52.919
I doubt anyone would try to stop me.

05:35:52.979 --> 05:35:55.740
But then there'd be no one left to be

05:35:55.740 --> 05:35:58.439
queen of the Sky Wings, since Scarlet

05:35:58.439 --> 05:36:00.540
brilliantly disposed of all her airs.

05:36:00.659 --> 05:36:02.939
A jolt ran through her.

05:36:03.060 --> 05:36:05.159
What about tourmaline?

05:36:05.220 --> 05:36:07.799
If Scarlet was telling the truth

05:36:07.799 --> 05:36:10.560
Tourmaline was still alive somewhere, and

05:36:10.560 --> 05:36:12.479
a backup air would probably be fairly

05:36:12.479 --> 05:36:13.500
useful right about now.

05:36:13.560 --> 05:36:16.200
Where could tourmaline be?

05:36:16.259 --> 05:36:18.900
Ruby would know if her sister were in any

05:36:18.900 --> 05:36:20.639
of the usual Sky Wing prisons.

05:36:20.700 --> 05:36:23.099
But peril already knew.

05:36:23.159 --> 05:36:24.659
She could have guessed from the moment

05:36:24.659 --> 05:36:26.040
she ripped off the necklace.

05:36:26.099 --> 05:36:29.580
Nobody knew where Tourmaline was, because

05:36:29.580 --> 05:36:31.319
Tourmaline wasn't herself anymore.

05:36:31.380 --> 05:36:34.860
Like peril, she must have been enchanted

05:36:34.860 --> 05:36:35.459
by chameleon.

05:36:35.520 --> 05:36:37.380
She could be anybody now.

05:36:37.439 --> 05:36:40.380
Which meant that only Chameleon and

05:36:40.380 --> 05:36:42.360
Scarlet would be able to identify her.

05:36:42.419 --> 05:36:45.779
Peril narrowed her eyes, searching the

05:36:45.779 --> 05:36:46.860
audience of Skywings.

05:36:46.919 --> 05:36:49.380
One thing about Chameleon's disguise as

05:36:49.380 --> 05:36:51.959
sore, he blended right into the rest of

05:36:51.959 --> 05:36:52.439
the tribe.

05:36:52.560 --> 05:36:55.080
It took her several minutes to spot him

05:36:55.080 --> 05:36:57.000
and then she only did because she caught

05:36:57.000 --> 05:36:58.979
his eyes watching her instead of the

05:36:58.979 --> 05:36:59.220
fight.

05:36:59.279 --> 05:37:02.700
She pointed at him, and then at the rock

05:37:02.700 --> 05:37:03.240
beside her.

05:37:03.299 --> 05:37:06.779
Come here, right now.

05:37:06.840 --> 05:37:10.259
He wavered for a moment, then flapped

05:37:10.259 --> 05:37:12.720
down to land, she noticed, in a way that

05:37:12.720 --> 05:37:14.099
kept Cliff between him and her.

05:37:14.159 --> 05:37:18.299
Oh, very brave, father, hiding behind a

05:37:18.299 --> 05:37:19.919
dragonette, classy.

05:37:20.040 --> 05:37:23.639
I was thinking, he said quickly, before

05:37:23.639 --> 05:37:24.540
she could speak.

05:37:24.599 --> 05:37:26.220
Perhaps we should try a different

05:37:26.220 --> 05:37:26.939
enchantment.

05:37:27.000 --> 05:37:29.340
Maybe you don't even want to be a Sky

05:37:29.340 --> 05:37:30.000
Wing anymore.

05:37:30.060 --> 05:37:32.220
We could both be mudwings.

05:37:32.279 --> 05:37:35.220
In fact, I could do that right now, and

05:37:35.220 --> 05:37:36.659
we could fly away from here together.

05:37:36.720 --> 05:37:37.500
What do you think?

05:37:37.560 --> 05:37:40.619
I hear the Mud Kingdom is tolerable.

05:37:40.680 --> 05:37:42.599
We could start a new life together.

05:37:42.659 --> 05:37:45.360
Very far away from whoever wins this

05:37:45.360 --> 05:37:45.720
fight.

05:37:45.779 --> 05:37:49.380
I don't want a new life, Pearl said

05:37:49.380 --> 05:37:49.979
bristling.

05:37:50.040 --> 05:37:52.740
I want my own life, with all my memories

05:37:52.740 --> 05:37:54.240
intact, thank you very much.

05:37:54.299 --> 05:37:57.840
You could word the enchantment yourself

05:37:57.840 --> 05:38:00.840
he said desperately, or slyly.

05:38:00.900 --> 05:38:01.919
Parel wasn't sure.

05:38:02.040 --> 05:38:04.740
She found him hard to read, even when he

05:38:04.740 --> 05:38:06.900
wasn't drowned out by thunder and rain.

05:38:06.959 --> 05:38:10.619
We could, no, peril said.

05:38:10.680 --> 05:38:12.479
I'm never letting you change me again.

05:38:12.540 --> 05:38:14.520
I can't trust you.

05:38:14.639 --> 05:38:17.700
He wilted a little, but she was pretty

05:38:17.700 --> 05:38:19.200
far from feeling sorry for him.

05:38:19.259 --> 05:38:23.220
Now tell me what you did to Tourmaline

05:38:23.220 --> 05:38:23.939
she added.

05:38:24.060 --> 05:38:25.680
Me?

05:38:25.740 --> 05:38:26.520
he said.

05:38:26.580 --> 05:38:28.200
Tourmaline.

05:38:28.259 --> 05:38:29.819
I don't.

05:38:29.880 --> 05:38:31.020
Well, I can't even...

05:38:31.020 --> 05:38:32.099
Was there?

05:38:32.279 --> 05:38:33.060
Who's that?

05:38:33.180 --> 05:38:36.240
Very amusing, she said.

05:38:36.299 --> 05:38:39.060
Almost as amusing as your ears on fire

05:38:39.060 --> 05:38:39.540
would be.

05:38:39.659 --> 05:38:42.720
All right, all right, yes, I changed her

05:38:42.720 --> 05:38:43.680
he said.

05:38:43.740 --> 05:38:45.540
She was getting too ambitious.

05:38:45.599 --> 05:38:47.939
Scarlet wanted her out of the way, but

05:38:47.939 --> 05:38:48.419
not dead.

05:38:48.479 --> 05:38:51.900
She couldn't get rid of all her heirs, a

05:38:51.900 --> 05:38:54.060
kingdom without any heirs is in perpetual

05:38:54.060 --> 05:38:54.299
danger.

05:38:54.360 --> 05:38:57.299
I think all the queens learned that from

05:38:57.299 --> 05:38:58.919
what happened to the mud wings a couple

05:38:58.919 --> 05:38:59.639
of centuries ago.

05:38:59.700 --> 05:39:02.520
So Tourmaline is still available if

05:39:02.520 --> 05:39:04.380
Scarlet ever needs her.

05:39:04.439 --> 05:39:06.900
She just doesn't know it herself.

05:39:07.020 --> 05:39:10.680
He trailed off, regarding the battling

05:39:10.680 --> 05:39:12.840
dragons and rubbing his snout worriedly.

05:39:12.900 --> 05:39:16.860
You shouldn't do that, peril burst out.

05:39:16.919 --> 05:39:19.080
You can't just take away a dragon's

05:39:19.080 --> 05:39:19.740
memory.

05:39:19.799 --> 05:39:21.720
Turn them into someone completely new.

05:39:21.779 --> 05:39:22.979
That's horrible.

05:39:23.040 --> 05:39:26.340
I thought becoming someone completely new

05:39:26.340 --> 05:39:28.979
was exactly what you wanted, he said

05:39:28.979 --> 05:39:29.759
ruffled.

05:39:29.880 --> 05:39:32.520
I like being different dragons.

05:39:32.580 --> 05:39:35.819
Yes, but you still have your memory when

05:39:35.819 --> 05:39:37.619
you do that, Pearl said.

05:39:37.680 --> 05:39:39.540
You know who you are underneath.

05:39:39.599 --> 05:39:42.779
Tourmaline, I assume, does not.

05:39:42.840 --> 05:39:45.000
True, he said.

05:39:45.060 --> 05:39:46.979
But she was safer that way.

05:39:47.040 --> 05:39:49.560
Otherwise, she would have challenged

05:39:49.560 --> 05:39:51.299
Scarlet and wound up dead before she

05:39:51.299 --> 05:39:51.659
turned 11.

05:39:51.900 --> 05:39:54.119
Pearl shook her head.

05:39:54.180 --> 05:39:56.159
Scattering the cloud of steam that was

05:39:56.159 --> 05:39:58.560
forming around her, as raindrops hit her

05:39:58.560 --> 05:39:59.340
fiery scales.

05:39:59.400 --> 05:40:03.060
You're like 18,000 different kinds of

05:40:03.060 --> 05:40:03.959
untrustworthy.

05:40:04.020 --> 05:40:05.939
Are you even really my father?

05:40:06.060 --> 05:40:08.639
Yes, he said firmly.

05:40:08.700 --> 05:40:10.619
Kestrel didn't know who I was.

05:40:10.680 --> 05:40:12.959
She thought I was assigned to partner

05:40:12.959 --> 05:40:13.259
with her.

05:40:13.319 --> 05:40:14.459
But I knew her.

05:40:14.520 --> 05:40:17.099
I am unquestionably your father.

05:40:17.159 --> 05:40:20.279
Wonderful, Pearl said.

05:40:20.340 --> 05:40:21.900
Such fantastic news.

05:40:21.959 --> 05:40:23.880
So where is Tourmaline?

05:40:23.939 --> 05:40:25.139
Is she here now?

05:40:25.200 --> 05:40:27.840
He hesitated, and then nodded.

05:40:27.900 --> 05:40:30.900
At the same moment, Ruby let out another

05:40:30.900 --> 05:40:33.360
cry of pain, a scarlet slammed into her

05:40:33.360 --> 05:40:35.159
chest, knocking her off her feet.

05:40:35.220 --> 05:40:38.040
Lightning cracked the sky in half above

05:40:38.040 --> 05:40:40.319
the fighting dragons, illuminating

05:40:40.319 --> 05:40:42.900
Scarlet's gloating face as she advanced

05:40:42.900 --> 05:40:44.220
on her daughter.

05:40:44.279 --> 05:40:46.680
Why isn't mommy fighting better?

05:40:46.799 --> 05:40:48.240
Cliff cried.

05:40:48.299 --> 05:40:50.700
Pearl looked down at Cliff's anguished

05:40:50.700 --> 05:40:51.240
face.

05:40:51.299 --> 05:40:52.680
You know what?

05:40:52.740 --> 05:40:54.180
She said to Chameleon.

05:40:54.240 --> 05:40:55.020
Fine.

05:40:55.080 --> 05:40:56.159
Keep your secret.

05:40:56.220 --> 05:40:58.439
It doesn't matter who Tremaline is

05:40:58.439 --> 05:41:00.240
because Ruby has to win this fight.

05:41:00.299 --> 05:41:04.080
For the entire Skywing tribe, but mostly

05:41:04.080 --> 05:41:05.040
for Cliff.

05:41:05.099 --> 05:41:07.380
Oh, Chameleon said.

05:41:07.439 --> 05:41:08.459
She can't.

05:41:08.580 --> 05:41:10.380
Peril stared at him.

05:41:10.439 --> 05:41:11.759
Yes, she can.

05:41:11.880 --> 05:41:12.840
Of course she can.

05:41:12.900 --> 05:41:14.099
What are you talking about?

05:41:14.159 --> 05:41:17.639
Uh, nothing, he said.

05:41:17.700 --> 05:41:19.319
You're right, of course you can.

05:41:19.380 --> 05:41:22.200
Did you do something?

05:41:22.259 --> 05:41:23.159
Pearl asked.

05:41:23.279 --> 05:41:25.979
Did you do something to Ruby like you did

05:41:25.979 --> 05:41:26.459
to me?

05:41:26.520 --> 05:41:30.360
Below them, Ruby leaped up and sliced one

05:41:30.360 --> 05:41:33.180
claw across Scarlet's throat, but Scarlet

05:41:33.180 --> 05:41:35.159
caught her arm and kicked Ruby back into

05:41:35.159 --> 05:41:35.580
a boulder.

05:41:35.700 --> 05:41:38.580
Ruby struggled back to her feet, her

05:41:38.580 --> 05:41:40.259
wings drooping and heavy with rain.

05:41:40.319 --> 05:41:45.900
Well, he said, even if I did, it's not

05:41:45.900 --> 05:41:46.439
working anyway.

05:41:46.500 --> 05:41:48.840
This shouldn't be able to happen at all.

05:41:48.900 --> 05:41:51.599
So really, anything could happen next.

05:41:51.659 --> 05:41:53.700
It's basically like I didn't do

05:41:53.700 --> 05:41:53.880
anything.

05:41:53.939 --> 05:41:57.180
What did you do?

05:41:57.240 --> 05:41:59.939
Pearl's wings flared open, scattering

05:41:59.939 --> 05:42:01.740
warm raindrops all over cliff.

05:42:01.799 --> 05:42:04.200
Nightmare possibilities were flashing

05:42:04.200 --> 05:42:04.919
through her head.

05:42:04.979 --> 05:42:07.560
He could have done anything to Ruby with

05:42:07.560 --> 05:42:08.340
that scroll.

05:42:08.400 --> 05:42:10.080
He could have enchanted her to fall

05:42:10.080 --> 05:42:11.759
asleep whenever Scarlet hit her.

05:42:11.819 --> 05:42:13.979
He could have enchanted her to go blind

05:42:13.979 --> 05:42:16.380
whenever she tried to hit Scarlet.

05:42:16.439 --> 05:42:18.299
He could have enchanted her to lose any

05:42:18.299 --> 05:42:20.220
challenge battle with Scarlet.

05:42:20.279 --> 05:42:22.919
But he'd need a thing to enchant.

05:42:22.979 --> 05:42:26.400
That's how animus magic works, peril

05:42:26.400 --> 05:42:27.000
remembered.

05:42:27.060 --> 05:42:29.340
Something with room for a piece of scroll

05:42:29.340 --> 05:42:29.880
inside.

05:42:29.939 --> 05:42:33.299
She stared wildly down at the battling

05:42:33.299 --> 05:42:36.000
queens, trying to spot something on Ruby

05:42:36.000 --> 05:42:38.040
that might be hiding an animus touched

05:42:38.040 --> 05:42:39.419
scrap of scroll.

05:42:39.479 --> 05:42:40.560
There.

05:42:40.619 --> 05:42:44.159
Ruby had one small earring that she

05:42:44.159 --> 05:42:45.299
always seemed to be wearing.

05:42:45.360 --> 05:42:47.700
Peril had never seen her without it.

05:42:47.759 --> 05:42:50.939
A teardrop shaped pendant hung from it

05:42:50.939 --> 05:42:53.819
studded with rubies, and just big enough

05:42:53.819 --> 05:42:55.979
to open and fit a piece of paper inside.

05:42:56.040 --> 05:42:59.700
Wait here, Pearl said to Cliff.

05:42:59.759 --> 05:43:02.639
But, he protested as she lifted off.

05:43:02.700 --> 05:43:05.939
But you said not to interrupt mommy.

05:43:06.000 --> 05:43:09.000
Parel dove at the wrestling sky wings

05:43:09.000 --> 05:43:11.220
just as Scarlet was about to stamp her

05:43:11.220 --> 05:43:14.340
talons down on Ruby's face, but she must

05:43:14.340 --> 05:43:15.840
have heard something over the wind and

05:43:15.840 --> 05:43:17.939
thunder, because she looked up at the

05:43:17.939 --> 05:43:20.520
last moment, saw peril hurtling toward

05:43:20.520 --> 05:43:22.139
them, and leaped backward instead.

05:43:22.200 --> 05:43:25.080
Ruby scrambled up and turned to look at

05:43:25.080 --> 05:43:25.799
peril too.

05:43:25.860 --> 05:43:27.479
Don't interfere.

05:43:27.540 --> 05:43:28.740
She gasped.

05:43:28.799 --> 05:43:31.259
Her heaving sides slick with blood and

05:43:31.259 --> 05:43:31.619
rain.

05:43:31.680 --> 05:43:33.659
I have to win this myself.

05:43:33.720 --> 05:43:36.599
Peril skidded to a stop in front of her.

05:43:36.659 --> 05:43:39.659
I know, but it's not a fair fight right

05:43:39.659 --> 05:43:39.900
now.

05:43:39.959 --> 05:43:41.340
Don't move.

05:43:41.400 --> 05:43:44.880
She reached out and crushed the dangling

05:43:44.880 --> 05:43:46.619
earring pendant between 2 of her claws.

05:43:46.740 --> 05:43:50.159
The metal exterior melted first, caving

05:43:50.159 --> 05:43:52.560
in, and Peril called a glimpse of

05:43:52.560 --> 05:43:54.840
something white inside before it crumbled

05:43:54.840 --> 05:43:56.819
into black ash, and then the whole

05:43:56.819 --> 05:43:58.200
pendant dropped to the ground.

05:43:58.259 --> 05:44:00.360
Why did you do that?

05:44:00.419 --> 05:44:01.799
Ruby cried.

05:44:01.860 --> 05:44:05.279
That was a present from my sister, from, I

05:44:05.279 --> 05:44:05.939
have a...

05:44:06.540 --> 05:44:07.020
She stopped.

05:44:07.080 --> 05:44:09.779
Her talons moving slowly to her head, as

05:44:09.779 --> 05:44:11.639
if a glacier were trying to climb out her

05:44:11.639 --> 05:44:12.240
eye sockets.

05:44:12.299 --> 05:44:16.080
Ruby's dark red scales glimmered once

05:44:16.080 --> 05:44:19.259
twice, and then faded softly into dark

05:44:19.259 --> 05:44:20.099
orange instead.

05:44:20.159 --> 05:44:23.639
Her horns curved inward, and her snout

05:44:23.639 --> 05:44:25.979
lengthened slightly, and her whole body

05:44:25.979 --> 05:44:28.080
seemed to get thicker and stronger.

05:44:28.200 --> 05:44:31.080
Not only that, but all her wounds

05:44:31.080 --> 05:44:31.799
vanished.

05:44:31.860 --> 05:44:34.619
What in the sun?

05:44:34.740 --> 05:44:38.040
Ruby trailed off, blinking at her newly

05:44:38.040 --> 05:44:38.939
sharp talons.

05:44:39.000 --> 05:44:41.099
Peril was surprised too.

05:44:41.159 --> 05:44:43.319
She hadn't expected Ruby to be something

05:44:43.319 --> 05:44:44.099
different underneath.

05:44:44.159 --> 05:44:47.459
I'm sorry, she stammered.

05:44:47.520 --> 05:44:49.259
You were under a spell too.

05:44:49.319 --> 05:44:51.959
All I know is that it was enchanted to

05:44:51.959 --> 05:44:53.580
stop you from winning this battle, and I

05:44:53.580 --> 05:44:55.259
thought that wasn't fair.

05:44:55.380 --> 05:44:57.540
Tourmaline?

05:44:57.599 --> 05:45:00.540
Vermilion said, stepping out of the crowd

05:45:00.540 --> 05:45:01.919
of gawking sky wings.

05:45:01.979 --> 05:45:04.139
But aren't you dead?

05:45:04.200 --> 05:45:08.279
Not yet, said Scarlet, but she will be

05:45:08.279 --> 05:45:08.759
soon.

05:45:08.819 --> 05:45:10.740
She shot a glare at peril.

05:45:10.799 --> 05:45:13.439
This is Tourmaline?

05:45:13.500 --> 05:45:14.400
Pearl cried.

05:45:14.459 --> 05:45:17.459
But if I'm Tourmaline, said the

05:45:17.459 --> 05:45:21.900
transformed queen, then where, or who, is

05:45:21.900 --> 05:45:22.380
Ruby?

05:45:22.439 --> 05:45:26.639
Chapter 18.

05:45:26.819 --> 05:45:30.180
A new flash of greenish lightning

05:45:30.180 --> 05:45:32.400
illuminated the horrible crooked grin on

05:45:32.400 --> 05:45:33.540
the old queen's face.

05:45:33.599 --> 05:45:38.700
There is no ruby, Scarlett said with

05:45:38.700 --> 05:45:39.900
malicious delight.

05:45:39.959 --> 05:45:40.979
I made her up.

05:45:41.040 --> 05:45:44.340
It turns out, when you're the queen, no

05:45:44.340 --> 05:45:46.740
one questions which dragons you claim as

05:45:46.740 --> 05:45:49.680
daughters, I invented Ruby completely

05:45:49.680 --> 05:45:51.840
exactly the way I wanted her.

05:45:51.900 --> 05:45:55.020
After all, I've always been disappointed

05:45:55.020 --> 05:45:56.580
in the daughters I actually had.

05:45:56.639 --> 05:46:00.360
If she was hoping for a more devastated

05:46:00.360 --> 05:46:02.279
reaction, she must have been

05:46:02.279 --> 05:46:03.000
disappointed.

05:46:03.060 --> 05:46:05.520
Tourmaline only narrowed her eyes at her

05:46:05.520 --> 05:46:08.159
mother, and lifted her chin, with an

05:46:08.159 --> 05:46:09.720
expression that looked exactly like one

05:46:09.720 --> 05:46:13.799
of Queen Ruby's, Your Majesty, Peril said

05:46:13.799 --> 05:46:16.500
to Ruby Tourmaline, my advice is to

05:46:16.500 --> 05:46:18.299
finish killing Scarlet, and then figure

05:46:18.299 --> 05:46:18.599
this out.

05:46:18.659 --> 05:46:20.880
I have someone who can answer all your

05:46:20.880 --> 05:46:22.139
questions when you're done.

05:46:22.200 --> 05:46:24.119
Tourmaline set her jaw.

05:46:24.180 --> 05:46:25.979
Good idea.

05:46:26.099 --> 05:46:28.680
She launched herself at Scarlet with

05:46:28.680 --> 05:46:31.319
startling speed. suddenly full of all the

05:46:31.319 --> 05:46:33.419
ferocity and danger that peril had

05:46:33.419 --> 05:46:34.080
expected before.

05:46:34.139 --> 05:46:37.680
With 2 quick slashes, she ripped into one

05:46:37.680 --> 05:46:39.779
of Scarlet's wings, and then sank her

05:46:39.779 --> 05:46:42.060
claws into Scarlet's shoulders, and her

05:46:42.060 --> 05:46:43.380
teeth into Scarlet's neck.

05:46:43.439 --> 05:46:46.500
Another heavy roll of thunder rumbled

05:46:46.500 --> 05:46:47.459
over their shrieks.

05:46:47.520 --> 05:46:49.500
Peril backed away from the fight

05:46:49.500 --> 05:46:51.779
cautiously working her way to the boulder

05:46:51.779 --> 05:46:52.919
where Cliff was waiting.

05:46:52.979 --> 05:46:55.619
Below the thunder and dragon roars.

05:46:55.680 --> 05:46:57.479
She caught some of the conversations

05:46:57.479 --> 05:46:58.560
running through the crowd.

05:46:58.619 --> 05:47:00.599
But who is that?

05:47:00.659 --> 05:47:02.040
Where did Ruby go?

05:47:02.099 --> 05:47:04.139
Did peril do something to her?

05:47:04.200 --> 05:47:05.700
Doesn't matter.

05:47:05.759 --> 05:47:06.959
She's winning now, isn't she?

05:47:07.020 --> 05:47:09.360
I remember Tourmaline.

05:47:09.419 --> 05:47:11.099
I thought the queen had her killed a long

05:47:11.099 --> 05:47:12.060
time ago.

05:47:12.119 --> 05:47:14.819
How does a dragon just change like that?

05:47:14.880 --> 05:47:16.319
Who did that magic?

05:47:16.380 --> 05:47:18.599
We don't have any animus dragons in the

05:47:18.599 --> 05:47:19.560
Skywing tribe?

05:47:19.619 --> 05:47:21.840
Wait, I liked Ruby.

05:47:21.900 --> 05:47:22.740
Can we get Ruby back?

05:47:22.799 --> 05:47:25.500
Peril climbed back up onto the boulder

05:47:25.500 --> 05:47:27.779
and found dismayed faces on both

05:47:27.779 --> 05:47:29.040
chameleon and cliff.

05:47:29.099 --> 05:47:33.000
I wish you hadn't done that, Chameleon

05:47:33.000 --> 05:47:33.299
said.

05:47:33.360 --> 05:47:35.880
So publicly too.

05:47:35.939 --> 05:47:38.040
It's going to raise a lot of questions.

05:47:38.099 --> 05:47:41.159
And I'm afraid it'll be really awkward

05:47:41.159 --> 05:47:43.200
for me around here if you start pointing

05:47:43.200 --> 05:47:43.680
talons.

05:47:43.740 --> 05:47:47.639
Oh, I'm sorry, Pearl said.

05:47:47.700 --> 05:47:48.360
You're right.

05:47:48.419 --> 05:47:50.759
I should have let Ruby die, so you

05:47:50.759 --> 05:47:52.439
wouldn't have to feel awkward.

05:47:52.500 --> 05:47:54.720
Where's mommy?

05:47:54.779 --> 05:47:56.819
Cliff asked, reaching out his little

05:47:56.819 --> 05:47:58.139
talons?

05:47:58.200 --> 05:47:59.819
You said you not a bad guy.

05:47:59.880 --> 05:48:00.840
You said that.

05:48:00.900 --> 05:48:02.340
Where did you put her?

05:48:02.459 --> 05:48:04.380
He started to cry.

05:48:04.439 --> 05:48:07.080
I want mommy back.

05:48:07.200 --> 05:48:10.080
Now peril really did feel sorry.

05:48:10.139 --> 05:48:12.659
She wished desperately that she could hug

05:48:12.659 --> 05:48:15.060
him, or at least take one of his talons

05:48:15.060 --> 05:48:17.220
in hers, the way Clay did when he was

05:48:17.220 --> 05:48:17.880
comforting someone.

05:48:17.939 --> 05:48:20.340
It's all right, little prince.

05:48:20.400 --> 05:48:22.860
She said, crouching to look him in the

05:48:22.860 --> 05:48:23.099
eyes.

05:48:23.220 --> 05:48:25.740
She has to look like that to win this

05:48:25.740 --> 05:48:27.720
fight, but she's still your mother.

05:48:27.779 --> 05:48:30.419
She's just bigger and tougher and a

05:48:30.419 --> 05:48:31.439
different color, that's all.

05:48:31.560 --> 05:48:33.479
She still loves you the same.

05:48:33.540 --> 05:48:38.400
Well, she might not, said Chameleon.

05:48:38.459 --> 05:48:41.040
That was a whole other personality I

05:48:41.040 --> 05:48:43.020
built for her, with a lot of false

05:48:43.020 --> 05:48:44.220
memories in it.

05:48:44.279 --> 05:48:46.259
She may feel differently about everyone

05:48:46.259 --> 05:48:48.060
now, even him.

05:48:48.119 --> 05:48:51.180
Cliff buried his face in his talons and

05:48:51.180 --> 05:48:52.139
started to sob.

05:48:52.200 --> 05:48:54.479
Stupendously helpful.

05:48:54.540 --> 05:48:57.659
Peril said to her father, for our next

05:48:57.659 --> 05:49:00.119
trick, Let's burn out all your teeth one

05:49:00.119 --> 05:49:00.540
by one.

05:49:00.599 --> 05:49:03.479
He took a nervous step away from her.

05:49:03.540 --> 05:49:06.540
I only mean that I don't know what will

05:49:06.540 --> 05:49:07.139
happen.

05:49:07.259 --> 05:49:09.180
Ruby wasn't supposed to be able to

05:49:09.180 --> 05:49:11.279
challenge her mother at all. and

05:49:11.279 --> 05:49:13.619
certainly never win, but she's been

05:49:13.619 --> 05:49:15.659
wearing that personality for over 7 years

05:49:15.659 --> 05:49:16.020
now.

05:49:16.080 --> 05:49:19.439
Maybe over that much time, it becomes

05:49:19.439 --> 05:49:21.720
real enough to change, like a real dragon

05:49:21.720 --> 05:49:22.080
would.

05:49:22.139 --> 05:49:24.540
So she became strong enough to make the

05:49:24.540 --> 05:49:24.900
challenge.

05:49:24.959 --> 05:49:27.119
You were strong like that already.

05:49:27.180 --> 05:49:29.400
I couldn't believe how quickly you

05:49:29.400 --> 05:49:31.259
overcame the loyalty to Queen Scarlet.

05:49:31.319 --> 05:49:34.139
Peril snorted in disgust.

05:49:34.200 --> 05:49:37.560
You specifically put loyalty to her in my

05:49:37.560 --> 05:49:38.099
spell?

05:49:38.159 --> 05:49:40.680
Of course, he said.

05:49:40.740 --> 05:49:44.040
That was my assignment before I ever knew

05:49:44.040 --> 05:49:44.819
you were my daughter.

05:49:44.880 --> 05:49:48.180
Remove fire scales, add Queen Scarlet

05:49:48.180 --> 05:49:50.580
loyalty, subtract all memories of clay.

05:49:50.639 --> 05:49:53.819
I'd say you are the worst dragon I've

05:49:53.819 --> 05:49:55.139
ever met, Pearl said.

05:49:55.200 --> 05:49:57.360
But Scarlet still has you beat.

05:49:57.419 --> 05:50:00.360
Another wild scream came from the

05:50:00.360 --> 05:50:02.520
combatants, drawing peril's attention

05:50:02.520 --> 05:50:03.240
back to the fight.

05:50:03.299 --> 05:50:06.060
Scarlet was trying to sink her claws into

05:50:06.060 --> 05:50:08.400
Tourmaline's eyes, but Tourmaline was

05:50:08.400 --> 05:50:10.139
holding her off with brute strength

05:50:10.139 --> 05:50:12.840
pummeling her underbelly with razor sharp

05:50:12.840 --> 05:50:13.500
back talons.

05:50:13.560 --> 05:50:16.080
Scarlet's scales were more red than

05:50:16.080 --> 05:50:18.479
orange now, covered in blood from her

05:50:18.479 --> 05:50:20.520
shredded wing, shoulders and neck.

05:50:20.580 --> 05:50:23.639
The rain slammed down on their backs, and

05:50:23.639 --> 05:50:25.740
the clouds seemed to be leaning in closer

05:50:25.740 --> 05:50:27.479
as though they wanted to watch the fight

05:50:27.479 --> 05:50:28.020
as well.

05:50:28.080 --> 05:50:31.080
Suddenly, Scarlet slipped on the wet

05:50:31.080 --> 05:50:33.000
rocks. and went crashing down on her

05:50:33.000 --> 05:50:33.240
back.

05:50:33.299 --> 05:50:36.180
Tourmaline immediately leaped on top of

05:50:36.180 --> 05:50:37.919
her, digging in her talons.

05:50:38.040 --> 05:50:41.520
You shouldn't have come back, mother, she

05:50:41.520 --> 05:50:41.819
said.

05:50:41.880 --> 05:50:44.040
Tourmaline glanced up at the waiting

05:50:44.040 --> 05:50:47.220
crowd and shouted, For the Sky Wings.

05:50:47.279 --> 05:50:50.099
And then, with a ferocious crack.

05:50:50.159 --> 05:50:52.919
She snapped Queen Scarlet's neck.

05:50:52.979 --> 05:50:58.020
For a long moment, the only sound was the

05:50:58.020 --> 05:51:00.900
rain falling, pattering on rocks and

05:51:00.900 --> 05:51:02.639
scales, and wings.

05:51:02.700 --> 05:51:06.900
Then someone shouted, Long live Queen

05:51:06.900 --> 05:51:07.619
Ruby!

05:51:07.680 --> 05:51:09.119
Queen Ruby!

05:51:09.180 --> 05:51:11.159
Queen Ruby!

05:51:11.279 --> 05:51:13.080
The crowd roared in response.

05:51:13.139 --> 05:51:16.500
I gather that most of these dragons

05:51:16.500 --> 05:51:18.240
missed the message about who she really

05:51:18.240 --> 05:51:20.459
is, Chameleon said dryly.

05:51:20.520 --> 05:51:23.819
Shows how smart you are, Pearl said.

05:51:23.880 --> 05:51:27.720
She really is Ruby to them, and if she

05:51:27.720 --> 05:51:29.340
has all her memories.

05:51:29.400 --> 05:51:30.659
Isn't she really Ruby?

05:51:30.720 --> 05:51:33.240
What else makes a dragon who she is?

05:51:33.299 --> 05:51:35.220
Moral fiber?

05:51:35.279 --> 05:51:37.200
A voice suggested behind her.

05:51:37.259 --> 05:51:39.540
A coherent philosophy of life.

05:51:39.659 --> 05:51:41.759
Peril whirled around.

05:51:41.819 --> 05:51:43.020
Turtle?

05:51:43.080 --> 05:51:44.520
she cried with delight.

05:51:44.580 --> 05:51:46.979
The sea wing edged out from behind one of

05:51:46.979 --> 05:51:49.139
the boulders, nervously eyeing the

05:51:49.139 --> 05:51:51.000
raucous, celebrating sky wings.

05:51:51.060 --> 05:51:53.639
He looked extremely wet and somewhat

05:51:53.639 --> 05:51:54.360
bedraggled.

05:51:54.419 --> 05:51:58.319
I, uh, came to rescue you?

05:51:58.319 --> 05:51:59.279
he said.

05:51:59.400 --> 05:52:02.220
Well, to find out what was going on

05:52:02.220 --> 05:52:02.639
anyway.

05:52:02.700 --> 05:52:05.340
I heard there was a spell or something

05:52:05.340 --> 05:52:07.740
but then I got here, and it was very

05:52:07.740 --> 05:52:10.200
stormy, and I couldn't find you, and

05:52:10.200 --> 05:52:12.900
suddenly there were 8000000 sky wings

05:52:12.900 --> 05:52:15.060
pouring out of the mountains, and a big

05:52:15.060 --> 05:52:17.639
fight going on, and I thought, maybe

05:52:17.639 --> 05:52:19.619
better to stay out of the way until it's

05:52:19.619 --> 05:52:20.700
over, right?

05:52:20.759 --> 05:52:23.400
Yes, smart thinking.

05:52:23.459 --> 05:52:26.220
If Scarlet had won, it might have gotten

05:52:26.220 --> 05:52:28.319
a little dangerous around here, Pearl

05:52:28.319 --> 05:52:28.619
said.

05:52:28.680 --> 05:52:31.080
But don't worry, I rescued myself.

05:52:31.139 --> 05:52:32.759
No more spells on me.

05:52:32.880 --> 05:52:35.819
She gave Chameleon a sharp glance, and he

05:52:35.819 --> 05:52:36.659
nodded frantically.

05:52:36.720 --> 05:52:39.900
Plus, also, I kind of saved the day.

05:52:39.959 --> 05:52:42.299
It was epic, and you missed it.

05:52:42.360 --> 05:52:46.380
Nuh-uh, Cliff said, suddenly looking up.

05:52:46.439 --> 05:52:49.200
His face was still streaked with tears

05:52:49.200 --> 05:52:51.419
but indignation had broken through his

05:52:51.419 --> 05:52:51.779
distress.

05:52:51.840 --> 05:52:53.880
Cliff did that.

05:52:53.939 --> 05:52:55.380
I saved the day.

05:52:55.500 --> 05:52:59.759
Well, a little bit, peril admitted, but

05:52:59.759 --> 05:53:01.619
it was maybe 85% meat.

05:53:01.740 --> 05:53:06.419
It was 90, 65, 90 person me.

05:53:06.540 --> 05:53:07.979
Cliff objected.

05:53:08.040 --> 05:53:11.340
I have little brothers, Turtle said to

05:53:11.340 --> 05:53:12.659
Parel. trust me.

05:53:12.720 --> 05:53:14.520
You're not going to win this argument.

05:53:14.580 --> 05:53:17.459
She couldn't believe Turtle was here.

05:53:17.520 --> 05:53:20.159
That was something only a friend would do

05:53:20.159 --> 05:53:20.700
wasn't it?

05:53:20.759 --> 05:53:22.740
Come to rescue her from a spell?

05:53:22.799 --> 05:53:25.439
Deep inside another tribe's kingdom

05:53:25.439 --> 05:53:28.380
risking the wrath of a dangerous queen?

05:53:28.439 --> 05:53:31.619
Maybe you do like me after all, she said

05:53:31.619 --> 05:53:32.340
to Turtle.

05:53:32.400 --> 05:53:34.740
You're alone, he said.

05:53:34.799 --> 05:53:37.439
Of course I do, even when you're scary

05:53:37.439 --> 05:53:40.619
which, let's be fair, is most of the

05:53:40.619 --> 05:53:40.799
time.

05:53:40.860 --> 05:53:45.419
But what if I'm the talons of power and

05:53:45.419 --> 05:53:47.580
fire, parallel asked?

05:53:47.639 --> 05:53:50.459
Shouldn't you beware me instead of being

05:53:50.459 --> 05:53:51.240
friends with me?

05:53:51.299 --> 05:53:54.479
I can be wear you and like you at the

05:53:54.479 --> 05:53:54.900
same time.

05:53:54.959 --> 05:53:55.919
He joked.

05:53:55.979 --> 05:53:59.400
Besides, if I have a choice, I think I'd

05:53:59.400 --> 05:54:02.400
rather be on the side with any talons of

05:54:02.400 --> 05:54:03.540
power and fire, frankly.

05:54:03.659 --> 05:54:06.360
Cliff Cliff.

05:54:06.419 --> 05:54:09.180
Tourmaline came bounding over the crowd

05:54:09.180 --> 05:54:11.220
barreling through sky wings with her

05:54:11.220 --> 05:54:11.939
wings spread.

05:54:12.060 --> 05:54:14.580
She landed on the boulder and swept Cliff

05:54:14.580 --> 05:54:15.180
up in her arms.

05:54:15.240 --> 05:54:17.340
Did you see that?

05:54:17.400 --> 05:54:18.900
Mommy won.

05:54:19.020 --> 05:54:21.900
He wriggled anxiously, trying to see her

05:54:21.900 --> 05:54:22.259
face.

05:54:22.319 --> 05:54:25.080
But where is mommy?

05:54:25.139 --> 05:54:26.279
He pleaded.

05:54:26.340 --> 05:54:28.200
You don't look like mommy.

05:54:28.259 --> 05:54:29.580
I want her.

05:54:29.639 --> 05:54:33.659
Tourmaline winced, set him down gently

05:54:33.659 --> 05:54:34.680
and looked over at peril.

05:54:34.740 --> 05:54:37.619
Scarlet's blood had almost turned her

05:54:37.619 --> 05:54:40.259
scales back to red, but the rain spilled

05:54:40.259 --> 05:54:42.360
over her wings and back, revealing

05:54:42.360 --> 05:54:44.159
Tourmaline's unfamiliar orange again.

05:54:44.220 --> 05:54:46.680
Do you know how this happened?

05:54:46.740 --> 05:54:48.180
She asked peril.

05:54:48.240 --> 05:54:49.680
Do you know who can fix it?

05:54:49.740 --> 05:54:51.119
Fix it?

05:54:51.180 --> 05:54:52.860
Peril asked.

05:54:52.919 --> 05:54:55.080
She skewered chameleon with her gaze as

05:54:55.080 --> 05:54:56.700
he started to sidle off.

05:54:56.759 --> 05:55:00.720
Yes, change me back into Ruby, said the

05:55:00.720 --> 05:55:01.080
new queen.

05:55:01.200 --> 05:55:04.080
Behind her back, Chameleon shook his head

05:55:04.080 --> 05:55:06.659
furiously, and clasped his front talons

05:55:06.659 --> 05:55:08.880
together, like he was begging peril to

05:55:08.880 --> 05:55:09.299
keep quiet.

05:55:09.360 --> 05:55:11.939
Peril blinked away raindrops.

05:55:12.060 --> 05:55:15.119
You, you want to be Ruby again?

05:55:15.180 --> 05:55:18.060
I am Ruby.

05:55:18.180 --> 05:55:19.619
Tourmaline answered.

05:55:19.680 --> 05:55:21.599
I remember everything about being her.

05:55:21.720 --> 05:55:24.000
All I need is to look like her again.

05:55:24.060 --> 05:55:27.419
But don't you want to be yourself?

05:55:27.479 --> 05:55:28.020
Peril asked.

05:55:28.080 --> 05:55:30.599
The real true actual tourmaline?

05:55:30.720 --> 05:55:33.900
Tourmaline put one wing around Cliff and

05:55:33.900 --> 05:55:34.619
shook her head.

05:55:34.680 --> 05:55:36.479
I will be myself.

05:55:36.540 --> 05:55:39.959
Ruby is the sky wing queen, and Cliff's

05:55:39.959 --> 05:55:40.200
mother.

05:55:40.259 --> 05:55:42.900
Now that I know the truth about my sister

05:55:42.900 --> 05:55:44.400
about me.

05:55:44.459 --> 05:55:47.400
I can be even better at both of those

05:55:47.400 --> 05:55:47.700
things.

05:55:47.759 --> 05:55:52.560
If I show her what chameleon can do, I'll

05:55:52.560 --> 05:55:54.360
be giving another queen his power.

05:55:54.419 --> 05:55:57.540
He could fly away right now with no one

05:55:57.540 --> 05:55:59.639
the wiser about his scroll or his shape

05:55:59.639 --> 05:56:00.180
shifting.

05:56:00.240 --> 05:56:03.540
But if I let him do that, no one will

05:56:03.540 --> 05:56:05.880
know what he's doing with it, he could

05:56:05.880 --> 05:56:07.319
end up working for another terrible

05:56:07.319 --> 05:56:07.740
queen.

05:56:07.799 --> 05:56:10.439
I guess it comes down to who I trust

05:56:10.439 --> 05:56:10.799
more.

05:56:10.860 --> 05:56:15.060
My new queen, who always hated me, or my

05:56:15.060 --> 05:56:17.700
father, who betrayed me as soon as he met

05:56:17.700 --> 05:56:17.880
me.

05:56:17.939 --> 05:56:22.680
She thought about clay, and loyalty, and

05:56:22.680 --> 05:56:24.240
everything he'd ever said about the

05:56:24.240 --> 05:56:26.580
family you make, and the dragons you

05:56:26.580 --> 05:56:28.560
should trust, and how to make the world

05:56:28.560 --> 05:56:29.639
safer for everyone.

05:56:29.700 --> 05:56:33.119
Peril sprang across the boulder and

05:56:33.119 --> 05:56:35.040
cornered chameleon just before he could

05:56:35.040 --> 05:56:35.459
take off.

05:56:35.520 --> 05:56:39.000
This is the dragon you need, your

05:56:39.000 --> 05:56:39.540
majesty.

05:56:39.599 --> 05:56:43.319
The Queen took them to a quiet library

05:56:43.319 --> 05:56:45.840
room of the palace, lined with scroll

05:56:45.840 --> 05:56:48.659
jars, desks, and wooden sculptures of

05:56:48.659 --> 05:56:51.060
trees that made peril very nervous, but

05:56:51.060 --> 05:56:52.439
it was private enough that they wouldn't

05:56:52.439 --> 05:56:52.979
be interrupted.

05:56:53.040 --> 05:56:55.919
She kept her wings and tail tucked in

05:56:55.919 --> 05:56:58.020
close to her, and ignored her father when

05:56:58.020 --> 05:57:00.720
he noticed and gave her a significant, I

05:57:00.720 --> 05:57:02.459
can still help you with that Look.

05:57:02.520 --> 05:57:06.060
Show the queen, Pearl said to him.

05:57:06.180 --> 05:57:07.979
Do I have to?

05:57:07.979 --> 05:57:08.939
he asked.

05:57:09.000 --> 05:57:11.759
Yes said Tourmaline.

05:57:11.819 --> 05:57:14.639
Let's ask my talons.

05:57:14.700 --> 05:57:17.459
Pearl said, lifting them up and nodding

05:57:17.459 --> 05:57:18.779
thoughtfully at them.

05:57:18.840 --> 05:57:20.099
Oh, guess what?

05:57:20.220 --> 05:57:21.900
They say yes too.

05:57:21.959 --> 05:57:23.759
Cliff giggled.

05:57:23.819 --> 05:57:25.680
He and Turtle were the only other 2

05:57:25.680 --> 05:57:27.659
allowed in the room, and both watched

05:57:27.659 --> 05:57:30.360
curiously as Chameleon undid his metal

05:57:30.360 --> 05:57:30.779
sheath again.

05:57:30.840 --> 05:57:34.139
This time, he did not reach for his pouch

05:57:34.139 --> 05:57:36.479
of shapes, and Peril decided not to point

05:57:36.479 --> 05:57:36.840
that out.

05:57:36.900 --> 05:57:40.020
She could leave him one secret, since he

05:57:40.020 --> 05:57:40.860
loved them so much.

05:57:40.979 --> 05:57:44.220
But he did bring out the scroll, and

05:57:44.220 --> 05:57:45.840
undid the leather binding with an

05:57:45.840 --> 05:57:46.680
aggrieved sigh.

05:57:46.740 --> 05:57:49.680
Carefully, he unrolled the blank end of

05:57:49.680 --> 05:57:50.279
it along the floor.

05:57:50.340 --> 05:57:52.860
This is what I use.

05:57:52.919 --> 05:57:53.880
He said.

05:57:54.000 --> 05:57:55.919
It's animus touched.

05:57:56.040 --> 05:57:58.680
Tourmaline tilted her head at it.

05:57:58.740 --> 05:58:01.020
Where did it come from?

05:58:01.080 --> 05:58:05.159
I found it, he said evasively.

05:58:05.220 --> 05:58:07.740
All I have to do is write an enchantment

05:58:07.740 --> 05:58:08.159
in here.

05:58:08.220 --> 05:58:10.799
Tear it off, and give it to you to wear

05:58:10.799 --> 05:58:12.540
in whatever way you want.

05:58:12.599 --> 05:58:15.000
Then as long as you wear it, you'll be

05:58:15.000 --> 05:58:16.680
whatever the enchantment says you are.

05:58:16.740 --> 05:58:20.040
Chameleon straightened his shoulders, and

05:58:20.040 --> 05:58:22.080
gave Tourmaline a sly, sideways look.

05:58:22.200 --> 05:58:25.979
In fact, I could make you anything, he

05:58:25.979 --> 05:58:26.340
offered.

05:58:26.459 --> 05:58:29.220
For the right price, I can make you

05:58:29.220 --> 05:58:29.819
invincible.

05:58:29.880 --> 05:58:32.580
I can make you as strong as 10 dragons.

05:58:32.639 --> 05:58:35.880
I might even be able to make you a mind

05:58:35.880 --> 05:58:36.419
reader.

05:58:36.479 --> 05:58:38.520
Imagine the possibilities.

05:58:38.580 --> 05:58:40.560
What have you always dreamed of being?

05:58:40.619 --> 05:58:43.259
Don't trust him.

05:58:43.380 --> 05:58:44.639
Peril interjected.

05:58:44.700 --> 05:58:49.259
Queen, said Tourmaline, both as

05:58:49.259 --> 05:58:51.840
Tourmaline and as Ruby, that was what I

05:58:51.840 --> 05:58:54.000
always wanted to become, and I did.

05:58:54.060 --> 05:58:56.040
Without any strange magic.

05:58:56.159 --> 05:58:58.619
She tapped the scroll.

05:58:58.680 --> 05:59:02.099
I wanted to say, turn this dragon back

05:59:02.099 --> 05:59:05.040
into Ruby, Queen of the Sky Wings, with

05:59:05.040 --> 05:59:06.540
all her memories intact.

05:59:06.599 --> 05:59:08.220
That's it?

05:59:08.279 --> 05:59:10.319
Chameleon said irritably.

05:59:10.380 --> 05:59:11.939
No superpowers?

05:59:12.000 --> 05:59:15.180
That's it, Tourmaline said.

05:59:15.240 --> 05:59:17.759
I want to watch you write it.

05:59:17.819 --> 05:59:18.299
Do it now.

05:59:18.419 --> 05:59:21.779
She leaned over his shoulder, staring

05:59:21.779 --> 05:59:23.520
narrowly at the page as he dipped his

05:59:23.520 --> 05:59:26.279
claw in a small ink pot, and wrote in

05:59:26.279 --> 05:59:27.959
scratching crooked handwriting.

05:59:28.020 --> 05:59:30.720
As soon as he was finished, he blew on

05:59:30.720 --> 05:59:33.360
the paper, tore out the written part, and

05:59:33.360 --> 05:59:34.259
passed it to the queen.

05:59:34.319 --> 05:59:36.360
Check this for me.

05:59:36.479 --> 05:59:39.900
Tourmaline said, holding it out for peril

05:59:39.900 --> 05:59:41.159
and turtle to examine.

05:59:41.220 --> 05:59:45.000
You saw me ride it, Chameleon protested.

05:59:45.060 --> 05:59:47.099
When could I have snuck in any extra

05:59:47.099 --> 05:59:48.060
instructions?

05:59:48.180 --> 05:59:51.180
Turtle took the paper and studied it on

05:59:51.180 --> 05:59:53.340
both sides, bringing it close to his

05:59:53.340 --> 05:59:53.700
eyes.

05:59:53.759 --> 05:59:56.340
It said exactly what Tourmaline had asked

05:59:56.340 --> 05:59:56.520
for.

05:59:56.639 --> 06:00:00.119
I think it's the best possible solution

06:00:00.119 --> 06:00:02.880
he said, handing it back to Tourmaline.

06:00:02.939 --> 06:00:04.200
Peril nodded.

06:00:04.259 --> 06:00:06.000
If this was what the queen really

06:00:06.000 --> 06:00:06.479
wanted.

06:00:06.540 --> 06:00:07.919
She wasn't going to argue.

06:00:07.979 --> 06:00:09.540
She could understand it.

06:00:09.599 --> 06:00:13.860
But as for herself, she was staying peril

06:00:13.860 --> 06:00:16.979
exactly the way she was, fire scales and

06:00:16.979 --> 06:00:17.279
all.

06:00:17.400 --> 06:00:20.220
No more magic shortcuts to becoming a

06:00:20.220 --> 06:00:20.880
better dragon.

06:00:20.939 --> 06:00:23.520
For clay or for any other reason.

06:00:23.580 --> 06:00:27.060
In the end, it didn't matter what other

06:00:27.060 --> 06:00:28.020
dragons thought of her.

06:00:28.080 --> 06:00:31.080
What mattered was learning to accept the

06:00:31.080 --> 06:00:34.080
dragon she was, and then making herself

06:00:34.080 --> 06:00:35.459
the dragon she wanted to be.

06:00:35.520 --> 06:00:39.060
The long, hard, real way.

06:00:39.119 --> 06:00:43.500
Chapter 19.

06:00:43.680 --> 06:00:47.520
This doesn't feel like a normal Skywing

06:00:47.520 --> 06:00:50.340
party somehow, Peril said to Queen Ruby.

06:00:50.400 --> 06:00:53.159
That's because it's missing all the fun

06:00:53.159 --> 06:00:55.439
brutal murder parts, Queen Ruby

06:00:55.439 --> 06:00:55.860
explained.

06:00:55.919 --> 06:00:58.619
They were standing on the top level of

06:00:58.619 --> 06:01:01.200
the great hall, looking down at a mass of

06:01:01.200 --> 06:01:03.000
dancing, singing sky wings.

06:01:03.060 --> 06:01:06.119
Peril watched them hug and spin, and clap

06:01:06.119 --> 06:01:08.040
wings with one another, and thought

06:01:08.040 --> 06:01:10.560
wistfully of the full moon festival, and

06:01:10.560 --> 06:01:12.060
how she might never get to dance with

06:01:12.060 --> 06:01:15.000
anyone in her entire life, even if she

06:01:15.000 --> 06:01:16.860
could ever talk clay into it.

06:01:16.919 --> 06:01:18.299
She had a feeling he was the kind of

06:01:18.299 --> 06:01:20.340
dragon with 4 left talons.

06:01:20.400 --> 06:01:23.040
I mean, Ruby went on.

06:01:23.099 --> 06:01:25.799
Think about how Scarlet's parties usually

06:01:25.799 --> 06:01:27.479
went, or what they were for.

06:01:27.540 --> 06:01:30.659
Actually, you'll sleep better if you

06:01:30.659 --> 06:01:31.259
don't know.

06:01:31.319 --> 06:01:34.020
She added to Turtle, that was true.

06:01:34.080 --> 06:01:36.060
Pearl shivered.

06:01:36.119 --> 06:01:38.580
Parties for executions, parties for

06:01:38.580 --> 06:01:41.340
thrillingly bloody arena days, parties

06:01:41.340 --> 06:01:43.979
for Scarlet's hatching day, or Burns

06:01:43.979 --> 06:01:46.380
visits that featured all kinds of dragon

06:01:46.380 --> 06:01:47.639
killing entertainment.

06:01:47.700 --> 06:01:50.159
The Sky Kingdom probably hadn't seen a

06:01:50.159 --> 06:01:52.200
party in 20 years that didn't revolve

06:01:52.200 --> 06:01:54.180
around Scarlet's gladiator fetish.

06:01:54.299 --> 06:01:57.060
But the Sky Wings were making up for it

06:01:57.060 --> 06:01:57.299
now.

06:01:57.419 --> 06:02:00.659
Somehow about 8 orchestras worth of

06:02:00.659 --> 06:02:03.000
percussion and stringed instruments had

06:02:03.000 --> 06:02:04.799
materialized over the course of the day.

06:02:04.860 --> 06:02:07.560
Now that night had fallen and the storm

06:02:07.560 --> 06:02:10.259
had passed, music filled the halls of a

06:02:10.259 --> 06:02:12.540
palace that had once reverberated only

06:02:12.540 --> 06:02:14.580
with the shrieks of burning dragons.

06:02:14.639 --> 06:02:17.220
Peril looked down at her claws.

06:02:17.340 --> 06:02:19.200
Your Majesty?

06:02:19.259 --> 06:02:21.900
I, I'm sorry about the eggs on the

06:02:21.900 --> 06:02:22.560
brightest night.

06:02:22.619 --> 06:02:25.979
Stop, Ruby said.

06:02:26.040 --> 06:02:28.200
She drew Cliff closer under her wing.

06:02:28.319 --> 06:02:31.259
He'd insisted on staying up till midnight

06:02:31.259 --> 06:02:33.060
and he looked a lot more awake than

06:02:33.060 --> 06:02:35.220
turtle who kept yawning and leaning on

06:02:35.220 --> 06:02:35.459
things.

06:02:35.520 --> 06:02:39.419
Listen, you were only a dragonette.

06:02:39.479 --> 06:02:42.840
Not much older than Cliff, and Scarlet

06:02:42.840 --> 06:02:45.360
was the only parent you ever had, or

06:02:45.360 --> 06:02:46.259
friend, or anything.

06:02:46.380 --> 06:02:49.680
None of the rest of us even tried to see

06:02:49.680 --> 06:02:50.759
you as a real dragon.

06:02:50.819 --> 06:02:53.759
I saw a weapon, and that was it.

06:02:53.880 --> 06:02:57.599
But now, I think about what could happen

06:02:57.599 --> 06:02:59.880
to Cliff, if he'd been born with fire

06:02:59.880 --> 06:03:02.400
scales, or if my mother had gotten her

06:03:02.400 --> 06:03:03.119
claws into him.

06:03:03.180 --> 06:03:06.779
I think a lot about how he'll turn out

06:03:06.779 --> 06:03:08.220
with me as his mother.

06:03:08.279 --> 06:03:09.779
So I don't blame you anymore.

06:03:09.840 --> 06:03:13.740
Gosh, I do, Pearl said.

06:03:13.799 --> 06:03:17.040
All the things I, I mean, if you just do

06:03:17.040 --> 06:03:19.319
the arena numbers, plus the random

06:03:19.319 --> 06:03:22.319
dragons she disliked, and all the burning

06:03:22.319 --> 06:03:24.720
and then you think, peril.

06:03:24.779 --> 06:03:28.139
Turtle interrupted, this might be one of

06:03:28.139 --> 06:03:31.139
those instances where less detail is the

06:03:31.139 --> 06:03:31.500
way to go.

06:03:31.560 --> 06:03:33.959
I know it was bad.

06:03:34.020 --> 06:03:37.439
Ruby said, but you can make up for what

06:03:37.439 --> 06:03:37.979
you've done.

06:03:38.040 --> 06:03:39.900
At least you can try.

06:03:39.959 --> 06:03:41.759
If we let you try.

06:03:41.819 --> 06:03:44.520
Oh, peril said.

06:03:44.580 --> 06:03:45.779
You bet.

06:03:45.840 --> 06:03:46.919
Of course I'll try.

06:03:46.979 --> 06:03:49.319
I just need a few more epic battles to

06:03:49.319 --> 06:03:51.240
the death that I can throw myself into.

06:03:51.299 --> 06:03:53.700
Point me at some more dragonettes in

06:03:53.700 --> 06:03:55.979
distress or viper bites I can tackle.

06:03:56.040 --> 06:03:58.560
I'm also great at toasting squirrels and

06:03:58.560 --> 06:04:00.840
boiling water anytime you need either of

06:04:00.840 --> 06:04:01.020
those.

06:04:01.080 --> 06:04:04.439
Ruby laughed, then glanced at her

06:04:04.439 --> 06:04:06.180
dragonette, and looked serious again.

06:04:06.240 --> 06:04:09.000
This should be obvious to everyone who

06:04:09.000 --> 06:04:11.159
saw you save Cliff, she added.

06:04:11.220 --> 06:04:13.200
But just to make it official.

06:04:13.259 --> 06:04:15.060
You are no longer banished.

06:04:15.119 --> 06:04:17.340
You are welcome throughout the sky

06:04:17.340 --> 06:04:19.500
kingdom and anywhere Cliff and I go.

06:04:19.560 --> 06:04:22.020
If you want to move back to the palace

06:04:22.020 --> 06:04:22.439
you can.

06:04:22.560 --> 06:04:26.639
Oh, Peril said, oddly embarrassed.

06:04:26.700 --> 06:04:27.900
Thanks.

06:04:28.020 --> 06:04:29.459
I'll think about it.

06:04:29.520 --> 06:04:31.259
Is this it?

06:04:31.319 --> 06:04:34.020
Is this what being a hero feels like?

06:04:34.080 --> 06:04:37.200
Is this what clay and tsunami and Sunny

06:04:37.200 --> 06:04:38.099
feel like every day?

06:04:38.159 --> 06:04:42.119
I thought I'd be more... different.

06:04:42.180 --> 06:04:44.520
I thought suddenly it would be easier to

06:04:44.520 --> 06:04:44.880
be good.

06:04:44.939 --> 06:04:48.299
I thought it would come naturally, once I

06:04:48.299 --> 06:04:51.060
did enough good things, or the right big

06:04:51.060 --> 06:04:52.020
good thing.

06:04:52.080 --> 06:04:54.959
But I still feel just as muddled about

06:04:54.959 --> 06:04:55.799
what to do next.

06:04:55.919 --> 06:05:00.060
And I kind of still want to set that

06:05:00.060 --> 06:05:02.700
guard over there on fire because I swear

06:05:02.700 --> 06:05:03.779
he's laughing at me.

06:05:03.840 --> 06:05:06.540
Not to mention, there are lots of

06:05:06.540 --> 06:05:08.759
wonderfully vengeful things I could do to

06:05:08.759 --> 06:05:10.860
chameleon that keep parading through my

06:05:10.860 --> 06:05:11.159
brain.

06:05:11.279 --> 06:05:13.500
Speaking of chameleon.

06:05:13.560 --> 06:05:16.619
Pearl frowned down at a commotion on the

06:05:16.619 --> 06:05:17.220
level below them.

06:05:17.279 --> 06:05:21.360
Your Majesty, she said, isn't that one of

06:05:21.360 --> 06:05:23.040
the guards who is supposed to be keeping

06:05:23.040 --> 06:05:25.740
an eye on com- er sore?

06:05:26.520 --> 06:05:27.900
Queen Ruby didn't have to answer.

06:05:27.959 --> 06:05:30.360
The guard was now swooping up toward them

06:05:30.360 --> 06:05:31.799
with a terribly alarmed expression.

06:05:31.860 --> 06:05:35.759
I'm sorry. she cried, landing next to the

06:05:35.759 --> 06:05:36.060
Queen.

06:05:36.119 --> 06:05:37.979
I don't know what happened.

06:05:38.040 --> 06:05:39.299
I know you said not to let any other

06:05:39.299 --> 06:05:42.000
dragons in or out, but suddenly there was

06:05:42.000 --> 06:05:45.779
a night wing there, a really big one, and

06:05:45.779 --> 06:05:48.720
he came from inside the room, and I don't

06:05:48.720 --> 06:05:50.939
know how he got in there, and he knocked

06:05:50.939 --> 06:05:53.520
out Harrier with his tail in one blow, and

06:05:53.520 --> 06:05:55.560
then he flew off and the sky wing was

06:05:55.560 --> 06:05:55.799
gone.

06:05:55.860 --> 06:05:58.020
I'm sorry, I'm so, so sorry.

06:05:58.080 --> 06:06:01.200
She flung herself into a deep, abject

06:06:01.200 --> 06:06:01.500
bow.

06:06:01.560 --> 06:06:05.099
On the other side of the queen, Turtle

06:06:05.099 --> 06:06:07.200
sat up, all his sleepiness gone.

06:06:07.319 --> 06:06:10.080
He looked much more worried and much less

06:06:10.080 --> 06:06:12.599
puddle like than usual.

06:06:12.659 --> 06:06:15.299
Queen Ruby reached out and raised the

06:06:15.299 --> 06:06:16.380
guard to standing.

06:06:16.439 --> 06:06:18.900
I'm not going to hurt you, she said.

06:06:18.959 --> 06:06:21.959
We didn't expect him to run, so it's my

06:06:21.959 --> 06:06:23.159
own fault for not taking more

06:06:23.159 --> 06:06:24.060
precautions.

06:06:24.119 --> 06:06:25.799
Go make sure Harrier is all right.

06:06:25.860 --> 06:06:29.340
The guards' face was all relief from

06:06:29.340 --> 06:06:32.040
snout to horns as she bowed and flew away

06:06:32.040 --> 06:06:32.279
again.

06:06:32.340 --> 06:06:34.919
How worried should I be?

06:06:34.979 --> 06:06:37.080
Queen Ruby asked peril.

06:06:37.139 --> 06:06:39.419
What do you know about that dragon?

06:06:39.479 --> 06:06:41.459
Peril had thought there would be more

06:06:41.459 --> 06:06:41.819
time.

06:06:41.880 --> 06:06:44.040
Time to tell her queen everything.

06:06:44.159 --> 06:06:47.220
Time to make chameleon feel safe here, and

06:06:47.220 --> 06:06:49.139
figure out what to do with him, and how

06:06:49.139 --> 06:06:50.939
to deal with the scroll.

06:06:51.000 --> 06:06:52.560
She hadn't thought he would bolt the 1st

06:06:52.560 --> 06:06:53.220
chance he got.

06:06:53.279 --> 06:06:56.580
Without saying goodbye, without thinking

06:06:56.580 --> 06:06:58.319
about me at all, maybe.

06:06:58.319 --> 06:07:01.799
I know he's really a rain wing, she

06:07:01.799 --> 06:07:02.459
confessed.

06:07:02.520 --> 06:07:05.400
He could use that scroll for anything, but

06:07:05.400 --> 06:07:07.560
so far, he mostly only uses it for shape

06:07:07.560 --> 06:07:08.040
shifting.

06:07:08.099 --> 06:07:10.500
I think because he could never change his

06:07:10.500 --> 06:07:12.119
scales when he was a rain wing.

06:07:12.240 --> 06:07:14.520
I don't think he would do evil things

06:07:14.520 --> 06:07:15.419
with it on his own.

06:07:15.540 --> 06:07:17.819
That was just for Scarlet.

06:07:17.880 --> 06:07:20.520
But actually, I don't really know him

06:07:20.520 --> 06:07:20.939
that well.

06:07:21.000 --> 06:07:24.659
He has a night wing shape, Turtle said.

06:07:24.720 --> 06:07:26.759
And he was working for Scarlet?

06:07:26.819 --> 06:07:29.759
Is he the one who hurt Kinkaju?

06:07:29.880 --> 06:07:31.500
Peril flinched.

06:07:31.560 --> 06:07:33.540
Why had she let herself forget about

06:07:33.540 --> 06:07:33.720
that?

06:07:33.779 --> 06:07:37.080
Because he offered me everything I

06:07:37.080 --> 06:07:37.619
thought I wanted?

06:07:37.680 --> 06:07:40.200
Yes, she admitted.

06:07:40.259 --> 06:07:43.259
He hates rain wings because they banished

06:07:43.259 --> 06:07:44.279
him from the rainforest.

06:07:44.340 --> 06:07:47.700
Then we can't let him wander around free

06:07:47.700 --> 06:07:50.040
with a weapon like that, Turtle said.

06:07:50.099 --> 06:07:52.560
I should have taken it from him right

06:07:52.560 --> 06:07:55.619
away, Queen Ruby said, shaking her head.

06:07:55.680 --> 06:07:58.200
I was trying to reward his cooperation.

06:07:58.259 --> 06:08:00.840
All right, I'll send out a search party.

06:08:00.900 --> 06:08:03.419
She saw the anxious expression on

06:08:03.419 --> 06:08:07.080
Turtle's face and added, or 6, 6 search

06:08:07.080 --> 06:08:07.740
parties.

06:08:07.799 --> 06:08:09.779
Don't worry, we'll find him.

06:08:09.840 --> 06:08:12.779
She spread her wings and flew down to the

06:08:12.779 --> 06:08:14.520
throne room with Cliff right behind her.

06:08:14.580 --> 06:08:18.479
We can't wait, Turtle said to Parel.

06:08:18.540 --> 06:08:20.159
We have to go after him right now.

06:08:20.220 --> 06:08:22.979
Yes, she said.

06:08:23.040 --> 06:08:25.680
But, Turtle, one more thing you should

06:08:25.680 --> 06:08:25.919
know.

06:08:25.979 --> 06:08:27.360
He's my father.

06:08:27.419 --> 06:08:29.939
Wow, he said.

06:08:30.000 --> 06:08:33.180
You have had bad luck with parents.

06:08:33.240 --> 06:08:37.080
But good luck with friends, she said

06:08:37.080 --> 06:08:38.279
grinning at him.

06:08:38.279 --> 06:08:41.759
You big sap, he said, and I can't even

06:08:41.759 --> 06:08:42.900
punch you to shut you up.

06:08:42.959 --> 06:08:46.139
You could, she said.

06:08:46.200 --> 06:08:47.880
That would be pretty funny for me.

06:08:47.939 --> 06:08:50.819
He flicked his tail ladder and lifted off

06:08:50.819 --> 06:08:52.860
sailing through the open roof and into

06:08:52.860 --> 06:08:54.299
the star speckled sky.

06:08:54.360 --> 06:08:57.060
Peril followed, feeling the rush of cold

06:08:57.060 --> 06:08:58.740
wind against her blazing wings.

06:08:58.860 --> 06:09:01.560
Every moment that she got farther away

06:09:01.560 --> 06:09:03.599
from that necklace, she felt more and

06:09:03.599 --> 06:09:04.619
more like herself again.

06:09:04.680 --> 06:09:07.319
No more troubling or guilty thoughts

06:09:07.319 --> 06:09:09.959
about Scarlet, nothing but clear memories

06:09:09.959 --> 06:09:10.560
of clay.

06:09:10.680 --> 06:09:13.500
Can I go back to Jade Mountain now?

06:09:13.560 --> 06:09:14.939
Have I done enough?

06:09:15.000 --> 06:09:18.419
The questions somehow felt less pressing

06:09:18.419 --> 06:09:19.259
than they had before.

06:09:19.319 --> 06:09:22.740
She still missed clay very much, but she

06:09:22.740 --> 06:09:25.380
had important things to do, such as find

06:09:25.380 --> 06:09:28.439
her father, get that scroll into talons

06:09:28.439 --> 06:09:30.479
that could be trusted, and maybe help

06:09:30.479 --> 06:09:32.819
turtle and his friends stop some big new

06:09:32.819 --> 06:09:35.340
terrible prophecy if they'd have her.

06:09:35.400 --> 06:09:38.819
If he's a night wing, he'll blend right

06:09:38.819 --> 06:09:39.299
in up here.

06:09:39.419 --> 06:09:42.479
Turtle called to her, lashing his tail in

06:09:42.479 --> 06:09:43.200
frustration.

06:09:43.200 --> 06:09:46.319
One of the moons was almost full, but

06:09:46.319 --> 06:09:48.479
leftover clouds from the storm hid most

06:09:48.479 --> 06:09:49.619
of the moonlight from the mountain

06:09:49.619 --> 06:09:50.159
peaks.

06:09:50.220 --> 06:09:52.080
We need help.

06:09:52.139 --> 06:09:54.180
He angled south abruptly.

06:09:54.240 --> 06:09:56.520
Uh-oh, peril said.

06:09:56.580 --> 06:09:58.560
Tell me we're not off to find a mind

06:09:58.560 --> 06:10:00.479
reader and an ice wing who might be

06:10:00.479 --> 06:10:01.259
holding a grudge.

06:10:01.319 --> 06:10:05.159
I left them in that valley, Turtles said

06:10:05.159 --> 06:10:05.520
pointing.

06:10:05.580 --> 06:10:07.500
They said to signal when I needed them.

06:10:07.560 --> 06:10:10.799
His scales began flashing, and peril

06:10:10.799 --> 06:10:12.479
nearly flew into a cliff, she was so

06:10:12.479 --> 06:10:12.900
startled.

06:10:12.959 --> 06:10:15.479
She knew Seawings had glow in the dark

06:10:15.479 --> 06:10:18.360
scales, but she'd never seen a dragon use

06:10:18.360 --> 06:10:19.080
them at night before.

06:10:19.139 --> 06:10:22.319
Luminescent spirals and shapes like

06:10:22.319 --> 06:10:24.900
webbed talon prints lit up all along his

06:10:24.900 --> 06:10:25.979
wings.

06:10:26.040 --> 06:10:28.259
It was sort of beautiful in a weird, fishy

06:10:28.259 --> 06:10:28.439
way.

06:10:28.560 --> 06:10:32.159
Almost immediately, she saw an answering

06:10:32.159 --> 06:10:34.259
burst of twin flames from the dark valley

06:10:34.259 --> 06:10:34.799
below them.

06:10:34.860 --> 06:10:38.040
Soon after that, 3 shapes rose up to meet

06:10:38.040 --> 06:10:41.459
them, 2 of them pale and ghostly, one

06:10:41.459 --> 06:10:42.840
barely a flicker of shadow.

06:10:42.900 --> 06:10:45.180
You did it?

06:10:45.240 --> 06:10:46.979
Kibley said, as soon as they were close

06:10:46.979 --> 06:10:47.520
enough to talk.

06:10:47.580 --> 06:10:49.979
You actually rescued her?

06:10:50.040 --> 06:10:53.700
Not exactly, Pearl said.

06:10:53.759 --> 06:10:56.759
But thanks very much for the skeptical

06:10:56.759 --> 06:10:58.139
tone, Turtle said.

06:10:58.200 --> 06:11:00.540
Is she safe to be around?

06:11:00.659 --> 06:11:02.159
Winter asked harshly.

06:11:02.220 --> 06:11:03.299
What do you think?

06:11:03.419 --> 06:11:05.400
He tilted his head at Moon.

06:11:05.459 --> 06:11:08.639
I am, Pearl said.

06:11:08.700 --> 06:11:12.299
She thought mushrooms and mongooses at

06:11:12.299 --> 06:11:14.580
the night wing as loud as she could, and

06:11:14.580 --> 06:11:15.900
moon started giggling.

06:11:15.959 --> 06:11:19.500
That seems like a good sign, said Kibley

06:11:19.560 --> 06:11:22.020
giving Moon a smile that reminded peril

06:11:22.020 --> 06:11:23.819
of that night wing who always followed

06:11:23.819 --> 06:11:24.779
Queen Gloria around.

06:11:24.840 --> 06:11:28.619
Guys, we don't have time for a prickly

06:11:28.619 --> 06:11:29.099
reunion.

06:11:29.220 --> 06:11:30.720
Turtle interrupted.

06:11:30.779 --> 06:11:33.840
Scarlet's ally has escaped, and it's

06:11:33.840 --> 06:11:34.619
worse than we thought.

06:11:34.740 --> 06:11:36.060
He's a shapeshifter.

06:11:36.119 --> 06:11:38.939
So he can look like a dragon from any

06:11:38.939 --> 06:11:39.299
tribe.

06:11:39.360 --> 06:11:42.180
And he's got this animus touched scroll

06:11:42.180 --> 06:11:45.000
that can enchant anything, as far as we

06:11:45.000 --> 06:11:45.299
can tell.

06:11:45.360 --> 06:11:49.439
Moon let out a Yelp so loud, it echoed

06:11:49.439 --> 06:11:50.279
off the mountains.

06:11:50.340 --> 06:11:51.840
A scroll?

06:11:51.900 --> 06:11:52.619
she cried.

06:11:52.680 --> 06:11:53.400
Really?

06:11:53.459 --> 06:11:54.540
You're sure?

06:11:54.599 --> 06:11:57.720
Uh, yes, Turtle said.

06:11:57.779 --> 06:11:58.619
We saw it.

06:11:58.680 --> 06:12:02.040
Moon looked deeply agitated now.

06:12:02.099 --> 06:12:05.340
Peril regarded her with new interest, was

06:12:05.340 --> 06:12:07.020
the night wing hiding something from all

06:12:07.020 --> 06:12:07.500
of them?

06:12:07.560 --> 06:12:09.659
Even her alleged friends?

06:12:09.720 --> 06:12:12.060
What do you know about this scroll?

06:12:12.119 --> 06:12:13.139
Peril asked.

06:12:13.259 --> 06:12:15.180
Nothing, Moon said.

06:12:15.240 --> 06:12:17.099
Was it wrapped in a black leather

06:12:17.099 --> 06:12:17.520
casing?

06:12:17.580 --> 06:12:19.560
Yes.

06:12:19.680 --> 06:12:21.720
Turtle said, staring at her.

06:12:21.779 --> 06:12:25.020
Maybe you should tell us all the nothing

06:12:25.020 --> 06:12:27.180
you know about it, Pearl suggested.

06:12:27.240 --> 06:12:31.500
I just, I heard a story once, Moon said

06:12:31.500 --> 06:12:33.779
about a night wing scroll from long ago

06:12:33.779 --> 06:12:35.279
that was animus touched.

06:12:35.340 --> 06:12:37.680
It sounds like this could be the same

06:12:37.680 --> 06:12:38.459
scroll.

06:12:38.580 --> 06:12:41.880
She fidgeted anxiously, twitching her

06:12:41.880 --> 06:12:43.080
tail over her talons.

06:12:43.139 --> 06:12:44.939
That would be bad.

06:12:45.060 --> 06:12:48.840
We would really, really need to get it

06:12:48.840 --> 06:12:50.939
back if it's the same scroll.

06:12:51.900 --> 06:12:52.439
That's what I know.

06:12:52.500 --> 06:12:55.200
I was hoping you could try listening for

06:12:55.200 --> 06:12:55.439
him.

06:12:55.560 --> 06:12:56.580
Turtle said.

06:12:56.639 --> 06:12:59.819
He escaped the palace not long ago, so he

06:12:59.819 --> 06:13:00.659
can't have gone too far.

06:13:00.720 --> 06:13:04.560
He's in his nightwing form, Pearl added

06:13:04.560 --> 06:13:06.060
the one where he calls himself

06:13:06.060 --> 06:13:07.319
Shapeshifter.

06:13:07.380 --> 06:13:10.740
Very subtle, said Kibley.

06:13:10.799 --> 06:13:13.200
Moon said, closing her eyes.

06:13:13.259 --> 06:13:15.479
I don't think I could pick up anything

06:13:15.479 --> 06:13:16.319
from way up here.

06:13:16.380 --> 06:13:19.860
Let's fly along the river, Perl said.

06:13:19.919 --> 06:13:21.900
I have a feeling he's gone that way.

06:13:21.959 --> 06:13:24.000
He said something to me about becoming

06:13:24.000 --> 06:13:24.659
mudwings.

06:13:24.720 --> 06:13:27.360
She saw the hesitation in their wing

06:13:27.360 --> 06:13:27.840
beats.

06:13:27.900 --> 06:13:30.299
Should we trust this dragon?

06:13:30.360 --> 06:13:31.740
Are we really going to follow her?

06:13:31.799 --> 06:13:34.500
But when she turned and swooped away

06:13:34.500 --> 06:13:36.900
Turtle was right beside her, and the

06:13:36.900 --> 06:13:37.979
others weren't far behind.

06:13:38.040 --> 06:13:41.159
Going to the mud wings sounded like the

06:13:41.159 --> 06:13:42.419
next thing her father would do.

06:13:42.479 --> 06:13:45.779
He wouldn't become Sirius again, now that

06:13:45.779 --> 06:13:46.740
peril knew that shape.

06:13:46.799 --> 06:13:48.840
She guessed he wouldn't be comfortable

06:13:48.840 --> 06:13:51.959
underwater, even in a sea wing form, and

06:13:51.959 --> 06:13:53.400
he'd have to worry about keeping the

06:13:53.400 --> 06:13:53.939
scroll dry.

06:13:54.000 --> 06:13:57.180
Going west to the sand wings meant Queen

06:13:57.180 --> 06:13:59.639
Thorn, who already had a reputation as

06:13:59.639 --> 06:14:02.159
someone impossible to corrupt, and she

06:14:02.159 --> 06:14:03.720
couldn't imagine him returning to the

06:14:03.720 --> 06:14:06.479
rainforest, either as a rain wing or a

06:14:06.479 --> 06:14:07.080
night wing.

06:14:07.139 --> 06:14:10.500
But the mud wings were close, and Queen

06:14:10.500 --> 06:14:12.840
Morin had once been Scarlet's ally.

06:14:12.900 --> 06:14:14.880
She might be willing to take in a strange

06:14:14.880 --> 06:14:17.580
dragon, who offered mysterious power in

06:14:17.580 --> 06:14:18.419
exchange for treasure.

06:14:18.479 --> 06:14:21.959
Peril dove toward the Diamond Spray River

06:14:21.959 --> 06:14:24.479
which glimmered like molten silver in the

06:14:24.479 --> 06:14:25.799
places where moonlight broke through.

06:14:25.860 --> 06:14:28.680
She remembered clay swimming away down

06:14:28.680 --> 06:14:31.080
this river with his friends, heading home

06:14:31.080 --> 06:14:33.180
to the mud kingdom, and away from her.

06:14:33.299 --> 06:14:36.119
The memory still made her chest ache.

06:14:36.240 --> 06:14:39.540
But at least, I have that memory.

06:14:39.599 --> 06:14:42.599
Suddenly moon banked right and stopped.

06:14:42.659 --> 06:14:45.720
Hovering in place with her front talons

06:14:45.720 --> 06:14:47.099
pressed to her head.

06:14:47.159 --> 06:14:49.259
After a moment, she lifted one of them

06:14:49.259 --> 06:14:49.740
and pointed.

06:14:49.860 --> 06:14:53.279
I think he's over there, she whispered.

06:14:53.340 --> 06:14:56.279
They slipped after her, gliding as

06:14:56.279 --> 06:14:57.180
quietly as they could.

06:14:57.240 --> 06:15:00.419
In a clearing by the river, fiddling with

06:15:00.419 --> 06:15:02.700
something in his talons, hulked a large

06:15:02.700 --> 06:15:03.540
black shape.

06:15:03.659 --> 06:15:07.619
He made himself enormous, peril thought

06:15:07.619 --> 06:15:10.619
the kind of scary nightwing everyone is

06:15:10.619 --> 06:15:11.639
always whispered about.

06:15:11.700 --> 06:15:15.000
Kibli flicked his wing to catch her eye

06:15:15.000 --> 06:15:17.400
then pointed to each of them, conveying

06:15:17.400 --> 06:15:18.360
silent instructions.

06:15:18.419 --> 06:15:21.360
A moment later, they landed in a circle

06:15:21.360 --> 06:15:22.200
around Chameleon.

06:15:22.259 --> 06:15:25.380
Peril's talons were only an inch from his

06:15:25.380 --> 06:15:25.680
tail.

06:15:25.740 --> 06:15:28.740
Don't move, she said.

06:15:28.799 --> 06:15:33.180
Chapter 20.

06:15:33.360 --> 06:15:36.840
The night wing reared up, flaring his

06:15:36.840 --> 06:15:39.659
wings, and he was so big and unfamiliar

06:15:39.659 --> 06:15:42.119
and angry looking, that peril had a brief

06:15:42.119 --> 06:15:44.159
moment of fear that they had cornered the

06:15:44.159 --> 06:15:44.880
wrong dragon.

06:15:44.939 --> 06:15:48.599
No, that's him all right, Moon said.

06:15:48.659 --> 06:15:49.439
I'm sure.

06:15:49.500 --> 06:15:52.860
Then peril saw the pouch of shapeshifting

06:15:52.860 --> 06:15:54.900
jewelry at his feet, and the case that

06:15:54.900 --> 06:15:56.400
held the scroll around his chest.

06:15:56.459 --> 06:15:58.020
This was definitely him.

06:15:58.080 --> 06:16:01.020
Father, peril shouted.

06:16:01.080 --> 06:16:01.919
Stop.

06:16:01.979 --> 06:16:04.020
I don't want to hurt you, but I will.

06:16:04.139 --> 06:16:05.939
And so will we.

06:16:06.060 --> 06:16:07.619
Winter hissed.

06:16:07.680 --> 06:16:09.840
The sound of frost breath gathering under

06:16:09.840 --> 06:16:10.200
his words.

06:16:10.259 --> 06:16:14.220
Chameleon froze, but peril still had

06:16:14.220 --> 06:16:16.080
never seen such a look of fury and

06:16:16.080 --> 06:16:17.099
disgust on him before.

06:16:17.159 --> 06:16:21.299
That's him, Winter said to Kibley and

06:16:21.299 --> 06:16:21.720
Turtle.

06:16:21.779 --> 06:16:24.540
That's the dragon who attacked us, and

06:16:24.540 --> 06:16:25.740
wounded Kinkachu.

06:16:25.799 --> 06:16:29.340
Turtle growled softly in his throat, and

06:16:29.340 --> 06:16:31.979
Kibley raised his venomous tail, digging

06:16:31.979 --> 06:16:33.659
his claws into the muddy river bank.

06:16:33.720 --> 06:16:36.959
But that's impossible, Min said.

06:16:37.020 --> 06:16:39.659
We hit him with my fire and your frost

06:16:39.659 --> 06:16:40.080
breath.

06:16:40.139 --> 06:16:43.139
This dragon has no scars, no injuries

06:16:43.139 --> 06:16:43.619
nothing.

06:16:43.680 --> 06:16:47.159
It's the enchantment, Kibley guessed.

06:16:47.220 --> 06:16:50.040
It probably starts to shape off new and

06:16:50.040 --> 06:16:51.000
uninjured every time.

06:16:51.060 --> 06:16:53.939
He just has to take it off, and all the

06:16:53.939 --> 06:16:54.720
wounds disappear.

06:16:54.779 --> 06:16:57.840
Then when he puts it back on, the scroll

06:16:57.840 --> 06:16:59.459
makes him a night wing, purr the

06:16:59.459 --> 06:17:00.540
instructions all over again.

06:17:00.659 --> 06:17:03.119
No lasting damage, ever.

06:17:03.180 --> 06:17:06.060
That's useful, said Pearl.

06:17:06.119 --> 06:17:08.400
She remembered how Ruby's injuries had

06:17:08.400 --> 06:17:10.200
disappeared when she turned back into

06:17:10.200 --> 06:17:10.979
Tourmaline.

06:17:11.040 --> 06:17:12.180
Is that right?

06:17:12.299 --> 06:17:15.900
Chameleon breathed a small spire of smoke

06:17:15.900 --> 06:17:17.040
then nodded.

06:17:17.099 --> 06:17:19.740
She wished he would say something, instead

06:17:19.740 --> 06:17:21.959
of just glaring at all of them, at her

06:17:21.959 --> 06:17:24.000
especially, with those narrow black

06:17:24.000 --> 06:17:24.540
eyes.

06:17:24.599 --> 06:17:28.139
Listen, she said, we just want the

06:17:28.139 --> 06:17:28.619
scroll.

06:17:28.680 --> 06:17:30.000
No.

06:17:30.119 --> 06:17:31.319
He spat.

06:17:31.439 --> 06:17:33.540
Spike's bristling all along his back.

06:17:33.659 --> 06:17:38.159
Actually, I want the scroll and justice

06:17:38.159 --> 06:17:39.180
Winter said.

06:17:39.299 --> 06:17:41.580
I think he should pay for what he did to

06:17:41.580 --> 06:17:42.299
Kinka Jew.

06:17:42.360 --> 06:17:45.180
Me too, said Turtle.

06:17:45.240 --> 06:17:48.840
Me too, said Moon, but the scroll is the

06:17:48.840 --> 06:17:49.500
most important thing.

06:17:49.560 --> 06:17:53.220
And I think taking it from him will be

06:17:53.220 --> 06:17:55.259
punishment enough, said Peril.

06:17:55.319 --> 06:17:57.959
Winter snorted disbelievingly, and she

06:17:57.959 --> 06:17:58.560
ignored him.

06:17:58.619 --> 06:18:01.380
I'm sorry, father, but you can't keep

06:18:01.380 --> 06:18:01.680
it.

06:18:01.740 --> 06:18:03.540
Not after what you've done with it.

06:18:03.599 --> 06:18:05.040
We can't trust you.

06:18:05.099 --> 06:18:09.419
I won't do anything terrible, he said.

06:18:09.479 --> 06:18:12.240
I was only following Scarlet's orders.

06:18:12.299 --> 06:18:13.500
You know all about that.

06:18:13.560 --> 06:18:16.680
You weren't following her orders when you

06:18:16.680 --> 06:18:18.119
put Kinkaju in the hospital.

06:18:18.180 --> 06:18:19.319
Kibley observed.

06:18:19.380 --> 06:18:20.700
That was all you.

06:18:20.819 --> 06:18:24.659
And you could have chosen me over her

06:18:24.659 --> 06:18:27.060
once you knew we were family, Pearl

06:18:27.060 --> 06:18:27.299
said.

06:18:27.360 --> 06:18:29.880
You didn't have to betray me by taking

06:18:29.880 --> 06:18:30.599
away my memories.

06:18:30.720 --> 06:18:33.900
You could have also stayed and been loyal

06:18:33.900 --> 06:18:36.119
to Queen Ruby, but it's clear you're not

06:18:36.119 --> 06:18:36.659
planning on that.

06:18:36.720 --> 06:18:39.540
You've had choices, and we haven't seen

06:18:39.540 --> 06:18:40.860
you make any good ones yet.

06:18:40.919 --> 06:18:45.000
But this is an easy one, Moon said.

06:18:45.060 --> 06:18:47.880
Give us the scroll, and we let you go.

06:18:47.939 --> 06:18:53.040
Or don't give us the scroll, said Kibley

06:18:53.040 --> 06:18:55.500
and get another face full of flames and

06:18:55.500 --> 06:18:56.700
frost breath.

06:18:56.759 --> 06:18:59.040
Wow, try saying that 5 times fast.

06:18:59.099 --> 06:19:02.400
You'll still have your treasure, Pearl

06:19:02.400 --> 06:19:04.860
said, and she would leave him the scraps

06:19:04.860 --> 06:19:06.659
of scroll he'd already enchanted with his

06:19:06.659 --> 06:19:08.220
different shapes.

06:19:08.279 --> 06:19:10.919
He could still be sore, and shapeshifter

06:19:10.919 --> 06:19:13.080
and Sirius, and whoever else, when he

06:19:13.080 --> 06:19:14.220
didn't want to be chameleon.

06:19:14.279 --> 06:19:16.560
She knew what it was like to wish for

06:19:16.560 --> 06:19:18.840
different scales, and she knew how much

06:19:18.840 --> 06:19:21.240
he needed them, as a rain wing with no

06:19:21.240 --> 06:19:22.380
scale shifting powers.

06:19:22.439 --> 06:19:24.959
You'll keep having your great life

06:19:24.959 --> 06:19:26.400
wherever you decide to go.

06:19:26.459 --> 06:19:28.680
You just won't be able to hurt anyone

06:19:28.680 --> 06:19:28.979
else.

06:19:29.040 --> 06:19:31.319
Winter hissed again.

06:19:31.380 --> 06:19:34.560
But it's mine, Chameleon said.

06:19:34.619 --> 06:19:36.659
Clutching the metal sheath to his chest.

06:19:36.720 --> 06:19:38.340
I found it.

06:19:38.400 --> 06:19:39.900
I get to keep it.

06:19:39.959 --> 06:19:41.580
Why should you have it?

06:19:41.639 --> 06:19:44.700
What makes you all any better than me?

06:19:44.759 --> 06:19:47.580
Peril didn't really know the answer to

06:19:47.580 --> 06:19:48.060
that question.

06:19:48.119 --> 06:19:50.639
Was she any better than her father?

06:19:50.700 --> 06:19:53.639
Did she know these other dragonettes well

06:19:53.639 --> 06:19:54.840
enough to say that they were?

06:19:54.900 --> 06:19:57.479
What would they do with power like that?

06:19:57.540 --> 06:19:59.520
But she knew one thing.

06:19:59.580 --> 06:20:01.740
She couldn't leave it with Chameleon.

06:20:01.799 --> 06:20:04.319
Give it to us, she said.

06:20:04.380 --> 06:20:06.959
Please don't make us fight you for it.

06:20:07.020 --> 06:20:09.840
Or do, said Winter.

06:20:09.900 --> 06:20:10.919
I'm ready.

06:20:10.979 --> 06:20:14.099
You think you can hurt me?

06:20:14.159 --> 06:20:15.540
Chameleon snarled.

06:20:15.599 --> 06:20:18.180
But I've made some modifications to this

06:20:18.180 --> 06:20:21.180
shape since we last met Ice Wing.

06:20:21.240 --> 06:20:23.700
Shapeshifter already has strength beyond

06:20:23.700 --> 06:20:24.419
any dragon.

06:20:24.479 --> 06:20:27.540
But now I also have scales that cannot be

06:20:27.540 --> 06:20:30.119
harmed, and flames as hot as my

06:20:30.119 --> 06:20:31.020
daughter's scales.

06:20:31.139 --> 06:20:34.319
I foresee a pretty horrible death ahead

06:20:34.319 --> 06:20:35.279
for most of you.

06:20:35.340 --> 06:20:37.680
Peril felt sick.

06:20:37.740 --> 06:20:39.900
Why hadn't she seen this?

06:20:39.959 --> 06:20:41.880
Dangerous power hungry side of him

06:20:41.880 --> 06:20:42.119
before.

06:20:42.180 --> 06:20:44.939
She didn't want anything bad to happen to

06:20:44.939 --> 06:20:45.479
Turtle.

06:20:45.540 --> 06:20:48.240
She was pretty sure she'd even be able to

06:20:48.240 --> 06:20:50.220
muster some sadness if anything happened

06:20:50.220 --> 06:20:50.759
to winter.

06:20:50.819 --> 06:20:53.819
But father, she started.

06:20:53.880 --> 06:20:55.740
What's happening?

06:20:55.799 --> 06:20:57.299
Chameleon suddenly shouted.

06:20:57.360 --> 06:20:59.580
He scrabbled at his chest?

06:20:59.639 --> 06:21:00.659
How are you doing that?

06:21:00.720 --> 06:21:01.860
Stop.

06:21:01.919 --> 06:21:02.520
It's mine.

06:21:02.580 --> 06:21:06.180
Peril stepped back in astonishment as the

06:21:06.180 --> 06:21:08.639
sheath unbuckled itself and started to

06:21:08.639 --> 06:21:10.740
wriggle free of the hulking night wing's

06:21:10.740 --> 06:21:11.279
talons.

06:21:11.340 --> 06:21:13.259
Chameleon held on to it desperately.

06:21:13.319 --> 06:21:15.479
No, he roared.

06:21:15.540 --> 06:21:16.860
You can't take it.

06:21:16.919 --> 06:21:20.580
The metal sheath hesitated, poised in the

06:21:20.580 --> 06:21:22.319
air as if it were trying to launch itself

06:21:22.319 --> 06:21:24.900
out of Chameleon's claws, and then it

06:21:24.900 --> 06:21:27.180
pivoted abruptly and bashed him in the

06:21:27.180 --> 06:21:27.360
face.

06:21:27.419 --> 06:21:31.439
Chameleon yowled with pain, let go of the

06:21:31.439 --> 06:21:33.720
scroll and fell back, covering his snout

06:21:33.720 --> 06:21:34.619
with his talons.

06:21:34.680 --> 06:21:36.599
Blood was running from one of his eyes.

06:21:36.659 --> 06:21:39.779
The sheath bashed him in the face once

06:21:39.779 --> 06:21:42.119
more, with what looked like the force of

06:21:42.119 --> 06:21:44.880
a mountain behind it, Chameleon shrieked

06:21:44.880 --> 06:21:46.799
and Perl guessed that several of the

06:21:46.799 --> 06:21:48.240
bones in his snout were broken.

06:21:48.299 --> 06:21:51.000
That's enough, she cried.

06:21:51.060 --> 06:21:53.580
She knew that soon he'd recover from the

06:21:53.580 --> 06:21:55.740
shock and gathered the strength to take

06:21:55.740 --> 06:21:58.020
off his night wing shape, and then he'd

06:21:58.020 --> 06:21:58.979
be healed instantly.

06:21:59.040 --> 06:22:01.680
But it was still beyond horrible to see

06:22:01.680 --> 06:22:02.580
him suffering like that.

06:22:02.700 --> 06:22:05.639
No matter what he'd done, she believed

06:22:05.639 --> 06:22:07.319
there was a part of him that had wanted

06:22:07.319 --> 06:22:07.919
to help her.

06:22:07.979 --> 06:22:10.020
That had wanted to be a family.

06:22:10.080 --> 06:22:13.799
For a moment, the sheath hovered in the

06:22:13.799 --> 06:22:16.020
air, as if considering whether to listen

06:22:16.020 --> 06:22:19.020
to her, and then it spun slowly, and

06:22:19.020 --> 06:22:21.299
floated over to land in turtles' talons.

06:22:21.360 --> 06:22:23.040
Let's go.

06:22:23.159 --> 06:22:24.299
He said.

06:22:24.360 --> 06:22:27.060
They all spread their wings and lift it

06:22:27.060 --> 06:22:27.599
off at once.

06:22:27.659 --> 06:22:30.419
Peril swerved to make sure she stayed

06:22:30.419 --> 06:22:31.500
clear of the others.

06:22:31.560 --> 06:22:33.840
That scroll is mine.

06:22:33.900 --> 06:22:36.720
Chameleon screamed as they flew into the

06:22:36.720 --> 06:22:37.439
dark clouds.

06:22:37.500 --> 06:22:39.419
I'll find you.

06:22:39.479 --> 06:22:40.500
I'll take it back.

06:22:40.560 --> 06:22:41.819
You'll be sorry.

06:22:41.880 --> 06:22:43.259
It's mine.

06:22:43.319 --> 06:22:44.639
It's mine, it's mine.

06:22:44.700 --> 06:22:48.599
Peril glanced left at Turtle's determined

06:22:48.599 --> 06:22:51.360
jawline, and then right, at Moon's

06:22:51.360 --> 06:22:52.619
nervously twitching talons.

06:22:52.680 --> 06:22:55.319
Now that they had the most dangerous

06:22:55.319 --> 06:22:56.340
scroll in Pyria.

06:22:56.459 --> 06:22:58.619
What were they going to do with it?

06:22:58.680 --> 06:23:03.240
They flew south for a long time before it

06:23:03.240 --> 06:23:04.200
felt safe enough to stop.

06:23:04.259 --> 06:23:07.319
Peril kept imagining she could hear a

06:23:07.319 --> 06:23:09.119
shapeshifter's ominous wing beats

06:23:09.119 --> 06:23:10.139
following them.

06:23:10.200 --> 06:23:12.119
But soon they came to a part of the

06:23:12.119 --> 06:23:14.939
mountains that was jagged with canyons

06:23:14.939 --> 06:23:17.279
and steep ravines, and at the bottom of

06:23:17.279 --> 06:23:19.500
one of these, they found a cave deep

06:23:19.500 --> 06:23:21.779
enough to crawl into and set a fire

06:23:21.779 --> 06:23:23.580
without anyone seeing them from above.

06:23:23.639 --> 06:23:27.000
Moon caught some kind of mountain cat for

06:23:27.000 --> 06:23:29.220
them to eat, and they huddled against the

06:23:29.220 --> 06:23:31.500
stone walls, listening to the rain that

06:23:31.500 --> 06:23:33.180
had started again outside.

06:23:33.240 --> 06:23:37.020
Peril ate her portion in a famished rush

06:23:37.020 --> 06:23:38.639
keeping herself on the far side of the

06:23:38.639 --> 06:23:39.419
fire from the others.

06:23:39.479 --> 06:23:42.119
Even if Turtle still had his ridiculous

06:23:42.119 --> 06:23:44.700
healing rock, she imagined it wouldn't go

06:23:44.700 --> 06:23:46.080
over well if she burned any of them

06:23:46.080 --> 06:23:46.319
again.

06:23:46.380 --> 06:23:49.439
Turtle put the scroll carefully on top of

06:23:49.439 --> 06:23:51.180
a ledge at the back of the cave.

06:23:51.240 --> 06:23:54.360
Everyone kept looking at it, although

06:23:54.360 --> 06:23:55.979
Pearl thought that Moon had the most

06:23:55.979 --> 06:23:57.720
interesting range of expressions about

06:23:57.720 --> 06:23:57.900
it.

06:23:57.959 --> 06:24:00.119
What did that one mean?

06:24:00.180 --> 06:24:01.319
And that one.

06:24:01.380 --> 06:24:03.060
What was she thinking?

06:24:03.119 --> 06:24:06.659
You didn't have to do that, turtle, Moon

06:24:06.659 --> 06:24:08.700
said finally. breaking the silence.

06:24:08.759 --> 06:24:11.700
You shouldn't use your animus power if

06:24:11.700 --> 06:24:12.119
you can help it.

06:24:12.180 --> 06:24:15.419
Maybe, you shouldn't use it ever.

06:24:15.479 --> 06:24:16.979
Aren't you worried about your soul?

06:24:17.099 --> 06:24:18.360
How do you feel?

06:24:18.419 --> 06:24:22.799
A little cold, he said with a shrug.

06:24:22.860 --> 06:24:25.680
But only the tiniest bit evil.

06:24:25.740 --> 06:24:29.939
I'm serious, she protested, as Kibley

06:24:29.939 --> 06:24:30.419
laughed.

06:24:30.479 --> 06:24:32.279
I read about what happened with

06:24:32.279 --> 06:24:33.119
Albatross.

06:24:33.180 --> 06:24:36.959
My murderous ancestor, I know, Turtle

06:24:36.959 --> 06:24:37.200
said.

06:24:37.259 --> 06:24:39.720
But my enchantments have been so small

06:24:39.720 --> 06:24:42.000
and I feel exactly the same as I always

06:24:42.000 --> 06:24:42.360
have.

06:24:42.419 --> 06:24:44.759
I think you'll notice if I start turning

06:24:44.759 --> 06:24:45.479
homicidal.

06:24:45.540 --> 06:24:48.299
Moon did not look in the least bit

06:24:48.299 --> 06:24:49.080
reassured.

06:24:49.139 --> 06:24:52.860
It's all right to use animus magic, if

06:24:52.860 --> 06:24:54.959
you're careful about it, Winter said.

06:24:55.020 --> 06:24:58.619
In the eyes kingdom, our animus dragons

06:24:58.619 --> 06:25:00.479
used to spend their lives planning one

06:25:00.479 --> 06:25:02.400
enchantment that would benefit the whole

06:25:02.400 --> 06:25:02.759
tribe.

06:25:02.819 --> 06:25:05.819
They used their magic once for something

06:25:05.819 --> 06:25:08.520
beautiful and useful, and they were fine

06:25:08.520 --> 06:25:09.540
all the rest of their lives.

06:25:09.599 --> 06:25:11.340
Huh.

06:25:11.400 --> 06:25:12.720
Kibley said.

06:25:12.779 --> 06:25:15.000
I thought I heard something about an

06:25:15.000 --> 06:25:18.180
animus ice wing queen went crazy once, a

06:25:18.180 --> 06:25:19.020
long, long time ago.

06:25:19.080 --> 06:25:22.979
Oh, Winter said, shifting on his talons.

06:25:23.040 --> 06:25:25.740
Maybe, but she...

06:25:26.340 --> 06:25:28.860
Well, she used her magic more than she

06:25:28.860 --> 06:25:29.340
was supposed to.

06:25:29.400 --> 06:25:31.860
If it's the queen I'm guessing it was

06:25:31.860 --> 06:25:32.340
anyway.

06:25:32.400 --> 06:25:34.919
What do we do with this scroll now?

06:25:34.919 --> 06:25:36.180
Pearl asked.

06:25:36.240 --> 06:25:38.220
Should we take it back to Jade Mountain

06:25:38.220 --> 06:25:40.380
and give it to Clay and the others?

06:25:40.439 --> 06:25:41.819
She added hurriedly.

06:25:41.880 --> 06:25:44.459
Maybe, Turtle said.

06:25:44.520 --> 06:25:47.099
But I'm not sure anyone should have this

06:25:47.099 --> 06:25:49.439
much power, no matter how good we think

06:25:49.439 --> 06:25:49.799
they are.

06:25:49.860 --> 06:25:51.779
It can't be good for your soul.

06:25:51.840 --> 06:25:55.740
I think a very wise and good dragon would

06:25:55.740 --> 06:25:56.880
know how to use it the right way.

06:25:56.939 --> 06:25:59.099
Kibli objected.

06:25:59.159 --> 06:26:00.299
I think we should give it to Queen

06:26:00.299 --> 06:26:00.779
Thorn.

06:26:00.840 --> 06:26:03.840
Maybe we should give it to Queen Glacier

06:26:03.840 --> 06:26:04.799
Winter snapped.

06:26:04.860 --> 06:26:07.919
We shouldn't give it to anyone, Moon

06:26:07.919 --> 06:26:08.340
said.

06:26:08.459 --> 06:26:10.619
It already belongs to someone.

06:26:10.680 --> 06:26:13.560
The fire crackled in the silence that

06:26:13.560 --> 06:26:16.139
fell. devouring the scraps of wood they

06:26:16.139 --> 06:26:16.860
had found to burn.

06:26:16.919 --> 06:26:20.639
Everyone was watching Moon now, and Perel

06:26:20.639 --> 06:26:21.779
wondered what she could hear in their

06:26:21.779 --> 06:26:22.319
minds.

06:26:22.380 --> 06:26:23.939
What do you mean?

06:26:24.060 --> 06:26:25.860
Winter asked finally.

06:26:25.919 --> 06:26:28.380
Just as Kibley said, who?

06:26:28.439 --> 06:26:31.619
The animus dragon who made it, Moon

06:26:31.619 --> 06:26:32.040
said.

06:26:32.099 --> 06:26:35.580
He put all his power into that scroll, so

06:26:35.580 --> 06:26:36.959
that he could use his magic without

06:26:36.959 --> 06:26:39.419
damaging his soul, which is pretty smart

06:26:39.419 --> 06:26:39.659
right?

06:26:39.720 --> 06:26:42.240
He was trying to protect the world from

06:26:42.240 --> 06:26:45.240
whatever he might become, or give himself

06:26:45.240 --> 06:26:47.819
unlimited power, Winter observed.

06:26:47.880 --> 06:26:50.279
But doesn't it seem like a good idea?

06:26:50.340 --> 06:26:51.479
Moon asked.

06:26:51.599 --> 06:26:54.540
If his magic doesn't turn him evil, he'll

06:26:54.540 --> 06:26:55.919
only do good things with it, right?

06:26:56.040 --> 06:26:57.720
Doesn't?

06:26:57.779 --> 06:26:58.919
Kibli echoed.

06:26:58.979 --> 06:27:01.740
Moon, I thought you said this was some

06:27:01.740 --> 06:27:02.580
ancient legend.

06:27:02.700 --> 06:27:05.099
So why are you using the present tense?

06:27:05.220 --> 06:27:09.779
Because, she started, then hesitated and

06:27:09.779 --> 06:27:10.439
started again.

06:27:10.500 --> 06:27:12.659
Because he's still alive.

06:27:12.779 --> 06:27:14.220
Who?

06:27:14.279 --> 06:27:16.200
Winter said, rising to his feet.

06:27:16.259 --> 06:27:20.220
And he's trapped, she said, her words

06:27:20.220 --> 06:27:21.840
suddenly spilling out like smoke.

06:27:21.900 --> 06:27:24.659
I started hearing his voice in my head

06:27:24.659 --> 06:27:26.220
when I got to Jade Mountain.

06:27:26.279 --> 06:27:29.220
He stuck underground somewhere, and he's

06:27:29.220 --> 06:27:31.439
starving and alone, and he just wants to

06:27:31.439 --> 06:27:33.599
get out, and the scroll is the one thing

06:27:33.599 --> 06:27:35.099
that could help him do that.

06:27:35.159 --> 06:27:37.860
So I said, I said I'd look for it.

06:27:37.919 --> 06:27:40.080
And give it back to him?

06:27:40.200 --> 06:27:42.900
Turtle said, then answered himself.

06:27:42.959 --> 06:27:45.540
Actually, I guess that's fair.

06:27:45.599 --> 06:27:47.700
It is his magic after all.

06:27:47.759 --> 06:27:52.319
Moon, Winter growled, his voice low and

06:27:52.319 --> 06:27:54.659
ominous, who is he?

06:27:54.720 --> 06:27:58.139
Well, she said.

06:27:58.200 --> 06:28:00.119
First, I want you to remember that

06:28:00.119 --> 06:28:02.639
everything you know about him is 2000

06:28:02.639 --> 06:28:05.400
years old and comes from stories told by

06:28:05.400 --> 06:28:06.720
the dragons who defeated him.

06:28:06.779 --> 06:28:09.419
You don't really know him, even if you

06:28:09.419 --> 06:28:10.020
think you do.

06:28:10.080 --> 06:28:12.119
Dark stalker?

06:28:12.180 --> 06:28:15.060
Winter roared, are you serious?

06:28:15.119 --> 06:28:19.200
There's no need to yell, Kibley said

06:28:19.200 --> 06:28:20.159
standing up as well.

06:28:20.220 --> 06:28:23.279
If the dark stalker is trapped and

06:28:23.279 --> 06:28:25.680
starving and alone, that is exactly what

06:28:25.680 --> 06:28:27.479
he deserves, Winter said.

06:28:27.540 --> 06:28:29.159
Oh, really?

06:28:29.220 --> 06:28:30.240
Moon countered.

06:28:30.299 --> 06:28:32.880
What about the misunderstood nightwing

06:28:32.880 --> 06:28:33.720
that you set free?

06:28:33.779 --> 06:28:36.540
Wasn't she a legendary enemy of the ice

06:28:36.540 --> 06:28:37.020
wings too?

06:28:37.080 --> 06:28:40.560
Yes, but she didn't have horrible powers

06:28:40.560 --> 06:28:41.639
Winter said.

06:28:41.700 --> 06:28:44.880
Moon's wings flew open, and she rose onto

06:28:44.880 --> 06:28:46.560
her back legs, growling.

06:28:46.619 --> 06:28:48.419
Horrible powers?

06:28:48.479 --> 06:28:51.180
You mean mind reading and visions of the

06:28:51.180 --> 06:28:51.659
future?

06:28:51.720 --> 06:28:53.459
You mean my horrible powers?

06:28:53.580 --> 06:28:57.959
And, uh, winter trailed off, glancing at

06:28:57.959 --> 06:28:58.380
turtle.

06:28:58.439 --> 06:29:02.459
And my horrible power, turtle finished.

06:29:02.520 --> 06:29:07.319
Well, peril said, flexing our talons, at

06:29:07.319 --> 06:29:08.159
least he doesn't have mine.

06:29:08.220 --> 06:29:12.240
He killed his own father, Winter said

06:29:12.240 --> 06:29:16.200
rallying to his argument again, our ice

06:29:16.200 --> 06:29:18.840
wing prince. isn't your whole tribe

06:29:18.840 --> 06:29:19.500
terrified of him?

06:29:19.560 --> 06:29:23.459
Yes, Moon admitted, but they don't know

06:29:23.459 --> 06:29:23.759
him either.

06:29:23.819 --> 06:29:26.459
And you do?

06:29:26.580 --> 06:29:27.599
Kibley asked.

06:29:27.659 --> 06:29:30.119
The question hung in the air.

06:29:30.180 --> 06:29:32.939
And Peril noticed for the 1st time, the

06:29:32.939 --> 06:29:34.799
intensity in Kibley's eyes as he looked

06:29:34.799 --> 06:29:35.279
at Moon.

06:29:35.400 --> 06:29:38.580
She couldn't interpret it exactly, but

06:29:38.580 --> 06:29:40.020
she got the feeling there were several

06:29:40.020 --> 06:29:42.000
layers to the question he was asking

06:29:42.060 --> 06:29:45.419
layers like, if he's so important to you

06:29:45.419 --> 06:29:47.159
why didn't you tell us about him before?

06:29:47.220 --> 06:29:51.180
And one she especially recognized, do you

06:29:51.180 --> 06:29:52.200
like him better than me?

06:29:52.259 --> 06:29:54.779
Moon looked away 1st.

06:29:54.840 --> 06:29:57.479
Maybe, she said.

06:29:57.540 --> 06:29:58.560
I think so.

06:29:58.619 --> 06:29:59.700
I don't know.

06:29:59.759 --> 06:30:03.479
I can't let you use this scroll to free

06:30:03.479 --> 06:30:04.500
the dark stalker.

06:30:04.560 --> 06:30:05.520
Winter said.

06:30:05.580 --> 06:30:10.020
What you can't do is order me around, Moon

06:30:10.020 --> 06:30:10.799
said sharply.

06:30:10.860 --> 06:30:13.979
What you can do instead is have a

06:30:13.979 --> 06:30:16.380
rational conversation with me, and listen

06:30:16.380 --> 06:30:18.479
to me, and try to talk me out of it if

06:30:18.479 --> 06:30:18.779
you must.

06:30:18.840 --> 06:30:22.680
But not right now, Turtle said.

06:30:22.740 --> 06:30:26.400
Right now, we should all sleep, and then

06:30:26.400 --> 06:30:27.840
we can talk about it in the morning.

06:30:27.900 --> 06:30:28.680
All right?

06:30:28.740 --> 06:30:31.319
I agree, Kibley said.

06:30:31.439 --> 06:30:33.659
Fine, said Moon.

06:30:33.720 --> 06:30:36.180
Fine. said Winter.

06:30:36.240 --> 06:30:39.959
Peril found herself wondering again, if

06:30:39.959 --> 06:30:41.700
friends might be more trouble than they

06:30:41.700 --> 06:30:42.060
were worth.

06:30:42.119 --> 06:30:45.360
She was quite glad she was not snarled up

06:30:45.360 --> 06:30:45.779
in this fight.

06:30:45.840 --> 06:30:49.680
I'll sleep outside, she offered, standing

06:30:49.680 --> 06:30:50.040
up.

06:30:50.099 --> 06:30:51.900
In the rain?

06:30:51.959 --> 06:30:52.979
Turtle asked.

06:30:53.040 --> 06:30:54.659
It won't bother me.

06:30:54.720 --> 06:30:57.060
Pearl said, and I've been told I'm a

06:30:57.060 --> 06:30:57.840
restless sleeper.

06:30:57.900 --> 06:31:01.860
Oh, Turtle said, eyeing her wings

06:31:01.860 --> 06:31:02.580
nervously.

06:31:02.639 --> 06:31:05.040
In that case, sure, absolutely.

06:31:05.099 --> 06:31:05.819
You bet.

06:31:05.880 --> 06:31:06.540
Great plan.

06:31:06.599 --> 06:31:09.240
Peril shot him a grin as she went out of

06:31:09.240 --> 06:31:10.259
the cave into the rain.

06:31:10.319 --> 06:31:12.900
There was a somewhat sheltered spot at

06:31:12.900 --> 06:31:14.819
the base of the cliff, and she huddled

06:31:14.819 --> 06:31:17.340
there, thinking about the scroll and the

06:31:17.340 --> 06:31:20.040
argument, and whatever this dark stalker

06:31:20.040 --> 06:31:22.259
was, until she finally fell asleep.

06:31:22.319 --> 06:31:26.159
And for the 1st time in years, Her dreams

06:31:26.159 --> 06:31:26.819
were peaceful.

06:31:26.939 --> 06:31:30.479
No furious queen Scarlet chased her

06:31:30.479 --> 06:31:32.099
through winding hallways with too many

06:31:32.099 --> 06:31:33.180
doors.

06:31:33.240 --> 06:31:35.040
Nobody burned between her talons.

06:31:35.099 --> 06:31:38.700
There was no fire, no smoke, no death or

06:31:38.700 --> 06:31:42.959
screaming, just long, quiet, dreamless

06:31:42.959 --> 06:31:43.919
slumber.

06:31:43.979 --> 06:31:46.979
Peril, peril.

06:31:47.040 --> 06:31:49.740
She was awoken by something poking her

06:31:49.740 --> 06:31:51.720
gently in the shoulder, followed by

06:31:51.720 --> 06:31:55.020
turtle yelling, ah, and leaping backward

06:31:55.020 --> 06:31:57.299
as the stick he'd poked her with burst

06:31:57.299 --> 06:32:00.360
into flames, peril stretched, yawning.

06:32:00.479 --> 06:32:02.819
Well, what did you think was going to

06:32:02.819 --> 06:32:03.900
happen?

06:32:03.900 --> 06:32:04.380
she asked.

06:32:04.439 --> 06:32:07.380
And then she noticed the 2 serious faces

06:32:07.380 --> 06:32:08.759
lined up behind Turtle.

06:32:08.819 --> 06:32:11.580
Uh-oh, she said.

06:32:11.639 --> 06:32:14.880
Moon's gone, said Turtle, and she's taken

06:32:14.880 --> 06:32:15.720
the scroll with her.

06:32:15.779 --> 06:32:20.159
Chapter 21.

06:32:20.340 --> 06:32:24.060
The world after the storm was dazzling

06:32:24.060 --> 06:32:27.240
sunbeams glinted off all the new puddles

06:32:27.240 --> 06:32:29.340
and the sky felt as though it had just

06:32:29.340 --> 06:32:30.900
taken a dive in a lake.

06:32:30.959 --> 06:32:33.599
It seems as if more dragons were out

06:32:33.599 --> 06:32:35.279
flying than peril had seen in ages.

06:32:35.340 --> 06:32:38.099
Everyone wanted to spread their wings in

06:32:38.099 --> 06:32:38.759
the beautiful air.

06:32:38.819 --> 06:32:41.580
She saw a lot of sky wings, especially

06:32:41.580 --> 06:32:43.799
and realized guiltily that they should

06:32:43.799 --> 06:32:45.779
have let Queen Ruby know the scroll was

06:32:45.779 --> 06:32:46.200
safe.

06:32:46.259 --> 06:32:49.619
Except, apparently, it wasn't very safe

06:32:49.619 --> 06:32:50.340
after all.

06:32:50.400 --> 06:32:52.380
She wouldn't.

06:32:52.439 --> 06:32:55.680
Winter fretted as they flew south, she

06:32:55.680 --> 06:32:56.520
wouldn't.

06:32:56.580 --> 06:32:59.819
Kimley was silent for once, deep in

06:32:59.819 --> 06:33:00.119
thought.

06:33:00.240 --> 06:33:05.459
Uh, Turtle said, maybe she, I thought we

06:33:05.459 --> 06:33:07.619
were all going to talk about it, Winter

06:33:07.619 --> 06:33:08.099
yelled.

06:33:08.159 --> 06:33:10.560
Maybe she didn't think you'd be a good

06:33:10.560 --> 06:33:12.360
listener, Pearl suggested.

06:33:12.419 --> 06:33:15.299
I mean, I haven't known you very long, and

06:33:15.299 --> 06:33:16.560
even I can already see that.

06:33:16.619 --> 06:33:21.360
I listen, Winter growled, when there is

06:33:21.360 --> 06:33:22.319
something worth hearing.

06:33:22.439 --> 06:33:25.619
Yeah, I don't think that's the same thing

06:33:25.619 --> 06:33:27.779
Pearl said, shaking her head.

06:33:27.900 --> 06:33:30.240
You can fly faster than us.

06:33:30.299 --> 06:33:32.279
Kibley said suddenly.

06:33:32.340 --> 06:33:34.560
He twisted himself in the air so he could

06:33:34.560 --> 06:33:35.279
look at peril.

06:33:35.340 --> 06:33:37.439
You can fly faster than her.

06:33:37.500 --> 06:33:39.180
Maybe you can catch her.

06:33:39.240 --> 06:33:42.419
Oh, yes, Pearl said.

06:33:42.479 --> 06:33:43.319
Probably.

06:33:43.380 --> 06:33:44.880
You guys are slow pokes.

06:33:44.939 --> 06:33:46.979
It's like flying with a trio of banana

06:33:46.979 --> 06:33:47.639
slugs.

06:33:47.700 --> 06:33:50.700
So go, Turtle said wildly.

06:33:50.759 --> 06:33:53.880
Fly as fast as you can, stop her before

06:33:53.880 --> 06:33:55.200
she sets him free.

06:33:55.319 --> 06:33:58.500
Um, all right, Peril said.

06:33:58.560 --> 06:34:00.599
Except how do I do that?

06:34:00.659 --> 06:34:04.319
Just tell her what a bad idea it is

06:34:04.319 --> 06:34:05.400
Winter said.

06:34:05.459 --> 06:34:08.759
Ah, okay, Pearl said.

06:34:08.819 --> 06:34:11.880
So stop her with words.

06:34:11.939 --> 06:34:16.380
Well, write, don't set her on fire, Turtle

06:34:16.380 --> 06:34:16.680
said.

06:34:16.740 --> 06:34:18.299
Let's be clear about that.

06:34:18.360 --> 06:34:19.919
Are you sure?

06:34:19.979 --> 06:34:20.880
Parel said.

06:34:20.939 --> 06:34:22.319
It would be very efficient.

06:34:22.380 --> 06:34:24.000
I bet it would stop her right away.

06:34:24.060 --> 06:34:25.979
Just a tiny bit of her tail.

06:34:26.040 --> 06:34:27.900
I'm kidding, I'm kidding.

06:34:27.959 --> 06:34:31.919
She hadn't exactly been kidding, but she

06:34:31.919 --> 06:34:33.360
could tell from the expressions on their

06:34:33.360 --> 06:34:35.520
faces that she'd better act as though she

06:34:35.520 --> 06:34:35.759
was.

06:34:35.819 --> 06:34:38.819
Not that she wanted to use her fire

06:34:38.819 --> 06:34:41.220
scales on moon, but if the alternative

06:34:41.220 --> 06:34:43.439
was some big ancient nightmare dragon

06:34:43.439 --> 06:34:45.900
rising from the earth, then shouldn't all

06:34:45.900 --> 06:34:46.799
the options be open?

06:34:46.860 --> 06:34:49.979
Kibley looked close to panicked, though

06:34:49.979 --> 06:34:52.080
and winter was giving her the most

06:34:52.080 --> 06:34:55.080
suspicious, untrusting face, and even

06:34:55.080 --> 06:34:57.180
turtle looked worried about this plan, so

06:34:57.180 --> 06:34:58.619
no.

06:34:58.680 --> 06:35:01.319
The answer was evidently, let the

06:35:01.319 --> 06:35:03.119
nightmare dragon escape rather than

06:35:03.119 --> 06:35:05.099
harming even one of Moon's scales.

06:35:05.159 --> 06:35:08.939
If she insists on doing it, Tell her at

06:35:08.939 --> 06:35:11.220
least to wait for us, Kibli pleaded.

06:35:11.279 --> 06:35:12.959
Tell her she shouldn't release him

06:35:12.959 --> 06:35:13.259
alone.

06:35:13.319 --> 06:35:17.520
All right, Pearl said, flicking her wings

06:35:17.520 --> 06:35:19.080
to rise to a higher up draft.

06:35:19.139 --> 06:35:20.279
I'll try.

06:35:20.340 --> 06:35:24.000
But I suspect, I might be exactly the

06:35:24.000 --> 06:35:25.259
wrong dragon for this particular

06:35:25.259 --> 06:35:25.919
mission.

06:35:25.979 --> 06:35:28.740
She'll be close to Jade Mountain

06:35:28.740 --> 06:35:30.659
somewhere, Kibley called after her.

06:35:30.720 --> 06:35:33.119
He must be buried near there if that's

06:35:33.119 --> 06:35:33.779
where she could hear him.

06:35:33.840 --> 06:35:36.900
Got it, Parel called back.

06:35:36.959 --> 06:35:39.599
She was surprised when she hadn't caught

06:35:39.599 --> 06:35:40.919
up with Moon by midday.

06:35:40.979 --> 06:35:43.259
Either the night wing had a much bigger

06:35:43.259 --> 06:35:45.720
head start than peril had guessed, or she

06:35:45.720 --> 06:35:47.400
flew a lot faster than peril would have

06:35:47.400 --> 06:35:47.639
expected.

06:35:47.759 --> 06:35:51.180
Peril stopped only once, to drink from a

06:35:51.180 --> 06:35:53.279
mountain lake, and spent the rest of the

06:35:53.279 --> 06:35:54.840
day flying as fast as she could.

06:35:54.900 --> 06:35:58.919
She was exhausted when the 1st stars of

06:35:58.919 --> 06:36:01.259
the evening began to emerge, and she saw

06:36:01.259 --> 06:36:03.180
Jade Mountain starting to fill the sky

06:36:03.180 --> 06:36:03.840
ahead of her.

06:36:03.900 --> 06:36:07.619
Clays in there, she thought, with a

06:36:07.619 --> 06:36:08.520
thrill of excitement.

06:36:08.580 --> 06:36:10.439
I could see him tonight.

06:36:10.500 --> 06:36:12.419
I can tell him everything that's

06:36:12.419 --> 06:36:12.959
happened.

06:36:13.020 --> 06:36:16.080
But 1st, she had to stop Moon.

06:36:16.139 --> 06:36:19.200
Carol slowed down as she got closer to

06:36:19.200 --> 06:36:20.099
Jade Mountain.

06:36:20.159 --> 06:36:22.500
She began to scan the peaks around her

06:36:22.500 --> 06:36:24.840
with her eagle sharp eyes, looking for

06:36:24.840 --> 06:36:25.680
unusual movements.

06:36:25.740 --> 06:36:29.400
Once she swooped down, only to discover

06:36:29.400 --> 06:36:30.959
an extremely startled moose.

06:36:31.020 --> 06:36:33.900
The 2nd time, she nearly got a snout full

06:36:33.900 --> 06:36:35.040
of porcupine quills.

06:36:35.099 --> 06:36:38.520
But on her 3rd try, she found the dragon

06:36:38.520 --> 06:36:39.419
she was looking for.

06:36:39.540 --> 06:36:41.700
Moon wasn't exactly hiding.

06:36:41.759 --> 06:36:44.340
She was sitting on a grassy slope on the

06:36:44.340 --> 06:36:46.439
western side of a mountain not far from

06:36:46.439 --> 06:36:47.459
Jade Mountain.

06:36:47.459 --> 06:36:50.459
The sunset cast golden rays over her

06:36:50.459 --> 06:36:53.220
huddled form, and her shadow sloped like

06:36:53.220 --> 06:36:55.740
a long 2nd tail up the hill behind her.

06:36:55.799 --> 06:36:59.040
Peril looped around overhead, studying

06:36:59.040 --> 06:37:01.560
the ground around Moon, until she spotted

06:37:01.560 --> 06:37:03.419
a boulder where she could safely land.

06:37:03.479 --> 06:37:06.180
It wobbled slightly as she thumped down

06:37:06.180 --> 06:37:08.340
threatening to tumble into the narrow

06:37:08.340 --> 06:37:10.500
ravine nearby, but she steadied it with

06:37:10.500 --> 06:37:11.159
her claws.

06:37:11.220 --> 06:37:12.720
The night wing didn't look up.

06:37:12.779 --> 06:37:15.659
She was curled over the scroll, reading

06:37:15.659 --> 06:37:17.939
it so intently that her claws were

06:37:17.939 --> 06:37:19.439
crushing the binding where she held it.

06:37:19.500 --> 06:37:24.119
Um, Peril said, so, hello.

06:37:24.180 --> 06:37:26.639
I've been instructed not to set you on

06:37:26.639 --> 06:37:29.340
fire, in case you were worried, she added

06:37:29.340 --> 06:37:30.000
hastily.

06:37:30.000 --> 06:37:33.419
Moon raised her head, and peril realized

06:37:33.419 --> 06:37:34.860
that her eyes were full of tears.

06:37:34.919 --> 06:37:37.799
In fact, her whole face was full of

06:37:37.799 --> 06:37:38.159
tears.

06:37:38.220 --> 06:37:40.439
She looked as if she'd been crying for a

06:37:40.439 --> 06:37:40.680
while.

06:37:40.740 --> 06:37:43.740
Yikes, Pearl said.

06:37:43.799 --> 06:37:47.520
I'd offer you a hug, but I just wanted to

06:37:47.520 --> 06:37:49.500
hear him again, Moon said.

06:37:49.560 --> 06:37:52.919
I wanted to tell him we found it, to talk

06:37:52.919 --> 06:37:55.380
to him, and remember why I trusted him.

06:37:55.439 --> 06:37:58.860
But then I started reading, and he

06:37:58.860 --> 06:38:01.200
clearly didn't want me to, and I found

06:38:01.200 --> 06:38:01.560
this.

06:38:01.680 --> 06:38:05.099
She trailed off, touching the scroll with

06:38:05.099 --> 06:38:06.240
one mournful claw.

06:38:06.360 --> 06:38:09.000
Pearl tilted her head at the paper.

06:38:09.060 --> 06:38:11.279
She could see that Moon was on the page

06:38:11.279 --> 06:38:13.439
where the writing stopped, and the rest

06:38:13.439 --> 06:38:15.959
of the scroll was blank, but she couldn't

06:38:15.959 --> 06:38:18.000
read the letters from where she was, and

06:38:18.000 --> 06:38:19.319
she didn't dare get any closer.

06:38:19.380 --> 06:38:21.419
What does it say?

06:38:21.479 --> 06:38:22.799
Pearl asked.

06:38:22.860 --> 06:38:25.619
When Moon stared into space instead of

06:38:25.619 --> 06:38:28.919
answering, she added, hey, I'm not a mind

06:38:28.919 --> 06:38:29.459
reader.

06:38:29.520 --> 06:38:31.740
Different horrible power over here

06:38:31.740 --> 06:38:32.040
remember?

06:38:32.099 --> 06:38:36.119
Stop talking, Moon said sharply, making

06:38:36.119 --> 06:38:36.959
peril jump.

06:38:37.020 --> 06:38:41.040
Oh, not you, she said to Parel, him.

06:38:41.099 --> 06:38:43.740
He's talking to you right now?

06:38:43.799 --> 06:38:44.880
Parel said.

06:38:44.939 --> 06:38:47.279
That's creepy.

06:38:47.340 --> 06:38:51.060
He has trouble reading your mind too, Moon

06:38:51.060 --> 06:38:51.419
said.

06:38:51.479 --> 06:38:53.639
Although he agrees, it's a lot less

06:38:53.639 --> 06:38:56.639
Inferno-esque than it was before you went

06:38:56.639 --> 06:38:57.720
to the Sky Palace.

06:38:57.779 --> 06:38:59.400
Yay?

06:38:59.459 --> 06:39:01.680
A dragon's not a thing.

06:39:01.740 --> 06:39:04.319
Moon suddenly exploded, talking to the

06:39:04.319 --> 06:39:04.799
air again.

06:39:04.860 --> 06:39:07.380
You shouldn't be able to enchant someone

06:39:07.380 --> 06:39:07.919
like that.

06:39:07.979 --> 06:39:09.180
It's wrong.

06:39:09.240 --> 06:39:10.500
Don't you?

06:39:10.560 --> 06:39:12.419
No, stop.

06:39:12.540 --> 06:39:14.400
It doesn't matter how bad he was.

06:39:14.520 --> 06:39:15.419
This.

06:39:15.540 --> 06:39:18.240
She jabbed the scroll so hard it ripped a

06:39:18.240 --> 06:39:18.419
little.

06:39:18.479 --> 06:39:21.479
This is the cruelest thing I've ever

06:39:21.479 --> 06:39:21.779
read.

06:39:21.840 --> 06:39:25.200
Okay, you really have to tell me now.

06:39:25.259 --> 06:39:27.540
Peril was itching with curiosity.

06:39:27.599 --> 06:39:30.659
I am, Moon said.

06:39:30.720 --> 06:39:33.599
I am going to tell her When you do

06:39:33.599 --> 06:39:35.759
something this terrible, you kind of

06:39:35.759 --> 06:39:37.680
cancel out any privacy rights.

06:39:37.799 --> 06:39:39.479
She turned to peril.

06:39:39.540 --> 06:39:42.659
Remember how Winter said, that dark

06:39:42.659 --> 06:39:44.759
stalker killed his father, Prince

06:39:44.759 --> 06:39:45.360
Arctic.

06:39:45.419 --> 06:39:48.299
Yeah, peril said.

06:39:48.299 --> 06:39:49.680
That confused me a bit.

06:39:49.740 --> 06:39:51.779
Why was his dad an ice wing?

06:39:51.840 --> 06:39:55.500
Long story, not important, Moon said.

06:39:55.560 --> 06:39:57.720
I mean, except to the ice wings.

06:39:57.779 --> 06:40:01.319
Anyway, the other rumor I'd heard about

06:40:01.319 --> 06:40:03.959
Dark Stalker was that he did something so

06:40:03.959 --> 06:40:06.599
awful that it terrified the entire night

06:40:06.599 --> 06:40:09.360
wing tribe into abandoning their city and

06:40:09.360 --> 06:40:11.639
going into hiding so that he would never

06:40:11.639 --> 06:40:13.259
find them again if he ever came back.

06:40:13.319 --> 06:40:17.220
They thought he was gone, maybe dead, but

06:40:17.220 --> 06:40:19.500
they still uprooted the entire tribe to

06:40:19.500 --> 06:40:21.360
hide from him, just in case.

06:40:21.479 --> 06:40:23.759
Yeesh!

06:40:23.880 --> 06:40:25.979
And I thought my tribe hated me.

06:40:26.040 --> 06:40:27.599
Pearl tried to joke.

06:40:27.720 --> 06:40:30.240
She was starting to get a creepy, crawly

06:40:30.240 --> 06:40:31.380
feeling under her scales.

06:40:31.439 --> 06:40:35.040
This menacing dragon was buried alive

06:40:35.040 --> 06:40:37.200
somewhere right below their talons.

06:40:37.319 --> 06:40:42.299
Well, Moon said, now I know what it was.

06:40:42.360 --> 06:40:43.319
Yes, I do.

06:40:43.380 --> 06:40:44.700
I'm sure.

06:40:44.759 --> 06:40:47.580
If I saw a dragon do this, I'd go into

06:40:47.580 --> 06:40:48.119
hiding too.

06:40:48.240 --> 06:40:50.340
Yes?

06:40:50.459 --> 06:40:52.259
Peril said impatiently.

06:40:52.319 --> 06:40:54.060
Moon dropped her voice.

06:40:54.119 --> 06:40:58.080
He used his magic on his father.

06:40:58.139 --> 06:41:02.520
He enchanted him as if Prince Arctic was

06:41:02.520 --> 06:41:05.459
no more than a necklace or rock or a

06:41:05.459 --> 06:41:06.000
piece of cheese.

06:41:06.060 --> 06:41:10.919
Ooh, peril said, momentarily distracted

06:41:10.919 --> 06:41:12.659
by the idea of an enchanted piece of

06:41:12.659 --> 06:41:13.139
cheese.

06:41:13.200 --> 06:41:17.040
The spell is right here, Moon said.

06:41:17.099 --> 06:41:19.740
She spread her front talons on the scroll

06:41:19.740 --> 06:41:21.000
starting to cry again.

06:41:21.060 --> 06:41:25.799
Enchant Arctic the Ice Wing to obey my

06:41:25.799 --> 06:41:26.520
every command.

06:41:26.580 --> 06:41:28.380
That's it.

06:41:28.439 --> 06:41:29.759
It's that simple.

06:41:29.880 --> 06:41:32.220
What did you make him do?

06:41:32.279 --> 06:41:33.180
she demanded.

06:41:33.240 --> 06:41:36.479
You made him kill himself, didn't you?

06:41:36.540 --> 06:41:39.419
Whoa, peril said.

06:41:39.479 --> 06:41:40.619
Is that possible?

06:41:40.740 --> 06:41:41.939
That could happen?

06:41:42.000 --> 06:41:43.860
Could turtle do that?

06:41:43.919 --> 06:41:46.680
Moon gave a furious shake of her head.

06:41:46.740 --> 06:41:48.959
There was a long pause, and then she

06:41:48.959 --> 06:41:51.419
yelped, disembowel?

06:41:51.479 --> 06:41:53.819
Did you seriously just say disembowel?

06:41:53.880 --> 06:41:56.279
Who disemboweled who?

06:41:56.340 --> 06:41:57.299
Pearl asked.

06:41:57.360 --> 06:41:59.279
Oh, gross.

06:41:59.340 --> 06:42:01.560
Did Arctic disembowel himself?

06:42:01.619 --> 06:42:04.020
That is much worse than anything that

06:42:04.020 --> 06:42:05.159
happened in the arena.

06:42:05.220 --> 06:42:06.360
Oh my goodness.

06:42:06.419 --> 06:42:08.939
Scarlet would have loved to get a self

06:42:08.939 --> 06:42:10.979
disemboweling dragon in her arena.

06:42:11.040 --> 06:42:12.299
She's dead, by the way.

06:42:12.360 --> 06:42:13.319
Did we mention that?

06:42:13.380 --> 06:42:16.259
But Moon was lying down on top of the

06:42:16.259 --> 06:42:18.840
scroll now, pressing her talons over her

06:42:18.840 --> 06:42:20.159
ears with her eyes closed.

06:42:20.220 --> 06:42:22.680
Carol wondered if she should try to get

06:42:22.680 --> 06:42:25.319
Moon away from Dark Stalker's voice, but

06:42:25.319 --> 06:42:26.520
she couldn't think of a way to do that

06:42:26.520 --> 06:42:29.340
without either touching her or throwing

06:42:29.340 --> 06:42:31.619
rocks at her to get her attention, which

06:42:31.619 --> 06:42:33.360
seemed a little heartless considering

06:42:33.360 --> 06:42:34.319
what Moon was going through.

06:42:34.380 --> 06:42:37.500
So she decided to watch over her and wait

06:42:37.500 --> 06:42:37.919
for the others.

06:42:37.979 --> 06:42:40.200
That seems like a sensible plan of

06:42:40.200 --> 06:42:40.439
action.

06:42:40.500 --> 06:42:44.159
She glanced around, found a tree that was

06:42:44.159 --> 06:42:46.439
growing at an angle out of a ravine, and

06:42:46.439 --> 06:42:47.580
lit its branches on fire.

06:42:47.639 --> 06:42:50.099
That should help turtle, Kibli, and

06:42:50.099 --> 06:42:50.759
winter find them.

06:42:50.819 --> 06:42:56.040
It felt like hours of moon not moving, and

06:42:56.040 --> 06:42:57.599
peril sitting there watching her not

06:42:57.599 --> 06:42:57.959
move.

06:42:58.020 --> 06:43:01.439
But at last, peril heard wing beats, and

06:43:01.439 --> 06:43:03.180
she turned to see the other 3 dragons

06:43:03.180 --> 06:43:05.759
straggling up, looking much the worse for

06:43:05.759 --> 06:43:07.020
wear after flying all day.

06:43:07.080 --> 06:43:09.659
Turtle in particular looked like the

06:43:09.659 --> 06:43:12.060
world's unhappiest squashed frog.

06:43:12.119 --> 06:43:15.119
There she is, he gasped.

06:43:15.180 --> 06:43:16.619
Moon.

06:43:16.680 --> 06:43:19.020
Kibley and Winter cried at the same

06:43:19.020 --> 06:43:19.500
time.

06:43:19.560 --> 06:43:22.860
And hello to you too, Parel said.

06:43:22.919 --> 06:43:25.500
The 2 of them landed and ran over to Moon

06:43:25.500 --> 06:43:27.659
but Turtle came over to Peril's Boulder

06:43:27.659 --> 06:43:27.900
first.

06:43:27.959 --> 06:43:29.459
What happened?

06:43:29.520 --> 06:43:30.299
He asked.

06:43:30.360 --> 06:43:31.619
Has she?

06:43:32.220 --> 06:43:34.919
No, she hasn't freed him, Pearl said.

06:43:35.040 --> 06:43:36.479
I don't think she's going to.

06:43:36.540 --> 06:43:39.900
She's had some bad news though, so don't

06:43:39.900 --> 06:43:42.119
be a phlegm snorting rat breath adder.

06:43:42.180 --> 06:43:43.740
She yelled over to Winter.

06:43:43.799 --> 06:43:47.099
Kibli crouched beside Moon, covering her

06:43:47.099 --> 06:43:48.180
gently with one of his wings.

06:43:48.240 --> 06:43:51.360
Tell us what happened, he said.

06:43:51.419 --> 06:43:53.159
Is he talking to you right now?

06:43:53.220 --> 06:43:57.599
Yes, and he won't shut up, she said

06:43:57.720 --> 06:44:00.000
sitting up and wiping away her tears.

06:44:00.060 --> 06:44:02.400
Winter, you were right.

06:44:02.459 --> 06:44:03.900
We can't free him.

06:44:03.959 --> 06:44:07.380
She passed the scroll to Winter, who let

06:44:07.380 --> 06:44:09.659
out an almost imperceptible sigh of

06:44:09.659 --> 06:44:09.959
relief.

06:44:10.020 --> 06:44:13.020
Kibley breathed out a small flame so they

06:44:13.020 --> 06:44:13.680
could both read it.

06:44:13.740 --> 06:44:15.720
Whoa.

06:44:15.779 --> 06:44:17.759
Kibley said after a moment.

06:44:17.819 --> 06:44:21.840
We absolutely can't free him if he can

06:44:21.840 --> 06:44:23.279
control other dragons that way.

06:44:23.340 --> 06:44:26.220
That easily, Moon said.

06:44:26.279 --> 06:44:29.099
And we can't free him, because he's the

06:44:29.099 --> 06:44:30.779
kind of dragon who thought of doing it in

06:44:30.779 --> 06:44:31.439
the 1st place.

06:44:31.560 --> 06:44:33.599
She listened for a moment.

06:44:33.659 --> 06:44:36.659
He says he promises he won't ever do that

06:44:36.659 --> 06:44:36.900
again.

06:44:36.959 --> 06:44:38.939
Dark stalker.

06:44:39.000 --> 06:44:40.500
How can we trust you?

06:44:40.560 --> 06:44:43.740
No one could ever stop you with a power

06:44:43.740 --> 06:44:44.279
like that?

06:44:44.340 --> 06:44:46.560
No, stop.

06:44:46.680 --> 06:44:48.900
I don't want to see another fairy tale

06:44:48.900 --> 06:44:49.319
vision.

06:44:49.380 --> 06:44:51.000
I'll have my own visions.

06:44:51.060 --> 06:44:51.959
Thank you very much.

06:44:52.020 --> 06:44:56.220
Winter let his wings drift softly down, as

06:44:56.220 --> 06:44:57.720
though there were heavy weights he could

06:44:57.720 --> 06:44:58.200
finally drop.

06:44:58.319 --> 06:45:01.799
So, what do we do with it?

06:45:01.860 --> 06:45:04.439
Kibli asked. taking the scroll from

06:45:04.439 --> 06:45:05.459
Winter's claws.

06:45:05.520 --> 06:45:07.979
He brushed one talon lightly across the

06:45:07.979 --> 06:45:08.580
blank space.

06:45:08.639 --> 06:45:11.279
I was thinking about it today while we

06:45:11.279 --> 06:45:11.639
flew.

06:45:11.700 --> 06:45:13.439
We could do a lot of good with this.

06:45:13.500 --> 06:45:15.840
We could use it to protect our queens.

06:45:15.900 --> 06:45:18.360
I could enchant something so that Thorn

06:45:18.360 --> 06:45:20.939
will never die, or make her palace immune

06:45:20.939 --> 06:45:21.360
to attack.

06:45:21.419 --> 06:45:23.040
Moon, think about it.

06:45:23.099 --> 06:45:25.500
We can enchant something to make all the

06:45:25.500 --> 06:45:27.000
night wings love glory.

06:45:27.060 --> 06:45:29.279
You know how many of them hate her

06:45:29.279 --> 06:45:31.740
probably better than anyone, because

06:45:31.740 --> 06:45:34.200
you've seen into their minds, but imagine

06:45:34.200 --> 06:45:35.459
if they all loved her instead.

06:45:35.520 --> 06:45:38.159
What if she could rule without the threat

06:45:38.159 --> 06:45:39.779
of assassination hanging over her?

06:45:39.840 --> 06:45:43.560
She wouldn't want that, Moon said.

06:45:43.619 --> 06:45:46.799
She wouldn't want enchanted obedience or

06:45:46.799 --> 06:45:47.459
fake love.

06:45:47.520 --> 06:45:51.000
How about buyerproof scales at least

06:45:51.000 --> 06:45:52.139
Kibley said?

06:45:52.200 --> 06:45:54.840
Ooh, peril thought.

06:45:54.900 --> 06:45:57.720
We could give all my friends fireproof

06:45:57.720 --> 06:46:01.319
scales, which I guess means turtle, turtle

06:46:01.319 --> 06:46:03.599
could be fireproof, and safe for me too.

06:46:03.659 --> 06:46:07.740
Kibli went on, holding the scroll closer

06:46:07.740 --> 06:46:10.500
or something that could warn glory before

06:46:10.500 --> 06:46:11.639
someone tries to kill her.

06:46:11.700 --> 06:46:13.439
Wouldn't that be a good idea?

06:46:13.500 --> 06:46:15.779
And then you wouldn't have to use your

06:46:15.779 --> 06:46:16.799
own powers to help her.

06:46:16.860 --> 06:46:18.720
You could do whatever you want with

06:46:18.720 --> 06:46:18.959
them.

06:46:19.020 --> 06:46:21.900
Moon put her talons to her head.

06:46:21.959 --> 06:46:24.840
He really doesn't love this

06:46:24.840 --> 06:46:25.560
conversation.

06:46:25.619 --> 06:46:28.500
If we're in the business of protecting

06:46:28.500 --> 06:46:31.799
queens with magic, Winter growled, we

06:46:31.799 --> 06:46:33.180
should include Queen Glacier.

06:46:33.240 --> 06:46:34.799
She's a good queen too.

06:46:34.919 --> 06:46:37.619
And what about my mom?

06:46:37.740 --> 06:46:41.220
Turtle interjected, or Queen Ruby for

06:46:41.220 --> 06:46:41.580
peril.

06:46:41.700 --> 06:46:45.720
But if we enchant all the queens to never

06:46:45.720 --> 06:46:48.659
die or be magically protected or whatever

06:46:48.659 --> 06:46:52.319
peril said, then won't we end up stuck

06:46:52.319 --> 06:46:54.779
with the same queens forever?

06:46:54.840 --> 06:46:55.799
Wouldn't that be bad too?

06:46:55.860 --> 06:47:00.360
Not in the case of Queen Thorn, Kibley

06:47:00.360 --> 06:47:01.200
said stubbornly.

06:47:01.259 --> 06:47:04.500
Look, the 3 of you have these crazy gifts

06:47:04.500 --> 06:47:06.299
and you're figuring out how to use them

06:47:06.299 --> 06:47:07.380
safely, aren't you?

06:47:07.439 --> 06:47:09.180
Shush.

06:47:09.240 --> 06:47:11.520
Moon whispered, closing her eyes.

06:47:11.580 --> 06:47:13.979
I've been fine without you.

06:47:14.099 --> 06:47:16.860
Kibley paused, with a puzzled

06:47:16.860 --> 06:47:17.279
expression.

06:47:17.340 --> 06:47:20.159
Not you, Pearl explained.

06:47:20.279 --> 06:47:22.200
The crazy dragon in her head.

06:47:22.259 --> 06:47:25.680
So if I can trust you with your powers

06:47:25.680 --> 06:47:26.759
Kimley said.

06:47:26.819 --> 06:47:28.680
Couldn't you trust me to take care of

06:47:28.680 --> 06:47:29.340
this one?

06:47:29.400 --> 06:47:31.439
To think carefully about the consequences

06:47:31.439 --> 06:47:33.119
and only use it for good?

06:47:33.240 --> 06:47:36.000
You, Winter snarled.

06:47:36.060 --> 06:47:37.439
By yourself?

06:47:37.500 --> 06:47:40.139
We just let you saunter off for the most

06:47:40.139 --> 06:47:41.700
powerful talisman in the world.

06:47:41.759 --> 06:47:44.040
Why should you get it instead of me?

06:47:44.159 --> 06:47:45.840
Maybe I should take care of it.

06:47:45.900 --> 06:47:49.020
Or maybe all of us together?

06:47:49.080 --> 06:47:51.840
Turtle suggested, but no one was

06:47:51.840 --> 06:47:52.560
listening anymore.

06:47:52.619 --> 06:47:55.799
You just flew off and abandoned us in

06:47:55.799 --> 06:47:58.200
possibility, Kibley shouted at Winter.

06:47:58.259 --> 06:48:00.659
You were really mean to Moon, and you

06:48:00.659 --> 06:48:01.560
haven't even apologized.

06:48:01.619 --> 06:48:04.740
Winter opened and closed his mouth

06:48:04.740 --> 06:48:07.380
looking at Moon with an oddly heartbroken

06:48:07.380 --> 06:48:07.979
expression.

06:48:08.040 --> 06:48:11.520
So how could we trust you, Kibley

06:48:11.520 --> 06:48:11.939
demanded.

06:48:12.000 --> 06:48:15.419
At least I'm a prince, and have some

06:48:15.419 --> 06:48:17.459
experience making decisions to help my

06:48:17.459 --> 06:48:17.939
tribe.

06:48:18.000 --> 06:48:19.500
Winter shouted.

06:48:19.560 --> 06:48:23.520
Oh, awesome logic, Kibley shouted back.

06:48:23.580 --> 06:48:24.779
Your royalty.

06:48:24.840 --> 06:48:27.299
So you've always had power, so you should

06:48:27.299 --> 06:48:28.979
get to keep any new power that comes

06:48:28.979 --> 06:48:29.279
along.

06:48:29.400 --> 06:48:31.860
Stop fighting.

06:48:31.919 --> 06:48:34.619
Moon cried, covering her ears again.

06:48:34.680 --> 06:48:35.700
All of you.

06:48:35.759 --> 06:48:38.340
Dark stalker, stop yelling at me.

06:48:38.400 --> 06:48:41.400
Kibley and Winter were too busy roaring

06:48:41.400 --> 06:48:42.419
at each other to hear her.

06:48:42.479 --> 06:48:45.419
Turtle was curled in a ball below Peril's

06:48:45.419 --> 06:48:47.040
boulder, with his wings around him

06:48:47.040 --> 06:48:49.020
looking indecisive and worried.

06:48:49.080 --> 06:48:53.220
Fighting over power, peril thought, like

06:48:53.220 --> 06:48:54.360
every dragon ever.

06:48:54.419 --> 06:48:56.340
But it's not their power.

06:48:56.400 --> 06:48:59.459
It's dark stalkers, and they want to use

06:48:59.459 --> 06:49:02.099
it, the same way Scarlet used mine.

06:49:02.159 --> 06:49:05.340
But that scroll is too dangerous to be in

06:49:05.340 --> 06:49:05.700
this world.

06:49:05.759 --> 06:49:08.459
Even if a good dragon controlled it?

06:49:08.580 --> 06:49:11.520
Even if it didn't change that good dragon

06:49:11.520 --> 06:49:12.900
to have that much power?

06:49:13.080 --> 06:49:15.659
Even if we could somehow guarantee that

06:49:15.659 --> 06:49:17.700
it would never fall into evil talons.

06:49:17.759 --> 06:49:19.860
It shouldn't exist.

06:49:19.919 --> 06:49:23.279
Look how good dragons are fighting over

06:49:23.279 --> 06:49:23.759
it already.

06:49:23.819 --> 06:49:26.400
Nobody should be the boss of someone

06:49:26.400 --> 06:49:27.299
else's magic.

06:49:27.419 --> 06:49:30.840
And nobody else should ever be hurt by

06:49:30.840 --> 06:49:31.680
that scroll.

06:49:31.799 --> 06:49:35.099
Peril sidled to the edge of the boulder.

06:49:35.159 --> 06:49:38.099
Hopped down onto the grass, hurried

06:49:38.099 --> 06:49:40.259
through the scorched path she made toward

06:49:40.259 --> 06:49:43.020
the fighting dragons, and paused, right

06:49:43.020 --> 06:49:44.040
behind Kibley.

06:49:44.099 --> 06:49:46.020
The sandwing didn't notice her.

06:49:46.139 --> 06:49:49.080
He swept his talons wide, shouting

06:49:49.080 --> 06:49:51.419
something at winter about being careful.

06:49:51.479 --> 06:49:54.119
And Peril reached out and lifted the

06:49:54.119 --> 06:49:55.619
scroll right out of his claws.

06:49:55.680 --> 06:49:59.220
There was a heartbeat of silence as Pearl

06:49:59.220 --> 06:50:00.119
flew back onto the boulder.

06:50:00.180 --> 06:50:03.659
She sat down and held out her talons, and

06:50:03.659 --> 06:50:06.060
the other dragons turned around, and they

06:50:06.060 --> 06:50:09.240
all watched the scroll burn, burn, burn

06:50:09.240 --> 06:50:11.459
into tiny black ashes.

06:50:11.520 --> 06:50:15.659
As the last piece of the scroll flickered

06:50:15.659 --> 06:50:18.419
out of existence, peril brushed the ashes

06:50:18.419 --> 06:50:19.080
off her scales.

06:50:19.139 --> 06:50:21.419
There, she said.

06:50:21.479 --> 06:50:23.220
That solves that problem.

06:50:23.279 --> 06:50:27.240
Now nothing can set the dark stalker free

06:50:27.240 --> 06:50:28.979
and no one can abuse his power.

06:50:29.040 --> 06:50:32.220
She looked down and saw a turtle smiling

06:50:32.220 --> 06:50:32.639
up at her.

06:50:32.700 --> 06:50:35.279
Moon's expression was all relief as

06:50:35.279 --> 06:50:35.520
well.

06:50:35.580 --> 06:50:38.279
So, despite a shock on Winter and

06:50:38.279 --> 06:50:41.400
Kibley's faces, peril felt a sudden, clear

06:50:41.400 --> 06:50:45.180
bolt of that was the right thing to do.

06:50:45.240 --> 06:50:49.259
For once, she was sure, and not because

06:50:49.259 --> 06:50:50.819
someone else was telling her what the

06:50:50.819 --> 06:50:52.979
right thing was, but because she could

06:50:52.979 --> 06:50:54.299
feel it in her own bones.

06:50:54.360 --> 06:50:55.979
I did it.

06:50:56.099 --> 06:50:57.659
I saved the world.

06:50:57.720 --> 06:51:00.540
And Clay wasn't even watching.

06:51:00.599 --> 06:51:03.779
Even if he never knows about it, I'll

06:51:03.779 --> 06:51:05.459
still know I did the right thing.

06:51:05.520 --> 06:51:08.939
She lifted her head to the rising moon

06:51:08.939 --> 06:51:11.639
taking a deep, tranquil breath.

06:51:11.639 --> 06:51:15.180
Wait, why was the moon wobbling?

06:51:15.240 --> 06:51:17.220
It wasn't the moon.

06:51:17.279 --> 06:51:19.020
It was the ground.

06:51:19.080 --> 06:51:22.799
The ground was shaking, harder and harder

06:51:22.799 --> 06:51:25.020
an earthquake trembling through all the

06:51:25.020 --> 06:51:28.020
veins of the mountain, Peril's boulder

06:51:28.020 --> 06:51:30.000
toppled into the ravine, and she had to

06:51:30.000 --> 06:51:32.400
leap into the air, pounding her wings to

06:51:32.400 --> 06:51:34.259
get as far away from the shuddering

06:51:34.259 --> 06:51:35.279
hillside as possible.

06:51:35.340 --> 06:51:38.580
The other dragons threw themselves aloft

06:51:38.580 --> 06:51:39.000
too.

06:51:39.119 --> 06:51:40.680
What's happening?

06:51:40.740 --> 06:51:43.740
Turtle yelled, is Jade Mountain falling?

06:51:43.799 --> 06:51:45.360
Is this the prophecy?

06:51:45.479 --> 06:51:48.060
Peril twisted in the air to look toward

06:51:48.060 --> 06:51:48.720
the academy.

06:51:48.779 --> 06:51:50.279
Clay.

06:51:50.459 --> 06:51:52.500
But Jade Mountain wasn't moving.

06:51:52.560 --> 06:51:56.220
Only this mountain was, and in fact, it

06:51:56.220 --> 06:51:58.080
was doing more than shaking and dropping

06:51:58.080 --> 06:51:58.979
giant rocks everywhere.

06:51:59.099 --> 06:52:01.979
It was splitting apart.

06:52:02.040 --> 06:52:04.860
An enormous crack appeared in the earth

06:52:04.860 --> 06:52:08.400
and out of the darkness rose the hugest

06:52:08.400 --> 06:52:10.319
dragon the world had ever seen.

06:52:10.380 --> 06:52:13.979
Silver scales glittered in the corners of

06:52:13.979 --> 06:52:16.439
his eyes, and along the underside of his

06:52:16.439 --> 06:52:17.340
black wings.

06:52:17.400 --> 06:52:19.680
His bones were visible under his skin.

06:52:19.740 --> 06:52:23.580
He was long and frighteningly thin, with

06:52:23.580 --> 06:52:26.700
a narrow, handsome face, long twisted

06:52:26.700 --> 06:52:29.880
horns, and eyes as black as underground

06:52:29.880 --> 06:52:30.599
caverns.

06:52:30.659 --> 06:52:34.500
Dark stalker, stretched his wings out to

06:52:34.500 --> 06:52:37.259
their fullest reach, as wide as the

06:52:37.259 --> 06:52:37.979
mountain itself.

06:52:38.040 --> 06:52:41.639
He swiveled his neck, expanding in every

06:52:41.639 --> 06:52:44.400
direction, like a dragon who hadn't been

06:52:44.400 --> 06:52:47.700
able to turn or stretch or move in 2000

06:52:47.700 --> 06:52:48.180
years.

06:52:48.240 --> 06:52:52.139
And then, he smiled down at peril.

06:52:52.200 --> 06:52:54.240
A smile that was all teeth.

06:52:54.360 --> 06:52:57.779
Somehow menacing and charming at the same

06:52:57.779 --> 06:52:58.020
time.

06:52:58.080 --> 06:53:00.419
Ah.

06:53:00.419 --> 06:53:04.380
That's infinitely better, he said.

06:53:04.439 --> 06:53:07.259
Nice to finally meet you, peril.

06:53:07.319 --> 06:53:10.380
Thank you so much for your help.

06:53:10.439 --> 06:53:15.060
Epilogue.

06:53:15.119 --> 06:53:18.000
Starflight was working late in the

06:53:18.000 --> 06:53:18.779
library.

06:53:18.840 --> 06:53:20.279
Or was it early?

06:53:20.340 --> 06:53:22.680
He wasn't sure how long he'd been in

06:53:22.680 --> 06:53:24.779
there, since he no longer needed light to

06:53:24.779 --> 06:53:27.060
work by, but he thought the sun was not

06:53:27.060 --> 06:53:29.040
yet up when he heard tiny footsteps

06:53:29.040 --> 06:53:30.299
coming into the room.

06:53:30.360 --> 06:53:31.619
Hello?

06:53:31.619 --> 06:53:32.459
he said.

06:53:32.520 --> 06:53:34.919
He tried to run to all the students in

06:53:34.919 --> 06:53:38.759
his head, small talon steps, light, but

06:53:38.759 --> 06:53:39.720
not kinkaju.

06:53:39.779 --> 06:53:42.119
With an extra flap sound when they hit

06:53:42.119 --> 06:53:42.479
the floor.

06:53:42.540 --> 06:53:44.220
Sea wing talons.

06:53:44.279 --> 06:53:45.900
Anemone?

06:53:45.959 --> 06:53:46.680
He gasped.

06:53:46.740 --> 06:53:50.759
Yes, it's me. said the little sea wing

06:53:50.759 --> 06:53:51.119
princess.

06:53:51.180 --> 06:53:53.580
What are you doing awake?

06:53:53.580 --> 06:53:54.240
he asked.

06:53:54.299 --> 06:53:57.360
I had a nightmare. she said.

06:53:57.419 --> 06:53:59.220
And then something woke me.

06:53:59.279 --> 06:54:00.959
Didn't you feel it?

06:54:01.020 --> 06:54:02.400
Feel what?

06:54:02.459 --> 06:54:05.040
He heard her cross to the wall of

06:54:05.040 --> 06:54:05.340
windows.

06:54:05.459 --> 06:54:08.220
It sounded as if she put one talon on the

06:54:08.220 --> 06:54:10.619
translucent leaves and stood for a moment

06:54:10.619 --> 06:54:12.840
quietly, without speaking.

06:54:12.900 --> 06:54:15.599
Something that shook the earth.

06:54:15.659 --> 06:54:19.799
She said at last, so softly, that he

06:54:19.799 --> 06:54:21.119
wondered if he would have been able to

06:54:21.119 --> 06:54:23.459
hear her before, when he could see.

06:54:24.060 --> 06:54:26.819
I didn't notice anything, he said.

06:54:26.880 --> 06:54:28.860
A small sound.

06:54:28.919 --> 06:54:31.860
Anemones wings shivering together.

06:54:31.919 --> 06:54:34.560
It felt, she said.

06:54:34.680 --> 06:54:37.799
Like someone slithering over my grave.

